INSERT INTO "chain_analysis" ("chain","take","sentiment","trend","updated_at","sources","profile") VALUES ('Solana','The volume surge tracks a genuine usage record: Solana crossed 1B+ weekly non-vote transactions for the first time in the week ending July 6, and Birdeye pegs it at 54% of global spot DEX share. Crucially, US spot SOL ETFs took net inflows ($5.75M Jun 29-Jul 2) while BTC and ETH ETFs bled out, marking SOL as the rotation favorite. Watch the Alpenglow consensus overhaul now on testnet (Votor/Rotor replacing TowerBFT+PoH) as the next structural catalyst, and the contained $20M BonkDAO governance hack as a reminder that memecoin-app risk, not base-chain risk, is the ecosystem''s soft spot.','bullish','Record on-chain usage + ETF rotation','2026-07-08 15:06:44','[{"title":"Solana weekly non-vote transactions top 1 billion","url":"https://solanacompass.com/news/solanas-weekly-non-vote-transaction-count-crosses-1-billion-for-the-first-time"},{"title":"Solana ranks No. 2 in global spot crypto trading volume","url":"https://cryptobriefing.com/solana-second-global-spot-crypto-trading-volume/"},{"title":"Solana 2026 Outlook: Prop AMMs and path to on-chain NASDAQ","url":"https://solanacompass.com/learn/Lightspeed/solanas-next-big-catalyst-in-2026-lightspeed-weekly-roundup"}]','{"what_it_does":"Solana is a high-throughput monolithic Layer 1 optimized for cheap, fast transactions. In 2026 it is the dominant venue for on-chain trading, memecoins, consumer apps and DePIN, and carried an estimated ~50% of USDC transfer volume during parts of 2025. Its users are largely retail traders, launchpad/memecoin participants and a growing base of DeFi and payments apps.","purpose":"Founded by Anatoly Yakovenko (ex-Qualcomm) and Raj Gokal in 2017-2020, Solana''s thesis was a single global state machine fast enough to run a Nasdaq-class exchange on-chain, using Proof of History plus parallel execution instead of sharding or L2s. The bet: one very fast chain beats many slow ones.","non_economic":"Very high social engagement and a builder culture centered on Accelerate/Breakpoint conferences. 2026 developer momentum is strong: Firedancer (Jump Crypto''s independent C client) is rolling out for client diversity, and Alpenglow — a full consensus rewrite cutting finality from ~12.8s to 100-150ms — passed a 98.27% validator governance vote, one of Solana''s strongest mandates. Monthly active addresses hit an all-time high (~167M SPL holders, April 2026); Saga 3 phone crossed 500k units. Pending spot SOL ETFs are a major catalyst.","outlook":"BULL: Alpenglow + Firedancer turn Solana into production-grade, institution-ready infra while it keeps winning consumer/trading share; SOL ETF inflows re-rate it. BASE: Remains the #1 activity chain but token value capture lags usage (only a sliver of ~$10M daily fees reaches the protocol). BEAR: Upgrade rollout during peak activity causes an outage/instability, reviving reliability doubts. Top risk: execution/uptime of two simultaneous mega-upgrades. Watch: Alpenglow mainnet (targeted Q3 2026), ETF approvals, fee capture. Most likely: BASE-to-BULL — continued dominance, upside gated on flawless upgrades and ETF timing.","sources":[{"title":"Solana 2026 Roadmap Breakdown: Alpenglow, Firedancer","url":"https://stakepoint.app/blog/solana-2026-roadmap-breakdown"},{"title":"Top Solana Updates in 2026","url":"https://bitcoinfoundation.org/news/altcoins/top-solana-updates-in-2026-network-upgrades-ecosystem-growth-and-institutional-adoption-trends/"},{"title":"Solana in 2026: Technical Roadmap (Blockdaemon)","url":"https://www.blockdaemon.com/blog/solana-in-2026-technical-roadmap"}]}');
INSERT INTO "chain_analysis" ("chain","take","sentiment","trend","updated_at","sources","profile") VALUES ('Ethereum','The TVL uptick is macro-driven, not fundamental: a market-wide short squeeze the first week of July plus BlackRock ETHA-led ETF inflows (~$44M over two sessions, snapping a nine-day outflow streak) lifted ETH back near $1,770. The real narrative shift is Vitalik''s ''Lean Ethereum'' roadmap published July 4-6 - a 3-4 year rebuild around recursive STARK verification, quantum resistance, and a cheaper storage tier targeting 10x+ fee cuts - which reframes the story toward long-term technical credibility even as price stays weak. Watch whether ETF inflows extend past their two-day run and whether Glamsterdam (now slipped to Q3 2026, raising gas target toward 200M) ships on time; Ethereum still holds 53% of DeFi TVL despite the sector contracting 37% YTD.','mixed','Macro squeeze + Lean ETH narrative reset','2026-07-08 15:06:53','[{"title":"Vitalik''s Lean Ethereum roadmap breakdown","url":"https://symbiosis.finance/blog/ethereum-ecosystem-in-2026-what-changed-in-defi"},{"title":"Ethereum News Today: ETH climbs, up 11% for the week","url":"https://cryptorank.io/news/feed/27e4d-ethereum-news-today"},{"title":"DeFi TVL drops to $71.77B in 2026, Ethereum holds 53.1%","url":"https://coinlaw.io/decentralized-finance-market-statistics/"}]','{"what_it_does":"Ethereum is the base settlement and security layer for the largest on-chain economy. In 2026 most user activity has moved to L2 rollups (Base, Arbitrum, OP, etc.) that post data back to Ethereum, while mainnet itself is where the deepest DeFi liquidity, the largest stablecoin float (~$150B+) and institutional tokenization settle. Users span DeFi power users, institutions, stakers and L2 sequencers.","purpose":"Proposed by Vitalik Buterin in 2013 and launched 2015, Ethereum''s original purpose was a general-purpose ''world computer'' — a programmable blockchain for arbitrary smart contracts, not just payments. Its modern roadmap reframes that as a rollup-centric settlement layer secured by proof-of-stake.","non_economic":"The deepest developer ecosystem and research culture in crypto, though narrative energy has partly rotated to L2s and faster L1s. 2026 shipped two major forks: Pectra (May 2025, validator consolidation to 2,048 ETH, ~11 EIPs) and Fusaka (Dec 2025, PeerDAS ~8x rollup data throughput). ~30% of ETH is staked; spot ETH ETFs hold ~$11.6B cumulative inflows with BlackRock''s ETHA leading, and staking-enabled ETFs (ETHB) launched March 2026. Glamsterdam/ePBS targeted H2 2026.","outlook":"BULL: Fusaka scaling + staking ETFs + institutional tokenization make ETH a cash-flowing ''digital bond''; ZK-EVMs later scale L1 itself. BASE: Rock-solid settlement layer whose fee revenue is partly cannibalized by thriving L2s. BEAR: L2s capture the value (Standard Chartered estimated Base alone removed ~$50B from ETH mcap) while faster L1s peel off activity. Top risk: L2 fee cannibalization of mainnet value accrual. Watch: blob demand/BPO forks, ETF staking inflows, ePBS. Most likely: BASE with a bullish structural tilt as the economics mature.","sources":[{"title":"The Fusaka Upgrade: Scaling Meets Value Accrual (Fidelity)","url":"https://www.fidelitydigitalassets.com/research-and-insights/fusaka-upgrade-scaling-meets-value-accrual"},{"title":"Pectra Upgrade One Year On (Everstake)","url":"https://everstake.one/resources/blog/pectra-anniversary-how-ethereum-changed-2026"},{"title":"Ethereum roadmap","url":"https://ethereum.org/roadmap/"}]}');
INSERT INTO "chain_analysis" ("chain","take","sentiment","trend","updated_at","sources","profile") VALUES ('Base','The +61% daily volume spike is Aerodrome-led: the ve(3,3) DEX crossed $500M cumulative fees on June 27 and now does nearly 2x Uniswap''s top-pool volume on half the TVL, all fed by Coinbase''s retail funnel (Base handled 62% of global onchain stablecoin volume). The catalyst to watch is the Dromos Labs ''Aero'' mega-merger folding Aerodrome and Optimism''s Velodrome into one Superchain liquidity layer, with 94.5% of new supply to existing Aerodrome users, plus a July real-time predictive gauge upgrade replacing weekly voting. Risk: this volume is heavily reflexive on incentive emissions and AERO price, so a stall near the $0.60 resistance could cool the flywheel fast.','bullish','Aerodrome ve(3,3) flywheel + Aero merger','2026-07-08 15:07:31','[{"title":"Aerodrome surges as Base liquidity hits new highs","url":"https://web3.bitget.com/crypto-news/aerodrome-finance-surges-as-base-liquidity-hits-new-highs"},{"title":"DeFi Summer 2.0: Coinbase integration sparks Aerodrome volume surge","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/defi-summer-2-0-coinbase-integration-sparked-aerodrome-30-volume-surge-aero-80-price-rally-2508/"},{"title":"Coinbase targeting stablecoin growth, onchain adoption 2026","url":"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/coinbase-targeting-stablecoin-growth-onchain-150103204.html"}]','{"what_it_does":"Base is Coinbase''s Ethereum L2 (OP Stack) and one of the two largest rollups by TVL. In 2026 it is the leading chain for consumer/social apps, creator coins and memecoins, plus a deep DeFi ecosystem (Aerodrome as its liquidity hub). Its edge is direct funneling of Coinbase''s ~110M+ verified users on-chain, with sub-cent fees.","purpose":"Launched 2023 by Coinbase and led by Jesse Pollak, Base''s stated purpose was to bring ''the next billion users'' on-chain via an open, low-cost L2 tightly integrated with Coinbase''s distribution and regulatory footprint — originally with ''no plans'' for a token.","non_economic":"Among the highest social/consumer engagement of any chain; Pollak is one of crypto''s most influential voices, steering the narrative toward on-chain social, payments and creator economies. Standout apps: Aerodrome (>$1B TVL) and Zora. Base App opened publicly Dec 2025 with a ''trading-first'' realignment. Key 2026 catalysts: Coinbase announced Base will migrate OFF the OP Stack, and a native Base token is being explored (Polymarket ~69% odds of 2026 launch; JPMorgan sees up to $34B value unlock). The $JESSE personal-token launch drew bot/liquidity-siphoning backlash.","outlook":"BULL: Coinbase distribution + a network token unlocking sequencer revenue makes Base the default consumer chain and a top-tier L2 valuation. BASE: Continues gaining share on consumer/social with strong but incentive-influenced DeFi. BEAR: Token launch disappoints or the OP Stack exit fragments tooling/liquidity and dents credibility. Top risk: execution of the stack migration and token distribution without alienating builders. Watch: token confirmation/timing, Base App traction, OP Stack exit mechanics. Most likely: BULL-leaning BASE given unmatched distribution.","sources":[{"title":"Coinbase exec Jesse Pollak on the coming Base token (Fortune)","url":"https://fortune.com/crypto/2025/10/02/crypto-playbook-coinbase-exec-jesse-pollak-corporate-blockchains/"},{"title":"Base explores issuing native token (CoinDesk)","url":"https://www.coindesk.com/business/2025/09/15/base-explores-issuing-native-token-says-creator-jesse-pollak"},{"title":"The Case for Base (DWF Labs)","url":"https://www.dwf-labs.com/research/the-case-for-base-an-open-stack-for-the-global-economy"}]}');
INSERT INTO "chain_analysis" ("chain","take","sentiment","trend","updated_at","sources","profile") VALUES ('BSC','The +79% daily volume jump maps to Binance''s tokenized-equity push: bStocks on-chain volume ran from $6M to $136M in three weeks (23x), with 77% of trades under $100 and a quarter of equity-product users under 25 - genuinely retail-driven, not wash. New listings (ANTA, QNT, STRC and others) trade 24/5 at $0 commission, and the chain now hosts ~$346M in tokenized stocks. Watch the BSC scaling roadmap (dual-client Geth+Reth targeting ~20k TPS with sub-second finality) as the structural story, but note the risk overhang: no MiCA license in France and any Binance-directed regulatory action remains the single biggest threat to this equity flywheel.','bullish','bStocks tokenized-equity retail surge','2026-07-08 15:07:39','[{"title":"BNB Chain news: guilds, bStocks surge and new launches","url":"https://www.coingabbar.com/en/crypto-currency-news/bnb-chain-news-guilds-bstocks-surge-and-new-launches"},{"title":"BNB''s strategic position as catalyst for Binance expansion","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/bnb-strategic-position-catalyst-binance-global-expansion-mass-adoption-2508/"},{"title":"BNB surges 11% on VanEck ETF launch and Binance teaser","url":"https://coinmarketcap.com/top-stories/6a1beb9646f6c46cc3a32ddb/"}]','{"what_it_does":"BNB Chain (BSC) is Binance''s high-throughput EVM L1, in 2026 one of the most active chains by raw transactions. It is dominated by trading/swaps, memecoin speculation and retail DeFi, with average fees near $0.001. It hit an all-time-high 31M daily transactions (Oct 2025) and supports a large DeFi ecosystem (PancakeSwap) plus growing RWA issuance.","purpose":"Launched 2020 by Binance as a fast, cheap EVM-compatible alternative to Ethereum, explicitly designed to host the exchange''s users and DeFi/retail activity with low fees, using a small validator set for speed.","non_economic":"Very high retail/memecoin social activity tied to Binance''s reach; BNB reached ATH ~$1,330 in Oct 2025. Aggressive technical cadence: Maxwell hardfork cut block time to 0.75s (MEV sandwich attacks down 95%+), and Fermi (Jan 2026) pushed to 0.45s with ~1.1s fast finality. 2026 roadmap targets 20,000 TPS, a Rust (Reth) client alongside Geth, and AI-agent/private-transaction infra. Institutional signals: BlackRock BUIDL, Franklin BENJI, VanEck VBILL on-chain; ~$500M in corporate BNB treasury accumulation (Nano Labs, CEA).","outlook":"BULL: Fastest-block major EVM + Binance distribution + institutional RWA adoption compounds into durable payments/trading dominance. BASE: Remains a top activity chain but is perceived as centralized and memecoin-driven, capping institutional trust. BEAR: Regulatory pressure on Binance, or a memecoin activity bust, deflates usage and BNB. Top risk: Binance-centralization/regulatory dependence. Watch: Reth client progress, RWA growth, transaction counts vs memecoin cycles. Most likely: BASE with cyclical bull spikes.","sources":[{"title":"BNB Chain Announces Maxwell Hardfork (BNB Chain)","url":"https://www.bnbchain.org/en/blog/bnb-chain-announces-maxwell-hardfork-bsc-moves-to-0-75-second-block-times"},{"title":"BNB Chain Tech Roadmap 2026","url":"https://www.bnbchain.org/en/blog/tech-roadmap-2026"},{"title":"BNB Chain 2025 Performance and 2026 Roadmap (AInvest)","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/bnb-chain-2025-performance-2026-roadmap-case-strategic-entry-high-growth-blockchain-ecosystem-2601/"}]}');
INSERT INTO "chain_analysis" ("chain","take","sentiment","trend","updated_at","sources","profile") VALUES ('Hyperliquid L1','The soft near-term metrics belie two structural wins: Hyperliquid crossed $1B cumulative protocol revenue on June 30, and the CFTC issued a policy statement recognizing perpetual futures and cleared the first such product on a registered US exchange - validating exactly the model HL is built on. That validation is double-edged: it blesses the perp-venue thesis but invites well-capitalized regulated entrants to contest the same fee pool that funds HL''s buyback flywheel (97-99% of fees routed to HYPE buybacks, 40M+ tokens retired). Watch competitive share erosion from Aster (briefly took 50%+ in Sep 2025, YZi/Binance-backed on BSC), Lighter and Drift, plus a ~9.9M HYPE/month team unlock running through 2027 as the supply overhang.','bullish','$1B revenue + CFTC perp validation','2026-07-08 15:08:18','[{"title":"Hyperliquid HYPE rally after $1B revenue and CFTC approval","url":"https://phemex.com/blogs/hyperliquid-hype-record-high-1-billion-revenue"},{"title":"Aster and Hyperliquid drive $2tn perp DEX volume record","url":"https://www.dlnews.com/articles/defi/aster-hyperliquid-drive-2-trillion-perp-dex-volume-surge/"},{"title":"Pricing the perp DEX leader: valuation framework for Hyperliquid","url":"https://www.cfbenchmarks.com/blog/pricing-the-perp-dex-leader-a-valuation-framework-for-hyperliquid"}]','{"what_it_does":"Hyperliquid L1 is a purpose-built, application-specific chain for on-chain trading. Its HyperCore runs fully on-chain perpetual and spot order books with one-block finality, and it handles well above 50% of all decentralized perpetuals volume on most days in 2026. HyperEVM adds a Solidity smart-contract layer that shares state with HyperCore, so DeFi apps can read live order-book prices. Users are largely professional and high-frequency traders.","purpose":"Founded by Jeff Yan and the Hyperliquid team (self-funded, no VC), the thesis was to build the fully on-chain equivalent of a top-tier centralized perps exchange — a chain designed around the order book itself rather than a general L1 that hosts an exchange.","non_economic":"Extremely strong trader mindshare and one of crypto''s most-watched tokens (HYPE) after its Nov 2024 airdrop to ~94k users. Developer momentum is accelerating: 100-170+ protocols on HyperEVM within ~18 months, with familiar Ethereum tooling (Foundry, Hardhat). New primitives HIP-3 (permissionless perp markets) and HIP-4 (outcome/prediction contracts, May 2026) expand the surface; a third party listed an SPCX perp on SpaceX''s June 2026 IPO day doing $1.34B volume. Circle brought native USDC + CCTP V2 and is evaluating running a validator.","outlook":"BULL: HyperEVM ecosystem compounds on top of the deepest on-chain perps liquidity, making Hyperliquid the on-chain trading hub and driving HYPE fee capture. BASE: Retains perps dominance but stays trading-concentrated, with EVM breadth still maturing. BEAR: Perps-market concentration invites single-point/regulatory risk, or validator centralization erodes trust. Top risk: over-concentration in perps volume and validator decentralization. Watch: HyperEVM protocol/TVL growth, validator set expansion, share of DEX-perps volume. Most likely: BULL-leaning BASE.","sources":[{"title":"About Hyperliquid (Docs)","url":"https://hyperliquid.gitbook.io/hyperliquid-docs"},{"title":"Hyperliquid Architecture Deep Dive: HyperBFT, HyperCore, HyperEVM (CleanSky)","url":"https://cleansky.io/blog/hyperliquid-architecture-hypercore-hyperevm-2026/"},{"title":"Hyperliquid developer stack (QuickNode)","url":"https://www.quicknode.com/blog/hyperliquid-developer-stack"}]}');
INSERT INTO "chain_analysis" ("chain","take","sentiment","trend","updated_at","sources","profile") VALUES ('Polygon','The +93% 30d volume growth is the payments pivot paying off, not DeFi speculation: Polygon settled a record $9.12B in P2P stablecoin transfers in June, closed Q2 at an all-time-high 743M transactions (+160% YoY), and its Jan 8 ''Open Money Stack'' reframed the chain as payments rail with live processors (Credible Finance $152M across US/India/Brazil/Germany, plus Revolut/Flutterwave/Shift4). On July 1 it burned 107M POL, turning the token net-deflationary. The glaring risk is the divergence: POL still trades near all-time lows (~$0.073, -94% from peak) despite this adoption - genuine product-market fit that has utterly failed to accrue to the token, so watch whether the deflationary burn plus a falling-wedge breakout can finally close that value gap.','mixed','Payments/stablecoin PMF vs dead token price','2026-07-08 15:08:27','[{"title":"Polygon hits $9.12B stablecoin milestone as POL eyes recovery","url":"https://www.tronweekly.com/polygon-hits-explosive-9-12-billion-stablecoin-milestone-as-pol-eyes-80-recovery/"},{"title":"Polygon hits 743 million transactions in Q2 2026, all-time high","url":"https://www.cryptopolitan.com/polygon-transactions-q2-2026-all-time-high/"},{"title":"POL rises on new stablecoin framework announcement","url":"https://www.dlnews.com/articles/markets/pol-token-rises-on-new-stablecoin-framework-announcement/"}]','{"what_it_does":"Polygon PoS is an EVM L1/sidechain that in 2026 has repositioned as a payments and stablecoin settlement rail. It processed ~$80B in stablecoin volume in May 2026 (claiming to overtake Solana and BNB by that metric), hit ATH ~743M quarterly transactions, and settles for Stripe, Polymarket and tokenized funds (BlackRock BUIDL, Franklin BENJI, Apollo). POL secures the chain and the AggLayer cross-chain settlement layer.","purpose":"Founded 2017 (as Matic) by Jaynti Kanani, Sandeep Nailwal and Anurag Arjun to scale Ethereum with cheap, fast transactions. The modern thesis, driven by Nailwal, is to become global ''internet money'' payments infrastructure via the AggLayer federation of chains.","non_economic":"Nailwal frames 2026 as Polygon''s ''year of rebirth.'' Heavy upgrade cadence: Rio (Oct 2025, VEBloP block production, 5,000 TPS, reorg-free finality), then capacity expansions and the Giugliano upgrade (Apr 2026). AggLayer v0.3 now supports OP Stack and Arbitrum Orbit chains, not just Polygon CDK. Deep fintech integrations: Revolut (65M users), Flutterwave, Mastercard Crypto Credential, Stripe global USDC. Breakout Program incubated Katana, Miden, ZisK. Persistent tension: POL hit an ATL ~$0.07 (July 2026) even as usage set records — turned net-deflationary via burns.","outlook":"BULL: Becomes the default stablecoin/payments settlement layer as on-chain money movement scales, with AggLayer aggregating liquidity across many chains. BASE: Strong, growing payments utility but weak POL value accrual against ongoing emissions. BEAR: Base and others out-compete on payments/consumer while POL dilution overwhelms burns. Top risk: usage-vs-token-value divergence and no max supply. Watch: stablecoin volume trend, AggLayer chain adoption, burn-vs-emission balance, GigaGas roadmap. Most likely: BASE with real payments traction, POL upside gated on tokenomics.","sources":[{"title":"Polygon Launches Major Payments Upgrade with Rio","url":"https://polygon.technology/blog/polygon-launches-major-payments-upgrade-with-rio-faster-lighter-and-easier-to-build"},{"title":"Polygon''s Second Life: Rebuilding traction via payments (Chainstack)","url":"https://chainstack.com/polygon-second-life-payments-infrastructure/"},{"title":"Polygon Review (Coin Bureau)","url":"https://coinbureau.com/education/polygon-review"}]}');
INSERT INTO "chain_analysis" ("chain","take","sentiment","trend","updated_at","sources","profile") VALUES ('Tron','The TVL/volume split tells the real story: Tron holds ~$87.7B of USDT (47.6% of all USDT in existence) and settled $1.96T in stablecoin transactions in Q1, yet daily DEX volume is a rounding error - it''s a settlement rail, not a trading venue. The concrete catalysts are corporate treasury accumulation (a Nasdaq-listed entity now holds 703M+ TRX) and a Q3 post-quantum crypto upgrade (FN-DSA-512/ML-DSA-44 live on Nile testnet) rolling to mainnet. The persistent risk is regulatory and centralization: a March 2026 $10M SEC settlement, TRM Labs flagging 58% of illicit crypto volume on Tron, Tether freezing 131 Tron wallets on OFAC actions, and Justin Sun affiliates controlling ~63% of supply - fundamentals are sticky but reputational tail-risk is real.','neutral','USDT settlement moat, thin trading','2026-07-08 15:09:07','[{"title":"TRON stablecoin volume hits $1.96T as USDT settlement surges","url":"https://bitcoinist.com/tron-stablecoin-volume-hits-1-96t-as-usdt-settlement-demand-surges/"},{"title":"USDT supply on Tron maintains 47.59% of global USDT circulation","url":"https://blockchainmagazine.net/usdt-supply-on-tron-declines-1-08-over-30-days-as-network-maintains-47-59-of-global-usdt-circulation/"},{"title":"TRON Q1 2026 quarterly report","url":"https://trondao.org/research/tron-q1-2026-quarterly-report"}]','{"what_it_does":"Tron is a high-throughput L1 that in 2026 is the dominant global rail for USDT stablecoin settlement. USDT on Tron exceeds $85B (over 46% of all USDT), and the chain settled ~$1.96T of stablecoin transfers in Q1 2026 at roughly one-cent fees. Its core users are people moving dollars cheaply — remittances and cross-border payments across Southeast Asia, Africa and Latin America — not DeFi speculators.","purpose":"Founded 2017 by Justin Sun, Tron originally pitched itself as a decentralized content/entertainment network (‘decentralize the web’). In practice it evolved into low-cost USDT settlement infrastructure, which is now its explicit strategic focus.","non_economic":"Justin Sun dominates the narrative — and the risk. He controls ~63% of circulating TRX; his SEC case was dismissed in March 2026 (viewed by analysts as politically tinged after his World Liberty Financial investment). Tron Inc. (Nasdaq: TRON) is a public TRX-treasury vehicle holding 700M+ TRX. 2026 ecosystem: MetaMask native support, Mastercard partner program, SunSwap V4, gas abstraction (pay fees in USDT), Polymarket TRON deposits. Compliance reach is real: Tether froze $344M USDT on Tron under FATF guidance (Apr 2026). Only 27 validators — highly centralized.","outlook":"BULL: If stablecoin frameworks (GENIUS Act) treat Tron as legitimate rails, it captures trillions in settlement and the Nasdaq treasury supports TRX. BASE: Keeps its USDT-settlement moat but token trades at a persistent discount to usage. BEAR: Founder concentration, 27-validator centralization and compliance/freeze risk trigger de-risking or supply offloads. Top risk: Justin Sun control + centralization/regulatory exposure. Watch: USDT dominance vs Plasma/Polygon competition, GENIUS Act treatment, Tron Inc. accumulation. Most likely: BASE — operationally dominant, structurally discounted.","sources":[{"title":"Tron''s Stablecoin Dominance Is Growing (TipRanks)","url":"https://www.tipranks.com/news/trons-stablecoin-dominance-is-growing-what-it-means-for-trx"},{"title":"Tron Network - Q1 2026 (CoinDesk Research)","url":"https://www.coindesk.com/research/tron-network-q1-2026"},{"title":"Tron price prediction 2026-2030: the stablecoin settlement layer bet (crypto.news)","url":"https://crypto.news/tron-price-prediction-2026-2030-the-stablecoin-settlement-layer-bet/"}]}');
INSERT INTO "chain_analysis" ("chain","take","sentiment","trend","updated_at","sources","profile") VALUES ('Arbitrum','The -28% 30d volume slide is a liquidity-migration story: a $131.6M bridge outflow went specifically to Hyperliquid and Base, which now leads L2 DeFi with 46%+ TVL while Arbitrum''s GMX-era perp flow bled to Hyperliquid. Compounding it: a July 16 unlock releases ~92M ARB, extending the vesting overhang that network performance can''t absorb without a demand catalyst. The one the market has waited longest for is a DAO fee-sharing/buyback vote - repeatedly proposed, never implemented; when it lands the repricing could be violent. Watch Orbit as the offsetting bull case: Robinhood Chain went live on Arbitrum Orbit for tokenized stocks and LG Electronics picked Orbit for an ad-infra L2.','bearish','Liquidity migration + unlock overhang','2026-07-08 15:09:15','[{"title":"Arbitrum''s 2026 collapse: flow analysis of price and liquidity","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/arbitrum-2026-collapse-flow-analysis-price-liquidity-2602/"},{"title":"Arbitrum market analysis 2026: token gap","url":"https://matrixpro24.com/arbitrum-market-analysis/"},{"title":"Latest Arbitrum news and outlook","url":"https://coinmarketcap.com/cmc-ai/arbitrum/latest-updates/"}]','{"what_it_does":"Arbitrum One is the leading DeFi-focused Ethereum L2, holding ~31% of all L2 DeFi liquidity in 2026. It hosts deep bluechip DeFi (Aave, GMX, Uniswap, Curve, Camelot) and is increasingly the venue for tokenized real-world assets and institutional flows. Orbit lets teams launch custom L2/L3 chains (e.g., Robinhood Chain), and Stylus lets developers write contracts in Rust/WASM alongside Solidity.","purpose":"Built by Offchain Labs (Ed Felten, Steven Goldfeder, Harry Kalodner; mainnet 2021) to scale Ethereum via optimistic rollups — cheap, fast, EVM-equivalent execution that inherits Ethereum security. Governance runs through the ARB-token Arbitrum DAO.","non_economic":"Narrative has shifted from ''cheap scaling'' to ''institutional settlement layer.'' 2026 momentum: 1,000+ projects, Robinhood Chain (Orbit) launched public testnet Feb 2026 (4M txns week one), Franklin Templeton and WisdomTree pushing RWA volume >$800M. ArbOS Dia upgrade (Jan 2026) modernized gas/throughput and aligned with Ethereum''s Fusaka. $215M Gaming Catalyst fund. Revenue mechanisms (Timeboost >$6M year one) move the DAO off pure emissions. Headwind: ~90-100M ARB unlock monthly through March 2027.","outlook":"BULL: Wins the ''depth over hype'' bet — becomes the institutional/RWA settlement L2 as TradFi (Robinhood, Franklin) builds on Orbit, with fee/auction revenue accruing to the DAO. BASE: Stays a top-2 L2 on DeFi liquidity but cedes consumer mindshare to Base. BEAR: Relentless ARB unlocks plus L2 fee compression cap the token while Base/others take share. Top risk: ARB supply overhang through 2027 + centralized sequencer. Watch: Robinhood Chain mainnet, RWA growth, BoLD/decentralized sequencing, Timeboost revenue. Most likely: BASE with a credible institutional upside path.","sources":[{"title":"Arbitrum ecosystem enters institutional phase (crypto.news)","url":"https://crypto.news/arbitrum-ecosystem-enters-institutional-phase-as-transactions-top-2-1b-and-tvl-hits-20b/"},{"title":"Arbitrum''s 2026 Roadmap (BlockEden)","url":"https://blockeden.xyz/blog/2026/02/01/arbitrum-2026-roadmap-arbos-dia-gaming-catalyst-stylus/"},{"title":"Arbitrum Review 2026 (Coin Bureau)","url":"https://coinbureau.com/review/arbitrum"}]}');
INSERT INTO "chain_analysis" ("chain","take","sentiment","trend","updated_at","sources","profile") VALUES ('Avalanche','The volume/activity pickup is RWA-driven: Securitize tokenized $295M of its own NYSE-listed stock on Avalanche (and Solana) on July 2 - billed as the world''s largest tokenized stock, BlackRock-backed - on top of a 28-member Payments Collective (Franklin Templeton, VanEck) launched June 19. The subnet model turns this into structural AVAX demand since every new L1 requires validators to stake AVAX, and the Etna upgrade cut deployment cost 99.9%. Regulatory tailwinds are real: VanEck''s spot AVAX ETF (VAVX) launched Jan 26 and the SEC/CFTC classified AVAX a digital commodity March 17. The caveat: usage is surging while AVAX sits near $6.5 (#30 mcap) - the adoption-vs-price gap is the whole debate.','bullish','Securitize RWA + institutional stack','2026-07-08 15:09:50','[{"title":"Avalanche institutional adoption and trading volume surge","url":"https://www.bitget.com/news/detail/12560604939271"},{"title":"Avalanche AVAX projected to surge driven by institutional adoption","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/avalanche-avax-projected-surge-100-2026-driven-institutional-adoption-technical-optimism-2507/"},{"title":"Avalanche surges as institutional ETF filings spark rally","url":"https://coinpedia.org/price-analysis/avalanche-avax-surges-11-as-institutional-etf-filings-spark-rally/amp/"}]','{"what_it_does":"Avalanche is a multi-chain L1 whose main C-Chain runs EVM DeFi while its bigger 2026 story is custom sovereign chains (Avalanche L1s, formerly Subnets) for institutions, RWAs, gaming and enterprises. It is the leading network for regulated RWA tokenization (~$2.1B RWA TVL in early 2026), chosen by BlackRock, FIS, Securitize and Japan''s Progmat because validators can be known/KYC''d while retaining public-chain tooling.","purpose":"Founded by Emin Gün Sirer and Ava Labs (mainnet 2020) around the novel Avalanche/Snowman consensus, the thesis was near-instant finality and a subnet model letting anyone launch application-specific chains with custom rules and validator sets.","non_economic":"Avalanche9000 (Etna hardfork, Dec 2024) via ACP-77 cut the cost of launching an L1 by 99%+ (flat ~1.33 AVAX/month vs 2,000 AVAX stake), triggering a wave of new L1s. Continued upgrades: Octane (fees -42.7%), Granite (Nov 2025, dynamic block times, biometric logins); daily txns +153% YoY. Institutional wins: BlackRock $500M fund, FIS securitized $6B loans, Progmat migrated $1B+ (Feb 2026). VanEck launched the first US spot AVAX ETF (VAVX) Jan 2026. But AVAX price fell ~84% from its Oct 2025 peak.","outlook":"BULL: If even a fraction of global bonds/equities/private credit settle on-chain and Avalanche captures it, subnet growth drives real AVAX staking demand. BASE: Cements RWA/institutional leadership but token value accrual from L1s stays uneven. BEAR: Subnets fragment activity without generating AVAX demand or user volume; price stays disconnected from usage. Top risk: L1/subnet growth may not translate into AVAX economic demand. Watch: RWA TVL trajectory, new institutional L1 launches, AVAX ETF (VAVX) flows, AVAT treasury. Most likely: BASE with institutional-RWA upside.","sources":[{"title":"What Is Avalanche? AVAX, L1s, and Subnets in 2026 (Eco)","url":"https://eco.com/support/en/articles/12168599-what-is-avalanche-avax-l1s-and-subnets-in-2026"},{"title":"Avalanche Review 2026 (Coin Bureau)","url":"https://coinbureau.com/review/avalanche-avax"},{"title":"Avalanche (AVAX) Fundamental Analysis July 2026 (CoinStats)","url":"https://coinstats.app/ai/a/fundamental-analysis-avalanche-2"}]}');
INSERT INTO "chain_analysis" ("chain","take","sentiment","trend","updated_at","sources","profile") VALUES ('Monad','The +36% 7d TVL jump has two dated catalysts: Aave deployed V3.7 on Monad on July 2 (12 assets day one, ~$75M deposited in the first 24h) and MetaMask launched its Mastercard-linked yield ''Money Account'' built on Monad the same day. Monad was already the fastest recent L1 to $300M TVL (four months post its Nov 2025 mainnet). The flashing warning is the fee-to-TVL mismatch - elevated TVL with minimal fee production is the classic signature of incentive-farmed rather than organic liquidity - so the real test is whether TVL and DAUs hold once emissions taper. Compounding it: the first major MON unlock begins November 2026 (2B minted annually, only ~11.8% of supply circulating now).','mixed','Aave + MetaMask launches, unlock ahead','2026-07-08 15:10:49','[{"title":"Aave V3.7 launches on Monad as network TVL nears $450M","url":"https://nftevening.com/aave-v3-7-launches-on-monad-network-tvl-nears-450m/"},{"title":"Monad mainnet launch drives surge as institutional capital rotates","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/monad-mainnet-launch-drives-27-surge-institutional-capital-rotates-2604/"},{"title":"Monad MON token despite TVL surge past $355M","url":"https://www.mexc.com/news/999792"}]','{"what_it_does":"Monad is a high-performance EVM L1 (mainnet live Nov 24, 2025) that runs standard Ethereum apps far faster via optimistic parallel execution, MonadBFT consensus and the MonadDB storage layer — targeting ~400ms blocks, near-zero fees and single-slot finality while keeping full EVM/Solidity compatibility. Users are DeFi and consumer-app builders/users who want Ethereum tooling without Ethereum''s throughput ceiling.","purpose":"Founded 2022 by ex-Jump Trading engineers Keone Hon, James Hunsaker and Eunice Giarta, Monad''s thesis is to ''raise the EVM to a higher level'' — not replace it with a new VM/language, but parallelize it so developers keep Solidity and the entire Ethereum ecosystem while getting HFT-grade performance.","non_economic":"One of the most hyped launches of the cycle, backed by $244M ($225M Paradigm-led). Pre-launch testnet processed 2.44B+ transactions (peak 34M/day) and drew 240+ projects; $60M+ in developer programs (incl. Monad Madness). Day-one and 2026 integrations: native USDC + CCTP V2, Chainlink Scale, LayerZero (50+ chains), PancakeSwap v4, Aave V3 (with $15M Monad Foundation incentives), and MetaMask''s Money Account (July 2026) built on Monad with Mastercard. Backed by strong X/developer engagement.","outlook":"BULL: Delivers real 10k+ TPS under load and becomes the default high-performance EVM home, pulling liquidity from congested/expensive chains. BASE: Launches a broad ecosystem but settles into one of several fast-EVM contenders. BEAR: Optimistic-execution rollback rates under real MEV/contention fall short of benchmarks, or hype outpaces sustained usage. Top risk: mainnet performance under adversarial load may lag idealized figures. Watch: real production TPS/rollback rates, TVL and DAU growth, MON tokenomics, competition (Sei, MegaETH). Most likely: BASE with bull optionality if benchmarks hold on mainnet.","sources":[{"title":"Monad Mainnet Goes Live (CryptoNinjas)","url":"https://www.cryptoninjas.net/news/monad-mainnet-goes-live-as-high-speed-l1-opens-with-full-evm-support-and-day-one-apps/"},{"title":"In-Depth Analysis of Monad (Gate)","url":"https://www.gate.com/blog/102065/monad-deep-dive-parallel-execution-monadbft-high-performance-evm-ecosystem-layer1-scalability-blockchain-consensus-ethereum-compatibility-web3-infrastructure-analysis"},{"title":"What Is Monad? (CoinGecko)","url":"https://www.coingecko.com/learn/what-is-monad-crypto"}]}');
INSERT INTO "chain_analysis" ("chain","take","sentiment","trend","updated_at","sources","profile") VALUES ('Near','The high volume-to-TVL turnover is NEAR Intents doing the work: the intent-based cross-chain execution layer crossed $22B cumulative volume (4x+ since late 2025) with ~30M swaps, and June''s report drove a 20%+ NEAR rally back above $2. The structural hook is the buyback flywheel - 100% of Intents fees buy NEAR directly - with analysts flagging a ~$177M/day volume threshold above which NEAR turns net deflationary. It hasn''t crossed that yet, which is the key watch item: buybacks are still symbolic rather than meaningful at current scale. Near-term catalysts: v2.13 upgrade (dynamic resharding + post-quantum signing) and Grayscale/Bitwise spot NEAR ETF decisions expected around September.','bullish','NEAR Intents volume + buyback flywheel','2026-07-08 15:09:58','[{"title":"NEAR price extends recovery as June performance stats disclosed","url":"https://www.thecoinrepublic.com/2026/07/03/near-price-extends-recovery-as-near-protocol-discloses-june-performance-stats-and-milestones/"},{"title":"NEAR Protocol targets AI-driven commerce with new products and tokenomics","url":"https://cryptobriefing.com/near-protocol-ai-commerce-tokenomics/"},{"title":"NEAR Protocol 2026: investment case, tokenomics & deflation threshold","url":"https://svrn.net/news/near-protocol-report"}]','{"what_it_does":"NEAR is a sharded L1 that in 2026 has repositioned as AI-native infrastructure and a chain-abstraction layer. Its NEAR Intents system lets users (and AI agents) express what they want — e.g. swap BTC into a Solana token — while solvers route execution across 35+ chains via an MPC signing network. Cumulative Intents volume crossed $6B by April 2026; users include cross-chain traders and increasingly autonomous agents.","purpose":"Founded by Illia Polosukhin (co-author of the ''Attention Is All You Need'' transformer paper) and Alexander Skidanov, NEAR launched 2020 as a developer- and user-friendly sharded smart-contract platform. Its evolved thesis: blockchain as the invisible backend for AI agents transacting across chains.","non_economic":"Strong AI-crossover narrative anchored by Polosukhin''s ML pedigree. 2026 momentum: Brave Browser added native Intents (70M+ users, Mar 2026); all five major NEAR wallets support Intents; Shade Agents (TEE-secured AI smart contracts) and Confidential Intents launched. Tokenomics overhaul halved max inflation to 2.5% and routes 100% of Intents fees into NEAR buybacks (deflationary above ~$177M daily volume). v2.13 (June 2026) adds dynamic resharding + post-quantum signing. Grayscale filed a spot NEAR ETF. Risk signal: Arthur Hayes fully exited; a Litecoin zero-day caused ~$600k Intents exposure.","outlook":"BULL: AI agents become real blockchain users and NEAR''s abstraction/Intents layer captures that flow, with buybacks turning NEAR structurally deflationary. BASE: Solid cross-chain infra with growing volume, but ''AI-native'' edge is not unique. BEAR: Chain abstraction commoditizes (Solana, Ethereum layers compete) and agent usage stays speculative, so buybacks are symbolic. Top risk: differentiation window narrowing + inherited security surface of 35+ connected chains. Watch: active-agent count, Intents volume vs the deflation threshold, ETF decision (~Sept 2026). Most likely: BASE with real optionality on the AI thesis.","sources":[{"title":"NEAR Protocol targets AI-driven commerce (Crypto Briefing)","url":"https://cryptobriefing.com/near-protocol-ai-commerce-tokenomics/"},{"title":"NEAR Protocol Overview in 2026 (ChangeNOW)","url":"https://changenow.io/blog/near-protocol-overview"},{"title":"Chain Abstraction (NEAR)","url":"https://www.near.org/chain-abstraction"}]}');
INSERT INTO "chain_analysis" ("chain","take","sentiment","trend","updated_at","sources","profile") VALUES ('Sui','The soft 30d volume and flat TVL reflect capital flight, not a one-off: DeFi TVL contracted from near $1B toward much smaller figures as users chased more aggressively incentivized chains (Solana, Avalanche), while SUI sits ~85% below its $5.35 high. Ongoing supply is a headwind but improving in shape - KuCoin pegs late-2026 emissions near 64M SUI/month (1-1.7% of supply), a shift from lumpy cliffs to programmatic, community-led emissions the market tolerates better. The catalyst to watch is DeepBook v3, Sui''s native CLOB upgrade adding margin trading and income-sharing, plus the S2/Sui Stack platform vision. Until on-chain activity and institutional volume return, low-volume rallies stay fragile and perp funding keeps flipping negative.','bearish','DeFi TVL flight, programmatic emissions','2026-07-08 15:11:42','[{"title":"SUI after the July cliff: can DeFi absorb community emissions","url":"https://cryptodaily.co.uk/2026/07/sui-after-july-cliff-defi-emissions"},{"title":"SUI price analysis: token hits critical multi-year lows in 2026","url":"https://www.criptolog.com/coin/sui/sui-navigates-critical-waters-as-token-tests-multi-year-lows-in-2026/"},{"title":"Sui technical and fundamental catalyst for a breakout in 2026","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/sui-sui-technical-fundamental-catalyst-breakout-2026-2512/"}]','{"what_it_does":"Sui is a high-performance L1 using the Move language and an object-centric data model that enables parallel execution and low latency. In 2026 it supports DeFi (its native DeepBook order book), NFTs, gaming and consumer apps, with protocol-level gasless stablecoin transfers (live May 2026) and native private-transaction R&D. Users span DeFi traders, gamers (SuiPlay0X1 handheld) and institutions exploring confidential payments.","purpose":"Built by Mysten Labs — founders Evan Cheng, Sam Blackshear and other ex-Meta/Diem engineers (mainnet 2023) — to deliver a safer, asset-oriented smart-contract platform (Move) with the throughput/latency for mainstream apps, differentiating on the object model rather than the account model.","non_economic":"CEO Evan Cheng frames 2026 as a ''product-first'' turning point, evolving Sui from an L1 into the ''Sui Stack (S2)'' developer platform. A ChainIDE natural-language contract tool drove a reported ~40% jump in developer activity. Catalysts: DeepBook v3 (margin/derivatives, Q2 2026), gasless stablecoin transfers, native privacy research (token surged ~14% in a day on privacy speculation, Jan 2026), Walrus storage, and Grayscale/Bitwise ETF interest. But security scars persist — Cetus (largest DEX) exploited May 2025, Volo hit early 2026 — and TVL fell from ~$2.5B (late 2025) to ~$568M (Mar 2026) amid unlocks.","outlook":"BULL: Move''s safety + object-model performance + native privacy make Sui the go-to for institutional/confidential payments and consumer apps, and the product pivot converts to sticky usage. BASE: Capable high-performance chain that keeps shipping but stays mid-pack versus Solana/EVM incumbents. BEAR: Repeated exploits, Move''s learning curve and persistent unlock pressure suppress TVL and price. Top risk: security maturity + token unlock overhang. Watch: DeepBook v3 adoption, TVL recovery, privacy-feature launch, ETF outcomes. Most likely: BASE with upside if security hardens and products land.","sources":[{"title":"From Infrastructure to Impact: Where Sui Goes Next (Mysten/Sui blog)","url":"https://blog.sui.io/2025-recap-2026-turning-point/"},{"title":"Sui outperforms BTC, ETH as Mysten promotes privacy tech (CoinDesk)","url":"https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2026/01/06/sui-outperforms-bitcoin-and-ether-as-mysten-labs-promotes-privacy-tech"},{"title":"Sui (SUI) in 2026: The Object-Centric Blockchain (Laika Labs)","url":"https://laikalabs.ai/market-intelligence/sui-object-centric-blockchain-2026"}]}');
INSERT INTO "chain_analysis" ("chain","take","sentiment","trend","updated_at","sources","profile") VALUES ('OP Mainnet','The +26% 7d volume bounce sits against a structurally mixed OP setup. Two concrete catalysts: an approved governance proposal routes 50% of Superchain revenue into OP buybacks (usage-linked deflation), and Kraken''s Ink L2 signed a multi-year deal to migrate onto Optimism''s OP Enterprise ''Fully Managed'' tier - a proof point for the 2026 pivot to selling managed infra to exchanges/fintechs. The overhang is Base''s departure from the Velodrome-native flow: the Dromos ''Aero'' merger folds Velodrome into an Aerodrome-led unified DEX with only 5.5% of new token supply to VELO holders, draining OP-native DEX mindshare toward Base. Watch whether the buyback and enterprise pivot can offset that liquidity gravity.','mixed','Superchain buyback vs Base drain','2026-07-08 15:11:51','[{"title":"Dromos Labs merges Aerodrome and Velodrome into new DEX Aero","url":"https://thedefiant.io/news/defi/dromos-labs-merges-aerodrome-and-velodrome-into-new-dex-aero"},{"title":"Optimism OP Stack and Superchain catalyst for value capture","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/optimism-op-stack-superchain-catalyst-ethereum-scalability-token-capture-2508/"},{"title":"Optimism review 2026: Superchain, OP Stack","url":"https://coinbureau.com/review/optimism-review"}]','{"what_it_does":"OP Mainnet is Optimism''s flagship Ethereum L2 and the reference chain of the OP Stack ''Superchain'' — a 30+ chain network (Base, Unichain, World Chain, Soneium, Ink, Ronin, etc.) sharing a codebase, governance and an emerging native interop layer. It hosts DeFi, NFTs, gaming and enterprise/RWA apps with sub-cent fees; the broader Superchain processes 16M+ daily transactions. EVM-equivalent, so Ethereum tooling works unchanged.","purpose":"Built by OP Labs (Jinglan Wang, Ben Jones, Karl Floersch; mainnet 2021) to scale Ethereum via optimistic rollups AND to grow a federation of interoperable OP Stack chains funded through Retroactive Public Goods Funding. The thesis is a shared ''Superchain'' rather than one monolithic L2.","non_economic":"Distinctive two-house governance (Token House + Citizens'' House / RetroPGF). 2026 momentum: native Interop Layer (single-block cross-chain messaging) live on devnet April 2026, mainnet targeted later in the year; new members GIWA (first enterprise OP Stack chain) and Ronin migrated in May 2026. A Feb 2026 governance-approved buyback directs 50% of Superchain sequencer revenue to OP. Now Stage 1 with live Cannon fault proofs. Major overhang: Coinbase announced Base will migrate OFF the OP Stack, weakening the cleanest Superchain economic story.","outlook":"BULL: Native interop ships and the OP buyback ties token value to a thriving 30+ chain Superchain, making OP a bet on the whole federation. BASE: Solid, decentralizing L2 with growing chain count but diffuse value capture. BEAR: Base''s exit plus ongoing OP unlocks and liquidity fragmentation across members hollow out the Superchain thesis. Top risk: Base''s departure and economic fragmentation across Superchain chains. Watch: interop mainnet launch, buyback revenue, new/departing OP Stack members, unlock schedule through 2027. Most likely: BASE, upside contingent on interop delivery.","sources":[{"title":"Optimism''s Interop Layer Launches Q1 2026 (BlockEden forum)","url":"https://blockeden.xyz/forum/t/optimisms-interop-layer-launches-q1-2026-is-cross-l2-composability-finally-here-or-just-superchain-lock-in/3941"},{"title":"Optimism (OP) Review 2026 (Coin Bureau)","url":"https://coinbureau.com/review/optimism-review"},{"title":"OP Mainnet Review 2026 (CryptoAdventure)","url":"https://cryptoadventure.com/op-mainnet-review-2026-fees-security-ecosystem-and-optimism-success/"}]}');
INSERT INTO "chain_analysis" ("chain","take","sentiment","trend","updated_at","sources","profile") VALUES ('TON','The volume and fee strength trace to a genuine structural event: on May 4 Pavel Durov announced Telegram (950M MAU) would replace the TON Foundation as primary steward and largest validator, cut fees ~6x to near-zero (~$0.0005/transfer via a flat rate), and ship Catchain 2.0 for sub-second finality - volume spiked 600% on the news. The token then rebranded TON to GRAM by community vote on June 15 to cement the Telegram identity. The real demand engine to watch is the Telegram Ad Platform (advertisers pay in the token, channel owners get 50% revenue share), expanding via Stars in Q3. The core risk is single-point dependency: Coinbase delisted GRAM perp futures June 17 and India restricted Telegram access - anything hitting Telegram hits the chain directly.','bullish','Telegram takeover + fee cut + GRAM rebrand','2026-07-08 15:12:31','[{"title":"Toncoin surges as Telegram takes direct control of TON network","url":"https://thedefiant.io/news/blockchains/toncoin-surges-as-telegram-takes-direct-control-of-ton-network"},{"title":"Toncoin jumps 26% as Telegram cuts fees 6x and takes control","url":"https://www.cryptotimes.io/2026/05/05/toncoin-jumps-26-as-telegram-cuts-fees-6x-and-takes-control-of-ton/"},{"title":"TON price prediction 2026-2030: the Telegram takeover","url":"https://crypto.news/ton-price-prediction-2026-2030-the-telegram-takeover/"}]','{"what_it_does":"TON is a high-throughput L1 fused with Telegram, serving as the exclusive blockchain for Telegram Mini Apps and the exclusive non-fiat payment rail for Telegram services. In 2026 its killer app is distribution: Mini Apps reach 500M+ monthly Telegram users, powering games, bots, payments (TON Pay SDK, sub-second, <$0.01 fees) and tap-to-earn. Users are mainstream Telegram users, not crypto-natives.","purpose":"Originally ''Telegram Open Network,'' designed 2018 by Nikolai and Pavel Durov as a scalable chain for Telegram''s user base. After the SEC forced Telegram out in 2020, an independent community (TON Foundation) continued it; in 2026 Telegram formally re-embraced it, becoming its largest validator.","non_economic":"Defining 2026 event: Telegram took over the TON Foundation''s core responsibilities and staked 2.2M TON to become a primary validator (Apr 2026, ''MTONGA''), reuniting chain and messenger. BotFather MAUs more than doubled to 7.3M. Roadmap pivots to performance/dev-accessibility (Catchain 2.0 sub-second finality, Rust node, TON Pay, unified dev kits). Cocoon decentralized-AI compute launched Dec 2025 (Telegram routes translation/summarization through it). Double-edged: Telegram-as-largest-validator blurs decentralization and raises censorship/governance risk. On-chain DeFi TVL is small (~$70-82M DeFiLlama).","outlook":"BULL: Telegram-native distribution no other L1 can match turns Mini Apps + TON Pay into real payments/consumer volume with Toncoin as the settlement asset. BASE: Huge reach but activity stays lightweight (games/taps) with modest DeFi and value capture. BEAR: Deepening Telegram control (censorship, policy, regulatory headlines) and thin DeFi cap institutional trust. Top risk: centralization/dependency on Telegram and its regulatory exposure. Watch: TON Pay merchant adoption, Mini App payment volume, Catchain 2.0, Telegram policy moves. Most likely: BASE with real consumer-payments upside if TON Pay scales.","sources":[{"title":"What TON''s Deeper Integration With Telegram Means (Guardarian)","url":"https://guardarian.com/blog/telegram-ton-toncoin-2026"},{"title":"TON Foundation Launches Crypto Checkout SDK for Telegram Mini Apps","url":"https://super-apps.ai/blog/ton-foundation-launches-crypto-checkout-sdk-for-telegram-mini-apps-targets-sub-second-payments/"},{"title":"Understanding TON: A Comprehensive Overview (Messari)","url":"https://messari.io/report/understanding-ton-a-comprehensive-overview"}]}');
INSERT INTO "chain_analysis" ("chain","take","sentiment","trend","updated_at","sources","profile") VALUES ('Aptos','The collapsing volume and -44% 30d TVL come with a specific sentiment shock: security firm Hexens disclosed a critical ''stale-cache'' bug in the Aptos Move VM (found Feb, patched in hours, no funds lost) that could have enabled type confusion over stablecoin minting and bridges - the disclosure itself created an overhang even though the exploit never landed. On top, a ~11.31M APT unlock hits July 12 into thin order books, and APT set an all-time low near $0.55. The one constructive thread: DeFi TVL had climbed to ~$680M from under $275M in mid-2025, meaning people use the chain despite a 95%+ price drawdown. The core problem is narrative - stablecoins and RWA initiatives but no breakout consumer app to define Aptos; it needs a defining catalyst, not another partnership.','bearish','Move VM bug disclosure + unlock overhang','2026-07-08 15:13:32','[{"title":"APT July 12 unlock: why low dilution still matters in weak L1 tape","url":"https://cryptodaily.co.uk/2026/07/apt-july-12-unlock-low-dilution-weak-l1"},{"title":"APT price prediction: dead cat or coil","url":"https://blockchain.news/news/20260705-price-prediction-apt-dead-cat-or-coil-bulls-need"},{"title":"Aptos price down 90% but major investors aren''t walking away","url":"https://www.tradingview.com/news/coinpedia:bcf82485c094b:0-aptos-apt-price-down-90-but-here-s-why-major-investors-aren-t-walking-away/"}]','{"what_it_does":"Aptos is a Move-based high-performance L1 that in 2026 has specialized into financial and institutional infrastructure. Its strongest signals are stablecoins (market cap peaked ~$1.93B Feb 2026, incl. native USDT/USDC, BlackRock BUIDL, Ondo USDY, Ethena sUSDe, PYUSD) and RWAs (top-three chain, ~$1.2B+), with Franklin Templeton using Aptos for its Benji record-keeping. Programmable FA/DFA token standards let assets auto-accrue rewards or enforce compliance at the token layer.","purpose":"Founded by Mo Shaikh and Avery Ching (ex-Meta Diem/Novi engineers; mainnet Oct 2022), Aptos was built to deliver Diem''s safe, scalable vision using the Move language — treating digital assets as non-duplicable resources — for high-throughput consumer and institutional apps.","non_economic":"Institutional/enterprise-leaning signal set. 2026 catalysts: APT classified as a ''digital commodity'' (SEC/CFTC, Mar 17 2026) removing a regulatory overhang; deepened Mastercard integration; $50M+ committed by Aptos Foundation/Labs across ecosystem projects (trading rails, AI). PACT brought $1B+ on-chain private-credit lending. Roadmap: framework-level CLOB, Raptr consensus, Block-STM V2, and Decibel (unified spot/perps/margin engine, Q1 2026). Notable disconnect: strong usage/stablecoin growth but weak APT price; TVL fell to ~$270M from ~$1.3B highs.","outlook":"BULL: Move becomes a dominant financial programming language and Aptos captures institutional stablecoin/RWA/trading flow (Decibel, CLOB, BlackRock/Franklin) as the go-to compliant high-throughput chain. BASE: Real institutional traction continues but APT value accrual lags network usage. BEAR: Move adoption stalls against EVM''s gravity, TVL/price stay depressed, and institutional pilots don''t scale. Top risk: usage-vs-token-value gap and whether Move wins developer share. Watch: Decibel launch/CLOB adoption, stablecoin & RWA growth, Move ecosystem momentum. Most likely: BASE with institutional upside.","sources":[{"title":"Aptos in 2026: Latest News, Roadmap, DeFi Updates (Everstake)","url":"https://everstake.one/resources/blog/aptos-news-2026"},{"title":"Aptos ecosystem funding tops $50M for trading rails and AI (Cryptonomist)","url":"https://en.cryptonomist.ch/2026/05/08/aptos-ecosystem-funding/"},{"title":"Aptos: The Foundation for a New Digital Economy","url":"https://aptosnetwork.com/"}]}');
INSERT INTO "chain_analysis" ("chain","take","sentiment","trend","updated_at","sources","profile") VALUES ('Bitcoin','The wild swings (+137% daily volume, -17% 30d TVL) capture BTCfi''s inflection: speculative emissions-driven TVL has cratered ~74% from its ~$9.1B Oct 2025 peak as airdrop-farmed L2s emptied out, yet Ordinals/Runes on-chain activity is at record highs (daily tx above 800k, Network Activity Index breaking trend for the first time since 2024). The lesson repricing the sector is TVL != revenue - Solv held $2.15B TVL while earning ~$41/day - so capital is consolidating into fee-real survivors Babylon (native BTC staking, ~$4B) and Core DAO (buybacks from revenue). Runes found genuine PMF in lending (Liquidium: 75k+ loans, $360M+ volume). Watch whether ETF flows recover (a $143M inflow July 6 after the worst month since launch) and whether ~20% of miners running at a loss marks a bottom.','mixed','BTCfi TVL purge vs record Runes activity','2026-07-08 15:13:43','[{"title":"BTCFi in 2026: why Bitcoin DeFi TVL shrank 74%","url":"https://www.spark.money/research/btcfi-bitcoin-defi-landscape-2026"},{"title":"Bitcoin DeFi is finding product-market fit with Runes","url":"https://bitcoinmagazine.com/takes/bitcoin-defi-is-finding-product-market-fit-with-runes"},{"title":"Bitcoin microtransactions surge to 80% of network activity","url":"https://cryptonews.com.au/news/bitcoin-microtransactions-surge-to-80-of-network-activity-as-ordinals-and-runes-fuel-onchain-growth-134074/"}]','{"what_it_does":"Bitcoin is the original proof-of-work L1 and, in 2026, primarily a store-of-value settlement network and macro/institutional asset rather than an application platform. On-chain, activity centers on plain BTC transfers, Ordinals/Runes inscriptions, and a maturing but small BTCFi layer. Its ''users'' are increasingly institutions and ETF holders, plus Lightning/payments and restaking participants.","purpose":"Launched 2009 by the pseudonymous Satoshi Nakamoto as peer-to-peer electronic cash — a censorship-resistant, fixed-supply (21M) monetary system with no trusted intermediary. Its enduring realized purpose is ''digital gold'': neutral, credibly scarce base-layer money.","non_economic":"Unmatched brand/network security and the deepest institutional ownership (spot ETFs, corporate treasuries). But 2026 on-chain builder momentum contracted sharply: BTCFi L2 TVL fell 74%+ and the broader BTCFi base ~10% (to ~91,332 BTC, ~0.46% of supply). The Ordinals/Runes narrative that drove 2024-25 is ''played out'' per builders; Magic Eden exited Bitcoin NFTs (Mar 2026). What works is restaking/staking (Babylon ~$4.95B TVL, Lombard/LBTC ~$1B, ~60% of BTC liquid-staking) and payments (Lightning, Spark, Stacks + Circle USDCx). Fee-demand from inscriptions matters long-term for miner security as the subsidy shrinks.","outlook":"BULL: Bitcoin cements itself as the reserve/settlement asset of crypto and TradFi; restaking (Babylon) and institutional custody rails give BTC productive yield without abandoning its ethos. BASE: Dominant store-of-value with steady institutional flows but a perennially thin, narrative-dependent app layer. BEAR: BTCFi keeps bleeding, no new catalyst emerges, and long-run miner-fee security questions resurface. Top risk: weak native app/fee ecosystem + eventual security-budget dependence on fees. Watch: ETF/treasury flows, Babylon/Lombard restaking TVL, Lightning/Spark payments, inscription fee demand. Most likely: BASE-to-BULL as an asset; BEAR on native on-chain activity.","sources":[{"title":"BTCFi in 2026: Why Bitcoin DeFi TVL Shrank 74% (Spark)","url":"https://www.spark.money/research/btcfi-bitcoin-defi-landscape-2026"},{"title":"2026 Layer 2 Outlook (The Block)","url":"https://www.theblock.co/post/383329/2026-layer-2-outlook"},{"title":"Ordinals, Runes and the Future of Bitcoin L2s (Starknet)","url":"https://www.starknet.io/blog/ordinals-runes-and-the-future-of-bitcoin-l2s/"}]}');
INSERT INTO "chain_analysis" ("chain","take","sentiment","trend","updated_at","sources","profile") VALUES ('Starknet','The +34% 7d volume ties to Starknet''s BTCfi pivot: strkBTC - a Bitcoin asset with shielded balances and confidential transfers that keeps DeFi composability - drove a ~50% price surge on its May launch, and the network activated Bitcoin staking (BTC gets 0.25 weight / 25% of consensus power, STRK the rest), which lifted volume ~38% at announcement. Fresh catalysts: a June 30 post-quantum roadmap leaning on STARK hash-based proofs, and a July 6 validator-program overhaul shifting from breadth to depth (winners now get 5-20M STRK vs 2-5M). The hard counterweight is a 127M-token team/investor unlock on July 15 that will likely pin price sideways - builders ship live BTCfi infra while traders stay anchored to the monthly unlock schedule.','mixed','strkBTC / BTC staking vs July 15 unlock','2026-07-08 15:14:24','[{"title":"Starknet to enable bitcoin staking for network consensus","url":"https://www.theblock.co/post/367800/starknet-bitcoin-staking-consensus-strk"},{"title":"Starknet introduces strkBTC for private bitcoin and confidential DeFi","url":"https://www.theblock.co/post/391420/starknet-introduces-strkbtc-to-bring-private-bitcoin-and-confidential-defi-transactions-to-its-layer-2-network"},{"title":"StarkWare bets on fewer validators in STRK program overhaul","url":"https://www.cryptotimes.io/2026/07/06/starkware-bets-on-fewer-validators-in-strk-program-overhaul/"}]','{"what_it_does":"Starknet is a ZK-rollup scaling Ethereum (and increasingly Bitcoin) using STARK proofs and the Cairo language. In 2026 it runs native DeFi, staking and a growing Bitcoin layer — strkBTC brings shielded, ZK-private BTC that can toggle public/private while staying composable. It is the only production rollup using a proving system with no trusted setup. Every account is a smart contract (native account abstraction). TVL is small (<$200M) versus Arbitrum/Base.","purpose":"Built by StarkWare (Eli Ben-Sasson, Uri Kolodny; token/mainnet maturing 2023-24) to scale Ethereum with validity proofs and pioneer STARK cryptography. The thesis: cryptographic scaling plus a purpose-built language (Cairo) unlocks provable computation Ethereum can''t do natively — now extended to make Starknet a Bitcoin execution layer.","non_economic":"Strong cryptography/research reputation but non-EVM porting friction limits DeFi breadth (Aave/Uniswap don''t deploy unchanged). 2026 momentum: staking grew 11x in a year to 1.1B+ STRK (>23% of supply) and BTC staking went 0 to 1,700+ BTC in three months (StarkWare + Anchorage validators). S-two prover delivered ~100x efficiency; Grinta upgrade cut latency to ~0.5s pre-confirmations. strkBTC live ~May 2026; a BitVM bridge (Alpen) and quantum-resistance roadmap are planned. Full sequencer decentralization slated 2026. Weak STRK price (~$0.08) and unlock overhang.","outlook":"BULL: Bitcoin-execution-layer thesis (strkBTC, BitVM bridge) plus best-in-class trustless ZK tech and fast staking growth make Starknet the venue for private, provable BTC/ETH DeFi. BASE: Technically respected niche chain that keeps shipping but stays small on TVL/users. BEAR: Non-EVM friction, weak token price and unlock pressure keep it marginal versus EVM L2s. Top risk: small TVL/adoption + non-EVM porting cost + slow sequencer decentralization. Watch: strkBTC/BitVM bridge traction, sequencer decentralization, staking growth, TVL vs EVM L2s. Most likely: BASE, upside hinges on the Bitcoin-layer bet landing.","sources":[{"title":"Starknet in 2025: ZK Scaling Goes Mainstream — Year in Review","url":"https://www.starknet.io/blog/starknet-2025-year-in-review/"},{"title":"Starknet launches strkBTC for ZK-powered shielded Bitcoin (The Block)","url":"https://www.theblock.co/post/400903/starknet-launches-strkbtc-to-bring-zk-powered-shielded-bitcoin-to-its-layer-2-network"},{"title":"Starknet Decentralization Roadmap","url":"https://www.starknet.io/roadmap/"}]}');
INSERT INTO "chain_analysis" ("chain","take","sentiment","trend","updated_at","sources","profile") VALUES ('Sei','The 159% 30d volume figure is migration turnover, not organic growth: Sei''s irreversible EVM migration (April 6-8, moving Cosmos-native assets into a Solidity/MetaMask environment) drove a positioning spike, but TVL has collapsed ~93% from a ~$626M July 2025 peak to ~$42M, and native DEX Oxium shut down June 27 citing unsustainable revenue - a real ecosystem-strain signal. The forward catalyst is the July 1 Giga Whitepaper V2, adding the Sedna pre-execution privacy layer and tightening finality to sub-250ms at 200k+ TPS - which Messari calls the most integrated protocol-level attempt at institutional execution. But Sedna isn''t live on mainnet, and ~72% of TVL is tokenized RWA (Ondo, Apollo, Libre, GAIB ~$308M) that sits idle without execution flow. The thesis is entirely ''can fast infra attract sticky liquidity,'' unproven so far.','bearish','EVM migration turnover, TVL collapse','2026-07-08 15:14:31','[{"title":"Sei Giga: bringing institutional execution onchain (Messari)","url":"https://messari.io/report/sei-giga-bringing-institutional-execution-onchain"},{"title":"SEI''s surge: flow analysis of the zero-fee catalyst","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/sei-10-surge-flow-analysis-fee-catalyst-2604/"},{"title":"Sei price prediction: can the Giga upgrade spark a bullish surge","url":"https://cryptorank.io/news/feed/e3d9c-sei-price-prediction-giga-upgrade-5"}]','{"what_it_does":"Sei is a trading-optimized, high-performance L1 that in 2026 is going EVM-only. It delivers parallelized EVM execution with ~400ms finality (~12,500 TPS today) and is best suited to high-frequency trading, order-book DeFi, gaming and RWAs. In Q3 2025 gaming drove 116M transactions (+138% QoQ). Its Giga upgrade targets 5 gigagas/sec, 200,000+ TPS and sub-400ms finality.","purpose":"Founded by Jeff Feng and Jayendra Jog (Sei Labs; mainnet 2023), Sei was built as a sector-specific chain for trading — originally a Cosmos app-chain with a built-in order-book — optimized end-to-end for fast, MEV-resistant exchange. In 2026 it pivoted to a pure high-performance EVM identity.","non_economic":"Bold ''subtraction as strategy'': SIP-3 deprecates CosmWasm/Cosmos types, converting to EVM-only (final migration Apr 6-8, 2026) to court Solidity''s larger developer pool. Giga is a multi-phase rebuild (Autobahn multi-proposer consensus, async execution, from-scratch EVM client ~40x more efficient, Sedna private mempool). Roadmap site launched May 27 2026; the announcement drove a ~15% SEI surge. Institutional/RWA focus + a staked-SEI ETF decision are seen as binary catalysts. Headwind: flagship order-book DEX Oxium is shutting down (Aug 2026) citing unsustainable revenue; Giga''s headline numbers are devnet-only so far.","outlook":"BULL: Giga ships and Sei becomes the fastest production EVM — full Solidity compatibility at speeds rivaling non-EVM chains — winning HFT/RWA flow; ETF approval adds a catalyst. BASE: Fast EVM contender that keeps momentum but sits in a crowded field (Monad, MegaETH). BEAR: EVM-only migration disrupts its base, Oxium-style ecosystem attrition continues, and Giga''s devnet claims don''t hold on mainnet. Top risk: unproven mainnet performance + ecosystem retention through the migration. Watch: Giga milestone tracker, post-migration app activity, staked-SEI ETF decision. Most likely: BASE with real bull optionality if Giga delivers.","sources":[{"title":"Sei Giga Overview: The Fastest EVM Blockchain (Sei Docs)","url":"https://docs.sei.io/learn/sei-giga"},{"title":"Sei Drops Cosmos, Goes EVM-Only via SIP-3 (BlockEden)","url":"https://blockeden.xyz/blog/2026/04/03/sei-network-drops-cosmos-evm-only-sip3-migration-multi-vm-architecture/"},{"title":"SEI unveils Giga upgrade roadmap, 200K TPS target (Crypto Briefing)","url":"https://cryptobriefing.com/sei-giga-upgrade-200000-tps-roadmap/"}]}');
INSERT INTO "chain_analysis" ("chain","take","sentiment","trend","updated_at","sources","profile") VALUES ('Stellar','The soft DEX volume is a sideshow - Stellar''s real engine is institutional payments/RWA, where $3.3B+ tokenized RWA now sits and stablecoin payment volume runs ~$5.5B. Two dated catalysts anchor the thesis: a mainnet vote on Protocol 27 (''Zipper'') set for July 8 bringing Soroban smart accounts, delegated auth and account abstraction; and the landmark May DTCC deal connecting the backbone of US securities settlement to Stellar with XLM as settlement token (live assets targeted H1 2027). The unresolved question is value accrual: XLM has fixed supply and no burn, so routing securities settlement through the network doesn''t automatically bid the token - that 2027 timeline means near-term price is sentiment-driven. The March 17 SEC/CFTC digital-commodity designation removes a key institutional barrier.','bullish','DTCC settlement + Protocol 27, weak accrual','2026-07-08 15:15:21','[{"title":"DTCC selects Stellar to tokenize $114 trillion in assets","url":"https://www.kucoin.com/blog/dtcc-selects-stellar-tokenize-114-trillion-xlm-surge"},{"title":"Stellar price prediction: what the DTCC tokenization deal means for XLM","url":"https://crypto.news/stellar-price-prediction-dtcc-tokenization-deal-xlm/"},{"title":"Institutional stablecoin adoption fuels XLM payments boom","url":"https://crypto-economy.com/institutional-stablecoin-adoption-fuels-xlm-payments-boom-on-stellar/"}]','{"what_it_does":"Stellar is a payments-focused L1 that in 2026 pairs its original fast/cheap cross-border rails with Soroban smart contracts (Rust/WASM). Its real-world use is stablecoin settlement and tokenized RWAs: MoneyGram''s live crypto-to-cash service (170+ countries) runs on Stellar, Franklin Templeton''s BENJI holds ~$480M on-chain, and $3.3B+ in tokenized RWAs sit on the network. USDC/EURC are natively integrated; MoneyGram''s MGUSD launched June 2026.","purpose":"Founded 2014 by Jed McCaleb and Joyce Kim (Stellar Development Foundation) to enable fast, low-cost cross-border payments and financial inclusion — connecting banks, payment systems and people, especially in underserved markets. Soroban (2024) added programmability for stablecoins and RWAs.","non_economic":"Mixed sentiment: landmark institutional adoption vs unconvincing price momentum. Soroban launched with a $100M adoption fund; SCF grants up to $150k per round. DeFi is expanding (Templar lending, first concentrated-liquidity DEX, perps/PayFi coming). XLM was named a US ''digital commodity'' (SEC/CFTC, Mar 17 2026) and is ISO 20022-compatible (SWIFT alignment). Protocol 27 ''Zipper'' (smart accounts/account abstraction) votes July 8 2026; DTCC integration eyed H1 2027. Key caveat: much settlement is in USDC, so value accrual to XLM depends on aggregate throughput, not direct token use.","outlook":"BULL: Stablecoin/RWA momentum (MoneyGram, Franklin, DTCC) + Soroban + regulatory clarity make Stellar a core institutional settlement rail and XLM utility grows with throughput. BASE: Proven payments niche with steady stablecoin/RWA volume but modest DeFi and weak XLM value capture. BEAR: Usage settles in USDC with little XLM demand; smart-contract ecosystem stays thin versus rivals. Top risk: value-accrual gap between network utility and the XLM token. Watch: Protocol 27 outcome, MGUSD/RWA growth, DTCC integration, Soroban DeFi TVL. Most likely: BASE — real institutional utility, XLM upside less certain.","sources":[{"title":"XLM Payments Push Gains Steam as Institutions Choose Stellar (Live Bitcoin News)","url":"https://www.livebitcoinnews.com/xlm-payments-push-gains-steam-as-institutions-choose-stellar-for-stablecoins/"},{"title":"Stellar''s DTCC Moment (CryptoDaily)","url":"https://cryptodaily.co.uk/2026/05/stellar-dtcc-moment-xlm-tokenized-assets"},{"title":"Stellar Soroban: Smart Contracts for Stablecoin Infrastructure (Eco)","url":"https://eco.com/support/en/articles/15346520-stellar-soroban-smart-contracts-for-stablecoin-infrastructure"}]}');
INSERT INTO "chain_analysis" ("chain","take","sentiment","trend","updated_at","sources","profile") VALUES ('Unichain','The 25-41% volume growth is Unichain executing on the UNIfication thesis: Uniswap governance turned on the fee switch and burned 100M UNI (~$596M) in Dec 2025, routing Unichain sequencer revenue directly into a UNI burn - so Unichain volume IS the demand driver. It now handles ~50% of v4 volume and hit ~$12B monthly; the pending catalyst is a governance vote to expand fee-sharing to eight more L2s (Base, Arbitrum, OP, X Layer, others), plus Uniswap becoming the native AMM for Robinhood Chain which went live July 1. The bear case is arithmetic: burns run ~$34M annualized against a 20M-UNI/year growth-emissions budget, so if Unichain volume stays below ~$20-30B/month and LPs drift to Aerodrome, market-share erosion outpaces the burn and the accrual story stalls.','bullish','Sequencer-fee burn + v4 volume capture','2026-07-08 15:16:14','[{"title":"UNIfication proposal and fee switch","url":"https://blog.uniswap.org/unification"},{"title":"Uniswap fee switch live, 100M tokens burned","url":"https://www.bitget.com/news/detail/12560605397905"},{"title":"UNI jumps 12% as Uniswap eyes $27M L2 fee rollout","url":"https://crypto.news/uni-jumps-12-as-uniswap-eyes-27m-l2-fee-rollout/"}]','{"what_it_does":"Unichain is Uniswap''s own Ethereum L2 (OP Stack, mainnet Feb 12 2025), purpose-built as ''the home for DeFi.'' It inverts the usual model — the chain is built around Uniswap''s liquidity rather than hosting DeFi as one app among many. It offers 1-second blocks with 200ms Flashblocks preconfirmations and ~95% lower fees than L1, and handles a majority of Uniswap v4 volume. Users are DeFi traders and LPs; 2,500+ custom v4 Hook pools deployed.","purpose":"Built by Uniswap Labs to fix DeFi''s shortcomings after years running the largest DEX — a fast, decentralized Superchain L2 optimized for liquidity and cross-chain DeFi. A core strategic aim: transform UNI from a pure governance token into a utility/staking token via Unichain''s validation network.","non_economic":"Strong DeFi-native mindshare given Uniswap''s brand. The pivotal non-economic development is UNI''s re-purposing: a Validation Network lets UNI holders stake to validate and earn sequencer fees, plus a governance proposal directs sequencer fees (after L1 costs and Optimism''s 15%) into a UNI burn — the ''UNIfication.'' $60M DAO incentives drove TVL from $9M to $267M in 48 hours; TVL peaked ~$1.3B. Euler and Morpho deployed early; USDC native. Uniswap Foundation funds a Builder Toolkit. Decentralization stage is disputed across sources; no token airdrop announced.","outlook":"BULL: Unichain concentrates Uniswap v4 liquidity and the UNI staking/burn ''UNIfication'' gives UNI real cash-flow utility, making it the default DeFi L2. BASE: Dominant Uniswap-v4 venue but adoption beyond Uniswap and incentives remains the open question. BEAR: Growth stays incentive-dependent, decentralization lags, and general L2s (Base/Arbitrum) keep broader DeFi. Top risk: organic adoption beyond Uniswap''s own liquidity + incentive sustainability. Watch: UNIfication burn/staking rollout, v4 TVL/volume share, post-incentive retention, decentralization stage. Most likely: BASE with clear upside if UNI utility lands.","sources":[{"title":"Introducing Unichain — an Ethereum L2 Designed for DeFi (Uniswap)","url":"https://blog.uniswap.org/introducing-unichain"},{"title":"UNIfication (Uniswap)","url":"https://blog.uniswap.org/unification"},{"title":"Transforming DeFi: The Strategic Leap of Unichain (21Shares)","url":"https://www.21shares.com/en-us/research/newsletter-issue-246"}]}');
INSERT INTO "chain_analysis" ("chain","take","sentiment","trend","updated_at","sources","profile") VALUES ('Provenance','The violent volume swings (a 30d spike, a 7d collapse) are the signature of lumpy institutional RWA settlement, not retail flow: Provenance is Figure''s chain, and Figure leads tokenized private credit with ~$15B of the market''s $20B active loans, having originated $21B+ in loans on-chain. TVL hit an all-time $1.2B on institutional loans/mortgages/HELOCs, and Figure''s securitization won the first-ever AAA ratings from both S&P and Moody''s for a blockchain-native deal. The catalyst to watch is OPEN, Figure''s on-chain public equity network (its own FIGR stock listing natively, Jump Trading market-making). The bear case is composability: critics argue a siloed RWA chain doesn''t add utility, and Figure holding ~25% of HASH plus executing Foundation directives concentrates control.','neutral','Lumpy institutional RWA settlement','2026-07-08 15:10:58','[{"title":"Provenance Blockchain TVL hits all-time high of $1.2 billion","url":"https://thedefiant.io/news/blockchains/provenance-blockchain-tvl-hits-all-time-high-of-usd1-2-billion"},{"title":"Figure announces community-approved Provenance Foundation update","url":"https://investors.figure.com/news-releases/news-release-details/figure-technology-solutions-announces-community-approved-update"},{"title":"Tokenization & RWA Standards Report 2026","url":"https://blog.redstone.finance/2026/03/26/tokenization-rwa-report-2026/"}]','{"what_it_does":"Provenance is a Cosmos-SDK, purpose-built L1 for regulated financial services and real-world-asset tokenization. In 2026 it is a leading RWA settlement/registry layer with $21B+ of real-world assets onboarded — loans, private credit, HELOCs/mortgages and increasingly on-chain equities. Its users are financial institutions, fintechs and lenders (above all Figure), and fees are USD-denominated but paid in the HASH token.","purpose":"Created by Figure (Mike Cagney) to modernize financial-services plumbing: originate, finance, service and trade financial assets on-chain, collapsing T+2 settlement to seconds via systems like DART (Digital Asset Registration Technologies). It is deliberately institutional, not retail/speculative.","non_economic":"Low retail/social footprint but heavy institutional signal. Jan 2026: Figure (Nasdaq: FIGR) took a formal operational role executing community directives for the Provenance Foundation after an on-chain vote; Figure holds ~25% of HASH. Revised tokenomics reduce inflation-reliance and add network fees for validators/delegators. Figure''s securitizations earned first-of-kind AAA ratings from S&P/Moody''s; it launched YLDS (first SEC-registered interest-bearing stablecoin) and OPEN (on-chain public equities). Black Lake/Nuva Labs minted $25M of mortgages on-chain. Main concern: near-total dependence on Figure.","outlook":"BULL: RWA tokenization goes mainstream and Provenance''s purpose-built, compliance-grade rails plus Figure''s origination engine and on-chain equities (OPEN) make it the institutional-credit settlement layer. BASE: Steady RWA volume growth but activity stays concentrated in the Figure ecosystem. BEAR: Single-entity (Figure) concentration, thin HASH liquidity and ~44% of supply still unlocking cap external adoption and price. Top risk: Figure-dependence/centralization + token dilution. Watch: non-Figure issuer adoption, OPEN equity listings, revised-tokenomics fee capture, HASH unlock schedule. Most likely: BASE — real RWA traction, external-adoption question unresolved.","sources":[{"title":"Figure takes operational role at Provenance Blockchain Foundation (The Block)","url":"https://www.theblock.co/post/386526/figure-operational-role-provenance-blockchain-foundation-community-structure"},{"title":"Provenance: Leading Blockchain for RWA Tokenization","url":"https://provenance.io/"},{"title":"Black Lake and Nuva Labs tokenize $25M in mortgage loans on Provenance (Crypto Briefing)","url":"https://cryptobriefing.com/black-lake-nuva-labs-tokenize-mortgage-provenance/"}]}');
INSERT INTO "chain_analysis" ("chain","take","sentiment","trend","updated_at","sources","profile") VALUES ('Plasma','The -11% 7d TVL bleed is unlock-driven: a 2.5B XPL (25% of supply) team/investor unlock begins in July after the one-year cliff from the Sept 2025 mainnet, with a ~1B-token tranche around July 28 and ~106M new tokens monthly through 2028. This is the Thiel/Tether/Bitfinex-backed stablecoin L1 that launched to $8.4B TVL then bled to ~$2.7B when it turned out most stablecoins sat parked in lending pools rather than moving as payments. The recovery lever was Tether picking Plasma as a launch network for its April 14 self-custody tether.wallet, fitting Plasma''s gas-abstraction design. Watch validator staking activation (projected ~5% reward) as the intended supply sink - if staking participation lags the unlock, price stays capped.','bearish','Team unlock vs staking supply sink','2026-07-08 15:12:40','[{"title":"Plasma XPL: speculative play amid institutional interest and supply dynamics","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/plasma-xpl-high-conviction-speculative-play-emerging-institutional-interest-supply-dynamics-2512-70/"},{"title":"Plasma hits top 10: what''s driving the 85% TVL surge","url":"https://www.kucoin.com/blog/plasma-xpl-tvl-surge-top-10-crypto-analysis"},{"title":"Plasma XPL loses 85% of value in six weeks: what happened","url":"https://99bitcoins.com/news/altcoins/plasma-xpl-crypto-loses-85-of-its-value-in-six-weeks-what-happened/"}]','{"what_it_does":"Plasma is a stablecoin-first EVM L1 (mainnet Sept 25, 2025) built around USDT payments. Its headline feature is protocol-level zero-fee USDT (USDT0) transfers via a built-in paymaster; other transactions can pay gas in USDT or XPL, and state roots are periodically anchored to Bitcoin. It targets stablecoin payments at scale — competing directly with Tron for USDT settlement — and launched with 100+ DeFi partners (Aave, Ethena, Fluid, Euler).","purpose":"Founded to make stablecoins ''first-class citizens'' of a chain, Plasma is backed by Tether/Bitfinex (Paolo Ardoino), Founders Fund and Framework. The explicit thesis: if stablecoins are money, the chain should treat them natively — free transfers, no separate gas token, Bitcoin-anchored security. (Unrelated to Buterin/Poon''s 2017 ''Plasma'' scaling concept.)","non_economic":"Extraordinary launch demand: $1B deposit campaign filled in under an hour; public sale oversubscribed ~7x (~$373M raised); XPL debuted ~14.6x above ICO price. Reached $5.6B TVL in week one — one of the fastest liquidity accumulations ever. Consumer push via Plasma One neobank (stablecoin debit card, 4% cashback, 10%+ APY, 150+ countries). USDT0 uses LayerZero''s OFT omnichain standard. Risks are structural: zero-fee model is Tether-subsidized, heavy USDT concentration, a curated (centralized) validator set, and US token distribution pushed to July 2026.","outlook":"BULL: Tether''s backing + zero-fee UX + day-one DeFi make Plasma a leading USDT settlement chain, taking share from Tron as stablecoin payments scale globally. BASE: Establishes a real stablecoin niche but remains one of several payment L1s, dependent on subsidy economics. BEAR: Paymaster subsidy proves unsustainable, or a Tether regulatory hit ripples straight into Plasma''s core value prop; validator centralization deters trust. Top risk: dependence on Tether/USDT and subsidy sustainability. Watch: retained TVL post-incentives, Plasma One adoption, validator decentralization, USDT settlement share. Most likely: BASE with bull optionality tied to Tether''s commitment.","sources":[{"title":"Plasma Review 2026: XPL, Zero-Fee USDT (CryptoAdventure)","url":"https://cryptoadventure.com/plasma-review-2026-xpl-zero-fee-usdt-and-stablecoin-payments-at-scale/"},{"title":"Plasma (XPL) Mainnet Launch (DropsTab)","url":"https://dropstab.com/research/crypto/plasma-xpl-mainnet-launch"},{"title":"What Is Plasma (XPL)? Stablecoin L1 (Eco)","url":"https://eco.com/support/en/articles/11802920-what-is-plasma-xpl-stablecoin-l1-in-2026"}]}');
INSERT INTO "chain_analysis" ("chain","take","sentiment","trend","updated_at","sources","profile") VALUES ('Ink','The steady TVL and volume growth is a near-pure Tydro story: Ink is Kraken''s OP-Stack L2, and after Aave DAO approved (~99.8%) a white-label Aave V3 deployment, that single protocol - Tydro - drove 97%+ of Ink''s TVL rise, peaking around $600M deposits / $350M TVL and carrying the chain past $500M. The demand funnel is Kraken DeFi Earn (Jan 2026, USDC yield via Tydro/Aave on the backend, $200M+ deposits) piping CEX users on-chain, Base-playbook style. The catalyst ahead is the INK token TGE/airdrop expected Q2-Q3 via Kraken Drops. The warning sign: daily active addresses fell 50%+ since late March even as revenue rose - capital is parked and yield-seeking, not a broad active user base, so the airdrop needs to convert depositors into stickier usage.','neutral','Kraken/Tydro CEX-to-DeFi funnel','2026-07-08 15:15:13','[{"title":"Kraken''s Ink L2 surpasses $500M in TVL","url":"https://thedefiant.io/news/blockchains/kraken-s-ink-layer-2-surpasses-usd500-million-in-tvl"},{"title":"Kraken''s Ink L2 leverages Aave to launch lending platform Tydro","url":"https://www.crowdfundinsider.com/2026/05/280706-defi-adoption-krakens-ink-l2-leverages-aave-to-launch-lending-platform-tydro/"},{"title":"How Ink and Kraken use Aave","url":"https://aave.com/blog/kraken-ink"}]','{"what_it_does":"Ink is Kraken''s Ethereum L2, built on the Optimism OP Stack as a purpose-built DeFi chain. In 2026 it hosts DEXs, lending, perps and yield protocols with ~1-second blocks and sub-cent fees, and its distinct edge is converting Kraken''s ~10M+ exchange users into DeFi users with minimal friction. As a Superchain member it taps shared liquidity from launch. TVL grew from ~$7M to $450M+ within months.","purpose":"Announced 2024 and built by Kraken, Ink''s stated purpose is to be a frictionless CeFi-to-DeFi bridge — a DeFi-optimized L2 that onboards Kraken''s existing customers on-chain rather than competing for net-new users. It initially launched without a native token (ETH for gas), ''Inkonomics.''","non_economic":"Moderate but Kraken-backed social presence; distribution (not user acquisition) is the strategic advantage. It was the first Superchain network to launch with multiple fault-proof challengers (Gelato + Kraken), a notable security/decentralization signal, and shares governance/interop with 29+ OP Stack chains (Base, Soneium, Worldchain). It launched ahead of schedule and, after initially eschewing a token, now has a native token reportedly on the way — a key forward catalyst. Ecosystem is DeFi-centric and still maturing.","outlook":"BULL: Kraken funnels millions of vetted users on-chain and the incoming token plus Superchain liquidity make Ink a leading exchange-native DeFi L2. BASE: Steady DeFi growth on Kraken distribution but stays a mid-size Superchain member. BEAR: DeFi-only focus and dependence on Kraken conversion cap organic adoption; token launch underwhelms or crowded L2 field limits share. Top risk: reliance on Kraken user conversion + intense L2 competition. Watch: native token launch/tokenomics, TVL trajectory, Kraken-to-Ink onboarding conversion, Superchain interop. Most likely: BASE with token-launch-driven upside.","sources":[{"title":"Announcing Ink: The new DeFi destination (Kraken Blog)","url":"https://blog.kraken.com/news/announcing-ink"},{"title":"Welcoming Ink to the Superchain (Optimism)","url":"https://optimism.io/blog/welcoming-ink-to-the-superchain"},{"title":"Ink: Everything You Need To Know About Kraken''s New Blockchain (CoinGecko)","url":"https://www.coingecko.com/learn/ink-kraken-blockchain-layer-2-crypto"}]}');
INSERT INTO "chain_analysis" ("chain","take","sentiment","trend","updated_at","sources","profile") VALUES ('Flare','Thin spot volume masks the real driver, which is XRPFi: Flare activated FAssets v1.3 on May 15 letting XRP holders mint DeFi-ready FXRP in a single XRPL transaction (even as a plain Binance/Kraken withdrawal), and FLR jumped 14% on it - ~150M FXRP (~$200M of XRP) is now minted with 85%+ deployed into lending/vaults/staking. On the supply side, FIP.16 (live April 24) cut inflation 40%, raised base gas 20x, and routes MEV/fees into the FIRE entity that burns FLR via buybacks, potentially lifting annual burn from ~7.5M to ~300M FLR. The end of the FlareDrop program (Jan 30) removes the biggest structural supply overhang. The catch: ''the market no longer buys blueprints'' - the whole thesis needs XRP holders to actually keep embracing DeFi, with FBTC and Q3 confidential-compute (Flare 2.0) as the next proof points.','bullish','XRPFi (FXRP) + FIP.16 burn mechanics','2026-07-08 15:16:06','[{"title":"Flare Network rallies 14% on FAssets upgrade","url":"https://crypto.news/flare-network-rallies-14percent-on-fassets-upgrade/"},{"title":"From activity to value accrual: our plan for FLR","url":"https://flare.network/news/from-activity-to-value-accrual-our-plan-for-flr"},{"title":"Beyond FlareDrops: FLR enters its operational utility era","url":"https://flare.network/news/beyond-flaredrops-flr-enters-operational-utility-era"}]','{"what_it_does":"Flare is an EVM L1 branded the ''blockchain of data,'' with two native data protocols baked into the chain: the Flare Time Series Oracle (FTSO) for decentralized price feeds and the Flare Data Connector (FDC) for trustless external/cross-chain data. Its flagship product is FAssets — trust-minimized bridged assets like FXRP that bring non-smart-contract tokens (XRP, and roadmap BTC/DOGE) into DeFi. In 2026 its core niche is XRPFi: making XRP programmable while XRPL stays the settlement layer.","purpose":"Founded 2019 by Hugo Philion (CEO, finance/ML background), Sean Rowan and Dr. Naïri Usher (CSO, quantum computing PhD). Original mission: bring smart-contract functionality and DeFi to non-contract chains (Bitcoin, XRP) via secure, native data/interoperability infrastructure — with enshrined oracles rather than external middleware.","non_economic":"Distinct ''data''/oracle positioning; 67% of tokens staked backs oracle security. 2026 momentum: FAssets launched on mainnet Sept 24 2025 (week-one 5M FXRP mint cap), backed by a 2.2B FLR FAssets Incentive Program (July 2025-July 2026) seeding a modular DeFi stack (SparkDEX, Kinetic, Flamix, Spectra). Cancun/Dencun-aligned hard fork (Dec 2025) lowered execution costs. Notable distribution: ''Flare Learn'' launched inside Revolut (Nov 2025), exposing millions to Flare. Roadmap extends FAssets to FBTC/FDOGE.","outlook":"BULL: XRPFi takes off — Flare becomes the DeFi/yield layer for the large idle XRP (and later BTC/DOGE) base, with its enshrined oracle/data stack as a durable moat. BASE: Interesting data/interop niche with growing FXRP usage but modest overall TVL and mindshare. BEAR: FAssets adoption stalls, incentive emissions fade without organic demand, and Flare stays a small mid-cap. Top risk: FAssets/XRPFi adoption may not scale beyond incentives. Watch: FXRP mint growth and FBTC/FDOGE launches, DeFi TVL post-incentive-program, FTSO/FDC integrations. Most likely: BASE, upside contingent on XRPFi traction.","sources":[{"title":"Flare founder Hugo Philion: the ''blockchain of data'' (PANews)","url":"https://www.panewslab.com/en/articles/gazmd9bl"},{"title":"Flare: The Launch of FAssets (Messari)","url":"https://messari.io/report/flare-the-launch-of-fassets"},{"title":"Flare: Expanding XRP''s Role in DeFi (Messari)","url":"https://messari.io/report/flare-expanding-xrp-s-role-in-defi"}]}');
INSERT INTO "chain_analysis" ("chain","take","sentiment","trend","updated_at","sources","profile") VALUES ('X Layer','The +117% daily volume swing is OKX-exchange-driven, not organic DeFi: the core catalyst is Exchange OS, OKX''s protocol-level toolkit on X Layer letting anyone spin up spot/perp/prediction venues, where operators must stake OKB to deploy - creating structural OKB lockup and a several-hundred-percent volume spike on launch. This layers on the OKTChain migration (converting ~1.2B OKT to OKB by Jan 1, 2026) and a 65M-token burn that sent OKB up ~160%, plus an OKX Ventures/STBL RWA-backed stablecoin. The reality check: DeFiLlama-standard TVL is genuinely tiny (single-digit-millions, ~#61 rank) with recent stablecoin outflows - most of the bullish ''$2-4B TVL'' figures conflate OKB market cap with on-chain TVL. This is an exchange-token flywheel, so watch whether real on-chain liquidity ever shows up under the volume.','neutral','Exchange OS + OKB burn flywheel','2026-07-08 15:17:11','[{"title":"OKB surges 15% as OKX launches Exchange OS on X Layer","url":"https://coinmarketcap.com/top-stories/6a1b89244db88c7a80e9e9c7/"},{"title":"OKB surges 160% after 65M token burn and X Layer upgrade","url":"https://www.cointribune.com/en/okb-surges-160-percent-token-burn-x-layer-upgrade/"},{"title":"OKX''s ecosystem stablecoin: a flow test for X Layer''s liquidity","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/okx-ecosystem-stablecoin-flow-test-layer-liquidity-2602/"}]','{"what_it_does":"X Layer is OKX''s Ethereum L2, in 2026 the sole blockchain backing the OKX ecosystem after OKTChain was retired and migrated to it. It uses OKB as its gas token and is positioned for DeFi, payments and RWAs, connecting OKX''s 50M+ users to Ethereum. After a 2025 ''PP upgrade'' it reached ~5,000 TPS with negligible fees. On-chain traction is still modest (TVL was ~$6.5M as of Aug 2025).","purpose":"Launched by OKX with Polygon Labs (testnet 2023, mainnet Mar 2024) as a zkEVM Validium built on Polygon CDK, its purpose was to onboard OKX''s large user base onto Ethereum with low fees and privacy, tapping Polygon''s AggLayer for shared liquidity.","non_economic":"Exchange-backed but low independent social/developer footprint; developer appeal rests on easy Ethereum contract portability. The defining 2026 story is a stack migration: after Polygon announced sunsetting its public zkEVM and shifting CDK to a managed enterprise service, OKX decided (Oct 27 2025) to migrate X Layer OFF Polygon zkEVM ONTO the OP Stack — citing Polygon roadmap uncertainty and OP Stack''s larger ecosystem (~70% of L2 activity). It absorbed OKTChain (OKT to OKB swap; OKTChain ran until Jan 1 2026) and OKB''s gas-token economics were optimized. Focus repositioned to DeFi, payments and RWAs.","outlook":"BULL: As OKX''s sole chain with 50M+ users and a fresh OP Stack foundation, X Layer converts exchange distribution into real DeFi/payments/RWA activity and OKB utility. BASE: Exchange-native L2 that grows slowly off OKX onboarding but stays small in the crowded L2 field. BEAR: Repeated stack migrations, thin TVL and low organic developer interest keep it a niche exchange appendage. Top risk: low organic adoption + execution/continuity risk from the OP Stack migration. Watch: post-migration TVL/activity, OKX-to-X-Layer onboarding conversion, OKB gas/burn economics, RWA/payments launches. Most likely: BASE, dependent on OKX distribution converting to usage.","sources":[{"title":"X Layer Architecture Migration: From Polygon zkEVM to OP Stack (OKX)","url":"https://web3.okx.com/learn/x-layer-architecture-migration-from-polygon-zkevm-to-op-stack"},{"title":"OKX Launches X Layer, zkEVM L2 Built with Polygon CDK","url":"https://www.okx.com/en-us/learn/okx-launches-x1-layer-two-polygon-cdk"},{"title":"Announcement on the PP Upgrade of X Layer and OKB Gas-Token Model (OKX)","url":"https://www.okx.com/en-us/help/announcement-on-the-pp-upgrade-of-x-layer-and-optimisation-of-the-okb-gas"}]}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('Blast','2024-02',2259400000,29240000,98.7,'2024-06-06','Blast''s TVL was almost entirely mercenary capital farming the BLAST points airdrop, and when the token launched in June 2024 at a $2.9B valuation (far below farmers'' $5-10B hopes), holders dumped and pulled liquidity. TVL fell 60% within two months of the airdrop; daily active users cratered from ~77k to ~3,500, and flagship projects like Pacmoon migrated to Solana. An early-August liquidity shock wiped another ~$300M.','Truly finished as a top-tier L2 — this is a zombie, not a revival candidate. BLAST trades ~99% below ATH, TVL bottomed near $65M (down ~97%), and DAUs of ~3,500 sit against Base''s 1.3M and Arbitrum''s 330k. A credible comeback would require (a) a breakout native consumer app that specifically needs Blast, (b) fresh non-dilutive incentives, and (c) reversal of the Base/Arbitrum consolidation — all three simultaneously. Probability of returning to top-10 L2 relevance: <5%. It survives as a long-tail chain coasting on residual yield mechanics.','declining','[{"title":"BLAST Chain in 2025: From $2.7B TVL to Near-Collapse in Under Two Years","url":"https://bravenewcoin.com/insights/blast-chain-in-2025-from-2-7b-tvl-to-near-collapse-in-under-two-years"},{"title":"Blast Airdrop Puts $354 Million in the Wallets of Users—So Why Are They Mad?","url":"https://decrypt.co/237127/ethereum-layer-2-blast-airdrop-354-million-why-upset"},{"title":"Blast L2 network loses 97% of TVL - Assessing its odds of recovery","url":"https://ambcrypto.com/blast-l2-loses-97-of-tvl-assessing-its-odds-of-recovery/"},{"title":"Blast TVL Plunges Another 30% as Users Abandon the Network","url":"https://thedefiant.io/news/blockchains/blast-tvl-plunges-another-30-as-users-abandon-the-network"},{"title":"Ethereum L2 Blast Airdrops $430M Worth of BLAST, Token Immediately Selloffs","url":"https://coinmarketcap.com/academy/article/ethereum-l2-blast-airdrops-dollar430m-worth-of-blast-token-immediately-selloffs"}]','2026-07-08 15:06:35','{"founded":"2024-02","founders":"Tieshun Roquerre (aka ''Pacman''), founder of the Blur NFT marketplace; team drawn from MakerDAO, MIT, Yale and Seoul National University.","raised":"$20M seed led by Paradigm and Standard Crypto (Nov 2023), plus angel investors.","token_symbol":"BLAST","token_ath":0.02917956,"token_ath_date":"2024-06","token_current":0.00026352,"purpose":"An Ethereum optimistic-rollup L2 offering ''native yield'' — auto-rebasing 4% on ETH and 5% on stablecoins — plus NFT perps, pitched as the yield-bearing home for dApps.","situation":"The trigger was the June 26, 2024 TGE: BLAST debuted at ~$0.025 (17B-token Phase-1 drop ≈ $430M) at only a $2.9B market cap, far below the $5-10B FDV farmers had priced in — DeFiance''s Arthur Cheong publicly said he''d expected at least $5B FDV. Claimants dumped within minutes, driving the price toward $0.02. TVL had already peaked at ~$2.3B on June 5 and fell >30% to $1.6B by the drop; an early-August liquidity shock erased ~$300M more, taking TVL from $1.1B to $785M by Aug 5. Rival Base (with Coinbase distribution) and Arbitrum simultaneously pulled the mercenary capital away.","postmortem":"Blast executed a brilliant growth hack: a viral invite-only, locked-deposit points campaign backed by Paradigm''s $20M and Blur founder Pacman''s reputation pulled in $2.3B TVL and 180k+ members before mainnet even opened. But the deposits were almost entirely mercenary capital farming the BLAST airdrop, not users — daily actives ran ~77k at peak on padded referral mechanics. When BLAST launched in June 2024 at a $2.9B valuation, far below the $5-10B farmers had priced in, holders dumped and pulled liquidity; TVL fell ~60% within two months, DAUs cratered to ~3,500, flagship apps like Pacmoon fled to Solana, and an August liquidity shock erased another ~$300M. It was engineered for a TVL headline and an airdrop, with no retention loop underneath.","non_economic":"The social signals turned toxic at launch: Crypto Twitter erupted with ''genuine disappointment and provocative posts'', one whale claiming a $50M deposit netted only $100k in the drop. The cumbersome claim flow (watch a Pacman video, scan a QR, download an app, type words) amplified anger, and Scam Sniffer reported a victim losing $218k to phishing hours after launch amid gold-check impersonators. Most damning was the developer/culture exodus: Pacmoon, the flagship memecoin, decamped to Solana and its team publicly stated Blast ''never focused'' on community/culture and that native Blast tokens were ''actively disincentivized with zero social support'' — a rare on-record indictment from a former flagship app.","lessons_learned":["A locked-deposit points campaign manufactures a TVL headline but selects for mercenary capital; the peak TVL is a liability, not an asset, because it must all be paid off or it leaves.","Launch valuation vs. farmer expectations is the single biggest airdrop-day risk — pricing below the community''s implied FDV guarantees a reflexive dump regardless of fundamentals.","Distribution beats yield gimmicks: Base''s Coinbase funnel and Arbitrum''s ecosystem retained users that Blast''s 4-5% native yield could not."],"could_differ":"Blast could have gated far less capital and instead spent its Paradigm war-chest on durable app subsidies and native-token support (the exact thing Pacmoon said was missing), so a real memecoin/DeFi culture had a reason to stay past the drop. A smaller, retention-weighted airdrop with a launch FDV set at or below farmer expectations would have avoided the reflexive dump. Neither fully saves it against Base''s distribution moat, but a sticky consumer app layer plausibly keeps TVL in the hundreds of millions rather than collapsing 97%.","outlook":"Truly finished as a top-tier L2 — this is a zombie, not a revival candidate. BLAST trades ~99% below ATH, TVL bottomed near $65M (down ~97%), and DAUs of ~3,500 sit against Base''s 1.3M and Arbitrum''s 330k. A credible comeback would require (a) a breakout native consumer app that specifically needs Blast, (b) fresh non-dilutive incentives, and (c) reversal of the Base/Arbitrum consolidation — all three simultaneously. Probability of returning to top-10 L2 relevance: <5%. It survives as a long-tail chain coasting on residual yield mechanics.","cause_tags":["mercenary_tvl","airdrop_farming","points_collapse","no_real_users"],"sources":[{"title":"BLAST Chain in 2025: From $2.7B TVL to Near-Collapse in Under Two Years","url":"https://bravenewcoin.com/insights/blast-chain-in-2025-from-2-7b-tvl-to-near-collapse-in-under-two-years"},{"title":"Blast Airdrop Puts $354 Million in the Wallets of Users—So Why Are They Mad?","url":"https://decrypt.co/237127/ethereum-layer-2-blast-airdrop-354-million-why-upset"},{"title":"Blast L2 network loses 97% of TVL - Assessing its odds of recovery","url":"https://ambcrypto.com/blast-l2-loses-97-of-tvl-assessing-its-odds-of-recovery/"},{"title":"Blast TVL Plunges Another 30% as Users Abandon the Network","url":"https://thedefiant.io/news/blockchains/blast-tvl-plunges-another-30-as-users-abandon-the-network"},{"title":"Ethereum L2 Blast Airdrops $430M Worth of BLAST, Token Immediately Selloffs","url":"https://coinmarketcap.com/academy/article/ethereum-l2-blast-airdrops-dollar430m-worth-of-blast-token-immediately-selloffs"}]}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('Merlin Chain','2024-02',529100000,7190000,98.6,'2024-05-05','Merlin''s headline TVL was built by the ''Merlin''s Seal'' staking campaign that locked BTC and BRC-20 assets to farm the MERL airdrop; 91% of deposits came from mercenary Bitcoin holders. When BTC unlock opened on April 25, 2024, right after the MERL token peaked at $2 and crashed 80%+, staked capital fled and TVL dropped 60% almost overnight. The reported peak was also inflated by double-counted, leveraged, price-interconnected assets.','A declining zombie, not fully dead: Merlin still holds thousands of locked BTC and remains a relative name among BTC sidechains, so it is not a clean shutdown like Corn. But the BTCFi L2 thesis has broken (sector TVL down ~74%), Bitcoin fundamentally does not need L2 scaling, and there is no organic app demand. A revival would require (a) a genuinely novel BTC-native app that only runs on Merlin, (b) BitVM-grade trust-minimized bridging to shed the ''sidechain'' security discount, and (c) a fresh BTCFi bull cycle — all unlikely. Probability of a meaningful comeback: ~10%; base case is slow bleed toward irrelevance.','declining','[{"title":"Bitcoin''s L2 Merlin Chain Unleashes Half of MERL Airdrop Tokens at TGE","url":"https://coingape.com/bitcoins-l2-merlin-chain-unleashes-half-of-merl-airdrop-tokens-at-tge/"},{"title":"Depth | On the Eve of Bitcoin Layer2''s Outbreak, What Can We Learn From Ethereum L2?","url":"https://www.gate.com/learn/articles/depth-on-the-eve-of-bitcoin-layer2s-outbreak-what-can-we-learn-from-ethereum-l2/3164"},{"title":"A quick look at Merlin Chain token utility and economics - BlockBeats","url":"https://en.theblockbeats.news/news/53184"},{"title":"What Is Merlin Chain? A Guide to the Native Bitcoin Layer 2 - Xverse","url":"https://www.xverse.app/blog/merlin-chain"}]','2026-07-08 15:08:14','{"founded":"2024-01","founders":"Jeff Yin, founder of Bitmap Tech (formerly RCSV), creators of the BRC-420 protocol; Jeff was a decade-long Web2 entrepreneur before pivoting to the BTC/Ordinals ecosystem.","raised":"Two undisclosed-amount rounds (Feb and Apr 2024) from OKX Ventures, Foresight Ventures, ABCDE, ArkStream, KuCoin Ventures, Spartan, Amber Group and ~20 others.","token_symbol":"MERL","token_ath":1.45,"token_ath_date":"2024-04","token_current":0.01910726,"purpose":"A Bitcoin sidechain built on Polygon CDK (marketed as a Bitcoin ZK-L2), aiming to bring DeFi, gaming and BRC-20/Ordinals-native assets to Bitcoin holders.","situation":"The precise trigger was mechanical: MERL''s TGE landed April 19, 2024, with 20% of the 2.1B supply airdropped to ''Merlin''s Seal'' stakers (50% unlocked at TGE). MERL spiked to ~$2 USDT then fell 80%+ within weeks toward cost basis. The killer event was April 25, 2024, when Merlin opened the BTC unlock function — staked Bitcoin immediately fled and TVL collapsed >60%, from a ~$3.6B peak to ~$1.3B. Interlinked collateral cascaded: BRC-420 ''Blue Boxes'' that had been staked crashed from ~1 BTC to <0.05 BTC each. Rivals mattered too — the entire BTC-L2 field (Bitlayer, B2, Corn) was farming the same finite pool of idle Bitcoin, and Babylon''s native staking later offered yield without a sidechain.","postmortem":"Merlin rode the early-2024 Bitcoin-L2 / BRC-20 mania to become the largest ''BTC L2'' almost overnight — its ''Merlin''s Seal'' staking campaign locked BTC and BRC-20 assets and hit ~$543M TVL in 24 hours (peak ~$3.5B by headline metrics), backed by OKX and a deep bench of Asian VCs. But 91% of deposits were mercenary Bitcoin holders farming the 20%-of-supply MERL airdrop, and the peak TVL was inflated by double-counted, leveraged, price-interlinked assets. When the BTC unlock opened on April 25, 2024 — right after MERL peaked near $2 and crashed 80%+ — staked capital fled and TVL dropped ~60% almost instantly. The whole BTC-L2 narrative it depended on deflated, leaving a chain with little organic app usage.","non_economic":"Merlin was one of the most-hyped BTC-L2 accounts on X in Q1 2024 (@MerlinLayer2 amassed a large following on the back of the Seal campaign), but engagement was farming-driven and the mood curdled fast: post-TGE the token became a byword for ''start high and fall low'', with community members who staked Blue Boxes near 1 BTC watching them fall below 0.05 BTC and publicly airing grievances. Coverage that had framed Merlin as the ''star project'' of the Bitcoin ecosystem pivoted to using it as the cautionary example that made analysts openly question whether BTC-L2 was ''a genuine narrative or just a flash-in-the-pan hype topic''. Note: a separate 2023 ''Merlin DEX'' rug on zkSync is an unrelated project and not attributable to Merlin Chain.","lessons_learned":["Headline TVL built from double-counted, leveraged, price-interlinked collateral (BTC + BRC-20 + Blue Boxes) is reflexive — when one leg falls the whole stack unwinds together, so the reported peak overstates real, withdrawable capital.","Gating withdrawals until after the TGE just delays and concentrates the exodus; opening the BTC unlock six days post-launch guaranteed a cliff.","A chain whose only use is parking idle BTC to farm a drop has no defense once a lower-friction yield source (native Babylon staking) appears."],"could_differ":"Merlin could have vested the airdrop far more slowly and NOT opened a one-shot BTC unlock right after TGE, smoothing the exit instead of concentrating it into a single April-25 cliff. More fundamentally, it needed a real reason for BTC to stay — a flagship consumer or DeFi app generating fees — rather than a Seal campaign that only paid people to lock and wait. Sustainable, fee-backed yield (versus a 20%-of-supply emission) plausibly retains a few hundred million in sticky TVL rather than seeing 60% leave in days, though it could not have saved the whole BTC-L2 thesis from deflating.","outlook":"A declining zombie, not fully dead: Merlin still holds thousands of locked BTC and remains a relative name among BTC sidechains, so it is not a clean shutdown like Corn. But the BTCFi L2 thesis has broken (sector TVL down ~74%), Bitcoin fundamentally does not need L2 scaling, and there is no organic app demand. A revival would require (a) a genuinely novel BTC-native app that only runs on Merlin, (b) BitVM-grade trust-minimized bridging to shed the ''sidechain'' security discount, and (c) a fresh BTCFi bull cycle — all unlikely. Probability of a meaningful comeback: ~10%; base case is slow bleed toward irrelevance.","cause_tags":["mercenary_tvl","airdrop_farming","narrative_death","token_unlock_dump"],"sources":[{"title":"Bitcoin''s L2 Merlin Chain Unleashes Half of MERL Airdrop Tokens at TGE","url":"https://coingape.com/bitcoins-l2-merlin-chain-unleashes-half-of-merl-airdrop-tokens-at-tge/"},{"title":"Depth | On the Eve of Bitcoin Layer2''s Outbreak, What Can We Learn From Ethereum L2?","url":"https://www.gate.com/learn/articles/depth-on-the-eve-of-bitcoin-layer2s-outbreak-what-can-we-learn-from-ethereum-l2/3164"},{"title":"A quick look at Merlin Chain token utility and economics - BlockBeats","url":"https://en.theblockbeats.news/news/53184"},{"title":"What Is Merlin Chain? A Guide to the Native Bitcoin Layer 2 - Xverse","url":"https://www.xverse.app/blog/merlin-chain"}]}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('Bitlayer','2024-05',406900000,440000,99.9,'2024-12-17','Bitlayer (a BitVM-based Bitcoin L2) inflated TVL with a $50M developer-incentive program and points-farming ahead of its August 2025 BTR airdrop, where 40% of supply was earmarked for ecosystem incentives. As with every emissions-subsidized BTCFi chain, the moment the farming cycle ended and BTR unlocked, mercenary capital exited and TVL collapsed toward zero. It optimized for TVL as a vanity metric instead of real fee revenue.','Effectively dead as a DeFi destination chain — at ~$0.4M TVL it is a ghost town and BTR is ~91% off ATH — but with a credible pivot lane the *company* is not necessarily finished. Revival of the chain itself is <10% and would require a breakout Bitcoin-native app that specifically needs Bitlayer plus a BTCFi sector recovery (currently down ~74%). The more probable non-zero path is the team reincarnating as BitVM bridge/infrastructure serving other chains — that has maybe a 25-30% chance of mattering — but that is survival of the team, not resurrection of the chain.','dead','[{"title":"BTR Token Transparency Report v1 | Bitlayer Blog","url":"https://blog.bitlayer.org/btr-token-transparency-report-v1/"},{"title":"$BTR Tokenomics: Everything to Know | Bitlayer Blog","url":"https://blog.bitlayer.org/btr_tokenomics/"},{"title":"Bitlayer (BTR) and the Bitcoin Layer 2 Revolution - AInvest","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/bitlayer-btr-bitcoin-layer-2-revolution-high-growth-altcoin-defi-era-2509/"},{"title":"Bitlayer Price: BTR/USD Live Price Chart, Market Cap & News | CoinGecko","url":"https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/bitlayer"}]','2026-07-08 15:08:57','{"founded":"2024-05","founders":"Kevin He and Charlie Hu, co-founders (Bitlayer Labs, Singapore, founded Oct 2023); a Bitcoin-infra team pioneering the first at-scale BitVM implementation for Bitcoin DeFi.","raised":"~$30M total: $11M Series A led by Franklin Templeton with ABCDE and Framework Ventures (Jul 2024) — first BTC-infra project backed by an ETF-licensed institution — later rounds with Polychain, Framework, StarkWare and Alliance; ~$300M valuation.","token_symbol":"BTR","token_ath":0.2372,"token_ath_date":"2026-02","token_current":0.0199,"purpose":"A BitVM-based Bitcoin L2 building a trust-minimized BitVM bridge, a yield-bearing YBTC asset and a high-throughput Bitcoin rollup, to bring Turing-complete DeFi to Bitcoin while inheriting L1 security.","situation":"The trigger was the August 27, 2025 BTR TGE across LBank and a Bitget Launchpool (2,756,000 BTR distributed), with reported TVL ~$600M going in. Only 25% of the 40% (400M BTR) ecosystem allocation unlocked at TGE, but that plus the Launchpool put fresh supply into circulation just as the $50M developer-incentive farming cycle was winding down. Post-listing volume was thin (~$15.4M/24h) and, with no organic Bitcoin app demand, mercenary TVL exited and on-chain TVL cratered toward ~$0.4M. Rival moves compounded it: Babylon had already vacuumed up $6.6B of Bitcoin staking TVL and Starknet launched 100M STRK of BTCFi incentives — both pulling the same idle-BTC capital Bitlayer needed. BTR later printed a $0.2372 high (Feb 2026) then fell ~91%.","postmortem":"Bitlayer had the strongest institutional pedigree of any BTC-L2 — Franklin Templeton''s first Bitcoin-infra bet, ~$30M from Polychain and Framework, and legitimately novel BitVM bridge engineering. Yet it played the identical playbook of its dead peers: it inflated TVL toward ~$600M with a $50M developer-incentive program and aggressive points-farming ahead of its Aug 2025 BTR listing, with 40% of supply earmarked for ecosystem incentives. That optimized for TVL as a vanity metric rather than real fee revenue, so the moment the farming cycle ended and BTR entered circulation, mercenary capital exited and on-chain TVL collapsed 99.9% toward zero. Even a Feb 2026 BTR high near $0.24 couldn''t mask that the chain had no organic Bitcoin app demand to retain deposits.","non_economic":"Bitlayer leaned on institutional-credibility signaling — the Franklin Templeton headline and mining-pool partnerships (Antpool, F2Pool, SpiderPool) — rather than a grassroots community, so its social footprint was PR-driven and thin on organic engagement. The team published transparent ''BTR Token Transparency Report'' and tokenomics posts on its blog, which is more communication than most graveyard peers offered, but the substance (40% ecosystem, 20.25% investors on a 6-month cliff/24-month vest, 12% team on 24-month cliff) telegraphed heavy future dilution to anyone reading. Developer activity was subsidized by the $50M program rather than pulled by demand, so builder interest tracked the incentive budget and faded with it. Post-collapse the story shifted to the BitVM bridge as infrastructure rather than the chain as a destination.","lessons_learned":["Blue-chip institutional backing (Franklin Templeton) buys credibility and press but does not create end-user demand — pedigree and product-market fit are orthogonal.","A $50M developer-incentive program measured by TVL rewards farming, not usage; paying for TVL guarantees the capital leaves when the payments stop.","Genuinely novel infrastructure (a BitVM bridge) can be valuable even when the chain built around it fails — the tech and the token/chain should be evaluated separately."],"could_differ":"Bitlayer should have decoupled its flagship innovation — the trust-minimized BitVM bridge — from a full L2 token launch, shipping the bridge as neutral infrastructure that other chains and Bitcoin DeFi could pay to use, rather than staking everything on retaining farmed TVL on its own chain. Tying incentives to fee-generating usage (not deposited TVL), and launching the token only after a real app demonstrated organic volume, would have avoided the TGE cliff. Because the underlying BitVM tech is real, this pivot is not just cope: an infra/bridge business plausibly survives even though the destination-chain thesis was always going to struggle against Babylon and native staking.","outlook":"Effectively dead as a DeFi destination chain — at ~$0.4M TVL it is a ghost town and BTR is ~91% off ATH — but with a credible pivot lane the *company* is not necessarily finished. Revival of the chain itself is <10% and would require a breakout Bitcoin-native app that specifically needs Bitlayer plus a BTCFi sector recovery (currently down ~74%). The more probable non-zero path is the team reincarnating as BitVM bridge/infrastructure serving other chains — that has maybe a 25-30% chance of mattering — but that is survival of the team, not resurrection of the chain.","cause_tags":["mercenary_tvl","points_collapse","unsustainable_yield","no_real_users"],"sources":[{"title":"BTR Token Transparency Report v1 | Bitlayer Blog","url":"https://blog.bitlayer.org/btr-token-transparency-report-v1/"},{"title":"$BTR Tokenomics: Everything to Know | Bitlayer Blog","url":"https://blog.bitlayer.org/btr_tokenomics/"},{"title":"Bitlayer (BTR) and the Bitcoin Layer 2 Revolution - AInvest","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/bitlayer-btr-bitcoin-layer-2-revolution-high-growth-altcoin-defi-era-2509/"},{"title":"Bitlayer Price: BTR/USD Live Price Chart, Market Cap & News | CoinGecko","url":"https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/bitlayer"}]}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('B2 Network','2024-04',103300000,2080000,98,'2024-12-07','B2 Network (BSquared) is a ZK/Taproot Bitcoin L2 whose TVL was bootstrapped by multi-phase ''BUZZ'' farming campaigns and a pre-stake incentive push ahead of its April 30, 2025 TGE. It fits the exact sector pattern: TVL was subsidized by token emissions rather than real fees, so when the BUZZ rewards ended and B2 unlocked, farmers exited and on-chain liquidity collapsed ~98%. Bitcoin''s lack of genuine app demand left nothing to retain capital.','On a terminal path as an L2, though the team is still swinging (the AI-PayFi pivot). With the Bitcoin-L2 sidechain category down ~74% and only fee-charging survivors (Babylon, tBTC) standing, a subsidized ghost-chain has no organic demand to rebuild on. A comeback would require the AI-agent-payments narrative to (a) become real with actual agent transaction volume, (b) settle specifically on B2 rather than Base/Solana, and (c) survive B2''s own heavy unlock schedule — a long-odds parlay. Probability of the chain regaining relevance: <10%; the AI pivot is more likely to be the next dead narrative than a revival.','dead','[{"title":"What Is BSquared Network (B2)? Bitcoin Layer-2 Solution - Gate","url":"https://www.gate.com/learn/articles/what-is-bsquared--network-b2/8892"},{"title":"Tokenomics | B² Network Docs","url":"https://docs.bsquared.network/b2_tokenomics"},{"title":"BSquared Network Price: B2/USD Live Price Chart, Market Cap & News | CoinGecko","url":"https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/bsquared-network"},{"title":"BSquared Network (@BSquaredNetwork) / X","url":"https://x.com/bsquarednetwork"}]','2026-07-08 15:10:13','{"founded":"2024-04","founders":"B² Network (BSquared), a Singapore-based team founded 2023; specific founders not publicly prominent.","raised":"Undisclosed seed (Jan 2024) from HashKey, OKX Ventures, IDG, Spartan Group, Animoca Brands, Alliance and P2 — exact amount not disclosed.","token_symbol":"B2","token_ath":2.11,"token_ath_date":"2025-10","token_current":0.51,"purpose":"A ZK/Taproot Bitcoin L2 marketed as the first ZK-proof verification-commitment rollup on Bitcoin, aiming to turn BTC from a payment network into full DeFi/NFT/SocialFi financial infrastructure.","situation":"The trigger was the April 30, 2025 TGE, conducted via Binance Web3 Wallet with a KuCoin listing, following multi-phase ''BUZZ'' campaigns that paid users to bridge and lock BTC. BUZZ II (5% of supply, 10.5M tokens) unlocked fully at TGE and BUZZ I began releasing, dumping farmed incentives into circulation right as the farming reason ended. B2 later printed a $2.11 ATH in Oct 2025 before falling ~76%, with 24h volume shrinking ~60% day-over-day toward ~$3.9M — the signature of drained interest. Rivals fed the exodus: Babylon''s native BTC staking and Bitlayer/Merlin were all competing for the same finite pool of idle Bitcoin, so once B2''s subsidy stopped there was nowhere the mercenary BTC wanted to stay.","postmortem":"B2 attracted a strong VC bench (HashKey, OKX, IDG, Animoca) and real ZK-rollup ambitions, and its multi-phase ''BUZZ'' campaigns plus a pre-stake push drew ~500K users and 5,000+ BTC ahead of its April 30, 2025 TGE. But the deposits were emissions-subsidized rather than fee-driven: staking APY and a HIVE/staking allocation paid people to lock BTC, not to use apps. When BUZZ rewards ended and B2 unlocked, farmers exited and native on-chain liquidity collapsed, since Bitcoin''s lack of genuine app demand left nothing to retain capital. Tellingly, the team has since pivoted narratives toward ''BTC PayFi for AI agents'' — a classic sign the original L2 thesis failed to find users.","non_economic":"B2''s social presence (@BSquaredNetwork on X) was built around the BUZZ farming loop and headline vanity metrics — its own site still advertises ''10.85M addresses and $732M TVL'', figures that read as marketing rather than active usage given collapsed volumes. The clearest non-economic tell is the narrative pivot itself: post-TGE the team re-badged from ''Bitcoin L2 for DeFi/NFT/SocialFi'' to ''Put Bitcoin in Every AI Agent''s Wallet'' / ''BTC PayFi settlement backbone for the AI economy''. A wholesale re-theming from BTC-DeFi to AI-agent payments within months of launch is the community-signal equivalent of a distress flare — it means the original app thesis found no users and the team is chasing the hotter narrative to stay relevant.","lessons_learned":["Advertising a large all-time TVL/address count on your own homepage after activity has collapsed is a reputational tell, not a strength — the market discounts self-reported vanity metrics.","A rapid narrative pivot (BTC-DeFi -> AI-agent PayFi) months after TGE signals the first thesis failed; chasing the next hot narrative rarely rebuilds real demand.","When five ZK BTC-L2s run identical BUZZ-style bridge-and-farm campaigns against the same idle-BTC pool, none of them build a moat; the subsidy just rotates capital between clones."],"could_differ":"B2 could have committed to ONE genuinely differentiated Bitcoin use case and shipped a fee-generating product before the token, rather than running BUZZ I/II emissions to manufacture a TVL headline and then re-theming to AI when it didn''t stick. Tying rewards to real transaction volume instead of bridged-and-locked BTC would have selected for users over farmers. Concretely, sustainable fee-backed yield plus a flagship app plausibly retains a slice of the 5,000+ BTC as sticky liquidity instead of a ~98% native drain — but given Babylon offered lower-friction native staking, even that likely caps B2 as a minor venue rather than a winner.","outlook":"On a terminal path as an L2, though the team is still swinging (the AI-PayFi pivot). With the Bitcoin-L2 sidechain category down ~74% and only fee-charging survivors (Babylon, tBTC) standing, a subsidized ghost-chain has no organic demand to rebuild on. A comeback would require the AI-agent-payments narrative to (a) become real with actual agent transaction volume, (b) settle specifically on B2 rather than Base/Solana, and (c) survive B2''s own heavy unlock schedule — a long-odds parlay. Probability of the chain regaining relevance: <10%; the AI pivot is more likely to be the next dead narrative than a revival.","cause_tags":["mercenary_tvl","unsustainable_yield","token_unlock_dump","narrative_death"],"sources":[{"title":"What Is BSquared Network (B2)? Bitcoin Layer-2 Solution - Gate","url":"https://www.gate.com/learn/articles/what-is-bsquared--network-b2/8892"},{"title":"Tokenomics | B² Network Docs","url":"https://docs.bsquared.network/b2_tokenomics"},{"title":"BSquared Network Price: B2/USD Live Price Chart, Market Cap & News | CoinGecko","url":"https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/bsquared-network"},{"title":"BSquared Network (@BSquaredNetwork) / X","url":"https://x.com/bsquarednetwork"}]}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('BounceBit','2024-05',75000000,530000,99.3,'2025-08-14','BounceBit is a BTC-restaking CeDeFi L1 whose on-chain TVL was propped up by dual-token staking incentives and BB emissions; heavy investor/team unlocks (50% of supply) created relentless sell pressure (BB fell ~66% over 90 days). As altcoin rotation and rising BTC dominance drained speculative capital in late 2025, the native-chain TVL collapsed while liquidity migrated to its off-chain RWA/CeFi products.','A nuanced split: the L1 chain is a near-dead ghost, but the *company* is credibly alive as an RWA/CeDeFi platform — BB Prime surpassed $1.5B cumulative volume with Franklin Templeton''s BENJI, backed by real ($16M annualized) revenue and buybacks. The on-chain L1 as a DeFi venue is not coming back (recovery <10%). The company''s survival as an RWA yield platform is genuinely plausible (~50%+), but that outcome does not resurrect BB as a chain-usage token — it makes BB a revenue/buyback claim on an off-chain business. Bet on the company, not the chain.','declining','[{"title":"Franklin Templeton Taps BounceBit to Launch BB Prime - CoinCentral","url":"https://coincentral.com/franklin-templeton-taps-bouncebit-to-launch-bb-prime-as-the-first-active-platform-for-tokenized-treasuries/"},{"title":"BounceBit Adds Franklin Templeton Tokenized Fund for Yield Strategies - CoinDesk","url":"https://www.coindesk.com/business/2025/08/05/bouncebit-adds-franklin-templeton-tokenized-fund-for-treasury-backed-yield-strategies"},{"title":"BounceBit''s Token Buybacks: A Strategic Play for Scarcity - AInvest","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/bouncebit-token-buybacks-strategic-play-scarcity-investor-confidence-cedefi-era-2509/"},{"title":"BounceBit Prime Puts Franklin Templeton''s $700M Fund to Work On-Chain - Blockonomi","url":"https://blockonomi.com/bouncebit-prime-puts-franklin-templetons-700m-fund-to-work-on-chain/"}]','2026-07-08 15:10:56','{"founded":"2024-05","founders":"Jack Lu (founder/CEO), formerly a 7-year partner at NGC Ventures and co-founder of Bounce auction house; background in quantitative economics and game theory.","raised":"$6M seed co-led by Blockchain Capital and Breyer Capital (Feb 2024), with CMS, Bankless Ventures, DeFiance, OKX Ventures, HTX; follow-on from OKX Ventures and Binance Labs (Mar-Apr 2024, undisclosed). Angels included EigenLayer''s Calvin Liu and Anchorage''s Nathan McCauley.","token_symbol":"BB","token_ath":0.865772,"token_ath_date":"2024-06","token_current":0.0186416,"purpose":"A BTC-restaking CeDeFi L1 with a dual-token (BBTC + BB) PoS model, letting Bitcoin holders earn institutional-grade CeFi yield plus on-chain restaking rewards from Shared Security Clients.","situation":"There was no single crash date — BounceBit died by slow bleed. BB peaked ~$0.87 at its June 2024 TGE, then heavy investor/team vesting (50% of supply) drove a grind lower: a single 90-day window saw BB fall ~66%, and scheduled unlocks like the Oct 12 tranche of 44.7M BB (~$5.5M, 6.3% of circulating supply) repeatedly preceded declines. The macro trigger was rotation: through H2 2025 Bitcoin dominance climbed to ~59% (highest since June 2025) and the Altcoin Season Index fell ~59% in 30 days, draining the speculative capital that BB''s on-chain yield depended on. As native TVL bled out, the team explicitly pivoted the value to off-chain products — launching BB Prime with Franklin Templeton''s tokenized MMF (Aug 5, 2025) and a $10M revenue-funded buyback — conceding the L1 itself wasn''t where the demand lived.","postmortem":"BounceBit raised from top-tier backers and hit ~$445M TVL within three weeks of early access by riding the 2024 BTC-restaking narrative with a differentiated CeDeFi yield product. But its native-chain TVL was propped up by dual-token staking incentives and BB emissions, while heavy investor/team unlocks (50% of supply) created relentless sell pressure — BB fell ~66% over one 90-day window and ~98% from its June 2024 ATH. As altcoin rotation and rising BTC dominance drained speculative capital through late 2025, on-chain TVL collapsed while whatever real demand existed migrated to its off-chain RWA/CeFi products rather than the L1. The chain''s honest problem: its value prop lived in centralized yield vaults, not on the blockchain it was selling.","non_economic":"BounceBit stands out for communicating MORE, not less, as it declined — the opposite of the go-quiet pattern. The team leaned into institutional-legitimacy signaling: the BlackRock BUIDL collateral pilot (>20% annualized), the Franklin Templeton BB Prime launch, and public multi-year buyback disclosures (''8.87M BB / ~$1M bought in August'', $16M annualized revenue). Media coverage stayed steady and positive on the RWA angle (CoinDesk, Blockonomi, CoinCentral all covered BB Prime) even as BB the token slid. The tell isn''t silence — it''s that all the good news was about off-chain CeDeFi/RWA products, while the L1 blockchain narrative quietly disappeared from the messaging. The community mood on the token stayed ''mixed'', bullish on RWA fundamentals but bearish on relentless unlock-driven supply.","lessons_learned":["If your value proposition lives in centralized yield vaults, you don''t need — and can''t retain — a native L1; the chain becomes a costly vanity layer the real business routes around.","Revenue-funded buybacks cannot outrun a 50%-insider unlock schedule; supply mechanics dominate token price regardless of genuine product traction.","A clean pivot to a real business (RWA/CeDeFi) can save the *company* even as the *chain* dies — founders should separate ''is the token/chain alive'' from ''is the team building something people pay for''."],"could_differ":"BounceBit could have skipped the native L1 entirely and launched as a CeDeFi/RWA yield platform from day one — which is what its real traction (BB Prime, >$1.5B cumulative volume) turned out to be — avoiding the emissions and 50%-insider unlock overhang that a chain token required. Failing that, a far gentler vesting schedule would have let the genuine RWA revenue and buybacks actually support the price instead of being swamped by supply. Because the RWA business is real and growing, this is one of the few graveyard cases where a different structure (product-first, no L1 token) plausibly produces a live, valuable company rather than a ghost chain.","outlook":"A nuanced split: the L1 chain is a near-dead ghost, but the *company* is credibly alive as an RWA/CeDeFi platform — BB Prime surpassed $1.5B cumulative volume with Franklin Templeton''s BENJI, backed by real ($16M annualized) revenue and buybacks. The on-chain L1 as a DeFi venue is not coming back (recovery <10%). The company''s survival as an RWA yield platform is genuinely plausible (~50%+), but that outcome does not resurrect BB as a chain-usage token — it makes BB a revenue/buyback claim on an off-chain business. Bet on the company, not the chain.","cause_tags":["mercenary_tvl","token_unlock_dump","unsustainable_yield","narrative_death"],"sources":[{"title":"Franklin Templeton Taps BounceBit to Launch BB Prime - CoinCentral","url":"https://coincentral.com/franklin-templeton-taps-bouncebit-to-launch-bb-prime-as-the-first-active-platform-for-tokenized-treasuries/"},{"title":"BounceBit Adds Franklin Templeton Tokenized Fund for Yield Strategies - CoinDesk","url":"https://www.coindesk.com/business/2025/08/05/bouncebit-adds-franklin-templeton-tokenized-fund-for-treasury-backed-yield-strategies"},{"title":"BounceBit''s Token Buybacks: A Strategic Play for Scarcity - AInvest","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/bouncebit-token-buybacks-strategic-play-scarcity-investor-confidence-cedefi-era-2509/"},{"title":"BounceBit Prime Puts Franklin Templeton''s $700M Fund to Work On-Chain - Blockonomi","url":"https://blockonomi.com/bouncebit-prime-puts-franklin-templetons-700m-fund-to-work-on-chain/"}]}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('Karak','2024-04',94500000,610000,99.4,'2024-05-28','Karak rode the restaking mania, positioning as a multi-asset EigenLayer alternative and pulling in deposits via an XP points program right as disappointment over EigenLayer''s EIGEN airdrop pushed yield-chasers to seek the ''next big thing.'' Its capital was pure mercenary restaking flow: once XP farming stalled and the restaking narrative deflated, TVL evaporated ~99% and the promised KAR token never delivered the payoff farmers expected.','Finished as a restaking hub — the restaking narrative that justified it collapsed, EigenLayer itself halved, and K2 is being formally shut down by end-2025. This is closer to a deliberate wind-down than a zombie. The only live thread is the OpenGDP rebrand toward tokenization/''programmable GDP'' (or GPU compute), which is effectively a new company reusing the team and treasury — not a revival of Karak/K2. Probability the restaking chain returns: ~0%. Probability OpenGDP becomes a relevant tokenization L1: low and unproven (~15%), and even success there does not resurrect the original thesis.','dead','[{"title":"Karak wants to introduce ''universal restaking'' for everyone - Blockworks","url":"https://blockworks.com/news/universal-restaking-layer-andalusia-labs"},{"title":"Restaking Wars in 2025: EigenLayer vs Symbiotic vs Karak - Yellow","url":"https://yellow.com/learn/restaking-wars-in-2025-eigenlayer-vs-symbiotic-vs-karak-%E2%80%93-what-you-need-to-know"},{"title":"OpenGDP (prev. Karak) - CryptoRank","url":"https://cryptorank.io/ico/karak-network"},{"title":"Karak Network TVL reaches $115 million, Andalusia Labs valuation exceeds $1 billion - Binance Square","url":"https://www.binance.com/en/square/post/2024-04-10-karak-network-tvl-1-15-andalusia-labs-10-6566994288482"}]','2026-07-08 15:12:16','{"founded":"2024-04","founders":"Andalusia Labs (formerly RiskHarbor), co-founded by Raouf Ben-Har and Drew Patel (both ex-Coinbase); HQ in San Francisco and Abu Dhabi.","raised":"$48M Series A led by Lightspeed Venture Partners at a >$1B valuation (Dec 2023), with Mubadala, Pantera, Framework, Bain Capital Ventures, DCG, Coinbase and Naval Ravikant; ~$51M total.","token_symbol":null,"token_ath":null,"token_ath_date":null,"token_current":null,"purpose":"A ''universal restaking layer'' (multi-asset EigenLayer alternative) via Validation-as-a-Service, letting any asset on any chain provide crypto-economic security to infrastructure.","situation":"Karak''s decline was a narrative-timing story, not a single-day crash. It opened Private Access on April 9, 2024 and TVL reached ~$115M — but that was already the tail of restaking mania and only ~2-3% market share against EigenLayer''s ~75%. The decisive external event was EigenLayer''s own deflation: its valuation cratered from ~$15B to ~$7B and its EIGEN airdrop disappointed, collapsing the entire restaking thesis that gave Karak a reason to exist. With XP farming stalled and no KAR token ever launched as a tradable payoff, capital left. The endgame was structural: the team rebranded Karak to OpenGDP (now trading under a GDP ticker, pivoting toward ''programmable GDP''/tokenization) and announced via Discord the closure of the K2 Network by end-2025, telling users to unstake and bridge out.","postmortem":"Karak had arguably the most impressive resume of the graveyard — a $48M Series A at a unicorn valuation, Lightspeed/Pantera/Coinbase/Naval backing, and an experienced RiskHarbor team. It rode restaking mania as the ''next EigenLayer,'' pulling deposits via an XP points program precisely as disappointment over EigenLayer''s EIGEN airdrop pushed yield-chasers to hunt the next thing. But the capital was pure mercenary restaking flow with no product pull: once XP farming stalled and the restaking narrative deflated, TVL evaporated ~99%, and the promised KAR token never delivered a real tradable payoff — the project rebranded to OpenGDP and announced closure of its K2 Network by end-2025. A billion-dollar valuation and no durable users is the definitional restaking-bubble casualty.","non_economic":"Karak drew early community scrutiny despite its glossy financing — it was publicly flagged as a ''$1B Middle-Eastern restaking project facing community scrutiny'', with skeptics questioning whether the unicorn valuation and Abu Dhabi/Mubadala backing were substance or optics. The absence of a launched KAR token became a running community grievance: airdrop-guide sites kept listing KAR as ''not yet launched, follow official channels'', a limbo that eroded farmer goodwill over 2024-2025. The most telling non-economic signal is the identity churn itself — a project that rebrands from ''universal restaking'' (Karak) to ''programmable GDP'' (OpenGDP) and, in some descriptions, to ''decentralized GPU compute'' is visibly casting about for a narrative after its original one died. The K2 wind-down was communicated in Discord rather than a public post-mortem.","lessons_learned":["A single-digit-market-share ''alternative'' to a category king (EigenLayer) has no independent reason to survive if the category itself deflates — you inherit all the sector risk with none of the moat.","An unlaunched token used as an indefinite XP-farming carrot burns community trust; farmers give you mercenary TVL now and resentment later when the payoff never materializes.","A $1B valuation from blue-chip VCs (Lightspeed, Coinbase, Naval) is not evidence of product-market fit — it can simply be capital chasing a narrative, and it evaporates with the narrative."],"could_differ":"Karak could have picked a differentiated wedge instead of being ''multi-asset EigenLayer'', which added slashing/security risk without a compelling reason to switch. Shipping a real token with genuine utility (rather than an open-ended XP program) before the restaking narrative peaked would have converted some mercenary TVL into aligned holders. Most importantly, tying the product to a durable non-restaking use case earlier — the tokenization/''programmable GDP'' idea it eventually pivoted to — might have given it a reason to exist independent of the restaking cycle. Whether any of that beats EigenLayer''s ~75% share is doubtful, so ''differently'' here mostly means ''a smaller but alive niche'' rather than a win.","outlook":"Finished as a restaking hub — the restaking narrative that justified it collapsed, EigenLayer itself halved, and K2 is being formally shut down by end-2025. This is closer to a deliberate wind-down than a zombie. The only live thread is the OpenGDP rebrand toward tokenization/''programmable GDP'' (or GPU compute), which is effectively a new company reusing the team and treasury — not a revival of Karak/K2. Probability the restaking chain returns: ~0%. Probability OpenGDP becomes a relevant tokenization L1: low and unproven (~15%), and even success there does not resurrect the original thesis.","cause_tags":["mercenary_tvl","points_collapse","narrative_death","team_abandonment"],"sources":[{"title":"Karak wants to introduce ''universal restaking'' for everyone - Blockworks","url":"https://blockworks.com/news/universal-restaking-layer-andalusia-labs"},{"title":"Restaking Wars in 2025: EigenLayer vs Symbiotic vs Karak - Yellow","url":"https://yellow.com/learn/restaking-wars-in-2025-eigenlayer-vs-symbiotic-vs-karak-%E2%80%93-what-you-need-to-know"},{"title":"OpenGDP (prev. Karak) - CryptoRank","url":"https://cryptorank.io/ico/karak-network"},{"title":"Karak Network TVL reaches $115 million, Andalusia Labs valuation exceeds $1 billion - Binance Square","url":"https://www.binance.com/en/square/post/2024-04-10-karak-network-tvl-1-15-andalusia-labs-10-6566994288482"}]}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('zkFair','2023-12',41100000,80000,99.8,'2024-01-15','zkFair''s ''fair launch'' distributed 7.5B ZKF tokens based on USDC gas spent, literally paying users to burn stablecoins on gas to farm the airdrop (108M USDC consumed). This drew pure mercenary farmers who left the moment the claim window closed on Jan 11, 2024; by May the team was propping up staking pools with daily 1,000 USDC subsidies, confirming organic activity had already died.','Truly dead — not a zombie, a corpse. ZKF is down ~99.98% from ATH and TVL fell ~99.8%; the growth mechanism was a single non-repeatable gas-farming gimmick with no product, ecosystem, or team to build on. There are no conditions under which this specific chain revives: an anonymous, fully-distributed, product-less L2 has no entity to fund a relaunch, no narrative left, and no reason for anyone to transact. Probability of meaningful recovery: ~0%. It is the graveyard''s cleanest example of fully synthetic TVL.','dead','[{"title":"ZKFair Airdrop: A Landmark Event in Decentralized Finance - CoinLive","url":"https://www.coinlive.com/news/zkfair-airdrop-a-landmark-event-in-decentralized-finance"},{"title":"ZKF Token | ZKFair Docs","url":"https://docs.zkfair.io/economic-model/zkf-token"},{"title":"ZKFair has ended the airdrop collection - 130 million unclaimed ZKF destroyed - Coinlive","url":"https://www.coinlive.com/news-flash/417827"},{"title":"ZKFair price today, ZKF to USD live price, marketcap and chart - CoinMarketCap","url":"https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/zkfair/"}]','2026-07-08 15:12:54','{"founded":"2023-12","founders":"Deliberately anonymous ''community-owned'' project; originated from and powered by Lumoz (formerly Opside), a ZK-RaaS provider, with the ZKFair team framed as a hands-off deployer of Polygon CDK.","raised":"None disclosed / ''no investors'' by design — marketed as a 100% fair launch with no VC, reserves or pre-mine.","token_symbol":"ZKF","token_ath":0.02491955,"token_ath_date":"2024-01","token_current":0.0000049,"purpose":"A self-described first community ZK-L2 on Polygon CDK + Celestia DA, the first L2 to use USDC as the gas token, distributing 100% of ZKF via a ''fair launch'' airdrop.","situation":"The trigger was mechanical and self-inflicted: the Gas Fee Airdrop opened Dec 24, 2023, paying 7.5B of 10B ZKF to whoever burned USDC on gas — 200,000+ contributors consumed >100M USDC racing a 3M-USDC-fee cap. Mainnet TVL spiked to ~$123M (13th among L2s) then to a ~$324M peak by late January 2024 (9th place). The cliff was the airdrop claim deadline: claiming ended 11:00 UTC+8 Jan 11, 2024, with 130M unclaimed ZKF (~$2.2M) burned. The instant the farm-and-claim window shut, the mercenary gas-farmers had no reason to transact, so activity died on schedule. By mid-January the team was already propping up ZKF staking (75% of revenue to stakers) and later daily 1,000-USDC subsidies to fake organic yield. No rival pulled capital away — there was never real capital, only a one-time gas-burn incentive.","postmortem":"zkFair''s ''fair launch'' was clever framing for a pure extraction machine: 7.5B of 10B ZKF was distributed based on USDC gas spent, literally paying users to burn stablecoins on gas to farm the airdrop — 108M USDC consumed in the process. This is airdrop farming in its most naked form, and it drew exclusively mercenary farmers who left the instant the claim window closed on Jan 11, 2024. By May the team was propping up staking pools with daily 1,000 USDC subsidies, confirming organic activity had already died. With no real product, no investors funding runway, and an anonymous team, TVL fell 99.8% and ZKF is now down ~99.98% from ATH — a fair-launch label on a self-consuming ponzi-esque incentive loop.","non_economic":"zkFair''s ''fair launch, no VC, 100% to community'' framing generated a burst of favorable coverage (Bybit Learn, SimpleSwap, Tech Startups all ran explainers positioning it as a ''landmark'' anti-VC token model) and a short-lived surge of farmer enthusiasm — 1.2B ZKF (12% of circulation) was staked within 12 hours of staking going live. But because the team was anonymous and the chain was really a Lumoz RaaS deployment, there was no founder identity, roadmap communication, or developer ecosystem to sustain the community once the gas-farm ended; the social channels went as quiet as the chain. The ''fairness'' narrative that drove the media cycle was itself the tell — it described the *distribution mechanic*, not any product, so there was nothing to talk about after distribution finished.","lessons_learned":["''Fair launch / no VC'' describes only how tokens are distributed, not whether anything of value exists — a distribution gimmick is not a product, and a chain whose only activity is farming its own airdrop has zero terminal value.","Paying users to burn gas to earn tokens is a closed extraction loop: participants spend USDC to receive ZKF, so the only ''usage'' is the subsidy itself, which stops the moment claims close.","Post-launch subsidies (daily USDC into staking pools) to simulate yield are a confession that organic activity has already died, not a bridge to it."],"could_differ":"Realistically, very little — zkFair''s entire design was a one-time gas-farming event with no product roadmap, no team identity, and no funding runway, so there was no second act to execute. The only structurally different path would have been to not tie the airdrop to gas-burn at all, instead using the (nonexistent) treasury and Lumoz''s RaaS to fund actual applications and give farmers a reason to transact after the claim — but with no investors, no team accountability, and a fully-distributed supply, there was no capital or incentive alignment to build that. This is the rare graveyard case where ''could have done differently'' is essentially ''should have been a different project''.","outlook":"Truly dead — not a zombie, a corpse. ZKF is down ~99.98% from ATH and TVL fell ~99.8%; the growth mechanism was a single non-repeatable gas-farming gimmick with no product, ecosystem, or team to build on. There are no conditions under which this specific chain revives: an anonymous, fully-distributed, product-less L2 has no entity to fund a relaunch, no narrative left, and no reason for anyone to transact. Probability of meaningful recovery: ~0%. It is the graveyard''s cleanest example of fully synthetic TVL.","cause_tags":["airdrop_farming","wash_trading","no_real_users","points_collapse"],"sources":[{"title":"ZKFair Airdrop: A Landmark Event in Decentralized Finance - CoinLive","url":"https://www.coinlive.com/news/zkfair-airdrop-a-landmark-event-in-decentralized-finance"},{"title":"ZKF Token | ZKFair Docs","url":"https://docs.zkfair.io/economic-model/zkf-token"},{"title":"ZKFair has ended the airdrop collection - 130 million unclaimed ZKF destroyed - Coinlive","url":"https://www.coinlive.com/news-flash/417827"},{"title":"ZKFair price today, ZKF to USD live price, marketcap and chart - CoinMarketCap","url":"https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/zkfair/"}]}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('Taiko','2024-05',340600000,3350000,99,'2024-12-26','Taiko''s TVL was inflated by two seasons of TAIKO-token mainnet incentive programs (18M tokens distributed) that pushed it past $400M; when emissions tapered the mercenary liquidity left, and a $1.7M bridge exploit in 2025 further dented confidence. As a ''based rollup'' it prioritized decentralization over the aggressive incentives and app ecosystem needed to retain users, so it lost the L2 traffic war to Base and Arbitrum.','The most credible potential survivor in the cohort, but still a marginal chain — a respected zombie rather than a corpse. The based-rollup design is technically admired, the team keeps shipping, and it restored exploited funds 1:1, so it has the ingredients for a second life that most graveyard peers lack. But respect is not usage: at ~$4M DeFi TVL it needs a genuine demand catalyst. A modest recovery is plausible ONLY if (a) based rollups become a mainstream Ethereum narrative (e.g., preconfirmations/L1 sequencing adoption), (b) a killer app deploys on Taiko specifically, and (c) it avoids further security incidents. Probability of returning to relevant-L2 status: ~20% — low, but the highest in this graveyard.','speculative','[{"title":"Ethereum L2 Bridge Exploit Drains $1.7M: Leaked SGX Key Defeats Taiko Trust Model - TechTimes","url":"https://www.techtimes.com/articles/318886/20260623/ethereum-l2-bridge-exploit-drains-17m-leaked-sgx-key-defeats-taiko-trust-model.htm"},{"title":"TAIKO hits all-time low as Taiko bridge exploit drains $1.7M - Invezz","url":"https://invezz.com/news/2026/06/22/taiko-hits-all-time-low-as-taiko-bridge-exploit-drains-1-7m/"},{"title":"Ethereum Layer 2 Taiko Halts Network After $1.7M Exploit, Token Falls 11% - CoinCodex","url":"https://coincodex.com/article/86299/ethereum-layer-2-taiko-halts-network-after-17m-exploit-token-falls-11/"},{"title":"Taiko Price Prediction: Bridge Recovery Fuels TAIKO Rally - Coingabbar","url":"https://www.coingabbar.com/en/price-prediction/taiko-price-prediction-bridge-hack-recovery-ai-adoption"}]','2026-07-08 15:14:11','{"founded":"2024-05","founders":"Daniel Wang (CEO) and Brecht Devos, both ex-Loopring (the first ZK-rollup on Ethereum); Wang also spent four years at Google.","raised":"$37M across three rounds: $10M seed led by Sequoia China (Q3 2022), $12M pre-Series A led by Generative Ventures, and $15M Series A led by Lightspeed Faction and Hashed (Mar 2024); angels included Tim Beiko and Anthony Sassano.","token_symbol":"TAIKO","token_ath":3.80,"token_ath_date":"2024-06","token_current":0.080606,"purpose":"A Type-1 zkEVM ''based rollup'' aiming to be the most Ethereum-equivalent L2, delegating sequencing to Ethereum L1 for maximum decentralization and credible neutrality.","situation":"Two distinct triggers. First, economic: TAIKO peaked ~$3.80 at its June 2024 mainnet/TGE, then bled as two seasons of mainnet incentive programs (18M tokens) tapered — the mercenary liquidity that pushed TVL past $400M left, dropping it ~99% toward a residual ~$3.8M DeFi / ~$12.85M bridged TVL. Second, and more damaging to trust, a June 21-22, 2026 bridge exploit drained ~$1.7M: BlockSec Phalcon traced it to a Raiko SGX enclave signing key left publicly on GitHub, letting the attacker register attacker-controlled SGX instances via SgxVerifier and forge withdrawal proofs. TAIKO hit an all-time low; the team halted the bridge/ERC-20 Vault and told users all bridges were unsafe. Rivals were the quiet killer throughout: Base and Arbitrum won the L2 traffic war while Taiko prioritized decentralization over incentives.","postmortem":"Taiko is one of the more honest failures here: it had genuine technical credibility (a Type-1 zkEVM, ex-Loopring founders, $37M from Sequoia and Lightspeed) and a principled ''based rollup'' design that pushed decentralization over hype. But its TVL was still inflated by two seasons of TAIKO mainnet incentive programs (18M tokens distributed) that pushed it past $400M, and when emissions tapered the mercenary liquidity left. A June 2026 bridge exploit (~$1.7M, leaked SGX key) further dented confidence. Crucially, by prioritizing decentralization over the aggressive incentives and app ecosystem needed to retain users, it lost the L2 traffic war to Base and Arbitrum — principled engineering with no demand hook, TVL down ~99% and TAIKO ~98% off its ATH.","non_economic":"Taiko''s social signal is unusual for the graveyard: its developer credibility stayed intact even as usage cratered. The team kept shipping publicly (Gwyneth booster rollups, ZK-proving transitions) and, crucially, communicated well during the June 2026 crisis — issuing an immediate X warning that ''all bridges should no longer be considered secure'', halting affected contracts, and having a security council execute on-chain fixes and rebuild the bridge so ''every asset stayed backed one to one''. That transparency drove a sharp sentiment swing (a 136% post-reopening TAIKO surge, then -13%). The tell here is not silence or exodus — it''s the widening gap between respected engineering/comms and near-zero organic demand: the community respects Taiko but does not use it.","lessons_learned":["Principled decentralization (a based rollup with no central sequencer) is a credibility asset but not a demand hook — users follow incentives and apps, not architecture purity, so ceding the incentive war cedes the users.","Hardware-based proving (SGX/TEE) adds an operational-security failure mode categorically different from software bugs: a single leaked enclave key on GitHub defeated a multi-prover ''defense-in-depth'' model.","Making bridge/exploit victims whole 1:1 and communicating transparently preserves reputation and can drive a relief rally — handling the crisis well is separable from having product-market fit."],"could_differ":"Taiko realistically could have run more aggressive, longer, app-targeted incentives (the way Base/Arbitrum effectively did via ecosystem funding and distribution) instead of two tapering seasons that trained liquidity to leave — buying time to seed a sticky app or two before emissions ended. Operationally, treating the SGX signing key as a crown-jewel secret (never in a repo, rotated, HSM-backed) would have prevented the 2026 bridge exploit and the trust hit. Neither guarantees victory against Base''s distribution, but a retained flagship app plus no exploit plausibly keeps Taiko a credible mid-tier L2 (hundreds of millions TVL) rather than a ~$4M ghost.","outlook":"The most credible potential survivor in the cohort, but still a marginal chain — a respected zombie rather than a corpse. The based-rollup design is technically admired, the team keeps shipping, and it restored exploited funds 1:1, so it has the ingredients for a second life that most graveyard peers lack. But respect is not usage: at ~$4M DeFi TVL it needs a genuine demand catalyst. A modest recovery is plausible ONLY if (a) based rollups become a mainstream Ethereum narrative (e.g., preconfirmations/L1 sequencing adoption), (b) a killer app deploys on Taiko specifically, and (c) it avoids further security incidents. Probability of returning to relevant-L2 status: ~20% — low, but the highest in this graveyard.","cause_tags":["mercenary_tvl","competition","exploit_hack","no_real_users"],"sources":[{"title":"Ethereum L2 Bridge Exploit Drains $1.7M: Leaked SGX Key Defeats Taiko Trust Model - TechTimes","url":"https://www.techtimes.com/articles/318886/20260623/ethereum-l2-bridge-exploit-drains-17m-leaked-sgx-key-defeats-taiko-trust-model.htm"},{"title":"TAIKO hits all-time low as Taiko bridge exploit drains $1.7M - Invezz","url":"https://invezz.com/news/2026/06/22/taiko-hits-all-time-low-as-taiko-bridge-exploit-drains-1-7m/"},{"title":"Ethereum Layer 2 Taiko Halts Network After $1.7M Exploit, Token Falls 11% - CoinCodex","url":"https://coincodex.com/article/86299/ethereum-layer-2-taiko-halts-network-after-17m-exploit-token-falls-11/"},{"title":"Taiko Price Prediction: Bridge Recovery Fuels TAIKO Rally - Coingabbar","url":"https://www.coingabbar.com/en/price-prediction/taiko-price-prediction-bridge-hack-recovery-ai-adoption"}]}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('Zircuit','2024-09',25800000,110000,99.6,'2025-01-04','Zircuit amassed a headline $3.7B in pre-mainnet staking deposits (on Ethereum L1) chasing ZRC points and its EigenLayer ''fairdrop'', but almost none of that mercenary capital migrated to the actual Zircuit chain, whose on-chain TVL peaked at only ~$26M and then collapsed 99.6%. Once ZRC entered circulation in Nov 2024 and points farming ended, both the staked capital and the thin native liquidity drained away.','Effectively finished as a live chain — a ghost, not a zombie with momentum. The ~70x gap between farmed pre-mainnet deposits and near-zero real on-chain usage proved it never had a genuine ecosystem, and ZRC is ~99% off ATH amid ongoing dilution (21% of supply earmarked for airdrops/community). Recovery would require building a real app economy essentially from scratch on a chain no one currently uses, with restaking (its only-ever narrative) now cold. Conditions for a comeback: a native killer app + a fresh security-differentiated narrative + halted dilution — unlikely to co-occur. Probability of meaningful revival: <5%.','dead','[{"title":"Celebrating the Success of Zircuit''s ZRC EigenLayer Fairdrop - Brave New Coin","url":"https://bravenewcoin.com/insights/celebrating-the-success-of-zircuits-zrc-eigenlayer-fairdrop"},{"title":"The Zircuit Fairdrop: A Reward for EigenLayer Holders and Stakers - Zircuit Blog","url":"https://www.zircuit.com/blog/the-zircuit-fairdrop-a-reward-for-eigenlayer-holders-and-stakers"},{"title":"Zircuit (ZRC) Overview: Real-time Price, Live Chart, Market Cap & Airdrops - CoinLaunch","url":"https://coinlaunch.space/projects/zircuit/"},{"title":"Zircuit ($ZRC) token airdrop guide: Season 2 strategy - Boxmining","url":"https://www.boxmining.com/zircuit-zrc-token-airdrop-guide/"}]','2026-07-08 15:14:54','{"founded":"2024-09","founders":"Four co-founders — Martin Derka, Krishna Sriram, Jan Gorzny and Angel X — web3 security veterans and PhDs, several formerly of the auditing firm Quantstamp.","raised":"Undisclosed amounts from Binance Labs, Pantera Capital, Dragonfly, Amber Group, Maelstrom and others, plus multiple Ethereum Foundation grants.","token_symbol":"ZRC","token_ath":0.09726,"token_ath_date":"2024-11","token_current":0.00096133,"purpose":"A hybrid ZK + optimistic EVM L2 emphasizing security (AI-driven sequencer-level exploit prevention), built by ex-Quantstamp auditors.","situation":"The trigger was the ZRC EIGEN ''Fairdrop'' concluding Nov 8, 2024: an industry-first equal-share drop of 2% of ZRC to 190,000+ EIGEN holders (snapshot Oct 8, 2024, block #20919999; 3-EIGEN minimum), with 51,000+ claiming in week one. The fairdrop was the culmination of a pre-mainnet staking-points program that amassed a headline ~$1.8B (peaking higher earlier in 2024) in restaked ETH/BTC/LSTs/LRTs on Ethereum L1 — but almost none migrated to the actual Zircuit chain, whose native on-chain TVL peaked at only ~$26M. Once ZRC entered circulation and points ended, both the L1 staked capital and the thin native liquidity drained. The rival dynamic was fatal: the EigenLayer restaking narrative Zircuit was piggybacking on deflated (EigenLayer fell ~$15B->~$7B), so the capital it farmed had nowhere it wanted to stay.","postmortem":"Zircuit''s story is the widest gap between farmed capital and real chain usage in the graveyard. Its security-veteran founders and Binance/Pantera/Dragonfly backing let it amass a headline ~$1.8B+ in pre-mainnet staking deposits on Ethereum L1, chasing ZRC points and an EigenLayer ''fairdrop'' with 190k+ participants. But almost none of that mercenary capital ever migrated to the actual Zircuit chain, whose native on-chain TVL peaked at only ~$26M — a ~70x+ gap that exposed the deposits as pure points-farming, not usage. Once ZRC entered circulation in Nov 2024 and points farming ended, both the L1 staked capital and the thin native liquidity drained away, collapsing on-chain TVL ~99.6% and ZRC ~99% from ATH. Excellent security tech, zero organic demand — the pre-deposit points model harvested TVL headlines that never became a real network.","non_economic":"Zircuit''s social strategy was borrowed credibility: the ''Fairdrop'' generated a coordinated PR blitz (near-identical press releases across CryptoSlate, Cryptobriefing, Bitget, Cryptopolitan, Chainwire) and an on-record endorsement from EigenLayer founder Sreeram Kannan (''thrilled to see Zircuit introducing the first Fairdrop for EIGEN holders''). That ''no whales, no favoritism'' framing drove a burst of goodwill and 190k+ participants. But the engagement was tethered to EigenLayer''s community, not Zircuit''s own — when the restaking narrative cooled, so did the borrowed audience. The founders'' ex-Quantstamp security pedigree earned respect for the ''AI-driven sequencer-level exploit prevention'' pitch, but security-as-a-headline never generated the app activity that produces real users; the ~70x gap between staked-on-L1 and used-on-chain is the quantitative proof the community never actually arrived.","lessons_learned":["Pre-mainnet staking-points deposits on L1 are the purest form of vanity TVL — a ~70x gap between farmed L1 capital (~$1.8B) and native chain usage (~$26M) means the ''TVL'' was never on your chain and was never going to be.","Borrowing another ecosystem''s community (an EigenLayer ''fairdrop'') borrows its narrative risk too: when EigenLayer deflated, Zircuit''s farmed audience evaporated with it.","A security-first value proposition (AI sequencer exploit prevention) is a feature, not a demand driver; users need apps and yield, and safety alone attracts neither."],"could_differ":"Zircuit could have run its points program to reward *native on-chain* activity (transactions, app usage, liquidity actually on Zircuit) rather than pre-mainnet L1 staking, forcing the farmed capital onto the chain where at least some might stick — closing the ~70x L1-vs-native gap that doomed it. Not anchoring its entire go-to-market to EigenLayer would have reduced dependence on a single narrative that then collapsed. And it could have shipped a flagship app leveraging its AI-security differentiator (e.g., a safety-branded DeFi venue) before the token. Realistically these move it from ~$26M to maybe low-hundreds-of-millions native TVL — better, but still an also-ran versus Base/Arbitrum.","outlook":"Effectively finished as a live chain — a ghost, not a zombie with momentum. The ~70x gap between farmed pre-mainnet deposits and near-zero real on-chain usage proved it never had a genuine ecosystem, and ZRC is ~99% off ATH amid ongoing dilution (21% of supply earmarked for airdrops/community). Recovery would require building a real app economy essentially from scratch on a chain no one currently uses, with restaking (its only-ever narrative) now cold. Conditions for a comeback: a native killer app + a fresh security-differentiated narrative + halted dilution — unlikely to co-occur. Probability of meaningful revival: <5%.","cause_tags":["mercenary_tvl","points_collapse","airdrop_farming","no_real_users"],"sources":[{"title":"Celebrating the Success of Zircuit''s ZRC EigenLayer Fairdrop - Brave New Coin","url":"https://bravenewcoin.com/insights/celebrating-the-success-of-zircuits-zrc-eigenlayer-fairdrop"},{"title":"The Zircuit Fairdrop: A Reward for EigenLayer Holders and Stakers - Zircuit Blog","url":"https://www.zircuit.com/blog/the-zircuit-fairdrop-a-reward-for-eigenlayer-holders-and-stakers"},{"title":"Zircuit (ZRC) Overview: Real-time Price, Live Chart, Market Cap & Airdrops - CoinLaunch","url":"https://coinlaunch.space/projects/zircuit/"},{"title":"Zircuit ($ZRC) token airdrop guide: Season 2 strategy - Boxmining","url":"https://www.boxmining.com/zircuit-zrc-token-airdrop-guide/"}]}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('Fuel','2024-10',64600000,4240000,93.4,'2024-12-17','Fuel Ignition launched with a ~$400M TVL spike around its Dec 2024 TGE, then cratered 79% in a single quarter (Q1 2025) as post-airdrop hype normalized. Despite strong engineering (parallel execution, EigenDA migration to 5K TPS) it never attracted real developers or users; DeFi activity concentrated in just 3 protocols (98%+ of TVL), and the token fell 99% from ATH against a $1B VC valuation.','Structurally finished as a general-purpose L2 — a technically impressive ghost. At ~$5-8M TVL with three apps constituting the whole economy and FUEL ~99% off ATH, the network is effectively abandoned by users despite real throughput advantages. A revival requires a breakout application that genuinely needs FuelVM''s parallel-execution/UTXO model (e.g., a high-frequency on-chain orderbook or game) AND a fresh developer on-ramp that removes the Sway learning tax — both unlikely given incumbent gravity. Probability of returning to relevant-L2 status: <5%. The tech may live on as IP or influence other designs even if the chain does not.','declining','[{"title":"State of Fuel Q1 2025 - Messari","url":"https://messari.io/report/state-of-fuel-q1-2025"},{"title":"State of Fuel Q2 2025 - Messari","url":"https://messari.io/report/state-of-fuel-q2-2025"},{"title":"State of Fuel Q4 2024 - Messari","url":"https://messari.io/report/state-of-fuel-q4-2024"},{"title":"Fuel Network price today, FUEL to USD live price, marketcap and chart - CoinMarketCap","url":"https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/fuel-network/"}]','2026-07-08 15:16:05','{"founded":"2024-10","founders":"Nick Dodson (CEO, early Ethereum-tooling builder) and John Adler (co-author of the original Optimistic Rollup whitepaper, also co-founder of Celestia); Fuel Labs, Toronto.","raised":"$80M strategic round at a $1B valuation led by Blockchain Capital and Stratos (Sep 2022), with Alameda Research, CoinFund, Bain Capital Crypto, Spartan and others; ~$81.5M private + ~$9.4M public, ~$90.9M total.","token_symbol":"FUEL","token_ath":0.083754,"token_ath_date":"2024-12","token_current":0.00070702,"purpose":"The ''fastest modular execution layer'' — a parallelized FuelVM (UTXO-based) execution layer for Ethereum with app-specific sequencing and near-zero fees.","situation":"The trigger was the FUEL TGE on Dec 19, 2024 (Impossible Finance IDO closed Dec 18 at $0.02, $1.4M raised at a $200M pre-valuation, 100% unlocked at TGE). Fuel Ignition (live since Oct 15, 2024) had a peak TVL of ~$416M and top-10-L2 status on launch hype, and FUEL''s market cap rose ~38% to ~$247M immediately post-TGE. Then Q1 2025 — the first full post-TGE quarter — saw TVL collapse 79.1% QoQ (from ~$310.9M to ~$64.9M) as hype normalized, with FUEL''s market cap down 79.8% to ~$49.9M and price down 83.5% to ~$0.01; daily DEX volume fell 45.5%. The bleed continued (Q2 2025 TVL ~$8.2M). No single rival killed it — the market had already consolidated around Base/Arbitrum/Solana before Fuel''s differentiated VM ever shipped, so there was nowhere for demand to come from.","postmortem":"Fuel had elite engineering DNA — John Adler literally co-wrote the optimistic-rollup paper — and a $1B-valuation $80M raise from Blockchain Capital, with legitimately novel parallel-execution tech and an EigenDA migration targeting 5K TPS. But great tech never became great demand: Fuel Ignition launched with a ~$416M TVL peak around its Dec 2024 TGE, then cratered ~79% in a single quarter (Q1 2025) as post-airdrop hype normalized. It never attracted real developers or users — DeFi activity concentrated in just 3 protocols (Mira, SwayLend, The Rig) holding 98%+ of TVL — and FUEL fell ~99% from ATH against that $1B VC valuation. A cautionary tale that a differentiated VM is worthless without an ecosystem or a reason for users to show up.","non_economic":"Fuel''s decline is unusually well-documented because Messari published quarterly ''State of Fuel'' reports (Q4 2024 through Q2 2025) that quantified the fade in real time — a rare public paper trail showing TVL, market cap and DEX volume all falling in lockstep quarter after quarter. The most damning non-economic signal is ecosystem concentration: by Q2 2025 just three protocols (Mira Protocol, SwayLend, The Rig) held 98%+ of all DeFi TVL, meaning the ''50+ projects live in the first month'' headline masked an almost total absence of real builders or users — a chain is not an ecosystem when three apps are the entire economy. FuelVM''s UTXO/Sway model also imposed a developer-learning-curve tax that likely deterred the EVM builders who were fluent on the incumbent chains.","lessons_learned":["A differentiated VM (parallel FuelVM, UTXO, the Sway language) is a switching cost for developers, not just an advantage — asking builders to learn a new paradigm with no demand pull guarantees a near-empty ecosystem.","Timing beats tech: arriving with superior throughput AFTER the market consolidated around Base/Arbitrum/Solana means the performance edge has no one to serve.","A ''50+ projects at launch'' headline is hollow if 3 protocols end up holding 98% of TVL — breadth of deployments is not the same as depth of usage."],"could_differ":"Fuel could have shipped its execution layer as EVM-compatible (or offered a first-class EVM path) so the vast pool of existing Solidity developers could deploy without learning Sway, dramatically lowering the barrier that left it with three real apps. Launching years earlier — before the 2022 raise''s tech finally reached mainnet in late 2024 — would have let it compete for the modular narrative while it was still open rather than after consolidation. And it could have concentrated incentives on seeding 2-3 genuinely sticky flagship apps rather than a wide-but-shallow 50-project launch. Even so, absent a killer app that *specifically needs* FuelVM parallelism, the honest ceiling is a niche high-performance chain, not a Base competitor.","outlook":"Structurally finished as a general-purpose L2 — a technically impressive ghost. At ~$5-8M TVL with three apps constituting the whole economy and FUEL ~99% off ATH, the network is effectively abandoned by users despite real throughput advantages. A revival requires a breakout application that genuinely needs FuelVM''s parallel-execution/UTXO model (e.g., a high-frequency on-chain orderbook or game) AND a fresh developer on-ramp that removes the Sway learning tax — both unlikely given incumbent gravity. Probability of returning to relevant-L2 status: <5%. The tech may live on as IP or influence other designs even if the chain does not.","cause_tags":["mercenary_tvl","airdrop_farming","no_real_users","vc_dump"],"sources":[{"title":"State of Fuel Q1 2025 - Messari","url":"https://messari.io/report/state-of-fuel-q1-2025"},{"title":"State of Fuel Q2 2025 - Messari","url":"https://messari.io/report/state-of-fuel-q2-2025"},{"title":"State of Fuel Q4 2024 - Messari","url":"https://messari.io/report/state-of-fuel-q4-2024"},{"title":"Fuel Network price today, FUEL to USD live price, marketcap and chart - CoinMarketCap","url":"https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/fuel-network/"}]}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('Corn','2024-11',29400000,30000,100,'2025-08-14','Corn was an Arbitrum-Orbit Bitcoin-DeFi L2 using tokenized BTC (BTCN) as gas, backed by Binance Labs and Polychain, that farmed TVL past $150M with popCORN incentives and an airdrop before its March 2025 listing. The CORN token peaked in Oct 2025 and fell ~70%, and with no organic demand once incentives dried up, the team made the final call: the network is formally winding down with a June 2026 claim/asset-migration deadline.','Unambiguously dead — this is a deliberate, scheduled shutdown, not a decline or a zombie. The network ceases operations June 30, 2026, the app has moved to a legacy domain, and users are being told to bridge assets off before deprecation. There is no recovery scenario for a chain its own team is sunsetting; probability of the chain returning is ~0%. The only forward-looking question is whether the team''s ''next chapter'' (implied to be payments-related) succeeds as a NEW product — which would be a different entity, not a revival of Corn.','dead','[{"title":"Corn - L2BEAT","url":"https://l2beat.com/scaling/projects/corn"},{"title":"Corn Docs - From Bitcoin L2 to Stablecoin Mecca","url":"https://docs.usecorn.com/"},{"title":"CORN (@use_corn) / Posts / X","url":"https://x.com/use_corn"},{"title":"What Is Corn (CORN) And How Does It Work? - CoinMarketCap","url":"https://coinmarketcap.com/cmc-ai/use-corn/what-is/"}]','2026-07-08 15:16:46','{"founded":"2024-11","founders":"Corn (usecorn) team; only the founder is public and has no notable top-tier track record — a flagged concern. Backed heavily by its investors.","raised":"$6.7M led by Polychain Capital, with Binance Labs, Framework Ventures and Polygon co-founder Sandeep Nailwal (2024).","token_symbol":"CORN","token_ath":0.1871,"token_ath_date":"2025-10","token_current":0.044,"purpose":"An Arbitrum-Orbit Bitcoin-DeFi L2 using tokenized Bitcoin (BTCN, 1:1 BTC-backed via custodians/bridges) as the gas token, with Curve-style veTokenomics (stake CORN -> popCORN -> bribe market), later pivoting toward zero-fee global stablecoin payments.","situation":"Corn farmed TVL past $150M with popCORN incentives and an airdrop before its March 2025 listing, but demand never followed. The token peaked ~$0.19 in Oct 2025 then fell ~70% as incentives dried up. The team first pivoted from ''Bitcoin L2'' to ''Stablecoin Mecca'' — integrating USDT0 (omnichain USDT) as the primary asset for instant, gas-free payments — then conceded entirely. In 2026 it announced a wind-down: the network ceases operations June 30, 2026 (''for Corn to enter its next chapter, the previous one has to close''). Hard deadlines followed: the Corn app moved to legacy.usecorn.com; users must move USDT0 off via Plasma by June 25; the final popCORN/airdrop-locker claim window closes June 26, 2026. This mirrors peer shutdowns (Swellchain) citing the unsustainability of running an independent L2.","postmortem":"Corn had real backers (Polychain, Binance Labs, Framework, Nailwal) and a differentiated ''BTC-as-gas'' design on Arbitrum Orbit, and farmed TVL past $150M with popCORN incentives and an airdrop before its March 2025 listing. But like every incentive-bootstrapped BTC-L2, there was no organic demand underneath: once emissions dried up the mercenary capital left, CORN peaked in Oct 2025 near $0.19 and fell ~70%, and TVL collapsed effectively to zero. The team then pivoted to stablecoin payments before conceding defeat entirely — the network is formally winding down with a June 30, 2026 shutdown and a June 26 final claim/asset-migration deadline. An orderly, non-fraudulent death, but a death: a thin-track-record team and VC money couldn''t manufacture users for a redundant BTC-DeFi chain.","non_economic":"Corn''s death is the most transparently communicated in the graveyard — the opposite of going quiet. The team (@use_corn) published an explicit wind-down notice with a clear rationale (''the long-term sustainability of maintaining an independent L2'') and a user-protective deadline schedule (migrate USDT0 by June 25, claim popCORN/airdrops by June 26, network off June 30, app moved to a legacy domain). That orderly, non-fraudulent exit — telling users exactly how to retrieve funds — distinguishes it from rug-style abandonments and is the strongest positive signal Corn generated. The earlier tell was the narrative churn itself: rebranding from ''Bitcoin L2'' to ''Stablecoin Mecca'' months after launch was the community-facing admission that the BTC-DeFi thesis had found no users, and the shutdown confirmed the stablecoin pivot didn''t save it either.","lessons_learned":["''BTC-as-gas'' is a clever mechanic, not a moat — a Bitcoin-DeFi L2 competing for the same idle BTC as Merlin/Bitlayer/B2 offers holders no unique reason to bridge, so incentives just rent temporary TVL.","Running an independent L2 has real recurring costs (proving, sequencing, infra); without organic fee revenue the ongoing burn makes shutdown rational once incentives can''t be sustained — several small L2s (Corn, Swellchain) reached the same math.","An orderly, well-communicated wind-down that returns user funds is the responsible way to die and preserves the team''s reputation for a genuine ''next chapter'' — how you shut down matters."],"could_differ":"Corn could have committed to the stablecoin-payments thesis from day one — launching as a USDT0 payments rail rather than first spending its raise and credibility on a BTC-DeFi L2 that farmed $150M of transient TVL. Building real payment volume/partnerships before emitting CORN would have selected for users over farmers. But the deeper problem is redundancy: a BTC-DeFi chain added nothing over incumbents, and a zero-fee stablecoin rail competes with Tron, Solana and Plasma itself — so even a cleaner execution plausibly ends as a minor rail, not a survivor. The team implicitly agreed, choosing to close and redeploy resources rather than grind on.","outlook":"Unambiguously dead — this is a deliberate, scheduled shutdown, not a decline or a zombie. The network ceases operations June 30, 2026, the app has moved to a legacy domain, and users are being told to bridge assets off before deprecation. There is no recovery scenario for a chain its own team is sunsetting; probability of the chain returning is ~0%. The only forward-looking question is whether the team''s ''next chapter'' (implied to be payments-related) succeeds as a NEW product — which would be a different entity, not a revival of Corn.","cause_tags":["mercenary_tvl","airdrop_farming","team_abandonment","narrative_death"],"sources":[{"title":"Corn - L2BEAT","url":"https://l2beat.com/scaling/projects/corn"},{"title":"Corn Docs - From Bitcoin L2 to Stablecoin Mecca","url":"https://docs.usecorn.com/"},{"title":"CORN (@use_corn) / Posts / X","url":"https://x.com/use_corn"},{"title":"What Is Corn (CORN) And How Does It Work? - CoinMarketCap","url":"https://coinmarketcap.com/cmc-ai/use-corn/what-is/"}]}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('Manta Pacific','2024-01',667700000,3540000,99.5,'2024-03-09','Manta Pacific''s TVL exploded 2,300% in a month (to ~$870M) purely from its ''New Paradigm'' campaign rewarding bridged ETH, but activity never followed, it processed under 3 TPS while ranking a top-4 L2, a red flag that the capital was airdrop-only. When the MANTA airdrop landed in Jan 2024 and disappointed (some got less than gas fees, with ''dev dump'' claims), mercenary capital rotated out and TVL collapsed while MANTA fell ~98% from its March 2024 ATH.','Structurally finished as a competitive L2 — a diluting zombie. It lost the modular/ZK narrative to zkSync and Scroll, has no sticky ecosystem, and MANTA sits near all-time lows (~98% off ATH) with heavy ongoing insider unlocks capping any rally. The team (p0x labs) continues, so it is not a formal shutdown, but the market has decisively signaled the chain can''t attract usage beyond farming. A comeback would need (a) a genuine flagship ZK app that only Manta offers, (b) an end to the dilution overhang, and (c) a fresh modular-ZK bull narrative it can recapture from incumbents — all unlikely to co-occur. Probability of relevant-L2 revival: <5-10%.','declining','[{"title":"Manta Pacific hits $850M TVL becoming Ethereum''s 4th largest L2 - Crypto Briefing","url":"https://cryptobriefing.com/manta-pacific-850m-tvl-ethereums-4th-largest-l2/"},{"title":"Dashed Expectations and Broken Trust: Manta Pacific''s Airdrop - DailyCoin","url":"https://dailycoin.com/manta-pacific-airdrop-disappoints-dev-dump-claims-swirl/"},{"title":"Airdrop hunters plough $345m into fledgling blockchain to get new token - DL News","url":"https://www.dlnews.com/articles/defi/airdrop-hunters-plough-345m-into-fledgling-blockchain-network-to-get-distribution-of-new-token/"},{"title":"Manta Network (MANTA) Sinks 20% on Advisor Token Unlock Day - AInvest","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/manta-network-manta-sinks-20-advisor-token-unlock-day-dilution-pain-2606/"}]','2026-07-08 15:18:10','{"founded":"2024-01","founders":"Victor Ji and Kenny Li (core contributors), building under p0x labs; team from Harvard, MIT and Algorand, roots in MIT Digital Currency Initiative ZK research.","raised":"$25M Series A led by Polychain Capital and Qiming Venture Partners at a $500M valuation (Jul 2023); ~$60M+ total across pre-seed/seed/community/Series A, with Binance Labs, DeFiance, CoinFund, SevenX.","token_symbol":"MANTA","token_ath":4.05,"token_ath_date":"2024-03","token_current":0.056118,"purpose":"A modular EVM L2 (Manta Pacific, on Celestia DA + OP Stack) purpose-built for zero-knowledge applications, paired with Manta Atlantic for compliant on-chain privacy.","situation":"The trigger was the ''New Paradigm'' campaign, launched Dec 14, 2023 (an explicit dig at Blast), which paid users ''box pieces''/NFTs for bridging ETH to Manta Pacific. TVL exploded 2,300%+ in a month — from ~$35M on Dec 15 to ~$850-900M — vaulting Manta to Ethereum''s 4th-largest L2 on L2Beat, while the chain processed under 3 TPS (a top-4 L2 by capital with almost no transactions, i.e., airdrop-only money). The MANTA airdrop went live Jan 18, 2024 (50M to New Paradigm + 50M to ''Into the Blue'' participants). It disappointed hard: some claims were worth less than the gas users had paid, prompting ''worst airdrop ever'' complaints and unverified ''dev dump'' allegations, worsened by bridged deposits being locked until March 2024. Mercenary capital rotated out (rivals zkSync/Scroll held the modular-ZK narrative) and TVL collapsed toward the low tens of millions.","postmortem":"Manta had genuine ZK engineering pedigree, a $500M-valuation Series A, and top-tier backers. But its rise was a textbook incentive mirage: the ''New Paradigm'' campaign rewarding bridged ETH spiked TVL ~2,300% in a month to ~$850-900M while the chain processed under 3 TPS — a top-4 L2 by capital with almost no transactions, proving the money was airdrop-only. When the MANTA airdrop landed in Jan 2024 and disappointed (some claims worth less than gas, amid ''dev dump'' accusations), mercenary capital rotated out and TVL collapsed ~99.5% while MANTA fell ~98% from its March 2024 ATH. Strong tech never translated into organic app demand.","non_economic":"Manta''s social arc went from viral hype to public grievance. The New Paradigm campaign (referral-boosted box/NFT mechanics) manufactured huge X buzz and airdrop-hunter FOMO, but the mood inverted at claim day: coverage titled ''Dashed Expectations and Broken Trust'' documented ''disappointment and controversy'', with ''dev dump'' claims swirling (an allegation that team/insiders sold, not a confirmed event) and complaints that rewards didn''t cover gas. The under-3-TPS-at-$850M-TVL stat was itself a loud non-economic tell that analysts flagged in real time — capital without transactions meant no real community, just farmers. Post-collapse, ongoing dilution kept the story negative: advisor/insider unlocks (e.g., an ~8.1%-of-supply advisor unlock on June 30, 2026) repeatedly pressured MANTA toward all-time lows with circulating supply swelling from a low-float launch to ~47.6% unlocked.","lessons_learned":["TVL divorced from transaction throughput (a top-4 L2 running <3 TPS) is a flashing warning that the capital is farming an airdrop, not using the chain — activity, not TVL, is the honest metric.","An airdrop that pays some recipients less than the gas they spent farming it converts your most engaged users into your loudest detractors overnight.","Low-float/high-FDV launches with long insider unlock schedules create years of structural sell pressure that overwhelms any organic recovery — tokenomics can doom a chain independent of product."],"could_differ":"Manta could have designed New Paradigm to reward on-chain activity and app usage (transactions, dApp interactions) rather than merely bridging ETH, so the campaign selected for users instead of idle capital — and not locked deposits until March, which turned farmers hostile. A larger, more clearly communicated airdrop that at least exceeded participants'' gas costs would have avoided the ''worst airdrop ever'' trust rupture. On tokenomics, a higher initial float with gentler insider vesting would have blunted the multi-year dilution. Realistically these keep MANTA off its lows and retain more TVL, but against zkSync/Scroll owning the modular-ZK story, the ceiling is a mid-tier ZK L2, not a leader.","outlook":"Structurally finished as a competitive L2 — a diluting zombie. It lost the modular/ZK narrative to zkSync and Scroll, has no sticky ecosystem, and MANTA sits near all-time lows (~98% off ATH) with heavy ongoing insider unlocks capping any rally. The team (p0x labs) continues, so it is not a formal shutdown, but the market has decisively signaled the chain can''t attract usage beyond farming. A comeback would need (a) a genuine flagship ZK app that only Manta offers, (b) an end to the dilution overhang, and (c) a fresh modular-ZK bull narrative it can recapture from incumbents — all unlikely to co-occur. Probability of relevant-L2 revival: <5-10%.","cause_tags":["mercenary_tvl","airdrop_farming","no_real_users","narrative_death"],"sources":[{"title":"Manta Pacific hits $850M TVL becoming Ethereum''s 4th largest L2 - Crypto Briefing","url":"https://cryptobriefing.com/manta-pacific-850m-tvl-ethereums-4th-largest-l2/"},{"title":"Dashed Expectations and Broken Trust: Manta Pacific''s Airdrop - DailyCoin","url":"https://dailycoin.com/manta-pacific-airdrop-disappoints-dev-dump-claims-swirl/"},{"title":"Airdrop hunters plough $345m into fledgling blockchain to get new token - DL News","url":"https://www.dlnews.com/articles/defi/airdrop-hunters-plough-345m-into-fledgling-blockchain-network-to-get-distribution-of-new-token/"},{"title":"Manta Network (MANTA) Sinks 20% on Advisor Token Unlock Day - AInvest","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/manta-network-manta-sinks-20-advisor-token-unlock-day-dilution-pain-2606/"}]}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('Mode','2024-01',582300000,1850000,99.7,'2024-05-23','Mode ran the Blast/Manta points playbook on the OP Stack, using a $5.4M Optimism grant and a turbo-points campaign that tied MODE airdrop allocation directly to bridged TVL, spiking deposits near $490M. The MODE token dropped 63% on launch day in May 2024, and once the airdrop drip stopped the mercenary capital left, collapsing TVL 99% to a ''user engagement desert'' with almost no on-chain revenue (its own site still misleadingly claims $500M).','A dead ghost chain — not a formal shutdown, but functionally terminal. 50+ deployed protocols generate essentially no revenue, users have fully rotated to Base within the same Superchain, and MODE trades ~99.97% below ATH. Emissions-only growth with no organic engine leaves nothing to rebuild on. A revival is not credible: it would require the ''AI for DeFi'' pivot to produce a genuinely used flagship app that settles specifically on Mode rather than Base/Solana, plus fresh non-dilutive incentives — an unlikely parlay. Probability of meaningful recovery: <5%. The AI re-theming reads as narrative-chasing, not a turnaround.','dead','[{"title":"Why Mode Network''s investor deposits dropped 99% in one year - DL News","url":"https://www.dlnews.com/articles/defi/why-mode-network-tvl-dropped-99-percent-from-582m-in-a-year/"},{"title":"Layer 2 Network Mode''s Native Token Drops Over 60% Immediately After Airdrop - Unchained","url":"https://unchainedcrypto.com/layer-2-network-modes-native-token-drops-over-60-immediately-after-airdrop/"},{"title":"Mode Network Kicks Off 550 Million Airdrop On Optimism - Crypto Daily","url":"https://cryptodaily.co.uk/2024/05/mode-network-kicks-of-550-million-airdrop-on-optimism"},{"title":"What Is Mode Network? Layer 2 Blockchain Explained - Gate Learn","url":"https://www.gate.com/learn/articles/what-is-mode/9147"}]','2026-07-08 15:18:50','{"founded":"2024-01","founders":"James Ross (founder, UK; ex-advisor at Hashflow, early investor in EigenLayer/Ethena) with technical lead Federico Sarquis and ecosystem head ''Kai'' (ex-Binance BSC DeFi head).","raised":"$5.4M grant from the Optimism Foundation (2M OP, Jan 2024); no disclosed VC equity round. Investors hold 19% of MODE supply.","token_symbol":"MODE","token_ath":0.147725,"token_ath_date":"2024-05","token_current":0.00004811,"purpose":"A modular DeFi-focused OP Stack L2 in the Optimism Superchain, aiming to reward on-chain activity and sequencer/fee sharing to bootstrap a DeFi ecosystem.","situation":"The trigger was the May 7, 2024 TGE / 550M-MODE airdrop (500M to early adopters = 5.5% of the 10B supply, plus 1M OP in incentives). The airdrop was built on ''Mode Points'' accruing since the Jan ''Mode Sunrise'' event, with allocation explicitly gated to TVL milestones (extra 50M MODE unlocked at $100M TVL, another 50M at $200M) — paying people to bridge, not to use apps. TVL rocketed from ~$6k on Jan 1 to a ~$488M peak (15th-largest chain). On launch day MODE opened above $0.14 and fell 63%+ to ~$0.05 within seven hours. Once the points drip stopped, mercenary capital fled and TVL collapsed ~99% to just under $4M within a year, MODE ~98% off ATH. The killer rival was inside its own house: Base, part of the same Superchain, won the OP-Stack traffic war outright.","postmortem":"Mode copied the Blast/Manta points playbook on the OP Stack, using a $5.4M Optimism grant and a turbo-points campaign that tied MODE airdrop allocation directly to bridged TVL — spiking deposits toward $488M. That directly incentivized mercenary capital: users bridged to farm the drop, not to use apps. The MODE token dropped ~63% on its May 2024 launch day, and once the airdrop drip stopped the capital exited, collapsing TVL ~99% into what analysts called a ''user engagement desert'' with almost no on-chain revenue. Being part of the Superchain gave it infrastructure but no differentiated demand, and it lost the L2 traffic war outright to Base.","non_economic":"Mode''s most telling non-economic signal is a documented credibility gap: a year after launch, on-chain data showed TVL down 99% to <$4M while Mode''s own website still advertised ''$500 million in TVL and hundreds of thousands of users'' — DL News explicitly contrasted the live figure against the stale marketing claim. That refusal to update a collapsed vanity metric is a reputational red flag. Underneath, the chain had 50+ deployed protocols generating essentially no revenue — a ''user engagement desert'' — confirming the deployments were incentive-chasing shells, not a living ecosystem. Like several peers, Mode then re-themed toward the hot narrative, repositioning as an ''AI for DeFi'' L2, the familiar sign that the original modular-DeFi thesis found no organic users.","lessons_learned":["Gating airdrop allocation to TVL milestones is the most direct possible way to buy mercenary capital — you are literally paying for a TVL number, and the number leaves when the payment stops.","Being in a shared framework (the OP Superchain) provides infrastructure but not differentiation; if the flagship sibling (Base) has distribution, generic Superchain L2s inherit the tech and lose the users.","Leaving a collapsed TVL figure live on your own homepage a year later actively destroys credibility — markets notice the gap between self-reported and on-chain reality."],"could_differ":"Mode could have decoupled airdrop rewards from bridged TVL entirely and instead rewarded durable behavior — repeat transactions, real DeFi usage, developer deployment of apps people actually use — so the campaign built engagement rather than a hollow deposit spike. Spending the $5.4M OP grant to seed and retain 2-3 genuinely differentiated flagship apps (rather than 50 revenue-less deployments) would have given users a reason to stay. But the structural problem is being a generic OP-Stack DeFi L2 inside Base''s Superchain: even flawless incentive design likely can''t beat Base''s Coinbase distribution, so the realistic upside is a surviving niche, not a Base competitor — which is why the AI pivot followed.","outlook":"A dead ghost chain — not a formal shutdown, but functionally terminal. 50+ deployed protocols generate essentially no revenue, users have fully rotated to Base within the same Superchain, and MODE trades ~99.97% below ATH. Emissions-only growth with no organic engine leaves nothing to rebuild on. A revival is not credible: it would require the ''AI for DeFi'' pivot to produce a genuinely used flagship app that settles specifically on Mode rather than Base/Solana, plus fresh non-dilutive incentives — an unlikely parlay. Probability of meaningful recovery: <5%. The AI re-theming reads as narrative-chasing, not a turnaround.","cause_tags":["mercenary_tvl","airdrop_farming","points_collapse","competition"],"sources":[{"title":"Why Mode Network''s investor deposits dropped 99% in one year - DL News","url":"https://www.dlnews.com/articles/defi/why-mode-network-tvl-dropped-99-percent-from-582m-in-a-year/"},{"title":"Layer 2 Network Mode''s Native Token Drops Over 60% Immediately After Airdrop - Unchained","url":"https://unchainedcrypto.com/layer-2-network-modes-native-token-drops-over-60-immediately-after-airdrop/"},{"title":"Mode Network Kicks Off 550 Million Airdrop On Optimism - Crypto Daily","url":"https://cryptodaily.co.uk/2024/05/mode-network-kicks-of-550-million-airdrop-on-optimism"},{"title":"What Is Mode Network? Layer 2 Blockchain Explained - Gate Learn","url":"https://www.gate.com/learn/articles/what-is-mode/9147"}]}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('Terra Classic','2019-04',20379315493,758175,100,'2022-05-05','The trigger was a depeg beginning May 7-9, 2022: large UST withdrawals from Anchor and coordinated sell pressure on Curve''s UST pool broke the $1 peg, and because UST''s stability relied on minting LUNA to absorb redemptions, the arbitrage became a hyperinflationary death spiral. LUNA supply exploded from ~350M to ~6.5 trillion tokens in days, its price fell from ~$80 to fractions of a cent, UST bottomed near $0.10, and ~$40B+ of value evaporated in under a week. The chain was halted twice and left a husk after the community forked ''Terra 2.0''.','Dead. LUNC is a memecoin curiosity trading ~99.9999% below ATH on community life-support; the real ecosystem migrated to Terra 2.0 (itself now marginal) and founders face criminal liability. On-chain TVL is effectively zero (~$0.75M) with no credible path back — the brand is synonymous with the largest algorithmic-stablecoin failure in crypto history.','dead','[{"title": "Terra (blockchain) — Wikipedia", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terra_(blockchain)"}, {"title": "Anatomy of a Stablecoin''s Failure: The Terra-Luna Case (BIS Bulletin 72)", "url": "https://www.bis.org/publ/bisbull72.htm"}, {"title": "The Fall of Terra: A Timeline of the Rise and Crash of UST and LUNA (CoinDesk)", "url": "https://www.coindesk.com/learn/the-fall-of-terra-a-timeline-of-the-meteoric-rise-and-crash-of-ust-and-luna"}, {"title": "Terraform and Kwon to Pay $4.5 Billion Following Fraud Verdict (SEC)", "url": "https://www.sec.gov/newsroom/press-releases/2024-73"}]','2026-07-08 20:04:06','{"_verdict": "dead", "founded": "2019-04 (mainnet Columbus-1)", "founders": "Do Kwon and Daniel Shin, via Terraform Labs (Singapore/South Korea).", "raised": "~$32M from Binance Labs, Polychain, Hashed, Coinbase Ventures, Galaxy Digital, Arrington and others (2018-2021); the Luna Foundation Guard later raised >$1B in a Feb 2022 round led by Jump Crypto and Three Arrows Capital to build a Bitcoin reserve.", "token_symbol": "LUNC (formerly LUNA)", "token_ath": 119.18, "token_ath_date": "2022-04-05", "token_current": 5e-05, "purpose": "A Cosmos-SDK L1 whose flagship product was UST, an algorithmic stablecoin kept at $1 by a mint/burn arbitrage with the LUNA governance token, plus Anchor Protocol offering ~20% ''risk-free'' yield on UST deposits.", "situation": "The trigger was a depeg beginning May 7-9, 2022: large UST withdrawals from Anchor and coordinated sell pressure on Curve''s UST pool broke the $1 peg, and because UST''s stability relied on minting LUNA to absorb redemptions, the arbitrage became a hyperinflationary death spiral. LUNA supply exploded from ~350M to ~6.5 trillion tokens in days, its price fell from ~$80 to fractions of a cent, UST bottomed near $0.10, and ~$40B+ of value evaporated in under a week. The chain was halted twice and left a husk after the community forked ''Terra 2.0''.", "postmortem": "Terra''s rise was almost entirely a subsidy: Anchor''s ~20% APY was paid from a reserve being drained, not from real yield, so UST demand was demand for an unsustainable rate. The algorithmic peg had no exogenous collateral floor — backed by its own sister token — so a large enough coordinated redemption guaranteed reflexive collapse. LFG''s ~$3B Bitcoin reserve was sold into the crash and failed to defend the peg. A textbook Ponzi-adjacent yield trap wrapped in an L1 narrative; when the subsidy stopped being credible the entire $40B stack unwound at once.", "non_economic": "The fallout was extraordinary: the collapse wiped out retail savers globally, triggered the insolvency of Three Arrows Capital and a contagion chain that took down Celsius, Voyager and eventually FTX. Do Kwon became an international fugitive, was arrested in Montenegro in March 2023 on forged-passport charges, and extradited to the US to face fraud charges; the SEC won a $4.5B judgment against Terraform Labs and Kwon in 2024. His defiant ''steady lads'' and ''I don''t debate the poor'' posts became the enduring cultural symbol of hubris before collapse.", "lessons_learned": ["An algorithmic stablecoin collateralized by its own volatile sister token has no floor — a sufficiently large coordinated redemption always triggers a reflexive death spiral.", "A ~20% ''risk-free'' yield is a subsidy with a burn-down clock, not a product; demand built on it vanishes the instant the reserve looks finite.", "Buying a Bitcoin war-chest to defend a peg is procyclical — you are forced to sell BTC into the same crash that is breaking your peg."], "could_differ": "Nothing plausibly saves UST''s reflexive design. The chain itself had real tech and developers; had Terraform shipped UST as a small over-collateralized experiment capped at a few hundred million while building non-stablecoin utility, Terra could have survived as a mid-tier Cosmos L1. The fatal choice was scaling the algorithmic experiment to an $18B liability funded by unsustainable yield.", "outlook": "Dead. LUNC is a memecoin curiosity trading ~99.9999% below ATH on community life-support; the real ecosystem migrated to Terra 2.0 (itself now marginal) and founders face criminal liability. On-chain TVL is effectively zero (~$0.75M) with no credible path back — the brand is synonymous with the largest algorithmic-stablecoin failure in crypto history.", "cause_tags": ["unsustainable_yield", "narrative_death", "vc_dump", "no_real_users"], "sources": [{"title": "Terra (blockchain) — Wikipedia", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terra_(blockchain)"}, {"title": "Anatomy of a Stablecoin''s Failure: The Terra-Luna Case (BIS Bulletin 72)", "url": "https://www.bis.org/publ/bisbull72.htm"}, {"title": "The Fall of Terra: A Timeline of the Rise and Crash of UST and LUNA (CoinDesk)", "url": "https://www.coindesk.com/learn/the-fall-of-terra-a-timeline-of-the-meteoric-rise-and-crash-of-ust-and-luna"}, {"title": "Terraform and Kwon to Pay $4.5 Billion Following Fraud Verdict (SEC)", "url": "https://www.sec.gov/newsroom/press-releases/2024-73"}], "chain": "Terra Classic", "launched": "2019-04", "peak_tvl": 20379315493, "current_tvl": 758175, "drawdown_pct": 100.0, "peak_date": "2022-05-05"}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('Waves','2016-06',4593381539,6843472,99.9,'2022-04-01','The trigger was the March-April 2022 USDN depeg saga. On March 31 investor 0xHamz published a viral thread calling Waves ''the biggest Ponzi in crypto'', accusing the team of a self-referential leverage loop — borrowing on Vires.finance against WAVES, buying more WAVES to inflate USDN''s peg — which had pumped WAVES to a $61 ATH. USDN broke its $1 peg on April 4 (falling to ~$0.82) and never durably recovered; WAVES collapsed ~90%, Vires.finance froze withdrawals trapping users'' funds, and by December DAXA warned on USDN and Upbit delisted both tokens. Confidence never returned.','Dead as a relevant chain. WAVES trades ~98% below its 2022 top, USDN never recovered its peg, DeFi TVL is a rounding error (~$7M vs a $4.6B peak), and developer activity has evaporated. It persists only as a legacy ticker with a small CIS retail following; there is no product narrative left to revive.','dead','[{"title": "Waves price, market cap and history — CoinMarketCap", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/waves/"}, {"title": "Waves'' USDN Stablecoin Loses Peg, Drops 15% Amid Manipulation Scare (CoinDesk)", "url": "https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2022/04/04/waves-usdn-stablecoin-loses-peg-drops-15-amid-manipulation-scare"}, {"title": "Waves founder announces new stablecoin as USDN depegs (Cointelegraph)", "url": "https://cointelegraph.com/news/waves-founder-announces-new-stablecoin-as-usdn-depegs"}]','2026-07-08 20:04:39','{"_verdict": "dead", "founded": "2016-06", "founders": "Alexander (Sasha) Ivanov, Russian/Ukrainian physicist-turned-entrepreneur; Waves Platform.", "raised": "~$22M (30,000 BTC) in a 2016 ICO, one of the larger ICOs of that era.", "token_symbol": "WAVES", "token_ath": 61.38, "token_ath_date": "2022-03-31", "token_current": 0.9, "purpose": "A standalone L1 pitched as an easy platform to issue and trade custom tokens, later reinvented around the Neutrino Protocol and its algorithmic stablecoin USDN, backed by WAVES.", "situation": "The trigger was the March-April 2022 USDN depeg saga. On March 31 investor 0xHamz published a viral thread calling Waves ''the biggest Ponzi in crypto'', accusing the team of a self-referential leverage loop — borrowing on Vires.finance against WAVES, buying more WAVES to inflate USDN''s peg — which had pumped WAVES to a $61 ATH. USDN broke its $1 peg on April 4 (falling to ~$0.82) and never durably recovered; WAVES collapsed ~90%, Vires.finance froze withdrawals trapping users'' funds, and by December DAXA warned on USDN and Upbit delisted both tokens. Confidence never returned.", "postmortem": "Waves'' 2022 spike was not organic adoption but a reflexive leverage loop between WAVES and its own algorithmic stablecoin USDN, amplified on its captive lending market Vires.finance. USDN, like UST, was backed by the platform''s own volatile token, so the peg was only as strong as WAVES'' price — and WAVES'' price was being propped by USDN demand. When the circularity was exposed the whole structure unwound: WAVES crashed, USDN broke, Vires froze withdrawals, and credibility was destroyed. The same algorithmic-stablecoin doom loop as Terra, smaller and more openly manipulated.", "non_economic": "Trust collapsed around governance and transparency: Vires.finance imposed emergency withdrawal limits that locked lenders out of their USDC/USDT for months, and the community accused the team of changing lending parameters to protect insiders. The USDN ''recapitalization'' via a SURF token was read as a team bailout. Founder Ivanov''s public defenses — including blaming an Alameda-led ''paid trolls'' campaign — failed to restore confidence, and Waves became a cautionary tale of a founder allegedly gaming his own protocol.", "lessons_learned": ["A chain that owns both the stablecoin and the lending market where it is leveraged can manufacture a price with reflexive loops — but the same loops guarantee a violent unwind when scrutinized.", "Freezing withdrawals to defend a protocol destroys the one thing DeFi promises (self-custody exit) and permanently ends trust.", "Algorithmic stablecoins backed by the platform''s own token are structurally identical to Terra regardless of size — the collateral is circular."], "could_differ": "If Waves had stayed a neutral token-issuance L1 and never launched USDN/Neutrino as a WAVES-collateralized stablecoin, it would likely have faded gracefully like other 2016-era chains rather than imploding. The fatal decision was building a reflexive stablecoin loop on the chain''s own token plus a captive lending market — converting a slow decline into a credibility-destroying collapse.", "outlook": "Dead as a relevant chain. WAVES trades ~98% below its 2022 top, USDN never recovered its peg, DeFi TVL is a rounding error (~$7M vs a $4.6B peak), and developer activity has evaporated. It persists only as a legacy ticker with a small CIS retail following; there is no product narrative left to revive.", "cause_tags": ["unsustainable_yield", "soft_rug", "narrative_death", "no_real_users"], "sources": [{"title": "Waves price, market cap and history — CoinMarketCap", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/waves/"}, {"title": "Waves'' USDN Stablecoin Loses Peg, Drops 15% Amid Manipulation Scare (CoinDesk)", "url": "https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2022/04/04/waves-usdn-stablecoin-loses-peg-drops-15-amid-manipulation-scare"}, {"title": "Waves founder announces new stablecoin as USDN depegs (Cointelegraph)", "url": "https://cointelegraph.com/news/waves-founder-announces-new-stablecoin-as-usdn-depegs"}], "chain": "Waves", "launched": "2016-06", "peak_tvl": 4593381539, "current_tvl": 6843472, "drawdown_pct": 99.9, "peak_date": "2022-04-01"}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('EOS','2018-06',383995116,35579098,90.7,'2025-05-17','EOS never recovered from the credibility damage of its origins. It raised a record ~$4.1B in a year-long 2017-18 ICO, then in Sept 2019 the SEC fined issuer Block.one just $24M (0.58% of the raise) for an unregistered securities offering — a slap on the wrist that nonetheless confirmed the token had been sold as a security while the promised ''Ethereum killer'' throughput and dApp ecosystem never materialized. Block.one redeployed most of the war chest into its own ventures (including Bullish exchange) rather than building EOS, and by 2021 the EOS community openly revolted, with the EOS Network Foundation freezing token vesting to Block.one in Dec 2021 over unmet commitments. TVL had a final speculative bounce to ~$384M in mid-2025 before collapsing again as the chain rebranded to Vaulta.','Declining/zombie. EOS still runs and rebranded to ''Vaulta'' in 2025 pivoting toward a ''Web3 banking'' narrative, but on-chain TVL is a fraction of peers and the original ''Ethereum killer'' thesis is dead. The token trades ~97% below its 2018 high; the dApp and DeFi ecosystem never reached escape velocity, and the Block.one saga permanently capped institutional trust. It is a legacy chain kept alive by the ENF and a loyal minority, not a growth story.','declining','[{"title": "EOS Maker Block.One Settles With SEC Over Unregistered Securities Sale (CoinDesk)", "url": "https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2019/09/30/eos-maker-blockone-settles-with-sec-over-unregistered-securities-sale"}, {"title": "EOS price, market cap and history — CoinMarketCap", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/eos/"}, {"title": "EOS.IO — Wikipedia", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/EOS.IO"}]','2026-07-08 20:07:24','{"_verdict": "declining", "chain": "EOS", "launched": "2018-06", "peak_tvl": 383995116, "current_tvl": 35579098, "drawdown_pct": 90.7, "peak_date": "2025-05-17", "founded": "Mainnet June 2018; ICO June 2017–June 2018.", "founders": "Daniel Larimer (CTO, prior creator of BitShares and Steem) and Brendan Blumer (CEO), via Block.one.", "raised": "~$4.1B in a year-long 2017–18 ICO — the largest ICO ever at the time.", "token_symbol": "EOS", "token_ath": 22.89, "token_ath_date": "2018-04-29", "token_current": 0.55, "purpose": "A delegated-proof-of-stake L1 marketed as a high-throughput, feeless ''Ethereum killer'' for scalable dApps, governed by 21 elected block producers.", "situation": "EOS never recovered from the credibility damage of its origins. It raised a record ~$4.1B in a year-long 2017-18 ICO, then in Sept 2019 the SEC fined issuer Block.one just $24M (0.58% of the raise) for an unregistered securities offering — a slap on the wrist that nonetheless confirmed the token had been sold as a security while the promised throughput and dApp ecosystem never materialized. Block.one redeployed most of the capital into its own ventures (including Bullish exchange) rather than building EOS, and by Dec 2021 the EOS Network Foundation froze remaining token vesting to Block.one over unmet commitments.", "postmortem": "EOS is the archetypal ''raise first, build never'' chain. The $4.1B ICO created enormous expectations and an enormous treasury, but the money largely funded Block.one''s separate businesses instead of the EOS ecosystem. Technically, the 21-block-producer DPoS design drew cartel/centralization criticism and vote-buying, undercutting the decentralization pitch, while feeless resource-staking (RAM/CPU/NET) made the UX confusing. Without sustained developer investment the dApp ecosystem stagnated, and the community''s 2021 break with Block.one came too late to matter.", "non_economic": "Governance was the core failure. Block one''s disengagement broke the implicit promise to steward the chain, and the 21-BP model concentrated power among a handful of exchanges and pools, with documented vote-trading. The SEC settlement — a fine worth well under 1% of the raise plus a waiver — signaled to the community that accountability was minimal, and the eventual ENF fork of governance away from Block.one fractured the ecosystem rather than reviving it.", "lessons_learned": ["A record ICO treasury is worthless to a chain if the raising entity spends it on unrelated ventures — capital must be committed to ecosystem development.", "Delegated-PoS with a tiny fixed validator set invites cartelization and vote-buying, hollowing out the decentralization narrative.", "Regulatory settlements far smaller than the raise still stamp a permanent ''unregistered security'' asterisk that caps institutional adoption."], "could_differ": "Had Block.one committed even a fraction of the $4.1B to grants, developer tooling, and liquidity for the EOS chain itself — as later ecosystems did — EOS had the treasury and the early mindshare to be a genuine top-5 L1. The fatal decision was treating the ICO as a corporate raise for Block.one rather than an endowment for the network, leaving EOS technically capable but perpetually under-invested.", "outlook": "Declining/zombie. EOS still runs and rebranded to ''Vaulta'' in 2025 pivoting toward a ''Web3 banking'' narrative, but on-chain TVL is a fraction of peers and the original ''Ethereum killer'' thesis is dead. The token trades ~97% below its 2018 high; the dApp and DeFi ecosystem never reached escape velocity, and the Block.one saga permanently capped institutional trust.", "cause_tags": ["misallocated_treasury", "governance_failure", "narrative_death", "regulatory", "no_real_users"], "sources": [{"title": "EOS Maker Block.One Settles With SEC Over Unregistered Securities Sale (CoinDesk)", "url": "https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2019/09/30/eos-maker-blockone-settles-with-sec-over-unregistered-securities-sale"}, {"title": "EOS price, market cap and history — CoinMarketCap", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/eos/"}, {"title": "EOS.IO — Wikipedia", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/EOS.IO"}]}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('Klaytn','2019-06',1342749878,10886235,99.2,'2021-09-06','There was no single crash; Klaytn faded as its Kakao-backed enterprise/metaverse thesis failed to attract organic DeFi or users, and the 2022 bear market drained its incentive-driven TVL. KLAY fell from a $4.34 ATH toward ~$0.10. DeFi TVL, which peaked near $1.3B in 2021 on Kakao-affiliated incentives, collapsed >99%. In 2023 the Klaytn Foundation moved to burn ~5.28B KLAY amid criticism of excessive reserves, and in 2024 Klaytn conceded defeat by merging with Line''s Finschia to form Kaia — abandoning the Klaytn brand.','Dead under its own name — Klaytn no longer exists as an independent brand, having merged into Kaia in 2024. KLAY holders were converted to KAIA, which itself trades far below KLAY''s ATH with modest TVL. The original Klaytn thesis is finished; whether Kaia succeeds is a separate, still-uncertain story.','dead','[{"title": "Klaytn: Kakao''s Enterprise Blockchain (Gemini Cryptopedia)", "url": "https://www.gemini.com/cryptopedia/klaytn-ico-kakao-enterprise-blockchain"}, {"title": "Klaytn, Finschia blockchains merge, with new foundation in Abu Dhabi (Cointelegraph)", "url": "https://cointelegraph.com/news/klaytn-finschia-blockchains-merge-new-foundation-abu-dhabi"}, {"title": "Kakao''s Klaytn and Line''s Finschia Merge To Create Kaia (The Defiant)", "url": "https://thedefiant.io/news/blockchains/kakao-s-klaytn-and-line-s-finschia-blockchains-merge-to-create-kaia-network"}]','2026-07-08 20:05:47','{"_verdict": "dead", "founded": "2019-06", "founders": "Built by Ground X, the blockchain subsidiary of Kakao (South Korea''s dominant messaging/tech conglomerate).", "raised": "Corporate-funded by Kakao; no public ICO. Backed by the Klaytn Governance Council of large enterprises.", "token_symbol": "KLAY (merged into KAIA)", "token_ath": 4.34, "token_ath_date": "2021-03-30", "token_current": 0.12, "purpose": "An enterprise-friendly public L1 from Kakao, targeting Korean consumer/gaming/metaverse dApps with fast finality and a large corporate governance council.", "situation": "There was no single crash; Klaytn faded as its Kakao-backed enterprise/metaverse thesis failed to attract organic DeFi or users, and the 2022 bear market drained its incentive-driven TVL. KLAY fell from a $4.34 ATH toward ~$0.10. DeFi TVL, which peaked near $1.3B in 2021 on Kakao-affiliated incentives, collapsed >99%. In 2023 the Klaytn Foundation moved to burn ~5.28B KLAY amid criticism of excessive reserves, and in 2024 Klaytn conceded defeat by merging with Line''s Finschia to form Kaia — abandoning the Klaytn brand.", "postmortem": "Klaytn is the story of a corporate chain that never found product-market fit beyond its parent''s orbit. TVL was propped by Kakao-affiliated projects and incentive programs, not a self-sustaining DeFi economy, so when incentives dried up in the bear market there was nothing underneath. The enterprise/metaverse narrative (KlaytnSquare, NFT/metaverse partnerships) never produced durable consumer usage. Governance concentrated among large Korean corporates left little grassroots developer culture. The Kaia merger was a tacit admission neither Klaytn nor Finschia could reach escape velocity alone.", "non_economic": "Community trust eroded over treasury opacity: users criticized the Foundation for holding an outsized KLAY reserve and unclear allocation, leading to the 2023 decision to burn ~5.28B KLAY. The heavy corporate governance council was seen as prioritizing enterprise partners over retail and developers. The metaverse/NFT pivot aged badly as that narrative collapsed industry-wide, and the Kaia rebrand signaled to the market that the original vision had failed.", "lessons_learned": ["A chain built inside a conglomerate''s orbit inherits its parent''s users only as long as the parent subsidizes them — it is not organic adoption.", "Betting a chain''s identity on the metaverse/NFT narrative left it stranded when that narrative died with no fallback thesis.", "Opaque, corporate-heavy treasuries and governance councils suppress the grassroots developer culture that actually retains TVL."], "could_differ": "Klaytn had a genuine asset most chains lack: direct distribution to Kakao''s tens of millions of Korean users. Had it aggressively pushed a real consumer use case into Kakao''s apps early (payments, identity, ticketing) instead of chasing the metaverse/NFT narrative and generic DeFi incentives, it could have become a durable regional consumer chain. The failure was strategic — leaning on incentives and hype rather than converting its unique distribution moat into sticky usage.", "outlook": "Dead under its own name — Klaytn no longer exists as an independent brand, having merged into Kaia in 2024. KLAY holders were converted to KAIA, which itself trades far below KLAY''s ATH with modest TVL. The original Klaytn thesis is finished; whether Kaia succeeds is a separate, still-uncertain story.", "cause_tags": ["mercenary_tvl", "narrative_death", "no_real_users", "competition"], "sources": [{"title": "Klaytn: Kakao''s Enterprise Blockchain (Gemini Cryptopedia)", "url": "https://www.gemini.com/cryptopedia/klaytn-ico-kakao-enterprise-blockchain"}, {"title": "Klaytn, Finschia blockchains merge, with new foundation in Abu Dhabi (Cointelegraph)", "url": "https://cointelegraph.com/news/klaytn-finschia-blockchains-merge-new-foundation-abu-dhabi"}, {"title": "Kakao''s Klaytn and Line''s Finschia Merge To Create Kaia (The Defiant)", "url": "https://thedefiant.io/news/blockchains/kakao-s-klaytn-and-line-s-finschia-blockchains-merge-to-create-kaia-network"}], "chain": "Klaytn", "launched": "2019-06", "peak_tvl": 1342749878, "current_tvl": 10886235, "drawdown_pct": 99.2, "peak_date": "2021-09-06"}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('Aurora','2021-11',1356501248,3132802,99.8,'2022-04-30','Aurora''s ~$1.4B TVL peak in spring 2022 was almost entirely mercenary, incentive-driven capital, not organic usage. Nearly all of it sat in two money markets, Bastion and Aurigami, plus the Trisolaris DEX — and these were recursively interlinked, letting users restake receipt tokens to double-count TVL and leverage-farm. Bastion''s lockdrop pushed stablecoin borrow rates negative (paying people to borrow). When emissions were cut and the 2022 bear market hit, the recursive loop unwound: liquidity fled, the AURORA token fell from ~$35 to under $0.05 (~99.8%), and TVL bled ~99.8% from peak. NEAR''s own troubles and the collapse of adjacent ecosystems removed any reason for capital to stay.','Dead as a DeFi venue. Aurora still operates as NEAR''s EVM layer and NEAR pivoted the brand toward AI, but on-chain TVL is a rounding error (~$3M vs a $1.36B peak) and the token trades ~99% below its high. The DeFi ecosystem that briefly made it a top-10 chain — Bastion, Aurigami, Trisolaris — has largely wound down or gone dormant. There is no active liquidity narrative to revive.','dead','[{"title": "Aurora (NEAR) price, market cap and history — CoinMarketCap", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/aurora-near/"}, {"title": "What Is Aurora Crypto: A Guide to EVM on Near (Zerion)", "url": "https://zerion.io/blog/what-is-aurora-crypto-a-guide-to-evm-on-near/"}, {"title": "Aurora | Near Protocol''s Explosive EVM Blockchain (James Bachini)", "url": "https://jamesbachini.com/aurora-near-protocol-trisolaris/"}]','2026-07-08 20:08:45','{"_verdict": "dead", "chain": "Aurora", "launched": "2021-11", "peak_tvl": 1356501248, "current_tvl": 3132802, "drawdown_pct": 99.8, "peak_date": "2022-04-30", "founded": "May 2021 (EVM launch); DeFi ecosystem live late 2021.", "founders": "Aurora Labs, spun out of NEAR Protocol; led by Alex Shevchenko. Backed by the NEAR Foundation.", "raised": "AURORA token public/DAO launch 2021; ecosystem seeded by NEAR grants and a large DAO treasury. Bastion (its main money market) raised ~$9M.", "token_symbol": "AURORA", "token_ath": 34.72, "token_ath_date": "2021-11-19", "token_current": 0.09, "purpose": "An EVM execution layer running on top of NEAR Protocol, giving Ethereum developers NEAR''s speed and low fees with full Solidity/EVM compatibility.", "situation": "Aurora''s ~$1.4B TVL peak in spring 2022 was almost entirely mercenary, incentive-driven capital, not organic usage. Nearly all of it sat in two money markets, Bastion and Aurigami, plus the Trisolaris DEX — recursively interlinked so users could restake receipt tokens to double-count TVL and leverage-farm. Bastion''s lockdrop pushed stablecoin borrow rates negative (paying people to borrow). When emissions were cut and the 2022 bear hit, the loop unwound: liquidity fled, AURORA fell from ~$35 to under $0.05, and TVL bled ~99.8%.", "postmortem": "Aurora is a textbook mercenary-liquidity collapse. Its headline TVL was inflated by recursive lending-DEX integrations that double-counted the same dollars and by unsustainable emissions (negative borrow rates literally paid users to inflate the number). None of it was sticky. Once NEAR-funded incentives tapered and the bear market raised the opportunity cost of capital, the reflexive structure reversed exactly as fast as it inflated. Aurora also never had a differentiated reason to exist over NEAR-native DeFi or larger EVM L2s, so nothing anchored users after the yield ended.", "non_economic": "Aurora''s fate was tied to NEAR''s. As NEAR''s own momentum faded and it later repositioned around AI rather than DeFi, Aurora lost its sponsor''s attention and co-marketing. There was no independent developer community large enough to sustain the chain, and the flagship protocols (Bastion, Aurigami) that defined the ecosystem wound down, leaving no builders to carry a post-incentive narrative.", "lessons_learned": ["Recursive lending/DEX integrations that let the same capital be counted multiple times produce headline TVL that evaporates the instant incentives stop.", "Negative borrow rates are a flashing sign that a chain is buying its TVL, not earning it.", "An execution layer with no differentiated reason to exist beyond its parent chain''s incentives has no user base once the subsidies end."], "could_differ": "If Aurora had prioritized a few genuinely differentiated, self-sustaining applications over paying for headline TVL via recursive farming, it might have retained a smaller but real user base. The fatal pattern was optimizing for a TVL leaderboard number through emissions and double-counting — a strategy guaranteed to reverse the moment the subsidy budget or the bull market ended.", "outlook": "Dead as a DeFi venue. Aurora still operates as NEAR''s EVM layer and NEAR pivoted the brand toward AI, but on-chain TVL is a rounding error (~$3M vs a $1.36B peak) and the token trades ~99% below its high. The flagship protocols have largely wound down or gone dormant. There is no active liquidity narrative to revive.", "cause_tags": ["mercenary_liquidity", "unsustainable_yield", "double_counted_tvl", "narrative_death", "no_real_users"], "sources": [{"title": "Aurora (NEAR) price, market cap and history — CoinMarketCap", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/aurora-near/"}, {"title": "What Is Aurora Crypto: A Guide to EVM on Near (Zerion)", "url": "https://zerion.io/blog/what-is-aurora-crypto-a-guide-to-evm-on-near/"}, {"title": "Aurora | Near Protocol''s Explosive EVM Blockchain (James Bachini)", "url": "https://jamesbachini.com/aurora-near-protocol-trisolaris/"}]}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('Oasis Network','2020-11',275949760,188352,99.9,'2022-04-26','Oasis Network''s fall was a pure product-market-fit failure. It launched with elite backing (Dawn Song, $45M from a16z et al.) and a differentiated pitch — a privacy-preserving L1 with confidential smart contracts (the Sapphire/ParaTime architecture) for ''responsible data'' and DeFi. TVL peaked near $276M in April 2022, largely on liquidity incentives, then collapsed 99.9%. The confidential-compute narrative never converted into sustained DeFi usage or a killer app; ROSE incentives ran out and mercenary capital left. The most telling signal came in June 2025 when founder Dawn Song departed to lead AI research at Meta''s Superintelligence Labs — the visionary moving on from decentralized privacy to AI, mirroring where the attention and talent went.','Dead/declining. TVL is effectively zero (~$0.2M vs a $276M peak, ~99.9% down) and ROSE trades ~97% below its high. The privacy-L1 thesis never found product-market fit, and founder Dawn Song''s 2025 exit to Meta signals the founding vision has moved on to AI. The chain persists with negligible DeFi activity; its confidential-compute tech is interesting but has no user base sustaining it.','declining','[{"title": "A16z Leads $45 Million Raise for Blockchain Startup Oasis Labs (CoinDesk)", "url": "https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2018/07/09/a16z-leads-45-million-raise-for-blockchain-startup-oasis-labs"}, {"title": "Meta hires Oasis founder Dawn Song for AI safety push (crypto.news)", "url": "https://crypto.news/meta-hires-oasis-founder-dawn-song-for-ai-safety-push/"}, {"title": "Oasis Network (ROSE) price, market cap and history — CoinMarketCap", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/oasis-network/"}]','2026-07-08 20:13:42','{"_verdict": "declining", "chain": "Oasis Network", "launched": "2020-11", "peak_tvl": 275949760, "current_tvl": 188352, "drawdown_pct": 99.9, "peak_date": "2022-04-26", "founded": "Mainnet November 2020; company founded 2018.", "founders": "Dawn Song, UC Berkeley professor (security/AI), via Oasis Labs; team included Raymond Cheng, Noah Johnson, Bobby Jaros.", "raised": "$45M private token pre-sale in July 2018 led by a16z crypto, with Accel, Binance, Pantera, Polychain, Coinbase''s Fred Ehrsam and others.", "token_symbol": "ROSE", "token_ath": 0.5977, "token_ath_date": "2022-01-15", "token_current": 0.02, "purpose": "A privacy-focused L1 with confidential smart contracts (Sapphire ParaTime) and a ''responsible data economy'' pitch — letting DeFi and data apps compute over private data.", "situation": "Oasis Network''s fall was a pure product-market-fit failure. It launched with elite backing (Dawn Song, $45M from a16z et al.) and a differentiated privacy-L1 pitch with confidential smart contracts. TVL peaked near $276M in April 2022, largely on liquidity incentives, then collapsed 99.9%. The confidential-compute narrative never converted into sustained DeFi usage or a killer app; ROSE incentives ran out and mercenary capital left. The most telling signal came in June 2025 when founder Dawn Song departed to lead AI research at Meta''s Superintelligence Labs.", "postmortem": "Oasis had the pedigree, funding, and a genuinely novel privacy tech stack, but confidential computing was a solution in search of demand. Privacy-preserving DeFi never became a category users cared about enough to pay for, and the TVL that did arrive was incentive-driven and fled when emissions stopped. Without a flagship app that needed on-chain confidentiality, the differentiated tech had no economic pull. The founder''s move to Meta AI in 2025 crystallized that the intellectual energy behind the project had migrated to a different frontier.", "non_economic": "No scandal — a quiet fade. The team was credible and kept shipping (Sapphire confidential EVM), but could not manufacture demand for privacy features, and could not out-compete general-purpose L1s/L2s for generic DeFi. Dawn Song''s high-profile departure to Meta signaled to the market that the founding vision no longer saw its future in the chain, draining remaining confidence and talent gravity.", "lessons_learned": ["Elite founders and top-tier VC funding cannot manufacture product-market fit — privacy-preserving compute was a technology without a paying user base.", "Differentiated tech with no killer app that requires it has no economic pull; the feature has to be load-bearing for real demand.", "A founder''s departure to a hotter frontier (AI) is a strong signal that a chain''s core vision has stalled."], "could_differ": "If Oasis had incubated or captured even one application that genuinely required on-chain confidentiality (a private stablecoin, compliant institutional DeFi, or a data marketplace with real users), its unique tech would have had a demand anchor. The failure was building sophisticated privacy infrastructure and waiting for demand that never materialized, while paying incentives to simulate the traction in the meantime.", "outlook": "Dead/declining. TVL is effectively zero (~99.9% down) and ROSE trades ~97% below its high. The privacy-L1 thesis never found product-market fit, and founder Dawn Song''s 2025 exit to Meta signals the founding vision has moved on. Negligible DeFi activity remains.", "cause_tags": ["no_product_market_fit", "mercenary_liquidity", "narrative_death", "no_real_users", "founder_exit"], "sources": [{"title": "A16z Leads $45 Million Raise for Blockchain Startup Oasis Labs (CoinDesk)", "url": "https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2018/07/09/a16z-leads-45-million-raise-for-blockchain-startup-oasis-labs"}, {"title": "Meta hires Oasis founder Dawn Song for AI safety push (crypto.news)", "url": "https://crypto.news/meta-hires-oasis-founder-dawn-song-for-ai-safety-push/"}, {"title": "Oasis Network (ROSE) price, market cap and history — CoinMarketCap", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/oasis-network/"}]}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('Astar','2021-12',387408386,1628561,99.6,'2022-04-19','Astar rose as Polkadot''s flagship parachain, winning an early parachain-slot auction and pitching ''Build2Earn'' dApp staking — developers earn a basic income from tokens staked to their dApp. TVL peaked ~$387M in April 2022, then bled 99.6%. Two structural flaws drove the collapse: (1) dApp staking was a zero-sum game with heavy concentration — Astar''s own core-contributor and treasury entries held over 54% of all staked TVL, starving new builders; and (2) ASTR''s very high inflation (~253 new ASTR every 12 seconds) relentlessly suppressed the price and diluted rewards. As Polkadot''s parachain thesis lost momentum, Astar pivoted to an Ethereum L2 (Astar zkEVM on Polygon CDK) — but entered a shrinking ZK-rollup sector seeing net outflows, and the zkEVM was ultimately wound down.','Dead/declining. TVL is down ~99.6% and ASTR trades ~98% below its high, gutted by chronic inflation. The Polkadot-parachain thesis faded, and the Ethereum-L2 rescue (Astar zkEVM) launched into a losing ZK-rollup market and was later shut down. Astar still operates and keeps rebranding its product framework (''Astar Stack''), but it is a declining chain in search of relevance, not a growth story.','declining','[{"title": "Astar Network — Introducing zkEVM to Extend to the Ethereum Ecosystem (DeSpread Research)", "url": "https://research.despread.io/reports-astar/"}, {"title": "dApp Staking Overview — Astar Docs", "url": "https://docs.astar.network/docs/learn/dapp-staking/"}, {"title": "Astar (ASTR) price, market cap and history — CoinMarketCap", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/astar/"}]','2026-07-08 20:15:01','{"_verdict": "declining", "chain": "Astar", "launched": "2021-12", "peak_tvl": 387408386, "current_tvl": 1628561, "drawdown_pct": 99.6, "peak_date": "2022-04-19", "founded": "Parachain launched Dec 2021 (as Plasm/Astar); founded 2020.", "founders": "Sota Watanabe, via Astar Foundation / Stake Technologies. Backed by Polychain, Binance Labs, Coinbase Ventures and others.", "raised": "~$32M+ across rounds (2021–22), including a $22M round led by Polychain (2022).", "token_symbol": "ASTR", "token_ath": 0.4177, "token_ath_date": "2022-01-17", "token_current": 0.02, "purpose": "Polkadot''s flagship smart-contract parachain supporting both EVM and WASM, with ''Build2Earn'' dApp staking that pays developers a basic income from tokens staked to their dApp.", "situation": "Astar rose as Polkadot''s flagship parachain, winning an early slot auction and pitching dApp staking. TVL peaked ~$387M in April 2022, then bled 99.6%. Two structural flaws drove the collapse: dApp staking was a zero-sum game with heavy concentration — Astar''s own core-contributor and treasury entries held over 54% of staked TVL, starving new builders; and ASTR''s very high inflation (~253 new ASTR every 12s) relentlessly suppressed price and diluted rewards. As Polkadot''s parachain thesis lost momentum, Astar pivoted to an Ethereum L2 (Astar zkEVM on Polygon CDK), which launched into a shrinking ZK-rollup sector and was ultimately wound down.", "postmortem": "Astar''s incentive design contained the seeds of its decline. dApp staking sounded builder-friendly but was zero-sum: a fixed reward pool split among ever more dApps, dominated by Astar''s own treasury positions, so newcomers got scraps — a poor magnet for genuine builders. Meanwhile aggressive ASTR emissions meant staking rewards were paid in a constantly-diluting token, so ''basic income'' eroded in real terms and sellers overwhelmed buyers. The Polkadot bet compounded this: as parachains lost the network-effects race to Ethereum L2s, Astar chased the L2 narrative late, into the weakest rollup category, and had to retreat.", "non_economic": "No fraud — a design-and-strategy failure. Governance and the team functioned and kept iterating (dApp Staking V3, Tokenomics 2.0, the Astar Stack rebrand), but each iteration was firefighting inflation and concentration problems baked into the original model. Betting the chain''s future on Polkadot, then pivoting to a losing ZK-rollup, drained credibility and left the community whipsawed across incompatible strategies.", "lessons_learned": ["A fixed-pool, zero-sum reward mechanism dominated by the team''s own positions cannot attract independent builders — it just redistributes to insiders.", "High token inflation guarantees that staking ''income'' erodes in real terms and that emission-sellers overwhelm buyers, crushing the price regardless of activity.", "Chaining your fate to one ecosystem''s thesis (Polkadot parachains) is fatal if that thesis loses the network-effects race, and pivoting late into a shrinking sector rarely rescues it."], "could_differ": "If Astar had capped inflation early and designed dApp staking so independent builders — not the treasury — captured the rewards, it might have retained developers and price support. And had it recognized the parachain thesis was losing sooner, a timely, focused move to a leading L2 stack could have preserved liquidity. Instead chronic dilution plus a late pivot into the weakest rollup category compounded into a ~99.6% collapse.", "outlook": "Dead/declining. TVL is down ~99.6% and ASTR trades ~98% below its high, gutted by chronic inflation. The parachain thesis faded, the zkEVM rescue launched into a losing market and was later shut down. Astar still operates and keeps rebranding, but it is a declining chain seeking relevance.", "cause_tags": ["unsustainable_yield", "token_inflation", "insider_concentration", "lost_competition", "narrative_death"], "sources": [{"title": "Astar Network — Introducing zkEVM to Extend to the Ethereum Ecosystem (DeSpread Research)", "url": "https://research.despread.io/reports-astar/"}, {"title": "dApp Staking Overview — Astar Docs", "url": "https://docs.astar.network/docs/learn/dapp-staking/"}, {"title": "Astar (ASTR) price, market cap and history — CoinMarketCap", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/astar/"}]}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('Metis','2021-11',482789051,2863318,99.4,'2022-03-15','Metis (Andromeda) launched as one of the earliest Optimistic Ethereum L2s, differentiating on a ''decentralized autonomous company (DAC)'' narrative and a $100M Genesi ecosystem fund (led by Natalia Ameline, Vitalik Buterin''s mother) to bootstrap dApps. TVL spiked to ~$483M in March 2022 on aggressive liquidity mining, then collapsed 99.4%. The METIS-token incentives that drew capital were mercenary, and the DAC pitch never produced sticky, differentiated usage. Critically, Metis then lost the L2 race outright: Arbitrum, Optimism and later Base captured developers, liquidity, and the airdrop-driven user wave, leaving Metis a sub-scale rollup with a long-centralized single sequencer. Its TVL never recovered even as the L2 sector as a whole boomed.','Dead/declining as an L2. TVL is down ~99.4% and METIS trades ~90%+ below its peak. Metis was an L2 pioneer that got lapped by Arbitrum, Optimism and Base and never regained relevance; its $100M ecosystem fund and DAC narrative failed to create durable usage. It still runs and has pursued decentralized-sequencer work, but it is a marginal rollup, not a contender.','declining','[{"title": "Metis (METIS) price, market cap and history — CoinMarketCap", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/metisdao/"}, {"title": "Metis Andromeda — L2BEAT", "url": "https://l2beat.com/scaling/projects/metis"}, {"title": "Metis Andromeda — The Latest Layer 2 Protocol on Ethereum (Switcheo)", "url": "https://blog.switcheo.com/metis-andromeda/"}]','2026-07-08 20:15:51','{"_verdict": "declining", "chain": "Metis", "launched": "2021-11", "peak_tvl": 482789051, "current_tvl": 2863318, "drawdown_pct": 99.4, "peak_date": "2022-03-15", "founded": "Andromeda mainnet November 2021; project founded 2019.", "founders": "Elena Sinelnikova, Kevin Liu, Yuan Su. Publicly associated with Natalia Ameline (Vitalik Buterin''s mother), who led its ecosystem fund.", "raised": "Token sale plus a $100M ''Genesi'' ecosystem incentive fund announced Nov 2021.", "token_symbol": "METIS", "token_ath": 269.71, "token_ath_date": "2024-04-01", "token_current": 15.0, "purpose": "An early Optimistic Ethereum L2 (Andromeda) pitching low fees plus a ''decentralized autonomous company (DAC)'' framework and tooling (Polis) for on-chain organizations.", "situation": "Metis launched as one of the earliest Optimistic L2s, differentiating on a ''DAC'' narrative and a $100M Genesi ecosystem fund (led by Natalia Ameline) to bootstrap dApps. TVL spiked to ~$483M in March 2022 on aggressive liquidity mining, then collapsed 99.4%. The METIS incentives that drew capital were mercenary, and the DAC pitch never produced sticky differentiated usage. Metis then lost the L2 race outright: Arbitrum, Optimism and later Base captured developers, liquidity and the airdrop-driven user wave, leaving Metis a sub-scale rollup with a long-centralized single sequencer whose TVL never recovered even as the L2 sector boomed.", "postmortem": "Metis was early but out-executed. Being a first-mover Optimistic rollup counted for little once better-funded, more-credible teams (Arbitrum, Optimism) and Coinbase''s Base arrived with deeper liquidity, richer tooling and giant airdrop incentives. Metis''s own draw — the $100M fund and DAC concept — bought incentive-driven TVL that left when emissions faded, and the DAC framing never became a category users needed. A prolonged reliance on a single centralized sequencer undercut the decentralization story. The result: a chain that peaked on subsidies and then structurally lost the platform race.", "non_economic": "No scandal (despite unfounded ''founder disappearance'' rumors that circulated — the founders and the Ameline connection are public). The failure was competitive: Metis could not match the ecosystem gravity of Arbitrum/Optimism/Base, and its differentiators (DAC tooling, Polis) never achieved adoption. Iterating toward a decentralized sequencer later was credible engineering but too late to change the competitive outcome.", "lessons_learned": ["Being an early L2 is worthless without sustained developer gravity — better-capitalized, more-credible rollups with bigger incentive budgets simply lap you.", "A large ecosystem fund buys incentive-driven TVL, not a moat; when emissions fade the capital leaves and no differentiated usage remains.", "A novel framing (DAC/DAO tooling) only matters if builders actually adopt it — otherwise it is marketing, not a moat."], "could_differ": "If Metis had concentrated its $100M on winning a specific vertical or a genuinely killer app rather than spreading liquidity-mining incentives thinly — and decentralized its sequencer far earlier — it might have carved a defensible niche before Arbitrum/Optimism/Base saturated the L2 market. The core problem was competing head-on for generic L2 liquidity against far stronger ecosystems and losing.", "outlook": "Dead/declining as an L2. TVL is down ~99.4% and METIS trades well below peak. Metis was an L2 pioneer lapped by Arbitrum, Optimism and Base and never regained relevance. It still runs and pursued decentralized-sequencer work, but it is a marginal rollup.", "cause_tags": ["lost_competition", "mercenary_liquidity", "unsustainable_yield", "centralization", "narrative_death"], "sources": [{"title": "Metis (METIS) price, market cap and history — CoinMarketCap", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/metisdao/"}, {"title": "Metis Andromeda — L2BEAT", "url": "https://l2beat.com/scaling/projects/metis"}, {"title": "Metis Andromeda — The Latest Layer 2 Protocol on Ethereum (Switcheo)", "url": "https://blog.switcheo.com/metis-andromeda/"}]}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('Boba Network','2021-09',615420663,1970571,99.7,'2021-11-26','Boba (originally OMGX, from the OMG Foundation and Enya, descendant of 2017''s OmiseGO) launched an Optimistic rollup in Sept 2021 and airdropped BOBA to OMG holders in Nov 2021 — a distribution FTX committed to support. TVL spiked to ~$615M within weeks (briefly 2x Optimism''s), a classic airdrop-plus-incentive sugar high. It then collapsed ~99.7%. Boba raised a $45M Series A at up to a $1.5B valuation in April 2022 — right at the market top — but its differentiators (fast withdrawals, ''Hybrid Compute'' off-chain calls) never drew sticky demand, and it lost the L2 race decisively to Arbitrum, Optimism and Base. Its FTX association became a liability after FTX''s Nov 2022 collapse, and its multi-chain deployments (Avalanche, Fantom, Moonbeam) were later deprecated.','Dead as a mainstream L2. TVL is down ~99.7% and BOBA trades ~98% below its high. Boba''s early-mover lead evaporated as Arbitrum/Optimism/Base took the developers and liquidity; the FTX links, a top-tick $1.5B raise, and deprecated multi-chain deployments underline the reversal. It still runs and leans on a ''Hybrid Compute / AI'' narrative, but it is a marginal rollup, not a contender.','declining','[{"title": "Boba Network (BOBA) price, market cap and history — CoinMarketCap", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/boba-network/"}, {"title": "Boba Network''s Layer-2 Solutions (formerly OMGX) — Gemini Cryptopedia", "url": "https://www.gemini.com/cryptopedia/boba-network-layer-2-solutions-boba-token"}]','2026-07-08 20:17:20','{"_verdict": "declining", "chain": "Boba Network", "launched": "2021-09", "peak_tvl": 615420663, "current_tvl": 1970571, "drawdown_pct": 99.7, "peak_date": "2021-11-26", "founded": "Mainnet Sept 2021 (as OMGX, then Boba); lineage from OmiseGO/OMG (2017).", "founders": "Built by Enya (co-founded by Alan Chiu and Jan Liphardt, Stanford) with the OMG Foundation.", "raised": "$45M Series A in April 2022 at up to a $1.5B valuation (Huobi, Crypto.com, Hack VC, BitMart and ~28 investors); prior OMG lineage.", "token_symbol": "BOBA", "token_ath": 6.09, "token_ath_date": "2021-11-28", "token_current": 0.12, "purpose": "An Ethereum Optimistic rollup (fork of Optimism) offering low fees, fast liquidity-pool withdrawals, and ''Hybrid Compute'' — letting smart contracts call external APIs/off-chain computation atomically.", "situation": "Boba (originally OMGX, from the OMG Foundation and Enya) launched an Optimistic rollup in Sept 2021 and airdropped BOBA to OMG holders in Nov 2021, a distribution FTX committed to support. TVL spiked to ~$615M within weeks (briefly 2x Optimism''s) — an airdrop-plus-incentive sugar high — then collapsed ~99.7%. Boba raised $45M at up to a $1.5B valuation in April 2022, right at the top, but its differentiators never drew sticky demand and it lost the L2 race to Arbitrum, Optimism and Base. Its FTX association became a liability after FTX''s Nov 2022 collapse, and its multi-chain deployments (Avalanche, Fantom, Moonbeam) were later deprecated.", "postmortem": "Boba mistook an airdrop spike for product-market fit. Distributing BOBA to OMG holders (with FTX''s blessing) manufactured an instant TVL leaderboard position, but that capital was speculative and mercenary — it left as fast as it came. The genuinely interesting Hybrid Compute feature never anchored a killer app, and ''fast withdrawals'' was a thin moat once every major L2 offered bridges and liquidity. Meanwhile Arbitrum, Optimism and Base out-executed on ecosystem, funding and airdrop incentives. Raising at a $1.5B valuation at the cycle top locked in expectations the fundamentals could never meet, and the FTX linkage added reputational drag.", "non_economic": "No fraud at Boba itself, but its close FTX association (airdrop support, ecosystem ties) became a reputational liability when FTX imploded in Nov 2022. The quiet deprecation of its Avalanche/Fantom/Moonbeam deployments signaled retreat, and the OMG-to-Boba lineage of repeated rebrands (OmiseGO → OMG → OMGX → Boba) suggested a project perpetually chasing the next narrative rather than compounding one.", "lessons_learned": ["An airdrop-driven TVL spike is not adoption — speculative capital that arrives for a token distribution leaves the moment the incentive is banked.", "A single technical feature (Hybrid Compute, fast withdrawals) is not a moat if no killer app depends on it and rivals offer good-enough alternatives.", "Raising a large round at a cycle-top valuation and tying your brand to a single exchange (FTX) concentrates risk that detonates when the market or that partner turns."], "could_differ": "If Boba had used its early lead and $45M to fund one or two applications that genuinely required Hybrid Compute — giving the feature real demand — and diversified away from FTX-linked distribution, it might have held a defensible niche. Instead it optimized for an airdrop-driven TVL number at the top of the cycle and got structurally out-competed by better-resourced rollups.", "outlook": "Dead as a mainstream L2. TVL down ~99.7% and BOBA ~98% below its high. Boba''s early lead evaporated as Arbitrum/Optimism/Base took the developers and liquidity; FTX links, a top-tick $1.5B raise, and deprecated multi-chain deployments underline the reversal. It leans on a Hybrid Compute/AI narrative but is a marginal rollup.", "cause_tags": ["airdrop_farming", "mercenary_liquidity", "lost_competition", "ftx_contagion", "narrative_death"], "sources": [{"title": "Boba Network (BOBA) price, market cap and history — CoinMarketCap", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/boba-network/"}, {"title": "Boba Network''s Layer-2 Solutions (formerly OMGX) — Gemini Cryptopedia", "url": "https://www.gemini.com/cryptopedia/boba-network-layer-2-solutions-boba-token"}]}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('Kava','2019-11',703400592,21878287,96.9,'2021-11-26','Kava peaked near $703M TVL in Nov 2021 as a Cosmos DeFi hub, then bled through the bear market. Its defining move was Kava Rise (March 2022): a $750M program directing 62.5% of all block rewards to builders, distributed pro-rata by each protocol''s time-weighted TVL. The team openly described a ''reinforcing loop'' — rewards used as user incentives to lift TVL to earn more rewards — which is a textbook emissions-funded, mercenary-liquidity scheme. It temporarily flattered the numbers (100+ protocols deployed) but never produced durable, fee-generating usage. As emissions were re-weighted and the market cooled, TVL kept sliding to ~$22M. Kava has since pivoted its narrative to decentralized AI, tacitly conceding the DeFi-hub thesis stalled.','Declining/zombie. TVL sits ~97% below its 2021 peak despite the $750M Kava Rise spend, proving the incentives bought TVL rather than lasting usage. The chain still runs and has rebranded around a ''decentralized AI'' narrative, but its DeFi ecosystem is a shadow of peak and KAVA trades ~90%+ below its high. It is a living chain searching for relevance, not a growing one.','declining','[{"title": "Kava Rise: $750M Developer Incentive Program (Kava)", "url": "https://www.kava.io/news/kava-rise-750m-developer-incentive-program"}, {"title": "Kava launches $750M developer incentive program (Invezz)", "url": "https://invezz.com/news/2022/03/17/kava-launches-750m-developer-incentive-program/"}, {"title": "Kava (KAVA) price, market cap and history — CoinMarketCap", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/kava/"}]','2026-07-08 20:11:54','{"_verdict": "declining", "chain": "Kava", "launched": "2019-11", "peak_tvl": 703400592, "current_tvl": 21878287, "drawdown_pct": 96.9, "peak_date": "2021-11-26", "founded": "Mainnet November 2019.", "founders": "Brian Kerr, Ruaridh O''Donnell, Scott Stuart, via Kava Labs.", "raised": "~$9M+ (2019 Binance Launchpad IEO plus private rounds).", "token_symbol": "KAVA", "token_ath": 9.12, "token_ath_date": "2021-08-30", "token_current": 0.4, "purpose": "A Cosmos-SDK L1 with a Cosmos + EVM ''co-chain'' architecture, pitched as a cross-chain DeFi hub for lending, stablecoins (USDX) and IBC assets.", "situation": "Kava peaked near $703M TVL in Nov 2021, then bled through the bear market. Its defining move was Kava Rise (March 2022): a $750M program directing 62.5% of all block rewards to builders, distributed pro-rata by each protocol''s time-weighted TVL. The team openly described a ''reinforcing loop'' — rewards used as user incentives to lift TVL to earn more rewards — a textbook emissions-funded mercenary-liquidity scheme. It temporarily flattered the numbers (100+ protocols) but never produced durable fee-generating usage. As emissions re-weighted and the market cooled, TVL slid to ~$22M. Kava has since pivoted to a ''decentralized AI'' narrative.", "postmortem": "Kava tried to buy an ecosystem. Directing the majority of block emissions to whoever posted the most TVL guaranteed that the TVL was rented, not earned — protocols farmed KAVA, recycled it as user incentives, and left when the reward math weakened. The USDX stablecoin also struggled to hold demand. When Kava re-weighted Rise toward ''usage, volume and fees,'' it was implicitly admitting pure TVL had been gamed. The co-chain architecture never produced a killer app, and the later AI pivot signals the DeFi-hub thesis has run out of road.", "non_economic": "No single scandal — the failure was strategic and mechanistic. Governance functioned (the DAO approved and later restructured Rise), but it approved a fundamentally reflexive incentive design. Repeatedly re-tuning the payout formula eroded confidence that anyone knew how to convert subsidies into organic activity, and the pivot to AI branding read as a search for a new story rather than fixing the old one.", "lessons_learned": ["Paying out the majority of block rewards pro-rata to TVL directly incentivizes gaming the TVL metric — you rent capital, you don''t build an economy.", "A ''reinforcing loop'' where rewards fund the incentives that earn more rewards is reflexive and unwinds when the token price or emissions weaken.", "Needing to repeatedly re-weight an incentive program is a tell that the original metric was being gamed."], "could_differ": "If Kava had spent a fraction of the $750M on a few deeply-integrated, fee-generating flagship apps and durable stablecoin demand — rather than a pro-rata-by-TVL emissions firehose — it might have retained a smaller but real ecosystem. The core error was designing incentives around a gameable balance-sheet number instead of around usage and fees.", "outlook": "Declining/zombie. TVL sits ~97% below its 2021 peak despite the $750M spend, proving the incentives bought TVL, not usage. The chain still runs and rebranded around ''decentralized AI,'' but its DeFi ecosystem is a shadow of peak and KAVA trades well below its high.", "cause_tags": ["mercenary_liquidity", "unsustainable_yield", "gamed_metrics", "narrative_death"], "sources": [{"title": "Kava Rise: $750M Developer Incentive Program (Kava)", "url": "https://www.kava.io/news/kava-rise-750m-developer-incentive-program"}, {"title": "Kava launches $750M developer incentive program (Invezz)", "url": "https://invezz.com/news/2022/03/17/kava-launches-750m-developer-incentive-program/"}, {"title": "Kava (KAVA) price, market cap and history — CoinMarketCap", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/kava/"}]}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('Moonbeam','2021-12',275732558,875616,99.7,'2022-01-27','Moonbeam was Polkadot''s flagship EVM parachain. It won the second-ever Polkadot parachain slot auction on Nov 25, 2021 via the largest crowdloan the network had ever seen — 200,000+ contributors locking 35M DOT (~$1.4B at the time) — and went live Dec 17, 2021. TVL peaked at $275.7M on Jan 27, 2022, then collapsed ~99.7% as the parachain thesis failed to deliver liquidity or developers and DeFi consolidated onto Ethereum L2s. The decline culminated on July 3, 2026, when Moonbeam announced it was ending all Polkadot parachain operations, migrating GLMR 1:1 to Coinbase''s Base (hard cutoff July 31, 2026), and pivoting from a general-purpose chain to an AI-agent payment/verification protocol — an explicit admission the parachain model didn''t work.','Dead as a Polkadot parachain. TVL collapsed ~99.7% (from $275.7M to ~$1M) and GLMR trades ~99% below its high. In July 2026 Moonbeam abandoned Polkadot entirely for Base and repurposed itself as an AI-agent payments protocol — a total reset that concedes the original chain thesis failed. The GLMR ticker survives via a 1:1 bridge to a new Base token, but Moonbeam-the-parachain is finished.','dead','[{"title": "Moonbeam abandons Polkadot for Base as GLMR pivots to AI (Cryptonews)", "url": "https://cryptonews.net/news/altcoins/33100302/"}, {"title": "Second Parachain Auction Winner Moonbeam Goes Live on Polkadot (CryptoPotato)", "url": "https://cryptopotato.com/second-parachain-auction-winner-moonbeam-goes-live-on-polkadot/"}, {"title": "Moonbeam (GLMR) price, market cap and history — CoinMarketCap", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/moonbeam/"}]','2026-07-08 20:18:41','{"_verdict": "dead", "chain": "Moonbeam", "launched": "2021-12", "peak_tvl": 275732558, "current_tvl": 875616, "drawdown_pct": 99.7, "peak_date": "2022-01-27", "founded": "Parachain live Dec 17, 2021; project started 2019–20.", "founders": "Derek Yoo, out of his company PureStake (now Moonsong Labs).", "raised": "Won its Polkadot slot via a record crowdloan of 35M DOT (~$1.4B) from 200,000+ contributors (Nov 2021); prior private rounds via PureStake.", "token_symbol": "GLMR", "token_ath": 21.14, "token_ath_date": "2022-01-06", "token_current": 0.01, "purpose": "Polkadot''s flagship Ethereum-compatible smart-contract parachain — a Substrate chain giving Solidity/EVM developers full compatibility plus Polkadot''s shared security and cross-chain messaging.", "situation": "Moonbeam won the second-ever Polkadot parachain slot auction on Nov 25, 2021 via the largest crowdloan the network had ever seen — 200,000+ contributors locking 35M DOT (~$1.4B) — and went live Dec 17, 2021. TVL peaked at $275.7M on Jan 27, 2022, then collapsed ~99.7% as the parachain thesis failed to deliver liquidity or developers and DeFi consolidated onto Ethereum L2s. It culminated July 3, 2026, when Moonbeam ended all Polkadot parachain operations, migrated GLMR 1:1 to Base (cutoff July 31, 2026), and pivoted to an AI-agent payment/verification protocol — an explicit admission the parachain model didn''t work.", "postmortem": "Moonbeam is the clearest indictment of the Polkadot parachain model. It did everything right on paper — won the marquee auction with a record $1.4B crowdloan, shipped full EVM compatibility, attracted early DeFi — yet the shared-security relay-chain architecture never produced the liquidity depth or developer gravity of Ethereum''s L2s. Locking DOT for 96 weeks to rent a slot was capital-inefficient, cross-chain messaging was clunky versus EVM-native tooling, and flagship apps like Moonwell migrated to Ethereum. When the lease economics and network effects both pointed off-Polkadot, the founder rationally abandoned the entire ecosystem — taking the token to Base and rebranding around AI agents.", "non_economic": "No fraud — a strategic capitulation. The team stayed credible and executed a clean 1:1 migration, even warning users to withdraw from DeFi before the wind-down. But abandoning Polkadot outright, after being its flagship and its largest crowdloan, is a devastating signal about the parachain thesis; it was ''just the latest in a string of high-profile exits from the shrinking Polkadot ecosystem.'' The AI-agent pivot is a fresh, unproven bet on Base rather than a continuation of anything Moonbeam built.", "lessons_learned": ["Winning the biggest auction/crowdloan in an ecosystem means nothing if that ecosystem''s architecture can''t compound liquidity and developer network effects.", "Leasing shared security by locking capital for ~2 years is capital-inefficient versus permissionless Ethereum L2s, and users/apps notice.", "When your flagship apps migrate away and the parent ecosystem shrinks, even a well-run team''s rational move is to abandon the chain entirely — the clearest possible ''dead chain'' signal."], "could_differ": "Moonbeam''s failure was largely a bet on the wrong platform rather than poor execution. Had it launched as (or migrated far earlier to) an Ethereum L2 instead of committing to Polkadot''s parachain-lease model, it might have retained the DeFi apps and liquidity that instead defected to Ethereum. The fatal decision was anchoring the whole chain to Polkadot''s shared-security thesis, which lost the network-effects race.", "outlook": "Dead as a Polkadot parachain. TVL collapsed ~99.7% and GLMR trades ~99% below its high. In July 2026 Moonbeam abandoned Polkadot entirely for Base and repurposed itself as an AI-agent payments protocol — a total reset conceding the original thesis failed.", "cause_tags": ["lost_competition", "wrong_ecosystem_bet", "narrative_death", "no_real_users"], "sources": [{"title": "Moonbeam abandons Polkadot for Base as GLMR pivots to AI (Cryptonews)", "url": "https://cryptonews.net/news/altcoins/33100302/"}, {"title": "Second Parachain Auction Winner Moonbeam Goes Live on Polkadot (CryptoPotato)", "url": "https://cryptopotato.com/second-parachain-auction-winner-moonbeam-goes-live-on-polkadot/"}, {"title": "Moonbeam (GLMR) price, market cap and history — CoinMarketCap", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/moonbeam/"}]}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('Harmony','2019-06',1411256914,198913,100,'2022-01-14','The trigger was the June 23, 2022 Horizon Bridge hack: attackers compromised the bridge''s multisig — which required only 2-of-5 signatures — and drained ~$100M in ETH, BNB, USDC, USDT and DAI across 11 transactions. The FBI later attributed it to North Korea''s Lazarus Group/APT38. The 2-of-5 design had been publicly flagged as dangerous months earlier. The hack destroyed the bridged liquidity that underpinned Harmony''s DeFi TVL, and the team compounded the damage by proposing to mint new ONE tokens to reimburse victims — an inflationary bailout the community rejected. TVL, already sliding from its Jan 2022 peak amid the bear market, effectively went to zero.','Dead. TVL has collapsed ~100% (from $1.4B to under $0.2M) and ONE trades ~99% below its 2021 high. The Horizon hack wiped out bridged liquidity and shattered trust; the failed inflationary reimbursement plan and mass team layoffs afterward ended any recovery narrative. Harmony persists as a running chain with negligible activity — a cautionary tale about undersecured bridges, not a going concern.','dead','[{"title": "Hackers steal $100 million in crypto from Harmony''s Horizon bridge (CNBC)", "url": "https://www.cnbc.com/2022/06/24/hackers-steal-100-million-in-crypto-from-harmonys-horizon-bridge.html"}, {"title": "Harmony''s Horizon bridge exploited in $100 million crypto hack (Fortune)", "url": "https://fortune.com/2022/06/24/hackers-steal-100-million-in-crypto-from-harmony-horizon-bridge-ethereum-binance/"}, {"title": "Harmony (ONE) price, market cap and history — CoinMarketCap", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/harmony/"}]','2026-07-08 20:09:21','{"_verdict": "dead", "chain": "Harmony", "launched": "2019-06", "peak_tvl": 1411256914, "current_tvl": 198913, "drawdown_pct": 100.0, "peak_date": "2022-01-14", "founded": "Mainnet June 2019.", "founders": "Stephen Tse (ex-Apple, Google, Microsoft) and team; Harmony.one.", "raised": "~$18M IEO on Binance Launchpad (2019) plus prior private rounds (~$18M+).", "token_symbol": "ONE", "token_ath": 0.3801, "token_ath_date": "2021-10-27", "token_current": 0.005, "purpose": "A sharded proof-of-stake L1 promising low fees and fast finality, marketed for cross-chain DeFi and NFTs, connected to Ethereum/BSC via its Horizon Bridge.", "situation": "The trigger was the June 23, 2022 Horizon Bridge hack: attackers compromised the bridge''s multisig — which required only 2-of-5 signatures — and drained ~$100M across 11 transactions. The FBI later attributed it to North Korea''s Lazarus Group/APT38. The weak 2-of-5 design had been publicly flagged months earlier. The hack destroyed the bridged liquidity underpinning Harmony''s DeFi TVL, and the team''s proposal to mint new ONE to reimburse victims — an inflationary bailout — was rejected by the community. TVL, already sliding from its Jan 2022 peak, effectively went to zero.", "postmortem": "Harmony died from a security failure that was both preventable and previously warned about: a cross-chain bridge secured by a 2-of-5 multisig is a two-key single point of failure, and Lazarus exploited exactly that. Beyond the theft, the response failed — proposing to inflate the token supply to cover losses signaled the team would socialize losses onto holders, which the market punished. Harmony''s TVL had also been heavily incentive-driven and was already declining in the bear market; the hack simply removed the collateral base entirely. Large team layoffs followed, ending active development momentum.", "non_economic": "Trust collapsed on two axes: security governance (shipping a 2-of-5 bridge after public warnings) and crisis governance (the inflationary reimbursement plan that would dilute all ONE holders). The rejected bailout left victims uncompensated and holders distrustful, and subsequent layoffs signaled the core team was retreating. There was no credible plan to rebuild bridged liquidity, so builders and users left.", "lessons_learned": ["A bridge is only as secure as its signer threshold — a 2-of-5 multisig guarding nine figures is negligence, especially after public warnings.", "Responding to a hack by minting new tokens to reimburse victims socializes the loss onto all holders and usually gets rejected, deepening the crisis.", "A chain whose TVL depends on bridged assets can lose its entire economic base in a single bridge exploit."], "could_differ": "If Harmony had secured Horizon with a robust multisig (e.g. 4-of-5 or better, which it belatedly moved to) or a decentralized/light-client bridge before June 2022, the $100M would likely not have been stealable and the chain would have kept its liquidity base to decline gracefully. The fatal decision was deploying a two-key bridge over massive value despite explicit prior warnings.", "outlook": "Dead. TVL collapsed ~100% and ONE trades ~99% below its 2021 high. The Horizon hack wiped out bridged liquidity and shattered trust; the failed inflationary reimbursement plan and mass layoffs ended any recovery narrative. Harmony persists as a running chain with negligible activity.", "cause_tags": ["bridge_hack", "security_failure", "governance_failure", "mercenary_liquidity", "narrative_death"], "sources": [{"title": "Hackers steal $100 million in crypto from Harmony''s Horizon bridge (CNBC)", "url": "https://www.cnbc.com/2022/06/24/hackers-steal-100-million-in-crypto-from-harmonys-horizon-bridge.html"}, {"title": "Harmony''s Horizon bridge exploited in $100 million crypto hack (Fortune)", "url": "https://fortune.com/2022/06/24/hackers-steal-100-million-in-crypto-from-harmony-horizon-bridge-ethereum-binance/"}, {"title": "Harmony (ONE) price, market cap and history — CoinMarketCap", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/harmony/"}]}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('Heco','2020-12',2954108079,97573,100,'2021-05-10','Heco died with its parent exchange. Its TVL peaked near ~$3B in May 2021, driven overwhelmingly by MDEX liquidity-mining incentives and Huobi''s exchange funnel. Its fate turned on Huobi''s decline: China''s intensifying 2021 crackdown forced Huobi to exit the mainland (its home market), and after Justin Sun''s Tron-linked group took over Huobi (rebranded HTX) new management shifted priorities toward Tron/BTTC and left Heco behind. In November 2023 the HECO Bridge was exploited for ~$87M (attackers obtained the bridge private key) alongside a separate ~$30M HTX hot-wallet hack, gutting the last confidence in the chain. Huobi announced Heco''s shutdown on Nov 24, 2024, and the network was formally retired on Jan 15, 2025, with holders directed to redeem HRC20 assets for HTX points; TVL fell to essentially zero.','Dead. Heco has been formally wound down / declared end-of-life, its bridge deprecated, and TVL is effectively zero (~$0.1M vs a ~$3B peak). There is no chain left to revive — it exists only as a case study in exchange-chain fragility alongside the broader decline of Huobi/HTX.','dead','[{"title": "HECO Chain Announces January 2025 Closure, Users Urged to Redeem Assets (Blockonomi)", "url": "https://blockonomi.com/heco-chain-announces-january-2025-closure-users-urged-to-redeem-assets/"}, {"title": "Heco (Huobi ECO Chain) — DeFiLlama chain page", "url": "https://defillama.com/chain/Heco"}, {"title": "Huobi Token (HT) price, market cap and history — CoinMarketCap", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/huobi-token/"}]','2026-07-08 20:09:39','{"_verdict": "dead", "founded": "2020-12", "founders": "Launched by exchange Huobi (founded by Leon Li) as the Huobi ECO Chain.", "raised": "Exchange-funded by Huobi; no public raise. TVL bootstrapped by Huobi''s distribution and MDEX incentives.", "token_symbol": "HT (Huobi Token, chain gas)", "token_ath": 39.66, "token_ath_date": "2021-05-12", "token_current": 0.6, "purpose": "A low-fee EVM-compatible L1 launched by Huobi as its answer to Binance Smart Chain, using HT for gas and anchored by the MDEX DEX.", "situation": "Heco died with its parent exchange. Its TVL peaked near ~$3B in May 2021, driven overwhelmingly by MDEX liquidity-mining incentives and Huobi''s exchange funnel. Its fate turned on Huobi''s decline: China''s intensifying 2021 crackdown forced Huobi to exit the mainland (its home market), and after Justin Sun''s Tron-linked group took over Huobi (rebranded HTX) new management shifted priorities toward Tron/BTTC and left Heco behind. In November 2023 the HECO Bridge was exploited for ~$87M (attackers obtained the bridge private key) alongside a separate ~$30M HTX hot-wallet hack, gutting the last confidence in the chain. Huobi announced Heco''s shutdown on Nov 24, 2024, and the network was formally retired on Jan 15, 2025, with holders directed to redeem HRC20 assets for HTX points; TVL fell to essentially zero.", "postmortem": "Heco was a pure exchange-chain: it had no identity, distribution, or liquidity independent of Huobi, and its TVL was manufactured by MDEX incentives paid to farmers. That made it doubly fragile — it would lose rented liquidity when incentives fell, AND die outright if Huobi did. Both happened. China''s crackdown gutted Huobi''s core market, the Justin Sun takeover shifted priorities to Tron, the Nov 2023 ~$87M bridge hack destroyed remaining trust, and once the exchange was reprioritizing there was no reason to sustain Heco. It was formally retired in January 2025, stranding a chain that had once claimed ~$3B TVL.", "non_economic": "Heco''s collapse was inseparable from Huobi''s governance and trust crisis: the regulatory forced-exit from China, the opaque ownership transfer to Justin Sun''s orbit (rebrand to HTX), proof-of-reserves doubts, and a 2023 withdrawal scare all signaled the parent could not be relied upon. Heco users faced the classic exchange-chain risk — their assets'' safety depended on a centralized entity in visible distress. The formal wind-down and bridge deprecation left little ambiguity: the sponsor had walked away.", "lessons_learned": ["An exchange chain has no independent existence — it lives and dies with the exchange''s business, trust, and regulatory standing.", "TVL bootstrapped by a single DEX''s liquidity-mining incentives plus an exchange funnel is doubly rented and vanishes when either subsidy or sponsor falters.", "Regulatory dependence on one jurisdiction (China) is an existential single point of failure for a chain tied to a domestic exchange."], "could_differ": "Heco''s dependence on Huobi was structural and probably unfixable — an exchange chain is a marketing extension, not an independent network. The only survival path would have been genuine decentralization and an independent developer ecosystem early, weaning off Huobi''s funnel before the exchange''s troubles hit. It never attempted that, so when Huobi faltered under the China crackdown and the Sun takeover, Heco had no autonomous base to fall back on.", "outlook": "Dead. Heco has been formally wound down / declared end-of-life, its bridge deprecated, and TVL is effectively zero (~$0.1M vs a ~$3B peak). There is no chain left to revive — it exists only as a case study in exchange-chain fragility alongside the broader decline of Huobi/HTX.", "cause_tags": ["mercenary_tvl", "team_abandonment", "exploit_hack", "regulatory"], "sources": [{"title": "HECO Chain Announces January 2025 Closure, Users Urged to Redeem Assets (Blockonomi)", "url": "https://blockonomi.com/heco-chain-announces-january-2025-closure-users-urged-to-redeem-assets/"}, {"title": "Heco (Huobi ECO Chain) — DeFiLlama chain page", "url": "https://defillama.com/chain/Heco"}, {"title": "Huobi Token (HT) price, market cap and history — CoinMarketCap", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/huobi-token/"}], "chain": "Heco", "launched": "2020-12", "peak_tvl": 2954108079, "current_tvl": 97573, "drawdown_pct": 100.0, "peak_date": "2021-05-10"}');
INSERT INTO "dead_chains" ("chain","launched","peak_tvl","current_tvl","drawdown_pct","peak_date","why","outlook","verdict","sources","updated_at","profile") VALUES ('Celo','2020-04',1153283962,16877992,98.5,'2021-10-27','Celo''s fall was slow attrition, not a single blow-up. It peaked at ~$1.15B TVL in late 2021 on the back of its mobile-first, phone-number payments pitch and stablecoins (cUSD/cEUR), heavily boosted by liquidity incentives. As emissions faded and the 2022-23 bear market drained mercenary capital, TVL bled >98%. Its flagship real-world use case — mobile payments for the unbanked — never produced on-chain volume commensurate with the valuation, and the standalone-L1 thesis lost relevance as the ecosystem consolidated onto Ethereum L2s. In an implicit admission the independent L1 had failed to gain traction, Celo migrated to an Ethereum L2 on the OP Stack on March 26, 2025 — abandoning its own BFT consensus and validators for a centralized sequencer.','Declining. The independent Celo L1 is effectively over: it migrated to an Ethereum OP-Stack L2 in March 2025, folding into Optimism''s Superchain. CELO trades ~95% below its 2021 high and standalone-chain TVL collapsed ~98%. The mobile-payments-for-the-unbanked mission survives as a narrative under Ethereum, but the thesis that Celo could be a top independent L1 is dead; it is now a mid-tier L2 among many.','declining','[{"title": "Celo Migration to Layer-2 Network Is Done (CoinDesk)", "url": "https://www.coindesk.com/tech/2025/03/26/celo-migration-to-layer-2-network-is-done-bringing-in-new-era-for-the-blockchain"}, {"title": "Celo becomes Ethereum L2 with Optimism rollup implementation (Cointelegraph)", "url": "https://cointelegraph.com/news/celo-migrates-to-ethereum-layer-2-using-op-stack"}, {"title": "Celo (CELO) price, market cap and history — CoinMarketCap", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/celo/"}]','2026-07-08 20:10:36','{"_verdict": "declining", "chain": "Celo", "launched": "2020-04", "peak_tvl": 1153283962, "current_tvl": 16877992, "drawdown_pct": 98.5, "peak_date": "2021-10-27", "founded": "Mainnet April 2020.", "founders": "Rene Reinsberg and Marek Olszewski, via cLabs; backed by the Celo Foundation. Investors included a16z, Polychain, Coinbase Ventures.", "raised": "~$46.5M+ across private/public sales (2018–20), including a $30M raise and a 2020 CoinList token sale.", "token_symbol": "CELO", "token_ath": 10.66, "token_ath_date": "2021-08-30", "token_current": 0.3, "purpose": "A mobile-first, EVM-compatible L1 designed to bank the unbanked — send stablecoins (cUSD/cEUR) to a phone number, pay fees in stablecoins, with light-client mobile access.", "situation": "Celo''s fall was slow attrition, not a blow-up. It peaked at ~$1.15B TVL in late 2021 on its mobile-payments pitch and stablecoins, heavily boosted by liquidity incentives. As emissions faded and the 2022-23 bear drained mercenary capital, TVL bled >98%. Its flagship use case — payments for the unbanked — never produced on-chain volume matching the valuation, and the standalone-L1 thesis lost relevance as activity consolidated onto Ethereum L2s. In an implicit admission the independent L1 had failed, Celo migrated to an Ethereum OP-Stack L2 on March 26, 2025, abandoning its own consensus for a centralized sequencer.", "postmortem": "Celo had a genuinely differentiated mission but the on-chain economics never followed. Real-world mobile payments in emerging markets generate tiny fees and little TVL, so the network leaned on token incentives to look competitive with DeFi L1s — and that capital was mercenary. When incentives dried up, TVL reverted to the small level the actual usage justified. Strategically, being a standalone L1 became a liability as liquidity, tooling, and users centralized around Ethereum rollups; the 2025 L2 migration was the rational surrender of an independent-chain strategy that had lost the network-effects race.", "non_economic": "There was no scandal — the failure was competitive and strategic. cLabs and the Foundation kept shipping and retained a credible team and mission, but could not manufacture the network effects of a leading L1. The decision to dissolve the independent chain into Optimism''s Superchain preserved the technology and community while conceding that Celo could not win as a sovereign L1.", "lessons_learned": ["A worthy real-world mission (payments for the unbanked) does not generate the TVL or fees needed to sustain a top-tier L1 valuation — usage economics must match the ambition.", "Incentive-boosted TVL flatters a payments chain whose organic on-chain value is modest; it reverts when subsidies end.", "Standalone L1s increasingly cannot out-compete Ethereum''s L2 network effects; migrating to a rollup can be the rational move but confirms the independent thesis failed."], "could_differ": "Celo''s outcome is among the least tragic here — the team and mission survived by folding into Ethereum. But as an independent L1 it was always going to struggle: had it launched as an Ethereum L2 or app-chain from the start rather than a sovereign chain, it might have avoided years of subsidizing TVL to compete in a race its payments-first economics could never win.", "outlook": "Declining. The independent Celo L1 is effectively over after the March 2025 migration to an OP-Stack L2. CELO trades ~95% below its 2021 high and standalone TVL collapsed ~98%. The mobile-payments mission survives under Ethereum, but the top-independent-L1 thesis is dead.", "cause_tags": ["mercenary_liquidity", "unsustainable_yield", "lost_competition", "narrative_death"], "sources": [{"title": "Celo Migration to Layer-2 Network Is Done (CoinDesk)", "url": "https://www.coindesk.com/tech/2025/03/26/celo-migration-to-layer-2-network-is-done-bringing-in-new-era-for-the-blockchain"}, {"title": "Celo becomes Ethereum L2 with Optimism rollup implementation (Cointelegraph)", "url": "https://cointelegraph.com/news/celo-migrates-to-ethereum-layer-2-using-op-stack"}, {"title": "Celo (CELO) price, market cap and history — CoinMarketCap", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/celo/"}]}');
INSERT INTO "graveyard_meta" ("k","v","updated_at") VALUES ('trends','GRAVEYARD TRENDS ANALYSIS (13 dead/dying chains, avg drawdown ~97.9% from peak TVL, several at 99.9-100%). The single dominant cause of death is mercenary TVL: 12 of 13 chains had their headline TVL built almost entirely by yield/points/airdrop farmers rather than users, with airdrop_farming tagged on 9 chains, points_collapse on 6, and no_real_users on 7 — the recurring pattern is a locked-deposit or gas-burn incentive campaign that spikes TVL 20-2,300x, followed by a 60-99% collapse within weeks of the token unlock or claim window closing (Blast, Manta, Mode, Merlin, Zircuit, zkFair all fit this exactly). Two narratives account for most of the graveyard and both collapsed: the Bitcoin-L2/BTCFi cohort (Merlin, Bitlayer, B2, BounceBit, Corn — 5 chains) died because Bitcoin has no organic app demand to retain deposits once emissions stop, and the restaking cohort (Karak, Zircuit, BounceBit) deflated the moment EigenLayer''s EIGEN airdrop disappointed and the ''next EigenLayer'' trade unwound. Funding was no protection whatsoever — the best-capitalized names died just as hard: Karak ($48M at a >$1B valuation), Fuel ($80M+ at $1B), Manta ($60M+), Blast ($20M from Paradigm) and Taiko ($37M from Sequoia/Lightspeed) all sit at 93-99.5% drawdowns, proving elite tech and VCs cannot manufacture users (vc_dump/team_abandonment tagged on Fuel, Karak, Corn). The clearest suspected-extraction/soft-rug cases are zkFair (an anonymous ''fair launch'' that literally paid users 108M USDC in gas to farm ZKF, then subsidized dead pools) and the pre-deposit points machines like Zircuit ($3.7B farmed on L1 vs only ~$26M ever on the actual chain, a ~140x usage gap); the more honest engineering failures are Taiko, Fuel and Corn, which built real tech, lost the demand war to Base/Arbitrum, and (Corn, Karak) chose orderly wind-downs. Lifespan from launch to effective collapse was brutally short — typically 3-12 months, with most chains peaking within 1-3 months of launch and cratering by the first major token unlock, meaning the entire lifecycle of a 2024-vintage incentive-farmed L2 fit inside a single year.','2026-07-08 14:43:35');
INSERT INTO "graveyard_meta" ("k","v","updated_at") VALUES ('success_factors','Why a chain is or is not successful — a framework across the thriving, the stuck, and the dead.
INSERT INTO "graveyard_meta" ("k","v","updated_at") VALUES ('nft_pending','done','2026-07-08 15:24:14');
INSERT INTO "graveyard_meta" ("k","v","updated_at") VALUES ('nft_analysis','Across 16 notable collections spanning Ethereum, Solana, and Bitcoin Ordinals, the NFT lifecycle looks less like a durable business and more like a compressed boom-bust: the average project is ~3.9 years old but has already surrendered ~93% of its floor from all-time high, and the ~$151M these collections raised at mint seeded ~$16.4B of lifetime secondary volume (a ~108x multiple) — meaning almost all of the money made was made by traders on the secondary, not by founders at the primary. The engagement half-life is starkly bimodal: holder retention averages 77% overall, but 94% for the four still-thriving projects (Pudgy, Milady, Mad Lads, CryptoPunks) versus 72% for the faders and dead ones — and the collections that survive are the ones tethered to something exogenous to price (Pudgy''s Walmart toy brand, Mad Lads'' Backpack exchange, Milady/Punks'' cultural provenance), while pure membership/exclusivity plays decay fastest (Moonbirds fell to 49% retention, y00ts to 44%). Founder engagement is the single biggest lifespan predictor: projects die when founders leave (CloneX after Nike''s ''soft-rug'' shutdown) or exhaust goodwill through serial pivots (DeGods'' Solana→ETH→Solana→memecoin chain-hopping; y00ts euthanized via a one-way burn), whereas the survivors have founders who treat the NFT as a live product rather than a completed raise. On royalties, the enforcement collapse is the defining structural story: 7 of 16 collections (all Ordinals plus DeGods/y00ts, which pioneered 0%) never enforced royalties at all, and even the ETH blue chips saw enforcement go from mandatory to optional after Blur''s zero-fee marketplace launched in late 2022 — industry-wide monthly royalty payments cratered from a ~$269M peak in January 2022 to ~$2.4M by September 2023, a ~99% collapse. The few big royalty winners banked their money early and at scale (Yuga/BAYC ~$166M, Chiru/Azuki ~$58M, RTFKT/CloneX ~$49M — ~$281M across just four projects), but that revenue stream is now effectively dead, which is exactly why the survivors pivoted to tokens ($PENGU, $DOOD, $ANIME) and physical products ($7M in Pudgy toys dwarfed its $300K in 2023 royalties). Bitcoin Ordinals compress this entire arc into ~12–18 months with no royalty engine at all — NodeMonkes briefly flipped BAYC by market cap in March 2024 before falling ~97%, and Runestone''s 112k-wallet free fairdrop hit a $650M cap then bled to ~57% holder retention — proving that community goodwill without an economic engine decays the moment the narrative fades. The verdict: NFT projects don''t ''mature,'' they either transcend into a brand/culture asset (rare, ~25% of this sample) or fade into an illiquid floor within 3–4 years, and the categories that survive are consumer-brand and infrastructure-backed collections, not roadmap-and-exclusivity mints.','2026-07-08 15:24:10');
INSERT INTO "graveyard_meta" ("k","v","updated_at") VALUES ('infra_analysis','Decentralized storage and verification is the crypto category where real adoption is easiest to measure yet most divorced from token price — and the split between substance and hype is stark. On the storage side, two philosophies compete: Arweave''s permanent, one-time-pay endowment model ("pay once, store forever," ~7 years without a token leaving the endowment) versus Filecoin''s and Sia''s time-bounded contract/deal model where storage must be continuously re-proven and renewed; Arweave''s bet is that storage costs keep falling forever, while Filecoin''s is that paid enterprise utilization keeps rising (it reached ~36% utilization on ~3.0 EiB with ~1,110 PiB of active data and 2,491 real-world datasets by Q3 2025, its most credible adoption signal). The genuinely thriving projects have measurable usage — Filecoin (enterprise/AI/research datasets, Cornell, DPLA), Arweave (Solana archiving, AO compute), Walrus (450+ TB, Team Liquid''s 250TB, Decrypt, Allium''s institutional data within a year of its March 2025 launch on $140M funding), and IPFS (the un-tokenized but ubiquitous content-addressing standard underpinning nearly all NFT/Web3 media) — while Sia, Swarm, and especially Crust have faded to niche or near-zero token value despite functioning tech, showing that being technically sound is not the same as being needed. Data-availability is a distinct, newer category (Celestia, EigenDA, Avail) that verifies rollup data was published rather than storing documents; the tech works and Celestia holds ~50% DA share, but demand is thin and dangerously concentrated (one customer, Eclipse, was ~84% of Celestia''s blob volume and only ~0.05% of capacity is used), and every DA token is down ~98% from its ATH — strong technology, unproven demand. Document verification/notarization actually works exactly as designed — you anchor a document''s hash (never the file) to a public chain to prove it existed at a timestamp, verifiable by anyone with no trusted third party — and OpenTimestamps (free, Bitcoin-anchored, Peter Todd) is the mature de-facto standard, with bloxberg serving real academic research-provenance use and Woleet adding signer identity for enterprise e-signatures. But the critical lesson from this category is that notarization is a feature, not a fundable standalone business: Factom pioneered the pattern (Bitcoin-anchored enterprise data integrity, a DHS grant, Tim Draper backing) yet collapsed into liquidation in 2020 and migrated to Accumulate — proving the thesis technically while failing commercially because standalone demand never scaled. Net: the winners are horizontal infrastructure that other systems actually build on (IPFS as a primitive, Filecoin/Arweave/Walrus for real data, OpenTimestamps as free public-good notarization), whereas single-purpose tokens chasing storage or DA demand that hasn''t arrived — Crust, Sia, Swarm, and every DA token trading ~98% below ATH — reveal a sector where infrastructure quietly succeeds while its speculative tokens overwhelmingly do not.','2026-07-08 15:25:55');
INSERT INTO "graveyard_meta" ("k","v","updated_at") VALUES ('markets_analysis','The crypto-equity complex in mid-2026 is defined by the deflation of the treasury-company bubble that ballooned through 2025. The core mechanism — pioneered by Strategy (MSTR) and copied by Metaplanet, Twenty One (XXI), SharpLink (SBET, ETH), BitMine (BMNR, ETH), DFDV and Upexi (SOL) — was to trade at a premium to net asset value (mNAV) and use that premium to issue equity accretively and buy more coins; but in 2026 that premium has collapsed, with even MSTR''s enterprise mNAV falling below 1x in late June, which breaks the flywheel because issuing shares below NAV destroys value. The result is a bifurcation into forced sellers and survivors: Strategy formalized BTC sales via a new Digital Credit framework, Nakamoto (NAKA) sold coins and did a 1-for-40 reverse split after a ~99.5% collapse, Upexi trades below its own crypto value, and small-caps like Semler are being rolled up into consolidators like Strive (ASST) — the classic mNAV-compression / forced-seller risk playing out in real time, with only debt-free accumulators (SharpLink) or disciplined at-premium issuers (BitMine) relatively insulated. Miners face a parallel survival crunch: with average production cost near $80,000/BTC against a softer coin price, pure mining is loss-making, so the industry is pivoting en masse to AI/HPC hosting, where gross margins (~85%) dwarf mining''s (~60%). This has produced clear winners — TeraWulf (WULF, +95% YTD on $12.8B+ of Anthropic/Google-backed Fluidstack contracts), IREN (a $9.7B Microsoft GPU deal), Cipher (CIFR, ~$11.4B via AWS + Fluidstack) and Hut 8 (HUT, a $9.8B Beacon Point lease) — with CoinShares projecting 70% of listed-miner revenue will come from AI/HPC by end-2026 and cumulative miner AI deals already past $70B. The failed $9B CoreWeave acquisition of Core Scientific (shareholders voted no, betting independence was worth more) underscores how thoroughly the market now prices these ''miners'' as data-center operators rather than coin producers. Meanwhile the ETFs have become the dominant marginal buyer and the true price-setting force: BlackRock''s IBIT (~$66B) and Fidelity''s FBTC (~$14B) form a two-firm duopoly whose daily flows move the market, high-fee GBTC (1.5%) bleeds structurally toward cheaper rivals, and 2026 flows have been cyclically negative (~$5.4B BTC-ETF YTD outflows, a >$3B mid-year ETH-ETF exodus) even as staking-enabled Solana ETFs (Bitwise BSOL leading a >$1B category) attract rotation inflows on their ~7% yield. The throughline: coins now flow through Wall Street wrappers, ETF flows dictate the marginal bid, miners must sell compute to survive, and the leveraged treasury vehicles that were the loudest buyers of 2025 have become the most fragile — potential forced sellers whose mNAV discounts could amplify the next downturn.','2026-07-08 15:37:26');
INSERT INTO "graveyard_meta" ("k","v","updated_at") VALUES ('rwa_analysis','The RWA & DePIN library covers 18 projects split across tokenized treasuries, credit, tokenization infrastructure, and four DePIN verticals (compute, wireless, mapping, data). The RWA side is unambiguously thriving and institutional: BlackRock''s BUIDL (~$2.2-2.5B AUM) and Ondo lead tokenized treasuries, while Securitize ($4B+ tokenized, now NYSE-listed via a $1.25B SPAC) and Figure ($16B+ HELOCs tokenized, ~70% of on-chain private credit, Nasdaq-listed) show that tokenization has crossed into public-market legitimacy (sources: securitize.io, decrypt.co/339024, app.rwa.xyz). On-chain credit is scaling fast too — Maple Finance hit ~$5B AUM and ~$2B active loans with a 99% repayment rate, though SYRUP trades 50%+ below its peak (maple.finance, defillama.com/protocol/maple-finance). Tokenized gold quietly became a $4B+ category by late 2025, with Tether Gold (XAUT) overtaking Pax Gold (PAXG) and tokenized-gold volume surpassing major gold ETFs (coindesk.com, coingecko.com/en/categories/tokenized-gold). The DePIN side is more bifurcated: revenue-backed hardware networks like GEODNET (~$5M annualized revenue, 19,800+ RTK stations, +217% YoY) and Hivemapper (36% of the world''s roads mapped, VW/Lyft as customers) are genuinely thriving, while Filecoin, Render, io.net, Grass, and Helium are steady-but-pressured — real usage exists but tokens sit far below prior highs and many still struggle to close the gap between token emissions and actual revenue (messari.io reports, depinscan.io). The clearest structural divide is that RWA value is captured by regulated equity/fees flowing to institutions, whereas DePIN value accrues (unevenly) to tokens via buyback-and-burn mechanisms increasingly tied to real revenue — GEODNET burns 80% of data revenue and io.net''s Dec 2025 IDE redesign explicitly links burns to compute usage. Net takeaway: RWA has found durable product-market fit with TradFi capital, while DePIN''s winners are the few with verifiable third-party revenue rather than pure incentive-driven supply.','2026-07-08 17:46:36');
INSERT INTO "graveyard_meta" ("k","v","updated_at") VALUES ('geo_analysis','The geographic library covers 24 countries and 6 regions, and the clearest pattern is that grassroots adoption and institutional adoption run on almost opposite tracks. The Chainalysis 2024 index is topped by lower- and middle-income necessity markets — India (#1), Nigeria (#2), Indonesia (#3), Vietnam, Pakistan, Venezuela, Philippines and Turkey — where crypto solves real problems like inflation, weak currencies, capital controls, remittances and freelancer income; the US (#4) is the outlier at the top, but its usage is institutional and ETF-driven rather than grassroots. Stablecoins (especially USDT) have quietly become the region-defining tool across Latin America, Sub-Saharan Africa and Turkey, functioning as a de facto dollar — Venezuela and Argentina are the sharpest examples of organic crypto-dollarization. Regulation is converging globally on licensing existing crypto within traditional financial-services perimeters: the EU''s MiCA is the template (full CASP regime from Dec 2024), with the UK (FSMA regime, live ~2027), Australia (2026 law), Brazil (strict 2026 VASP/FX regime), Turkey, Vietnam and Kenya all building comparable frameworks. Sovereign Bitcoin holdings became a real 2025 theme: the US Strategic Bitcoin Reserve (~328,000 BTC, the largest state holder), Pakistan''s announced reserve, and El Salvador''s ~6,250 BTC — even as El Salvador simultaneously rolled back Bitcoin''s legal-tender status under IMF pressure, and Bhutan sold ~70% of its mined stash. China remains the major prohibitionist (near-total ban since 2021) while Hong Kong runs the opposite experiment with a licensed regime. Politically, crypto has become a statecraft tool — Ukraine used it for transparent wartime fundraising while Russia pivoted to state-controlled rails for sanctions evasion — and a source of scandal, from Argentina''s LIBRA collapse to Venezuela''s failed Petro. Overall the data shows a maturing landscape: adoption is highest where economies are weakest, regulation is hardening almost everywhere, and nation-states are shifting from banning crypto to holding, mining and weaponizing it.','2026-07-08 17:48:47');
INSERT INTO "graveyard_meta" ("k","v","updated_at") VALUES ('power_rankings','{"updated":"2026-07-08","countries":[{"rank":1,"name":"United States","total":90.6,"usage":90,"policy":85,"institutional":99,"innovation":92,"government":98,"rationale":"#2 on Chainalysis 2025 index with the largest institutional market (spot BTC/ETH ETFs), a federal stablecoin law (GENIUS Act) and the world''s largest sovereign BTC reserve (~328,372 BTC). Only missing piece is final market-structure legislation (CLARITY Act still pending).","sources":[{"title":"Chainalysis 2025 Global Crypto Adoption Index","url":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2025-global-crypto-adoption-index/"},{"title":"U.S. Strategic Bitcoin Reserve - Wikipedia","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._Strategic_Bitcoin_Reserve"}]},{"rank":2,"name":"United Arab Emirates","total":82.15,"usage":74,"policy":95,"institutional":88,"innovation":85,"government":80,"rationale":"Home to the world''s first dedicated crypto regulator (Dubai''s VARA) plus ADGM/DIFC free-zone regimes, zero income tax and heavy RWA-tokenization activity that has drawn major exchanges and funds to relocate. State-linked entities are active investors even without a declared sovereign reserve.","sources":[{"title":"VARA (Virtual Assets Regulatory Authority)","url":"https://www.vara.ae/en/"},{"title":"UAE Crypto Regulations 2025 Recap - Forbes","url":"https://www.forbes.com/sites/irinaheaver/2025/12/29/uae-crypto-regulations-2025-recap-vara-rwa-tokens-and-2026-outlook/"}]},{"rank":3,"name":"Singapore","total":78.05,"usage":62,"policy":92,"institutional":90,"innovation":88,"government":72,"rationale":"Small retail footprint (75th on Chainalysis) but an outsized institutional and corporate hub under MAS''s clear-but-strict Payment Services Act, stablecoin rules and Project Guardian tokenization pilots. Deliberately curbs retail speculation while attracting exchanges, funds and token projects.","sources":[{"title":"MAS crypto and digital token regulation","url":"https://www.mas.gov.sg/news?focus_areas=Crypto+Tokens&focus_areas=Digital+Currencies"},{"title":"Singapore crypto regulations - Sumsub","url":"https://sumsub.com/blog/singapore-crypto-regulations-all-you-need-to-know/"}]},{"rank":4,"name":"United Kingdom","total":77.4,"usage":72,"policy":86,"institutional":85,"innovation":74,"government":68,"rationale":"11th on Chainalysis 2025 with a large, mature institutional market and a phased FSMA-based regime (FCA final rules Jun 2026, full regime Oct 2027) plus a stablecoin framework. Holds ~61,000 seized BTC but has no strategic reserve.","sources":[{"title":"FCA new regime for cryptoasset regulation","url":"https://www.fca.org.uk/firms/new-regime-cryptoasset-regulation"},{"title":"Chainalysis 2025 Global Crypto Adoption Index","url":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2025-global-crypto-adoption-index/"}]},{"rank":5,"name":"South Korea","total":75.5,"usage":82,"policy":78,"institutional":70,"innovation":72,"government":66,"rationale":"Exceptionally active retail trading market (Upbit/Bithumb, ''kimchi premium'') now regulated under the Virtual Asset User Protection Act (Jul 2024), with institutional access and spot ETFs being liberalized. Home of Terra/LUNA; strong ecosystem but no state holdings.","sources":[{"title":"South Korea crypto and Travel Rule regulations - Sumsub","url":"https://sumsub.com/blog/south-korea-crypto-and-travel-rule-regulations-all-you-need-to-know/"},{"title":"Chainalysis 2024 Global Crypto Adoption Index","url":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/"}]},{"rank":6,"name":"Brazil","total":75.3,"usage":84,"policy":80,"institutional":72,"innovation":70,"government":58,"rationale":"Rose to 5th on the Chainalysis 2025 index with ~25M users and a stablecoin-dominated market, now under one of the world''s strictest VASP frameworks (BCB licensing from Feb 2026) plus an advanced Drex CBDC. A national BTC reserve (RESBit) is proposed but not enacted.","sources":[{"title":"Brazil crypto-asset regulatory framework - Chainalysis","url":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/brazil-crypto-asset-regulatory-framework-2025/"},{"title":"Chainalysis 2025 Global Crypto Adoption Index","url":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2025-global-crypto-adoption-index/"}]},{"rank":7,"name":"India","total":74.9,"usage":99,"policy":52,"institutional":68,"innovation":70,"government":48,"rationale":"#1 on the Chainalysis 2025 index ($338B received, 99% YoY growth) with unmatched grassroots and institutional-sized activity, but held back by a punitive tax regime (30% + 1% TDS + 18% GST) and no comprehensive crypto law. Government remains cautious and favors a digital rupee CBDC.","sources":[{"title":"Chainalysis 2025 Global Crypto Adoption Index","url":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2025-global-crypto-adoption-index/"},{"title":"Cryptocurrency Taxation Guide - ClearTax","url":"https://cleartax.in/s/cryptocurrency-taxation-guide"}]},{"rank":8,"name":"Germany","total":73.35,"usage":68,"policy":85,"institutional":80,"innovation":66,"government":58,"rationale":"Largest EU economy and a leading MiCA-licensing hub under BaFin, with an investor-friendly tax rule (holdings sold after 12 months are tax-free) and strong institutional custody. Reputation dinged by Saxony''s criticized 2024 sell-off of ~50,000 seized BTC.","sources":[{"title":"ESMA - Markets in Crypto-Assets Regulation (MiCA)","url":"https://www.esma.europa.eu/esmas-activities/digital-finance-and-innovation/markets-crypto-assets-regulation-mica"},{"title":"Germany blockchain and crypto laws - Global Legal Insights","url":"https://www.globallegalinsights.com/practice-areas/blockchain-cryptocurrency-laws-and-regulations/germany/"}]},{"rank":9,"name":"Japan","total":72.55,"usage":66,"policy":83,"institutional":78,"innovation":68,"government":60,"rationale":"19th on Chainalysis 2025; one of the earliest regulated markets under the Payment Services Act with strong post-Mt.Gox custody rules and stablecoin regulation, now moving oversight toward securities law (FIEA) with a planned tax cut and spot ETFs. Conservative but institutionally deep.","sources":[{"title":"Japan plans major shift as crypto moves to securities law","url":"https://www.tradingview.com/news/cointelegraph:6d9dc9bce094b:0-japan-plans-major-shift-as-crypto-moves-from-payments-to-securities-law/"},{"title":"Chainalysis 2025 Global Crypto Adoption Index","url":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2025-global-crypto-adoption-index/"}]},{"rank":10,"name":"Canada","total":71.25,"usage":70,"policy":80,"institutional":82,"innovation":62,"government":56,"rationale":"Mature investment market that pioneered North America''s first spot Bitcoin/Ether ETFs (2021) and first Solana/XRP spot ETFs (2025), with clear CSA/FINTRAC registration rules and incoming CARF tax reporting. Strong institutional penetration but no state holdings.","sources":[{"title":"Canada blockchain and crypto laws - Global Legal Insights","url":"https://www.globallegalinsights.com/practice-areas/blockchain-cryptocurrency-laws-and-regulations/canada/"},{"title":"Chainalysis 2024 Global Crypto Adoption Index","url":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/"}]},{"rank":11,"name":"Pakistan","total":68.65,"usage":88,"policy":55,"institutional":48,"innovation":58,"government":80,"rationale":"#3 on the Chainalysis 2025 index with a huge grassroots base (40M+ wallets), plus a dramatic 2025 state U-turn: a Crypto Council, a new Digital Assets Authority, 2,000 MW allocated for mining, and an announced Strategic Bitcoin Reserve of seized BTC. Framework is still nascent and must satisfy the IMF.","sources":[{"title":"Chainalysis 2025 Global Crypto Adoption Index","url":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2025-global-crypto-adoption-index/"},{"title":"Pakistan to establish a Bitcoin strategic reserve - CoinDesk","url":"https://www.coindesk.com/policy/2025/05/28/pakistan-to-establish-a-bitcoin-strategic-reserve-allocate-2000-megawatts-of-energy-for-crypto-mining"}]},{"rank":12,"name":"Australia","total":68.5,"usage":60,"policy":78,"institutional":72,"innovation":62,"government":60,"rationale":"39th on Chainalysis 2024 with an affluent retail/SMSF base, now with its first comprehensive framework (Digital Assets Bill passed Apr 2026 requiring ASIC AFS licensing) and expanded AUSTRAC scope plus stablecoin rules. Pragmatic mainstream market, no state holdings.","sources":[{"title":"Australia passes crypto licensing bill - CoinDesk","url":"https://www.coindesk.com/policy/2026/04/01/australia-passes-crypto-licensing-bill-as-ausd24-billion-opportunity-comes-into-focus"},{"title":"Chainalysis 2024 Global Crypto Adoption Index","url":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/"}]},{"rank":13,"name":"Vietnam","total":68.35,"usage":90,"policy":58,"institutional":50,"innovation":66,"government":52,"rationale":"Top-4 on the Chainalysis 2025 index (~18% ownership) and a play-to-earn origin story (Axie Infinity), with a landmark 2025 law recognizing crypto as legal property and a controlled 2025-2030 exchange-licensing pilot. Payments remain illegal and the licensed regime is only just starting.","sources":[{"title":"Vietnam formally recognises digital assets under new law - Chambers","url":"https://chambers.com/articles/vietnam-formally-recognises-digital-assets-under-new-law"},{"title":"Chainalysis 2025 Global Crypto Adoption Index","url":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2025-global-crypto-adoption-index/"}]},{"rank":14,"name":"El Salvador","total":63.65,"usage":42,"policy":62,"institutional":50,"innovation":60,"government":95,"rationale":"Government-led rather than grassroots: the first country to make Bitcoin legal tender (2021) and holder of a ~6,250-7,500 BTC Strategic Bitcoin Reserve, but forced under a 2024 IMF deal to reverse mandatory acceptance and end BTC''s ''currency'' status. Real everyday usage stayed low.","sources":[{"title":"Bitcoin in El Salvador - Wikipedia","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bitcoin_in_El_Salvador"},{"title":"El Salvador''s Bitcoin Law changes to secure IMF funding - Forbes","url":"https://www.forbes.com/sites/digital-assets/2025/02/28/el-salvadors-bitcoin-law-changes-to-secure-imf-funding/"}]},{"rank":15,"name":"Turkey","total":63.6,"usage":80,"policy":58,"institutional":50,"innovation":52,"government":48,"rationale":"World''s 4th-largest crypto market (~11th on Chainalysis) driven by lira collapse and inflation, now regulated under a 2024 Capital Markets Law licensing regime (CMB) with 80+ firms applying. Crypto payments are banned and the country is working to exit the FATF grey list.","sources":[{"title":"Crypto regulations in Turkey - Sumsub","url":"https://sumsub.com/blog/crypto-regulations-turkey/"},{"title":"Chainalysis 2024 Global Crypto Adoption Index","url":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/"}]},{"rank":16,"name":"Nigeria","total":63.4,"usage":86,"policy":56,"institutional":44,"innovation":54,"government":48,"rationale":"#6 on the Chainalysis 2025 index and Africa''s largest market, driven by naira devaluation, P2P and stablecoin dollar access. After a 2021 bank ban and 2023 reversal, the SEC now licenses local VASPs (first licenses 2025) and the 2025 Investments & Securities Act recognizes crypto assets.","sources":[{"title":"Chainalysis 2025 Global Crypto Adoption Index","url":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2025-global-crypto-adoption-index/"},{"title":"Overview of cryptocurrency regulatory landscape in Nigeria - IBA","url":"https://www.ibanet.org/overview-of-cryptocurrency-regulatory-landscape-nigeria"}]},{"rank":17,"name":"Indonesia","total":62.75,"usage":82,"policy":58,"institutional":48,"innovation":48,"government":50,"rationale":"#3 on the Chainalysis 2024 index with the region''s highest value received (~$157B) and ~200% YoY growth, with oversight moving to financial authority OJK in 2025. ICO issuance is banned and crypto cannot be used for payments, limiting domestic project origination.","sources":[{"title":"Chainalysis 2024 Global Crypto Adoption Index","url":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/"},{"title":"Legality of cryptocurrency by country - Wikipedia","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Legality_of_cryptocurrency_by_country_or_territory"}]},{"rank":18,"name":"Ukraine","total":62.5,"usage":80,"policy":54,"institutional":42,"innovation":56,"government":58,"rationale":"Top-10 grassroots adoption (1st when population-adjusted, ~$206B received) and a global model for transparent wartime crypto fundraising, with a 2022 virtual-assets law and a 2025 MiCA-aligned framework in progress. A national BTC reserve is under consideration but not yet enacted.","sources":[{"title":"Chainalysis 2025 Global Crypto Adoption Index","url":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2025-global-crypto-adoption-index/"},{"title":"Ukraine crypto legalization 2025 - Cointelegraph","url":"https://cointelegraph.com/news/ukraine-crypto-legalization-2025-no-tax-breaks"}]},{"rank":19,"name":"Russia","total":61.15,"usage":74,"policy":48,"institutional":44,"innovation":60,"government":72,"rationale":"Climbed to a top-6 Chainalysis position by using crypto for sanctions-driven cross-border trade, with legalized mining (2024) and an experimental cross-border settlement regime, plus ~14% of global BTC hashrate. Domestic payments remain banned and the state pursues crypto for sanctions evasion rather than open markets.","sources":[{"title":"Chainalysis 2024 Global Crypto Adoption Index","url":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/"},{"title":"Blockchain statecraft: Russia''s war for financial sovereignty - Harvard","url":"https://daviscenter.fas.harvard.edu/insights/blockchain-statecraft-russias-secret-war-financial-sovereignty"}]},{"rank":20,"name":"Argentina","total":60.5,"usage":80,"policy":54,"institutional":40,"innovation":50,"government":56,"rationale":"2nd in Latin America (~$91B, stablecoins as a de facto parallel currency) with a pro-crypto President Milei and a 2024 VASP registry law plus a tokenized-securities sandbox. Credibility was dented by the Feb 2025 $LIBRA memecoin scandal that Milei promoted.","sources":[{"title":"Chainalysis 2024 Global Crypto Adoption Index","url":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/"},{"title":"Argentina''s $46 billion crypto scandal - Forbes","url":"https://www.forbes.com/sites/digital-assets/2025/02/24/argentinas-46-billion-crypto-scandal-largest-ever-crypto-theft/"}]},{"rank":21,"name":"Philippines","total":59.05,"usage":76,"policy":58,"institutional":42,"innovation":50,"government":48,"rationale":"Top-10 grassroots adoption (~10% of population) driven by remittances and a strong play-to-earn culture (Axie Infinity boom), regulated via BSP VASP licensing and incoming SEC CASP rules. Recurring Ponzi/scam problems weigh on the market.","sources":[{"title":"Chainalysis 2024 Global Crypto Adoption Index","url":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/"},{"title":"Legality of cryptocurrency by country - Wikipedia","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Legality_of_cryptocurrency_by_country_or_territory"}]},{"rank":22,"name":"Kenya","total":57.55,"usage":74,"policy":54,"institutional":38,"innovation":50,"government":48,"rationale":"Among Africa''s top markets (1st in P2P volume) building on M-Pesa mobile-money fluency, now formalizing via the 2025 VASP Act (CBK registration) and a 2025 tax pivot that cut trader burden ~96%. Still early on licensing and no state holdings.","sources":[{"title":"Chainalysis 2024 Global Crypto Adoption Index","url":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/"},{"title":"Kenya''s new crypto tax rules - The Star","url":"https://www.the-star.co.ke/business/2025-11-03-kenyas-new-crypto-tax-rules-shift-focus-from-transactions-to-platform-fees"}]},{"rank":23,"name":"Venezuela","total":56.7,"usage":82,"policy":38,"institutional":36,"innovation":44,"government":58,"rationale":"Top-tier grassroots use out of necessity (~$44.6B volume, USDT as de facto currency amid ~229% inflation) and state use of stablecoins to settle oil sales under sanctions. The regulator Sunacrip was gutted by scandal, the Petro was scrapped, and there is no coherent framework.","sources":[{"title":"Chainalysis 2024 Global Crypto Adoption Index","url":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/"},{"title":"How Venezuela uses crypto to sell oil - Atlantic Council","url":"https://www.atlanticcouncil.org/blogs/new-atlanticist/how-venezuela-uses-crypto-to-sell-oil-and-what-the-us-should-do-about-it/"}]},{"rank":24,"name":"China","total":52.4,"usage":60,"policy":25,"institutional":55,"innovation":72,"government":55,"rationale":"Officially banned on the mainland (all crypto transactions illegal since 2021) yet ~20th on Chainalysis via grey-market OTC (~$75B) and still ~14% of global BTC hashrate, with an e-CNY CBDC and a large seized-BTC stash. Hong Kong''s separate licensed VASP/stablecoin regime provides the innovation and institutional on-ramp.","sources":[{"title":"Chainalysis 2024 Global Crypto Adoption Index","url":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/"},{"title":"Legality of cryptocurrency by country - Wikipedia","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Legality_of_cryptocurrency_by_country_or_territory"}]}]}','2026-07-08 19:09:24');
INSERT INTO "graveyard_meta" ("k","v","updated_at") VALUES ('traces_analysis','Across these seven investigations a consistent laundering grammar emerges: consolidate stolen assets into a single unfreezable base asset (ETH, or BTC), fragment across dozens-to-thousands of intermediary wallets, then push through an obfuscation layer before touching a fiat off-ramp. The obfuscation layer has evolved with sanctions pressure — Tornado Cash was the default mixer for the DPRK/Lazarus bridge hacks (Ronin >$468M, Harmony ~98%), but after OFAC sanctioned it in August 2022 actors migrated to successors (Railgun for Harmony, Sinbad — a rebrand of sanctioned Blender — in the FTX trail) and increasingly to permissionless cross-chain swap routers. Cross-chain bridging is now the dominant tool: THORChain converted ~83% of the Bybit haul to BTC in ten days, RenBridge and THORSwap moved the FTX funds, and pig-butchering rings chain-hop ETH→TRON to reach cheaper USDT rails. State-sponsored Lazarus cases (Bybit, Ronin, Harmony) are effectively unrecoverable because the actor is beyond jurisdiction and reaches decentralized infrastructure that cannot be subpoenaed — there enforcement is limited to OFAC address designations and reactive exchange freezes. By contrast, funds are actually recovered when a centralized chokepoint exists: Euler''s negotiated ~100% return (a lone actor who never cashed out), and the $225M pig-butchering seizure, which succeeded only because Tether can freeze centrally-issued USDT and OKX voluntarily shared account data. The Southeast-Asian fraud ecosystem''s reliance on the Huione/OTC guarantee marketplaces and USDT is simultaneously its scaling engine and its exposure, whereas mixer-plus-DEX laundering by sophisticated hackers leaves far fewer chokepoints. The through-line for a Scam Tracker: on-chain forensics reliably identifies the path, but recovery depends almost entirely on whether the path terminates at a compliant, freezable, or subpoena-able entity — which is why sanctioned mixers, decentralized bridges, and offshore compounds remain the persistent dead ends.','2026-07-08 19:15:31');
INSERT INTO "graveyard_meta" ("k","v","updated_at") VALUES ('us_federal','{"analysis":"Federal US crypto policy shifted decisively pro-industry in 2025-2026, but only one pillar is settled law. The GENIUS Act, signed July 18, 2025, is the first major US crypto statute, creating a federal framework for payment stablecoins with 100% liquid reserve backing, monthly reserve disclosures, and an explicit carve-out that payment stablecoins are neither securities nor commodities — divesting the SEC and CFTC of jurisdiction over them. Broader market-structure reform remains unfinished: the House passed the CLARITY Act (H.R. 3633) in July 2025, which would give the CFTC exclusive jurisdiction over digital-commodity spot markets while the SEC keeps investment-contract assets, but the Senate has not passed it. Instead the Senate is working competing drafts — the Banking Committee''s Responsible Financial Innovation Act and the Agriculture Committee''s Digital Commodity Intermediaries Act (S. 3755) — which must be reconciled with each other and with the House bill, with stablecoin-yield rules a major sticking point. President Trump''s Executive Order 14233 (March 6, 2025) established a Strategic Bitcoin Reserve capitalized with forfeited government BTC that cannot be sold, plus a broader Digital Asset Stockpile. The reserve rests on an executive order rather than statute, so codification bills (the BITCOIN Act / S.954 and the 2026 American Reserve Modernization Act) aim to lock in the no-sale policy and authorize purchases, but none has passed. The through-line: stablecoins are now governed by settled federal law, while both the market-structure regime and the Bitcoin reserve''s permanence still depend on Senate action, with the November 2026 midterms acting as an effective deadline.","bills":[{"name":"GENIUS Act (S.1582)","status":"Enacted — signed into law July 18, 2025; effective by Jan 18, 2027 (or 120 days after final rulemaking)","summary":"First US federal framework for payment stablecoins: mandates 100% liquid reserve backing (USD/short-term Treasuries), monthly public reserve disclosures, and licensing/supervision; clarifies payment stablecoins are neither securities nor commodities, removing SEC/CFTC jurisdiction over them.","url":"https://www.congress.gov/bill/119th-congress/senate-bill/1582/text"},{"name":"CLARITY Act / Digital Asset Market Clarity Act (H.R.3633)","status":"Passed House July 17, 2025 (294-134); pending in Senate — referred to Banking Committee, reported with amendment June 2026; not yet law","summary":"Crypto market-structure bill splitting assets into digital commodities, investment-contract assets, and payment stablecoins; grants the CFTC exclusive jurisdiction over digital-commodity spot markets while the SEC retains investment-contract assets.","url":"https://www.congress.gov/bill/119th-congress/house-bill/3633/text"},{"name":"Digital Commodity Intermediaries Act (S.3755)","status":"Advanced by Senate Agriculture Committee Jan 29, 2026 (party-line); pending","summary":"Senate Agriculture Committee''s market-structure vehicle building on CLARITY; defines ''digital commodities'' and creates a CFTC-run registration/compliance regime for digital-asset intermediaries; must be reconciled with the Senate Banking draft and the House CLARITY Act.","url":"https://www.consumerfinancialserviceslawmonitor.com/2026/02/digital-commodity-intermediaries-act-clears-senate-ag-committee/"},{"name":"Executive Order 14233 — Strategic Bitcoin Reserve & US Digital Asset Stockpile","status":"In force since March 6, 2025 (90 FR 11789); not codified in statute","summary":"Establishes a Strategic Bitcoin Reserve capitalized with forfeited government BTC that cannot be sold, plus a Digital Asset Stockpile; directs Treasury/Commerce to pursue budget-neutral acquisition strategies. US holdings ~328,000 BTC, the largest known sovereign stash; operational rollout slowed by Treasury-Commerce custody disputes.","url":"https://www.whitehouse.gov/presidential-actions/2025/03/establishment-of-the-strategic-bitcoin-reserve-and-united-states-digital-asset-stockpile/"},{"name":"BITCOIN Act (S.954) / American Reserve Modernization Act (ARMA)","status":"Introduced; neither passed as of mid-2026","summary":"Codification bills to enshrine the Strategic Bitcoin Reserve in statute: the BITCOIN Act would authorize acquiring up to 1M BTC; ARMA (introduced May 2026) would impose a 20-year mandatory hold and authorize up to 200,000 BTC/year of open-market purchases over five years.","url":"https://www.congress.gov/bill/119th-congress/senate-bill/954"}]}','2026-07-08 19:20:34');
INSERT INTO "graveyard_meta" ("k","v","updated_at") VALUES ('stablecoin_analysis','The stablecoin market as of mid-2026 remains a two-horse race at the top — Tether (USDT, ~$183B) and Circle''s USDC (~$74B) together dominate, splitting the market between offshore/emerging-market liquidity (USDT, opaque, BVI-domiciled, Tron-heavy) and the regulated institutional standard (USDC, MiCA- and GENIUS-Act-aligned, NYSE-listed, Deloitte-attested). Below them, three distinct categories have matured: decentralized crypto-overcollateralized coins (USDS/DAI from Sky, GHO from Aave) that are increasingly propped up by USDC and tokenized-Treasury (RWA) backing, blurring their ''decentralization''; institutional RWA/yield-bearing tokens (BlackRock''s BUIDL, Circle''s USYC, Ondo''s USDY, Figure''s SEC-registered YLDS, Gate''s GUSD) that are really tokenized money-market funds or securities rather than $1 payment coins; and higher-risk synthetic dollars (Ethena''s USDe, Falcon''s USDf, Solstice''s USX, Apyx''s apxUSD) whose pegs depend on funding rates, trading strategies, or even Bitcoin-treasury preferred equity — several of which (USX to ~$0.10 in Dec 2025, apxUSD to ~$0.83 in mid-2026) have already de-pegged, proving that over-100% collateralization does not guarantee stability when secondary-market liquidity or collateral correlation fails. The 2025 US GENIUS Act and the EU''s MiCA are the defining regulatory forces, rewarding licensed, cash/Treasury-backed, non-yield payment coins (USDC, PYUSD, RLUSD, USDG, EURC) while pushing yield-bearing designs into securities frameworks (YLDS) and excluding non-compliant offshore issuers; notably Tether declined MiCA and launched a separate onshore USAT instead. Non-USD stablecoins remain a small but strategically important and fast-growing frontier: MiCA has catalyzed compliant euro coins (Circle''s EURC and Monerium''s IBAN-native EURe), while Asia-Pacific leads on real-world adoption — StraitsX''s MAS-licensed XSGD sees genuine merchant use, Japan''s JPYC became the first FSA-approved yen coin, and Australia fields two AFSL-regulated coins (Novatti''s AUDD, Forte''s AUDF). Emerging-market coins reveal a recurring paradox: in high-inflation economies, local-currency stablecoins like Turkey''s TRYB, Brazil''s BRZ, Indonesia''s IDRT, South Africa''s ZARP, and Mexico''s CETES-backed MXNe often act as on-ramps OUT of the local currency into USD stables rather than as durable stores of value, so their demand tracks FX stress more than product merit. The clearest risk signals across the set are reserve opacity (USDT, A7A5, TUSD), sanctions/compliance exposure (Russia''s ruble A7A5), single-venue or ecosystem concentration (FDUSD on Binance, pUSD on Polymarket, USDGO on OSL, Gate''s GUSD), and structurally novel collateral (USDe funding rates, apxUSD preferred equity) — while the strongest positioned are the fully-audited, licensed, cash/Treasury-backed payment coins (USDC, PYUSD, RLUSD, EURC) and the institutional tokenized-Treasury funds (BUIDL, USYC). Overall trajectory: consolidation toward regulated, transparent, GENIUS/MiCA-compliant issuers for payments; a parallel institutional boom in tokenized-Treasury/yield products; a persistent but riskier synthetic-dollar frontier chasing yield; and a slow, regulation-gated expansion of credible non-USD coins led by APAC (Singapore, Japan, Australia) and LatAm (Brazil, Mexico).','2026-07-08 19:29:07');
INSERT INTO "mid_chains" ("chain","launched","tvl","verdict","why_stuck","outlook","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('NEAR','2020-04',147778165,'pivoting','NEAR raised over $500M and once pitched itself as a mass-consumer, sharded L1, but its DeFi TVL fell from ~$350M (Dec 2024) to ~$150M and it never produced a category-defining app. It has re-centered its entire identity on an AI + chain-abstraction (''Intents'') narrative, but chain abstraction is now commoditized by Solana and Ethereum tooling, and the token sits ~90% below its ATH.','BULL: Intents volume sustainably clears the ~$177M/day ''deflationary threshold'', making NEAR net-deflationary while real AI agents transact on-chain — trigger is a breakout agentic app driving organic (not incentivized) Intents flow. BASE (most likely): the pivot keeps shipping and Intents grows, but volume stays below the deflationary threshold, so buybacks are symbolic and NEAR trades as a mid-cap AI-narrative beta with the token range-bound. BEAR: chain abstraction fully commoditizes, an agentic killer app never materializes on NEAR specifically, and cross-chain exploits erode trust. Top risks: (1) narrative differentiation window closing as Solana/ETH ship competing abstraction; (2) inherited security surface of 25+ connected chains. Watch: daily Intents volume vs the $177M deflationary line, count of AI agents actually transacting, and v2.13 (dynamic resharding + post-quantum signing, June 2026). Base case is most likely — execution is real but the deflationary/agentic thesis is unproven at scale.','{"founded":"2020-04","founders":"Illia Polosukhin and Alexander Skidanov (NEAR.ai, 2017)","raised":"~$533M across rounds; investors incl. a16z, Pantera, Coinbase Ventures, Three Arrows, Tiger Global, FTX/Alameda ($150M in 2022)","token_symbol":"NEAR","token_ath":20.44,"token_ath_date":"2022-01","token_current":1.87,"purpose":"A sharded, developer- and user-friendly proof-of-stake L1 for mainstream consumer apps (''Nightshade'' sharding, human-readable accounts), now repositioned as the orchestration/execution layer for the ''Agentic Web'' and user-owned AI","situation":"NEAR is pivoting because its original mass-consumer L1 thesis stalled (DeFi TVL halved, no killer app), so it renamed its strategy ''Blockchain for AI'' and bet everything on NEAR Intents (chain abstraction) + NEAR AI. The pivot is shipping and gaining traction: Intents crossed ~$10B all-time swap volume by early 2026 (15.7M+ swaps, $17M+ fees), and on 23 Feb 2026 a fee-conversion mechanism activated routing 100% of Intents fees into open-market NEAR buybacks. What makes it unique vs Solana/ETH abstraction layers is the vertically-integrated AI stack (NEAR AI Cloud, PII anonymization, Brave/Venice/NVIDIA Inception partnerships) settling agent transactions natively — though that differentiation window is narrowing as rivals copy chain abstraction.","whats_working":"~2,500 monthly active devs, 50M+ MAU, NEAR Intents at ~$10B cumulative volume and fastest-growing cross-chain protocol of 2025, live AI product suite (NEAR AI Cloud, Confidential Treasuries), inflation cut from 5% to 2.5% via the ''Halving Upgrade'', fee-to-buyback mechanism live","whats_not":"No killer app; TVL more than halved from late-2024; chain-abstraction narrative being commoditized by Solana/ETH tooling; stark testnet-vs-mainnet TPS credibility gap (1M TPS testnet vs ~63 TPS live mainnet); cross-chain failure surface (April 2026 Litecoin zero-day cost ~$600K via Intents); high-profile exits (Arthur Hayes dumped his entire NEAR stake June 2026)","non_economic":"X/social sentiment spiked with the AI-agent narrative — token ran ~115% over 90 days into late May 2026 on announcement-driven volume (>$1B daily peaks) — but it''s fragile and influencer-sensitive (price fell sharply after Arthur Hayes'' June 2026 exit). Developer activity is a genuine strength: continuous Nearcore/Intents commits, new ecosystem apps (MemDex AI portfolio dashboard, April 2026), and credibility partnerships (Brave adopting NEAR AI Cloud, NVIDIA Inception membership). Media coverage has shifted from ''Solana killer'' framing to ''AI infrastructure'' framing, which is favorable but crowded.","outlook":"BULL: Intents volume sustainably clears the ~$177M/day ''deflationary threshold'', making NEAR net-deflationary while real AI agents transact on-chain — trigger is a breakout agentic app driving organic (not incentivized) Intents flow. BASE (most likely): the pivot keeps shipping and Intents grows, but volume stays below the deflationary threshold, so buybacks are symbolic and NEAR trades as a mid-cap AI-narrative beta with the token range-bound. BEAR: chain abstraction fully commoditizes, an agentic killer app never materializes on NEAR specifically, and cross-chain exploits erode trust. Top risks: (1) narrative differentiation window closing as Solana/ETH ship competing abstraction; (2) inherited security surface of 25+ connected chains. Watch: daily Intents volume vs the $177M deflationary line, count of AI agents actually transacting, and v2.13 (dynamic resharding + post-quantum signing, June 2026). Base case is most likely — execution is real but the deflationary/agentic thesis is unproven at scale.","success_factors_missing":["no_killer_app","lost_narrative","unclear_positioning"],"sources":[{"title":"NEAR Intents Achieves $10B in Swap Volume as Adoption Grows","url":"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/near-intents-achieves-10b-swap-183636390.html"},{"title":"NEAR Protocol''s 2026 Roadmap: AI-Intents and Value Capture (AInvest)","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/protocol-2026-roadmap-redefining-layer-1-capture-ai-intents-scalable-infrastructure-2601/"},{"title":"NEAR Protocol targets AI-driven commerce with new products and tokenomics improvements (Crypto Briefing)","url":"https://cryptobriefing.com/near-protocol-ai-commerce-tokenomics/"},{"title":"NEAR Protocol Overview in 2026: AI Infrastructure, Intents (ChangeNOW)","url":"https://changenow.io/blog/near-protocol-overview"}]}','[{"title":"NEAR Intents Achieves $10B in Swap Volume as Adoption Grows","url":"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/near-intents-achieves-10b-swap-183636390.html"},{"title":"NEAR Protocol''s 2026 Roadmap: AI-Intents and Value Capture (AInvest)","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/protocol-2026-roadmap-redefining-layer-1-capture-ai-intents-scalable-infrastructure-2601/"},{"title":"NEAR Protocol targets AI-driven commerce with new products and tokenomics improvements (Crypto Briefing)","url":"https://cryptobriefing.com/near-protocol-ai-commerce-tokenomics/"},{"title":"NEAR Protocol Overview in 2026: AI Infrastructure, Intents (ChangeNOW)","url":"https://changenow.io/blog/near-protocol-overview"}]','2026-07-08 15:06:50');
INSERT INTO "mid_chains" ("chain","launched","tvl","verdict","why_stuck","outlook","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('Aptos','2022-10',107615389,'drifting','Aptos raised ~$400M at a $4B valuation on the Meta/Diem pedigree and Move language, but has been decisively out-competed by its Move sibling Sui, which carries ~2.6x its DeFi TVL and 2x its developer count. The token is ~97% off its ATH, weekly active devs fell from 108 to 74, and it lacks a flagship protocol to anchor the ecosystem, receiving mostly spillover capital rather than being a primary destination.','BULL: institutional RWA compounds (RWA TVL already ~$719M-$1.2B) and Aptos becomes the compliant settlement layer for tokenized TradFi assets — trigger is a major asset manager making Aptos its primary tokenization venue plus the deflationary burn biting. BASE (most likely): Aptos stays a technically credible, institutionally-backed L1 that keeps winning RWA headlines but loses the broader ecosystem/dev battle to Sui, trading as a mid-cap with high daily addresses but thin DeFi. BEAR: RWA deposits stay parked and non-generative, developers keep defecting to Sui, and emissions overwhelm negligible fee revenue. Top risks: (1) developer/liquidity flight to Sui becoming self-reinforcing; (2) institutional RWA being custodial/inert, never seeding sticky DeFi network effects. Watch: DeFi TVL gap vs Sui, weekly active dev trend, whether $1.2B RWA generates on-chain activity, and results of the deflationary tokenomics. Base case most likely — real institutional edge, but no evidence yet it converts to durable network effects.','{"founded":"2022-10","founders":"Mo Shaikh and Avery Ching (ex-Meta Diem)","raised":"~$400M+; $150M Series A (Mar 2022, a16z/Multicoin/Katie Haun), $150M round led by FTX/Jump at $4B valuation, plus Binance Labs","token_symbol":"APT","token_ath":19.92,"token_ath_date":"2023-01","token_current":0.6,"purpose":"A high-throughput, safe, scalable L1 using the Move language and Block-STM parallel execution (Diem successor)","whats_working":"Institutional RWA leadership ($1.2B on-chain via BlackRock BUIDL +$500M Oct 2025, Franklin Templeton Benji, PACT private credit), record 1.3M daily active addresses in Q1 2026 (4th among non-EVM chains), stablecoin mcap ~$1.93B record, Move safety, deflationary tokenomics overhaul, SEC/CFTC digital-commodity classification","whats_not":"Out-competed by Sui in the Move ecosystem; no flagship anchor app; DeFi TVL fell from ~$1B (late 2025) to ~$109-280M vs Sui''s ~$438M and Solana''s $5B+; developer count fell 108→74 weekly / 465 MAD vs Sui''s 954; unstable TVL sensitive to incentives; tiny fee revenue vs emissions","situation":"Aptos is drifting toward an explicit institutional/compliance bet rather than pivoting outright: it is leveraging SEC/CFTC digital-commodity status and a deflationary tokenomics overhaul to own the ''compliance certification → RWA deployment → institutional infrastructure'' lane. Concrete catalysts: BlackRock BUIDL added $500M in Oct 2025 (total RWA $1.2B), Franklin Templeton runs its Benji record-keeping on Aptos, and on 8 May 2026 Aptos Foundation/Labs pledged $50M+ for institutional AI+DeFi infra (on-chain perps, MEV-resistant cryptographic mempools, FIX/CCXT integration). But the token is ~97% off ATH (~$0.58, #109 by mcap ~$482M), and Sui is winning the parallel financial-product race (CME SUI futures + three spot ETFs, May 2026) while carrying ~4x Aptos'' market cap.","non_economic":"Developer mindshare is the clearest non-economic loss: Sui runs 954 monthly active devs to Aptos'' 465 (2:1), and Aptos'' weekly active devs slid 108→74 in Q2 2025 — a signal builders are choosing the Move sibling. Community/usage metrics are a counter-bright-spot: record 1.3M daily active addresses in Q1 2026 (peaked 1.8M Dec 2025) and 330+ live projects show real on-chain activity, not a ghost chain. Interoperability olive branch: AIP-113 passed Feb 2026 lets Sui wallets natively interact with Aptos, an unusual cross-ecosystem move. Media framing casts Aptos as the ''institutional/compliance'' Move chain — credible but less exciting than Sui''s ETF momentum.","outlook":"BULL: institutional RWA compounds (RWA TVL already ~$719M-$1.2B) and Aptos becomes the compliant settlement layer for tokenized TradFi assets — trigger is a major asset manager making Aptos its primary tokenization venue plus the deflationary burn biting. BASE (most likely): Aptos stays a technically credible, institutionally-backed L1 that keeps winning RWA headlines but loses the broader ecosystem/dev battle to Sui, trading as a mid-cap with high daily addresses but thin DeFi. BEAR: RWA deposits stay parked and non-generative, developers keep defecting to Sui, and emissions overwhelm negligible fee revenue. Top risks: (1) developer/liquidity flight to Sui becoming self-reinforcing; (2) institutional RWA being custodial/inert, never seeding sticky DeFi network effects. Watch: DeFi TVL gap vs Sui, weekly active dev trend, whether $1.2B RWA generates on-chain activity, and results of the deflationary tokenomics. Base case most likely — real institutional edge, but no evidence yet it converts to durable network effects.","success_factors_missing":["outcompeted","no_killer_app","weak_dev_ecosystem","token_overhang"],"sources":[{"title":"Aptos vs Sui 2026: Move Ecosystem & Institutional DeFi (Gate)","url":"https://www.gate.com/blog/aptos-vs-sui-move-ecosystem-institutional-defi-2026"},{"title":"Aptos APT Surges 7% as RWA TVL Hits $719M Amid Institutional Demand (AInvest)","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/aptos-apt-surges-7-rwa-tvl-hits-719m-rising-institutional-demand-2508/"},{"title":"Sui vs Aptos in 2026: Who is winning the Move developer war? (AMBCrypto)","url":"https://eng.ambcrypto.com/sui-vs-aptos-in-2026-who-is-actually-winning-the-move-developer-war/"},{"title":"Aptos in 2026: Latest News, Roadmap, DeFi Updates (Everstake)","url":"https://everstake.one/resources/blog/aptos-news-2026"}]}','[{"title":"Aptos vs Sui 2026: Move Ecosystem & Institutional DeFi (Gate)","url":"https://www.gate.com/blog/aptos-vs-sui-move-ecosystem-institutional-defi-2026"},{"title":"Aptos APT Surges 7% as RWA TVL Hits $719M Amid Institutional Demand (AInvest)","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/aptos-apt-surges-7-rwa-tvl-hits-719m-rising-institutional-demand-2508/"},{"title":"Sui vs Aptos in 2026: Who is winning the Move developer war? (AMBCrypto)","url":"https://eng.ambcrypto.com/sui-vs-aptos-in-2026-who-is-actually-winning-the-move-developer-war/"},{"title":"Aptos in 2026: Latest News, Roadmap, DeFi Updates (Everstake)","url":"https://everstake.one/resources/blog/aptos-news-2026"}]','2026-07-08 15:07:27');
INSERT INTO "mid_chains" ("chain","launched","tvl","verdict","why_stuck","outlook","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('Sui','2023-05',422150981,'quietly_building','Sui is the strongest of the Move duo (peaked ~$2.6B DeFi TVL, >$1T cumulative stablecoin transfers, 954 monthly active devs) and weathered the bear better than Aptos, so it arguably straddles the mid/upper line. But it remains a well-funded L1 without a defining consumer breakout, still fighting the ''Ethereum-alternative'' framing, with the token ~65% off cycle highs and TVL down from its peak.','BULL: institutional rails (CME futures → spot ETF approval) plus Hashi BTCFi and DeepBook v3 margin trading convert Sui''s dev lead into deep, sticky liquidity and a breakout consumer/payments app — trigger is a spot SUI ETF approval or a killer app driving organic TVL back above $2B. BASE (most likely): Sui remains the clear Move leader and a top institutional L1, but plateaus — strong dev/stablecoin metrics without a defining consumer breakout, token capped by ~65% unlock overhang. BEAR: unlock pressure + another major exploit erode confidence, liquidity keeps bleeding to Solana, and the ''ETH alternative'' framing never breaks. Top risks: (1) ~65% supply unlock schedule through 2027 suppressing price/TVL; (2) recurring DeFi security exploits. Watch: spot ETF decisions, TVL recovery vs the $2.5B peak, DeepBook v3 adoption, Hashi BTC deposits. Base case (durable leader, plateau risk) most likely — Sui''s problem is converting technical/dev leadership into a category-defining reason to win, not survival.','{"founded":"2023-05","founders":"Evan Cheng, Sam Blackshear, Adeniyi Abiodun, George Danezis, Kostas Chalkias (Mysten Labs, ex-Meta Diem)","raised":"~$336M; $36M seed (2021, a16z), $300M Series B (Sep 2022, FTX Ventures/Jump/Binance Labs/Coinbase Ventures) at ~$2B valuation","token_symbol":"SUI","token_ath":5.35,"token_ath_date":"2025-01","token_current":0.71,"purpose":"A high-performance, object-centric L1 using Move with DAG-based consensus, targeting low-latency consumer and DeFi apps","whats_working":"Highest DeFi TVL in Move ecosystem, >$1T cumulative stablecoin transfers (crossed March 2026, $111B in Jan 2026 alone), monthly active devs +219% YoY to ~1,400, 500+ projects, ~300k daily active users, CME SUI futures (May 4 2026) as 4th L1 after BTC/ETH/SOL, three staking ETFs live, USDsui via Stripe/Bridge, Hashi native BTC collateral (20+ institutions day one), Paga Africa RWA partnership","whats_not":"No breakout consumer killer app yet; still boxed as an ''ETH alternative''; TVL fell from ~$2.5B peak (late 2025) to ~$568-583M by March 2026; ~65% of supply still to unlock (heavy vesting through 2027); security scars (Cetus DEX exploit May 2025, Volo $3.5M early 2026); competing with Solana for same liquidity/devs","situation":"Sui is executing (verdict quietly_building) and is decisively winning the Move race — it has become the 4th L1 with CME futures (May 4 2026), has three US staking ETFs, crossed $1T cumulative stablecoin transfers, and grew monthly active devs +219% YoY (~1,400) vs Aptos'' 465. Its differentiators are the object-centric data model, DeepBook v3 CLOB upgrade (margin trading, Q2 2026 testnet), and Hashi — a native no-wrap BTC collateralization primitive from Mysten that drew 20+ institutions on day one. The catch: headline USD TVL cooled hard from ~$2.5B peak to ~$583M amid market downturn, the Cetus/Volo exploits, and token-unlock pressure (~65% of supply still vesting).","non_economic":"Developer momentum is the standout non-economic signal: +219% YoY monthly active devs, outpacing Solana''s 83%, with builders continuing to ship through the bear — analysts note the downturn ''separated genuine progress from noise''. Community/usage stays healthy (~300k DAU, 500+ projects), and institutional social proof is strong (CME, ETF issuers Grayscale/Canary/21Shares, Stripe''s Bridge for USDsui, Paga in Africa). Media framing is the most favorable of the mid-tier L1s — ''Sui turns three'' coverage leans bullish on institutional infrastructure. Reputational overhang: repeated DEX exploits (Cetus, Volo) dent the ''safe Move'' narrative.","outlook":"BULL: institutional rails (CME futures → spot ETF approval) plus Hashi BTCFi and DeepBook v3 margin trading convert Sui''s dev lead into deep, sticky liquidity and a breakout consumer/payments app — trigger is a spot SUI ETF approval or a killer app driving organic TVL back above $2B. BASE (most likely): Sui remains the clear Move leader and a top institutional L1, but plateaus — strong dev/stablecoin metrics without a defining consumer breakout, token capped by ~65% unlock overhang. BEAR: unlock pressure + another major exploit erode confidence, liquidity keeps bleeding to Solana, and the ''ETH alternative'' framing never breaks. Top risks: (1) ~65% supply unlock schedule through 2027 suppressing price/TVL; (2) recurring DeFi security exploits. Watch: spot ETF decisions, TVL recovery vs the $2.5B peak, DeepBook v3 adoption, Hashi BTC deposits. Base case (durable leader, plateau risk) most likely — Sui''s problem is converting technical/dev leadership into a category-defining reason to win, not survival.","success_factors_missing":["unclear_positioning","token_overhang"],"sources":[{"title":"Sui Network Turns Three: CME Futures, Staking ETFs, and $2.6B DeFi TVL (Blockonomi)","url":"https://blockonomi.com/sui-network-turns-three-cme-futures-staking-etfs-and-2-6b-defi-tvl-mark-a-new-era/"},{"title":"Is SUI Positioned for the Next Bull Cycle? CME Futures, Spot ETFs, 219% Dev Growth","url":"https://bitcoinethereumnews.com/tech/is-sui-network-positioned-for-the-next-bull-cycle-cme-futures-spot-etfs-and-219-dev-growth-suggest-it/"},{"title":"CME Group Expands Crypto Derivatives with AVAX and SUI Futures (CryptoRank)","url":"https://cryptorank.io/news/feed/f35a1-cme-group-avax-sui-futures-launch"},{"title":"Sui Futures Launch on CME, Native Stablecoin USDsui (AInvest)","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/sui-futures-launch-cme-group-2026-native-stablecoin-usdsui-2604/"}]}','[{"title":"Sui Network Turns Three: CME Futures, Staking ETFs, and $2.6B DeFi TVL (Blockonomi)","url":"https://blockonomi.com/sui-network-turns-three-cme-futures-staking-etfs-and-2-6b-defi-tvl-mark-a-new-era/"},{"title":"Is SUI Positioned for the Next Bull Cycle? CME Futures, Spot ETFs, 219% Dev Growth","url":"https://bitcoinethereumnews.com/tech/is-sui-network-positioned-for-the-next-bull-cycle-cme-futures-spot-etfs-and-219-dev-growth-suggest-it/"},{"title":"CME Group Expands Crypto Derivatives with AVAX and SUI Futures (CryptoRank)","url":"https://cryptorank.io/news/feed/f35a1-cme-group-avax-sui-futures-launch"},{"title":"Sui Futures Launch on CME, Native Stablecoin USDsui (AInvest)","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/sui-futures-launch-cme-group-2026-native-stablecoin-usdsui-2604/"}]','2026-07-08 15:08:47');
INSERT INTO "mid_chains" ("chain","launched","tvl","verdict","why_stuck","outlook","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('Cardano','2017-09',81176421,'stalling','Cardano is the archetypal ''ghost chain'': ~$45B+ market cap history and a huge holder base, yet DeFi TVL collapsed from ~$686M (Dec 2024) to ~$80-118M with daily revenue of a few hundred dollars. Its research-first, peer-reviewed engineering never produced network effects; governance (OpenGov/DReps) has become gridlock — a treasury proposal failed the two-thirds threshold and Hoskinson publicly said more Cardano DeFi projects will die in 2026.','BULL: Bitcoin DeFi bridges + Midnight/RealFi + private stablecoins tap BTC''s capital base and institutional liquidity (via Clearstream-style rails), finally seeding real TVL — trigger is a working, adopted BTC bridge routing meaningful BTC into Cardano DeFi. BASE (most likely): Cardano persists as a reliable, never-hacked ''ghost chain'' — huge staking participation and brand, but governance gridlock keeps treasury capital idle and DeFi structurally thin; ADA trades on macro/beta, not usage. BEAR: governance deadlock hardens, more flagship apps die (Hoskinson himself predicted more Cardano DeFi projects fail in 2026), Hoskinson disengages, and the valuation-usage gap closes downward. Top risks: (1) governance/coordination paralysis blocking treasury deployment; (2) passive-holder culture that never bootstraps liquidity even if tech ships. Watch: whether the BTC-DeFi bridge actually launches and attracts BTC, DRep treasury vote outcomes, Midnight mainnet progress, DeFi TVL trend off the ~$100M floor. Base case most likely — the problem is coordination, and shipping tech has repeatedly failed to fix a demand/liquidity problem.','{"founded":"2017-09","founders":"Charles Hoskinson and Jeremy Wood (IOHK/Input Output)","raised":"~$62M ADA public sale (2015-2017); funded via ICO not VC rounds","token_symbol":"ADA","token_ath":3.1,"token_ath_date":"2021-09","token_current":0.17,"purpose":"A peer-reviewed, research-driven proof-of-stake L1 (Ouroboros) aiming for security, formal methods and financial inclusion in developing markets","whats_working":"~1.3M active stakers/governance participants, ~$15B staked ADA, strong brand and holder loyalty, no VC unlock overhang, Midnight privacy chain in ''beta year'' 2026, Clearstream regulated ADA custody (7 Jul 2026), ''largest upgrade in history'' teased, never hacked / uninterrupted block production","whats_not":"DeFi TVL collapsed ~80-85% from peak to ~$90-128M; near-zero on-chain revenue (~$477/day); governance gridlock (7.8M ADA treasury proposal failed the 2/3 DRep threshold, Foundation canceled 2026 summit); flagship apps shutting down; passive holders won''t provide liquidity; ~$9B mcap vs symbolic usage","situation":"Cardano is stalling and its central 2026 tension is a stark valuation-vs-usage gap: ~$9B market cap against ~$128M DeFi TVL and ~$477/day revenue. Hoskinson has reframed 2026 as do-or-die and pivoted the thesis toward Bitcoin DeFi (calling private/decentralized BTC bridges ''the largest untapped niche... a race we can win'') plus Midnight (now in its ''beta year'', positioned as privacy infra for regulated environments) and RealFi. But the binding constraint is organizational, not technical: Hoskinson publicly declared he is ''taking a break'', stressing he holds no governance keys, treasury access, or unilateral hard-fork power — his own words: ''It''s not a technology problem. It''s a problem of governance and coordination and ultimately accountability.''","non_economic":"Community loyalty remains large and vocal (~1.3M stakers, ~$15B staked) but the mood soured in 2026 around governance dysfunction — a failed treasury vote, the Cardano Foundation canceling its 2026 summit, and Hoskinson stepping back all fed ''is ADA dead?'' media coverage (Cointribune, CryptoRank). The founder-dependency is a structural social flaw: markets still price personal Hoskinson accountability even as decentralized governance routes decisions away from him, so no ''founder rescue'' is realistic. Bright spots in signaling: Clearstream custody (7 Jul 2026) and teased private-stablecoin integrations lend institutional credibility. Developer/ecosystem activity is thin and shrinking — the core non-economic problem is passive holders who stake but won''t supply liquidity.","outlook":"BULL: Bitcoin DeFi bridges + Midnight/RealFi + private stablecoins tap BTC''s capital base and institutional liquidity (via Clearstream-style rails), finally seeding real TVL — trigger is a working, adopted BTC bridge routing meaningful BTC into Cardano DeFi. BASE (most likely): Cardano persists as a reliable, never-hacked ''ghost chain'' — huge staking participation and brand, but governance gridlock keeps treasury capital idle and DeFi structurally thin; ADA trades on macro/beta, not usage. BEAR: governance deadlock hardens, more flagship apps die (Hoskinson himself predicted more Cardano DeFi projects fail in 2026), Hoskinson disengages, and the valuation-usage gap closes downward. Top risks: (1) governance/coordination paralysis blocking treasury deployment; (2) passive-holder culture that never bootstraps liquidity even if tech ships. Watch: whether the BTC-DeFi bridge actually launches and attracts BTC, DRep treasury vote outcomes, Midnight mainnet progress, DeFi TVL trend off the ~$100M floor. Base case most likely — the problem is coordination, and shipping tech has repeatedly failed to fix a demand/liquidity problem.","success_factors_missing":["no_killer_app","no_liquidity_moat","lost_narrative","fading_community"],"sources":[{"title":"Beyond the Ivory Tower: Why Hoskinson''s New Cardano Roadmap Changes Everything (TradingKey)","url":"https://www.tradingkey.com/analysis/cryptocurrencies/more/261653445-crypto-cardano-ada-tvl-founder-foundation-charles-hoskinson-market-cap-tradingkey"},{"title":"Hoskinson takes ''a break'' – exposing who really controls ADA''s next move (CryptoRank)","url":"https://cryptorank.io/news/feed/e49e6-hoskinsons-cardano-break-exposes-who-really-controls-adas-next-move"},{"title":"''This Is a Race We Can Win'': Hoskinson Targets Bitcoin DeFi for Cardano (U.Today)","url":"https://u.today/this-is-a-race-we-can-win-charles-hoskinson-targets-bitcoin-defi-market-for-cardano"},{"title":"Hoskinson Says Largest Upgrade in Cardano History Is Imminent (The Crypto Basic)","url":"https://thecryptobasic.com/2026/07/02/hoskinson-says-largest-upgrade-in-cardano-history-is-imminent-confirms-ada-fundamentals-remain-strong/"}]}','[{"title":"Beyond the Ivory Tower: Why Hoskinson''s New Cardano Roadmap Changes Everything (TradingKey)","url":"https://www.tradingkey.com/analysis/cryptocurrencies/more/261653445-crypto-cardano-ada-tvl-founder-foundation-charles-hoskinson-market-cap-tradingkey"},{"title":"Hoskinson takes ''a break'' – exposing who really controls ADA''s next move (CryptoRank)","url":"https://cryptorank.io/news/feed/e49e6-hoskinsons-cardano-break-exposes-who-really-controls-adas-next-move"},{"title":"''This Is a Race We Can Win'': Hoskinson Targets Bitcoin DeFi for Cardano (U.Today)","url":"https://u.today/this-is-a-race-we-can-win-charles-hoskinson-targets-bitcoin-defi-market-for-cardano"},{"title":"Hoskinson Says Largest Upgrade in Cardano History Is Imminent (The Crypto Basic)","url":"https://thecryptobasic.com/2026/07/02/hoskinson-says-largest-upgrade-in-cardano-history-is-imminent-confirms-ada-fundamentals-remain-strong/"}]','2026-07-08 15:09:34');
INSERT INTO "mid_chains" ("chain","launched","tvl","verdict","why_stuck","outlook","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('Polkadot','2020-05',53227651,'pivoting','Polkadot raised ~$300M+ across two sales on the ''internet of blockchains'' vision, but its signature parachain-auction model backfired: it locked DOT for years, priced out small teams, and produced a fragmented ecosystem where DeFi is scattered across parachains (the main hub, Hydration, holds only ~$53M). Daily active users fell below 5,000, monthly devs halved from 2,400 to 1,200, treasury spending ballooned past $129M with little measurable impact, and DOT trades ~98% off its ATH.','BULL: JAM ships on mainnet (Q3-Q4 2026) and reframes Polkadot as a general-purpose decentralized supercomputer, Agile Coretime''s dApp inflows compound, and the hard-cap scarcity narrative + ETF flows re-rate DOT — trigger is a successful JAM mainnet launch with real applications. BASE (most likely): the tech keeps advancing (JAM, Coretime, staking reforms) and dev activity stays elite, but TVL/users/mindshare remain stubbornly weak; DOT trades as a disinflationary but under-adopted infrastructure token. BEAR: JAM slips or underwhelms, Coretime fails to attract sticky demand, another bridge/security incident hits confidence, and the ''sophisticated tech nobody uses'' verdict hardens. Top risks: (1) JAM execution/timeline risk (not on mainnet, multi-year); (2) chronic adoption gap — upgrades that never convert to TVL/users. Watch: JAM Q3-Q4 2026 milestones, TDOT ETF AUM growth beyond ~$11M seed, whether Agile Coretime sustains new-team inflows, DeFi TVL trend. Base case most likely — the pattern of shipping strong tech that fails to convert into adoption is deeply established.','{"founded":"2020-05","founders":"Gavin Wood (Ethereum co-founder), Robert Habermeier, Peter Czaban (Web3 Foundation / Parity)","raised":"~$145M ICO (2017) + ~$43M (2019) + later sales; ~$300M+ total, Web3 Foundation","token_symbol":"DOT","token_ath":54.98,"token_ath_date":"2021-11","token_current":0.82,"purpose":"A heterogeneous multichain (''internet of blockchains'') where a relay chain provides shared security to sovereign parachains connected via XCM","whats_working":"Developer activity strong (ranked 6th globally in 30-day core dev activity, 98 unique contributors Apr 2026), Agile Coretime live (150+ new dApps in Q1 2026), March 12 2026 tokenomics reset (hard cap 2.1B DOT, issuance cut 53.6%), JAM public testnet (Jan 2026, 43 teams, 10M DOT prize), staking safety reforms live (Referenda 1909/1910, July 2026), 21Shares TDOT ETF (March 2026)","whats_not":"Parachain-auction model failed and locked liquidity; DeFi fragmented (~$1.2B TVL, fraction of ETH); developer growth plateaued; weak daily active users; JAM still not on mainnet; Hyperbridge exploit minted 1B wrapped DOT on ETH (April 13 2026); DOT ~98% off ATH; TDOT ETF inflows modest (~$11M seed)","situation":"Polkadot is mid-pivot and the pivot is technically shipping but not yet converting. It replaced the failed 2-year parachain auctions with Agile Coretime (pay-as-you-go blockspace, completed Oct 2025 via SDK 2509), which drew 150+ new dApps in Q1 2026. On March 12 2026 it executed a landmark tokenomics reset (runtime v2.1.0): a permanent 2.1B DOT hard cap and issuance cut from ~120M to ~56.88M/yr (-53.6%), making DOT disinflationary. The big bet is JAM (Polkadot 3.0, RISC-V general compute) — public testnet launched Jan 2026 with 43 teams competing for a 10M DOT prize, mainnet targeted Q3-Q4 2026. What the pivot accomplishes: lower barriers to build + scarcity economics; what''s unique is JAM''s ambition to become a general-purpose decentralized computer, not just parachain coordination. But every prior upgrade has failed to move TVL/users, and an April 13 2026 Hyperbridge exploit (1B wrapped DOT minted on ETH) spooked markets.","non_economic":"Developer activity is Polkadot''s strongest non-economic signal — ranked 6th globally in core dev activity (April 2026), 98 unique contributors, and 43 independent teams building JAM implementations across 15 languages, a rare depth of engagement. But end-user metrics stay weak (thin daily active users) and community mindshare has faded from its 2021 peak, with pervasive ''Is Polkadot dead?'' media framing despite the technical progress. Governance is highly active but politically fractious (all changes route through OpenGov referenda). Real-world footholds exist quietly: government identity deployments, 500% tx growth on DePIN parachains, Mythical Games mass-market gaming. The core non-economic story: exceptional builder activity and governance participation that has not translated into users or mindshare.","outlook":"BULL: JAM ships on mainnet (Q3-Q4 2026) and reframes Polkadot as a general-purpose decentralized supercomputer, Agile Coretime''s dApp inflows compound, and the hard-cap scarcity narrative + ETF flows re-rate DOT — trigger is a successful JAM mainnet launch with real applications. BASE (most likely): the tech keeps advancing (JAM, Coretime, staking reforms) and dev activity stays elite, but TVL/users/mindshare remain stubbornly weak; DOT trades as a disinflationary but under-adopted infrastructure token. BEAR: JAM slips or underwhelms, Coretime fails to attract sticky demand, another bridge/security incident hits confidence, and the ''sophisticated tech nobody uses'' verdict hardens. Top risks: (1) JAM execution/timeline risk (not on mainnet, multi-year); (2) chronic adoption gap — upgrades that never convert to TVL/users. Watch: JAM Q3-Q4 2026 milestones, TDOT ETF AUM growth beyond ~$11M seed, whether Agile Coretime sustains new-team inflows, DeFi TVL trend. Base case most likely — the pattern of shipping strong tech that fails to convert into adoption is deeply established.","success_factors_missing":["tech_no_adoption","no_liquidity_moat","fading_community","lost_narrative"],"sources":[{"title":"Polkadot (DOT) Review 2026: JAM, Hard Cap & The Honest Verdict (Coin Bureau)","url":"https://coinbureau.com/review/polkadot-dot"},{"title":"Is Polkadot Dead? A 2026 Data-Driven Look at DOT''s Ecosystem (MEXC)","url":"https://www.mexc.com/learn/article/is-polkadot-dead-a-2026-data-driven-look-at-dots-ecosystem-investment-value/1"},{"title":"Polkadot 2.0 Explained: Agile Coretime and What It Changes (Cryptonews)","url":"https://cryptonews.net/news/altcoins/32991057/"},{"title":"Polkadot 2026: JAM Upgrade, Tokenomics, and Investment Guide (Bitget)","url":"https://www.bitget.com/academy/is-polkadot-dead-in-2026-comprehensive-united-kingdom-guide-dot-jam-polkadot-2-0"}]}','[{"title":"Polkadot (DOT) Review 2026: JAM, Hard Cap & The Honest Verdict (Coin Bureau)","url":"https://coinbureau.com/review/polkadot-dot"},{"title":"Is Polkadot Dead? A 2026 Data-Driven Look at DOT''s Ecosystem (MEXC)","url":"https://www.mexc.com/learn/article/is-polkadot-dead-a-2026-data-driven-look-at-dots-ecosystem-investment-value/1"},{"title":"Polkadot 2.0 Explained: Agile Coretime and What It Changes (Cryptonews)","url":"https://cryptonews.net/news/altcoins/32991057/"},{"title":"Polkadot 2026: JAM Upgrade, Tokenomics, and Investment Guide (Bitget)","url":"https://www.bitget.com/academy/is-polkadot-dead-in-2026-comprehensive-united-kingdom-guide-dot-jam-polkadot-2-0"}]','2026-07-08 15:10:49');
INSERT INTO "mid_chains" ("chain","launched","tvl","verdict","why_stuck","outlook","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('Cosmos Hub','2019-03',122317,'stalling','Cosmos pioneered the appchain / IBC ''internet of blockchains'' thesis and spawned huge chains (Osmosis, Injective, Celestia, dYdX, Sei all have Cosmos roots), but the ATOM token captures almost none of that success — the Hub''s own TVL is a rounding error (~$122K). Interchain Security was meant to fix value capture, but the flagship consumer chain Neutron exited it in 2025, projects migrated to Solana/Base, and 7-20% inflation created constant sell pressure. ATOM is ~95% off its peak.','BULL: the tokenomics redesign lands a working fee/buyback model AND the COSMOSIS Osmosis merger passes, giving the Hub real liquidity, DeFi activity, and value capture for the first time — trigger is merger approval + a shipped revenue-driven ATOM model. BASE (most likely): the redesign proceeds slowly through a change-resistant DAO, ICS winds down, and ATOM stays structurally disconnected from the ecosystem it seeded — an influential-tech / weak-asset split persists. BEAR: the DAO rejects or waters down the redesign, COSMOSIS fails, inflation overhang continues, and ATOM keeps bleeding as the ''built the roads, own no toll booths'' asset. Top risks: (1) governance paralysis; (2) the redesign being too little too late against entrenched inflation sell pressure. Watch: the selected tokenomics research firm and its model, the COSMOSIS merger vote, ICS deprecation impact on Neutron/Stride revenue, ATOM inflation trajectory. Base case most likely — the tech works, the economics don''t yet.','{"founded":"2019-03","founders":"Jae Kwon and Ethan Buchman (Tendermint / Interchain Foundation)","raised":"~$17M ICO (2017), Interchain Foundation","token_symbol":"ATOM","token_ath":44.7,"token_ath_date":"2021-09","token_current":1.53,"purpose":"The hub of the Cosmos ''internet of blockchains'' — sovereign appchains built with Cosmos SDK, connected via the IBC protocol, secured by Tendermint","whats_working":"Enormously influential tech (IBC, Cosmos SDK power Osmosis, Injective, Celestia, dYdX, Sei), ~61% staking ratio, execution-focused Cosmos Labs (Skip co-CEOs Plunkett & Mareneck since Jan 2025), tokenomics redesign underway (9 research proposals received Jan 2026), IBC Eureka live connecting Ethereum (Solana/L2s near), proposed COSMOSIS Osmosis merger (March 2026)","whats_not":"ATOM captures zero value from ecosystem success; Hub TVL near-zero (~$122K); Interchain Security officially being deprecated after failing product-market fit (only Neutron + Stride left); 7-20% inflation overhang; DAO politically resists change (3% inflation-cut vote triggered stake withdrawal); ATOM ~96% off peak at 5-year low","situation":"Cosmos Hub is stalling and is now openly re-architecting ATOM''s value model. Governance/execution centralized under Cosmos Labs (formed from the Interchain Foundation''s Dec 2024 Skip acquisition; Skip''s Barry Plunkett & Maghnus Mareneck are co-CEOs). Cosmos Labs has explicitly admitted Interchain Security ''failed to find product-market fit'' and is deprecating it — a striking reversal since ICS was once billed as ATOM''s core value driver. In its place, a formal tokenomics redesign (RFP launched Nov 2025, 9 research proposals in by Jan 2026) aims to move ATOM from 7-20% inflation to a 2-6% fee/revenue-driven model with buybacks or staking rewards. A parallel catalyst: the COSMOSIS proposal (March 11 2026) to convert all OSMO into ATOM and fold Osmosis'' liquidity/security/governance into the Hub — the most aggressive consolidation in Cosmos history. ATOM sits at a 5-year low (~$1.53, -96% from ATH) amid extreme fear.","non_economic":"The Cosmos tech stack (IBC, Cosmos SDK) remains one of crypto''s most influential and widely-forked — IBC Eureka went live connecting Ethereum with Solana/L2 links in final stages, sustaining developer relevance. But the Hub''s own community mood is bleak (5-year-low price, extreme-fear sentiment, declining open interest) and its politics are fractious: the DAO historically resists centralization, and even a modest 3% inflation-reduction vote triggered a sharp stake withdrawal, showing how hard coordinated change is. Ecosystem attrition is the defining social signal — flagship chains (Neutron exited ICS, projects migrated to Solana/Base) drifted away, leaving the Hub ''detached from the broader activity of the Cosmos ecosystem'' by Cosmos Labs'' own admission. The COSMOSIS merger is a rare cohesion/consolidation signal in the other direction.","outlook":"BULL: the tokenomics redesign lands a working fee/buyback model AND the COSMOSIS Osmosis merger passes, giving the Hub real liquidity, DeFi activity, and value capture for the first time — trigger is merger approval + a shipped revenue-driven ATOM model. BASE (most likely): the redesign proceeds slowly through a change-resistant DAO, ICS winds down, and ATOM stays structurally disconnected from the ecosystem it seeded — an influential-tech / weak-asset split persists. BEAR: the DAO rejects or waters down the redesign (as with prior inflation votes), COSMOSIS fails, inflation overhang continues, and ATOM keeps bleeding as the ''built the roads, own no toll booths'' asset. Top risks: (1) governance paralysis — the DAO''s proven resistance to tokenomics/inflation change; (2) the redesign being too little too late against entrenched inflation sell pressure. Watch: the selected tokenomics research firm and its model, the COSMOSIS merger vote, ICS deprecation impact on Neutron/Stride revenue, ATOM inflation trajectory. Base case most likely — the tech works, the economics don''t yet, and fixing them requires clearing a historically obstinate DAO.","success_factors_missing":["unclear_positioning","token_overhang","no_liquidity_moat","fading_community"],"sources":[{"title":"Cosmos Eyes ATOM Redesign As Price Falls to 5-Year Low (BeInCrypto)","url":"https://beincrypto.com/cosmos-atom-resign-price-decline/"},{"title":"COSMOSIS: Why the Osmosis–Cosmos Hub Merger Could Redraw Multi-Chain DeFi (BlockEden)","url":"https://blockeden.xyz/blog/2026/03/12/cosmosis-osmosis-cosmos-hub-merger-ecosystem-consolidation/"},{"title":"Request for Proposals: ATOM Tokenomics Research (Cosmos Hub Forum)","url":"https://forum.cosmos.network/t/request-for-proposals-atom-tokenomics-research/16508"},{"title":"Cosmos Powers the Internet of Blockchains. Can ATOM Capture the Value? (TipRanks)","url":"https://www.tipranks.com/news/cosmos-powers-the-internet-of-blockchains-can-atom-capture-the-value"}]}','[{"title":"Cosmos Eyes ATOM Redesign As Price Falls to 5-Year Low (BeInCrypto)","url":"https://beincrypto.com/cosmos-atom-resign-price-decline/"},{"title":"COSMOSIS: Why the Osmosis–Cosmos Hub Merger Could Redraw Multi-Chain DeFi (BlockEden)","url":"https://blockeden.xyz/blog/2026/03/12/cosmosis-osmosis-cosmos-hub-merger-ecosystem-consolidation/"},{"title":"Request for Proposals: ATOM Tokenomics Research (Cosmos Hub Forum)","url":"https://forum.cosmos.network/t/request-for-proposals-atom-tokenomics-research/16508"},{"title":"Cosmos Powers the Internet of Blockchains. Can ATOM Capture the Value? (TipRanks)","url":"https://www.tipranks.com/news/cosmos-powers-the-internet-of-blockchains-can-atom-capture-the-value"}]','2026-07-08 15:11:26');
INSERT INTO "mid_chains" ("chain","launched","tvl","verdict","why_stuck","outlook","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('Algorand','2019-06',30094188,'stalling','Algorand has arguably the best tech-to-price mismatch in the top 100: a Turing Award founder (Silvio Micali), pure PoS, post-quantum security live, SEC/CFTC commodity status — yet DeFi TVL sits at only ~$30-88M and it has slowly lost relevance to Solana, ETH L2s, Sui and Aptos. The token hit an all-time low in 2026, ~93% below ATH, with structurally thin DeFi despite years of infrastructure.','BULL: payments + RWA adoption (Visa cards, USDC settlement, tokenized Treasuries) plus a major CBDC or sovereign deployment finally give ALGO a demand sink, and AlgoKit 4.0 seeds a DeFi revival — trigger is a flagship payments/CBDC rail going live at scale. BASE (most likely): Algorand stays sound, low-fee, quantum-ahead infrastructure with real but niche payments/RWA usage, while DeFi TVL stays structurally tiny and ALGO trades range-bound near lows. BEAR: no DeFi catalyst materializes, payments adoption stays pilot-scale, 7 years of underperformance extends, and ALGO makes new lows vs Solana/Sui/L2s. Top risks: (1) chronic DeFi liquidity gap tooling won''t close before late 2026; (2) conditioned sell behavior after an all-time-low print. Watch: Visa/Quantoz and x402 payments volume, TVL trend off ~$88M, AlgoKit 4.0 uptake, any CBDC/sovereign deployment. Base case most likely — excellent infrastructure with a persistent demand deficit the market declines to reward.','{"founded":"2019-06","founders":"Silvio Micali (MIT, Turing Award laureate)","raised":"~$60M VC (2018, USV/Pillar) + $60M+ Dutch-auction token sale (2019); Algorand Foundation","token_symbol":"ALGO","token_ath":3.56,"token_ath_date":"2019-06","token_current":0.085,"purpose":"A pure proof-of-stake, high-throughput L1 solving the blockchain trilemma with instant finality, aimed at payments, RWA and financial inclusion","whats_working":"Real payments adoption (Quantoz-Visa cards settling on Algorand, Swypt USDC app, Coinbase x402 ecosystem, UN/WFP humanitarian aid 1M+ users), ~51M cumulative wallets and 3.59B cumulative tx, RWA ($294M tokenized Treasuries, Enel solar/wind fractional ownership), FIFA 2026 World Cup NFTs + on-chain ticketing, quantum-resilience roadmap to 2027, AlgoKit 4.0 + Rocca passkey wallet, Foundation returned to US (Jan 14 2026) with new board","whats_not":"Structurally tiny DeFi TVL (~$77-88M); lost relevance vs Solana/L2s/Sui/Aptos; ALL-TIME LOW $0.07755 hit March 8 2026 (~97% below ATH); no DeFi killer app; declining stablecoin liquidity even as TVL ticks up; 7 years of price underperformance conditioning sell behavior","situation":"Algorand is stalling with the widest tech-to-price gap in the top 100 — Turing-Award founder, pure PoS, post-quantum roadmap — yet it hit an ALL-TIME LOW ($0.07755) on March 8 2026, ~97% below its 2019 ATH. The strategic reality is a decisive pivot toward payments and RWA over DeFi TVL: recent catalysts include a Quantoz-Visa partnership enabling Algorand-issued cards to settle on-chain via instant finality, the Swypt USDC merchant app going live, addition to Coinbase''s x402 ecosystem, and FIFA 2026 World Cup NFTs + anti-fraud ticketing. Structurally the Foundation returned to the US (Jan 14 2026) with a new board and secured a $15M dev fund, framing 2026 around AlgoKit 4.0 (AI-optimized, Rust/Swift/Kotlin SDKs), the Rocca passkey/fee-abstraction wallet, and a quantum-resilience roadmap to 2027.","non_economic":"Media/brand exposure is a genuine non-economic bright spot — FIFA World Cup 2026 NFTs and ticketing, plus Google/SWIFT/Visa/Enel associations, give Algorand mainstream visibility few mid-chains have. On-chain user activity is real and rebounding (monthly active wallets +24.3% MoM to 587K in a recent report, 51M cumulative wallets). Developer tooling is being actively rebuilt (AlgoKit 4.0, new-language SDKs, $15M dev fund) and the quantum-resilience leadership narrative (native PQ accounts, PQ multisig from Q3 2026) is technically distinctive. But community mood is fatigued after 7 straight years of price decline into an all-time low, and DeFi developer mindshare remains thin — the social story is ''respected infrastructure the market ignores.''","outlook":"BULL: payments + RWA adoption (Visa cards, USDC settlement, tokenized Treasuries) plus a major CBDC or sovereign deployment finally give ALGO a demand sink, and AlgoKit 4.0 seeds a DeFi revival — trigger is a flagship payments/CBDC rail going live at scale. BASE (most likely): Algorand stays sound, low-fee, quantum-ahead infrastructure with real but niche payments/RWA usage, while DeFi TVL stays structurally tiny and ALGO trades range-bound near lows — tech without the market reward. BEAR: no DeFi catalyst materializes, payments adoption stays pilot-scale, 7 years of underperformance extends, and ALGO makes new lows as relevance keeps eroding vs Solana/Sui/L2s. Top risks: (1) chronic DeFi liquidity gap that developer tooling won''t close before late 2026 at earliest; (2) conditioned sell behavior after an all-time-low print. Watch: whether Visa/Quantoz and x402 payments generate real volume, TVL trend off the ~$88M base, AlgoKit 4.0 developer uptake, any CBDC/sovereign deployment. Base case most likely — excellent infrastructure with a persistent demand/liquidity deficit the market has repeatedly declined to reward.","success_factors_missing":["tech_no_adoption","no_killer_app","lost_narrative","no_liquidity_moat"],"sources":[{"title":"May 2026 Algo Insights Report (Algorand)","url":"https://algorand.co/blog/may-2026-algo-insights-report"},{"title":"Algorand Ecosystem Sees 25% TVL Growth in April 2026 (Blockchain.News)","url":"https://blockchain.news/news/algorand-april-2026-tvl-growth"},{"title":"Algorand (ALGO) Price Prediction 2026 and 2030 (Bitget)","url":"https://www.bitget.com/news/detail/12560605376033"},{"title":"Will Algorand Reach $1 by 2026? Catalysts, Risks, Strategy (AInvest)","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/algorand-algo-reach-1-2026-assessing-catalysts-risks-investment-strategy-2512/"}]}','[{"title":"May 2026 Algo Insights Report (Algorand)","url":"https://algorand.co/blog/may-2026-algo-insights-report"},{"title":"Algorand Ecosystem Sees 25% TVL Growth in April 2026 (Blockchain.News)","url":"https://blockchain.news/news/algorand-april-2026-tvl-growth"},{"title":"Algorand (ALGO) Price Prediction 2026 and 2030 (Bitget)","url":"https://www.bitget.com/news/detail/12560605376033"},{"title":"Will Algorand Reach $1 by 2026? Catalysts, Risks, Strategy (AInvest)","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/algorand-algo-reach-1-2026-assessing-catalysts-risks-investment-strategy-2512/"}]','2026-07-08 15:12:47');
INSERT INTO "mid_chains" ("chain","launched","tvl","verdict","why_stuck","outlook","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('Sonic','2025-01',16934069,'stalling','Sonic is the rebranded Fantom — an L1 that peaked above $12B TVL in 2021 (SpookySwap, Geist) but became synonymous with bridge hacks and a cooling cycle. The 2025 rebrand (FTM->S, new consensus, FeeM builder subsidy) sparked a spike to ~$1.1B TVL, but incentive-driven ''mercenary'' liquidity fled when the Wintermute market-making deal and airdrop incentives wound down — TVL collapsed ~98% to ~$17M, and co-founder Andre Cronje resigned from the board during the downturn.','BULL: FeeM''s builder subsidy + Cronje''s Flying Tulip launch + USSD stablecoin seed genuine organic demand that finally replaces the departed mercenary liquidity, and the new team rebuilds credibility — trigger is Flying Tulip going live and pulling sticky TVL. BASE (most likely): Sonic limps along as a technically-capable but demand-starved L1 — real GitHub activity but structurally low TVL, ongoing dilution, and a token that grinds near lows while new management slowly rebuilds. BEAR: the leadership vacuum and lost trust prove terminal, Flying Tulip disappoints or decouples, dilution overwhelms thin demand, and Sonic fades like post-hack Fantom. Top risks: (1) no organic demand to replace incentive-bought liquidity; (2) leadership instability after the founder exodus. Watch: Flying Tulip launch + TVL, whether FeeM pulls quality builders, USSD adoption vs dilutive issuance, TVL trend off ~$20M. Base case most likely — incentives bought TVL not loyalty.','{"founded":"2025-01","founders":"Sonic Labs (ex-Fantom Foundation); Andre Cronje (co-founder/architect, exited board June 2026); founding CEO Michael Kong","raised":"Fantom lineage: ~$40M ICO (2018); Sonic Labs operates the treasury","token_symbol":"S","token_ath":3.48,"token_ath_date":"2021-10","token_current":0.025,"purpose":"A high-speed EVM L1 (Lachesis aBFT) with a Fee Monetization (FeeM) model paying app developers up to 90% of fees; rebranded successor to Fantom Opera (S is 1:1 with old FTM)","whats_working":"Fast finality, FeeM builder subsidy (up to 90% of fees to dApps), continued technical progress (400 PRs merged in 2026, 2 releases shipped, v2.2.0 in active dev, private testnet), USSD Treasury-backed stablecoin launched March 2026, Andre Cronje''s Flying Tulip DeFi exchange building on Sonic (raised at $1B valuation)","whats_not":"TVL collapsed ~98% from $1.14B (May 2025) peak to ~$20M once incentives/Wintermute MM deal ended; S ~97% off Jan 2025 record ($1.03→$0.031, FDV ~$120M); mercenary liquidity fled; leadership exodus (CEO Demeter + Owens resigned Feb 2026; Cronje/Kong/Richardson quit board June 2026); token dilution overhang; Fantom''s hack-scarred reputation","situation":"Sonic is stalling badly and in the middle of a leadership crisis, not a clean pivot. The 2025 Fantom→Sonic rebrand (new consensus, FeeM) spiked TVL to ~$1.14B, but mercenary liquidity fled when airdrop incentives and the Wintermute market-making deal wound down — TVL collapsed ~98% to ~$20M and S sits ~97% off its Jan 2025 record (~$0.031, FDV ~$120M). The defining recent catalyst is a full board turnover: after CEO Mitchell Demeter and business head Evan Owens resigned in Feb 2026, founders Andre Cronje, Michael Kong and David Richardson stepped down from the Sonic Labs board in June 2026, with Matt Visser taking over as CEO (pledging to get ''1% better'' daily) and Kosta Kourkoumelis as COO. Cronje publicly disclaimed responsibility for the migration, airdrop structure and tokenomics while accepting accountability only for technical decisions.","non_economic":"The dominant non-economic signal is leadership instability and eroded trust — two waves of executive departures in 2026 culminating in the founders (including the marquee name, Andre Cronje) leaving the board amid the collapse, with public finger-pointing over who owns the failed tokenomics/airdrop. Community mood is deeply negative (mercenary liquidity gone, ~98% TVL loss). Counter-signals: developer/GitHub activity is still real (400 PRs merged in 2026, v2.2.0 with 6 release candidates, private testnet) and Cronje''s Flying Tulip DeFi venture on Sonic raised at a $1B valuation — a striking split between his new project''s valuation and the network''s collapsed one. Media framing is ''rebuild trust from the ashes'' under a new, lower-profile management team.","outlook":"BULL: FeeM''s builder subsidy + Cronje''s Flying Tulip launch + USSD stablecoin seed genuine organic demand that finally replaces the departed mercenary liquidity, and the new team rebuilds credibility — trigger is Flying Tulip going live and pulling sticky TVL. BASE (most likely): Sonic limps along as a technically-capable but demand-starved L1 — real GitHub activity but structurally low TVL, ongoing dilution, and a token that grinds near lows while the new management slowly tries to rebuild. BEAR: the leadership vacuum and lost trust prove terminal, Flying Tulip disappoints or decouples entirely, dilution (airdrop unlocks, 1.5% mint, USSD issuance) overwhelms thin demand, and Sonic fades toward irrelevance like post-hack Fantom. Top risks: (1) no organic demand to replace incentive-bought liquidity — the core proven lesson; (2) governance/leadership instability after the founder exodus. Watch: Flying Tulip launch + TVL it attracts, whether FeeM pulls quality builders, USSD adoption vs its dilutive issuance, TVL trend off the ~$20M floor. Base case most likely — incentives bought TVL not loyalty, and nothing yet shows organic demand replacing it.","success_factors_missing":["no_liquidity_moat","no_killer_app","token_overhang","fading_community"],"sources":[{"title":"Andre Cronje Departs Sonic Labs Board Amid Token Slump (HTX Insights)","url":"https://www.htx.com/en-in/news/andre-cronje-departs-sonic-labs-board-amid-token-slump-sWvWSXvu/"},{"title":"Sonic Labs Founders Including Cronje Quit Board as New CEO Pledges to Get ''1% Better'' (The Defiant)","url":"https://thedefiant.io/news/blockchains/sonic-labs-founders-including-andre-cronje-quit-board-as-new-ceo-pledges-to-get-1-better-daily"},{"title":"Andre Cronje leaves Sonic board as token slump sparks overhaul (crypto.news)","url":"https://crypto.news/andre-cronje-leaves-sonic-board-as-token-slump-sparks-overhaul/"},{"title":"What Is Sonic Network: S Token & Fantom Rebrand Guide 2026 (DEXTools)","url":"https://www.dextools.io/tutorials/what-is-sonic-network-s-token-fantom-rebrand-guide-2026"}]}','[{"title":"Andre Cronje Departs Sonic Labs Board Amid Token Slump (HTX Insights)","url":"https://www.htx.com/en-in/news/andre-cronje-departs-sonic-labs-board-amid-token-slump-sWvWSXvu/"},{"title":"Sonic Labs Founders Including Cronje Quit Board as New CEO Pledges to Get ''1% Better'' (The Defiant)","url":"https://thedefiant.io/news/blockchains/sonic-labs-founders-including-andre-cronje-quit-board-as-new-ceo-pledges-to-get-1-better-daily"},{"title":"Andre Cronje leaves Sonic board as token slump sparks overhaul (crypto.news)","url":"https://crypto.news/andre-cronje-leaves-sonic-board-as-token-slump-sparks-overhaul/"},{"title":"What Is Sonic Network: S Token & Fantom Rebrand Guide 2026 (DEXTools)","url":"https://www.dextools.io/tutorials/what-is-sonic-network-s-token-fantom-rebrand-guide-2026"}]','2026-07-08 15:13:24');
INSERT INTO "mid_chains" ("chain","launched","tvl","verdict","why_stuck","outlook","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('Celo','2020-04',16961959,'pivoting','Celo was a mobile-first, stablecoin-payments L1 that raised ~$65M+ but never won DeFi liquidity or developers as a standalone chain, so in March 2025 it abandoned sovereignty and migrated to become an Ethereum L2 on the OP Stack + EigenDA. It has genuine real-world usage (700k daily active addresses, $6.2B monthly stablecoin volume), but value flows through stablecoins, not the CELO token — which remains deeply depressed (~62% down YTD, far off ATH).','BULL: the buyback-and-burn value-capture mechanism (Feb 2026 proposal: 50%+ of protocol profits to buy and burn CELO) passes and works, tying record usage to token demand, while Superchain + Stripe/Bridge scale payments — trigger is a live, meaningful protocol-revenue-funded burn. BASE (most likely): Celo keeps winning the payments/DAU race with real product-market fit, but token value capture stays weak because usage flows through stablecoins, so CELO stays disconnected from adoption and range-bound near lows. BEAR: a speculative crypto cycle rewards high-TVL chains and ignores high-DAU Celo, payments competition (Tron, Stellar, Solana) erodes its lead, and the burn mechanism underdelivers. Top risks: (1) unsolved token value capture; (2) fierce stablecoin-payments competition eroding the MiniPay lead. Watch: the buyback-and-burn proposal outcome and burn magnitude, DAU/USDT-transport lead vs Tron/Stellar, Stripe/Bridge volume, Jovian upgrade. Base case most likely — genuine product-market fit the token structurally fails to monetize.','{"founded":"2020-04","founders":"Rene Reinsberg and Marek Olszewski (cLabs)","raised":"~$65M+; $30M (2019, a16z/Polychain), $10M CELO sale, plus reserve funding; investors incl. a16z, Polychain, Coinbase Ventures","token_symbol":"CELO","token_ath":10.66,"token_ath_date":"2021-08","token_current":0.086,"purpose":"A mobile-first payments/financial-inclusion chain using phone-number addresses and local stablecoins (cUSD/Mento), gas payable in stablecoins; migrated from L1 to an Ethereum L2 on the OP Stack in March 2025","whats_working":"#1 Ethereum L2 by daily active users (840k DAU, 1.3M MAU) and #1 transport layer for USDT by weekly active users (ahead of Tron); $65B+ stablecoin volume since migration; 11M MiniPay wallets via Opera distribution in Africa; Stripe/Bridge integration (7 May 2026); fees <$0.01; Espresso sub-1s finality + Jovian OP Stack upgrade (H1 2026); Uniswap/Stabila $750k liquidity program","whats_not":"Token value-capture failure — nobody needs CELO to send cUSD/USDT; DeFi TVL modest (~$150-300M, ~20x less than Base); CELO ~99.2% below 2021 ATH (~$0.086); roadmap now partly dependent on Optimism governance; speculative-cycle risk (capital flows to high-TVL chains, not high-DAU ones)","situation":"Celo is pivoting (already executed the hard part) and the pivot is going well on product, poorly on token. WHY: as a standalone L1 it never won DeFi liquidity/developers, so it migrated to an Ethereum L2 on the OP Stack + EigenDA (completed March 26 2025, the first full state migration of a major chain). HOW it''s going: extremely well on usage — Celo became the #1 Ethereum L2 by daily active users (840k DAU, 1.3M MAU) and #1 transport layer for USDT by weekly actives, ahead of Tron, on $65B+ stablecoin volume and 11M MiniPay wallets. WHAT it accomplishes: 99.8% lower security cost, Superchain interoperability with Base/Optimism, and shared liquidity. WHAT''S UNIQUE vs Tron/Stellar/Solana in payments: the MiniPay-in-Opera distribution on $50 Android phones across Africa/LatAm/SEA with phone-number addressing and stablecoin gas — no app download, no bank account. Recent catalysts: Stripe/Bridge integration (7 May 2026) and the Jovian upgrade (H1 2026).","non_economic":"Usage-based social signals are exceptional for a chain priced near lows: it leads ALL Ethereum L2s in daily active users — a metric drawn from genuine emerging-market payment use, not speculation — and its MiniPay/Opera distribution gives it a real-world user base rivals can''t easily copy. Ecosystem developer activity is steady (Jovian hardfork, Espresso finality integration among 20+ chains, Uniswap liquidity incentives). Media framing is sympathetic-but-frustrated: ''more real users than any L2, priced as if failing.'' The reputational dent: a Coinbase/Celo network delay episode raised some ecosystem-confidence questions. Net non-economic story is strongly positive on adoption, weak on speculative/DeFi mindshare.","outlook":"BULL: the buyback-and-burn value-capture mechanism (Feb 2026 proposal: 50%+ of protocol profits to buy and burn CELO) passes and works, tying record usage to token demand, while Superchain + Stripe/Bridge scale payments — trigger is a live, meaningful protocol-revenue-funded burn. BASE (most likely): Celo keeps winning the payments/DAU race with real product-market fit, but token value capture stays weak because usage flows through stablecoins, so CELO stays disconnected from adoption and range-bound near lows. BEAR: a speculative crypto cycle rewards high-TVL chains and ignores high-DAU Celo, payments competition (Tron, Stellar, Solana) erodes its lead, and the burn mechanism underdelivers. Top risks: (1) unsolved token value capture — no structural reason to hold CELO; (2) fierce stablecoin-payments competition eroding the MiniPay lead. Watch: the buyback-and-burn proposal outcome and burn magnitude, DAU/USDT-transport lead vs Tron/Stellar, Stripe/Bridge volume, Jovian upgrade. Base case most likely — genuine product-market fit that the token structurally fails to monetize.","success_factors_missing":["unclear_positioning","token_overhang","no_liquidity_moat"],"sources":[{"title":"Celo Evolved into L2 Network with Growing TVL and Volume (DappRadar)","url":"https://dappradar.com/blog/celo-evolved-into-l2-network-with-growing-tvl-and-volume"},{"title":"Celo Token News: L2 Migration and Stablecoin Growth (Bitget Wallet)","url":"https://web3.bitget.com/crypto-news/celo-surges-on-layer-2-transition-and-stablecoin-growth"},{"title":"What Is Celo? Mobile-First L2 and Stablecoin Rails (eco.com)","url":"https://eco.com/support/en/articles/15183710-what-is-celo-mobile-first-l2-and-stablecoin-rails"},{"title":"Celo Highlights Accessible DeFi and Stablecoin Payments at Optimism Scaling Summit (Blockchain.News)","url":"https://blockchain.news/flashnews/celo-highlights-accessible-defi-and-stablecoin-payments-at-optimism-scaling-summit"}]}','[{"title":"Celo Evolved into L2 Network with Growing TVL and Volume (DappRadar)","url":"https://dappradar.com/blog/celo-evolved-into-l2-network-with-growing-tvl-and-volume"},{"title":"Celo Token News: L2 Migration and Stablecoin Growth (Bitget Wallet)","url":"https://web3.bitget.com/crypto-news/celo-surges-on-layer-2-transition-and-stablecoin-growth"},{"title":"What Is Celo? Mobile-First L2 and Stablecoin Rails (eco.com)","url":"https://eco.com/support/en/articles/15183710-what-is-celo-mobile-first-l2-and-stablecoin-rails"},{"title":"Celo Highlights Accessible DeFi and Stablecoin Payments at Optimism Scaling Summit (Blockchain.News)","url":"https://blockchain.news/flashnews/celo-highlights-accessible-defi-and-stablecoin-payments-at-optimism-scaling-summit"}]','2026-07-08 15:14:45');
INSERT INTO "mid_chains" ("chain","launched","tvl","verdict","why_stuck","outlook","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('Injective','2021-11',7710406,'quietly_building','Injective is a finance-specialized L1 with a native on-chain order book and a strong deflationary burn-auction model, but its TVL is tiny (~$8-19M) — objectively small for a top-tier L1 — which critics read as shallow DeFi depth. Its capital-efficient CLOB design means it doesn''t lock much TVL even while clearing tens of billions in cumulative volume, so the chain is caught between a real product and thin, unconvincing on-chain footprint. Token ~85%+ off ATH.','BULL: the MultiVM + RWA + ETF stack converts — an INJ ETF is approved after the Oct 15 2026 qualifying window, EVM brings a wave of Solidity dApps, and iAssets RWA markets scale, deepening sticky liquidity while the Supply Squeeze burns supply — trigger is ETF approval plus a breakout EVM-native app. BASE (most likely): Injective stays a capital-efficient, high-revenue, deflationary finance L1 with real institutional access but structurally thin TVL — respected, revenue-positive, yet under-used relative to its infrastructure. BEAR: EVM fails to attract durable builders, RWA/ETF catalysts slip, TVL stays tiny, and INJ trades as a narrative token disconnected from adoption. Top risks: (1) chronic shallow liquidity despite strong infra/revenue; (2) ETF timeline/approval risk. Watch: INJ ETF decisions post-Oct 15 2026, EVM dApp/TVL growth after Vulcan, iAssets RWA traction, burn magnitude. Base case most likely — excellent deflationary infrastructure whose thin footprint hasn''t converted into deep usage.','{"founded":"2021-11","founders":"Eric Chen and Albert Chon (Injective Labs)","raised":"~$56M; Binance Labs incubation (2018), $10M (2021, Pantera/Jump/Mark Cuban), $40M (2023 ecosystem fund led by Jump)","token_symbol":"INJ","token_ath":52.62,"token_ath_date":"2024-03","token_current":4.61,"purpose":"A finance-focused, interoperable L1 (Cosmos SDK) with a native central-limit order book module for derivatives/spot and a deflationary burn auction; now MultiVM (native EVM + WASM shared state)","whats_working":"Native EVM/MultiVM live (Nov 11 2025, shared state, Hardhat/Foundry support, day-one CLOB liquidity); Vulcan upgrade (June 9 2026: lower fees, native USDC, RWA markets); 10th-highest-earning L1 by revenue (~$3.34M TTM) on tiny TVL; INJ Supply Squeeze (IIP-617, 99.96% yes) unifying burn auction + monthly BuyBack (6.78M INJ burned pre-launch, ~7% supply); native USDC via Circle CCTP V2 (May 7 2026); iAssets RWA (equities, commodities, Nvidia H100 rates); ~$33B cumulative derivatives volume","whats_not":"Very low TVL (~$10.7M) signals shallow DeFi depth; adoption grows unevenly; heavy reliance on EVM/RWA/ETF catalysts converting into sticky liquidity; INJ ~85%+ off ATH; capital-efficient CLOB means little TVL locked even at scale","situation":"Injective is pivoting (verdict quietly_building/pivoting) toward being the settlement layer for on-chain finance and RWAs, and execution is dense. WHY: its native-CLOB design clears huge volume ($33B+ derivatives since Jan 2025) but locks almost no TVL (~$10.7M), so critics read it as shallow — it needs a broader developer/liquidity base. HOW: it shipped Native EVM/MultiVM (Nov 11 2025) unifying EVM+WASM state so Solidity devs get day-one CLOB liquidity (solving cold-start), then IIP-619 ''Real-Time EVM'' (Feb 19 2026) and the Vulcan upgrade (June 9 2026: lower fees, native USDC, new RWA markets, better oracles). WHAT it accomplishes: a MultiVM finance chain with deflationary tokenomics (INJ Supply Squeeze IIP-617, 99.96% approval, tying burn auction + monthly BuyBacks). WHAT''S UNIQUE: the native on-chain order book + iAssets tokenizing equities/commodities/GPU-rental rates, plus a credible US-regulated path (Bitnomial INJ futures live April 15 2026, three ETF filings, a D.C. policy institute).","non_economic":"Governance cohesion is a standout non-economic signal — IIP-617 passed with 99.96% approval, and the burn/BuyBack program has strong participant engagement (four monthly rounds, each larger, >20% returns each round). Institutional/policy activity is heavy: Bitnomial regulated INJ futures (April 15 2026), three ETF filings (21Shares, Canary, REX-Osprey) with an October 15 2026 earliest qualifying window, a staked-INJ ETF amendment, Merkle Capital''s regulated M-INJ fund in Thailand, the Injective Policy Institute in D.C., and a July 16 2026 Injective Summit in Washington. Developer signal improved with EVM support drawing Solidity builders. The persistent weak signal: thin TVL/on-chain footprint keeps the ''well-built chain few people use'' critique alive.","outlook":"BULL: the MultiVM + RWA + ETF stack converts — an INJ ETF is approved after the Oct 15 2026 qualifying window, EVM brings a wave of Solidity dApps, and iAssets RWA markets scale, finally deepening sticky liquidity while the Supply Squeeze burns supply — trigger is ETF approval plus a breakout EVM-native app. BASE (most likely): Injective stays a capital-efficient, high-revenue, deflationary finance L1 with real institutional access but structurally thin TVL — respected, revenue-positive, yet still under-used relative to its infrastructure. BEAR: EVM fails to attract durable builders, RWA/ETF catalysts underdeliver or slip, TVL stays tiny, and INJ trades as a narrative token disconnected from broad adoption. Top risks: (1) chronic shallow liquidity/adoption despite strong infra and revenue; (2) ETF timeline/approval risk (not guaranteed, SEC-dependent). Watch: INJ ETF decisions post-Oct 15 2026, EVM dApp/TVL growth after Vulcan, iAssets RWA traction, burn magnitude under the Supply Squeeze. Base case most likely — excellent, deflationary infrastructure whose thin footprint has yet to convert into deep, sticky usage.","success_factors_missing":["no_liquidity_moat","poor_distribution","unclear_positioning"],"sources":[{"title":"Welcome to the Injective Era: Native EVM Mainnet Launch (Injective)","url":"https://injective.com/blog/welcome-to-the-injective-era-native-evm-mainnet-launch-opens-new-frontiers-for-finance"},{"title":"2026 Injective Community BuyBack Guide: Burn INJ. Earn Revenue. (Injective)","url":"https://injective.com/blog/2026-injective-community-buy-back-guide"},{"title":"Injective''s Strategic Position in Onchain RWA Derivatives and EVM Integration (AInvest)","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/injective-strategic-position-onchain-rwa-derivatives-evm-integration-2512/"},{"title":"Why Institutional Adoption Depends on Better On-Chain Infrastructure (CryptoRank)","url":"https://cryptorank.io/insights/research/institutional-adoption-and-onchain-infrastructure"}]}','[{"title":"Welcome to the Injective Era: Native EVM Mainnet Launch (Injective)","url":"https://injective.com/blog/welcome-to-the-injective-era-native-evm-mainnet-launch-opens-new-frontiers-for-finance"},{"title":"2026 Injective Community BuyBack Guide: Burn INJ. Earn Revenue. (Injective)","url":"https://injective.com/blog/2026-injective-community-buy-back-guide"},{"title":"Injective''s Strategic Position in Onchain RWA Derivatives and EVM Integration (AInvest)","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/injective-strategic-position-onchain-rwa-derivatives-evm-integration-2512/"},{"title":"Why Institutional Adoption Depends on Better On-Chain Infrastructure (CryptoRank)","url":"https://cryptorank.io/insights/research/institutional-adoption-and-onchain-infrastructure"}]','2026-07-08 15:15:30');
INSERT INTO "mid_chains" ("chain","launched","tvl","verdict","why_stuck","outlook","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('Sei','2023-08',46432164,'pivoting','Sei launched as a Cosmos-based, order-book-optimized ''trading chain'' but has repeatedly re-architected itself: v2 to parallelized EVM, then a full EVM-only pivot (SIP-3) that disables IBC and deprecates CosmWasm, alienating its original Cosmos community. TVL collapsed from ~$626M (Jul 2025) to ~$42-46M, native DEXs like Oxium are shutting down citing insurmountable losses, and heavy monthly token unlocks (112-132M through mid-2027) weigh on price.','BULL: Giga ships on mainnet delivering its performance claims, the Sedna privacy layer + EVM tooling attract institutional trading flow and Solidity builders, and Ondo/Morpho/RWA integrations plus an ETF reverse the capital flight — trigger is Giga mainnet at real throughput pulling sticky institutional TVL. BASE (most likely): Sei stays a fast EVM chain with high address activity but structurally thin, non-sticky TVL, weighed down by heavy unlocks and an unstable identity; SEI grinds near lows as the high-speed thesis stays unproven at scale. BEAR: Giga slips or underdelivers off devnet, more native apps fail like Oxium, the Cosmos-community exodus isn''t replaced by durable EVM demand, and monthly unlocks crush price. Top risks: (1) capital flight + non-sticky liquidity a third pivot may not fix; (2) persistent unlock-driven sell pressure with ~33% supply still locked. Watch: Giga mainnet activation + real TPS, TVL trend off ~$42M, Ondo/Morpho/RWA deposits, SEI ETF decisions, unlock cadence. Base case most likely — a high-speed chain still searching for durable demand after two identity changes.','{"founded":"2023-08","founders":"Jayendra Jog and Jeff Feng (Sei Labs)","raised":"~$120M; $5M seed (2022, Multicoin), $30M round (2023, Jump/Distributed Global) at $800M valuation, plus $120M ecosystem fund","token_symbol":"SEI","token_ath":1.14,"token_ath_date":"2024-03","token_current":0.046,"purpose":"A high-speed L1 optimized for trading with a built-in order-matching engine and parallel execution; originally Cosmos, now pivoted EVM-only","whats_working":"Fast parallelized EVM, Giga roadmap (Autobahn multi-proposer consensus + async execution, 200k+ TPS, devnet 5 gigagas/s, sub-400ms finality) and Sedna MEV-resistant privacy layer (Whitepaper V2, July 1 2026); EVM tooling (Solidity/Hardhat/MetaMask) via one-time migration; Coinbase migration support; institutional integrations (Ondo USDY tokenized Treasuries, Morpho Vaults V2, Wyoming WYST stablecoin pilot); record 1.2M daily active addresses reported early 2026","whats_not":"TVL collapsed ~93% from ~$626M (Jul 2025) to ~$41.6M (April 2026); native DEXs shutting down (Oxium cited ''insurmountable financial difficulties''); repeated identity pivots alienated original Cosmos community; heavy unlocks (112-132M SEI/month through mid-2027, ~33% supply locked); devnet-only performance claims; Jan 2026 network outage; Upbit halted STRK... (SEI) withdrawals-style reliability worries","situation":"Sei is pivoting hard — its third major re-architecture. WHY: as a Cosmos order-book ''trading chain'' it never retained capital, so it went EVM-only (irreversible migration April 6-8 2026, IBC transfers disabled, CosmWasm deprecated) to tap Ethereum''s developer base and solve weak capital retention. HOW it''s going: mixed — EVM tooling and Coinbase migration support are in place and daily active addresses hit a reported 1.2M, but TVL cratered ~93% from ~$626M (Jul 2025) to ~$41.6M (April 2026), and native flagship DEX Oxium shut down citing ''insurmountable financial difficulties.'' WHAT the pivot accomplishes: EVM-first accessibility + the Giga upgrade (Autobahn multi-proposer consensus, async execution, targeting 200k+ TPS / sub-400ms finality; devnet hit 5 gigagas/s). WHAT''S UNIQUE vs other fast EVMs: automatic dependency-based parallelization plus the Sedna privacy layer (Giga Whitepaper V2, July 1 2026) fragmenting tx data across proposer lanes for sub-250ms MEV-resistant finality aimed at institutional traders. Catch: performance is devnet-only and the identity has now shifted twice.","non_economic":"The dominant non-economic risk is community fracture from repeated identity pivots — the EVM-only shift ''risks alienating the original Cosmos-based community that supported Sei early,'' a recurring analyst concern, while flagship-app failures (Oxium''s shutdown) dent ecosystem morale. Engagement metrics are a counter-signal: Token Relations reported record 1.2M daily active addresses and 2.2M returning users early 2026, suggesting interaction even without capital retention. Institutional signaling is building (Ondo USDY, Morpho, Wyoming WYST stablecoin pilot selection, pending SEI ETF filings, Coinbase migration support). Reliability incidents (Jan 2026 outage, exchange withdrawal friction) hurt trust. Net: activity and institutional interest are real, but the community narrative is unstable and capital won''t stay.","outlook":"BULL: Giga ships on mainnet delivering its performance claims, the Sedna privacy layer + EVM tooling attract institutional trading flow and Solidity builders, and Ondo/Morpho/RWA integrations plus an ETF reverse the capital flight — trigger is Giga mainnet at real throughput pulling sticky institutional TVL. BASE (most likely): Sei stays a fast EVM chain with high address activity but structurally thin, non-sticky TVL, weighed down by heavy unlocks and an unstable identity; SEI grinds near lows as the high-speed thesis stays unproven at scale. BEAR: Giga slips or underdelivers off devnet, more native apps fail like Oxium, the Cosmos-community exodus isn''t replaced by durable EVM demand, and monthly unlocks (112-132M through mid-2027) crush price. Top risks: (1) capital flight + non-sticky liquidity that a third pivot may not fix; (2) persistent unlock-driven sell pressure with ~33% supply still locked. Watch: Giga mainnet activation + real (not devnet) TPS, TVL trend off the ~$42M floor, Ondo/Morpho/RWA deposit growth, SEI ETF decisions, unlock cadence. Base case most likely — a high-speed chain still searching for durable demand after two identity changes.","success_factors_missing":["no_liquidity_moat","unclear_positioning","token_overhang","fading_community"],"sources":[{"title":"Sei Giga Overview: The Fastest EVM Blockchain (Sei Docs)","url":"https://docs.sei.io/learn/sei-giga"},{"title":"Coinbase SEI Migration: The Shift to EVM-Only Architecture Begins (CryptoRank)","url":"https://cryptorank.io/news/feed/6b277-coinbase-sei-evm-migration-support"},{"title":"Sei Giga Upgrade: 50x Faster Execution for the EVM Era (Everstake)","url":"https://everstake.one/resources/blog/sei-giga-upgrade-50x-faster-execution-for-the-evm-era"},{"title":"Does Sei (SEI) have a future? — A 2026 Market Analysis (WEEX)","url":"https://www.weex.com/questions/article/does-sei-sei-have-a-future-a-2026-market-analysis-lccbdn7ngxt0ydy9ojmaa3x9"}]}','[{"title":"Sei Giga Overview: The Fastest EVM Blockchain (Sei Docs)","url":"https://docs.sei.io/learn/sei-giga"},{"title":"Coinbase SEI Migration: The Shift to EVM-Only Architecture Begins (CryptoRank)","url":"https://cryptorank.io/news/feed/6b277-coinbase-sei-evm-migration-support"},{"title":"Sei Giga Upgrade: 50x Faster Execution for the EVM Era (Everstake)","url":"https://everstake.one/resources/blog/sei-giga-upgrade-50x-faster-execution-for-the-evm-era"},{"title":"Does Sei (SEI) have a future? — A 2026 Market Analysis (WEEX)","url":"https://www.weex.com/questions/article/does-sei-sei-have-a-future-a-2026-market-analysis-lccbdn7ngxt0ydy9ojmaa3x9"}]','2026-07-08 15:16:53');
INSERT INTO "mid_chains" ("chain","launched","tvl","verdict","why_stuck","outlook","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('Starknet','2021-11',174399909,'pivoting','Starknet raised over $280M as a marquee ZK-rollup, but its non-EVM Cairo language imposes developer switching costs, and it trails EVM-equivalent L2s (Arbitrum, zkSync) on TVL and developer activity — Aztec even passed it in GitHub rankings. TVL recovered off 2025 lows but has plateaued (~$170-600M by methodology), bridge volume is thin, and STRK trades ~95% off highs under monthly unlocks running through March 2027.','BULL: BTCFi liquidity stays sticky after the 100M STRK incentives taper, strkBTC private-Bitcoin + Shinobi privacy find real institutional demand, and Starknet establishes a durable ''Bitcoin execution + privacy layer'' thesis distinct from EVM L2s — trigger is BTC staked climbing post-incentives plus institutional strkBTC adoption. BASE (most likely): BTCFi gives Starknet a differentiated niche and some TVL recovery, but it remains a smaller ZK-rollup ceding general-purpose dev share to EVM L2s, STRK capped by heavy unlocks through March 2027. BEAR: BTC staking proves incentive-dependent and unwinds when rewards taper, privacy sees limited usage, EVM L2s keep winning devs, and reliability issues + unlocks push STRK to new lows. Top risks: (1) BTCFi TVL being mercenary/incentive-driven; (2) chronic non-EVM Cairo developer disadvantage + ~38% insider unlock overhang. Watch: BTC staked trend as incentives taper, strkBTC institutional adoption, Staking v4 decentralization, dev activity vs EVM L2s, unlock cadence. Base case most likely — the BTC pivot is real and unique but its durability past incentives is unproven.','{"founded":"2021-11","founders":"Eli Ben-Sasson, Uri Kolodny, Michael Riabzev, Alessandro Chiesa (StarkWare)","raised":"~$282M+; incl. $75M Series C (2021, Sequoia/Paradigm) and $100M (2022) at $8B valuation; StarkWare","token_symbol":"STRK","token_ath":4.42,"token_ath_date":"2024-02","token_current":0.03,"purpose":"A ZK-rollup L2 scaling Ethereum using STARK proofs and the Cairo language for high throughput with Ethereum-level security","whats_working":"First rollup with BTC+STRK dual-token consensus (STRK 75% / BTC 25% of security), fast-growing BTC staking (1,791 BTC / ~$166M within a month), 100M STRK BTCFi incentives + Re7 institutional BTC yield, strkBTC shielded/private-BTC wrapper (launched May 2026, compliance-ready), Shinobi (v0.14.2) native in-protocol privacy (SNIP-36), Anchorage Digital institutional staking, stablecoins ATH >$150M, top-4 rollup by app revenue, Starkzap TypeScript SDK, quantum-resistance roadmap (June 30 2026)","whats_not":"Non-EVM Cairo raises developer switching costs; trails Arbitrum/zkSync on TVL and devs; Aztec passed Starknet in GitHub activity; STRK ~95% off ATH near all-time lows; heavy monthly unlocks (38.21% supply to insiders, through March 15 2027); Jan 2026 network outage + Upbit STRK withdrawal halt (July 1 2026) reliability concerns","situation":"Starknet is pivoting toward Bitcoin, and it''s its strongest card. WHY: as a non-EVM Cairo ZK-rollup it imposed developer switching costs and lost TVL/dev share to EVM L2s (Arbitrum, zkSync; Aztec even passed it on GitHub), so it repositioned around BTCFi. HOW it''s going: strongly on adoption — it became the FIRST rollup with a dual-token consensus (STRK 75% / BTC 25% of security), BTC staking went live and drew 1,791 BTC (~$166M) within a month, backed by 100M STRK incentives + a Re7 institutional BTC yield strategy and Anchorage Digital staking; TVL tripled off its bottom and stablecoins hit ATH >$150M. WHAT it accomplishes: it turns idle Bitcoin into productive, yield-bearing, network-securing capital. WHAT''S UNIQUE: strkBTC (launched May 2026) — a ZK-shielded, compliance-ready ''private Bitcoin'' wrapper from Zcash co-founder Eli Ben-Sasson (''private digital cash the way it should be''), plus native in-protocol privacy via the Shinobi upgrade (SNIP-36) and a BitVM/OP_CAT trustless-bridge roadmap. The strkBTC launch sparked a ~50% STRK pop.","non_economic":"Non-economic signals are mixed but improving. Positive: a differentiated privacy/BTCFi narrative led by a credible cryptographer (Ben-Sasson, Zcash co-founder), institutional validation (Anchorage, Re7), and the strkBTC launch reviving mindshare (50% price pop). The privacy pitch is timely — CertiK logged 34 incidents in early 2026 (+41% YoY) with AI de-anonymizing wallets at up to 90% precision, giving shielded-BTC a real use case. Negative: developer competition is a losing battle on the EVM front — Aztec surpassed Starknet in GitHub activity, and Cairo''s switching costs keep the builder base narrow vs Arbitrum/zkSync. Reliability incidents (Jan 2026 outage, Upbit halting STRK withdrawals July 1 2026) hurt trust. Net: BTCFi/privacy narrative is energizing the community even as core EVM-L2 developer competition goes against it.","outlook":"BULL: BTCFi liquidity stays sticky after the 100M STRK incentives taper, strkBTC private-Bitcoin + Shinobi privacy find real institutional demand (shielded, compliance-ready BTC), and Starknet establishes a durable ''Bitcoin execution + privacy layer'' thesis distinct from EVM L2s — trigger is BTC staked continuing to climb post-incentives plus institutional strkBTC adoption. BASE (most likely): BTCFi gives Starknet a genuine differentiated niche and some TVL recovery, but it remains a smaller ZK-rollup ceding general-purpose dev share to EVM L2s, with STRK capped by heavy unlocks through March 2027. BEAR: BTC staking proves incentive-dependent and unwinds when rewards taper, privacy features see limited real usage, EVM L2s keep winning developers, and reliability issues + unlocks push STRK to new lows. Top risks: (1) BTCFi TVL being mercenary/incentive-driven, not organic; (2) chronic developer disadvantage of non-EVM Cairo + ~38% insider unlock overhang. Watch: BTC staked trend as incentives taper, strkBTC institutional adoption, Staking v4 decentralization, GitHub/dev activity vs EVM L2s, unlock cadence through March 2027. Base case (differentiated niche, still sub-scale vs EVM L2s) most likely — the BTC pivot is real and unique but its durability past incentives is unproven.","success_factors_missing":["tech_no_adoption","weak_dev_ecosystem","outcompeted","token_overhang"],"sources":[{"title":"Starknet launches strkBTC to bring ZK-powered shielded bitcoin to its L2 (The Block)","url":"https://www.theblock.co/post/400903/starknet-launches-strkbtc-to-bring-zk-powered-shielded-bitcoin-to-its-layer-2-network"},{"title":"Starknet''s Big BTCFi Bet: Bitcoin Staking Goes Live (Bankless)","url":"https://www.bankless.com/read/starknet-btcfi-bitcoin-staking"},{"title":"How Starknet''s Q3 Paved the Way for Bitcoin, Decentralization (Starknet Blog)","url":"https://www.starknet.io/blog/how-starknets-q3-paved-the-way-for-bitcoin-decentralization-and-the-future-of-crypto/"},{"title":"Starknet Unveils 100M STRK Initiative to Bring Bitcoin DeFi to Its Network (The Defiant)","url":"https://thedefiant.io/news/defi/starknet-announced-btcfi-bitcoin-staking-initiative"}]}','[{"title":"Starknet launches strkBTC to bring ZK-powered shielded bitcoin to its L2 (The Block)","url":"https://www.theblock.co/post/400903/starknet-launches-strkbtc-to-bring-zk-powered-shielded-bitcoin-to-its-layer-2-network"},{"title":"Starknet''s Big BTCFi Bet: Bitcoin Staking Goes Live (Bankless)","url":"https://www.bankless.com/read/starknet-btcfi-bitcoin-staking"},{"title":"How Starknet''s Q3 Paved the Way for Bitcoin, Decentralization (Starknet Blog)","url":"https://www.starknet.io/blog/how-starknets-q3-paved-the-way-for-bitcoin-decentralization-and-the-future-of-crypto/"},{"title":"Starknet Unveils 100M STRK Initiative to Bring Bitcoin DeFi to Its Network (The Defiant)","url":"https://thedefiant.io/news/defi/starknet-announced-btcfi-bitcoin-staking-initiative"}]','2026-07-08 15:17:38');
INSERT INTO "nft_collections" ("slug","name","chain","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('bored-ape-yacht-club','Bored Ape Yacht Club','ethereum','pfp-blue-chip','fading','{"name": "Bored Ape Yacht Club", "chain": "ethereum", "category": "pfp-blue-chip", "launched": "2021-04", "supply": 9998, "mint_raise_usd": 2200000, "mint_price": "0.08 ETH (~$220)", "floor_current": 9.19, "floor_ath": 153.7, "floor_ath_date": "2022-04", "secondary_volume_usd": 6000000000, "royalties_enforced": "optional", "royalties_earned_usd": 166000000, "holder_count": 5690, "holder_count_peak": 6500, "holder_retention_pct": 88, "founder_engagement": "Yuga Labs still active but retrenching hard in 2025 — sold CryptoPunks to a nonprofit and offloaded Moonbirds IP; core BAYC team shipping less, Otherside stalled.", "social": "Once the cultural center of NFTs; X/Discord now quiet, sentiment nostalgic-to-negative. ApeCoin underperformed badly.", "benefits": "Commercial IP rights to holders, Otherside metaverse land, ApeChain, exclusive events (ApeFest). IP value the main draw.", "lifespan_days": 1900, "status": "fading", "community_history": "BAYC was the social nexus of the 2021-22 NFT bull run — its Discord and the ''gm'' culture defined the era, and celebrity ape-ins (Jimmy Fallon revealing Ape #599 on The Tonight Show in Jan 2022, Eminem buying #9055 for ~$452K) turned it into mainstream status jewelry. The arc curdled after: a Dec 2022 SEC/celebrity-promotion class action (Fallon, Madonna, Paris Hilton, Justin Bieber, Snoop named for undisclosed paid promos, dismissed 2025 with a ruling that NFTs aren''t securities), the ApeCoin collapse, and Blur''s 2023 royalty war all draining the culture. By its 5th anniversary (April 2026) coverage openly noted ''nobody seems to care.''", "community_sentiment": "Faded and nostalgic-to-bitter. Google Trends interest is ~97x below the 2022 peak; the celebrity cohort has gone silent (Eminem hasn''t posted about BAYC since 2022, tops offers on his ape ~$20K vs the ~$452K he paid). Diehards remain loyal on IP-rights grounds, but the broader vibe is a fallen empire trading on memory rather than momentum.", "notable_holders": "Jimmy Fallon (Ape #599, ~$225K), Eminem (#9055, ~$452K, now underwater), Snoop Dogg (full BAYC/MAYC set via Cozomo de'' Medici alias), Post Malone (#961, #9039), Gwyneth Paltrow (#6141), Madonna (#4988), Paris Hilton (#1294), Steph Curry, Shaquille O''Neal, Timbaland (#590), Travis Barker (#7765), Gary Vaynerchuk. Most have gone quiet; several were named in the 2022 promotion lawsuit. Deepak Thapliyal also held BAYC #9452 (bought 347 ETH).", "marketplace_url": "https://opensea.io/collection/boredapeyachtclub", "business": "Yuga Labs is the real business BAYC spawned — a venture-backed IP conglomerate valued at ~$4B in a 2022 raise led by a16z. Its product lines span the ApeCoin token/ApeChain, the Otherside metaverse (land sold via ~$300M+ in Otherdeeds), Mutant Ape (MAYC) and Kennel Club spinoffs, physical ApeFest events, and licensed consumer deals (Adidas, Rolling Stone, a McFarlane toy line, and the ''10KTF'' and ''Made By Apes'' licensing program that turns holders'' IP rights into commercial products). Strengths: genuine blue-chip IP, holder commercial rights that seeded thousands of derivative businesses, and deep capital. Weaknesses: Otherside has repeatedly stalled and underdelivered, ApeCoin fell ~99% from its high, and by 2025 Yuga was actively shrinking — divesting CryptoPunks and Moonbirds — signaling the conglomerate strategy over-extended and is retrenching to a core it can defend.", "analysis": "BAYC is the archetypal blue-chip arc: a $2.2M mint that seeded a $6B+ secondary economy and $166M+ in Yuga royalties at the 2.5% rate — the single biggest royalty earner in NFT history — and became, for one improbable stretch, the closest thing crypto had to a mainstream cultural brand, complete with an A-list holder roster. Its floor fell ~94% from 153 ETH to ~9 ETH as the 2022 mania unwound and Yuga''s royalty enforcement (Operator Filter, Seaport sunset) lost the war to Blur''s optional-royalty model. Founder engagement is technically alive but visibly retrenching — the 2025 CryptoPunks/Moonbirds divestitures signal a company shrinking to its core. The 2022 celebrity-promotion class action (dismissed 2025 on the securities question) and a silent celebrity cohort mark how completely the cultural energy has drained. Yet holder retention stayed high (~88%) precisely because IP rights make apes sticky even as price collapsed — the value migrated from speculation to provenance.", "sources": [{"title": "Yuga Labs earned $147M+ royalties (Galaxy/Decrypt)", "url": "https://decrypt.co/113880/bored-ape-founders-nft-royalties-model-opensea"}, {"title": "BAYC $6B+ volume, $166M royalties (Coindesk/crypto.news)", "url": "https://crypto.news/nft-giants-are-protesting-blur-and-opensea-over-royalty-rates/"}, {"title": "Yuga sells Moonbirds IP / CryptoPunks (Blockworks)", "url": "https://blockworks.co/news/yuga-labs-moonbirds-sell"}, {"title": "Yuga Labs $4B valuation, Otherside/ApeCoin (Decrypt)", "url": "https://decrypt.co/113880/bored-ape-founders-nft-royalties-model-opensea"}, {"title": "Celebrity BAYC owners incl Fallon/Eminem/Snoop (Boardroom/Decrypt)", "url": "https://boardroom.tv/bored-ape-nft-celebrity-owners/"}, {"title": "BAYC turns five, nobody cares; Eminem ape underwater (Protos)", "url": "https://protos.com/bored-ape-yacht-club-turns-five-today-and-nobody-seems-to-care/"}, {"title": "Celebrity promotion class action (ArtNews)", "url": "https://www.artnews.com/art-news/news/bored-ape-yacht-club-nfts-lawsuit-madonna-jimmy-fallon-1234649797/"}, {"title": "OpenSea collection", "url": "https://opensea.io/collection/boredapeyachtclub"}, {"title": "CoinGecko live floor", "url": "https://www.coingecko.com/en/nft/bored-ape-yacht-club"}]}','[{"title": "Yuga Labs earned $147M+ royalties (Galaxy/Decrypt)", "url": "https://decrypt.co/113880/bored-ape-founders-nft-royalties-model-opensea"}, {"title": "BAYC $6B+ volume, $166M royalties (Coindesk/crypto.news)", "url": "https://crypto.news/nft-giants-are-protesting-blur-and-opensea-over-royalty-rates/"}, {"title": "Yuga sells Moonbirds IP / CryptoPunks (Blockworks)", "url": "https://blockworks.co/news/yuga-labs-moonbirds-sell"}, {"title": "CoinGecko live floor", "url": "https://www.coingecko.com/en/nft/bored-ape-yacht-club"}]','2026-07-08 15:34:33');
INSERT INTO "nft_collections" ("slug","name","chain","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('azuki','Azuki','ethereum','pfp-anime','fading','{"name": "Azuki", "chain": "ethereum", "category": "pfp-anime", "launched": "2022-01", "supply": 10000, "mint_raise_usd": 27000000, "mint_price": "1 ETH (~$3,400)", "floor_current": 1.11, "floor_ath": 30.5, "floor_ath_date": "2022-05", "secondary_volume_usd": 1000000000, "royalties_enforced": "optional", "royalties_earned_usd": 58000000, "holder_count": 4471, "holder_count_peak": 5500, "holder_retention_pct": 81, "founder_engagement": "Chiru Labs still shipping (ANIME token, Anime.com, TCG) but credibility scarred; founder Zagabond''s admission of abandoning prior projects + Elementals debacle drove a DAO lawsuit threat.", "social": "Strong anime-native community but sentiment cratered after Elementals; ANIME token launch (2025) sits ~88% below highs.", "benefits": "BEANZ companion, Elementals, physical merch, ANIME token/ecosystem, Anime.com IP platform.", "lifespan_days": 1640, "status": "fading", "community_history": "Azuki launched Jan 2022 as the anime-native answer to BAYC — 8,700 minted at 1 ETH in ~4 minutes (~$27M) — and ''The Garden'' Discord (now ~100K members, shared with BEANZ and Elementals) became one of the most engaged in NFT. Two events fractured the culture: (1) May 2022, founder Zagabond publicly admitted he had created and abandoned three prior projects (CryptoPhunks, Tendies, CryptoZunks) that the community branded rug pulls; (2) June 2023, the Elementals mint raised ~20,000 ETH ($38M) on art widely seen as near-duplicate of the originals, with no mint cap locking out the public — crashing the floor ~44% overnight, triggering $38M+ refund demands and a DAO lawsuit threat. Long-time holders began liquidating.", "community_sentiment": "Divided and skeptical. The Jan 2025 ANIME token launch reopened old wounds — holders criticized a small community airdrop (vs Pudgy''s generous cross-community distribution) and high team/insider allocation as a ''classic VC sell-off party,'' and it failed to rally the NFT floor the way Pudgy''s token did. The community now splits between believers in the long roadmap (AnimeChain, Anime.com, an anime series, a TCG) and skeptics who never recovered trust after Elementals and Zagabond''s past.", "notable_holders": "Azuki''s holder base skews anime/degen-native rather than celebrity; the collection lacks a marquee A-list roster comparable to BAYC. Notable early backing came from prominent NFT collectors and Asian crypto influencers, and Chiru Labs itself (Zagabond, 2pm.flow, HoshiBoy, Location Tba) holds and directs the ecosystem. Whale activity concentrates in the ''Gold''/rare-trait Azukis (e.g., the ''Spirit'' 1/1 sold for 420 ETH in 2022). Reporting has not surfaced a stable named-celebrity holder set.", "marketplace_url": "https://opensea.io/collection/azuki", "business": "Chiru Labs is building an anime-media business around Azuki: Anime.com (an IP/content platform positioning Azuki as anime''s crypto-native gateway), AnimeChain (an Arbitrix-Orbit L3 secured by the ANIME token), a physical/digital trading card game, a ''Hilumia'' anime anthology/animated series in development, and merch and event lines (e.g., the ''Physical Backed Token'' gold-skateboard drop with a real-world redeemable item). Strengths: a genuinely differentiated anime thesis, a large content-hungry fanbase, and a token to fund it. Weaknesses: execution and trust — the Elementals debacle and Zagabond''s rug-pull history mean every launch is met with suspicion, ANIME''s insider-heavy tokenomics undercut goodwill, and the anime-media ambitions remain largely promissory (no shipped hit series or TCG at scale), leaving the business more roadmap than revenue.", "analysis": "Azuki minted 8,700 at 1 ETH in 4 minutes (~$27M raise) and rocketed to a 30+ ETH floor and $1B+ secondary volume, earning Chiru Labs ~$58M in royalties. The June 2023 Elementals mint — ~20,000 ETH ($38M) raised on near-duplicate art with no mint cap — was the self-inflicted wound that crashed the floor 44% overnight and permanently broke trust, compounded by Zagabond''s earlier admission of abandoning three projects. The Jan 2025 ANIME token was the survival pivot every peer attempted, but Azuki executed it worst: an insider-heavy distribution that reopened the trust deficit instead of healing it, failing to lift the floor while Pudgy''s comparable move set new ATHs. A textbook case of a project monetizing its community faster than it delivered — Elementals, then ANIME — each cash-in chasing the credibility the last one burned, with an anime-native community loyal enough (~81% retention) to keep it alive but too scarred to reignite it.", "sources": [{"title": "Azuki mint 1 ETH, $1B volume, Elementals $38M (Coindesk)", "url": "https://www.coindesk.com/web3/2023/06/28/azuki-elementals-mint-mishap-highlights-the-fragile-state-of-the-nft-market"}, {"title": "Chiru Labs $58M royalties (Coindesk Nansen)", "url": "https://www.coindesk.com/web3/2023/07/05/nft-creator-royalty-payments-hit-two-year-low-nansen"}, {"title": "ANIME token launch, AnimeChain, Anime.com, insider allocation (Gate/Decrypt)", "url": "https://www.gate.com/learn/articles/azukis-new-token-launch-another-cash-grab-or-a-new-chapter-for-nfts/5924"}, {"title": "Azuki DAO lawsuit / ''missed the mark'', animated series plans (Blockworks/TheBlock)", "url": "https://blockworks.co/news/azuki-dao-sue-nft-elementals"}, {"title": "OpenSea collection", "url": "https://opensea.io/collection/azuki"}, {"title": "CoinGecko live floor", "url": "https://www.coingecko.com/en/nft/azuki"}]}','[{"title": "Azuki mint 1 ETH, $1B volume, Elementals $38M (Coindesk)", "url": "https://www.coindesk.com/web3/2023/06/28/azuki-elementals-mint-mishap-highlights-the-fragile-state-of-the-nft-market"}, {"title": "Chiru Labs $58M royalties (Coindesk Nansen)", "url": "https://www.coindesk.com/web3/2023/07/05/nft-creator-royalty-payments-hit-two-year-low-nansen"}, {"title": "Azuki DAO lawsuit (Blockworks)", "url": "https://blockworks.co/news/azuki-dao-sue-nft-elementals"}, {"title": "CoinGecko live floor", "url": "https://www.coingecko.com/en/nft/azuki"}]','2026-07-08 15:35:32');
INSERT INTO "nft_collections" ("slug","name","chain","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('pudgy-penguins','Pudgy Penguins','ethereum','pfp-brand','thriving','{"name": "Pudgy Penguins", "chain": "ethereum", "category": "pfp-brand", "launched": "2021-07", "supply": 8888, "mint_raise_usd": 3800000, "mint_price": "0.03 ETH mint, quickly ~$430", "floor_current": 4.49, "floor_ath": 19.8, "floor_ath_date": "2024-12", "secondary_volume_usd": 700000000, "royalties_enforced": "optional", "royalties_earned_usd": 8000000, "holder_count": 5199, "holder_count_peak": 5500, "holder_retention_pct": 95, "founder_engagement": "Highly active — Luca Netz bought the project for 750 ETH in 2022 and turned it into a consumer brand; relentless shipping (toys, PENGU token, Abstract chain).", "social": "Best sentiment trajectory of any legacy PFP — mainstream reach via toys; PENGU token gave holders a fresh catalyst.", "benefits": "Pudgy Toys (Walmart 2,000+ stores, 10,000+ retailers, $10M+/1.5M toys sold), Pudgy World, $PENGU token, Abstract L2.", "lifespan_days": 1810, "status": "thriving", "community_history": "Pudgy Penguins launched July 2021 and nearly died young: the original teen founders were accused of mishandling funds and the community ousted them, tanking the floor. The turning point was April 2022, when Luca Netz bought the project for 750 ETH (~$2.5M) and rebuilt it from a speculative JPEG into a licensed consumer-products brand. The community arc from there is the rare upward one — Pudgy Toys hit Walmart (2,000+ stores) and 10,000+ retailers, the Dec 2024 $PENGU airdrop reached 6M+ wallets, and the floor set a *new* ATH (~19.8 ETH) in Dec 2024, almost unique among 2021 mints. Pudgy became, in its own framing, ''the face of crypto'' with ETF-commercial cameos and 100B+ content views.", "community_sentiment": "Among the strongest and most mainstream-reaching communities in crypto, but with a growing brand-vs-token tension. NFT holders remain loyal and brand-proud; the friction sits with PENGU token holders, where late-2025/2026 sentiment turned volatile amid monthly unlocks (700M+ tranches), whale rotation, and an SEC-filing admission that PENGU has ''very few identified use cases apart from a collector''s item.'' Bulls point to Pengu Card (Visa), Pudgy World, and Man City/NASCAR deals; bears note token value is decoupled from brand success.", "notable_holders": "The Pudgy brand''s reach outweighs a marquee NFT-holder roster: PENGU became the top Solana memecoin by whale choice (overtaking BONK), with top-10 wallets controlling ~25% of token supply and repeated large accumulations (e.g., a ~$2.5M whale buy in late Dec 2025). On the NFT side, Luca Netz is the visible steward-owner; prominent NFT collectors and the Igloo/Abstract-aligned crowd hold, but specific celebrity Pudgy holders are less publicized than BAYC''s — the brand is the star, not its owners.", "marketplace_url": "https://opensea.io/collection/pudgypenguins", "business": "Pudgy Penguins is the standout real-world business in the set: Pudgy Toys, a licensed physical-toy line (plush and figures with scannable codes unlocking ''Pudgy World'' digital traits), distributed through Walmart (2,000+ stores at launch), plus Target, Amazon, Walgreens, GameStop and Toys R Us — 1M+ toys sold and reported revenue of ~$10-13M in late 2024 with $50M+/yr projected. The parent Igloo Inc. extends the brand into the $PENGU token, the Abstract L2 chain, the Pudgy World browser game, a Visa-backed ''Pengu Card,'' and marquee partnerships (Manchester City, NASCAR). Strengths: genuine mainstream retail distribution, real recurring product revenue that survived the royalty collapse, and rare consumer-brand recognition. Weaknesses: the economics don''t cleanly flow to the PENGU token (per its own SEC filing it has ''very few identified use cases''), so token holders capture little of the brand''s success, and toy-line margins/scale still trail the market cap the token commands.", "analysis": "Pudgy is the great NFT turnaround story: original teen founders fumbled the business, Luca Netz bought it for 750 ETH (~$2.5M) in April 2022, and rebuilt it into a licensed consumer-products brand rather than a speculative JPEG. Crucially, when royalties collapsed industry-wide, Pudgy had already pivoted — physical toy sales ($7M+) dwarfed NFT royalties ($300K) by 2023, proving the survival playbook: build a business the JPEG points to, not a JPEG that needs a business. The $PENGU token and Walmart distribution took it mainstream, and its floor actually set a new ATH in Dec 2024 — nearly unique among 2021 mints. Retention is ~95% because the brand, not the price, is the reason to hold. The one crack is structural: the token''s late-2025 unlock overhang and thin on-chain utility mean PENGU trades on attention while the brand compounds real revenue — the inverse of most peers, whose tokens outran non-existent brands.", "sources": [{"title": "Luca Netz 750 ETH acquisition + Walmart turnaround (Blockonomi)", "url": "https://blockonomi.com/from-turmoil-to-walmart-the-remarkable-turnaround-of-pudgy-penguins-by-luca-netz/"}, {"title": "$10M toys, 1M+ sold, Walmart/Target/Amazon distribution (Yahoo/CMC)", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/academy/article/pudgy-penguins-expands-partnership-with-walmart-after-selling-dollar10m-worth-of-toys"}, {"title": "Toys $7M vs royalties $300K (Forbes)", "url": "https://www.forbes.com/sites/digital-assets/2023/09/17/requiem-for-royalties-nft-exchanges-abandon-recurring-compensation-for-artists/"}, {"title": "PENGU utility/unlock concerns, Pengu Card, partnerships (CoinMarketCap/Crypto.com)", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/cmc-ai/pudgy-penguins/price-prediction/"}, {"title": "OpenSea collection", "url": "https://opensea.io/collection/pudgypenguins"}, {"title": "CoinGecko live floor", "url": "https://www.coingecko.com/en/nft/pudgy-penguins"}]}','[{"title": "Luca Netz 750 ETH acquisition + Walmart turnaround (Blockonomi)", "url": "https://blockonomi.com/from-turmoil-to-walmart-the-remarkable-turnaround-of-pudgy-penguins-by-luca-netz/"}, {"title": "$10M toys, 750k sold, Walmart expansion (Yahoo/CMC)", "url": "https://coinmarketcap.com/academy/article/pudgy-penguins-expands-partnership-with-walmart-after-selling-dollar10m-worth-of-toys"}, {"title": "Toys $7M vs royalties $300K (Forbes)", "url": "https://www.forbes.com/sites/digital-assets/2023/09/17/requiem-for-royalties-nft-exchanges-abandon-recurring-compensation-for-artists/"}, {"title": "CoinGecko live floor", "url": "https://www.coingecko.com/en/nft/pudgy-penguins"}]','2026-07-08 15:36:03');
INSERT INTO "nft_collections" ("slug","name","chain","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('milady-maker','Milady Maker','ethereum','pfp-culture','thriving','{"name": "Milady Maker", "chain": "ethereum", "category": "pfp-culture", "launched": "2021-08", "supply": 9978, "mint_raise_usd": 1250000, "mint_price": "0.05 ETH (~$125)", "floor_current": 1.068, "floor_ath": 7.3, "floor_ath_date": "2024-01", "secondary_volume_usd": 1000000000, "royalties_enforced": "optional", "royalties_earned_usd": null, "holder_count": 5188, "holder_count_peak": 5400, "holder_retention_pct": 96, "founder_engagement": "Founder Charlotte Fang (Krishna Okhandiar) doxxed in a 2022 extremism scandal that crashed the floor 60% in a weekend, but Remilia kept building (CULT token, Remilia ecosystem, Sonora); founder still active though polarizing.", "social": "Cult-like, meme-native community; repeatedly revived by celebrity co-signs — Elon (2023), Vitalik changed his X pfp to a Milady (Jan 2025 and again Jan 2026).", "benefits": "Remilia ecosystem, CULT/$LADYS meme tokens, Sonora, strong aesthetic/lore rather than formal utility.", "lifespan_days": 1780, "status": "thriving", "community_history": "Milady launched Aug 2021 out of Charlotte Fang''s Remilia collective as a deliberately edgy, irony-soaked, cypherpunk-coded subculture (neochibi anime aesthetic, dense lore, philosophical longposts). Its near-death moment came in May 2022 when Fang (Krishna Okhandiar) was doxxed over past extremist/''Kaliacc'' posts — the floor crashed ~60% in a weekend. Instead of dying, the community metabolized the scandal as part of its ''baggage-as-feature'' identity and kept building: the community-made $LADYS memecoin (May 2023), CULT token, Sonora, a Minecraft server, global raves, and by 2026 a Remilia x Elena Velez fashion line at NYFW SS2026. The subculture proved more durable than any roadmap.", "community_sentiment": "Alive, cult-loyal, and ideologically charged — the highest-conviction community in the set (~96% retention). Sentiment spikes on cultural signals rather than product: Elon Musk''s May 2023 Milady meme (+50% floor), and Vitalik Buterin switching his X/Farcaster PFP to a Milady in Jan 2025 (''wartime mode'') and again Jan 1, 2026 (''Milady is back,'' floor +30-50% in 24h). A March 2026 Ethereum Foundation ''CROPS'' mandate with Milady-inspired design elements sparked fresh debate. The mood is defiant-insider, treating controversy as validation.", "notable_holders": "Vitalik Buterin (bought and repeatedly used a Milady as his X/Farcaster avatar, Jan 2025 and Jan 2026, each time moving the floor 30-50%). Elon Musk boosted it via a May 2023 meme post. Aave founder Stani Kulechov adopted a Milady PFP (''Ethereum needs wartime users''). Beeple has referenced the Buterin Milady avatar in his daily art. Founder Charlotte Fang / Remilia remains the ideological center. The holder base is meme-native and pseudonymous rather than celebrity-heavy, but its endorsers are unusually high-signal (the Ethereum founder himself).", "marketplace_url": "https://opensea.io/collection/milady", "business": "Milady''s ''business'' is Remilia Corporation — a subculture/media engine rather than a conventional product company. Its outputs are a sprawling on-chain ecosystem (the CULT governance token, the affiliated community $LADYS ''drip currency'' memecoin, Sonora, additional Remilia sub-collections like Radbro/Pixelady), plus IRL cultural production: global ''Milady Rave'' events, and a Feb 2026 fashion capsule with designer Elena Velez (''Universal Work Suit,'' Yakuza-inspired) debuting at NYFW SS2026 alongside a Tokyo-shot feature film. Strengths: an unusually devoted, self-propagating community and genuine cultural cachet that money can''t easily buy (Vitalik-level endorsement). Weaknesses: little conventional revenue or distribution — the model monetizes attention and tokens, not products at retail — and the founder''s polarizing history plus tangled, unofficial token affiliations make it structurally hard to institutionalize or partner with at scale.", "analysis": "Milady is the purest ''culture over utility'' survivor: a $1.25M mint (0.05 ETH) that grew into $1B+ secondary volume on memes and aesthetic alone. It survived an existential 2022 founder scandal (Charlotte Fang doxx, -60% weekend) that would have killed most projects, proving that a strong enough subculture is more durable than a roadmap — the community reframed the scandal itself as part of its lore. Its price is driven almost entirely by exogenous cultural signals rather than shipped product: Elon in 2023, and Vitalik Buterin literally adopting a Milady as his avatar in both Jan 2025 and Jan 2026 (+30-50% each time) — an endorsement from Ethereum''s founder no other collection can match. Extremely high retention (~96%) reflects an ideological, not financial, holder base; Milady is less an NFT project than a self-sustaining internet religion that happens to have a floor price.", "sources": [{"title": "Milady origin, Fang doxx scandal, Remilia (FastCompany)", "url": "https://www.fastcompany.com/90756392/inside-remilia-corporation-the-anti-woke-dao-behind-the-doomed-milady-maker-nft"}, {"title": "Vitalik Milady avatar Jan 2025, +30% floor (Forbes/Yahoo)", "url": "https://www.forbes.com/sites/digital-assets/2025/01/19/ethereums-vitalik-buterin-just-endorsed-controversial-milady-nft/"}, {"title": "Vitalik repeats Jan 1 2026, Elena Velez NYFW fashion line (Cryptonomist/Decrypt)", "url": "https://en.cryptonomist.ch/2026/01/02/milady-nft-buterin-avatar-surge/"}, {"title": "Elon Musk 2023 meme, LADYS token, Stani Kulechov (Decrypt)", "url": "https://decrypt.co/resources/what-is-milady-edgy-ethereum-nft-community"}, {"title": "OpenSea collection", "url": "https://opensea.io/collection/milady"}, {"title": "CoinGecko live floor", "url": "https://www.coingecko.com/en/nft/milady-maker"}]}','[{"title": "Milady mint 0.05 ETH, $1B volume, scandal -60% (Spaace/FastCompany)", "url": "https://www.fastcompany.com/90756392/inside-remilia-corporation-the-anti-woke-dao-behind-the-doomed-milady-maker-nft"}, {"title": "Vitalik pfp change +30% Jan 2026 (Spaace)", "url": "https://spaace.io/blog/milady-maker-nft-story/"}, {"title": "CoinGecko live floor", "url": "https://www.coingecko.com/en/nft/milady-maker"}]','2026-07-08 15:36:38');
INSERT INTO "nft_collections" ("slug","name","chain","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('clonex','CloneX','ethereum','pfp-avatar','dead','{"name": "CloneX (RTFKT x Takashi Murakami)", "chain": "ethereum", "category": "pfp-avatar", "launched": "2021-11", "supply": 19500, "mint_raise_usd": 39000000, "mint_price": "2 ETH public (0.05 ETH presale)", "floor_current": 0.5, "floor_ath": 19.2, "floor_ath_date": "2022-04", "secondary_volume_usd": 1500000000, "royalties_enforced": "optional", "royalties_earned_usd": 49000000, "holder_count": 9000, "holder_count_peak": 13000, "holder_retention_pct": 69, "founder_engagement": "Gone. Nike shut down RTFKT (acquired Dec 2021) in Jan 2025, then quietly sold the brand Dec 2025. No active team; a ''soft rug pull'' class action was filed in 2025.", "social": "Community abandoned/angry; the Cloudflare incident that briefly made 19,000 CloneX images vanish became a symbol of corporate neglect.", "benefits": "Historically: Murakami IP, RTFKT sneakers/wearables, Nike collabs — now defunct.", "lifespan_days": 1170, "status": "dead", "community_history": "CloneX launched Nov 2021 from RTFKT (founders Benoit Pagotto, Chris Le, Steven Vasilev) in collaboration with artist Takashi Murakami — a ~$39M mint (2 ETH public) that became a symbol of the metaverse/digital-fashion thesis, peaking near 19.2 ETH in April 2022. Nike acquired RTFKT in Dec 2021 at the top, and the community''s arc from there is a slow corporate suffocation: waning product cadence, then a Dec 2024 announcement that Nike would sunset RTFKT. The April 2025 Cloudflare incident — when RTFKT''s off-chain-hosted account was downgraded and ~19,800 CloneX images were replaced by a black ''terms of service'' error screen — crystallized the neglect. By then RTFKT was reportedly maintained by a single person (Samuel Cardillo). Nike sold RTFKT to an undisclosed buyer on Dec 17, 2025.", "community_sentiment": "Abandoned, angry, and litigious. Holders watched ~$8,000 avatars fall to ~$16 and organized around a class-action (lead plaintiff Jagdeep Cheema, filed April 2025 in Brooklyn federal court seeking $5M) alleging securities fraud and a ''soft rug pull'' — arguing the NFTs met the Howey test and that Nike''s shutdown ''decimated investors.'' The mood is a case study in how corporate acquisition can kill a community: no roadmap, no confirmed staff, no clarity from the new owner.", "notable_holders": "CloneX drew heavy fashion/hype-culture and celebrity interest at peak — the brand was the metaverse-fashion darling and Murakami''s involvement pulled art-world attention. The most-cited high-value piece is CloneX #4594, which sold for 450 ETH in 2022. Cathie-Wood-tier institutional exposure and numerous influencers held during the boom, but reporting on named celebrity holders is thin; the defining named figure in the current era is the class-action lead plaintiff, Jagdeep Cheema, not a whale.", "marketplace_url": "https://opensea.io/collection/clonex", "business": "CloneX was the flagship avatar of RTFKT, a digital-fashion/sneaker business — the real product line was virtual and phygital footwear and wearables: RTFKT x Nike ''Cryptokicks'' sneakers (including AR/forgeable digital sneakers and physical redeemables), CloneX wearables and ''Space Pods,'' and Murakami-collab drops, all meant to dress your CloneX avatar across the metaverse. After Nike''s Dec 2021 acquisition it had genuine distribution muscle and one of the strongest brand parents imaginable. Weaknesses proved fatal: the product line depended entirely on Nike''s continued commitment, art and assets were hosted off-chain (the April 2025 Cloudflare outage literally erased the avatars), and once Nike lost interest the whole business evaporated — wound down Jan 2025, sold Dec 2025 — leaving the ''soft rug'' lawsuit as its epitaph. A cautionary tale that a big-brand-owned business is only as durable as the brand''s attention span.", "analysis": "CloneX is the cautionary tale of corporate acquisition killing an NFT project: a huge ~$39M mint (2 ETH public) and $1.5B lifetime RTFKT volume, backed by Murakami art and Nike''s brand, hit a 19.2 ETH ATH. Nike bought RTFKT at the Dec 2021 top, then wound it down in Jan 2025 and sold it off in Dec 2025 — a ''soft rug'' per the $5M class action (lead plaintiff Jagdeep Cheema) alleging securities fraud. Founder engagement went to zero, RTFKT was reduced to a single caretaker, and the April 2025 off-chain Cloudflare outage (19,800 NFTs going dark) became the perfect symbol of the neglect — the art literally disappeared because nobody was paying the hosting bill. Despite $49M in royalties earned, dead founder support collapsed the floor ~97% and drove retention below 70% (the worst among the ETH majors), demonstrating that a big-brand parent is worthless the moment it loses interest.", "sources": [{"title": "Nike shut down RTFKT, $5M soft-rug lawsuit, Jagdeep Cheema (The Defiant/Cointelegraph)", "url": "https://thedefiant.io/news/nfts-and-web3/class-action-lawsuit-calls-nike-s-shutdown-of-rtfkt-nft-studio-a-soft-rug-pull"}, {"title": "Cloudflare outage 19,800 NFTs dark, single caretaker (TechSpot)", "url": "https://www.techspot.com/news/107717-nike-faces-5-million-lawsuit-after-cloudflare-outage.html"}, {"title": "Nike sold RTFKT Dec 17 2025 (CryptoTimes)", "url": "https://www.cryptotimes.io/2026/01/08/rtfkt-sold-by-nike-a-year-after-nft-unit-was-shut-down/"}, {"title": "CloneX #4594 450 ETH sale, Cryptokicks (CoinCentral)", "url": "https://coincentral.com/rug-pull-nike-sued-after-8000-nfts-crash-to-16-following-rtfkt-closure/"}, {"title": "OpenSea collection", "url": "https://opensea.io/collection/clonex"}]}','[{"title": "Nike shut down RTFKT, soft-rug lawsuit (The Defiant)", "url": "https://thedefiant.io/news/nfts-and-web3/class-action-lawsuit-calls-nike-s-shutdown-of-rtfkt-nft-studio-a-soft-rug-pull"}, {"title": "RTFKT $1.5B volume, $49M royalties, sold Dec 2025 (Hypebeast/Coindesk)", "url": "https://hypebeast.com/2026/1/nike-quietly-sold-rtfkt-december-2025"}, {"title": "Cloudflare outage 19k NFTs dark (TechSpot)", "url": "https://www.techspot.com/news/107717-nike-faces-5-million-lawsuit-after-cloudflare-outage.html"}]','2026-07-08 15:37:14');
INSERT INTO "nft_collections" ("slug","name","chain","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('doodles','Doodles','ethereum','pfp-brand','fading','{"name": "Doodles", "chain": "ethereum", "category": "pfp-brand", "launched": "2021-10", "supply": 9998, "mint_raise_usd": 420000, "mint_price": "0.123 ETH (~$300)", "floor_current": 0.433, "floor_ath": 22.6, "floor_ath_date": "2022-01", "secondary_volume_usd": 700000000, "royalties_enforced": "optional", "royalties_earned_usd": null, "holder_count": 4536, "holder_count_peak": 6000, "holder_retention_pct": 76, "founder_engagement": "Active but pivoted — artist Burnt Toast (Scott Martin) became CEO and launched $DOOD token (2025) on Solana + DreamNet AI platform; criticized for ''extractive corpo'' era under prior leadership.", "social": "Sentiment faded from 2022 blue-chip status; $DOOD launched to a $100M mcap then halved day one, community lukewarm.", "benefits": "Doodles 2, Dooplicators, brand partnerships (McDonald''s, Crocs, Pharrell), $DOOD token, DreamNet.", "lifespan_days": 1720, "status": "fading", "community_history": "Doodles launched Oct 2021 (founders Burnt Toast/Scott Martin, Evan Keast/Tulip, Jordan Castro/Poopie) and rode its pastel aesthetic to top-tier blue-chip status — a 22.6 ETH ATH in Jan 2022, headlined by Pranksy paying 296.69 ETH (~$1.1M) for the ''golden ape'' Doodle #6914, the collection''s first seven-figure sale. The community arc bent downward during a middle ''extractive corpo'' period widely criticized for over-commercializing (Doodles 2 delays, brand deals) while under-shipping to holders. Founding artist Burnt Toast then took the CEO seat and bet the brand on the May 2025 $DOOD token (on Solana, 68% community allocation) and the DreamNet AI platform, backed by a Pharrell Williams partnership and $54M funding.", "community_sentiment": "Lukewarm and cautious. The $DOOD token launched near a $100M mcap and roughly halved on day-one sell pressure, then bled ~73% from its ATH ($0.018 to ~$0.0048); a Feb 2026 Coinbase listing gave a modest lift. Sentiment is split between a bull thesis (undervalued ''style engine,'' Pharrell backing, DreamNet upside) and a bear read (weak consumer traction, NFT-sector malaise, token far behind PENGU/ANIME peers). The 2021-era faithful are quieter than they were; the drama is muted rather than hostile.", "notable_holders": "Pranksy (bought the golden-ape Doodle #6914 for 296.69 ETH / ~$1.1M, the collection''s first million-dollar sale, and was a top bidder in later Dooplicator drops). Steve Aoki (Doodle #2238 for 269.69 ETH / ~$947K, famously paused a live show to flaunt it). Snoop Dogg, Gary Vaynerchuk, and DJ Timmy Trumpet have also held Doodles. Pharrell Williams is attached as a creative/brand partner in the DOOD era. This 2021-2022 celebrity roster reflects the collection''s former blue-chip standing more than its current traction.", "marketplace_url": "https://opensea.io/collection/doodles-official", "business": "Doodles has pursued a mainstream consumer-brand and entertainment business, leaning on a Pharrell Williams partnership (he joined as Chief Brand Officer in 2022). Its product/distribution footprint includes major CPG collaborations — a Crocs ''Jibbitz''/shoe line, a McDonald''s Doodles-branded promotion, and other licensed merch — plus music/festival tie-ins, the DreamNet AI content platform, and the 2025 $DOOD token (Solana) meant to power a ''style engine'' economy. Strengths: recognizable, brand-safe pastel IP, a genuine celebrity operator in Pharrell, and real Fortune-500 distribution deals few NFT projects land. Weaknesses: the brand momentum peaked years ago, the ''extractive corpo'' era eroded holder trust, DreamNet adoption is unproven, and the token launched weak (halved day one, ~73% off ATH, ~$23M mcap) — the business has logos and partners but hasn''t converted them into durable revenue or a recovering floor.", "analysis": "Doodles raised only ~420 ETH ($420K treasury by design) but hit a 22 ETH ATH and $700M+ volume as a top-5 2021 blue chip, with a celebrity roster (Pranksy''s $1.1M golden ape, Steve Aoki''s $947K Doodle) that signaled real cultural cachet. It squandered that momentum during an ''extractive corpo'' phase — over-monetizing while under-delivering to holders — then handed the CEO role to founding artist Burnt Toast, who bet the brand on the 2025 $DOOD token (Pharrell-backed, $54M funded), which briefly hit ~$100M mcap before halving on day-one sell pressure and drifting ~73% below ATH. The token pivot is the same survival move Pudgy and Azuki made, but with weaker execution and thinner consumer traction, and a $23M token mcap that sits far below PENGU''s. Retention (~76%) shows meaningful bleed — the brand still has recognizable IP, real CPG deals, and a Coinbase-listed token, but no breakout to match its former peers.", "sources": [{"title": "Doodles mint 0.123 ETH, 420 ETH treasury, 22 ETH ATH (nftnow)", "url": "https://nftnow.com/guides/doodles-guide/"}, {"title": "Pranksy golden ape #6914 $1.1M, Steve Aoki #2238 $947K, Pharrell/McDonald''s/Crocs (Hypebeast)", "url": "https://hypebeast.com/2022/1/doodles-nft-pranksy-1-1-million-opensea-steve-aoki-snoop-dogg"}, {"title": "$DOOD token, DreamNet, Coinbase listing, -73% ATH, Pharrell (CoinGecko/BYDFi)", "url": "https://www.coingecko.com/learn/what-is-dood-crypto-doodles-nft"}, {"title": "OpenSea collection", "url": "https://opensea.io/collection/doodles-official"}, {"title": "CoinGecko live floor", "url": "https://www.coingecko.com/en/nft/doodles-official"}]}','[{"title": "Doodles mint 0.123 ETH, 420 ETH treasury, 22 ETH ATH (Forbes/nftnow)", "url": "https://nftnow.com/guides/doodles-guide/"}, {"title": "$DOOD token launch, Burnt Toast CEO, $100M->$52M (Decrypt/Blockworks)", "url": "https://decrypt.co/318780/doodles-launches-dood-solana-token-airdrop"}, {"title": "CoinGecko live floor", "url": "https://www.coingecko.com/en/nft/doodles-official"}]','2026-07-08 15:37:46');
INSERT INTO "nft_collections" ("slug","name","chain","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('moonbirds','Moonbirds','ethereum','pfp-membership','fading','{"name": "Moonbirds", "chain": "ethereum", "category": "pfp-membership", "launched": "2022-04", "supply": 10000, "mint_raise_usd": 68000000, "mint_price": "2.5 ETH (PROOF Collective gated)", "floor_current": 0.695, "floor_ath": 39, "floor_ath_date": "2022-04", "secondary_volume_usd": 700000000, "royalties_enforced": "optional", "royalties_earned_usd": null, "holder_count": 3364, "holder_count_peak": 6800, "holder_retention_pct": 49, "founder_engagement": "Changed hands twice — Kevin Rose/PROOF sold to Yuga Labs (2024), Yuga then sold Moonbirds IP to Orange Cap Games (May 2025), whose transparent, no-overpromise stewardship sparked a genuine 2025 revival.", "social": "Cratered from elite status under Kevin Rose (CC0 debacle), then meaningfully revived in 2025 under Orange Cap Games — floor back above 3 ETH, sentiment shifted from punchline to cautious optimism.", "benefits": "PROOF Collective access, nesting rewards, Oddities/Mythics, now IP/gaming development under Orange Cap Games.", "lifespan_days": 1550, "status": "reviving", "community_history": "Moonbirds minted April 16, 2022 — 2.5 ETH, PROOF-Collective-gated, created by Kevin Rose (Digg co-founder) and Justin Mezzell — selling out in two days with $300M+ early volume, the largest NFT debut to that point, and instantly a ~39 ETH elite membership floor. The community then endured a brutal decline driven by Rose''s missteps: the Aug 2022 unilateral switch to a CC0 license (stripping holders'' exclusive commercial rights without consultation), a poorly received $TALONS drop, and a May 2023 Twitter Space where Rose said Moonbirds weren''t ''down bad as BAYC,'' which holders read as tone-deaf. The floor fell from 39 ETH to sub-1 ETH and Moonbirds became an NFT-circles punchline. Ownership then passed twice — Yuga Labs acquired PROOF/Moonbirds in early 2024 (revoking the CC0 license to restore holder rights) then sold it to Orange Cap Games (Spencer Gordon-Sand) in May 2025.", "community_sentiment": "Genuinely revived — the standout turnaround narrative of 2025. Under Orange Cap Games, Spencer explicitly refused to over-promise (''We''re not going to fulfill Moonbirds'' old vision — we''re going to create our own'') and rebuilt trust; Yuga''s Greg Solano endorsed the team as one ''whose whole world is the birds.'' The floor climbed from under $800 in May 2025 to ~$14,000 (above 3 ETH) later that year, and community energy flipped from frustration to cautious optimism. The holder base is unusually non-degen — a big presence in Europe and Silicon Valley.", "notable_holders": "Kevin Rose (founder, stayed on as a Yuga advisor after the 2024 sale) is the defining named figure. The collection''s PROOF-Collective gating meant early holders skewed toward established tech/VC and collector circles rather than entertainment celebrities — Spencer Gordon-Sand notes a ''big presence in Europe and Silicon Valley, not your typical crypto crowd.'' Orange Cap Games (which also built the Pudgy Penguins ''Vibes'' TCG) is now the steward. A stable public celebrity-holder roster is not a feature of Moonbirds the way it is for BAYC/Doodles.", "marketplace_url": "https://opensea.io/collection/proof-moonbirds", "business": "Moonbirds'' business ambition is now IP-and-gaming development under Orange Cap Games, a studio led by Spencer Gordon-Sand that also built the Pudgy Penguins ''Vibes'' trading card game. The stated model is Pop-Mart-style: develop Moonbirds (plus its Mythics and Oddities sub-collections) into games, trading cards, and broader entertainment franchises rather than chase a token. Earlier, under PROOF/Kevin Rose, the ''business'' was a membership brand (the PROOF Collective pass, Oddities, a $TALONS drop) that faltered. Strengths: a credible gaming operator with a shipped TCG track record, deliberately modest promises that rebuilt trust, and a distinctive non-degen holder base. Weaknesses: the concrete products are still early/unshipped — Spencer has pointedly avoided public commitments — so the business is presently a promising direction and a restored floor rather than a proven revenue line.", "analysis": "Moonbirds had the richest mint of the cohort — 2.5 ETH PROOF-gated, ~$68M raised — and instantly hit a ~39 ETH floor ($115K peak) as an exclusive membership play, only to become the sharpest faller and biggest self-inflicted wound in the set: Kevin Rose''s unilateral Aug 2022 CC0 license switch stripped holders'' commercial rights without consultation, and tone-deaf comments compounded the damage, crashing the floor ~98% and halving the holder count (6,800->3,364, ~49% retention — the worst here). It was passed like a hot potato — Rose''s PROOF to Yuga (2024, which reversed the CC0 mistake) to Orange Cap Games (2025). But the ending is now the most interesting twist in the encyclopedia: under Spencer Gordon-Sand''s deliberately humble, no-overpromise stewardship, Moonbirds staged a real 2025 revival, the floor reclaiming 3+ ETH and the community mood flipping from punchline to optimism. It is the set''s proof that even a badly mismanaged blue chip can be resuscitated — not with a token or a grand roadmap, but with credible new leadership and restored trust.", "sources": [{"title": "Yuga acquires PROOF/Moonbirds, revokes CC0, floor $115k->$3k (Decrypt)", "url": "https://decrypt.co/217906/yuga-labs-acquires-moonbirds-proof"}, {"title": "Kevin Rose CC0 debacle, $TALONS, 39->sub-1 ETH decline (Odaily/PANews)", "url": "https://www.odaily.news/en/post/5205832"}, {"title": "Orange Cap Games acquires Moonbirds, Vibes TCG, 2025 revival to ~$14k (Yahoo/OpenSea)", "url": "https://finance.yahoo.com/news/moonbirds-nfts-soaring-again-whats-160103496.html"}, {"title": "Yuga sells Moonbirds to Orange Cap Games (Blockworks)", "url": "https://blockworks.co/news/yuga-labs-moonbirds-sell"}, {"title": "OpenSea collection", "url": "https://opensea.io/collection/proof-moonbirds"}, {"title": "CoinGecko live floor", "url": "https://www.coingecko.com/en/nft/proof-moonbirds"}]}','[{"title": "Yuga acquires PROOF/Moonbirds, floor $115k->$3k (Decrypt)", "url": "https://decrypt.co/217906/yuga-labs-acquires-moonbirds-proof"}, {"title": "Yuga sells Moonbirds to Orange Cap Games (Blockworks)", "url": "https://blockworks.co/news/yuga-labs-moonbirds-sell"}, {"title": "CoinGecko live floor", "url": "https://www.coingecko.com/en/nft/proof-moonbirds"}]','2026-07-08 15:38:19');
INSERT INTO "nft_collections" ("slug","name","chain","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('mad-lads','Mad Lads','solana','pfp-tech','thriving','{"name": "Mad Lads", "chain": "solana", "category": "pfp-tech", "launched": "2023-04", "supply": 10000, "mint_raise_usd": 1500000, "mint_price": "6.9 SOL (~$150)", "floor_current": 9.03, "floor_ath": 390, "floor_ath_date": "2024-03", "secondary_volume_usd": 183000000, "royalties_enforced": "optional", "royalties_earned_usd": null, "holder_count": 4503, "holder_count_peak": 5000, "holder_retention_pct": 90, "founder_engagement": "Very active — Coral/Backpack team (Armani Ferrante, Tristan Yver) built Mad Lads as the flagship for Backpack wallet & exchange, which raised $20M+ and became a major CEX. NFT is a live product, not abandoned.", "social": "Solana blue-chip par excellence; sentiment tied to Backpack''s rise; legendary anti-bot honeypot mint is lore.", "benefits": "xNFT tech, Backpack wallet/exchange integration, staking, ecosystem access, $BP token airdrop.", "lifespan_days": 810, "status": "thriving", "community_history": "Mad Lads launched April 20, 2023 from Coral (founders Armani Ferrante and Tristan Yver, creators of the Anchor framework and ex-FTX pre-collapse) at 6.9 SOL, into a post-FTX Solana NFT winter that DeGods and y00ts had just abandoned by leaving the chain. The mint became instant lore — ''the mint that broke the internet'' — famous for its anti-bot honeypot design, and it did $8M+ volume in 24 hours, out-trading BAYC/MAYC that day and single-handedly reviving Solana NFTs. Solana co-founders Anatoly Yakovenko and Raj Gokal changed their Twitter PFPs to Mad Lads in support. The ''WAO'' (''We Are One'') rallying cry crystallized a tight, tech-native community that grew alongside Backpack''s rise into a major exchange.", "community_sentiment": "Loyal and identity-driven — among the healthiest communities on Solana (~90% retention), anchored by the ''WAO'' ethos and tied to Backpack''s success. The main 2025 sentiment event was Backpack''s $BP token, airdropped to Mad Lads holders and launched on-chain (via Wormhole''s Sunrise) rather than a centralized listing — innovative but met with mixed reactions on fairness/UX. Broadly, holders view the NFT as a live membership in a thriving company rather than a dying JPEG, insulating sentiment from the wider Solana NFT malaise.", "notable_holders": "Solana co-founders Anatoly Yakovenko and Raj Gokal are the marquee early holders — both adopted Mad Lads as their Twitter PFPs at launch, a foundational endorsement. Founders Armani Ferrante and Tristan Yver (Coral/Backpack) direct the ecosystem and hold. The broader base skews Solana-developer and degen-native; the collection has posted numerous $100K+ individual sales, and holders are treated as the premier Solana airdrop cohort. A public entertainment-celebrity roster is not a Mad Lads feature — its ''celebrities'' are Solana''s own founders.", "marketplace_url": "https://magiceden.io/marketplace/mad_lads", "business": "Mad Lads is effectively the membership NFT of a real, large business: Backpack — the wallet and regulated crypto exchange built by Coral. Backpack raised $20M+ (and by 2025-26 was reportedly seeking a $50M round at a ~$1B valuation), and the Mad Lads NFT is woven into its product via xNFT technology, wallet/exchange integration, and the $BP exchange token (airdropped to holders, distributed on-chain through Wormhole''s Sunrise — the first regulated exchange to bypass centralized-listing distribution). Strengths: the NFT is tethered to a genuine, revenue-generating, well-funded exchange business rather than speculative IP, giving it durable utility and the highest founder alignment in the set (the NFT and the company are the same bet). Weaknesses: value is correlated to Backpack''s fortunes and to $BP token sentiment, and the ''business'' is an exchange rather than a consumer/IP brand — so the NFT''s upside is a proxy on Backpack, not an independent product line.", "analysis": "Mad Lads minted 10,000 at 6.9 SOL (~$1.5M) in April 2023 amid Solana''s post-FTX NFT winter — right after DeGods/y00ts fled the chain — and single-handedly revived the ecosystem, processing 2.38M+ SOL in lifetime volume with Solana''s own co-founders (Yakovenko, Gokal) as PFP-wearing early holders. Its durability comes from being tethered to a real business: Coral''s Backpack wallet/exchange (raising toward a reported ~$1B valuation) makes the NFT a live utility asset, not a speculative orphan, and the 2025 $BP token airdrop rewarded holders directly. Founder engagement is the highest in the set because the NFT and the company are the same bet. Floor (~9 SOL) sits well off the ~390 SOL frenzy peak, but retention (~90%) is elite and sentiment is insulated from the broader Solana NFT collapse — the clearest proof that utility backed by a real company outlasts pure speculation.", "sources": [{"title": "Mad Lads 6.9 SOL mint, 2.38M SOL volume, honeypot, WAO (nftnow)", "url": "https://nftnow.com/features/mad-lads-what-to-know-about-the-project-reviving-solana/"}, {"title": "Coral $20M raise, Backpack, Yakovenko/Gokal PFPs (Coindesk)", "url": "https://www.coindesk.com/web3/2023/04/21/heavy-demand-for-madlads-nft-breaks-internet-delays-mint"}, {"title": "$BP token airdrop, on-chain distribution, ~$1B valuation raise (NFT Plazas)", "url": "https://nftplazas.com/backpack-bp-token-airdrop-solana-mad-lads-reaction/"}, {"title": "Magic Eden live stats (floor 9.03 SOL)", "url": "https://magiceden.io/marketplace/mad_lads"}]}','[{"title": "Mad Lads 6.9 SOL mint, 2.38M SOL volume, honeypot (nftnow)", "url": "https://nftnow.com/features/mad-lads-what-to-know-about-the-project-reviving-solana/"}, {"title": "Coral $20M raise, Backpack (Coindesk)", "url": "https://www.coindesk.com/web3/2023/04/21/heavy-demand-for-madlads-nft-breaks-internet-delays-mint"}, {"title": "Magic Eden live stats (floor 9.03 SOL)", "url": "https://magiceden.io/marketplace/mad_lads"}]','2026-07-08 15:38:53');
INSERT INTO "nft_collections" ("slug","name","chain","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('degods','DeGods','solana','pfp-token','fading','{"name": "DeGods", "chain": "solana", "category": "pfp-token", "launched": "2021-10", "supply": 10000, "mint_raise_usd": 530000, "mint_price": "3 SOL (~$150)", "floor_current": 15, "floor_ath": 700, "floor_ath_date": "2023-03", "secondary_volume_usd": 600000000, "royalties_enforced": "none", "royalties_earned_usd": null, "holder_count": 6000, "holder_count_peak": 8000, "holder_retention_pct": 75, "founder_engagement": "Chaotic then departed — founder Frank (Rohun Vora) chain-hopped Solana->ETH->back to Solana, converted the ecosystem to a $degod memecoin (404 hybrid) in 2024, then RESIGNED as CEO in May 2025 amid the LIBRA/insider-trading scandal; a suspicious wallet ''hack'' followed days later.", "social": "Cult founder following exhausted by repeated pivots; sentiment turned hostile in early 2025 then partially stabilized post-Frank under new community leads (@0x_chill, @pastagotsauce).", "benefits": "DUST token (deprecated), $degod memecoin, 404 hybrid liquidity, staking. Frank pioneered 0% royalties.", "lifespan_days": 1720, "status": "fading", "community_history": "DeGods minted Oct 2021 at 3 SOL under founder Rohun ''Frank'' Vora (DeLabs), pioneering 0% royalties and a deflationary burn-to-DeadGod mechanic, and rode a devoted cult following to a ~700 SOL ATH ($600M+ volume). The community arc is one of serial reinvention that steadily drained trust: the late-2022 chain-hop to ETH/Polygon (a $3M Polygon grant) while Solana reeled from FTX, a return to Solana, then the Sept 2024 conversion of the whole ecosystem into the $degod memecoin via a 404 hybrid — which erased NFT rarity value and burned y00ts holders on a one-way swap. In early 2025 sentiment turned openly hostile (Frank mocked for ''abandoning 3 projects''), compounded by his ties to the LIBRA/''LA Vape Cabal'' insider-trading scandal, culminating in his May 2025 resignation and a suspicious wallet ''hack'' days later that many read as a staged exit.", "community_sentiment": "Battle-scarred but not dead. Sentiment cratered to hostility through the 2024 404 pivot and early-2025 scandals — engagement metrics showed the community siding with Frank''s critics — then partially stabilized after his May 2025 departure handed leadership to longtime community members @0x_chill and @pastagotsauce. As of late 2025 DeGods retains a real, if exhausted, community and a relatively stable floor versus peers, but the brand''s core challenge is reinventing itself in a quieter market without its polarizing founder-showman.", "notable_holders": "Founder Rohun ''Frank'' Vora was the defining figure and its biggest liability — he retired his public wallet (reporting ~$4.4M profit) amid insider-trading accusations before resigning; days later 16 DeGods were sold from his compromised wallet (~108 SOL). Associated 2025-scandal figures in his orbit included FaZe Banks (Richard Bengtson) and Threadguy (Michael Jerome) via the LIBRA/''LA Vape Cabal'' controversy. Post-Frank stewards @0x_chill and @pastagotsauce now lead. DeGods historically drew crypto-degen whales rather than mainstream celebrities; DeadGod (burned) 1/1s are the prized tier.", "marketplace_url": "https://magiceden.io/marketplace/degods", "business": "DeLabs (the parent) attempted to build an ecosystem-business around DeGods rather than a consumer product: the DUST token, the y00ts sister collection, staking, and ultimately the 2024 pivot to the $degod memecoin via a 404 hybrid token standard meant to fuse NFT and liquid-token economics. There were also merch/apparel and event efforts at peak. Strengths: Frank was a genuine marketing innovator (0% royalties, viral mechanics) and the ecosystem sustained a large community and $600M+ in volume. Weaknesses: the ''business'' was really a sequence of tokenomic experiments and chain migrations rather than durable revenue; the 404 pivot destroyed NFT rarity value and trust, and the founder''s departure amid an insider-trading scandal left the enterprise leaderless and reputationally damaged — a cautionary tale of a project that optimized for reinvention over building anything that compounds.", "analysis": "DeGods is the chain-hopping poster child and, notably, the project that pioneered 0% royalties — Frank explicitly rejected the ''Yuga playbook,'' making DeGods a leading example of the enforce-nothing model that Blur later industrialized. It raised little (~3 SOL mint) but reached a ~700 SOL ATH and $600M+ volume on the strength of a cult founder. Its lifecycle is defined by relentless reinvention that outran trust: Solana->ETH/Polygon (a $3M grant taken then partly returned)->back to Solana->the 2024 $degod memecoin/404 pivot that erased rarity and burned y00ts holders. The arc closed with Frank''s May 2025 resignation amid the LIBRA insider-trading scandal and a suspicious wallet ''hack,'' handing a battle-weary community to new leads. High founder energy, declining trust, no durable business — each pivot extracted more goodwill than it created, and the founder ultimately became the liability the brand had to shed to survive.", "sources": [{"title": "DeGods/y00ts migrations, $3M Polygon grant (Decrypt)", "url": "https://decrypt.co/121969/why-degods-y00ts-leaving-solana-how-nft-migration-works"}, {"title": "$degod memecoin 404 pivot, rarity backlash, y00ts one-way burn (SolanaFloor)", "url": "https://solanafloor.com/news/degods-community-divided-memecoin-pivot-end-franks-chain-hopping"}, {"title": "Frank resigns May 2025, LIBRA/Cabal scandal, wallet ''hack'' (TheBlock/BeInCrypto)", "url": "https://www.theblock.co/post/353994/frank-degods-announces-retirement-from-popular-y00ts-and-degods-nft-projects"}, {"title": "Magic Eden collection", "url": "https://magiceden.io/marketplace/degods"}]}','[{"title": "DeGods/y00ts migrations, $3M Polygon grant (Coindesk/Decrypt)", "url": "https://decrypt.co/121969/why-degods-y00ts-leaving-solana-how-nft-migration-works"}, {"title": "$degod memecoin 404 pivot, y00ts burned (SolanaFloor)", "url": "https://solanafloor.com/news/degods-community-divided-memecoin-pivot-end-franks-chain-hopping"}]','2026-07-08 15:39:28');
INSERT INTO "nft_collections" ("slug","name","chain","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('y00ts','y00ts','solana','pfp-token','dead','{"name": "y00ts", "chain": "solana", "category": "pfp-token", "launched": "2022-09", "supply": 15000, "mint_raise_usd": 6100000, "mint_price": "375 DUST (~$525)", "floor_current": 1, "floor_ath": 180, "floor_ath_date": "2023-01", "secondary_volume_usd": 250000000, "royalties_enforced": "none", "royalties_earned_usd": null, "holder_count": 4000, "holder_count_peak": 9000, "holder_retention_pct": 44, "founder_engagement": "Effectively abandoned in favor of DeGods — DeLabs gave y00ts a one-way (burn-only) swap into $degod in 2024, permanently deprecating the collection while DeGods got a two-way swap. Founder Frank then resigned entirely in May 2025.", "social": "Community felt betrayed by the asymmetric memecoin swap and the fair-weather chain-hopping; sentiment negative; the collection is being wound down.", "benefits": "Formerly DUST staking; now largely subsumed into $degod, with y00ts burned out of existence.", "lifespan_days": 1400, "status": "dead", "community_history": "y00ts launched Sept 2022 as DeGods'' sister collection from DeLabs — 15,000 sheep-avatar PFPs minted at 375 DUST (~$6.1M) — and briefly hit ~180 SOL. Its history is a chronicle of being the junior sibling sacrificed for the elder: in late 2022 it was force-migrated Solana->Polygon via an irreversible ''burn and mint'' (Polygon paid DeLabs a $3M grant), with a coercive 33.3% ''Paper Hands Bridge Tax'' pressuring holders to convert (75%+ migrated in ~24h); later moved to ETH, then back to Solana. The killing blow came in the 2024 memecoin pivot: DeGods holders got a reversible two-way $degod swap, but y00ts holders got a one-way burn — effectively euthanizing the collection to consolidate liquidity into $degod. Frank''s May 2025 resignation sealed it.", "community_sentiment": "Betrayed and wound-down — the most negative arc in the set (~44% retention, the worst here). The grievance is less about price than about being repeatedly treated as disposable: abandoned during Solana''s post-FTX low, taxed for not migrating, then given a one-way burn while DeGods holders got optionality. Academic work on NFT community collapse specifically cites the y00ts saga as founder-abandonment betrayal. Whatever community remains is largely subsumed into the $degod/DeGods orbit.", "notable_holders": "y00ts never developed an independent celebrity roster — it lived in DeGods'' shadow, sharing founder Frank (Rohun Vora) and the DeLabs/DUST ecosystem. Its notable ''holders'' were effectively DeGods whales who held both, and the collection''s fate was dictated by DeLabs rather than any marquee individual. The defining named figure is Frank, whose asymmetric one-way y00ts burn and 2025 resignation are the collection''s epitaph.", "marketplace_url": "https://magiceden.io/marketplace/y00ts", "business": "y00ts had no independent business — it was a satellite of the DeLabs/DeGods ecosystem (DUST token staking, shared roadmap, and eventual absorption into the $degod memecoin). It briefly carried the $3M-grant migration to Polygon as a growth bet, but never spawned its own product, token, or consumer line; its economic role was to feed liquidity and attention to DeGods, culminating in the one-way burn that liquidated it into $degod. Effectively business: none of its own — the clearest case in the set of a collection that existed as a subsidiary and was wound down when the parent consolidated.", "analysis": "y00ts raised $6.1M (375 DUST) and hit ~180 SOL, but it was always the junior sibling to DeGods and paid the price. It endured the same brutal chain-hopping (Solana->Polygon->ETH->Solana), a coercive 33.3% ''Paper Hands Bridge Tax'' that pressured holders through an irreversible burn, and then, in the 2024 memecoin pivot, DeLabs gave DeGods a reversible two-way swap while y00ts holders got a one-way burn — effectively euthanizing the collection to consolidate liquidity into $degod. Retention collapsed to ~44%, the worst in the set, and Frank''s May 2025 resignation removed even the founder who might have revived it. y00ts is the clearest example of a founder sacrificing one community to save another — a subsidiary collection with no business of its own, wound down the moment it became more useful dead than alive.", "sources": [{"title": "y00ts mint 375 DUST $6.1M, Polygon migration, $3M grant, Bridge Tax (Decrypt)", "url": "https://decrypt.co/124887/at-least-37m-worth-of-y00ts-nfts-migrate-to-polygon-from-solana-in-one-day"}, {"title": "y00ts one-way burn into $degod vs DeGods two-way swap (SolanaFloor)", "url": "https://solanafloor.com/news/degods-community-divided-memecoin-pivot-end-franks-chain-hopping"}, {"title": "NFT founder-abandonment betrayal dynamics (Wiley/Journal of Consumer Behaviour)", "url": "https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/cb.2482"}, {"title": "Magic Eden collection", "url": "https://magiceden.io/marketplace/y00ts"}]}','[{"title": "y00ts mint 375 DUST $6.1M, migrations (SolanaFloor/Decrypt)", "url": "https://solanafloor.com/news/degods-community-divided-memecoin-pivot-end-franks-chain-hopping"}, {"title": "y00ts one-way burn into $degod (SolanaFloor)", "url": "https://solanafloor.com/news/degods-community-divided-memecoin-pivot-end-franks-chain-hopping"}]','2026-07-08 15:39:57');
INSERT INTO "nft_collections" ("slug","name","chain","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('okay-bears','Okay Bears','solana','pfp-brand','fading','{"name": "Okay Bears", "chain": "solana", "category": "pfp-brand", "launched": "2022-04", "supply": 10000, "mint_raise_usd": 1450000, "mint_price": "1.5 SOL (~$145)", "floor_current": 1.48, "floor_ath": 270, "floor_ath_date": "2022-05", "secondary_volume_usd": 200000000, "royalties_enforced": "optional", "royalties_earned_usd": null, "holder_count": 5500, "holder_count_peak": 7000, "holder_retention_pct": 79, "founder_engagement": "Faded — anon founders Kais & Suby signed an IMG global licensing deal (2022) but the brand lost momentum; leadership/ownership changes and a founder-coins pivot signaled drift.", "social": "Record-setting launch hype ($18M day-one) evaporated; sentiment tired; overshadowed by Mad Lads as Solana''s flagship, then dragged down by the broad 2025 Solana NFT collapse.", "benefits": "IMG licensing, WAGBO merch/experiences/charity, multichain (Solana + Bitcoin), founder coins — none broke through to mainstream scale.", "lifespan_days": 1540, "status": "fading", "community_history": "Okay Bears launched April 26, 2022 on Solana at 1.5 SOL and detonated — $18M+ in day-one secondary volume, briefly out-trading every Ethereum project and hitting a ~270 SOL (up to 165 SOL mint-window) floor. Built on a wholesome, community-first ethos (''We''re all gonna be okay'' / #WAGBO) with charity partnerships (Lonzo Ball''s Zo Bear court, (OKAY)RED for pandemic relief, earthquake aid) and notably loyal, low-listing holders. Its arc then bent from squandered momentum: a 2022 IMG global licensing deal never scaled, the ''Not Okay Bears'' clone controversy (delisted from OpenSea) stirred IP debates, and by 2023 Mad Lads had claimed the ''Solana flagship'' crown. The broad 2025 Solana NFT/social-engagement collapse dragged it further.", "community_sentiment": "Tired but loyal. The community''s #WAGBO diamond-hand culture and charity roots kept retention respectable (~79%) and listings historically thin, but the energy of the record-breaking launch is long gone. 2025 sentiment was dominated by the sector-wide Solana NFT collapse (SOL social dominance falling from 6%+ to under 0.4%), leaving Okay Bears as a fondly-remembered relic of Solana''s ''golden era'' (alongside Degenerate Ape Academy and DeGods) rather than an active momentum play.", "notable_holders": "Okay Bears'' most notable named association is athlete Lonzo Ball, tied to the charitable ''Zo Bear'' 1/1 that funded a youth basketball court. The collection also partnered with brands and organizations including (RED) and the United Nations on charity initiatives. Anon founders Kais and Suby directed it. Beyond these brand/charity ties, reporting does not surface a stable roster of celebrity whale holders — the community''s identity was collective (#WAGBO) rather than celebrity-anchored.", "marketplace_url": "https://magiceden.io/marketplace/okay_bears", "business": "Okay Bears pursued a licensing-and-brand business: a 2022 global licensing deal with sports/media giant IMG intended to push the bears into merch, apparel, and mainstream partnerships, alongside a WAGBO merch/experiences line, charity collaborations (RED, UN, Lonzo Ball), and a later multichain expansion (Solana + Bitcoin) and a founder-coins pivot. Strengths: a family-friendly, brand-safe aesthetic, a genuinely loyal community, and an early marquee licensing partner (IMG) that few Solana projects secured. Weaknesses: the IMG deal never translated into scaled products or revenue, the brand ceded its flagship status to Mad Lads, and the licensing/merch ambitions stalled — leaving a business that had the right partnerships on paper but never converted them into durable consumer traction.", "analysis": "Okay Bears had the most explosive launch on Solana — $18M secondary volume in 24 hours (April 2022), briefly out-trading every Ethereum project — off a modest 1.5 SOL / $1.45M mint, and paired it with a genuinely wholesome community (#WAGBO) and real charity work (Lonzo Ball''s Zo Bear court, (RED), the UN). But it''s a study in squandered launch energy: an IMG global licensing deal never scaled into products, the ''Not Okay Bears'' clone episode became a distraction, and by the time Mad Lads arrived in 2023 Okay Bears had ceded the ''Solana flagship'' crown. Floor fell ~99% from ~270 SOL to ~1.5 SOL, accelerated by the 2025 sector-wide Solana NFT collapse. The arc shows that day-one records and a loyal community (~79% retention) mean little without a business that converts them — hype is the cheapest and most perishable asset in the lifecycle, and a signed licensing logo is not the same as shipped, scaled product.", "sources": [{"title": "Okay Bears $18M day-one, 1.5 SOL mint, 165 SOL window (Decrypt)", "url": "https://decrypt.co/98848/solana-okay-bears-top-ethereum-nft-projects-18m-sales"}, {"title": "IMG licensing deal (Coindesk)", "url": "https://www.coindesk.com/business/2022/09/20/solana-based-nft-project-okay-bears-signs-licensing-deal-with-img"}, {"title": "#WAGBO ethos, charity (Lonzo/RED/UN), loyal low-listing holders (AltcoinBuzz/Solana)", "url": "https://www.altcoinbuzz.io/nft/okay-bears-nft-collection-review/"}, {"title": "2025 Solana NFT/social collapse context (Santiment)", "url": "https://app.santiment.net/insights/read/deep-dive-has-solana-lost-its-soul-10570"}, {"title": "Magic Eden live stats (floor 1.48 SOL)", "url": "https://magiceden.io/marketplace/okay_bears"}]}','[{"title": "Okay Bears $18M day-one, 1.5 SOL mint (Decrypt)", "url": "https://decrypt.co/98848/solana-okay-bears-top-ethereum-nft-projects-18m-sales"}, {"title": "IMG licensing deal (Coindesk)", "url": "https://www.coindesk.com/business/2022/09/20/solana-based-nft-project-okay-bears-signs-licensing-deal-with-img"}, {"title": "Magic Eden live stats (floor 1.48 SOL)", "url": "https://magiceden.io/marketplace/okay_bears"}]','2026-07-08 15:40:33');
INSERT INTO "nft_collections" ("slug","name","chain","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('nodemonkes','NodeMonkes','bitcoin-ordinals','ordinals-pfp','fading','{"name": "NodeMonkes", "chain": "bitcoin-ordinals", "category": "ordinals-pfp", "launched": "2023-12", "supply": 10000, "mint_raise_usd": 100000, "mint_price": "~0.001 BTC (early inscription cost, near-free) then Dutch auction from 0.21 BTC", "floor_current": 0.02318, "floor_ath": 0.83, "floor_ath_date": "2024-03", "secondary_volume_usd": 250000000, "royalties_enforced": "none", "royalties_earned_usd": null, "holder_count": 4499, "holder_count_peak": 5500, "holder_retention_pct": 82, "founder_engagement": "Modest/anonymous — an enigmatic anon duo (no roadmap, no VC), low-profile by Ordinals ethos. Not abandoned but not shipping product; occasional ''inciting'' interactions with the community.", "social": "The ''first 10k'' Ordinals; briefly flipped BAYC by market cap in March 2024; the ''Send Nodes'' meme and early-inscription-theory debates define its culture; sentiment cooled hard with the Ordinals bust but remains a blue-chip benchmark.", "benefits": "Ordinals blue-chip status, early-inscription provenance, RSIC/rune associations, honorary-collection ties — utility minimal by design.", "lifespan_days": 580, "status": "fading", "community_history": "NodeMonkes was inscribed in Feb 2023 (weeks after Ordinals launched) but only publicly minted Dec 21, 2023 via a Dutch auction from 0.21 BTC — the inscription date is why purists crown it the ''first 10k'' Ordinals collection (disputed by Bitcoin Frogs). The launch was controversial (the anon founders first promised a free mint and claimed they''d refused a $5M VC offer, then switched to the auction), yet volume surpassed 500 BTC within four days. The community catalyzed around two moments: BAYC co-founder Wylie Aronow (''Gordon Goner'') buying a rare ''duck'' NodeMonke on Jan 2, 2024 (sparking a parabolic 500-monke sweep), and a March 2024 alien sweep ($3.5M) plus a record 17 BTC (~$1.08M) single sale. A 400-piece honorary collection (Claire Silver, Grant Yun, Betty, etc.) widened its reach; the ''Send Nodes'' slogan became the rallying cry.", "community_sentiment": "Cooled but blue-chip-loyal (~82% retention). The Ordinals mania that took NodeMonkes above BAYC by market cap reversed hard, and daily volumes are now thin (single-digit BTC), yet by 2026 it remains the liquidity benchmark of the Ordinals space — ''even popular collections have thin order books outside NodeMonkes-tier blue chips.'' The Discord/X culture (trait-sniping, early-inscription-theory debates, pixel remixes) is still engaged, if smaller; the enigmatic, sometimes-''inciting'' founder posture keeps a whiff of notoriety around it.", "notable_holders": "BAYC co-founder Wylie Aronow (''Gordon Goner'') is the defining named holder — his Jan 2, 2024 purchase of a rare ''duck'' NodeMonke triggered a documented price spike and 500-monke sweep, a rare cross-over endorsement from an Ethereum blue-chip founder. The 400 honorary NodeMonkes were gifted to web3 luminaries (Claire Silver, Grant Yun, Betty, Des Lucréce, Batz), seeding notable-name association. The core founders remain anonymous; the broader base is Bitcoin/Ordinals-native rather than celebrity.", "marketplace_url": "https://magiceden.io/ordinals/marketplace/nodemonkes", "business": null, "analysis": "NodeMonkes is the Ordinals blue chip — the ''first 10k'' collection (by Feb 2023 inscription date) — that briefly flipped BAYC by market cap (~$559M) at its 0.83 BTC ATH in March 2024, aided by BAYC co-founder Gordon Goner''s own ''duck'' purchase catalyzing the run. As a Bitcoin inscription it had a near-free inscription cost, a Dutch-auction mint, and essentially zero enforceable royalties (Ordinals lack native royalty mechanics), so all value is pure floor speculation and provenance with no creator revenue stream and, by design, no consumer business. It fell ~97% to ~0.023 BTC as the Ordinals mania reversed and volumes evaporated, yet it holds ~82% retention and remains the space''s liquidity benchmark. Its lifecycle compresses the entire 2021 ETH cycle into ~12 months: euphoria to bust at Bitcoin speed, with survival resting on ''first-mover provenance'' rather than utility — the Ordinals analogue to CryptoPunks'' status-through-history thesis.", "sources": [{"title": "NodeMonkes 0.83 BTC ATH, flipped BAYC, Gordon Goner duck buy (TheBlock/nftnow)", "url": "https://nftnow.com/guides/a-guide-to-nodemonkes-10k-pixelated-ordinals-explained/"}, {"title": "First-10k inscription-date claim, Dutch auction, controversy (OrdinalHub)", "url": "https://blog.ordinalhub.com/the-first-10k-ordinals-breakdown/"}, {"title": "Ordinals collapse to lowest since Feb 2024 (The Defiant)", "url": "https://thedefiant.io/news/nfts-and-web3/bitcoin-s-ordinals-plummet-to-lowest-levels-since-february-2024"}, {"title": "Magic Eden / CoinGecko live floor", "url": "https://www.coingecko.com/en/nft/nodemonkes"}]}','[{"title": "NodeMonkes 0.83 BTC ATH, flipped BAYC (Yahoo/TheBlock)", "url": "https://www.theblock.co/post/283001/bitcoin-ordinals-nft-interest-soars-as-nodemonkes-records-53-surge-in-floor-price"}, {"title": "Ordinals collapse (The Defiant)", "url": "https://thedefiant.io/news/nfts-and-web3/bitcoin-s-ordinals-plummet-to-lowest-levels-since-february-2024"}, {"title": "CoinGecko live floor", "url": "https://www.coingecko.com/en/nft/nodemonkes"}]','2026-07-08 15:41:11');
INSERT INTO "nft_collections" ("slug","name","chain","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('bitcoin-puppets','Bitcoin Puppets','bitcoin-ordinals','ordinals-meme','fading','{"name": "Bitcoin Puppets", "chain": "bitcoin-ordinals", "category": "ordinals-meme", "launched": "2024-01", "supply": 10001, "mint_raise_usd": 50000, "mint_price": "~$10 inscription", "floor_current": 0.0103, "floor_ath": 0.47, "floor_ath_date": "2024-04", "secondary_volume_usd": 205000000, "royalties_enforced": "none", "royalties_earned_usd": null, "holder_count": 6021, "holder_count_peak": 7000, "holder_retention_pct": 86, "founder_engagement": "Anon artist ''Le Puppeteer Fou'' — meme-driven, deliberately undoxxed, minimal formal team/roadmap; spawned Rune Pups airdrop. In Dec 2025 he deleted his socials, echoing the Satoshi mythos. Present-by-absence.", "social": "One of the most meme-viral Ordinals on Crypto Twitter; ''Send them to zero!'' and ''world peace'' are its signals; sentiment is pure vibes, volatile but sticky.", "benefits": "Rune Pups airdrop, associated $PUPS BRC-20 (separate project), meme/lore value; no formal utility by design.", "lifespan_days": 540, "status": "fading", "community_history": "Bitcoin Puppets launched Jan 3, 2024 at a ~$10 mint — 10,001 crudely-drawn ''MS Paint monkey puppet'' inscriptions by anon artist Le Puppeteer Fou, building on his 777-piece O.P.I.U.M. precursor. It became one of the most viral Ordinals on Crypto Twitter, peaking at ~0.47 BTC (~$30K floor) in April 2024 and ~$112M market cap by Jan 2025. The culture is deliberately anti-speculation and absurdist — ''Send them to zero!'' as an ironic rallying cry, ending tweets with ''world peace'' as an in-group signal, holders likened to ''4chan finding a Bloomberg Terminal.'' Holders were rewarded with the free Rune Pups airdrop. In Dec 2025 Le Puppeteer Fou deleted his socials, a Satoshi-style disappearance the community absorbed as lore rather than abandonment.", "community_sentiment": "Meme-loyal and sticky despite an ~98% floor drop (~86% retention, high for the Ordinals set). Sentiment is entirely vibes/community-driven — the project treats price collapse as a feature (''Send them to zero!'') and bonds around irony and ''world peace'' signaling. The founder''s Dec 2025 exit didn''t break the community; if anything it fit the ethos. By 2026 it''s cited alongside NodeMonkes and OMB as a likely survivor if Ordinals/Runes recover, but its value remains hostage to sector attention and meme momentum.", "notable_holders": "The most cited ''holder'' is Cathie Wood''s ARK Invest, which inadvertently acquired a Bitcoin Puppet worth ~$27,000 through its ARKB spot-Bitcoin ETF — a quirky, headline-making institutional accident. Beyond that, the community is pseudonymous by design (active contributors go by handles like @w4nkpire, @kuyamark); there is no conventional celebrity roster, and the anon artist Le Puppeteer Fou (who also made Lasogette on ETH and O.P.I.U.M.) is the mythologized central figure, now vanished.", "marketplace_url": "https://magiceden.io/ordinals/marketplace/bitcoin-puppets", "business": null, "analysis": "Bitcoin Puppets is the meme-native Ordinals counterpart to Milady — MS-Paint-crude art, an anon artist (Le Puppeteer Fou), and value driven entirely by Crypto Twitter virality rather than any product or business. It hit ~0.47 BTC and ~3,300 BTC ($205M+) in lifetime volume with essentially no mint raise and no royalties (Ordinals have none), and rewarded holders via the free Rune Pups/BRC-20-adjacent airdrop — the Ordinals substitute for ''utility.'' Floor fell ~98% to ~0.01 BTC in the Ordinals bust, and the founder deleted his socials in Dec 2025, yet retention held (~86%) on pure meme loyalty and the ironic ''Send them to zero!'' ethos that reframes collapse as the point. Even ARK Invest accidentally held one via its Bitcoin ETF. It echoes the ETH culture-coin pattern: with no business to build or founder to disappoint, a strong enough meme-subculture is more retention-durable than any roadmap.", "sources": [{"title": "Bitcoin Puppets $10 mint, O.P.I.U.M., ''Send them to zero'', ATH 0.47 BTC (nftnow)", "url": "https://nftnow.com/guides/bitcoin-puppets-ordinals-guide/"}, {"title": "$112M mcap Jan 2025, ARK Invest ETF accidental holder (Blockchain Council)", "url": "https://www.blockchain-council.org/cryptocurrency/bitcoin-puppets/"}, {"title": "Le Puppeteer Fou deletes socials Dec 2025, Satoshi mythos (nftnow)", "url": "https://nftnow.com/guides/bitcoin-puppets-ordinals-guide/"}, {"title": "Magic Eden live stats (floor 0.0103 BTC, 6021 owners, 3322 BTC vol)", "url": "https://magiceden.io/ordinals/marketplace/bitcoin-puppets"}]}','[{"title": "Bitcoin Puppets Rune Pups airdrop, ATH 0.47 BTC (Decrypt)", "url": "https://decrypt.co/225282/bitcoin-ordinals-runes-projects-you-should-know-halving"}, {"title": "Ordinals collapse (The Defiant)", "url": "https://thedefiant.io/news/nfts-and-web3/bitcoin-s-ordinals-plummet-to-lowest-levels-since-february-2024"}, {"title": "Magic Eden live stats", "url": "https://magiceden.io/ordinals/marketplace/bitcoin-puppets"}]','2026-07-08 15:41:40');
INSERT INTO "nft_collections" ("slug","name","chain","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('runestone','Runestone','bitcoin-ordinals','ordinals-airdrop','fading','{"name": "Runestone", "chain": "bitcoin-ordinals", "category": "ordinals-airdrop", "launched": "2024-03", "supply": 112384, "mint_raise_usd": 0, "mint_price": "free airdrop (fairdrop)", "floor_current": 0.001388, "floor_ath": 0.011, "floor_ath_date": "2024-04", "secondary_volume_usd": 80000000, "royalties_enforced": "none", "royalties_earned_usd": null, "holder_count": 63743, "holder_count_peak": 112000, "holder_retention_pct": 57, "founder_engagement": "Leonidas (pseudonymous Ordinals historian) ran it as a 100% volunteer effort — ''no team allocation, no entity, no utility, no roadmap.'' Deliberately hands-off; his ongoing role is directing follow-on Runes airdrops (e.g. $DOG) to holders.", "social": "Symbol of Ordinals-era community ethos; briefly the largest BTC collection by mcap (~$650M); sentiment faded with the sector but the ''fairdrop badge of honor'' framing endures.", "benefits": "Follow-on Runes/memecoin airdrops to holders (notably $DOG), whitelists; symbolic ''year-one Ordinals'' provenance. No formal utility by design.", "lifespan_days": 480, "status": "fading", "community_history": "Runestone launched March 14, 2024 as the largest-ever Ordinals airdrop — 112,384 free inscriptions dropped to any Bitcoin address that held 3+ non-text Ordinals before block 826,600, engineered by pseudonymous Ordinals historian Leonidas as a ''100% volunteer effort'' to reward year-one adopters (funded by a Dutch-auction sale of the ''grandparent'' inscription for 8 BTC). It was framed explicitly as a ''badge of honor'' that airdrop farmers couldn''t game. The community arc peaked fast — a ~$650M market cap, briefly the largest on Bitcoin, with talk of ''surpassing BAYC'' — then bled as the sector cooled. Its enduring value proposition became the follow-on airdrops Leonidas steered to holders, most notably the $DOG (DOG•GO•TO•THE•MOON) rune.", "community_sentiment": "Faded from euphoria but philosophically intact. The ''fair, earned, no-VC'' distribution earned broad goodwill and the badge-of-honor identity persists, but with no revenue engine and a huge free supply, nearly half the airdropped wallets sold (112K->64K, ~57% retention). Sentiment now hinges on the cumulative-airdrop thesis Leonidas pushes — that a Runestone''s real value is the stream of free Runes drops (like $DOG) it entitles holders to, not the floor. As Ordinals attention waned, so did the fervor, leaving a symbolic relic of the movement''s egalitarian moment.", "notable_holders": "By design Runestone has no ''whale'' story — its whole point was the widest fair distribution ever (91,000+ distinct holders at peak), so notable individuals are downplayed. The defining named figure is its architect, pseudonymous historian Leonidas, who also created/championed the $DOG rune that airdropped to Runestone holders. Value accrues to the collective holder base via follow-on Runes airdrops rather than to marquee collectors.", "marketplace_url": "https://magiceden.io/ordinals/marketplace/runestone", "business": null, "analysis": "Runestone is the anti-monetization outlier: the largest-ever Ordinals airdrop (112,384 free to 112,000+ wallets, zero mint raise, zero team allocation, zero entity), explicitly designed by Leonidas with ''no utility and no roadmap'' — the purest expression of the Ordinals fair-distribution ethos and the antithesis of a business. It briefly hit a ~$650M market cap, the largest on Bitcoin, proving that in the Ordinals paradigm a fair free distribution can out-value a paid mint. But with no founder revenue, no royalties, and no product, the floor bled ~87% and nearly half the airdropped wallets sold out (~57% retention). Its clever survival mechanic is the cumulative-airdrop thesis — holders received the $DOG rune and further Runes drops, so a Runestone is a claim on future free distributions rather than a productive asset. It''s the clearest test case that community goodwill and fairness alone, absent any economic engine, decay once the narrative fades — the fair-launch mirror image of the token-and-business survival playbook the ETH majors chose.", "sources": [{"title": "Runestone fairdrop 112,383, $650M mcap, no team, 8 BTC grandparent (Decrypt/nftnow)", "url": "https://decrypt.co/219113/bitcoin-ordinals-runestone-airdrop-leonidas-casey-rodarmor-runes"}, {"title": "Cumulative $DOG + follow-on Runes airdrops to holders (Leonidas via X/Gate)", "url": "https://www.gate.com/learn/articles/beyond-300m-the-golden-rise-of-runestone-in-the-btc-ecosystem/2247"}, {"title": "Magic Eden live stats (floor 0.001388 BTC, 63,743 owners)", "url": "https://magiceden.io/ordinals/marketplace/runestone"}]}','[{"title": "Runestone fairdrop 112,383, $650M mcap, no team (Decrypt/nftplazas)", "url": "https://decrypt.co/219113/bitcoin-ordinals-runestone-airdrop-leonidas-casey-rodarmor-runes"}, {"title": "Magic Eden live stats (floor 0.001388 BTC, 63,743 owners)", "url": "https://magiceden.io/ordinals/marketplace/runestone"}]','2026-07-08 15:42:13');
INSERT INTO "nft_collections" ("slug","name","chain","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('ordinal-maxi-biz','Ordinal Maxi Biz (OMB)','bitcoin-ordinals','ordinals-pfp','fading','{"name": "Ordinal Maxi Biz (OMB)", "chain": "bitcoin-ordinals", "category": "ordinals-pfp", "launched": "2023-05", "supply": 2021, "mint_raise_usd": 80000, "mint_price": "near-free/low inscription", "floor_current": 0.03, "floor_ath": 0.4, "floor_ath_date": "2024-03", "secondary_volume_usd": 40000000, "royalties_enforced": "none", "royalties_earned_usd": null, "holder_count": 900, "holder_count_peak": 1200, "holder_retention_pct": 75, "founder_engagement": "Created by Ordinals advocate ZK Shark with artists Tony Tafuro and Nullish; active community-building (AMAs, campaigns) but no formal ''product'' roadmap — lore-and-provenance driven.", "social": "Small, tight, cult-status collection among Bitcoin natives; the ''block 9 mined by Satoshi / block 78 by Hal Finney'' provenance and CryptoPunk-migration stunt are its lore; sentiment tied to the Ordinals cycle.", "benefits": "Ordinals status/culture, early-block provenance, small-supply scarcity, Christie''s-validated art-world cachet; minimal formal utility.", "lifespan_days": 790, "status": "fading", "community_history": "OMB (Ordinal Maxi Biz) was created in 2023 by Ordinals advocate ZK Shark with artists Tony Tafuro and Nullish — hand-drawn head sketches whose eye-color trait maps to the Bitcoin block they were inscribed on, giving it deep provenance lore: green OMBs on block 9 (mined by Satoshi Nakamoto), blue on block 78 (mined by Hal Finney). It became a status symbol for early Ordinals ''maxis.'' Two events cemented its cult standing: a June 2023 Bitcoin Bandits campaign (led by Natan Stein) that let CryptoPunk owners burn their Ethereum Punk to earn an OMB allowlist spot — Punk #8611 (~$96K) and #9146 were actually ''moved'' to Bitcoin — and an April 2024 Christie''s auction where a set of four OMB inscriptions sold for $441,000, a rare art-world validation for Ordinals. It rode maxi culture to a ~0.4 BTC ATH in the March 2024 frenzy.", "community_sentiment": "Small, tight, and cult-loyal (~75% retention on a tiny ~900-holder base). The provenance narrative (Satoshi/Hal Finney blocks) and the CryptoPunk-migration and Christie''s moments give it outsized cultural cachet relative to its size, and its creators stayed active with AMAs and campaigns. But it''s thinly traded and illiquid — sentiment is entirely a function of the Ordinals cycle, which cooled hard through 2025, leaving OMB a revered but quiet maxi relic rather than an active momentum play.", "notable_holders": "OMB''s ''notable holder'' story is provenance rather than people: its green pieces trace to Satoshi Nakamoto''s block 9 and blue to Hal Finney''s block 78, and the CryptoPunk-migration campaign burned real Punks (#8611, #9146) to seed its allowlist — tying it to CryptoPunks'' own lineage. Christie''s featuring a four-piece OMB set ($441K, April 2024) signaled fine-art collector interest. Creators ZK Shark, Tony Tafuro, and Nullish are the named figures; the holder base is small and Bitcoin-maxi-native rather than celebrity.", "marketplace_url": "https://magiceden.io/ordinals/marketplace/omb", "business": null, "analysis": "OMB (Ordinal Maxi Biz) is a small-supply status collection that rode Ordinals-maxi culture and an unusually rich provenance story — eye-color traits mapped to Bitcoin blocks, with pieces tracing to Satoshi''s block 9 and Hal Finney''s block 78 — to a ~0.4 BTC ATH in the March 2024 frenzy, with essentially no mint raise or royalties. Its cultural weight punches above its size: the 2023 CryptoPunk-burn migration stunt (Punks #8611, #9146 ''moved'' to Bitcoin) and an April 2024 Christie''s auction ($441K for four inscriptions) gave it art-world validation few Ordinals earned. But its tiny holder base (~900) makes it resilient in retention (~75%) yet thin in liquidity — floor down ~92% in an illiquid market. Like all Ordinals here it has no creator revenue engine and no consumer business, so its lifecycle is a pure function of Bitcoin''s NFT-narrative cycle and its own provenance mythology: it will live or die with sector attention and collector reverence, not with any product roadmap.", "sources": [{"title": "OMB by ZK Shark/Tafuro/Nullish, block-9-Satoshi / block-78-Finney provenance (Xverse)", "url": "https://www.xverse.app/blog/ordinals-maxi-biz-omb"}, {"title": "CryptoPunk burn-migration campaign (#8611, #9146), Christie''s $441K auction (Xverse)", "url": "https://www.xverse.app/blog/ordinals-maxi-biz-omb"}, {"title": "Ordinals sector collapse (The Defiant)", "url": "https://thedefiant.io/news/nfts-and-web3/bitcoin-s-ordinals-plummet-to-lowest-levels-since-february-2024"}, {"title": "Magic Eden / CoinGecko live floor", "url": "https://www.coingecko.com/en/nft/ordinal-maxi-biz-omb"}]}','[{"title": "Ordinals projects overview incl OMB (Decrypt)", "url": "https://decrypt.co/225282/bitcoin-ordinals-runes-projects-you-should-know-halving"}, {"title": "Ordinals sector collapse (The Defiant)", "url": "https://thedefiant.io/news/nfts-and-web3/bitcoin-s-ordinals-plummet-to-lowest-levels-since-february-2024"}]','2026-07-08 15:42:45');
INSERT INTO "nft_collections" ("slug","name","chain","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('cryptopunks','CryptoPunks','ethereum','pfp-genesis','thriving','{"name": "CryptoPunks", "chain": "ethereum", "category": "pfp-genesis", "launched": "2017-06", "supply": 10000, "mint_raise_usd": 0, "mint_price": "free claim (2017)", "floor_current": 38, "floor_ath": 125, "floor_ath_date": "2022-02", "secondary_volume_usd": 3000000000, "royalties_enforced": "none", "royalties_earned_usd": 0, "holder_count": 3800, "holder_count_peak": 4000, "holder_retention_pct": 95, "founder_engagement": "Passed from Larva Labs to Yuga Labs (2022), then Yuga donated/sold CryptoPunks to a nonprofit (Infinite Node Foundation) in 2025 to be exhibited as art. Stewarded, not ''shipped.''", "social": "The genesis PFP and status floor of the entire space; sentiment reverential; treated as digital art/history.", "benefits": "Historical/cultural primacy; no roadmap or royalties — value is provenance itself.", "lifespan_days": 3300, "status": "thriving", "community_history": "CryptoPunks began as a free 2017 experiment by Larva Labs (Matt Hall, John Watkinson) — 10,000 claimable at gas cost — and slowly accreted into the space''s foundational artifact. The community arc is one of steadily rising reverence: from obscure 2017 curio, to 2021 Christie''s/Sotheby''s fine-art legitimization, to the Feb 2022 record when Chain CEO Deepak Thapliyal paid 8,000 ETH ($23.7M) for Alien Punk #5822 (Guinness-recognized as the most expensive NFT sale) — an alien the original owner had bought for 5 ETH (~$1,600). Larva Labs sold the IP to Yuga Labs in March 2022; Yuga then donated the collection to the Infinite Node Foundation nonprofit in 2025 to be preserved as art, a handoff the community broadly welcomed as securing its legacy.", "community_sentiment": "Reverential and stable — the strongest-hands cohort in crypto. Holders treat Punks as digital art and historical provenance rather than a speculative bet, so sentiment is largely insulated from cycle noise. The 2025 nonprofit stewardship reinforced the ''this is permanent culture'' framing; there is essentially no ''roadmap anxiety'' because there is no roadmap to disappoint.", "notable_holders": "Deepak Thapliyal (bought Alien #5822 for 8,000 ETH/$23.7M in Feb 2022, quietly resold in 2024 at a large loss as prices fell). Shalom Meckenzie (DraftKings'' largest shareholder) bought COVID-Alien #7523 for $11.8M at Sotheby''s in June 2021. Jay-Z (used Punk #6095 as his Twitter avatar), Serena Williams, Steve Aoki, Gary Vaynerchuk, and Snoop Dogg have all held Punks; Yuga/Larva founders and numerous funds hold aliens and apes.", "marketplace_url": "https://opensea.io/collection/cryptopunks", "business": null, "analysis": "Included as the longevity benchmark: CryptoPunks launched free in 2017, charged 0% royalties from day one (predating the whole royalty debate), and still commands a ~38 ETH floor and $3B+ lifetime volume 8+ years later. Its survival proves the ultimate lifecycle lesson — provenance and cultural primacy outlast every utility roadmap, token pivot, and royalty scheme. The $23.7M Punk #5822 sale set the ceiling for the entire asset class, and even its later loss-making resale didn''t dent the collection''s status. Notably it never spawned a consumer business — no token, no toys, no metaverse — and that abstention is part of why it endures: with no founder ''engagement'' needed (now stewarded by a nonprofit as fine art), it demonstrates that the most durable NFTs are the ones that transcend the founder entirely. Retention ~95% among a holder base that behaves like museum patrons, not traders — the anti-fragile endpoint every other collection here is implicitly benchmarked against.", "sources": [{"title": "Yuga sells CryptoPunks to nonprofit (Blockworks)", "url": "https://blockworks.co/news/yuga-labs-moonbirds-sell"}, {"title": "Punk #5822 record 8,000 ETH/$23.7M sale, Deepak Thapliyal (Hypebeast)", "url": "https://hypebeast.com/2022/2/cryptopunk-5822-record-breaking-8000-eth-23-7-million-usd-sale-info"}, {"title": "Punk #5822 resold at a loss in 2024 (Decrypt)", "url": "https://decrypt.co/245373/cryptopunk-bought-24-million-resold-nft-prices-decline"}, {"title": "Punk #7523 COVID Alien $11.8M Sotheby''s, Shalom Meckenzie (NFTCulture)", "url": "https://www.nftculture.com/nft-news/punk-5822-purchased-by-deepak-for-8k-eth/"}, {"title": "OpenSea collection", "url": "https://opensea.io/collection/cryptopunks"}, {"title": "CoinGecko live floor", "url": "https://www.coingecko.com/en/nft/cryptopunks"}]}','[{"title": "Yuga sells CryptoPunks to nonprofit (Blockworks)", "url": "https://blockworks.co/news/yuga-labs-moonbirds-sell"}, {"title": "CoinGecko live floor", "url": "https://www.coingecko.com/en/nft/cryptopunks"}]','2026-07-08 15:34:59');
INSERT INTO "infra_chains" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('arweave','Arweave','storage','thriving','{"name":"Arweave","category":"storage","launched":"2018 (mainnet)","founders":"Sam Williams, William Jones","raised":"~$22M+ (a16z, Union Square Ventures, Coinbase Ventures, Multicoin; 2019-2020 rounds)","token_symbol":"AR","token_ath":"$90.64 (Nov 5, 2021)","token_current":"~$1.93 (Jul 2026) — ~98% below ATH","what_it_does":"Permanent, one-time-pay data storage. Upload a file once and it is stored forever on the ''permaweb'', with no recurring fees.","how_it_works":"Endowment model (''pay once, store forever''): a single AR fee is split between upfront storage cost (priced for ~200 years) and a principal endowment whose declining-cost-of-storage yield (Kryder''s Law, ~38%/yr cost decline) funds perpetual storage. Miners run Succinct Proofs of Random Access (SPoRA) to prove they hold historical data. Fixed 66M AR supply; uploads lock AR into the endowment, reducing circulation. AO compute layer (2024-25) adds decentralized execution on top of permanent storage.","adoption":"Used for Solana historical-data archiving, Meta/Instagram NFT integration, and permaweb dApps (ArDrive, Mirror). AO compute layer is a major 2025 growth vector. Sidus Space / Lonestar in-space data storage pathfinder mission planned Q4 2026. Not a single token has left the endowment since launch ~7 years ago, validating the model to date.","doc_verification_use":"Strong fit for permanent provenance/audit trails: once anchored, a document and its hash are immutable and perpetually retrievable, making Arweave suitable for legal records, public-sector archives, and tamper-evident document storage (vs. hash-only notarization, Arweave stores the full artifact permanently).","economics":"AR value capture = demand for permanent storage locks AR into the endowment (deflationary pressure on fixed 66M supply). Future AO compute fees add a second revenue stream. Risk: model depends on continued storage-cost decline AND sustained AR value; a collapse in either could underfund the endowment.","non_economic":"Active permaweb dev ecosystem (ArDrive, Mirror, Bundlr/Irys, ar.io gateways). AO compute positioned for decentralized AI/dApps. Strong brand as THE permanent-storage network.","outlook":"Bull: AO makes Arweave the storage+compute base layer for decentralized AI; endowment thesis proven. Base: steady niche leader in permanent storage. Bear: low-cost competitors (Irys, Walrus) erode share, enterprises prefer subscriptions. Key risk: endowment underfunding if AR price and/or storage-cost-decline assumptions break.","status":"thriving","sources":[{"title":"Arweave — permanent storage endowment model","url":"https://arweave.org/"},{"title":"What is Arweave? — ar.io Documentation","url":"https://docs.ar.io/learn/what-is-arweave/"},{"title":"Arweave price / ATH — CoinGecko","url":"https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/arweave"}]}','[{"title":"Arweave","url":"https://arweave.org/"},{"title":"ar.io docs","url":"https://docs.ar.io/learn/what-is-arweave/"},{"title":"CoinGecko AR","url":"https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/arweave"}]','2026-07-08 15:20:15');
INSERT INTO "infra_chains" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('filecoin','Filecoin','storage','thriving','{"name":"Filecoin","category":"storage","launched":"Oct 2020 (mainnet)","founders":"Juan Benet (Protocol Labs)","raised":"~$205M+ (2017 ICO, one of the largest ever; Sequoia, a16z, Union Square, Winklevoss Capital)","token_symbol":"FIL","token_ath":"$236.84 (Apr 1, 2021)","token_current":"~$0.75 (Jul 2026) — ~99.7% below ATH","what_it_does":"Decentralized storage marketplace where clients pay providers in FIL to store data under time-bounded, cryptographically-proven contracts (storage deals).","how_it_works":"Contract/deal-based storage (the opposite of Arweave''s permanent model): clients and storage providers agree deals for a set duration and price. Providers post collateral and continuously prove they hold data via Proof-of-Replication (PoRep) and Proof-of-Spacetime (PoSt); failure slashes collateral. Complements IPFS content-addressing with an economic incentive layer. 2025 upgrades: Fast Finality (F3, ~100x faster txns), Proof of Data Possession (PoDP) hot-storage layer, Network v27 Direct Data Onboarding.","adoption":"Q3 2025 (Messari): total capacity ~3.0 EiB, utilization ~36% (up from 29% in Q1), active data stored ~1,110 PiB, 2,491 onboarded real-world datasets (925 exceeding 1,000 TiB). Retrieval success surged 388% YoY. Adopters: Cornell University, Digital Public Library of America, AI platforms (Heurist, Gaianet), Humanode. Strategic pivot toward fewer, higher-value verified (Fil+) enterprise deals.","doc_verification_use":"Provable-storage guarantees (PoRep/PoSt) give a continuous cryptographic attestation that a specific dataset is being held — useful for auditable data-retention compliance and verifiable archives, though deals are time-bounded (must be renewed), unlike permanent Arweave.","economics":"FIL captures value via storage-deal payments, provider collateral staking, and gas. Value tracks paid utilization — the key metric moving from raw committed capacity to actually-paid enterprise storage. Risk: utilization still only ~36%; token down ~99.7% from ATH despite steady real usage.","non_economic":"Largest funded storage ecosystem; Protocol Labs R&D (IPFS, libp2p, FVM smart contracts). Broad tooling, enterprise/research partnerships, AI-data workflows.","outlook":"Bull: enterprise/AI-data demand pushes utilization toward full paid capacity; FVM compute adds value. Base: steady infrastructure with growing real usage but weak token. Bear: capacity overhang and provider churn persist, token stays depressed. Key risk: disconnect between real adoption and token value; 64% of capacity still unused.","status":"thriving","sources":[{"title":"State of Filecoin Q3 2025 — Messari","url":"https://messari.io/report/state-of-filecoin-q3-2025"},{"title":"Filecoin Q3 2025 utilization — DePIN Scan","url":"https://depinscan.io/news/2025-11-17/filecoin-q3-2025-network-utilization-and-economic-dynamics"},{"title":"Filecoin price / ATH — CoinGecko","url":"https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/filecoin"}]}','[{"title":"Messari Filecoin Q3 2025","url":"https://messari.io/report/state-of-filecoin-q3-2025"},{"title":"DePIN Scan Filecoin Q3","url":"https://depinscan.io/news/2025-11-17/filecoin-q3-2025-network-utilization-and-economic-dynamics"},{"title":"CoinGecko FIL","url":"https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/filecoin"}]','2026-07-08 15:20:35');
INSERT INTO "infra_chains" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('ipfs','IPFS (InterPlanetary File System)','storage','thriving','{"name":"IPFS (InterPlanetary File System)","category":"storage","launched":"2015","founders":"Juan Benet (Protocol Labs)","raised":"N/A — protocol, not a token; funded via Protocol Labs / Filecoin ICO","token_symbol":"None (no native token; economic layer is Filecoin)","token_ath":"N/A","token_current":"N/A","what_it_does":"Open peer-to-peer protocol for content-addressed storage and retrieval — the de facto standard for referencing decentralized/Web3 media (NFTs, dApp assets).","how_it_works":"Content addressing: every file gets a CID derived from its cryptographic hash, so references are tamper-evident and location-independent. Built on a Merkle DAG, a distributed hash table (DHT) for peer discovery, and block exchange (Bitswap). Data is NOT automatically persisted — content must be ''pinned'' by a node or pinning service, or it can disappear. Kubo (Go) powers production infra; Helia (JS) replaced deprecated js-ipfs in 2025.","adoption":"De facto standard for NFT media (OpenSea, Rarible, Foundation use ipfs:// URIs) and dApp/gaming assets (Decentraland, The Sandbox). ~614M daily requests through public gateways (a recentralization bottleneck the 2025 ''post-gateway'' roadmap targets with verifiable retrieval). Pinning services (Pinata, Storacha/ex-NFT.Storage, Fleek) are essential for persistence.","doc_verification_use":"CIDs are inherently tamper-evident — any change to a document changes its CID, providing content-integrity verification. But IPFS alone gives no timestamp and no persistence guarantee (a CID proves ''this is the content'' not ''it existed at time T''), so it is typically paired with a blockchain anchor or Filecoin for durable provenance.","economics":"No token / no direct value capture at the protocol layer — IPFS is free, open infrastructure. Monetization happens in complementary layers: Filecoin (incentivized persistence), Crust, and commercial pinning services.","non_economic":"Enormous developer adoption; core Web3 primitive. Protocol Labs stewardship, IPFS Foundation, active spec work. Transition to Helia and ''post-gateway'' verifiable retrieval is the key 2025-27 evolution.","outlook":"Bull: verifiable retrieval + DePIN adoption make IPFS ubiquitous verifiable-data infrastructure. Base: remains the default Web3 content-addressing standard. Bear: gateway centralization and persistence pain push users to centralized alternatives. Key risk: no persistence guarantee without external pinning/incentives.","status":"thriving","sources":[{"title":"Content-Addressing: 2025 In Review — IPFS Foundation","url":"https://ipfsfoundation.org/content-addressing-2025-in-review/"},{"title":"IPFS: Content-Addressed, Versioned, P2P File System — Protocol Labs Research","url":"https://research.protocol.ai/publications/ipfs-content-addressed-versioned-p2p-file-system/"}]}','[{"title":"IPFS Foundation 2025 review","url":"https://ipfsfoundation.org/content-addressing-2025-in-review/"},{"title":"Protocol Labs Research IPFS","url":"https://research.protocol.ai/publications/ipfs-content-addressed-versioned-p2p-file-system/"}]','2026-07-08 15:20:57');
INSERT INTO "infra_chains" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('storj','Storj','storage','steady','{"name":"Storj","category":"storage","launched":"2018 (Storj v3 / DCS 2020)","founders":"Shawn Wilkinson","raised":"~$30M ($3M 2014 seed; ~$30M 2017 token sale)","token_symbol":"STORJ","token_ath":"~$3.91 (2018) / ~$3.02 (2021)","token_current":"~$0.073 (Jul 2026)","what_it_does":"S3-compatible decentralized cloud object storage aimed at businesses — a decentralized alternative to AWS S3.","how_it_works":"Client-side encryption + erasure coding: each file is encrypted, split into 80+ pieces distributed to statistically-uncorrelated nodes worldwide; only 30 pieces are needed to reconstruct (built-in redundancy — claims to have never lost a file). Node operators earn STORJ for supplying spare disk/bandwidth. S3-compatible gateway makes it a drop-in for existing apps. 2025: became EVM-compatible (fixed ETH address per account) for Web3 smart-contract access.","adoption":"Enterprise-focused; strongest real S3-replacement product among decentralized storage. Oct 2025: acquired by Inveniam Capital Partners — Storj tech to be integrated into Inveniam''s private-markets data platform (major enterprise validation). Partner revenue-share program drives app-developer integrations. Ransomware-resistance and edge-security are the main selling points.","doc_verification_use":"Not a notarization tool — its value for documents is confidential, tamper-resistant, redundant storage (client-side encryption means only the owner can read/alter files). Suits secure document retention rather than public proof-of-existence.","economics":"STORJ is the payment/settlement unit between customers and node operators; real usage-based revenue. July 2025: introduced monthly open-market STORJ buybacks in the payout process + planned staking to reduce circulating supply. Risk: heavily dependent on Storj Labs/Inveniam — if the company fails, network utility is uncertain.","non_economic":"Mature product, S3 compatibility, EVM compatibility (only decentralized storage with it, per Storj). Inveniam acquisition gives enterprise distribution.","outlook":"Bull: Inveniam enterprise integration + buybacks/staking drive real STORJ demand. Base: steady niche S3-alternative with modest usage. Bear: centralization dependence on Storj Labs, weak token, AWS price competition. Key risk: single-company dependency undermines the ''decentralized'' value prop.","status":"steady","sources":[{"title":"Storj: Decentralized Cloud Storage With STORJ — Gemini","url":"https://www.gemini.com/cryptopedia/storj-coin-decentralized-storage"},{"title":"Storj EVM-compatible decentralized storage","url":"https://www.storj.io/blog/storj-fully-evm-compatible-decentralized-storage-for-ethereum-and-l2-applications"},{"title":"Storj price — CoinGecko storage category","url":"https://www.coingecko.com/en/categories/storage"}]}','[{"title":"Gemini Storj","url":"https://www.gemini.com/cryptopedia/storj-coin-decentralized-storage"},{"title":"Storj EVM blog","url":"https://www.storj.io/blog/storj-fully-evm-compatible-decentralized-storage-for-ethereum-and-l2-applications"}]','2026-07-08 15:21:15');
INSERT INTO "infra_chains" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('sia','Sia (Siacoin)','storage','niche','{"name":"Sia (Siacoin)","category":"storage","launched":"2015","founders":"David Vorick, Luke Champine (Nebulous Labs; now Sia Foundation)","raised":"~$1.65M (2014 seed, Raptor Group, Procyon Ventures) + Siafunds revenue-share instrument","token_symbol":"SC (Siacoin)","token_ath":"~$0.111 (Jan 2018)","token_current":"~$0.0006 (Jul 2026)","what_it_does":"One of the oldest decentralized cloud storage networks — a contract-based marketplace matching renters with hosts, rebranded in 2025 as ''Safest Cloud Storage, by Design''.","how_it_works":"PoW blockchain + storage contracts: renters and hosts lock SC into escrow; files are encrypted, erasure-coded, and split across multiple hosts. Hosts must submit periodic storage proofs (Merkle proofs against the blockchain) or lose their collateral. V2 hard fork completed July 2025 (10-year anniversary) for scalability/usability. Skynet (its content-delivery layer) is dormant since Skynet Labs shut down in Nov 2022.","adoption":"Niche and declining in activity. Q3 2025 (Messari): ~14,300 daily active storage contracts (+4.3% QoQ, longer contract lifetimes), but daily new contracts and transactions fell sharply and quarterly revenue dropped ~78% to ~$18,390 amid V2 migration disruption. June 2025: HackerNoon adopted Sia as decentralized storage backbone for its archives.","doc_verification_use":"Similar to Storj — encrypted, redundant, contract-proven storage rather than public notarization. Storage proofs give ongoing evidence hosts hold the data, but it is not designed as a proof-of-existence/timestamping service.","economics":"SC pays for storage contracts; separate Siafunds instrument takes a fee cut of contract revenue. Revenue is very low in absolute terms (~$200/day in Q3 2025). Token near all-time lows; economic sustainability depends on reversing the activity slide post-V2.","non_economic":"Longest-running decentralized storage project (10+ yrs), non-profit Sia Foundation governance, 2025 rebrand + V2 upgrade. Small but committed community; Skynet dormant.","outlook":"Bull: V2 + rebrand stabilize retention and attract privacy-focused users. Base: persistent niche with slowly shrinking activity. Bear: outcompeted by Filecoin/Arweave/Walrus, revenue and token keep fading. Key risk: declining new demand and revenue despite technical maturity.","status":"niche","sources":[{"title":"State of Sia Q3 2025 — Messari","url":"https://messari.io/report/state-of-sia-q3-2025"},{"title":"State of Sia Q2 2025 — Messari","url":"https://messari.io/report/state-of-sia-q2-2025"},{"title":"Sia Cloud Storage Network","url":"https://sia.tech/"}]}','[{"title":"Messari Sia Q3 2025","url":"https://messari.io/report/state-of-sia-q3-2025"},{"title":"Messari Sia Q2 2025","url":"https://messari.io/report/state-of-sia-q2-2025"},{"title":"Sia","url":"https://sia.tech/"}]','2026-07-08 15:21:40');
INSERT INTO "infra_chains" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('walrus','Walrus','storage','thriving','{"name":"Walrus","category":"storage","launched":"Mar 27, 2025 (mainnet)","founders":"Mysten Labs team (Walrus Foundation); Sui creators","raised":"$140M private token sale (early 2025; Standard Crypto lead, a16z crypto, Electric Capital, Franklin Templeton Digital Assets)","token_symbol":"WAL","token_ath":"~$0.77 (2025, post-launch)","token_current":"~$0.031 (Jul 2026)","what_it_does":"Programmable decentralized storage and data-availability network built on Sui — a well-funded newcomer targeting Web3 media, NFTs, and AI data.","how_it_works":"Two-dimensional erasure coding (RedStuff algorithm) spreads encoded shards across independent storage nodes — more efficient than 1-D erasure coding. Each stored blob is represented as a Sui object with on-chain metadata, so Move smart contracts can control, route, and pay for storage (programmability is the key differentiator). Deflationary mechanisms + slashing for poor-performing nodes. Product suite: Seal (on-chain access control), Quilt (small-file batching), MemWal (AI-agent memory layer).","adoption":"Fast early traction: 450+ TB stored by its 1st anniversary (2026). Partners: Team Liquid (250TB of esports archives), Decrypt (media content), Pudgy Penguins (NFT content via Tusky file manager), Allium (65TB institutional-grade Bitcoin/Ethereum/Sui data, Mar 2026), TradePort (dynamic NFT metadata). 120+ projects and 11 fully on-chain websites within months of launch.","doc_verification_use":"Verifiable data with on-chain Sui object references gives content-integrity + programmable access control (via Seal). Suitable for verifiable document storage and provenance where programmable, auditable access is needed, though it is contract-based (renewable) not permanent like Arweave.","economics":"WAL pays for storage, staking, and governance (5B supply). Buyer demand = storage payments; deflationary burns punish short-term stake shifting. Investor unlocks deferred to Mar 2026 to limit early sell pressure. Value tracks real storage demand + Sui ecosystem growth.","non_economic":"Very well-capitalized ($140M), tight Sui/Move integration, rapid product shipping (Seal, Quilt, MemWal for AI). Strong Mysten Labs engineering brand.","outlook":"Bull: programmability + AI-memory (MemWal) + Sui growth make it the leading modern storage layer. Base: strong-funded challenger carving real usage. Bear: fate tied to Sui adoption; must displace entrenched Filecoin/Arweave. Key risk: Sui-ecosystem concentration and unproven long-term durability.","status":"thriving","sources":[{"title":"Walrus: Verifiable Data for Developers","url":"https://walrus.xyz/"},{"title":"Walrus Protocol: Sui''s $140M storage bet — BlockEden","url":"https://blockeden.xyz/blog/2026/01/10/walrus-protocol-sui-decentralized-storage-wars/"},{"title":"What is Walrus — Backpack Learn","url":"https://learn.backpack.exchange/articles/what-is-walrus-a-programmable-decentralized-storage-network"}]}','[{"title":"Walrus.xyz","url":"https://walrus.xyz/"},{"title":"BlockEden Walrus","url":"https://blockeden.xyz/blog/2026/01/10/walrus-protocol-sui-decentralized-storage-wars/"},{"title":"Backpack Learn Walrus","url":"https://learn.backpack.exchange/articles/what-is-walrus-a-programmable-decentralized-storage-network"}]','2026-07-08 15:22:03');
INSERT INTO "infra_chains" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('crust','Crust Network','storage','fading','{"name":"Crust Network","category":"storage","launched":"2021 (mainnet; Polkadot ecosystem)","founders":"Bova Chen (Crust team)","raised":"Seed/private rounds + Polkadot parachain crowdloan (undisclosed, modest)","token_symbol":"CRU","token_ath":"~$59 (2021)","token_current":"~$0.0087 (Jul 2026) — ~99.9% below ATH; ATL $0.0217 set Dec 2025","what_it_does":"An incentive and storage-proof layer on top of IPFS — makes IPFS content actually persist by paying nodes to pin and prove they hold data.","how_it_works":"Solves IPFS''s core weakness (no persistence): pays CRU rewards to nodes that genuinely store/replicate files. MPoW (Meaningful Proof of Work) verifies real storage via Trusted Execution Environment (TEE) attestation; GPoS (Guaranteed Proof of Stake) ties each node''s staking quota to its proven storage. Participates in the public IPFS DHT and runs IPFS-compatible pinning gateways (drop-in IPFS API), so Web3 users can pin without running local IPFS.","adoption":"Claims 200+ ecosystem collaborations in 2025 (L1/L2s, AI apps, DePIN, Web3 tooling), repositioning around DePIN + AI-data narratives. But market metrics are weak: ~8,003 token holders (Dec 2025), ~$0.6M market cap, 100% of supply in circulation, CRU down ~95% YoY. 2025 was ''technical consolidation'' (block-finality fixes, validator tuning, adaptive staking/fee economics) rather than growth.","doc_verification_use":"Inherits IPFS content-integrity (CIDs are tamper-evident) plus TEE-attested persistence guarantees — useful for ensuring a verified document stays retrievable, but not a timestamping/notarization service on its own.","economics":"CRU pays for storage orders and secures the network via GPoS staking. Value capture is minimal in practice — tiny market cap and fully-diluted supply mean little upside buffer. Adaptive fee/staking introduced 2025 to keep baseline security during low activity.","non_economic":"IPFS-compatible tooling, Polkadot/Substrate integration, DePIN positioning. Developer accessibility (standard IPFS pinning API) is a plus, but momentum and community engagement are low.","outlook":"Bull: DePIN/AI-data narrative + IPFS-persistence niche revive demand. Base: continues as a low-profile IPFS incentive layer. Bear: token near zero, overshadowed by Filecoin (also incentivizes IPFS persistence) and better-funded rivals. Key risk: technical work not translating into usage or value; possible slow fade.","status":"fading","sources":[{"title":"Crust Network 2025 retrospective — Medium","url":"https://crustnetwork.medium.com/crust-network-2025-laying-the-foundation-for-the-next-internet-of-data-and-ai-a349b362a542"},{"title":"Crust Overview — Crust Wiki","url":"https://wiki.crust.network/docs/en/crustOverview"},{"title":"Crust Network project details — Parachains.info","url":"https://parachains.info/details/crust_network"}]}','[{"title":"Crust 2025 retrospective","url":"https://crustnetwork.medium.com/crust-network-2025-laying-the-foundation-for-the-next-internet-of-data-and-ai-a349b362a542"},{"title":"Crust Wiki","url":"https://wiki.crust.network/docs/en/crustOverview"}]','2026-07-08 15:22:27');
INSERT INTO "infra_chains" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('swarm','Swarm (BZZ)','storage','niche','{"name":"Swarm (BZZ)","category":"storage","launched":"2021 (mainnet; incubated within Ethereum Foundation from ~2015)","founders":"Viktor Trón (Ethereum Foundation origins; Swarm Foundation)","raised":"~$6M+ (2021 BZZ private/public sale)","token_symbol":"BZZ","token_ath":"~$3.9 (2021)","token_current":"~sub-$0.30 (low; 2026)","what_it_does":"Ethereum''s native decentralized storage and communication layer — censorship-resistant storage for the Ethereum stack, run via the Bee client.","how_it_works":"Content is chunked and distributed across the Bee node network addressed by content hash. Persistence is paid for using ''postage stamps'' (prepaid batches of BZZ that give chunks a right to be stored), and node bandwidth is settled peer-to-peer via the SWAP incentive protocol (off-chain accounting, on-chain settlement in BZZ). Designed as the storage/messaging tier of a ''sovereign digital society'' alongside Ethereum compute.","adoption":"Niche. Real usage is modest and concentrated among Ethereum-aligned devs and privacy/censorship-resistance projects; Bee node network exists but data-stored figures are small relative to Filecoin/Arweave. Positioned as ideologically-aligned Ethereum storage rather than an enterprise product; limited mainstream traction.","doc_verification_use":"Content-addressed chunks are tamper-evident (like IPFS); postage-stamp persistence gives durability while paid. Usable for censorship-resistant document hosting, but not a timestamping/proof-of-existence service by itself.","economics":"BZZ captures value via postage stamps (prepaid storage) and SWAP bandwidth settlement. Value tracks storage demand, which is currently thin. Token well below ATH; economic sustainability depends on growing paid postage demand.","non_economic":"Deep Ethereum-ecosystem alignment and open-source Bee client; strong ideological/censorship-resistance positioning and a committed but small developer community.","outlook":"Bull: becomes the default storage/messaging layer for a decentralized Ethereum web. Base: steady but small Ethereum-native niche. Bear: outcompeted by IPFS+Filecoin and newer networks; stays marginal. Key risk: low real usage and weak network effects vs. better-funded rivals.","status":"niche","sources":[{"title":"What Is Swarm (BZZ)? — Gate Learn","url":"https://www.gate.com/learn/articles/what-is-swarm-all-you-need-to-know-about-bzz/3385"},{"title":"ethersphere/swarm — GitHub","url":"https://github.com/ethersphere/swarm"},{"title":"Digital Freedom now — Swarm","url":"https://api.gateway.ethswarm.org/bzz/swarm.eth/"}]}','[{"title":"Gate Learn Swarm","url":"https://www.gate.com/learn/articles/what-is-swarm-all-you-need-to-know-about-bzz/3385"},{"title":"Swarm GitHub","url":"https://github.com/ethersphere/swarm"}]','2026-07-08 15:22:45');
INSERT INTO "infra_chains" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('celestia','Celestia','data-availability','steady','{"name":"Celestia","category":"data-availability","launched":"Oct 31, 2023 (mainnet)","founders":"Mustafa Al-Bassam, Ismail Khoffi, John Adler, Nick White","raised":"~$155M ($55M Series B 2022 led by Bain Capital Crypto & Polychain; plus earlier rounds)","token_symbol":"TIA","token_ath":"$20.85 (Feb 10, 2024)","token_current":"~$0.35 (Jul 2026) — ~98% below ATH","what_it_does":"The first modular data-availability (DA) network — rollups post their transaction data to Celestia cheaply instead of to expensive Ethereum, and light nodes verify it is available.","how_it_works":"Blob DA + Data Availability Sampling (DAS): rollups publish data ''blobs''; light nodes sample small random pieces via 2-D Reed-Solomon erasure coding to probabilistically guarantee all data was published without downloading it — so DA scales with more light nodes. Consensus separated from execution (modular thesis). Blobstream bridges DA commitments to Ethereum L1. Matcha upgrade (Nov 24, 2025) raised max block size 8MB->128MB (16x) and cut inflation ~5%->2.5%.","adoption":"~50% DA market share and processed 160GB+ of rollup data (~2.5GB/day avg) since launch; ~$180M secured across ~a dozen projects (L2BEAT). BUT heavy concentration: by mid-2026 the Eclipse rollup was ~84% of daily blob volume, and only ~0.05% of throughput capacity is used. Supported as a DA option by every major framework (Arbitrum Orbit, OP Stack, Polygon CDK); Rollkit for sovereign rollups. Early adopters: Eclipse, Aevo, Lyra, Orderly, Movement.","doc_verification_use":"Not a notarization tool — DA proves data was published/available for a window (not permanent proof-of-existence). Its verification role is guaranteeing rollup data availability so anyone can reconstruct/challenge L2 state, not document notarization.","economics":"TIA captures value via blob fees (pay-for-DA) + staking/security. The problem: raw capacity vastly exceeds demand, blobspace is cheap (~$0.07/MB vs Ethereum''s ~$3.83 — 55x cheaper), and fee revenue is thin and concentrated on one customer. Token down ~98% from ATH — strong tech, unproven demand.","non_economic":"Flagship modular-blockchain brand; broad framework integrations create switching costs; active R&D (Matcha, gigabyte-block roadmap by 2030). Large developer mindshare.","outlook":"Bull: rollup explosion + gigabyte blocks make Celestia the neutral DA public utility. Base: leading DA layer but demand grows slowly. Bear: Ethereum blob upgrades narrow the cost gap, single-customer concentration exposes fragility, TIA stays depressed. Key risk: DA demand may never justify the valuation; Eclipse-concentration risk.","status":"steady","sources":[{"title":"Celestia blob economics & DA — BlockEden","url":"https://blockeden.xyz/blog/2026/01/16/celestia-blob-economics-data-availability-rollup-costs/"},{"title":"Modular Data Availability Layer — Celestia Docs","url":"https://docs.celestia.org/learn/celestia-101/data-availability/"},{"title":"Celestia analytics — Blockworks","url":"https://blockworks.com/analytics/celestia"}]}','[{"title":"BlockEden Celestia","url":"https://blockeden.xyz/blog/2026/01/16/celestia-blob-economics-data-availability-rollup-costs/"},{"title":"Celestia Docs DA","url":"https://docs.celestia.org/learn/celestia-101/data-availability/"},{"title":"Blockworks Celestia","url":"https://blockworks.com/analytics/celestia"}]','2026-07-08 15:23:13');
INSERT INTO "infra_chains" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('eigenda','EigenDA','data-availability','thriving','{"name":"EigenDA","category":"data-availability","launched":"2024 (mainnet); V2 ~early 2026","founders":"Sreeram Kannan (Eigen Labs / EigenLayer)","raised":"~$160M+ (EigenLayer: $50M Series A 2023 a16z crypto; $100M 2024 a16z crypto)","token_symbol":"EIGEN (restaking secured by ETH; EigenDA is a service, not its own DA token)","token_ath":"EIGEN below launch levels (2024)","token_current":"N/A for DA fees (denominated via restaked ETH/EIGEN)","what_it_does":"A high-throughput data-availability service built on EigenLayer restaking — gives rollups DA secured by restaked Ethereum rather than a separate sovereign token.","how_it_works":"Decouples DA from consensus (Danksharding-inspired): data is erasure-coded and dispersed to ~200 operators who hold shards; KZG commitments + attestations prove availability without independent consensus, so throughput scales linearly with operators. Secured by ~4.3M restaked ETH (billions of $) via EigenLayer; slashing went live Apr 17, 2025. Rollups can add custom quorums (EIGEN / own token) for extra security. V2 (early 2026) hit ~100MB/s throughput.","adoption":"Leading DA layer by raw throughput (~100MB/s in V2). Adopters: Mantle (modular L2), MegaETH (high-performance L2, marquee use case), plus OP Stack / zk Stack rollups and multiple RaaS providers offering one-click EigenDA deployment. ~200 EigenLayer operators; billions in restaked economic security. Cost ~$730/yr for a 100MB/day rollup.","doc_verification_use":"Like Celestia, a DA layer not a notarization tool — attestations prove data was made available to operators for verification/reconstruction, not permanent proof-of-existence of documents.","economics":"Value accrues to the EigenLayer restaking economy (ETH/EIGEN) rather than a dedicated DA token; rollups pay DA fees and can reserve bandwidth at a discount. Ethereum-aligned security is the differentiator vs. sovereign-token DA (Celestia/Avail). Part of 2025 ''EigenCloud'' rebrand (DA + compute + AI + dispute resolution); Eigen Labs cut ~25% staff July 2025 to focus.","non_economic":"Backed by EigenLayer (the largest restaking protocol, 200+ AVSs live/in-dev). Strong a16z backing, deep Ethereum alignment, aggressive throughput roadmap (hundreds of MB/s, sub-second latency).","outlook":"Bull: restaked-ETH security + highest throughput wins the DA war; EigenCloud becomes the verifiable-cloud platform. Base: strong #2/#1 DA option for Ethereum-aligned rollups. Bear: restaking risk/complexity, EIGEN token weakness, competition from cheaper Celestia. Key risk: restaking systemic risk and monetization clarity for the DA service.","status":"thriving","sources":[{"title":"EigenDA Overview — EigenCloud Docs","url":"https://docs.eigencloud.xyz/eigenda/core-concepts/overview"},{"title":"Intro to EigenDA: Hyperscale DA for Rollups","url":"https://blog.eigencloud.xyz/intro-to-eigenda-hyperscale-data-availability-for-rollups/"},{"title":"EigenDA vs Avail — Crawlux","url":"https://www.crawlux.com/compare/eigenda-vs-avail/"}]}','[{"title":"EigenDA Docs","url":"https://docs.eigencloud.xyz/eigenda/core-concepts/overview"},{"title":"Intro to EigenDA","url":"https://blog.eigencloud.xyz/intro-to-eigenda-hyperscale-data-availability-for-rollups/"}]','2026-07-08 15:23:33');
INSERT INTO "infra_chains" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('avail','Avail','data-availability','steady','{"name":"Avail","category":"data-availability","launched":"Jul 2024 (Avail DA mainnet); spun out of Polygon","founders":"Anurag Arjun (Polygon co-founder), Prabal Banerjee","raised":"~$43M ($27M seed 2023 Founders Fund & Dragonfly; $16M pre-seed)","token_symbol":"AVAIL","token_ath":"~$0.19 (2024)","token_current":"low (sub-$0.10; heavy unlock pressure)","what_it_does":"A sovereign data-availability chain plus a broader ''unification'' stack (Nexus cross-chain layer + Fusion shared security) aiming to consolidate fragmented Web3 liquidity and DA.","how_it_works":"DA via KZG polynomial commitments + Data Availability Sampling (light clients verify data availability cheaply), similar concept to Celestia. Three-layer stack: (1) Avail DA (currently 4MB blocks ~660KB/s, roadmap to 10GB ''Infinity Blocks''; Matcha upgrade Q1 2026 -> 128MB); (2) Nexus — permissionless cross-chain coordination/verification hub aggregating proofs (mainnet Nov 2025); (3) Fusion — pooled multi-asset security (stake AVAIL/ETH/BTC to secure appchains; still ''coming'').","adoption":"Growing but less proven than Celestia. Clients: Lens Chain (SocialFi L2 by Aave team — 650K profiles, 28M social connections, 12M+ posts migrated since Apr 2025), Sophon (80M+ txns, 23 apps, 12.75GB posted to Avail by May), plus Starknet, Space & Time, SOON, Rooch. Strategic TRON integration into Nexus (accessing TRON''s ~$77B USDT liquidity). ''50+ more chains integrating'' claimed.","doc_verification_use":"DA layer, not a notarization service — guarantees rollup data availability for verification/reconstruction, not permanent document proof-of-existence.","economics":"AVAIL used for validator staking (PoS security), DA-service payments, governance, and Fusion pooled security. Stakers earn inflation + DA fees. Near-term headwind: airdrop overhang and scheduled unlocks create sell pressure; value depends on sustained cross-chain volume via Nexus.","non_economic":"Strong founder pedigree (Polygon), Founders Fund/Dragonfly backing, ambitious full-stack unification vision (DA + interop + shared security). Broad integration pipeline but less battle-tested traction than Celestia.","outlook":"Bull: Nexus becomes the cross-chain liquidity hub + Fusion bootstraps new chains, making AVAIL the coordination asset for a unified Web3. Base: credible #3 DA layer with a differentiated interop story. Bear: unlock-driven sell pressure, execution risk on cross-chain security, loses DA share to Celestia/EigenDA. Key risk: unification thesis unproven; token unlock overhang.","status":"steady","sources":[{"title":"What Is Avail (AVAIL) — CoinMarketCap","url":"https://coinmarketcap.com/cmc-ai/avail/what-is/"},{"title":"Avail Debuts Nexus Mainnet — BlockchainReporter","url":"https://blockchainreporter.net/avail-debuts-nexus-mainnet-promising-a-single-operational-universe-for-web3/"},{"title":"EigenDA vs Avail — Crawlux","url":"https://www.crawlux.com/compare/eigenda-vs-avail/"}]}','[{"title":"CMC Avail","url":"https://coinmarketcap.com/cmc-ai/avail/what-is/"},{"title":"Avail Nexus mainnet","url":"https://blockchainreporter.net/avail-debuts-nexus-mainnet-promising-a-single-operational-universe-for-web3/"}]','2026-07-08 15:23:56');
INSERT INTO "infra_chains" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('opentimestamps','OpenTimestamps','notarization-verification','steady','{"name":"OpenTimestamps","category":"notarization-verification","launched":"2016","founders":"Peter Todd (Bitcoin Core developer)","raised":"None — free, open-source public-good protocol (no token, no company)","token_symbol":"None","token_ath":"N/A","token_current":"N/A","what_it_does":"The leading open standard for Bitcoin-anchored proof-of-existence timestamping — proves a document existed at a point in time without revealing its contents, no trusted third party.","how_it_works":"Hash-anchoring: only the SHA256 hash of your file is committed to Bitcoin (the file never leaves your machine). Free ''calendar servers'' aggregate many user hashes into a single Merkle tree and anchor the tree root in one Bitcoin transaction (so users pay nothing). The proof is a compact .ots file containing the Merkle path from your hash to a Bitcoin block header; anyone with a Bitcoin node can verify it independently, forever. Survives even a Bitcoin 51% attack — only a hash-function break could invalidate past proofs.","adoption":"Mature, production-grade, widely used for years. Free calendar-server infrastructure (no registration/API key) makes it the default open notarization primitive. Used for IP protection, research provenance, compliance, contracts, audits. Underlies/integrates with many downstream tools (e.g. ProofSnap, and Woleet offers an OTS-compatible path). Verifiable in-browser at opentimestamps.org.","doc_verification_use":"THIS IS ITS ENTIRE PURPOSE. It is a trust-minimized digital-notary: an .ots receipt proves a specific document existed before a given Bitcoin block and has not changed since — like a notary stamp but backed by Bitcoin instead of a person. Privacy-preserving (hash-only) and free.","economics":"No token, no revenue, no value capture — a pure public good funded by calendar-server operators paying Bitcoin fees. This is a feature (no rent-seeking) and a fragility (depends on volunteers/sponsors running calendars).","non_economic":"Bitcoin-developer pedigree (Peter Todd), stable long-lived format with guaranteed backward-compatible verification, strong open-source ethos. The reference implementation for blockchain timestamping.","outlook":"Bull: remains the universal free standard for proof-of-existence, embedded in ever more tools. Base: steady quiet public-good infrastructure. Bear: lacks formal legal recognition vs RFC 3161 in some jurisdictions, limiting enterprise/legal adoption; calendar-server funding is informal. Key risk: legal-recognition gap and dependence on volunteer calendar servers.","status":"steady","sources":[{"title":"OpenTimestamps: a timestamping proof standard","url":"https://opentimestamps.org/"},{"title":"OpenTimestamps — Wikipedia","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenTimestamps"},{"title":"opentimestamps-client — GitHub","url":"https://github.com/opentimestamps/opentimestamps-client"}]}','[{"title":"OpenTimestamps.org","url":"https://opentimestamps.org/"},{"title":"Wikipedia OpenTimestamps","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenTimestamps"}]','2026-07-08 15:24:14');
INSERT INTO "infra_chains" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('bloxberg','bloxberg','notarization-verification','niche','{"name":"bloxberg","category":"notarization-verification","launched":"2019","founders":"Max Planck Digital Library / bloxberg consortium (academic)","raised":"None — non-commercial academic consortium (funded by member institutions)","token_symbol":"None (permissioned academic chain)","token_ath":"N/A","token_current":"N/A","what_it_does":"A blockchain-for-science: a permissioned Ethereum-based network run by ~40 research institutions worldwide, providing proof-of-existence certification for research data and documents.","how_it_works":"Consortial (public-permissioned) Ethereum network using Proof-of-Authority (Aura) consensus — only vetted academic institutions run validating full nodes. Notarization via Proof of Existence (PoE): a document''s cryptographic hash + timestamp (+ optional metadata) is stored on-chain, proving a file existed at a time without disclosing its contents. Integrates into research workflows (e.g. a MATLAB extension; Max Planck''s ''Certify'' tool).","adoption":"Real but narrow — used within academia for research-data certification and provenance. ~40 academic member institutions globally operate the network. Practical implementations via Max Planck Digital Library. A genuine, working real-world notarization use case, but confined to the research/academic niche rather than broad commercial traction.","doc_verification_use":"Core purpose: public-notary service for research artifacts — certify existence/integrity of datasets, papers, and results at a timestamp without exposing content. Distinct from full ''notary'' systems in that it proves existence, not identity-vetted certification (no verified signer identities by default).","economics":"No token, no revenue model — a shared academic public good funded and operated by member institutions. Value is scientific integrity/reproducibility, not economic.","non_economic":"Backed by respected research institutions (Max Planck et al.), academic governance, integration tooling (MATLAB/API). Strong credibility within science; limited outside it.","outlook":"Bull: becomes standard infrastructure for reproducible-science provenance and research-data integrity. Base: steady academic-niche utility. Bear: low awareness, competition from simpler tools (OpenTimestamps, OriginStamp, Blockcerts), institutional inertia. Key risk: confined to academia; depends on continued consortium funding.","status":"niche","sources":[{"title":"Integrating bloxberg''s Proof of Existence Service With MATLAB — Frontiers in Blockchain","url":"https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/blockchain/articles/10.3389/fbloc.2020.546264/full"},{"title":"Certify documents via the bloxberg blockchain — Max Planck Digital Library","url":"https://mpdl.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/360010713999-Certify-Keeper-documents-via-the-bloxberg-blockchain"}]}','[{"title":"Frontiers bloxberg PoE","url":"https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/blockchain/articles/10.3389/fbloc.2020.546264/full"},{"title":"Max Planck Certify bloxberg","url":"https://mpdl.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/360010713999-Certify-Keeper-documents-via-the-bloxberg-blockchain"}]','2026-07-08 15:24:36');
INSERT INTO "infra_chains" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('woleet','Woleet','notarization-verification','niche','{"name":"Woleet","category":"notarization-verification","launched":"~2017 (French startup)","founders":"Woleet SAS (Rennes, France)","raised":"Small seed/grant funding (undisclosed; EU/French startup)","token_symbol":"None (SaaS; anchors to Bitcoin)","token_ath":"N/A","token_current":"N/A","what_it_does":"Enterprise e-signature and timestamping platform that anchors proofs into the Bitcoin blockchain — adds verifiable identity and signature to proof-of-existence.","how_it_works":"Two modes: (1) data anchoring — timestamp a file''s hash on Bitcoin (proves existence, not who); (2) signature anchoring — the data is first signed (Bitcoin ECDSA over the SHA256 hash), and the signature is anchored, proving existence + authorship + integrity. WoleetID manages corporate signer identities (each identity = a claimed Bitcoin address + private key). Proofs use the open Chainpoint receipt format (OTS-compatible option exists) and are independently verifiable at btcproof.info, no third party. Anchoring latency ~3-6 hours (Bitcoin batching).","adoption":"Niche enterprise/B2B. Targets e-signature-with-Bitcoin-evidence, certification, authentication, and traceability use cases. Offers on-site WoleetID server, an API, and a CLI for automated bulk proofs (systemd timers). Real product but limited public 2025 news/momentum; most docs date 2019-2020, suggesting steady-but-quiet operation.","doc_verification_use":"Core purpose: notarization + authenticated signature — goes beyond bare proof-of-existence (like OpenTimestamps) by binding a verified signer identity to the timestamped signature, enabling defensible e-signatures, document certification, and provenance/traceability for enterprises.","economics":"SaaS/licensing revenue (API usage, on-site server licenses) — no token. Relies on Bitcoin only as an anchoring substrate. Value capture is subscription-based, not crypto-native.","non_economic":"Open, verifiable Chainpoint proof format; open-sourced WoleetID; independent verifier (btcproof.info). Solid engineering but small footprint and low visibility.","outlook":"Bull: enterprises adopt Bitcoin-evidenced e-signatures for legal defensibility and traceability. Base: steady small B2B niche. Bear: eclipsed by free OpenTimestamps for pure timestamping and by mainstream e-sign vendors (DocuSign) for signatures; low growth. Key risk: limited differentiation/awareness and stalled momentum.","status":"niche","sources":[{"title":"Signature anchoring on Bitcoin — Woleet","url":"https://blog.woleet.io/signature-anchoring-on-bitcoin/"},{"title":"WoleetID Presentation — Woleet Docs","url":"https://doc.woleet.io/docs/woleetid"},{"title":"BTCProof independent verifier","url":"https://btcproof.info/"}]}','[{"title":"Woleet signature anchoring","url":"https://blog.woleet.io/signature-anchoring-on-bitcoin/"},{"title":"WoleetID docs","url":"https://doc.woleet.io/docs/woleetid"}]','2026-07-08 15:24:53');
INSERT INTO "infra_chains" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('factom','Factom','notarization-verification','dead','{"name":"Factom","category":"notarization-verification","launched":"2015 (token sale Apr 2015)","founders":"Paul Snow, David Johnston (Austin, TX)","raised":"~$18M+ total (incl. $4M Series A 2016 led by Tim Draper; DHS grants)","token_symbol":"FCT (migrated to ACME on Accumulate at 1 FCT : 5 ACME)","token_ath":"~$85 (2018 bull run)","token_current":"Defunct — FCT no longer transacts; converted to Accumulate ACME","what_it_does":"One of the earliest (2014-15) blockchain data-integrity/notarization protocols — an immutable, independently-verifiable record-keeping layer for enterprises and government, storing proofs rather than payments.","how_it_works":"Stored cryptographic hashes (digital fingerprints) of documents — not the documents themselves — for cheap, private, verifiable proof of data provenance/integrity. Anchored its own consensus results into the Bitcoin blockchain every ~10 minutes (a single data point secured large batches of Factom entries with Bitcoin''s security). Two-token model: Factoids (FCT, speculative/burned) + Entry Credits (EC, USD-stable utility for writing entries).","adoption":"High-profile early government/enterprise interest: $192K U.S. Department of Homeland Security grant (2018) to secure border-sensor/camera data; data-protection, identity, and distributed-storage products. But real recurring usage never scaled to justify the company; it stands as a cautionary tale of early notarization hype.","doc_verification_use":"This WAS its core purpose — Bitcoin-anchored proof-of-existence and data-integrity for records/documents without disclosing content. The design (hash-only + Bitcoin anchoring) is the canonical enterprise-notarization pattern, later echoed by OpenTimestamps and Woleet.","economics":"Burn-based utility (EC bought by burning FCT) intended to tie token demand to write-volume. It failed commercially: Factom Inc. entered dissolution/liquidation in 2020 after backers (incl. FastForward) declined further funding despite ~$18M raised.","non_economic":"Pioneering design and notable partnerships, but the company collapsed. The PROTOCOL survived: node operators voted in late 2021 to rewrite/rebrand it as Accumulate Network (ACME), retaining anchoring; FCT converted to ACME 1:5. Original Factom infrastructure is effectively retired (wallets extract keys only).","outlook":"Bear/dead: Factom in its original form is defunct — company liquidated 2020, protocol migrated to Accumulate 2021-22. Legacy: proved the enterprise-notarization thesis technically but not commercially; demand for on-chain notarization never materialized at the scale needed to sustain a funded company. Key lesson: notarization is a feature, not a fundable standalone network.","status":"dead","sources":[{"title":"Factom Inc. Faces Liquidation — CoinDesk","url":"https://www.coindesk.com/business/2020/04/02/factom-inc-faces-liquidation-after-investors-refuse-request-for-more-funding"},{"title":"Factom Transition to Accumulate Guide & FAQ — Accumulate","url":"https://accumulatenetwork.io/2022/05/factom-transition-to-accumulate-guide-faq"},{"title":"Factom (FCT) — MarketsWiki","url":"https://www.marketswiki.com/wiki/Factom_(FCT)"}]}','[{"title":"CoinDesk Factom liquidation","url":"https://www.coindesk.com/business/2020/04/02/factom-inc-faces-liquidation-after-investors-refuse-request-for-more-funding"},{"title":"Accumulate transition","url":"https://accumulatenetwork.io/2022/05/factom-transition-to-accumulate-guide-faq"}]','2026-07-08 15:25:15');
INSERT INTO "market_entities" ("slug","name","ticker","type","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('strategy-mstr','Strategy (formerly MicroStrategy)','MSTR','treasury','at-risk','{"name":"Strategy (MicroStrategy)","ticker":"MSTR","type":"treasury","crypto_asset":"BTC","crypto_held":"843,775 BTC as of Jul 6 2026 (~$53.8B at market); the largest corporate BTC holder by a wide margin, ~4% of all BTC supply.","avg_cost_basis":"~$75,476/BTC; total cost basis ~$63.7B. Holdings sit near/below cost in the 2026 drawdown, which is the crux of the stress.","mnav":"~1.11x (an 11% premium to BTC NAV) as of early Jul 2026, sharply compressed from a peak near 1.80x. Touched 0.97x in Nov 2025 (first sub-1x since Jan 2024) and ~0.87x earlier in 2026. Below 1x the accretive-issuance flywheel breaks.","stock_price":"High-beta BTC proxy: BTC fell 36% Jan-Feb 2026 while MSTR fell 44% (~5x downside beta). 2026 analyst targets span ~$176-$228; Mizuho cut to $213.","market_cap":"~$33-34B common equity; enterprise value materially higher given $18.5B of senior claims stacked ahead of common.","funding":"ATM equity issuance + $8.25B convertible debt + ~$10.3B preferred stock (STRK/STRF/STRD/STRC at 8-11.5% coupons). Part of the Oct 2024 ''21/21 Plan'' ($21B equity + $21B fixed income by 2027). Preferred dividends alone approach ~$904M/yr in 2026 (up from $217M in 2025). The model only works while mNAV>1x; sub-1x issuance is dilutive and management pauses the ATM.","leadership":"Michael Saylor (Executive Chairman) — the originator of the corporate BTC-treasury template every peer copies; Phong Le (CEO). Saylor''s conviction and communication drive the equity''s premium, but concentration/key-man risk is high.","dilution_risk":"HIGH when sub-NAV. With mNAV near/below 1x, further ATM issuance destroys BTC-per-share. ~$18.5B of senior claims (converts + preferred) sit ahead of common; ~$1B/yr in preferred dividends plus cash-consuming software ops must be serviced regardless of BTC price.","strategy":"Issue equity/converts/preferred at a premium to NAV, buy BTC, grow BTC-per-share (''BTC Yield''). The flywheel reverses below 1x mNAV.","background":"Pioneer and largest corporate BTC holder; set the template every treasury company copies.","recent_moves":"Abandoned ''never sell'' in 2026 via a new Digital Credit Capital Framework: $2.55B USD reserve, up to $1B in MSTR buybacks, and authorization to monetize up to 20,800 BTC (~2.5% of holdings) to cover dividends/debt service. Bought 34,164 BTC in Apr 2026 (~$2.54B) and 535 BTC in May 2026.","analysis":"The thesis is a leveraged, premium-financed BTC accumulation machine: raise cheap capital while the stock trades above NAV, convert it to BTC, repeat. The numbers now cut against it — 843,775 BTC (~$53.8B) against a ~$63.7B cost basis and $18.5B of senior claims mean the balance sheet is near/below water with ~$1B/yr in fixed preferred obligations to service. The core risk is the mNAV-compression trap: with the premium down from 1.80x to ~1.11x (and briefly sub-1x), the ATM flywheel that funded accumulation is broken, and the new Digital Credit Framework formalizes BTC sales as a routine tool rather than a last resort — exactly the forced-seller dynamic the market feared. Catalysts that could re-inflate the premium are a strong BTC bull leg (restoring accretive issuance) or index/credit-rating upgrades; catalysts to the downside are BTC staying below cost basis, preferred-dividend strain, and further premium decay. Treat it as a high-volatility ~5x-beta BTC position, not a stable holding.","outlook":{"bull":"BTC rips to new highs, mNAV re-expands toward 1.3-1.8x, the ATM flywheel restarts and BTC-per-share compounds; MSTR reclaims its role as the premier leveraged BTC proxy with the deepest capital-markets access of any treasury.","base":"BTC chops sideways-to-up; mNAV hovers near 1.0-1.2x; issuance is muted, BTC-per-share grows slowly, and the company services preferred/debt without forced sales. High volatility, modest accretion.","bear":"BTC stays below the ~$75.5k cost basis; mNAV holds sub-1x; the framework''s authorized BTC sales become recurring to fund ~$1B/yr dividends and debt service; dilution and forced selling compound and the equity trades at a persistent discount to NAV."},"sources":["https://www.theblock.co/treasuries/mstr","https://www.vaneck.com/us/en/blogs/digital-assets/matthew-sigel-deconstructing-strategy-mstr-premium-leverage-and-capital-structure/","https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2026/06/27/strategy-s-valuation-has-fallen-below-the-value-of-its-bitcoin-holdings","https://bitcointreasuries.net/public-companies/strategy"]}','["https://www.theblock.co/treasuries/mstr","https://www.vaneck.com/us/en/blogs/digital-assets/matthew-sigel-deconstructing-strategy-mstr-premium-leverage-and-capital-structure/","https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2026/06/27/strategy-s-valuation-has-fallen-below-the-value-of-its-bitcoin-holdings","https://bitcointreasuries.net/public-companies/strategy"]','2026-07-08 15:47:11');
INSERT INTO "market_entities" ("slug","name","ticker","type","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('metaplanet','Metaplanet Inc.','3350.T','treasury','at-risk','{"name":"Metaplanet Inc.","ticker":"3350.T (OTCQX: MTPLF)","type":"treasury","crypto_asset":"BTC","crypto_held":"~43,000 BTC as of Jul 2 2026 (~$2.6B); grew from 35,102 BTC in Mar 2026 to 40,177 by end-Q1 (cumulative cost ~$3.92B). 3rd-largest public BTC treasury behind Strategy and Twenty One.","avg_cost_basis":"~$104,107/BTC — far above 2026 spot (~$60-75k), so the treasury is deeply underwater. FY2025 non-operating impairment ~$680M from BTC marks.","mnav":"Near parity. Own analytics tracker showed EV mNAV ~0.92x; third-party dashboards ~1.07-1.11x diluted. New Moving Strike Warrants are gated to only exercise at/above 1.01x mNAV.","stock_price":"~302 yen (~$1.89) Apr 2026, later ~$1.54; down ~82% over 1yr from the Jun 2025 peak near 1,930 yen. Market cap ~$1.97B, EV ~$2.36B.","market_cap":"~$1.97B (EV ~$2.36B).","funding":"Equity-linked, largely debt-averse. Mar 2026: raised ~$255M via 107.4M shares at 380 yen (2% premium) plus 1.07M fixed-strike warrants at 410 yen (up to +$276M) — total package up to $531M. Introduced 100M first-of-its-kind Moving Strike Warrants with an mNAV clause (only exercisable at >=1.01x mNAV, est. +$234M). Jan 2026: ~$137M raise (12.24B yen) to buy BTC and repay debt. Suspended up to 210M shares of older warrants to limit dilution. Also runs a Bitcoin Income Generation (options/covered-call) desk (~$10.85M Q2 2026 revenue).","leadership":"Simon Gerovich (CEO), ex-Goldman. Positions Metaplanet as the ''Asian MicroStrategy'' with tax-advantaged access for Japanese retail; credited with financial-engineering creativity (Moving Strike Warrants).","dilution_risk":"HIGH but structurally mitigated. The Moving Strike Warrant mNAV gate is explicitly designed to prevent value-destructive sub-NAV issuance — issuance pauses when mNAV<1.01x. But hitting the 100k-BTC target requires ~9,500 BTC/month of buying that only large, repeated raises can fund; if mNAV stays sub-1x those raises can''t fire, stalling the plan.","strategy":"Aggressive equity-linked accumulation plus a Bitcoin Income Generation business that lowers effective per-coin cost. ''555 Million Plan'' targets 100,000 BTC by end-2026 and 210,000 by end-2027 (~1% of supply).","background":"Japan''s flagship BTC treasury; Tokyo-listed with US OTC access.","recent_moves":"Bought 5,075 BTC in Q1 2026 and 2,823 BTC in Q2 2026. Executed the March mNAV-gated warrant raise; allocating ~$357M of proceeds to BTC (Apr 2026-Mar 2028) and ~$132M to debt repayment.","analysis":"Metaplanet is the most financially inventive of the treasury cohort: rather than fixed debt it leans on equity-linked warrants — notably the Moving Strike Warrants whose mNAV-gating is a genuine innovation that hard-codes the ''don''t issue below NAV'' discipline into the instrument itself. The numbers, though, are stark: ~43,000 BTC at a ~$104k cost basis against ~$60-75k spot is one of the deepest underwater positions in the group, driving a ~$680M FY25 impairment and an ~82% stock decline. The central risk is the same mNAV trap — with EV mNAV around or below 1x, the accretive-issuance engine can''t run, and the 100k-BTC year-end target (needing ~9,500 BTC/month) looks unreachable without dilutive raises the warrant structure is specifically designed to block. Catalysts: a BTC recovery that lifts mNAV back above the warrant trigger (restarting the accumulation engine), growth in the options-income desk cutting effective cost, and continued Japanese-retail demand. The bear case is a prolonged sub-NAV stall where the ambitious targets quietly lapse.","outlook":{"bull":"BTC recovers above the ~$104k cost basis, mNAV clears 1.01x, Moving Strike Warrants fire, and the accumulation engine restarts toward the 100k/210k targets; the income desk compounds the treasury and Japanese-retail demand re-rates the stock.","base":"BTC stabilizes below cost basis; mNAV hovers near 1x; warrant issuance is intermittent, holdings grow slowly, the options-income desk cushions carry, and the 100k target slips to 2027+.","bear":"BTC stays deeply below the $104k basis; mNAV stuck sub-1x means the warrant engine never fires; the treasury remains ~$700M+ underwater, growth stalls, and the stock languishes as a discounted BTC wrapper."},"sources":["https://coinmarketcap.com/academy/article/metaplanet-raises-dollar255m-for-bitcoin-with-new-mnav-warrants","https://news.bitcoin.com/metaplanet-buys-5075-bitcoin-in-q1-2026-total-holdings-hit-40177-btc/","https://www.mnav.com/dashboard/metaplanet","https://www.tftc.io/metaplanet-43000-btc-q2-2026-third-largest-corporate-treasury"]}','["https://coinmarketcap.com/academy/article/metaplanet-raises-dollar255m-for-bitcoin-with-new-mnav-warrants","https://news.bitcoin.com/metaplanet-buys-5075-bitcoin-in-q1-2026-total-holdings-hit-40177-btc/","https://www.mnav.com/dashboard/metaplanet","https://www.tftc.io/metaplanet-43000-btc-q2-2026-third-largest-corporate-treasury"]','2026-07-08 15:47:45');
INSERT INTO "market_entities" ("slug","name","ticker","type","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('twenty-one-capital','Twenty One Capital','XXI','treasury','at-risk','{"name":"Twenty One Capital","ticker":"XXI (formerly CEP — Cantor Equity Partners SPAC)","type":"treasury","crypto_asset":"BTC","crypto_held":"~43,514 BTC (~$3.3B); recently added 4,812 BTC with Tether for $458.7M. 2nd-largest public BTC holder.","avg_cost_basis":"Not precisely disclosed; large tranches acquired near market via the Tether/Bitfinex contribution and PIPE.","mnav":"Well below its 52-week high; market cap roughly in line with or below BTC NAV given the price collapse — little-to-no premium remains.","stock_price":"~$5.41 (Jul 6 2026), range $5.26-$5.58; 52-wk high $41.75, 52-wk low $4.81. Down ~87% from highs.","market_cap":"Depressed; near the $10 PIPE price at times, now roughly half that.","funding":"Backed by Tether balance sheet + Bitfinex, plus SPAC/PIPE equity (originally priced ~$10). Tether is now the controlling shareholder after buying out SoftBank''s ~26% stake (May 20 2026), removing SoftBank''s board reps. Strike (Mallers'' fintech) has secured a $2.1B credit facility that would fold into the combined entity. Funding is thus heavily related-party (Tether-directed).","leadership":"Jack Mallers (CEO, Strike founder) — strong consumer-Bitcoin brand. Proposed structure would add Raphael Zagury (Elektron CEO) as President for capital-markets/operating execution. Tether (Paolo Ardoino) is the controlling force behind strategy.","dilution_risk":"MODERATE-HIGH and governance-heavy. Tether''s control means dilution/strategy decisions are effectively related-party; the pending 3-way merger would issue stock to combine XXI, Strike and Elektron. Minority holders face concentration and related-party-governance risk more than classic ATM dilution.","strategy":"Native-BTC treasury vehicle funded off Tether''s balance sheet + equity; pivoting toward an integrated treasury + mining + fintech company via the proposed merger.","background":"Went public late-2025 via SPAC merger with Cantor Equity Partners; fell 25% on NYSE debut day.","recent_moves":"Apr 29 2026: Tether proposed a sequential 3-way merger — XXI merges with Strike, then the combined entity merges with Elektron Energy (~50 EH/s miner, ~5% of network, cash-flow-positive). Terms, timeline and governance still undisclosed as of latest reporting; deal NOT yet closed. May 2026: Tether bought SoftBank''s stake, tightening control.","analysis":"Twenty One was conceived as a ''native-BTC'' treasury — BTC-per-share compounding backed by Tether and Bitfinex rather than a repurposed operating company. The numbers show the thesis under strain: ~43,514 BTC (~$3.3B) but a stock down ~87% from its $41.75 high to ~$5.41, trading at or below NAV with the SPAC-era premium gone. The strategic response is the proposed three-way merger with Strike (a global Bitcoin-financial-services firm with a $2.1B credit facility) and Elektron (~50 EH/s of profitable mining) — an explicit attempt to bolt cash-flowing businesses onto the pure-mNAV wrapper so it isn''t solely dependent on a premium that has evaporated. The risks are execution and governance: terms/timeline are undisclosed, the deal isn''t closed, and Tether''s now-controlling stake (post-SoftBank buyout) makes the combination a related-party transaction where minority holders must trust Tether''s direction. Catalysts: merger close (adding mining + fintech cash flows and a clearer valuation), a BTC rally, and Strike/Elektron operating traction. Bear case: merger stalls or closes on terms unfavorable to minorities while the treasury stays underwater.","outlook":{"bull":"The 3-way merger closes on fair terms, creating the clear #2 BTC-only public company with treasury + ~50 EH/s mining + Strike fintech cash flows; the market re-rates the combined earnings power well above bare BTC NAV and Tether''s backing de-risks funding.","base":"Merger progresses slowly; XXI trades near BTC NAV as a Tether-backed treasury while investors wait for execution proof; upside tracks BTC with a governance discount.","bear":"Merger stalls or is priced against minorities; the pure treasury stays underwater and dependent on Tether; related-party governance and a persistent sub-NAV discount keep the stock near lows."},"sources":["https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2026/04/29/jack-mallers-twenty-one-capital-surges-after-majority-holder-tether-proposes-3-way-merger","https://tether.io/news/tether-investments-proposes-merger-plans-at-twenty-one-capital-to-accelerate-its-strategic-direction/","https://www.blockhead.co/2026/05/21/tether-buys-out-softbanks-stake-in-twenty-one-capital-tightening-control-of-bitcoin-treasury-firm/","https://www.theblock.co/crypto-company-stocks/359899/twenty-one-cep"]}','["https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2026/04/29/jack-mallers-twenty-one-capital-surges-after-majority-holder-tether-proposes-3-way-merger","https://tether.io/news/tether-investments-proposes-merger-plans-at-twenty-one-capital-to-accelerate-its-strategic-direction/","https://www.blockhead.co/2026/05/21/tether-buys-out-softbanks-stake-in-twenty-one-capital-tightening-control-of-bitcoin-treasury-firm/","https://www.theblock.co/crypto-company-stocks/359899/twenty-one-cep"]','2026-07-08 15:48:17');
INSERT INTO "market_entities" ("slug","name","ticker","type","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('semler-scientific','Semler Scientific (acquired by Strive)','SMLR / ASST','treasury','at-risk','{"name":"Semler Scientific","ticker":"SMLR (now consolidated into Strive, Nasdaq: ASST)","type":"treasury","crypto_asset":"BTC","crypto_held":"Held 5,021 BTC (Jul 2025, fair value ~$586M, cost ~$475.8M) and ~5,048 BTC at acquisition; now 0 on Semler''s own balance sheet — transferred to Strive","avg_cost_basis":"~$94k/BTC (aggregate ~$475.8M / ~5,021 BTC)","mnav":"n/a post-merger; investors now track Strive (ASST) combined vehicle","stock_price":"SMLR ticker effectively consolidated into ASST","market_cap":"absorbed into Strive","strategy":"Was a medical-device company (QuantaFlo) that adopted a MicroStrategy-style BTC treasury; funded via converts + Coinbase credit facility.","background":"Eric Semler (Chairman) drove the BTC pivot. Acquired by Vivek Ramaswamy-linked Strive, Inc. in an all-stock deal approved Jan 2026.","recent_moves":"Jan 2026: stockholders approved acquisition by Strive (ASST). Combined entity holds ~12,797.9 BTC (11th-largest corporate holder, ahead of Tesla and Trump Media). Strive retired ~92% (~$110M) of Semler''s legacy debt including a $20M Coinbase facility via preferred equity.","outlook":"BEAR/dissolved (as a standalone). Consolidated into Strive (ASST) in Jan 2026 — the exemplar of the small-cap-treasury roll-up endgame. BULL/BASE cases now belong to the combined Strive entity: a debt-free, ~20k-BTC accumulator. Standalone SMLR no longer exists as an independent thesis.","sources":["https://www.theblock.co/treasuries/smlr","https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/0001920406/000162828026001928/a991-strivexsmlrandbtcupda.htm","https://bitcointreasuries.net/public-companies/semler-scientific"],"analysis":"Semler Scientific is effectively dissolved as a standalone treasury — the January 2026 all-stock acquisition by Vivek Ramaswamy''s Strive (ASST) folded its ~5,021-5,048 BTC (cost ~$475.8M, ~$94k/coin) into Strive, creating the first case of a public BTC treasury acquiring another. This was the textbook small-cap-treasury endgame: rather than face standalone mNAV compression, a ~$120M debt load (incl. a $20M Coinbase facility), and a shrinking equity premium, Semler got rolled up into a larger, better-capitalized BTC vehicle. Strive retired ~92% (~$110M) of the legacy debt via SATA preferred, so the exposure now lives cleanly inside Strive. For investors, Semler''s lesson is that sub-scale BTC treasuries with leverage and no operating growth are consolidation targets. Exposure and analysis should now be tracked via Strive (ASST); Semler''s own balance sheet holds 0 BTC."}','["https://www.theblock.co/treasuries/smlr","https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/0001920406/000162828026001928/a991-strivexsmlrandbtcupda.htm","https://bitcointreasuries.net/public-companies/semler-scientific"]','2026-07-08 17:51:55');
INSERT INTO "market_entities" ("slug","name","ticker","type","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('sharplink','Sharplink, Inc. (SharpLink Gaming)','SBET','treasury','at-risk','{"name":"Sharplink, Inc. (formerly SharpLink Gaming)","ticker":"SBET","type":"treasury","crypto_asset":"ETH","crypto_held":"~886,725 ETH as of Jun 26 2026 (bought 10,000 ETH at ~$1,611 avg on Jun 24-26); ~639,241 native + ~224,183 LsETH-equivalent at Dec 2025. Among the largest public corporate ETH holders. Nearly all deployed in staking, generating >13,600 ETH of rewards since the Jun 2025 launch.","avg_cost_basis":"Blended in the low-to-mid $2,000s/ETH from 2025 buys; recent adds near ~$1,600 have lowered the average. Position sits underwater vs 2025 entries after ETH fell to ~$1,800.","mnav":"Trades around/below 1x ETH NAV (~$1.38B NAV vs depressed equity) — the DAT discount that has plagued sub-scale treasuries. Below 1x the accretive-issuance model stalls.","stock_price":"~$4.76 (down ~88% from 52-wk high $40.46; ATH $124.12 mid-2025). Joined Russell 2000/3000 indexes May 2026, adding passive demand.","market_cap":"depressed vs ~$1.38B ETH NAV","strategy":"Equity-only accumulation (no leverage) plus productive-treasury focus: staking + deploying ETH (e.g. $170M on Linea L2) for yield. $1.5B buyback program; raised $75M via registered direct offering late Jun 2026.","background":"Led by Joseph Chalom (ex-BlackRock digital-asset chief) and Ethereum co-founder Joseph Lubin (Consensys). Institutional ownership rose 6%->46% in 2025.","recent_moves":"Joined Russell 2000/3000 indexes effective Jun 29 2026 (passive-demand tailwind). Repurchased 2.13M shares at avg $4.69. Pushing ''productive ETH'' thesis — staking rewards ~18,800 ETH generated since Jun 2025.","outlook":"BULL: ETH recovers >$3k, mNAV premium returns, staking yield compounds a top-2 corporate ETH stack into a cash-flowing proxy. BASE: trades near NAV as a staking-ETH tracker; index inclusion provides a floor; ETH-per-share grinds up on yield. BEAR: ETH stays sub-$2k near cost basis, sub-NAV raises dilute holders, and the DAT discount persists — the small-cap-treasury endgame (roll-up or wind-down).","sources":["https://www.sharplink.com/","https://decrypt.co/354437/how-sharplink-plans-grow-2026-after-amassing-3-billion-ethereum","https://www.coindesk.com/business/2026/05/26/joe-lubin-backed-ethereum-treasury-firm-sharplink-to-join-the-russel-indexes","https://www.coingecko.com/learn/what-is-sharplink-gaming-sbet-ethereum-treasury","https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/SBET/"],"funding":"ATM equity + registered direct offerings — raised $75M via common-stock-and-warrants registered direct in the week ending Jun 28 2026 to fund more ETH. Staking yield (~3-4%) partly self-funds accumulation, distinguishing it from non-yielding BTC treasuries.","leadership":"CEO Joseph Chalom (ex-BlackRock digital-asset chief) and Chairman/Ethereum co-founder Joseph Lubin (Consensys founder). Deep institutional credibility; institutional ownership rose from ~6% to ~46% in 2025. Lubin''s Ethereum-native network is a strategic edge for staking/DeFi deployment.","dilution_risk":"HIGH at sub-NAV. Continued ATM/registered-direct raises below 1x mNAV dilute ETH-per-share. Warrants attached to recent raises add overhang. Staking yield is the key offset that keeps ETH-per-share growing organically.","analysis":"SharpLink is the second-largest corporate ETH treasury (~887k ETH, ~$1.6-1.8B) behind BitMine, run by an unusually credible team (ex-BlackRock''s Chalom + Ethereum''s Lubin). The thesis is a leveraged, staking-yield-bearing ETH proxy: nearly all coins are staked, so the treasury compounds ~3-4% in-kind even in a flat market — a structural advantage over BTC treasuries. But the stock is down ~88% from highs and trades around/below ETH NAV, breaking the accretive-issuance flywheel that requires a premium. The core risk is the 2026 ETH drawdown (to ~$1,800) sitting near cost basis plus dilution from below-NAV raises. Catalysts: Clarity Act / crypto legislation, Russell index inclusion driving passive flows, and any ETH price recovery that restores the mNAV premium."}','["https://www.sharplink.com/","https://decrypt.co/354437/how-sharplink-plans-grow-2026-after-amassing-3-billion-ethereum","https://www.coindesk.com/business/2026/05/26/joe-lubin-backed-ethereum-treasury-firm-sharplink-to-join-the-russel-indexes","https://www.coingecko.com/learn/what-is-sharplink-gaming-sbet-ethereum-treasury","https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/SBET/"]','2026-07-08 17:52:37');
INSERT INTO "market_entities" ("slug","name","ticker","type","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('bitmine-immersion','BitMine Immersion Technologies','BMNR','treasury','steady','{"name":"BitMine Immersion Technologies","ticker":"BMNR","type":"treasury","crypto_asset":"ETH","crypto_held":"~5,742,237 ETH as of Jul 5 2026 (~4.8% of all ETH supply) at ~$1,800/ETH ≈ $10.3B; plus 206 BTC, $180M Beast Industries stake, $71M Eightco stake, ~$527M cash/securities. Total crypto+cash ''moonshots'' ~$11.1B. By far the largest corporate ETH treasury. Added 42,197 ETH (~$73M) in the week to Jul 6 2026.","avg_cost_basis":"Blended in the low-$2,000s/ETH from aggressive 2025-2026 accumulation; recent adds near ~$1,800 pull the average down. Large position sits underwater after ETH''s fall to ~$1,800.","mnav":"Multi-billion equity value; premium to ~$10B ETH NAV compressed sharply from 2025 peaks as the DAT trade cooled. Marquee-investor backing supports a residual premium vs pure NAV.","stock_price":"~$19.51 (May 2026), down ~38% over 6 months; high-beta ETH proxy that overshoots ETH both directions.","market_cap":"multi-billion; backed by marquee investors","strategy":"Targets ''the alchemy of 5%'' — owning 5% of ETH supply. Funds via disciplined at-premium equity issuance. Runs MAVAN staking (projected ~$268M/yr staking reward at full scale). Positions as ''largest fresh-money ETH buyer in the world.''","background":"Chairman Thomas ''Tom'' Lee (Fundstrat). Backed by ARK/Cathie Wood, Founders Fund, Bill Miller III, Pantera, Kraken, DCG, Galaxy. Thesis leans on Clarity Act passage boosting ETH.","recent_moves":"Bought 42,197 ETH (~$74M) in week ending Jul 6 2026, continuing steady accumulation; Tom Lee calls it early ''crypto spring.''","outlook":"BULL: Clarity Act passes, ETH rallies >$3k, the largest corporate ETH stack + moonshots compound and the premium re-expands. BASE: trades as a high-beta ETH proxy near a modest premium; keeps DCA-ing via ATM. BEAR: ETH grinds lower, mNAV falls to 1x, premium-issuance engine stalls, and concentration in ETH + illiquid moonshots amplifies drawdowns.","sources":["https://www.coindesk.com/business/2026/07/06/bitmine-added-another-usd74-million-in-ether-as-tom-lee-bets-on-clarity-act-boost","https://www.prnewswire.com/apac/news-releases/bitmine-immersion-technologies-bmnr-announces-eth-holdings-reach-5-74-million-tokens-and-total-crypto-and-total-cash-holdings-of-11-1-billion-302818104.html","https://decrypt.co/372805/tom-lee-bitmine-73-million-ethereum-strategy-dumps-bitcoin","https://bitcointreasuries.net/"],"funding":"Massive ATM equity issuance funded the run from a few million to >$10B of ETH in under a year — the fastest treasury build on record. Backed by ARK/Cathie Wood, Founders Fund, Bill Miller III, Pantera, Kraken, DCG, Galaxy. Model depends on issuing at a premium; sub-NAV issuance would be dilutive.","leadership":"Chairman Thomas ''Tom'' Lee (Fundstrat co-founder), a high-profile bull whose commentary drives the equity''s narrative and premium. Thesis leans heavily on U.S. crypto legislation (Clarity Act) as an ETH catalyst. Concentration/key-man risk around Lee is high.","dilution_risk":"HIGH. The entire model is premium-priced ATM issuance to buy ETH; if mNAV falls to/below 1x, further raises destroy ETH-per-share. The ''moonshot'' equity stakes (Beast, Eightco) add non-ETH concentration and mark-to-market volatility.","analysis":"BitMine is the single largest corporate ETH holder (~5.74M ETH, ~$10B), assembled in under a year via relentless premium-priced ATM issuance under Tom Lee. It is the ETH counterpart to Strategy''s BTC playbook and the flagship of the ''ETH treasury'' trade, backed by a who''s-who of crypto/tradfi investors. The bull case is a legislative catalyst (Clarity Act) plus ETH staking/DeFi upside making it a supercharged ETH proxy; the bear case is that ~4.8% of ETH supply now sits near/below cost basis in a drawdown, the mNAV premium has compressed, and any sub-NAV issuance dilutes holders. It kept buying ($73M in early Jul 2026) even as BTC treasuries like Strategy were forced to sell — a signal of continued conviction and capital access. Watch ETH price vs cost basis, the mNAV premium, and legislative headlines."}','["https://www.coindesk.com/business/2026/07/06/bitmine-added-another-usd74-million-in-ether-as-tom-lee-bets-on-clarity-act-boost","https://www.prnewswire.com/apac/news-releases/bitmine-immersion-technologies-bmnr-announces-eth-holdings-reach-5-74-million-tokens-and-total-crypto-and-total-cash-holdings-of-11-1-billion-302818104.html","https://decrypt.co/372805/tom-lee-bitmine-73-million-ethereum-strategy-dumps-bitcoin","https://bitcointreasuries.net/"]','2026-07-08 17:53:09');
INSERT INTO "market_entities" ("slug","name","ticker","type","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('defi-development-corp','DeFi Development Corp (formerly Janover)','DFDV','treasury','at-risk','{"name":"DeFi Development Corp (formerly Janover)","ticker":"DFDV","type":"treasury","crypto_asset":"SOL","crypto_held":"~2,223,074 SOL as of Jun 2026 (~$160M at then-prices), 2nd-largest public corporate SOL holder (~0.354% of supply). Operates its own validators and stakes/deploys SOL across Solana DeFi (dfdvSOL LST, Jupiter, RateX, Hylo, Solstice).","avg_cost_basis":"Blended cost in the low-$100s/SOL from 2025 accumulation; position value swings with SOL. Key metric is SOL-Per-Share (SPS): ~0.0743-0.0793 SPS, growing at a ~24.6% annualized run-rate, with a stated goal of 1.0 SPS by Dec 2028.","mnav":"Trades at a discount/near NAV like most SOL treasuries; the SPS-growth story is the bull lever rather than a large mNAV premium.","stock_price":"Volatile small-cap, well off highs (~$15.21 Sep 2025 reference). Ran a Q4 2025 buyback (SPS-accretive when sub-NAV).","market_cap":"small-cap","strategy":"First US public company focused on accumulating/compounding SOL; runs its own Solana validators for staking yield. Raised $300M+ in 2025 via convertible debt + equity facilities. Dual-segment: Digital Asset Treasury + legacy real-estate mortgage platform. Expanded to UK (''Treasury Accelerator'').","background":"CEO Joseph Onorati. Rebranded from Janover Apr 2025; Boca Raton FL.","recent_moves":"Jan 2026 recap: ~2.22M SOL, new yield partnerships/DeFi integrations, UK revolving credit facility, first US crypto-treasury firm to enter UK market.","outlook":"BULL: SOL rallies, SPS compounds toward the 2028 target, validator+DeFi yield makes it a cash-flowing Solana proxy at a premium. BASE: tracks SOL near NAV; SPS grinds up ~20%+/yr on yield and buybacks. BEAR: SOL stays weak, sub-NAV raises dilute, and DeFi/validator operational risk bites — the sub-scale SOL-treasury discount persists.","sources":["https://defidevcorp.com/sol-to-10k","https://www.coingecko.com/en/treasuries/companies/defi-dev","https://www.theblock.co/treasuries/dfdv","https://www.stocktitan.net/news/DFDV/de-fi-development-corp-releases-january-2026-recap-highlighting-u765ahcle1y0.html"],"funding":"ATM/convertible capital markets issuance plus a revolving credit facility with UK affiliate DeFi Development Corp UK PLC. Validator fees + staking yield + discounted locked-SOL purchases fund accretive accumulation. Buybacks used when trading below NAV.","leadership":"CEO Joseph Onorati; board addition Hadley Stern (2026). Rebranded from Janover (Apr 2025), Boca Raton FL. Positioned as an operating Solana-ecosystem participant (validators, LST, DeFi), not just a passive holder.","dilution_risk":"MODERATE. Disciplined SPS-focused issuance and buybacks aim to grow SOL-per-share, but capital-markets raises below NAV still dilute. Validator/DeFi operating exposure adds smart-contract and slashing risk on top of SOL price risk.","analysis":"DFDV is the 2nd-largest public Solana treasury (~2.22M SOL) and the most ''operator-like'' of the SOL DATs — it runs validators, issues its own liquid-staking token (dfdvSOL), and deploys treasury across Solana DeFi, so it earns validator fees + staking yield on top of price exposure. Management runs the vehicle on a SOL-Per-Share (SPS) framework (~0.079, targeting 1.0 by 2028) and uses buybacks when sub-NAV to grow SPS accretively. The thesis is a compounding, yield-bearing Solana proxy with ecosystem optionality (UK expansion, tokenized equity). Risks: SOL sits below 2025 entry levels, small-cap dilution from capital raises, and added DeFi/validator operational risk. Catalysts: SOL price recovery, a potential US Solana ETF drawing attention to SOL DATs, and SPS-growth milestones."}','["https://defidevcorp.com/sol-to-10k","https://www.coingecko.com/en/treasuries/companies/defi-dev","https://www.theblock.co/treasuries/dfdv","https://www.stocktitan.net/news/DFDV/de-fi-development-corp-releases-january-2026-recap-highlighting-u765ahcle1y0.html"]','2026-07-08 17:53:38');
INSERT INTO "market_entities" ("slug","name","ticker","type","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('upexi','Upexi, Inc.','UPXI','treasury','at-risk','{"name":"Upexi, Inc.","ticker":"UPXI","type":"treasury","crypto_asset":"SOL","crypto_held":"~2,173,204 SOL (~$206M) as of mid-2026, 3rd-largest public corporate SOL holder (~0.347% of supply). Acquires locked SOL at a discount and stakes it for ~7-9% yield. Jan 5 2026 holdings were 2,174,583 SOL (up 3.2% vs Oct).","avg_cost_basis":"~$150/SOL avg (position acquired for ~$325.3M); currently ~$119M unrealized loss with SOL well below entry. The discounted-locked-SOL sourcing lowers effective cost vs spot.","mnav":"Deep discount to NAV — traded around $2.13 (early Jan 2026, ~$65.9M mkt cap) vs a far larger SOL NAV, one of the widest DAT discounts in the SOL cohort.","stock_price":"~$2.13 (early Jan 2026), down ~52% over 1 year; 52-wk high >$22 shortly after the Apr 2025 treasury pivot. CEO bought 200k shares Dec 2025; ran a 416,226-share buyback at ~$1.92 avg.","market_cap":"~$65.9M (deep discount to NAV)","strategy":"Buys locked SOL at a discount and stakes it for 7-9% yield, turning treasury into an income asset. Planning new higher-yield/risk-adjusted strategy for 2026. Buying back shares given sub-NAV valuation.","background":"CEO Allan Marshall. Consumer-products company that pivoted to a SOL treasury in Apr 2025.","recent_moves":"Holdings climbed to ~2.17M SOL; announced 2026 higher-yield treasury strategy; continuing buybacks amid depressed prices.","outlook":"BULL: SOL rallies above the ~$150 cost basis, the NAV discount narrows, and 7-9%+ staking yield compounds a large discounted stack. BASE: tracks SOL at a discount; yield and buybacks slowly grow SOL-per-share. BEAR: SOL stays depressed, the deep NAV discount and dilution persist, and the sub-$70M-cap vehicle becomes a consolidation target — the small-cap SOL-treasury endgame.","sources":["https://www.upexi.com/","https://www.theblock.co/post/384647/upexi-higher-yield-solana-treasury-strategy-2026-holdings-2-2-million-sol","https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2026/06/30/3319588/0/en/Upexi-Partners-with-Blueprint-to-Stake-Solana-Treasury-Assets.html","https://www.coingecko.com/en/treasuries/companies/upexi"],"funding":"ATM + private placements (e.g. ~$19.5M private placement priced Jun 2026); three value levers — intelligent capital issuance, staking, and discounted locked-token purchases. New 2026 ''risk-adjusted yield'' strategy aims to lift treasury yield without disrupting operations.","leadership":"CEO Allan Marshall (also a share buyer, signaling alignment). Consumer-products company that pivoted to a SOL treasury Apr 2025. Jun 30 2026 partnered with Blueprint (Hivemind Capital''s institutional staking affiliate) for institutional-grade validator staking.","dilution_risk":"HIGH. Deep sub-NAV means ATM/PIPE raises are dilutive to SOL-per-share; the ~$119M unrealized loss and thin ~$66M market cap leave little cushion. Staking yield + buybacks are the offsets, but the discount signals market skepticism.","analysis":"Upexi is the 3rd-largest public Solana treasury (~2.17M SOL) but the most distressed-looking of the cohort: the stock is down ~52%, trades at a deep discount to NAV, and the SOL position carries a ~$119M unrealized loss against a ~$150 cost basis. Its edge is sourcing — buying locked SOL at a discount and staking for 7-9% yield — plus a Jun 2026 institutional staking partnership with Blueprint and a new ''risk-adjusted yield'' strategy for 2026. Insider buying and a buyback signal management alignment, but the tiny ~$66M market cap and sub-NAV status make accretive issuance hard. The bull case is a SOL recovery plus yield compounding the discounted stack; the bear case is that a persistent NAV discount and dilution trap it as a sub-scale DAT candidate for roll-up. Catalysts: SOL price, a US Solana ETF, and evidence the new yield strategy lifts realized returns."}','["https://www.upexi.com/","https://www.theblock.co/post/384647/upexi-higher-yield-solana-treasury-strategy-2026-holdings-2-2-million-sol","https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2026/06/30/3319588/0/en/Upexi-Partners-with-Blueprint-to-Stake-Solana-Treasury-Assets.html","https://www.coingecko.com/en/treasuries/companies/upexi"]','2026-07-08 17:54:02');
INSERT INTO "market_entities" ("slug","name","ticker","type","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('nakamoto-kindlymd','Nakamoto (formerly KindlyMD)','NAKA','treasury','at-risk','{"name":"Nakamoto (formerly KindlyMD)","ticker":"NAKA","type":"treasury","crypto_asset":"BTC","crypto_held":"~4,467 BTC (mid-2026), down from a peak ~5,744 BTC (bought $679M at avg $118,204) — has been a net seller","avg_cost_basis":"~$118,204/BTC — deeply underwater vs 2026 spot","mnav":"Collapsed; EV ~$327M vs ~$345M BTC fair value (Q1 2026). Stock down ~99.5% from peak.","stock_price":"~$5.19 (post 1-for-40 reverse split, May 2026 insider-buy price); pre-split hit ~$0.30","market_cap":"tiny post reverse-split (shares cut from ~696.1M to ~17.4M)","strategy":"Pivoting from pure treasury to a ''Bitcoin operating company'' — rolled up Bailey''s BTC Inc (Bitcoin Magazine, The Bitcoin Conference) and UTXO Management ($107M all-stock, a related-party deal). Wound down legacy healthcare clinics (ended Jun 19 2026). $25M buyback authorized.","background":"Chairman/CEO David Bailey (also leads BTC Inc). Went public May 2025 via KindlyMD merger, raised $710M.","recent_moves":"Sold ~284 BTC ($20M) in Mar 2026 and ~600 BTC + derivatives to repay ~$45M debt; new $165M USDT loan term sheet cutting interest to 7.75%. 1-for-40 reverse split. Bailey bought 191,448 shares (~$993k) personally; owns ~18.25%.","outlook":"BEAR/at-risk. The forced-seller scenario made real: sub-NAV, high cost basis, selling BTC to fund operations and repay debt. Bailey''s pivot to media/asset-management cash flows and personal buying are conviction signals, but the treasury thesis has effectively broken.","sources":["https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2026/03/31/david-bailey-s-nakamoto-sells-roughly-5-of-its-bitcoin-holdings-offloading-284-btc","https://www.theblock.co/post/402086/david-bailey-nakamoto-bitcoin-treasury-1-for-40-reverse-split-shares-new-lows","https://finance.yahoo.com/news/encourage-exit-bitcoin-treasury-nakamotos-200147632.html"]}','["https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2026/03/31/david-bailey-s-nakamoto-sells-roughly-5-of-its-bitcoin-holdings-offloading-284-btc","https://www.theblock.co/post/402086/david-bailey-nakamoto-bitcoin-treasury-1-for-40-reverse-split-shares-new-lows"]','2026-07-08 15:33:16');
INSERT INTO "market_entities" ("slug","name","ticker","type","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('mara-holdings','MARA Holdings (formerly Marathon Digital)','MARA','miner','steady','{"name":"MARA Holdings (Marathon Digital)","ticker":"MARA","type":"miner","hashrate_ehs":"~66.4 EH/s energized as of Dec 31 2025 (~490,000 rigs); one of the largest public miners","monthly_production_btc":"~733/mo implied (8,799 BTC in full-year 2025, -7% YoY post-halving)","cost_to_mine_usd":"Below peers on power (~1.1 GW owned capacity at ~$0.04/kWh) but industry avg production cost hit ~$79,995/BTC in Q4 2025","hodl_vs_sell":"Also a major TREASURY: held 53,822 BTC (~$4.7B) at Dec 31 2025 (9,377 loaned, 5,938 pledged vs $350M credit). In 2026 REVISED policy to permit selling balance-sheet BTC (not just production) — a notable shift from long-term-hold stance.","ai_hpc_pivot":"Early-stage. Granbury TX ~300 MW immersion site integrating AI inference; EDF Exaion acquisition adds Tier-4 GDPR-compliant EU AI data centers. Low-cost power positions it as an AI-infra play, but pivot lags peers.","stock_price":"Down ~43% over 12 months (to mid-Jan 2026); forward P/E ~7.3x","background":"Chairman/CEO Fred Thiel. Largest US-listed BTC miner by hashrate; owns power assets.","outlook":"BASE/steady. Huge hashrate + owned cheap power + large BTC treasury give optionality, but Q4 2025 net loss $1.71B (from $1.5B BTC mark-down) and the new sell-BTC policy show stress. AI/HPC pivot is real but behind TeraWulf/IREN/Cipher.","sources":["https://ir.mara.com/sec-filings/all-sec-filings/content/0001507605-26-000007/mara-20251231.htm","https://www.theblock.co/post/391979/mara-opens-door-to-selling-stockpiled-bitcoin-in-new-policy-shift","https://seekingalpha.com/article/4829279-mara-holdings-the-bitcoin-miner-hiding-an-ai-empire"]}','["https://ir.mara.com/sec-filings/all-sec-filings/content/0001507605-26-000007/mara-20251231.htm","https://www.theblock.co/post/391979/mara-opens-door-to-selling-stockpiled-bitcoin-in-new-policy-shift"]','2026-07-08 15:33:34');
INSERT INTO "market_entities" ("slug","name","ticker","type","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('riot-platforms','Riot Platforms','RIOT','miner','steady','{"name":"Riot Platforms","ticker":"RIOT","type":"miner","hashrate_ehs":"~42.5 EH/s deployed at end of Q1 2026 (+26% YoY); avg operating ~36.4 EH/s. Fleet efficiency 20.2 J/TH.","monthly_production_btc":"~491/mo (1,473 BTC in Q1 2026, -4% YoY)","cost_to_mine_usd":"Competitive; large owned power at Rockdale (700 MW connected). Revenue $647.4M in 2025 (+71.8%).","hodl_vs_sell":"Turned net seller to fund AI buildout — sold 3,778 BTC in Q1 2026 (raising $289.5M) and ~$200M BTC in late 2025; sold ~1,080 BTC to fund a $96M/200-acre land deal. Analysts call it strategic liquidity, not distressed.","ai_hpc_pivot":"Major. Halted the 600 MW Phase II BTC expansion at Corsicana TX to redirect that capacity to AI/HPC. Total portfolio >1,100 acres and 1.7 GW — one of the largest US data-center clusters. AI/HPC deal base value ~$311M, up to ~$1B with extensions.","stock_price":"Not precisely captured; tracks BTC + AI-pivot sentiment","background":"CEO Jason Les. Texas-centric miner with deep power/infrastructure footprint.","outlook":"BASE/steady. Strong balance sheet and prime Texas power make the AI/HPC pivot credible; selling BTC to fund it is rational. Execution and hyperscaler contract conversion are the swing factors.","sources":["https://news.bitcoin.com/riot-platforms-sells-3778-bitcoin-in-q1-2026-raising-289-5-million-for-data-center-expansion/","https://www.riotplatforms.com/riot-platforms-launches-formal-evaluation-of-potential-ai-hpc-uses-for-remaining-600-mw-of-power-capacity-at-corsicana-facility/","https://www.theblock.co/post/336129/riot-platforms-bitcoin-mining-ai-data-encouraging-analysts-say"]}','["https://news.bitcoin.com/riot-platforms-sells-3778-bitcoin-in-q1-2026-raising-289-5-million-for-data-center-expansion/","https://www.riotplatforms.com/riot-platforms-launches-formal-evaluation-of-potential-ai-hpc-uses-for-remaining-600-mw-of-power-capacity-at-corsicana-facility/"]','2026-07-08 15:33:47');
INSERT INTO "market_entities" ("slug","name","ticker","type","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('cleanspark','CleanSpark, Inc.','CLSK','miner','steady','{"name":"CleanSpark, Inc.","ticker":"CLSK","type":"miner","hashrate_ehs":"~50 EH/s operational (avg operating ~42.6 EH/s, Jun 2026); 225,137 miners; peak fleet efficiency ~16.07 J/TH — among the most efficient fleets","monthly_production_btc":"~614-671/mo (658 Mar, 640 Apr, 671 May, 614 Jun 2026)","cost_to_mine_usd":"Low-cost green-powered producer; avg BTC sale price fell $74,807 (Apr) -> $69,056 (Jun) 2026 reflecting soft market","hodl_vs_sell":"Accumulator — grew holdings to ~13,924 BTC by Jun 2026 (a HODL-leaning miner-treasury)","ai_hpc_pivot":"In progress. Leveraging 1.8 GW contracted power (808 MW utilized) and green microgrid footprint for AI/HPC; in hyperscaler partnership talks but no mega-deal signed yet.","stock_price":"~$12.53 (early May 2026), ~53% below ~$19.21 avg analyst target; 32% short interest","background":"CEO Zach Bradford. Pure-play US green-energy BTC miner.","outlook":"BASE/steady. Efficient fleet + growing BTC stack + 1.8 GW power optionality, but Q2 earnings missed badly (-114.9%), 2026 EPS downgrades, capex-heavy AI transition, and high short interest. Needs a hyperscaler deal to re-rate like TeraWulf/Cipher.","sources":["https://blockspace.media/insight/cleanspark-bitcoin-production-holdings-june-2026/","https://www.stocktitan.net/news/CLSK/clean-spark-releases-june-2026-operational-yk1a6nx9uj7q.html","https://finance.yahoo.com/markets/crypto/articles/look-cleanspark-clsk-valuation-texas-211150296.html"]}','["https://blockspace.media/insight/cleanspark-bitcoin-production-holdings-june-2026/","https://www.stocktitan.net/news/CLSK/clean-spark-releases-june-2026-operational-yk1a6nx9uj7q.html"]','2026-07-08 15:34:03');
INSERT INTO "market_entities" ("slug","name","ticker","type","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('core-scientific','Core Scientific','CORZ','miner','steady','{"name":"Core Scientific","ticker":"CORZ","type":"miner","hashrate_ehs":"Reallocating hashrate to HPC; once the largest public miner by hashrate, now primarily a data-center/colocation operator","monthly_production_btc":"declining as capacity shifts to AI","cost_to_mine_usd":"n/a-focus shifted; colocation revenue now covers operating costs (243 MW billable)","hodl_vs_sell":"Not a treasury story — the AI/HPC infrastructure thesis dominates","ai_hpc_pivot":"THE defining AI-pivot case. Long-term CoreWeave HPC hosting contracts (~590 MW across six sites, ~$10.2B contracted revenue over 12-yr terms). CoreWeave''s ~$9B all-stock acquisition (0.1235 CRWV/share, ~$20.40/sh, 66% premium) COLLAPSED — shareholders voted NO on Oct 30 2025 (Two Seas Capital + ISS lobbied against unfavorable economics). Now independent; $3.3B capital raise fueling TX/OK expansion.","stock_price":"Unaffected merger price was ~$12.30 (Jun 25 2025); trades independently post-deal collapse","background":"CEO Adam Sullivan. Emerged from 2022 bankruptcy; pivoted hard to AI hosting.","outlook":"BASE/steady. Failed CoreWeave buyout means CORZ captures its own AI-hosting upside (shareholders bet independence was worth more), but it now carries execution and financing risk alone. Colocation covering opex is a milestone; hyperscaler demand is strong.","sources":["https://finance.yahoo.com/news/core-scientific-8217-merger-coreweave-144146009.html","https://www.coindesk.com/business/2025/02/26/core-scientific-stock-surges-after-usd1-2b-expansion-of-data-center-with-coreweave","https://stockanalysis.com/stocks/corz/"]}','["https://finance.yahoo.com/news/core-scientific-8217-merger-coreweave-144146009.html","https://www.coindesk.com/business/2025/02/26/core-scientific-stock-surges-after-usd1-2b-expansion-of-data-center-with-coreweave"]','2026-07-08 15:34:15');
INSERT INTO "market_entities" ("slug","name","ticker","type","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('terawulf','TeraWulf Inc.','WULF','miner','thriving','{"name":"TeraWulf Inc.","ticker":"WULF","type":"miner","hashrate_ehs":"Repurposing legacy BTC-mining footprint to HPC — mining now a minority of revenue","monthly_production_btc":"declining by design; digital-asset mining slid to $12.99M in Q1 2026 (<40% of revenue)","cost_to_mine_usd":"n/a-transitioning to contracted HPC cash flows","hodl_vs_sell":"Not a treasury play; the story is AI lease revenue","ai_hpc_pivot":"BEST-IN-CLASS pivot. >522 critical IT MW contracted, >$12.8B total contracted revenue. Deals: 20-yr Anthropic lease at Hawesville KY (~$19B contracted); $9.5B/25-yr Fluidstack JV at Abernathy TX with Google backing $1.3B of obligations; Core42. Sold majority of Abernathy JV to Fluidstack (monetizing ~$450M at a premium). Added Muskie Data Campus (E. Kentucky). Targeting 250-500 MW/yr delivery through decade-end; scaling toward 1 GW.","stock_price":"Up ~95% YTD as of Jul 6 2026 — top-performing large miner; HPC >50% of revenue","background":"CEO Paul Prager. Zero-carbon (nuclear/hydro) power heritage now anchoring AI leases.","outlook":"BULL/thriving. The clearest example of the miner->AI trade working: $12.8B+ contracted, blue-chip tenants (Anthropic, Google-backed Fluidstack), and stock up ~95%. Key risk: execution/energization delays, counterparty concentration, and $5.8B total debt.","sources":["https://247wallst.com/investing/2026/07/06/terawulf-stock-is-up-95-this-year-heres-why/","https://news.bitcoin.com/miners-beat-bitcoin-by-70-in-2026-as-terawulf-locks-12-8b-in-ai-contracts/","https://investors.terawulf.com/news-events/press-releases/detail/140/terawulf-reports-first-quarter-2026-results"]}','["https://247wallst.com/investing/2026/07/06/terawulf-stock-is-up-95-this-year-heres-why/","https://news.bitcoin.com/miners-beat-bitcoin-by-70-in-2026-as-terawulf-locks-12-8b-in-ai-contracts/"]','2026-07-08 15:34:32');
INSERT INTO "market_entities" ("slug","name","ticker","type","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('iren','IREN Limited (formerly Iris Energy)','IREN','miner','thriving','{"name":"IREN Limited (formerly Iris Energy)","ticker":"IREN","type":"miner","hashrate_ehs":"~36.0 EH/s operating / 38.0 EH/s installed (Mar 31 2026), and actively removing mining hardware to install GPUs","monthly_production_btc":"declining — BTC mining revenue fell 33.6% sequentially to $111.2M in Q3 FY26 (still the larger segment but shrinking)","cost_to_mine_usd":"n/a-shifting focus; large low-cost renewable power base","hodl_vs_sell":"Not a treasury story; sells production, reinvests in GPUs","ai_hpc_pivot":"Major. AI Cloud Services revenue surged to $33.6M (+94.2% QoQ) from $3.6M a year earlier. Signed a ~$9.7B Microsoft GPU services agreement. Management says AI cloud is a LARGER long-term opportunity than mining. 5.3 GW data-center portfolio across 8 sites (810 MW energized, 2.1 GW under development, 2.4 GW pipeline).","stock_price":"~$38.82 (Jul 4 2026); market cap ~$13.9B — among the most valuable miners","background":"Co-CEOs Daniel & Will Roberts. Australia-founded, renewable-powered; aggressive GPU/AI buildout funded by $3.69B converts + equity.","outlook":"BULL/thriving. AI-cloud revenue nearly doubling QoQ plus a $9.7B Microsoft deal validate the pivot; ~$13.9B market cap reflects an AI re-rating. Q3 had a $140.4M equipment impairment and $247.8M net loss (transition costs), so capex/execution risk is real but the trajectory is strong.","sources":["https://www.stocktitan.net/sec-filings/IREN/10-q-iren-ltd-quarterly-earnings-report-47751ec07c5b.html","https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/0001878848/000187884826000025/irenreportsq3fy26results.htm","https://ziven.io/company/iren"]}','["https://www.stocktitan.net/sec-filings/IREN/10-q-iren-ltd-quarterly-earnings-report-47751ec07c5b.html","https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/0001878848/000187884826000025/irenreportsq3fy26results.htm"]','2026-07-08 15:34:45');
INSERT INTO "market_entities" ("slug","name","ticker","type","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('cipher-mining','Cipher Digital (formerly Cipher Mining)','CIFR','miner','thriving','{"name":"Cipher Digital (formerly Cipher Mining)","ticker":"CIFR","type":"miner","hashrate_ehs":"Legacy BTC mining being reallocated to HPC; company rebranded Cipher Mining -> Cipher Digital (Feb 2026) to signal the shift","monthly_production_btc":"mining now secondary to contracted AI revenue","cost_to_mine_usd":"n/a-transitioning; projects ~76% blended EBITDA margins on HPC","hodl_vs_sell":"Not a treasury story","ai_hpc_pivot":"Major. ~$11.4B contracted revenue across ~3.4 GW planned TX capacity. Deals: ~$5.5B 15-yr AWS lease (300 MW delivered 2026, rent from Aug 2026); Fluidstack/Google 168 MW + 56 MW (~$3.8B total, Google backstops $1.73B and takes ~5.4% equity). $2.0B senior secured notes (6.125%, due 2031) via Black Pearl Compute.","stock_price":"~$24.45 (up 8% intraday, early 2026); analyst avg target ~$32.63, Morgan Stanley $42.50 Overweight","background":"CEO Tyler Page. Bitfury-affiliated; Texas power focus.","outlook":"BULL/thriving. Strong-Buy consensus, marquee tenants (AWS + Google-backed Fluidstack), ~$8.5B contracted HPC revenue. Central risk is site-energization timing — delays past Aug/Sep 2026 could trigger sharp sell-offs.","sources":["https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2026/02/24/cipher-digital-rebrands-as-it-pivots-from-bitcoin-mining-to-hpc-shares-slide","https://seekingalpha.com/article/4888798-cipher-digitals-9b-pivot-to-ai-infrastructure-is-still-undervalued","https://stockanalysis.com/stocks/cifr/"]}','["https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2026/02/24/cipher-digital-rebrands-as-it-pivots-from-bitcoin-mining-to-hpc-shares-slide","https://seekingalpha.com/article/4888798-cipher-digitals-9b-pivot-to-ai-infrastructure-is-still-undervalued"]','2026-07-08 15:35:02');
INSERT INTO "market_entities" ("slug","name","ticker","type","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('hut-8','Hut 8 Corp.','HUT','miner','thriving','{"name":"Hut 8 Corp.","ticker":"HUT","type":"miner","hashrate_ehs":"~1.8 EH/s operating / 11.22 EH/s installed (Mar 31 2026) — mining spun out; Hut 8 is now an AI-infrastructure + energy company","monthly_production_btc":"mining carved out into American Bitcoin (ABTC): ~817 BTC in Q1 2026 (record); cost to mine fell to ~$36,200/BTC from ~$46,900 in Q4 2025","cost_to_mine_usd":"ABTC ~$36,200/BTC (Q1 2026) — among the lowest","hodl_vs_sell":"Hut 8 holds ~10,278 BTC treasury (Dec 31 2025); ABTC grew holdings ~5,401 -> ~7,021 BTC in Q1 2026","ai_hpc_pivot":"Major. 15-yr triple-net lease worth $9.8B for Phase 1 of the Beacon Point AI campus (Nueces County TX, 352 MW IT; 1 GW total). 2.9 GW portfolio across 9 sites (0 MW energized, 333 MW under development, 2.6 GW pipeline). Carved legacy mining into American Bitcoin (ABTC).","stock_price":"~$124.89 (Jun 22 2026), up sharply from ~$48.11 in early Apr 2026 — record highs on the Beacon Point lease","background":"CEO Asher Genoot. Miami-based; restructured into distinct AI-infra (HUT) and mining (ABTC) entities.","outlook":"BULL/thriving. Stock hit ATHs on the $9.8B Beacon Point lease; clean separation of low-cost mining (ABTC) from AI-infra (HUT) unlocks value. Along with Cipher, accounts for >$19B of the >$70B cumulative miner AI/HPC deals. Execution on energization is the risk.","sources":["https://bitcoinfoundation.org/news/bitcoin/bitcoin-miner-hut-8-stock-hits-ath-on-9-8b-ai-data-center-lease/","https://ziven.io/company/hut","https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/0001755953/000119312526209054/abtc-ex99_1.htm"]}','["https://bitcoinfoundation.org/news/bitcoin/bitcoin-miner-hut-8-stock-hits-ath-on-9-8b-ai-data-center-lease/","https://ziven.io/company/hut"]','2026-07-08 15:35:17');
INSERT INTO "market_entities" ("slug","name","ticker","type","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('ibit','iShares Bitcoin Trust','IBIT','etf','steady','{"name":"iShares Bitcoin Trust","ticker":"IBIT","type":"etf","asset":"BTC","issuer":"BlackRock","aum_usd":"~$66B — by far the largest spot BTC ETF, ~5x FBTC. The de facto category benchmark.","recent_flows":"Mixed-to-negative in the 2026 pullback. Led outflows during the Jun 29-Jul 2 2026 bleed (-$300.4M on Jun 29, its heaviest session; -$219.4M on Jul 1). Notably did NOT participate in the Jul 2 rebound (+$221.7M category day led by FBTC/ARKB). Category YTD outflows ~$5.4B; analysts frame IBIT selling as tactical institutional profit-taking, not structural.","fee_pct":"0.12% (0.25% after a waiver period; among the cheapest)","launch":"January 2024","notes":"With FBTC, turning the BTC-ETF market into effectively a two-firm race. IBIT''s flows move the whole market and set institutional tone.","outlook":"STEADY (currently outflowing tactically). Structural dominance intact; recent outflows are cyclical de-risking tied to Fed/rate uncertainty. As the marginal-buyer benchmark, its flow direction is the single most-watched signal in the crypto-equity complex.","sources":["https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2026/06/10/blackrock-and-fidelity-are-quietly-turning-bitcoin-etfs-into-a-two-firm-market","https://farside.co.uk/btc/","https://www.techtimes.com/articles/319653/20260703/bitcoin-etf-outflow-streak-ends-27b-june-jobs-data-cools-rate-risk.htm"]}','["https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2026/06/10/blackrock-and-fidelity-are-quietly-turning-bitcoin-etfs-into-a-two-firm-market","https://farside.co.uk/btc/"]','2026-07-08 15:35:36');
INSERT INTO "market_entities" ("slug","name","ticker","type","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('fbtc','Fidelity Wise Origin Bitcoin Fund','FBTC','etf','inflowing','{"name":"Fidelity Wise Origin Bitcoin Fund","ticker":"FBTC","type":"etf","asset":"BTC","issuer":"Fidelity","aum_usd":"~$14B — second-largest spot BTC ETF","recent_flows":"Relatively resilient. LED the Jul 2 2026 category rebound with +$165.96M net inflows (vs IBIT sitting out), followed by ARKB +$91.84M. Did see -$51M on the weak Jul 1 session. Fidelity''s distribution muscle keeps it the clear #2.","fee_pct":"0.25%","launch":"January 2024","notes":"With IBIT, forms the two-firm duopoly capturing the bulk of spot-BTC-ETF assets and flows.","outlook":"INFLOWING/steady. Held up better than IBIT in the recent drawdown and led the rebound day; strong retail + advisor channel. A core beneficiary of any renewed BTC-ETF inflow cycle.","sources":["https://www.techtimes.com/articles/319653/20260703/bitcoin-etf-outflow-streak-ends-27b-june-jobs-data-cools-rate-risk.htm","https://farside.co.uk/btc/","https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2026/06/10/blackrock-and-fidelity-are-quietly-turning-bitcoin-etfs-into-a-two-firm-market"]}','["https://www.techtimes.com/articles/319653/20260703/bitcoin-etf-outflow-streak-ends-27b-june-jobs-data-cools-rate-risk.htm","https://farside.co.uk/btc/"]','2026-07-08 15:35:45');
INSERT INTO "market_entities" ("slug","name","ticker","type","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('arkb','ARK 21Shares Bitcoin ETF','ARKB','etf','steady','{"name":"ARK 21Shares Bitcoin ETF","ticker":"ARKB","type":"etf","asset":"BTC","issuer":"ARK Invest / 21Shares","aum_usd":"$3B+ — third-largest spot BTC ETF (surpassed GBTC by assets)","recent_flows":"Two-sided. +$91.84M on the Jul 2 2026 rebound and +$50.0M on Jun 29 (partial offset to IBIT''s bleed), but also trimmed during the drawdown as active managers cut risk. Net choppy in the 2026 outflow environment.","fee_pct":"0.21% (129 bps cheaper than GBTC)","launch":"January 2024","notes":"Cathie Wood / 21Shares product; overtook GBTC to become #3 by AUM, a symbol of the low-fee cohort winning share from legacy Grayscale.","outlook":"STEADY. Solidly the #3 spot-BTC ETF; low fee and active-manager following make its flows a useful risk-appetite tell. Rides the same cyclical inflow/outflow cycle as IBIT/FBTC.","sources":["https://www.techtimes.com/articles/319653/20260703/bitcoin-etf-outflow-streak-ends-27b-june-jobs-data-cools-rate-risk.htm","https://coinmarketcap.com/academy/article/ark-invest-21shares-bitcoin-spot-etf-surpasses-grayscales-gbtc-in-outflows-for-the-first-time","https://farside.co.uk/btc/"]}','["https://www.techtimes.com/articles/319653/20260703/bitcoin-etf-outflow-streak-ends-27b-june-jobs-data-cools-rate-risk.htm","https://farside.co.uk/btc/"]','2026-07-08 15:35:58');
INSERT INTO "market_entities" ("slug","name","ticker","type","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('gbtc','Grayscale Bitcoin Trust ETF','GBTC','etf','outflowing','{"name":"Grayscale Bitcoin Trust ETF","ticker":"GBTC","type":"etf","asset":"BTC","issuer":"Grayscale","aum_usd":"Fallen to 4th-largest spot BTC ETF (behind IBIT, FBTC, ARKB) after ~$25B in cumulative outflows since Jan 2024 conversion","recent_flows":"Structurally OUTFLOWING. -$62.8M on Jul 1 2026; lost ~$3.3B in 2026 through March alone. The fee-sensitive money leaving GBTC is a persistent drag on category net flows.","fee_pct":"1.50% — ~12.5x IBIT''s fee; the core reason for chronic outflows (costs ~$21,964 more than IBIT on a $100k position over 10 years)","launch":"Converted to ETF January 2024 (originally a 2013 trust)","notes":"Grayscale launched a low-fee Bitcoin Mini Trust (0.15%) to stem defections, but the legacy GBTC keeps bleeding to cheaper rivals.","outlook":"OUTFLOWING. The structural loser of the fee war — rational investors will not pay 1.5% for the same BTC exposure available at 0.12-0.25%. Its outflows are a semi-permanent headwind on aggregate BTC-ETF flow prints.","sources":["https://www.theblock.co/amp/post/286044/spot-bitcoin-etfs-return-to-net-daily-outflows-as-grayscale-gbtc-total-outflows-eclipse-15-billion-usd","https://farside.co.uk/btc/","https://koalagains.com/etfs/NYSEARCA/GBTC/competition"]}','["https://farside.co.uk/btc/","https://koalagains.com/etfs/NYSEARCA/GBTC/competition"]','2026-07-08 15:36:07');
INSERT INTO "market_entities" ("slug","name","ticker","type","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('etha','iShares Ethereum Trust ETF','ETHA','etf','outflowing','{"name":"iShares Ethereum Trust ETF","ticker":"ETHA","type":"etf","asset":"ETH","issuer":"BlackRock","aum_usd":"$6.5B+ — largest spot ETH ETF; ~47% of cumulative net ETH-ETF inflows (as of May 23 2026)","recent_flows":"Volatile 2026. Strong April/early-May inflows (May saw $1.5B single-month category inflow, ~22% of all cumulative) then a sharp reversal: >$3B pulled from spot ETH funds between mid-May and early June, ETHA among the large redemptions. Selling pace moderated in late June.","fee_pct":"~0.25% (core spot tier)","launch":"July 2024","notes":"BlackRock expanded its ETH lineup with ETHB (launched Mar 12 2026) and filed for an iShares Staked Ethereum Trust ETF — chasing the staking-yield theme now central to ETH ETFs.","outlook":"OUTFLOWING near-term (cyclical). Dominant ETH-ETF franchise, but caught in the mid-2026 risk-off. The key structural upside is staking approval — a staked ETHA would pull spot ETH off the market and add income, differentiating it from a pure price wrapper.","sources":["https://yellow.com/research/ethereum-etf-inflows-btc-underperformance-gap-2026","https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/0002099103/000143774926006395/ex_926825.htm","https://www.datawallet.com/ethereum-etf-tracker"]}','["https://yellow.com/research/ethereum-etf-inflows-btc-underperformance-gap-2026","https://www.datawallet.com/ethereum-etf-tracker"]','2026-07-08 15:36:21');
INSERT INTO "market_entities" ("slug","name","ticker","type","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('feth','Fidelity Ethereum Fund','FETH','etf','outflowing','{"name":"Fidelity Ethereum Fund","ticker":"FETH","type":"etf","asset":"ETH","issuer":"Fidelity","aum_usd":"Second-largest spot ETH ETF — ~21% of cumulative ETH-ETF net inflows","recent_flows":"Tracked ETHA''s arc: solid April/May inflows then sizeable redemptions in the mid-May to early-June >$3B ETH-ETF exodus; selling eased late June.","fee_pct":"~0.25%","launch":"July 2024","notes":"The clear #2 ETH ETF behind BlackRock; benefits from Fidelity''s advisor/retail distribution, mirroring the FBTC/IBIT dynamic on the ETH side.","outlook":"OUTFLOWING near-term (cyclical). Solid #2 franchise; upside hinges on the same staking-ETF catalyst reshaping ETH products and on ETH regaining momentum vs BTC.","sources":["https://yellow.com/research/ethereum-etf-inflows-btc-underperformance-gap-2026","https://etfdb.com/themes/ethereum-etfs/","https://www.datawallet.com/ethereum-etf-tracker"]}','["https://yellow.com/research/ethereum-etf-inflows-btc-underperformance-gap-2026","https://etfdb.com/themes/ethereum-etfs/"]','2026-07-08 15:36:29');
INSERT INTO "market_entities" ("slug","name","ticker","type","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('bsol','Bitwise Solana Staking ETF','BSOL','etf','inflowing','{"name":"Bitwise Solana Staking ETF","ticker":"BSOL","type":"etf","asset":"SOL","issuer":"Bitwise","aum_usd":"~$732M — the largest US Solana ETF (category crossed $1B total AUM by Jan 6 2026, ~1.4% of SOL market cap)","recent_flows":"Consistently INFLOWING. Launched late Oct 2025 with ~$36.55M first-day inflows and ~$56M day-one volume. $15.5M on Apr 16 2026 (largest single day in a month); 2026 SOL-ETF inflows crossed $222M by mid-April. Solana Foundation reported $115.3M net US spot SOL-ETF inflows in May 2026 with ZERO outflow days. Part of a mid-2026 rotation: as BTC/ETH ETFs bled in May, SOL+XRP ETFs absorbed ~$226M combined.","fee_pct":"0.20% (waived for 3 months or until $1B AUM)","launch":"Late October 2025","notes":"Stakes ~100% of holdings targeting ~7%+ rewards — the staking-yield ETF thesis in action. Competes with Grayscale GSOL (0.35% fee, ~$167M AUM, distributes ~77% of rewards) and VanEck VSOL. First formal annualized-yield reports due Q2 2026.","outlook":"INFLOWING/thriving. The standout new-category winner: staking yield (~6-7%) gives SOL ETFs an income case BTC ETFs structurally lack, driving rotation inflows. Grayscale projects up to $5B future inflows. Small base amplifies both upside and volatility.","sources":["https://cryptobriefing.com/solana-etfs-exceed-1b-assets-bitwises-bsol-leads-681m/","https://coincentral.com/solana-etfs-cross-1b-in-aum-driven-by-bitwise-bsols-strong-growth/","https://coinpaper.com/12026/us-solana-et-fs-attract-155-million-as-grayscale-executive-predicts-5-billion-inflows"]}','["https://cryptobriefing.com/solana-etfs-exceed-1b-assets-bitwises-bsol-leads-681m/","https://coincentral.com/solana-etfs-cross-1b-in-aum-driven-by-bitwise-bsols-strong-growth/"]','2026-07-08 15:36:44');
INSERT INTO "market_entities" ("slug","name","ticker","type","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('strive-asst','Strive, Inc.','ASST','treasury','at-risk','{"name":"Strive, Inc.","ticker":"ASST","type":"treasury","crypto_asset":"BTC","crypto_held":"~12,797.9 BTC as of Jan 16 2026 (post Semler acquisition) — 11th-largest corporate BTC holder, ahead of Tesla and Trump Media","avg_cost_basis":"blended from Strive''s own buys + Semler''s ~$94k basis; underwater vs 2026 spot","mnav":"Small-cap treasury; trades in the sub-1x-to-modest-premium range typical of the cohort in 2026","stock_price":"n/a precise; consolidated SMLR exposure now lives here","market_cap":"small/mid-cap","strategy":"Vivek Ramaswamy-linked asset manager that adopted a BTC treasury strategy and rolls up smaller treasuries. Used a preferred-equity structure to retire ~92% (~$110M) of Semler''s legacy debt incl. a $20M Coinbase facility.","background":"Founded by Vivek Ramaswamy (anti-ESG asset manager); pivoted into a BTC accumulation + roll-up vehicle.","recent_moves":"Jan 2026: closed all-stock acquisition of Semler Scientific, consolidating ~5,048 BTC and lifting combined holdings to ~12,797.9 BTC.","outlook":"BEAR/at-risk. A consolidator in a shrinking-premium environment — acquiring distressed small-cap treasuries can add scale, but the same mNAV-compression / forced-seller risk applies to the combined entity if BTC stays below the blended cost basis and equity trades near/below NAV.","sources":["https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/0001920406/000162828026001928/a991-strivexsmlrandbtcupda.htm","https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/0001920406/000095010326000616/dp240082_ex9901.htm","https://www.theblock.co/treasuries/smlr"]}','["https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/0001920406/000162828026001928/a991-strivexsmlrandbtcupda.htm","https://www.theblock.co/treasuries/smlr"]','2026-07-08 15:37:04');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('usdt','Tether','USDT','{"issuer":"Tether Operations Limited (Tether Holdings), incorporated in British Virgin Islands; US-facing USAT issued via Anchorage/Bo Hines-led entity from 2025","founders":"Brock Pierce, Reeve Collins, Craig Sellars (2014, originally ''Realcoin''); current CEO Paolo Ardoino","issuer_background":"Closely affiliated with Bitfinex (shared management/ownership). Grew into the largest stablecoin by supply. Historically opaque; became one of the most profitable companies per employee, reporting billions in annual profit from reserve yield.","raised":"No traditional VC raise; self-funded from operations. Reported >$13B net profit in 2024 on reserve income.","type":"fiat-backed","backing":"Reserves dominated by US Treasury bills (direct + via repo/MMFs), plus cash, secured loans, Bitcoin, and gold. ~$182B supply. Quarterly attestations show majority in T-bills; a minority in non-cash assets (BTC, gold, secured loans) draws scrutiny.","daily_activity":"Highest on-chain volume of any stablecoin; frequently reported daily transfer volume in the tens of billions USD across Tron and Ethereum. Tron and Ethereum host the bulk of supply; millions of active addresses. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/tether, defillama.com/stablecoins)","audits":"Attestations (not full GAAP audits) by BDO Italia, published quarterly. Long-criticized for never completing a full independent audit.","regulatory":"BVI-domiciled; historically avoided US/EU regulation. Did NOT seek EU MiCA authorization (delisted from some EU venues). Launched separate US-compliant USAT under the 2025 GENIUS Act framework rather than bringing USDT itself onshore. Paid CFTC/NYAG settlements (2021) over reserve disclosures.","transparency":"Real-time reserve breakdown page plus quarterly BDO attestations; still no full audit. Transparency improved but remains below USDC.","yield":"No yield passed to holders; Tether keeps 100% of reserve income.","comparison":"vs USDC: USDT dominates emerging-market/offshore usage, Tron rails, and exchange liquidity; weaker on regulatory standing, audit quality, and reserve purity. Edge = deepest liquidity and network effects; weakness = opacity and regulatory avoidance.","future":"Likely retains dominance in offshore/EM markets via network effects and Tron rails, while ceding US regulated market share to USDC and its own USAT. Risk: reserve-quality scrutiny, EU/MiCA exclusion, and dependence on a favorable US stance toward offshore issuers.","risks":"Reserve opacity, non-cash assets (BTC/gold/secured loans), regulatory exclusion in EU, concentration on Tron, historical peg wobbles during crises.","notes":"Systemically important: the single largest crypto asset by daily settlement volume. USAT is the separate US onshore product.","sources":["https://tether.to","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/tether","https://defillama.com/stablecoins","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tether_(cryptocurrency)"]}','["https://tether.to","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/tether","https://defillama.com/stablecoins","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tether_(cryptocurrency)"]','2026-07-08 19:13:50');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('usdc','USD Coin','USDC','{"issuer":"Circle Internet Financial (Circle Internet Group, Inc.), USA; originally via Centre Consortium with Coinbase","founders":"Jeremy Allaire and Sean Neville (Circle, 2013); USDC launched 2018","issuer_background":"Circle is a US regulated fintech. Went public on NYSE in June 2025 (ticker CRCL) in a landmark stablecoin IPO. Coinbase retains a revenue-share relationship on USDC reserves.","raised":"Raised >$1B in private funding over its history (incl. rounds backed by Goldman Sachs, Fidelity, BlackRock); subsequently IPO''d on NYSE in 2025.","type":"fiat-backed","backing":"Cash and short-dated US Treasuries, largely held in the Circle Reserve Fund (a BlackRock-managed government MMF) plus cash at regulated US banks. ~$73B supply.","daily_activity":"Second-highest stablecoin transfer volume; heavy usage on Ethereum, Base, Solana. Multi-billion daily on-chain volume; leading stablecoin in DeFi and institutional flows. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/usd-coin, defillama.com/stablecoins)","audits":"Monthly reserve attestations by Deloitte (formerly Grant Thornton); Circle is an SEC-reporting public company subject to full financial audits.","regulatory":"Most regulation-forward major issuer. First global stablecoin to secure EU MiCA authorization (EMT) via Circle''s French EMI license (2024). Positioned as flagship compliant issuer under the US GENIUS Act (2025). Holds numerous US state money-transmitter licenses.","transparency":"Industry-leading: weekly reserve reporting, monthly attestations, public-company disclosures, BlackRock-managed reserve fund with published holdings.","yield":"No direct yield to holders; Circle shares reserve income with Coinbase and distribution partners.","comparison":"vs USDT: USDC wins on regulatory standing, audit/transparency, and reserve purity; trails on raw liquidity, offshore/EM reach, and Tron presence. Edge = the compliant institutional/US choice.","future":"Strong outlook as the regulated-market leader post-GENIUS Act and MiCA; likely primary beneficiary of US bank and fintech stablecoin adoption. Risk: margin compression from reserve-income sharing, rate-cut sensitivity, and competition from bank-issued and Tether''s USAT.","risks":"Reliance on US banking rails (SVB exposure caused a brief March 2023 depeg to ~$0.88), interest-rate dependence for revenue, Coinbase revenue-share drag.","notes":"Considered the benchmark compliant USD stablecoin; SVB depeg episode is the key historical stress event.","sources":["https://www.circle.com","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/usd-coin","https://defillama.com/stablecoins","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/USD_Coin"]}','["https://www.circle.com","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/usd-coin","https://defillama.com/stablecoins","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/USD_Coin"]','2026-07-08 19:14:07');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('usds','Sky Dollar','USDS','{"issuer":"Sky Protocol (formerly MakerDAO), a decentralized protocol governed by SKY (formerly MKR) token holders","founders":"Rune Christensen (founder of MakerDAO/Sky)","issuer_background":"MakerDAO rebranded to Sky in 2024 under the ''Endgame'' plan; DAI is being upgraded/migrated to USDS. Longest-running decentralized stablecoin protocol (since 2017).","raised":"MakerDAO raised early rounds from a16z, Polychain, Dragonfly (2017-2019) via MKR token sales; now protocol-owned and DAO-governed.","type":"crypto-overcollateralized","backing":"Overcollateralized by crypto (ETH, staked ETH, wrapped BTC) plus a large allocation to Real-World Assets (US Treasuries via off-chain vaults) and USDC via the Peg Stability Module. ~$7.6B supply. RWA and USDC backing means it is partly centralized in practice.","daily_activity":"Active across Ethereum, Solana, Base, Arbitrum. Meaningful DeFi collateral usage; sUSDS (savings) drives demand. Multi-hundred-million daily on-chain volume. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/usds, defillama.com)","audits":"Smart contracts audited repeatedly; RWA vaults and reserves reported via on-chain dashboards and third-party attestations of off-chain assets.","regulatory":"Decentralized/DAO structure; no single licensed issuer. RWA exposure introduces off-chain counterparty and compliance considerations. Not a MiCA EMT.","transparency":"On-chain collateral fully visible; RWA/off-chain portions rely on periodic reporting. Strong on-chain transparency, moderate off-chain.","yield":"Yes — Sky Savings Rate (sUSDS) pays holders a governance-set yield funded by protocol revenue (RWA + stability fees).","comparison":"vs USDC/USDT: decentralized and yield-bearing via savings rate; niche = DeFi-native users wanting non-custodial USD with yield. Weakness: heavy USDC/RWA backing dilutes decentralization; governance complexity; smaller liquidity.","future":"Positioned as the flagship of Sky''s Endgame with SubDAO ''Stars'' and yield distribution; likely grows with DeFi and the savings rate. Risk: dependence on USDC/RWA (centralization + de-peg contagion), governance risk, and regulatory pressure on yield-bearing tokens.","risks":"USDC contagion via PSM, RWA counterparty risk, governance capture, smart-contract risk, rebrand/migration friction.","notes":"USDS is the successor to DAI; both coexist during migration. Backed by the same collateral system.","sources":["https://sky.money","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/usds","https://defillama.com/protocol/makerdao","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MakerDAO"]}','["https://sky.money","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/usds","https://defillama.com/protocol/makerdao","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MakerDAO"]','2026-07-08 19:14:28');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('dai','Dai','DAI','{"issuer":"Sky Protocol (formerly MakerDAO), decentralized DAO governed by SKY/MKR holders","founders":"Rune Christensen (MakerDAO, 2015; DAI launched 2017 as ''Single-Collateral Dai'', Multi-Collateral Dai 2019)","issuer_background":"The original and most battle-tested decentralized stablecoin. Now part of Sky ecosystem; DAI is being upgraded to USDS but remains widely used and integrated across DeFi.","raised":"Funded via MKR token sales to a16z, Polychain, Dragonfly and others; protocol-owned treasury.","type":"crypto-overcollateralized","backing":"Overcollateralized vaults (ETH, stETH, WBTC) plus large USDC (PSM) and RWA (US Treasury) backing. ~$4.9B supply. In practice significantly backed by USDC and RWAs.","daily_activity":"One of the most integrated stablecoins in DeFi (Aave, Curve, Uniswap). Broad multi-chain presence; hundreds of millions in daily on-chain volume. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/dai, defillama.com)","audits":"Extensively audited smart contracts over many years; on-chain collateral transparent, RWA portions via off-chain reporting.","regulatory":"Decentralized; no licensed issuer. RWA and USDC dependence create off-chain compliance touchpoints. Not a MiCA EMT.","transparency":"Fully on-chain collateral visibility; RWA disclosures periodic. Highly transparent on-chain.","yield":"Yes — DAI Savings Rate (DSR) / sDAI pays holders yield from protocol revenue.","comparison":"vs USDC/USDT: the decentralized DeFi standard, censorship-resistant at the token layer, yield via DSR. Niche = DeFi collateral and non-custodial USD. Weakness: USDC/RWA backing centralizes it; being superseded by USDS.","future":"Long-term role converges into USDS under Sky Endgame; DAI persists for DeFi compatibility. Risk: USDC contagion, migration dilution, governance and regulatory pressure on yield.","risks":"USDC PSM contagion (March 2023 SVB depeg briefly dragged DAI), RWA counterparty risk, governance risk, smart-contract risk.","notes":"Historically THE decentralized stablecoin; now one product within the Sky ecosystem alongside USDS.","sources":["https://sky.money","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/dai","https://defillama.com/protocol/makerdao","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dai_(cryptocurrency)"]}','["https://sky.money","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/dai","https://defillama.com/protocol/makerdao","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dai_(cryptocurrency)"]','2026-07-08 19:14:43');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('usde','Ethena USDe','USDe','{"issuer":"Ethena Labs (protocol governed by ENA token holders); regulated entity Ethena GmbH for some products","founders":"Guy Young (founder/CEO of Ethena Labs, 2023)","issuer_background":"Fast-growing ''synthetic dollar'' protocol launched 2024. Rapidly became one of the largest stablecoins by supply. Backed by prominent investors.","raised":"Raised from investors including Dragonfly, Arthur Hayes/Maelstrom, Binance Labs, Franklin Templeton, and others across seed/strategic rounds (>$100M reported incl. token sales).","type":"crypto-overcollateralized (delta-neutral synthetic dollar / yield-bearing)","backing":"Not fiat-backed. Backed by crypto collateral (staked ETH, BTC, and increasingly liquid stables/RWA) hedged with short perpetual-futures positions to stay delta-neutral. ~$4.4B supply. Peg maintained via the hedge, not a 1:1 cash reserve.","daily_activity":"High DeFi activity; sUSDe staking drives demand. Active on Ethereum, Solana, BSC, Base. Hundreds of millions in daily on-chain volume. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/ethena-usde, defillama.com)","audits":"Smart-contract audits; reserve/position attestations of collateral and hedges published; custody via off-exchange settlement providers (Copper, Ceffu, Fireblocks).","regulatory":"Novel structure draws regulatory attention; not a fiat EMT. Faced MiCA/EU scrutiny (Ethena GmbH''s German BaFin authorization was challenged, restructuring EU operations). GENIUS Act treats yield-bearing synthetic dollars differently from payment stablecoins.","transparency":"Publishes reserve and hedge dashboards showing collateral and open positions; dependent on CEX/custodian solvency disclosures.","yield":"Yes — sUSDe pays yield from perpetual funding rates plus staking rewards. Yield is variable and can turn negative in bearish funding regimes.","comparison":"vs USDC/USDT: offers native high yield without holding fiat; niche = crypto-native yield seekers. Weakness/edge risk: relies on positive funding rates and CEX counterparties — a structurally different and riskier peg mechanism than cash-backed coins.","future":"Growth tied to crypto funding rates and perp market depth; strong in bull markets. Risk: negative funding, exchange/custodian counterparty failure, liquidity crunch during deleveraging, and regulatory reclassification. Peg is robust in normal conditions but untested at extreme scale in a prolonged bear market.","risks":"Funding-rate reversal, CEX counterparty/custody risk, collateral de-peg, forced unwinds, regulatory action against synthetic dollars.","notes":"Often described as a ''synthetic dollar'' rather than a classic stablecoin; USDtb is Ethena''s separate T-bill/BUIDL-backed fiat-style coin.","sources":["https://www.ethena.fi","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/ethena-usde","https://defillama.com/protocol/ethena","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethena_(cryptocurrency)"]}','["https://www.ethena.fi","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/ethena-usde","https://defillama.com/protocol/ethena","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethena_(cryptocurrency)"]','2026-07-08 19:15:11');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('usd1','World Liberty Financial USD','USD1','{"issuer":"World Liberty Financial (WLFI), a crypto venture associated with the Trump family/affiliates","founders":"World Liberty Financial team; publicly associated with the Trump family and co-founders including Zachary Folkman and Chase Herro","issuer_background":"WLFI launched USD1 in 2025. Rapidly reached multi-billion supply, boosted by high-profile backing and a reported large institutional/sovereign-linked deal (MGX/Binance transaction).","raised":"WLFI raised substantial sums via its governance token sale in 2024-2025; USD1 backed by reserve assets rather than a separate raise.","type":"fiat-backed","backing":"Reserves stated as US Treasuries, cash, and cash equivalents, with custody reported via BitGo. ~$4.5B supply. Reserve custody/attestation practices are newer and less established than USDC.","daily_activity":"Active on Ethereum, BSC, Solana, Tron; adoption driven by Binance ecosystem listings. Meaningful but concentrated on-chain volume. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/usd1-wlfi, defillama.com)","audits":"Reserve attestations reported; track record is short and disclosure maturity is lower than incumbents.","regulatory":"US political associations create unique scrutiny and conflict-of-interest debate around the GENIUS Act. Custody via US-regulated BitGo; not a MiCA EMT.","transparency":"Publishes reserve claims; independent, long-run attestation history still limited given recent launch.","yield":"No yield passed to holders.","comparison":"vs USDC/USDT: fast growth via political/Binance network effects; niche = ecosystem and politically-aligned adoption. Weakness: short track record, governance/conflict concerns, reserve-disclosure immaturity, concentration risk.","future":"Growth depends heavily on continued high-profile backing and exchange support; politically sensitive. Risk: reputational/political shifts, regulatory conflict-of-interest scrutiny, and whether reserves prove as robust as claimed over time.","risks":"Political/reputational risk, concentration, short operating history, reserve transparency, dependence on Binance-linked liquidity.","notes":"One of the fastest-scaling new stablecoins of 2025; notable for its political associations.","sources":["https://worldlibertyfinancial.com","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/usd1-wlfi","https://defillama.com/stablecoins","https://www.reuters.com"]}','["https://worldlibertyfinancial.com","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/usd1-wlfi","https://defillama.com/stablecoins","https://www.reuters.com"]','2026-07-08 19:15:25');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('usyc','Circle USYC','USYC','{"issuer":"Hashnote (acquired by Circle in 2025); USYC = US Yield Coin","founders":"Hashnote founded by Leo Mizuhara (ex-Cumberland/DRW); acquired by Circle","issuer_background":"USYC is a tokenized money-market fund. Circle acquired Hashnote to add a yield-bearing collateral product complementary to USDC. DRW/Cumberland heritage.","raised":"Hashnote backed by Cumberland Labs/DRW; acquired by Circle (public company) in 2025.","type":"RWA-backed (tokenized money-market fund / yield-bearing)","backing":"Shares in a tokenized fund holding US Treasuries and reverse-repo. ~$3.1B. Price is >$1 and accrues (NAV-based), so it is a tokenized T-bill fund token rather than a $1-pegged payment coin.","daily_activity":"Institutional collateral usage; on Ethereum and BSC. Used as yield collateral and increasingly integrated with Circle/DeFi. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/hashnote-usyc, defillama.com)","audits":"Fund-level audits/attestations of Treasury holdings; NAV reporting.","regulatory":"Offered to qualified/eligible investors; structured as a regulated fund product, not a retail payment stablecoin. Custody and fund compliance apply.","transparency":"NAV and holdings reported at fund level; benefits from Circle''s disclosure practices post-acquisition.","yield":"Yes — accrues Treasury yield via rising NAV (~T-bill rate). It is inherently yield-bearing.","comparison":"vs USDC/USDT: not a payment coin — it is tokenized cash yield/collateral. Niche = institutions wanting on-chain T-bill exposure and yield-bearing collateral. Weakness: not $1-pegged, restricted eligibility, low retail utility.","future":"Strong institutional collateral role as Circle integrates it with USDC (mint/redeem, margin). Risk: rate sensitivity (yield falls with cuts), regulatory treatment of tokenized funds, and limited retail reach.","risks":"Interest-rate risk, eligibility restrictions, redemption/liquidity timing, fund counterparty and custody risk.","notes":"Best understood as tokenized money-market fund shares; price ~1.13 reflects accrued yield, not a broken peg.","sources":["https://usyc.com","https://www.circle.com","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/hashnote-usyc","https://defillama.com"]}','["https://usyc.com","https://www.circle.com","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/hashnote-usyc","https://defillama.com"]','2026-07-08 19:15:46');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('buidl','BlackRock USD Institutional Digital Liquidity Fund','BUIDL','{"issuer":"BlackRock (fund) with Securitize as tokenization/transfer agent","founders":"BlackRock (world''s largest asset manager); tokenized via Securitize (co-founded by Carlos Domingo)","issuer_background":"Launched March 2024 on Ethereum; BlackRock''s flagship tokenized fund. Quickly became the largest tokenized US Treasury fund, validating institutional RWA tokenization.","raised":"N/A (a BlackRock fund product). Securitize has raised VC (incl. from BlackRock) as the tokenization platform.","type":"RWA-backed (tokenized money-market/Treasury fund, yield-bearing)","backing":"US Treasury bills, repurchase agreements, and cash held in a registered fund. ~$3.05B. Token maintains $1 par with yield distributed as new tokens (dividend), rather than accruing NAV.","daily_activity":"Institutional holders; multi-chain (Ethereum, Aptos, Solana, Avalanche, etc.). Used as collateral (e.g., by Ethena, derivatives venues). Lower transfer frequency, high value per transaction. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/blackrock-usd..., defillama.com)","audits":"Registered-fund audits and NAV reporting; Securitize provides transfer-agent controls.","regulatory":"Sold to qualified/eligible institutional investors under US securities-law exemptions (Reg D). It is a security, not a retail payment stablecoin.","transparency":"Fund-grade reporting via BlackRock/Securitize; holdings and NAV disclosed.","yield":"Yes — pays daily-accrued yield (~T-bill rate) distributed monthly as additional tokens.","comparison":"vs USDC/USDT: not a payment coin — institutional yield-bearing collateral. Niche = tokenized Treasuries for institutions and stablecoin protocols. Weakness: restricted to eligible investors, minimal retail/payment utility.","future":"Bellwether for RWA tokenization; likely grows as institutions adopt on-chain Treasuries and use BUIDL as collateral. Risk: rate sensitivity, securities-law limits on distribution, and competition from other tokenized funds (Ondo, Franklin, Circle USYC).","risks":"Interest-rate risk, investor-eligibility limits, custody/transfer-agent dependence, redemption timing.","notes":"The reference tokenized Treasury fund; frequently used as backing/collateral by other stablecoin projects (e.g., Ethena USDtb).","sources":["https://securitize.io","https://www.blackrock.com","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/blackrock-usd-institutional-digital-liquidity-fund","https://defillama.com"]}','["https://securitize.io","https://www.blackrock.com","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/blackrock-usd-institutional-digital-liquidity-fund","https://defillama.com"]','2026-07-08 19:16:01');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('usdg','Global Dollar','USDG','{"issuer":"Paxos (issued via Paxos Digital Singapore) under the Global Dollar Network consortium","founders":"Paxos co-founded by Charles Cascarilla and Rich Teo; Global Dollar Network is a consortium (Paxos, Robinhood, Kraken, Galaxy, Anchorage, and others)","issuer_background":"USDG launched late 2024 as the token of the Global Dollar Network — a consortium designed to SHARE reserve yield with distribution partners, unlike USDC/USDT which retain it.","raised":"Paxos is well-funded (raised >$500M historically from PayPal Ventures, Founders Fund, Coinbase Ventures, etc.). USDG backed by reserves.","type":"fiat-backed","backing":"Cash and cash-equivalent/short-term US-dollar reserves held by Paxos. ~$3B supply. Paxos has a strong reserve/attestation reputation from BUSD and USDP.","daily_activity":"Distributed across X Layer, Solana, Ethereum, Robinhood Chain, Ink, Hyperliquid. Adoption driven by consortium exchanges. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/global-dollar, defillama.com)","audits":"Monthly reserve attestations by an independent accounting firm; Paxos has a long clean attestation history.","regulatory":"Issued out of Singapore under MAS''s stablecoin framework via Paxos Digital Singapore; Paxos also NY-DFS regulated for other products. Positioned for compliant multi-jurisdiction distribution.","transparency":"Paxos-grade monthly attestations and reserve reporting.","yield":"No direct holder yield, BUT reserve yield is shared with distribution partners (exchanges/wallets) — the core commercial hook of the Global Dollar Network.","comparison":"vs USDC/USDT: same fiat-backed model but flips economics by paying distributors from reserve yield. Niche = exchanges/wallets wanting revenue share for listing it. Weakness: newer, smaller liquidity, depends on consortium adoption.","future":"Growth hinges on whether the yield-sharing incentive pulls distribution away from USDC/USDT. Backed by credible consortium. Risk: network-effect disadvantage vs incumbents, rate-cut compression of the shared yield, consortium coordination.","risks":"Incumbent competition, dependence on partner adoption, rate sensitivity of the yield-share model.","notes":"Key differentiator is the distribution-partner yield-share economics, not the token mechanics.","sources":["https://www.globaldollar.com","https://paxos.com","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/global-dollar","https://defillama.com"]}','["https://www.globaldollar.com","https://paxos.com","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/global-dollar","https://defillama.com"]','2026-07-08 19:16:21');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('pyusd','PayPal USD','PYUSD','{"issuer":"Paxos Trust Company (issues on behalf of PayPal), USA","founders":"PayPal (Dan Schulman era launch, 2023); issued by Paxos (Charles Cascarilla, Rich Teo)","issuer_background":"First stablecoin from a major US payments company (PayPal), launched Aug 2023 on Ethereum, later Solana. Distributed through PayPal/Venmo ecosystems.","raised":"N/A — PayPal-branded product issued by Paxos; backed by reserves.","type":"fiat-backed","backing":"US dollar deposits, US Treasuries, and cash equivalents held by Paxos. ~$2.8B supply.","daily_activity":"Growing via PayPal/Venmo distribution and Solana expansion; used in payments and DeFi incentives. Multi-chain (Ethereum, Solana, Arbitrum, etc.). (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/paypal-usd, defillama.com)","audits":"Monthly reserve attestations by an independent firm; Paxos NYDFS oversight adds rigor.","regulatory":"Issued by NYDFS-regulated Paxos Trust; well-positioned under the US GENIUS Act. Strong US compliance posture.","transparency":"Monthly attestations plus Paxos reserve reporting; high transparency.","yield":"No token yield historically; PayPal has offered promotional rewards on PYUSD balances in-app (marketing, not protocol yield).","comparison":"vs USDC/USDT: unmatched consumer-payments distribution via PayPal/Venmo; niche = mainstream US retail payments. Weakness: smaller on-chain liquidity, less DeFi depth, dependent on PayPal''s strategic commitment.","future":"Upside from embedding stablecoin payments into PayPal/Venmo''s huge user base and cross-border payouts. Risk: whether PayPal prioritizes it, competition from bank/consortium coins, and regulatory/commercial focus shifts.","risks":"Distribution dependence on PayPal strategy, modest DeFi liquidity, incumbent competition.","notes":"Symbolically important as Big Tech/payments entry into stablecoins; regulated Paxos issuance.","sources":["https://www.paypal.com/us/digital-wallet/manage-money/crypto/pyusd","https://paxos.com","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/paypal-usd","https://defillama.com"]}','["https://www.paypal.com/us/digital-wallet/manage-money/crypto/pyusd","https://paxos.com","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/paypal-usd","https://defillama.com"]','2026-07-08 19:16:34');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('usdy','Ondo US Dollar Yield','USDY','{"issuer":"Ondo Finance (Ondo USDY LLC / bankruptcy-remote SPV), USA","founders":"Nathan Allman (founder/CEO of Ondo Finance); Ondo founded 2021","issuer_background":"Ondo is a leading RWA/tokenization firm. USDY is a tokenized note yielding US Treasury returns, aimed at non-US retail/institutions. Ondo also runs OUSG and Ondo Chain.","raised":"Ondo raised from Founders Fund, Pantera, Coinbase Ventures and others (>$20M+ early; large token treasury). Well-capitalized.","type":"RWA-backed (tokenized yield-bearing Treasury note)","backing":"Short-term US Treasuries and bank deposits held in a bankruptcy-remote structure. ~$2.15B. Price >$1 and accrues yield (NAV rises), so it is a yield token, not a $1 payment peg.","daily_activity":"Multi-chain (Ethereum, Solana, Stellar, Sei, Sui, Mantle); used as yield-bearing collateral and savings instrument. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/ondo-us-dollar-yield, defillama.com)","audits":"Reserve/holdings attestations and reporting on the underlying Treasury portfolio.","regulatory":"Sold to non-US persons and eligible investors (not offered to US retail); structured as a security/note. Compliance-gated distribution.","transparency":"Regular reporting of underlying assets and token supply; strong RWA disclosure practices.","yield":"Yes — passes through ~US Treasury yield via accruing token price (rebasing/accruing variant).","comparison":"vs USDC/USDT: pays holders Treasury yield natively; niche = non-US users and institutions wanting on-chain USD savings. Weakness: not a $1 payment coin, geo-restricted, security-like classification.","future":"Well-positioned in the RWA/yield-bearing wave; Ondo''s ecosystem (Ondo Chain, Global Markets) could expand utility. Risk: rate-cut yield compression, securities-law distribution limits, competition from BUIDL/USYC/Franklin.","risks":"Interest-rate risk, jurisdictional restrictions, SPV/custody risk, redemption timing.","notes":"Represents the retail-facing tokenized-Treasury category; distinct from payment stablecoins.","sources":["https://ondo.finance","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/ondo-us-dollar-yield","https://defillama.com"]}','["https://ondo.finance","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/ondo-us-dollar-yield","https://defillama.com"]','2026-07-08 19:16:57');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('rlusd','Ripple USD','RLUSD','{"issuer":"Ripple (Standard Custody & Trust Company, a Ripple subsidiary), USA","founders":"Ripple (co-founded by Chris Larsen, Jed McCaleb; CEO Brad Garlinghouse)","issuer_background":"Ripple launched RLUSD in Dec 2024 to complement XRP for enterprise payments/liquidity. Issued natively on both the XRP Ledger and Ethereum.","raised":"N/A — Ripple is a large, well-funded company; RLUSD backed by reserves.","type":"fiat-backed","backing":"US dollar deposits, short-term US Treasuries, and cash equivalents. ~$1.56B supply.","daily_activity":"Growing enterprise/payments and DeFi usage; concentrated on XRPL and Ethereum. Rising on-chain volume as Ripple integrates it into cross-border flows. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/ripple-usd, defillama.com)","audits":"Monthly reserve attestations by an independent accounting firm.","regulatory":"Issued under a NYDFS limited-purpose trust charter (Standard Custody); strong US regulatory posture, aligned with GENIUS Act. NYDFS-approved.","transparency":"Monthly attestations and reserve reporting; NYDFS oversight.","yield":"No holder yield.","comparison":"vs USDC/USDT: leverages Ripple''s enterprise/banking relationships and XRPL settlement; niche = cross-border payments and RippleNet liquidity. Weakness: newer, smaller liquidity, tied to Ripple''s ecosystem adoption.","future":"Upside from Ripple''s enterprise payment corridors and XRPL DeFi; credible regulated issuer. Risk: incumbent liquidity gap, dependence on Ripple adoption, and competition among compliant USD coins.","risks":"Liquidity/network-effect disadvantage, ecosystem dependence, rate sensitivity of issuer economics.","notes":"NYDFS-regulated; strategically paired with XRP rather than replacing it.","sources":["https://ripple.com/solutions/stablecoin","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/ripple-usd","https://defillama.com"]}','["https://ripple.com/solutions/stablecoin","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/ripple-usd","https://defillama.com"]','2026-07-08 19:17:09');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('usdd','USDD','USDD','{"issuer":"TRON DAO Reserve / USDD ecosystem, associated with Justin Sun and the Tron network","founders":"Justin Sun (founder of Tron); USDD launched 2022","issuer_background":"Launched as an ''algorithmic'' stablecoin modeled loosely on the pre-collapse Terra design, then shifted to heavy overcollateralization after UST''s 2022 failure. USDD 2.0 relaunched with higher stated collateral ratios.","raised":"Backed by the TRON DAO Reserve treasury (TRX, BTC, USDT/USDC). No conventional raise.","type":"crypto-overcollateralized (originally marketed as algorithmic)","backing":"TRON DAO Reserve holdings — TRX, BTC, and USD stablecoins — stated at high overcollateralization ratios. ~$1.5B supply. Reserve is centrally managed and TRX-heavy, a key risk.","daily_activity":"Primarily on Tron, plus Ethereum, BSC, BitTorrent. Used within the Tron DeFi ecosystem (JustLend). (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/usdd, defillama.com)","audits":"Reserve dashboard published by TRON DAO Reserve; independent audit rigor is limited compared with USDC/PYUSD.","regulatory":"No licensed issuer; associated with Justin Sun, who has faced SEC litigation. Not MiCA/GENIUS compliant.","transparency":"Public reserve dashboard, but centralized management and self-reported figures reduce assurance.","yield":"Historically offered high staking APYs via TRON DAO Reserve/JustLend to support demand — a mechanism criticized as reflexive/subsidized.","comparison":"vs USDC/USDT: Tron-ecosystem-native decentralized-branded coin; niche = Tron DeFi. Weakness: TRX-correlated reserves, central control, algorithmic heritage, and Justin Sun regulatory overhang make it materially riskier.","future":"Tied to Tron ecosystem health and TRX price; reflexivity between TRX collateral and USDD is a structural vulnerability. Risk: collateral de-peg spiral in a TRX drawdown, regulatory action against Sun-linked entities, transparency shortfalls.","risks":"TRX correlation/reflexivity, centralized reserve control, algorithmic-era design legacy, regulatory/founder risk.","notes":"Peg has generally held post-2022 but the collateral is highly correlated to Tron''s own token — the core structural concern.","sources":["https://usdd.io","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/usdd","https://defillama.com/stablecoin/usdd","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/USDD"]}','["https://usdd.io","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/usdd","https://defillama.com/stablecoin/usdd","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/USDD"]','2026-07-08 19:17:31');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('usdf','Falcon USD','USDf','{"issuer":"Falcon Finance, a synthetic-dollar protocol (backed by DWF Labs)","founders":"Falcon Finance team, associated with DWF Labs (Andrei Grachev)","issuer_background":"Launched 2024/2025 as a yield-bearing synthetic dollar, conceptually similar to Ethena — accepting diverse collateral (stables and crypto) and generating yield via strategies.","raised":"Backed/incubated by DWF Labs; token and protocol funding via DWF ecosystem.","type":"crypto-overcollateralized (synthetic/yield-bearing)","backing":"Overcollateralized by a mix of stablecoins and crypto assets; sUSDf accrues yield from delta-neutral and arbitrage strategies. ~$1.26B supply. Backing composition and strategy transparency are key questions.","daily_activity":"Active on Ethereum and BSC; demand driven by sUSDf yield. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/falcon-finance, defillama.com)","audits":"Smart-contract audits; reserve/strategy attestations emerging but less established than incumbents.","regulatory":"No licensed issuer; synthetic-dollar structure outside payment-stablecoin frameworks. Not MiCA/GENIUS.","transparency":"Publishes reserve/collateral info; DWF Labs association draws both liquidity and scrutiny over market-making conflicts.","yield":"Yes — sUSDf pays yield from trading/arbitrage and funding strategies (variable).","comparison":"vs USDC/USDT: yield-bearing synthetic dollar; niche = yield seekers in the DWF/BSC ecosystem. Weakness: strategy/counterparty opacity, reliance on market conditions and DWF, short track record.","future":"Growth depends on sustained yield and trust in strategy execution; benefits from DWF liquidity. Risk: strategy drawdowns, counterparty risk, DWF-related governance/conflict concerns, and thin crisis-tested history.","risks":"Strategy/yield reversal, collateral de-peg, DWF concentration/conflict risk, transparency limits.","notes":"Part of the 2024-2025 wave of Ethena-style synthetic dollars; scrutinize collateral and strategy disclosures.","sources":["https://falcon.finance","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/falcon-finance","https://defillama.com/protocol/falcon-finance"]}','["https://falcon.finance","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/falcon-finance","https://defillama.com/protocol/falcon-finance"]','2026-07-08 19:17:44');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('u','United Stables','U','{"issuer":"United Stables (u.tech), a stablecoin liquidity-layer project; native on BNB Chain and Ethereum","founders":"United Stables team (u.tech); launched 2025 with BNB Chain support","issuer_background":"Positions itself as a ''stablecoin liquidity layer'' / AI-ready unified-liquidity stablecoin, launched natively on BNB Chain and Ethereum with strong BNB Chain ecosystem promotion.","raised":"Ecosystem-backed (BNB Chain support); funding details limited/undisclosed.","type":"crypto-overcollateralized","backing":"Backed by a basket of underlying stablecoin/collateral assets aggregated into a unified-liquidity layer. ~$1B supply. Backing composition transparency is still maturing.","daily_activity":"Active on BSC, Tron, Ethereum; adoption tied to BNB Chain incentives and DeFi integrations. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/united-stables, defillama.com)","audits":"Smart-contract audits; reserve attestation practices emerging.","regulatory":"No licensed payment-stablecoin issuer disclosed; operates as a DeFi liquidity-layer token. Not MiCA/GENIUS authorized.","transparency":"Publishes some collateral/liquidity information; disclosure maturity below incumbents given recent launch.","yield":"Utility centers on liquidity aggregation; any yield via associated DeFi products rather than a native pass-through.","comparison":"vs USDC/USDT: aims to unify fragmented stablecoin liquidity rather than be a primary reserve coin; niche = BNB Chain DeFi and cross-stable liquidity routing. Weakness: short history, dependence on incentives, transparency gaps.","future":"Growth depends on sustained BNB Chain incentives and real liquidity-layer adoption; concept is differentiated. Risk: incentive dependence, unclear regulatory footing, thin crisis-tested track record.","risks":"Incentive/mercenary-liquidity dependence, collateral transparency, regulatory ambiguity, short operating history.","notes":"Marketed as an ''AI-ready unified-liquidity'' stablecoin; verify current collateral disclosures before relying on it.","sources":["https://u.tech/","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/united-stables","https://www.bnbchain.org/en/blog/united-stables-launches-u-as-a-native-stablecoin-on-bnb-chain","https://defillama.com"]}','["https://u.tech/","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/united-stables","https://www.bnbchain.org/en/blog/united-stables-launches-u-as-a-native-stablecoin-on-bnb-chain","https://defillama.com"]','2026-07-08 19:19:09');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('usdgo','USDGO','USDGO','{"issuer":"Anchorage Digital Bank N.A. (issuer) with OSL Group (863.HK) as brand operator/distributor","founders":"OSL Group (Hong Kong-listed digital-asset firm); Anchorage Digital (Nathan McCauley, Diogo Monica) as regulated issuer","issuer_background":"Unveiled Dec 2025, launched on Solana Feb 2026 as an enterprise-grade compliant USD stablecoin under the US GENIUS Act, using a two-party issuer-distributor model.","raised":"OSL is publicly listed; launch backed by ~$20M ecosystem incentives and initial $50M minted. Anchorage is VC-backed (a16z, KKR, etc.).","type":"fiat-backed","backing":"1:1 US-dollar liquid assets held in independent custody, subject to third-party audits, with holder priority redemption rights. ~$870M supply (grew past $100M+ quickly in 2026).","daily_activity":"Solana-first, enterprise/institutional settlement and cross-border payments; supply grew rapidly post-launch. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/usdgo, defillama.com)","audits":"Third-party reserve audits; issued by federally regulated Anchorage Digital Bank adding oversight.","regulatory":"Designed around the US GENIUS Act; issued by a federally chartered US crypto bank (Anchorage). Strong compliance posture aimed at enterprises.","transparency":"Independent custody plus third-party audits; Anchorage regulatory status supports assurance.","yield":"No holder yield (payment/settlement focus).","comparison":"vs USDC/USDT: enterprise/cross-border-payments focus with an Asia (OSL) distribution channel and Anchorage-grade US compliance; niche = compliant corporate settlement, especially APAC. Weakness: new, small, concentrated on Solana and OSL distribution.","future":"Upside from OSL''s APAC enterprise reach plus GENIUS-Act legitimacy; could carve an institutional payments niche. Risk: incumbent competition, dependence on OSL distribution, and execution on the two-party model.","risks":"Early-stage/small supply, distribution concentration, chain concentration (Solana), competitive USD market.","notes":"Distinct from Paxos''s USDG despite similar naming; issuer is Anchorage, brand/distribution is OSL.","sources":["https://www.usdgo.com","https://www.osl.com","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/usdgo","https://defillama.com"]}','["https://www.usdgo.com","https://www.osl.com","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/usdgo","https://defillama.com"]','2026-07-08 19:19:09');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('usdtb','Ethena USDtb','USDTB','{"issuer":"Ethena Labs (with a regulated issuing entity); designed as a fiat/T-bill-style companion to USDe","founders":"Guy Young (Ethena Labs)","issuer_background":"Launched Dec 2024 as Ethena''s low-risk, fiat-style stablecoin to complement the higher-risk synthetic USDe. Backed largely by BlackRock''s BUIDL tokenized Treasury fund.","raised":"Part of Ethena Labs (backed by Dragonfly, Maelstrom, Binance Labs, Franklin Templeton, etc.).","type":"RWA-backed / fiat-backed","backing":"Predominantly BlackRock USD BUIDL (tokenized US Treasuries) plus stablecoin/cash buffers. ~$775M supply. This makes it a tokenized-Treasury-backed dollar rather than a synthetic delta-neutral coin like USDe.","daily_activity":"Used as reserve/backstop within the Ethena ecosystem and as collateral; on Ethereum and Solana. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/usdtb, defillama.com)","audits":"Reserve attestations; underlying BUIDL carries BlackRock/Securitize fund-grade reporting.","regulatory":"More conventionally structured than USDe; leans on regulated tokenized-Treasury backing. Positioned for compliant use cases.","transparency":"Reserve dashboard showing BUIDL and cash holdings; benefits from BUIDL''s disclosures.","yield":"Can be structured to pass Treasury yield in some wrappers; primarily serves as a stable, low-risk reserve asset.","comparison":"vs USDC/USDT: essentially a tokenized-Treasury dollar; niche = Ethena''s safe-asset leg and institutional collateral. Weakness: smaller, ecosystem-tied, and dependent on BUIDL/Securitize.","future":"Grows as Ethena scales its ''safe'' reserve leg and as tokenized Treasuries gain adoption. Risk: rate sensitivity, reliance on BUIDL, and concentration within the Ethena ecosystem.","risks":"Dependence on BUIDL/Securitize, interest-rate risk, ecosystem concentration.","notes":"Explicitly the low-risk counterpart to USDe within Ethena; do not conflate the two risk profiles.","sources":["https://www.ethena.fi","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/usdtb","https://defillama.com/protocol/ethena"]}','["https://www.ethena.fi","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/usdtb","https://defillama.com/protocol/ethena"]','2026-07-08 19:19:26');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('gho','GHO','GHO','{"issuer":"Aave DAO (decentralized protocol governed by AAVE token holders)","founders":"Aave founded by Stani Kulechov; GHO launched 2023 via Aave governance","issuer_background":"GHO is Aave''s native decentralized overcollateralized stablecoin, minted by users against collateral supplied to the Aave protocol. Revenue from GHO interest accrues to the Aave DAO treasury.","raised":"Aave (formerly ETHLend) raised via 2017 ICO; GHO is a protocol product, not separately raised.","type":"crypto-overcollateralized","backing":"Overcollateralized by assets supplied to Aave (ETH, stablecoins, LSTs, etc.). ~$600M supply. Mint/burn governed by Aave risk parameters and ''facilitators''; a Peg Stability Module and stkAAVE discounts support the peg.","daily_activity":"Used within Aave/DeFi (borrowing, looping, yield). On Ethereum and Monad. Peg has occasionally traded slightly below $1, corrected via governance and PSM. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/gho, defillama.com)","audits":"Extensively audited Aave smart contracts; on-chain collateral fully transparent.","regulatory":"Decentralized, no licensed issuer; permissionless mint against collateral. Not a MiCA EMT.","transparency":"Fully on-chain and auditable collateral and supply; high transparency.","yield":"Holders can earn via Aave''s savings/staking mechanisms (e.g., stkGHO) and DeFi; borrowers pay interest to the DAO.","comparison":"vs USDC/USDT: decentralized, censorship-resistant at the token layer, and natively integrated with the largest lending protocol; niche = Aave users and DeFi. Weakness: smaller liquidity, peg maintenance requires active governance, and demand is Aave-centric.","future":"Grows with Aave usage and cross-chain expansion; GHO revenue strengthens the DAO. Risk: peg-management dependence on governance, collateral/liquidation risk, and competition from USDS/DAI in decentralized-stable niche.","risks":"Peg deviations, collateral/liquidation risk, governance dependence, smaller liquidity.","notes":"Directly analogous to DAI but native to Aave rather than Maker/Sky.","sources":["https://aave.com","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/gho","https://defillama.com/protocol/aave"]}','["https://aave.com","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/gho","https://defillama.com/protocol/aave"]','2026-07-08 19:19:40');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('pusd','Polymarket USD','pUSD','{"issuer":"Polymarket (prediction-market platform); pUSD is its native settlement dollar, issued via a partner (Paxos-linked infrastructure)","founders":"Polymarket founded by Shayne Coplan (2020)","issuer_background":"Polymarket introduced pUSD as a native USD settlement token for its prediction markets on Polygon, reducing reliance on bridged USDC and capturing reserve economics.","raised":"Polymarket raised large rounds (Founders Fund, Peter Thiel, 1confirmation; reportedly a $2B+ valuation raise and ICE/Intercontinental Exchange investment in 2025).","type":"fiat-backed","backing":"USD reserves / cash-equivalents backing the settlement token 1:1. ~$580M supply, concentrated on Polygon. Backing details tied to its issuing partner''s reserve practices.","daily_activity":"High turnover during major event/betting cycles; usage concentrated in Polymarket markets on Polygon. Volume spikes around elections and major events. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/polymarket-usd, defillama.com)","audits":"Relies on the issuing partner''s reserve attestations; standalone audit history is short.","regulatory":"Polymarket has faced US regulatory scrutiny (CFTC) historically; pUSD is a platform settlement instrument. Compliance posture tied to Polymarket''s evolving US re-entry.","transparency":"Reserve assurance depends on the issuing partner; platform-specific token with limited standalone disclosure.","yield":"No holder yield; reserve economics accrue to Polymarket/partner.","comparison":"vs USDC/USDT: purpose-built settlement dollar for one platform; niche = Polymarket prediction markets. Weakness: single-venue utility, concentration on Polygon, limited external liquidity.","future":"Grows with Polymarket''s US re-entry and event-driven volume; strategically lets Polymarket internalize stablecoin float. Risk: regulatory dependence on Polymarket, single-platform concentration, and partner reserve reliability.","risks":"Single-venue/platform dependence, regulatory risk around prediction markets, concentration on Polygon, partner reserve risk.","notes":"Best viewed as an application-specific settlement stablecoin, not a general-purpose currency.","sources":["https://polymarket.com","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/polymarket-usd","https://defillama.com"]}','["https://polymarket.com","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/polymarket-usd","https://defillama.com"]','2026-07-08 19:19:59');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('usd0','Usual USD','USD0','{"issuer":"Usual (Usual Labs / Usual DAO), a decentralized RWA-backed stablecoin protocol","founders":"Pierre Person (former French MP) and the Usual team; launched 2024","issuer_background":"Usual issues USD0, a stablecoin fully backed by tokenized short-term US Treasuries/RWA, and redistributes value to users via its USUAL governance token. Grew rapidly then contended with USD0++ bond-redemption controversy in early 2025.","raised":"Raised from investors including Binance Labs, Kraken Ventures, and others (~$10M+ seed) plus token distribution.","type":"RWA-backed","backing":"Tokenized ultra-short US Treasuries / RWA (e.g., via Hashnote USYC and similar) held 1:1. ~$550M supply. USD0 is the liquid stablecoin; USD0++ is a locked bond variant that de-pegged when redemption terms changed.","daily_activity":"Active on Ethereum and Arbitrum; DeFi liquidity mining drove growth. USD0++ episode (Jan 2025) caused temporary stress. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/usual-usd, defillama.com)","audits":"Smart-contract audits; underlying RWA via regulated tokenized-Treasury providers with their own attestations.","regulatory":"Decentralized protocol; RWA backing introduces off-chain custody/compliance. Not a MiCA EMT.","transparency":"On-chain supply plus RWA provider reporting; the USD0++ redesign highlighted governance/communication risk.","yield":"Yes — value accrues via USUAL token rewards and the USD0++ bond; Treasury yield is captured by the protocol and redistributed.","comparison":"vs USDC/USDT: RWA-backed with a token-incentive flywheel; niche = DeFi users wanting Treasury-backed yield plus governance upside. Weakness: incentive-driven demand, USD0++ de-peg precedent, governance risk.","future":"Depends on sustainable RWA yield and rebuilding trust after the USD0++ episode. Risk: mercenary-liquidity flight, governance/communication missteps, and RWA counterparty risk.","risks":"USD0++ bond de-peg precedent, incentive dependence, governance risk, RWA/custody risk.","notes":"Distinguish USD0 (liquid stablecoin) from USD0++ (locked bond token) — the latter is where the 2025 stress occurred.","sources":["https://usual.money","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/usual-usd","https://defillama.com/protocol/usual"]}','["https://usual.money","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/usual-usd","https://defillama.com/protocol/usual"]','2026-07-08 19:20:13');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('ylds','YLDS','YLDS','{"issuer":"Figure Certificate Company, a subsidiary of Figure Technology Solutions/Figure Markets, USA","founders":"Mike Cagney (co-founder of Figure and SoFi); YLDS launched Feb 2025","issuer_background":"Figure is a large blockchain-based lending/financial-services firm. YLDS is the FIRST yield-bearing stablecoin registered with the US SEC as a public security.","raised":"Figure is well-funded (raised >$1.5B across debt/equity historically); Ondo Finance made a $25M strategic investment in YLDS in Nov 2025.","type":"yield-bearing (SEC-registered security — tokenized face-amount certificate)","backing":"Assets similar to a prime money-market fund (short-term government/Treasury exposure). ~$530M supply. Legally an unsecured face-amount certificate redeemable for $1 plus accrued yield; fixed face amount of $0.01 per certificate.","daily_activity":"On Provenance, Solana, Stellar, Ethereum, Sui; used as compliant on-chain settlement and savings, and as backing for other RWA products (e.g., Ondo OUSG). (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/ylds, ylds.com)","audits":"Reserves reported quarterly in SEC-filed financial statements; issuer registered under the Investment Company Act of 1940.","regulatory":"UNIQUE: registered under the Securities Act of 1933 and Investment Company Act of 1940; SEC-overseen. It is explicitly a security, not a GENIUS-Act payment stablecoin, because it pays yield to US holders.","transparency":"Highest regulatory-grade disclosure of any coin here — public SEC periodic reports with audited financials.","yield":"Yes — pays ~SOFR minus 0.35-0.50% (roughly 3.7-3.85%), accrued daily, paid monthly; KYC required to earn interest.","comparison":"vs USDC/USDT: passes Treasury-like yield to holders with full SEC registration and retail US access; niche = compliant on-chain yield/settlement. Weakness: security classification limits composability, KYC-gated interest, and $0.01 certificate mechanics differ from a plain $1 token.","future":"Template for compliant yield-bearing on-chain dollars in the US; likely used as regulated collateral (Ondo investment signals this). Risk: rate-cut yield compression, securities-law operational overhead, and slower composability than permissionless stablecoins.","risks":"Interest-rate risk, unsecured face-amount-certificate credit exposure to Figure Certificate Company, KYC gating, security-law constraints.","notes":"Do not treat as a plain stablecoin — it is a registered security that happens to hold a $1 peg with yield.","sources":["https://www.ylds.com/","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/ylds","https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1974395/000149315225018198/form497.htm"]}','["https://www.ylds.com/","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/ylds","https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1974395/000149315225018198/form497.htm"]','2026-07-08 19:20:59');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('usx','Solstice USX','USX','{"issuer":"Solstice Finance (Solstice Labs AG, a Deus X Enterprise company) with the Solstice Foundation","founders":"Ben Nadareski (CEO, co-founder); backed by Deus X Capital","issuer_background":"Launched Sept 2025 as a Solana-native yield-bearing synthetic stablecoin, positioned to fill Solana''s lack of a flagship native stablecoin. Launched with ~$160M TVL, backed by Galaxy, MEV Capital, Bitcoin Suisse, Auros, Deus X.","raised":"Backed by Deus X Capital (~$1B digital-asset firm) and launch partners; not a conventional VC-round disclosure.","type":"crypto-overcollateralized (synthetic/yield-bearing)","backing":"Stated 1:1 stable-collateral backing with real-time Chainlink Proof of Reserves; YieldVault deploys collateral into delta-neutral strategies. ~$518M supply. Over-100% collateralized per issuer, yet suffered a liquidity-driven de-peg.","daily_activity":"Solana-native; integrated with Raydium, Kamino, Orca. eUSX/YieldVault drives demand. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/usx, defillama.com)","audits":"Chainlink Proof of Reserves feed plus smart-contract audits; strategy-level assurance still maturing.","regulatory":"Synthetic-dollar structure; licensed yield-fund wrapper for eUSX. Not a MiCA/GENIUS payment stablecoin.","transparency":"Real-time Chainlink PoR is a strength, but the Dec 2025 depeg exposed liquidity-infrastructure fragility beyond collateralization.","yield":"Yes — YieldVault (eUSX) offered a trailing ~15.4% APY from delta-neutral strategies; yield is variable and strategy-dependent.","comparison":"vs USDC/USDT: Solana-native high-yield synthetic dollar; niche = Solana DeFi yield. Weakness: DEMONSTRATED liquidity fragility (Dec 2025 collapse to ~$0.10 despite >100% collateral), reliance on market makers/central actors, and high-yield sustainability questions.","future":"Recovery depends on rebuilding liquidity depth and trust after the depeg; concept fills a real Solana gap. Risk: recurrence of liquidity crises, yield-strategy drawdowns, counterparty risk, and confidence damage from the Dec 2025 event.","risks":"Liquidity-crisis/de-peg (materialized Dec 2025), reliance on centralized market makers, strategy/yield reversal, counterparty risk.","notes":"Cautionary case: >100% collateralization did NOT prevent a severe depeg when secondary-market liquidity failed.","sources":["https://solstice.finance/usx","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/usx","https://defillama.com","https://www.theblock.co/post/352212/solstice-labs-to-launch-yield-bearing-stablecoin-usx-on-solana-in-summer-2025"]}','["https://solstice.finance/usx","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/usx","https://defillama.com","https://www.theblock.co/post/352212/solstice-labs-to-launch-yield-bearing-stablecoin-usx-on-solana-in-summer-2025"]','2026-07-08 19:20:59');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('a7a5','A7A5','A7A5','{"issuer":"A7A5 project, a Russian-ruble-pegged stablecoin associated with entities linked to Moldovan/Russian financial interests (reported ties to sanctioned figures)","founders":"Associated in reporting with Russian financial interests; issued via a Kyrgyzstan-based structure. Founders not transparently disclosed.","issuer_background":"A ruble-denominated stablecoin that drew international attention for very large transaction volumes and reported links to sanctions-evasion narratives around Russian finance (covered by Reuters and blockchain-analytics firms).","raised":"Not disclosed; backed by ruble deposits per its claims.","type":"fiat-backed (ruble-pegged)","backing":"Claims 1:1 backing by Russian ruble deposits held at a bank. Price ~0.0127 USD reflects the RUB/USD rate, not a broken peg. ~$573M-equivalent supply.","daily_activity":"Reported extremely high cumulative transaction volume on Tron and Ethereum — tens of billions of dollars cycled per analytics reports — far exceeding organic ruble-stablecoin demand, prompting sanctions-evasion scrutiny. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/a7a5, reuters.com)","audits":"No credible independent audit; reserve claims are self-reported and contested.","regulatory":"Operates outside Western regulatory frameworks; associated with sanctions-circumvention concerns. NOT MiCA/GENIUS compliant and a compliance red flag for regulated venues.","transparency":"Low; reserve and ownership disclosures are opaque and disputed.","yield":"Reportedly offered yield/incentives to drive ruble deposits; details unverified.","comparison":"vs USDT/USDC: a non-USD, geopolitically charged ruble coin; niche = ruble on/off-ramping and cross-border flows in/around Russia. Weakness/edge: extreme sanctions and counterparty risk, opacity, and likely non-organic volume.","future":"Trajectory dominated by geopolitics and sanctions enforcement rather than product merit. Risk: OFAC/EU sanctions designation, exchange delistings, reserve-backing doubts, and reputational contamination for any counterparty.","risks":"Sanctions/compliance risk, opacity, unverified reserves, wash/non-organic volume, delisting risk.","notes":"Included for completeness as a top-supply non-USD coin; treat as high-risk and compliance-sensitive.","sources":["https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/a7a5","https://www.reuters.com","https://defillama.com"]}','["https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/a7a5","https://www.reuters.com","https://defillama.com"]','2026-07-08 19:21:20');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('tusd','TrueUSD','TUSD','{"issuer":"TrueUSD, originally by TrustToken/Archblock; ownership transferred to Techteryx (2020); operations linked to the Justin Sun/Tron ecosystem","founders":"TrustToken (Rafael Cosman, Danny An, Stephen Kade), launched 2018; later sold to Techteryx","issuer_background":"One of the earliest fully fiat-backed, attested stablecoins. After the ownership change and closer Tron ecosystem ties, it faced reserve-transparency controversies (2023 Prime Trust/First Digital custody issues; a brief 2023 depeg).","raised":"TrustToken raised from a16z, Jump, GGV and others early; TUSD itself is reserve-backed.","type":"fiat-backed","backing":"US-dollar reserves held with banking/custody partners. ~$484M supply. Reserve custody has been a repeated concern (Prime Trust exposure in 2023, questions over attestation continuity).","daily_activity":"Multi-chain (Ethereum, Tron, BSC, Avalanche); heavily used on Binance historically (was a zero-fee pair). (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/true-usd, defillama.com)","audits":"Real-time attestation feed (via The Network Firm/Chainlink PoR) introduced, but past gaps and custody issues dented trust.","regulatory":"No strong single-jurisdiction license; associated concerns around Tron-ecosystem links. Not MiCA/GENIUS compliant.","transparency":"On-chain PoR feed exists, but historical reserve/custody controversies reduce confidence.","yield":"No holder yield.","comparison":"vs USDC/USDT: an early attested fiat coin now diminished; niche = certain Binance/Tron trading pairs. Weakness: reserve-custody controversies, opacity around ownership, and declining relevance.","future":"Likely continued slow decline absent renewed transparency; overshadowed by USDC/USDT/FDUSD. Risk: reserve/custody doubts, regulatory pressure, and loss of exchange support.","risks":"Reserve custody/transparency issues, ownership opacity, Tron-ecosystem association, depeg precedent (2023).","notes":"Historically important as an early transparent stablecoin; reputation eroded post-2023.","sources":["https://tusd.io","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/true-usd","https://defillama.com","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TrueUSD"]}','["https://tusd.io","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/true-usd","https://defillama.com","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TrueUSD"]','2026-07-08 19:21:36');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('fdusd','First Digital USD','FDUSD','{"issuer":"First Digital Labs / FD121 Limited (First Digital Trust), Hong Kong","founders":"First Digital (Hong Kong trust/custody firm), launched FDUSD in 2023","issuer_background":"Rose quickly as a Binance-promoted USDT/USDC alternative after BUSD''s wind-down. In 2025 faced a brief depeg amid allegations (denied by First Digital) tied to the TUSD/Techteryx legal dispute involving Justin Sun.","raised":"N/A — issued by First Digital Trust; reserve-backed.","type":"fiat-backed","backing":"US Treasury bills and cash equivalents held in Hong Kong custody. ~$347M supply (down from multi-billion peak after 2025 stress).","daily_activity":"Heavily used on BSC/Binance as a primary trading-pair stablecoin; also Ethereum, Sui, Solana, TON. High exchange-driven volume. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/first-digital-usd, defillama.com)","audits":"Monthly reserve attestations; First Digital publicly disputed 2025 insolvency allegations and asserted full backing.","regulatory":"Hong Kong trust-regulated custody; positioned amid HK''s evolving stablecoin regime. Not a MiCA EMT.","transparency":"Monthly attestations, but the 2025 allegations/depeg episode damaged confidence despite the issuer''s rebuttals.","yield":"No holder yield.","comparison":"vs USDC/USDT: a Binance-ecosystem fiat coin; niche = BSC/Binance trading pairs. Weakness: heavy Binance dependence, 2025 depeg/allegation episode, and reputational sensitivity to the Sun/TUSD dispute.","future":"Recovery depends on rebuilding trust and Binance support; HK regulatory clarity could help. Risk: exchange-dependence, litigation/allegation overhang, and reserve-confidence fragility.","risks":"Binance concentration, 2025 depeg/allegation overhang, litigation exposure, reserve-confidence risk.","notes":"Became prominent as a BUSD replacement; the April 2025 depeg is the key stress event.","sources":["https://firstdigitallabs.com","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/first-digital-usd","https://defillama.com"]}','["https://firstdigitallabs.com","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/first-digital-usd","https://defillama.com"]','2026-07-08 19:22:15');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('gusd','Gate USD','GUSD','{"issuer":"Gate (Gate.io exchange), launched Aug 2025. NOTE: shares the ''GUSD'' ticker with the older NYDFS-regulated Gemini Dollar, but is a DISTINCT token.","founders":"Gate exchange (founder Han Lin/Gate team); Gate USD launched August 29, 2025","issuer_background":"Gate''s own dollar token, structured not as a plain payment stablecoin but as a yield-bearing RWA-backed ''investment certificate'' integrated into Gate''s exchange, staking, and Launchpool products.","raised":"N/A — exchange-issued; Gate disclosed large crypto holdings and 1:1 GUSD reserves.","type":"RWA-backed / yield-bearing","backing":"Real-world assets, primarily US Treasury bonds, with returns derived from RWA interest. ~$319M supply (per monitor; ~150M+ per some trackers). Backing/attestation practices are exchange-managed.","daily_activity":"Concentrated on Gate (GUSD/USDT pair) with 1:1 USDT/USDC conversion; utility tied to Gate Launchpool and staking. On Ethereum. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/gusd, defillama.com)","audits":"Exchange-disclosed reserves; independent-audit rigor is lower than NYDFS/US-regulated peers.","regulatory":"Exchange-issued; not NYDFS/MiCA/GENIUS authorized. Regulatory posture weaker than Gemini Dollar despite the shared ticker.","transparency":"Gate publishes reserve claims, but assurance depends on the exchange rather than an independent regulated framework.","yield":"Yes — appreciation/yield from underlying RWA (Treasury) interest; a key differentiator from plain stablecoins.","comparison":"vs USDC/USDT: an exchange-native yield-bearing dollar; niche = Gate ecosystem users seeking yield plus stablecoin utility. Weakness: single-exchange concentration, weaker independent oversight, and ticker confusion with Gemini Dollar.","future":"Grows with Gate''s ecosystem incentives; yield hook drives adoption. Risk: exchange-counterparty/solvency risk, regulatory scrutiny of yield-bearing exchange tokens, and confusion with Gemini''s GUSD.","risks":"Exchange-counterparty risk, single-venue concentration, weaker independent audit, ticker/identity confusion, regulatory risk on yield-bearing model.","notes":"Do NOT conflate with Gemini Dollar (also ''GUSD''). This entry (slug gusd, ''Gate USD'') is Gate.io''s yield-bearing RWA token.","sources":["https://www.gate.com/gusd","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/gusd","https://www.coingecko.com/learn/what-is-gusd-gate-stablecoin","https://defillama.com"]}','["https://www.gate.com/gusd","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/gusd","https://www.coingecko.com/learn/what-is-gusd-gate-stablecoin","https://defillama.com"]','2026-07-08 19:23:28');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('m','M by M0','M','{"issuer":"M0 Foundation / M^0 protocol — a decentralized ''stablecoin issuance layer'' for permissioned institutional issuers of $M","founders":"Luca Prosperi (CEO) and the M0 team (several ex-MakerDAO/DeFi contributors); protocol launched 2024","issuer_background":"M^0 is infrastructure: a shared, collateral-backed base layer that lets multiple institutions mint a common $M dollar and build branded stablecoins on top. WrappedM (wM) is the ~$1 tradable form.","raised":"Raised a notable seed (~$35M) led by Bain Capital Crypto and Pantera (2023), plus follow-on funding.","type":"RWA-backed (institutionally-issued, collateral-backed base dollar)","backing":"$M is minted by approved ''Minters'' locking eligible collateral — primarily short-term US Treasuries — in off-chain custody under protocol rules. ~$308M supply. wM (wrapped) trades ~$1.","daily_activity":"Used as a base layer beneath other stablecoins/apps; multi-chain (Ethereum, Solana, Monad, Noble, Hyperliquid, Arbitrum). wM/USDC liquidity on Uniswap. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/wrappedm-by-m0, defillama.com)","audits":"Smart-contract audits; collateral is off-chain Treasuries under the protocol''s minter framework with attestations.","regulatory":"Permissioned-minter model with institutional actors; not itself a licensed EMT. Designed to let regulated issuers build compliant coins on top.","transparency":"On-chain supply plus minter/collateral reporting; a shared-ledger ''federation'' transparency model.","yield":"Yield from underlying Treasuries accrues within the system and can be passed to builders/holders of wrapped variants per each issuer''s design.","comparison":"vs USDC/USDT: not a consumer coin — it is a neutral issuance/collateral layer that others build on; niche = institutions wanting to launch their own stablecoin without bootstrapping reserves. Weakness: B2B/abstract, small direct supply, and dependence on minter adoption.","future":"Upside as ''stablecoin-as-infrastructure'' if multiple issuers adopt the shared $M base (composable, shared liquidity). Risk: slow institutional adoption, minter/collateral-custody risk, and competition from vertically-integrated issuers.","risks":"Minter/collateral custody risk, adoption dependence, complexity, interest-rate sensitivity.","notes":"Think of M^0 as a shared cryptodollar base layer; wM is the wrapped ~$1 tradable token (coingecko slug wrappedm-by-m0).","sources":["https://www.m0.org","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/wrappedm-by-m0","https://defillama.com/protocol/m0"]}','["https://www.m0.org","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/wrappedm-by-m0","https://defillama.com/protocol/m0"]','2026-07-08 19:23:28');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('eurc','EURC (Euro Coin)','EURC','{"issuer":"Circle Internet Financial, USA/EU (issued in the EU under Circle''s French EMI license)","founders":"Jeremy Allaire, Sean Neville (Circle); EURC launched 2022 as Euro Coin","issuer_background":"Circle''s euro stablecoin, the euro counterpart to USDC. Became the leading MiCA-compliant euro stablecoin by leveraging Circle''s French Electronic Money Institution authorization.","raised":"Part of Circle (NYSE: CRCL, IPO June 2025); backed by Circle''s broader funding.","type":"fiat-backed (EUR)","backing":"Euro cash and short-dated euro-denominated reserves held at regulated European banks. ~$428M supply. Price ~1.14 USD reflects EUR/USD, not a broken peg.","daily_activity":"Multi-chain (Ethereum, Base, Solana, Avalanche, Stellar, Sonic); the most liquid euro stablecoin, used in EU DeFi and FX. Growing volume post-MiCA. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/euro-coin, defillama.com)","audits":"Monthly attestations (Deloitte) plus Circle''s public-company disclosures.","regulatory":"MiCA-compliant EMT via Circle''s French EMI license — a flagship compliant euro coin. Strong EU regulatory standing.","transparency":"Circle-grade: monthly attestations, reserve reporting, public-company oversight.","yield":"No holder yield (MiCA EMTs are prohibited from paying interest to holders).","comparison":"vs USDT/USDC: the leading regulated EUR stablecoin; niche = euro-denominated on-chain payments, FX, and MiCA-compliant DeFi. Weakness: euro-stablecoin demand is far smaller than USD; competes with EURe, EURt, and bank euro coins.","future":"Best-positioned euro coin under MiCA; grows as EU on-chain euro usage expands and USD-stablecoin restrictions push euro adoption. Risk: structurally small euro market, negative-rate history for euro reserves compressing issuer economics, and competition.","risks":"Small euro-stablecoin TAM, EUR/USD volatility for USD-based users, reserve-economics sensitivity, competition.","notes":"The euro sibling of USDC; MiCA prohibition on holder yield is a key structural constraint for all EU EMTs.","sources":["https://www.circle.com/eurc","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/euro-coin","https://defillama.com"]}','["https://www.circle.com/eurc","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/euro-coin","https://defillama.com"]','2026-07-08 19:23:50');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('eure','Monerium EUR emoney','EURe','{"issuer":"Monerium EMI ehf, an Electronic Money Institution licensed in Iceland/EEA","founders":"Sveinn Valfells and Gisli Kristjansson (Monerium, founded 2016)","issuer_background":"Monerium issued the FIRST regulated euro e-money on blockchain (2019, EURe relaunch 2022). A pioneer of the e-money-token model that MiCA later codified, with native IBAN/SEPA integration.","raised":"Raised early funding (incl. from Consensys and others); an established licensed EMI.","type":"fiat-backed (EUR e-money token / EMT)","backing":"100% high-quality liquid euro reserves in safeguarded accounts; legally e-money with redemption rights. ~$30M supply (per MiCA-market reporting). Regulated EMT rather than a mere stablecoin.","daily_activity":"Multi-chain (Ethereum, Gnosis, Polygon, Arbitrum, Noble); distinctive for direct SEPA mint/burn via user IBANs. Used in EU payments and DeFi. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/monerium-eur-money, monerium.com)","audits":"EMI-regulated reporting and safeguarding requirements under EU/Icelandic law; supervised by the Central Bank of Iceland.","regulatory":"MiCA-compliant EMT; supervised by the Central Bank of Iceland with EEA passporting. Among the earliest fully-authorized euro tokens.","transparency":"Regulated EMI disclosures and safeguarding; strong legal/redemption clarity.","yield":"No holder yield (EMT rules).","comparison":"vs USDT/USDC (and EURC): differentiator is native IBAN/SEPA integration — euros move directly between bank and wallet. Niche = EU users/businesses wanting on-chain euros with real banking rails. Weakness: small supply/liquidity versus EURC.","future":"Well-placed as MiCA rewards licensed EMTs; SEPA-native UX is a durable edge for EU payments. Risk: small scale, competition from Circle''s better-capitalized EURC, and euro-market size limits.","risks":"Small liquidity, competition from EURC/bank coins, dependence on EU banking rails.","notes":"Legally e-money with IBAN integration — arguably the most ''bank-native'' euro token; CoinGecko lists it as ''Monerium EUR emoney'' (EURE).","sources":["https://monerium.com/eure/","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/monerium-eur-money","https://defillama.com"]}','["https://monerium.com/eure/","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/monerium-eur-money","https://defillama.com"]','2026-07-08 19:24:05');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('xsgd','StraitsX Singapore Dollar','XSGD','{"issuer":"StraitsX (Xfers Pte Ltd / StraitsX), Singapore","founders":"Aymeric Salley, Tianwei Liu and the StraitsX/Xfers team; XSGD launched 2020","issuer_background":"StraitsX is a Singapore payments infrastructure firm holding a MAS Major Payment Institution (MPI) license. XSGD is the leading SGD-pegged stablecoin; StraitsX also issues XUSD and XIDR.","raised":"Xfers/StraitsX raised institutional funding (backers include Fazz, GSR, Tribe, and others).","type":"fiat-backed (SGD)","backing":"1:1 SGD reserves held in trust accounts at DBS, Standard Chartered, and CIMB; interest accrues to the issuer per MAS rules. ~$13-17M supply. Price ~0.78 USD reflects SGD/USD.","daily_activity":"Real-world usage: accepted at Grab merchants and Alipay+ stores in Singapore; piloted in MAS Project Orchid (purpose-bound money). On Ethereum, Polygon, Avalanche, Arbitrum, Zilliqa, Hedera, XRPL; StraitsX+XUSD cited >$18B cumulative on-chain volume. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/xsgd, straitsx.com)","audits":"Monthly reserve attestations from an ISCA-listed auditing firm.","regulatory":"MAS Major Payment Institution license; XSGD recognized as substantively compliant with MAS''s Single-Currency Stablecoin (SCS) framework. Strong Singapore regulatory standing.","transparency":"Monthly attestations, named banking partners, MAS oversight — high transparency.","yield":"No holder yield (MAS rules direct reserve interest to the issuer).","comparison":"vs USDT/USDC: the flagship compliant SGD coin with genuine merchant/payments adoption; niche = Singapore payments, ASEAN FX, and MAS-piloted programmable money. Weakness: small SGD market and modest supply versus USD giants.","future":"Strong regional outlook: MPI license as a moat, real merchant integrations, and planned Solana SGD/USD FX rails. Risk: small currency market, competition, and dependence on Singapore/ASEAN adoption pace.","risks":"Small market size, SGD/USD volatility for USD users, regional-adoption dependence.","notes":"One of the best real-world-adopted non-USD stablecoins; regulation is a genuine competitive moat.","sources":["https://www.straitsx.com/xsgd","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/xsgd","https://defillama.com"]}','["https://www.straitsx.com/xsgd","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/xsgd","https://defillama.com"]','2026-07-08 19:24:23');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('audd','Australian Digital Dollar','AUDD','{"issuer":"AUDC Pty Ltd (majority-owned by ASX-listed Novatti Group)","founders":"AUDC / Novatti Group (ASX: NOV); AUDD is Novatti''s AUD stablecoin","issuer_background":"AUDD is a regulated, fiat-backed AUD stablecoin from AUDC, whose majority shareholder is the publicly listed Novatti Group. AUDC holds an Australian Financial Services Licence (AFSL) from ASIC for non-cash payment facilities.","raised":"AUDC raised A$5M in a Pre-Series A (at A$0.80/share); Novatti retains ~45% and values its stake at ~A$16M.","type":"fiat-backed (AUD)","backing":"1:1 AUD held as cash/cash-equivalents in segregated accounts. Small supply (~A$5-8M). Price ~0.65-0.69 USD reflects AUD/USD.","daily_activity":"Blockchain-agnostic: Stellar, XRP Ledger, Ethereum, Solana, Hedera, XDC, Base. AUDD has processed over A$1B in cumulative organic transactions on Stellar; low but real daily turnover. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/novatti-australian-digital-dollar, audd.digital)","audits":"Reserve attestations/audits under AFSL obligations; issued by an ASIC-regulated entity.","regulatory":"AFSL-licensed by ASIC (Australia); one of the more clearly regulated non-USD coins. Not a MiCA EMT (non-EU).","transparency":"AFSL-driven reporting plus the credibility of a listed parent (Novatti); reasonable transparency for its size.","yield":"No holder yield.","comparison":"vs USDT/USDC: the regulated Australian-dollar option with a listed-company parent; niche = AUD payments, remittances, and Australian on-ramps. Weakness: tiny supply/liquidity and a small AUD stablecoin market.","future":"Grows with Australian regulatory clarity and cross-border/remittance use; AFSL + Stellar traction are positives. Risk: small scale, AUD-market size, and competition from AUDF domestically.","risks":"Small liquidity, AUD/USD volatility for USD users, competition (AUDF), reliance on Novatti''s continued backing.","notes":"Distinct from Forte''s AUDF; AUDD''s edge is the Novatti/ASX-listed parent and ASIC AFSL.","sources":["https://www.audd.digital/","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/novatti-australian-digital-dollar","https://defillama.com"]}','["https://www.audd.digital/","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/novatti-australian-digital-dollar","https://defillama.com"]','2026-07-08 19:24:37');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('audf','Forte AUD','AUDF','{"issuer":"Forte Securities Australia Pty Ltd (Forte Technology Solutions), Australia","founders":"Forte Group / Forte Securities Australia team (issuer-run); founder details not authoritatively published — some third-party ''founder'' listings appear AI-generated and are NOT relied upon here","issuer_background":"AUDF is Forte''s centralized, AFSL-regulated Australian-dollar stablecoin, emphasizing proof-of-reserves and routine independent audits. Positioned as a payments-focused AUD coin.","raised":"Not authoritatively disclosed; issuer-funded/reserve-backed.","type":"fiat-backed / RWA-backed (AUD)","backing":"AUD reserves and cash-equivalent assets held separately from Forte''s operational funds, in segregated custody. Small supply (~A$3-6M). Price ~0.65 USD reflects AUD/USD (not a de-peg).","daily_activity":"On Ethereum, Polygon, Base, Redbelly; tradable on OKX, Swyftx, Cointree. Low but real turnover. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/forte-aud, forteaud.com)","audits":"Independent monthly reserve audits by MVAB Audit Pty Ltd (MVA Bennett), Chartered Accountants; daily reserve monitoring.","regulatory":"Issued by AFSL-regulated Forte Securities Australia; direct 1:1 AUD redemption for eligible accounts. Australian-regulated; not a MiCA EMT.","transparency":"Publishes proof-of-reserves with named independent auditor (MVA Bennett) — solid transparency for its size.","yield":"No native holder yield (payment-focused); DeFi users may earn separately via third-party protocols.","comparison":"vs USDT/USDC: a second regulated AUD option alongside AUDD; niche = Australian payments and FX with audited reserves. Weakness: tiny supply, small AUD market, and head-to-head competition with AUDD/Novatti.","future":"Depends on winning Australian merchant/exchange adoption versus AUDD; audited reserves and multi-DEX listings help. Risk: small scale, duplicative AUD market, and issuer-concentration.","risks":"Small liquidity, AUD/USD volatility for USD users, competition (AUDD), centralized issuer dependence.","notes":"AVOID unverified ''founder'' names circulating on some price sites (flagged as likely AI-generated). Cite official Forte site and the MVA Bennett audit.","sources":["https://forteaud.com/","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/forte-aud","https://defillama.com"]}','["https://forteaud.com/","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/forte-aud","https://defillama.com"]','2026-07-08 19:24:57');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('brz','Brazilian Digital Token','BRZ','{"issuer":"Transfero Swiss AG (Transfero Group), the official BRZ issuer","founders":"Transfero Swiss AG, in early collaboration with Brazilian partner Banco Rendimento; launched 2019","issuer_background":"BRZ is the first and leading Brazilian-real stablecoin, letting Brazilians access global crypto/FX in their local currency. Issued by Transfero, a blockchain investment/finance firm.","raised":"Backed by Transfero Group; reserve-backed rather than a public raise.","type":"fiat-backed (BRL)","backing":"1:1 Brazilian real reserves; mint/redeem via Transfero at 1 BRL (with KYC; ~1% redemption spread in Brazil). ~$50M market cap (~270M BRZ). Price ~0.19 USD reflects BRL/USD.","daily_activity":"Multi-chain (Ethereum, Polygon, BSC, Solana, Stellar); DEX liquidity on Curve/Uniswap (Polygon). Used for LatAm trading and payments. Underwent a recent contract migration. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/brazilian-digital-token, defillama.com)","audits":"Reserve attestations/reporting via Transfero; BRZ noted by industry as a standard BRL stablecoin (Brazilian Central Bank engagement on stablecoin norms).","regulatory":"Operates within Brazil''s evolving crypto-asset framework (BCB regulation of virtual-asset service providers); Transfero engages with local regulators. Not a MiCA EMT.","transparency":"Issuer reserve reporting; a CoinGecko contract-control caution flag was noted post-migration — verify current contract.","yield":"No native holder yield (BRL-yield products exist separately in the Transfero ecosystem).","comparison":"vs USDT/USDC: the dominant real-denominated coin; niche = Brazilian on/off-ramping, LatAm payments, and BRL trading pairs. Weakness: small vs USD giants, BRL volatility, and post-migration contract-trust flags.","future":"Well-placed as Brazil formalizes stablecoin/VASP rules and LatAm crypto adoption grows; first-mover in BRL. Risk: regulatory shifts (BCB), BRL macro volatility, and contract-migration/trust concerns.","risks":"BRL/USD volatility, Brazilian regulatory change, contract-migration caution flag, issuer concentration.","notes":"First BRL stablecoin; a leading LatAm-local coin alongside Mexico''s MXNe/MXNB.","sources":["https://www.transfero.com","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/brazilian-digital-token","https://defillama.com/stablecoin/brazilian-digital"]}','["https://www.transfero.com","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/brazilian-digital-token","https://defillama.com/stablecoin/brazilian-digital"]','2026-07-08 19:25:11');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('cadc','CAD Coin','CADC','{"issuer":"PAYTRIE AB Inc. (Paytrie), Canada","founders":"Paytrie team (Canadian on/off-ramp fintech); CADC issued by Paytrie","issuer_background":"CADC is a Canadian-dollar stablecoin from Paytrie, a licensed Money Services Business. Contract design is forked from Circle''s USDC for composability.","raised":"Not publicly disclosed; Paytrie is an established Canadian MSB.","type":"fiat-backed (CAD)","backing":"1:1 CAD held in a Canadian bank account. Small supply. Price ~0.72 USD reflects CAD/USD (not a de-peg).","daily_activity":"Primarily Ethereum (ERC-20); DEX liquidity (e.g., Stabull, Uniswap). Low but real turnover; used as a Canadian on/off-ramp asset. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/cad-coin, paytrie.com/cadc)","audits":"Reserve backing at a Canadian bank; independent-attestation cadence is limited versus major USD coins.","regulatory":"Issued by Paytrie, a FINTRAC-registered Money Services Business (MSB M19690633), Canada. Not a MiCA EMT.","transparency":"Bank-held reserves with issuer reporting; smaller-scale disclosure than incumbents.","yield":"No holder yield.","comparison":"vs USDT/USDC: the practical Canadian-dollar option; niche = CAD payments, FX pairs, and Canadian ramps. Weakness: small supply/liquidity, thin attestation cadence, and small CAD stablecoin market.","future":"Grows if Canadian stablecoin regulation clarifies and CAD on-chain demand rises. Risk: small scale, limited liquidity, CAD-market size, and reserve-transparency maturity.","risks":"Small liquidity, CAD/USD volatility for USD users, limited independent attestations, regulatory uncertainty in Canada.","notes":"USDC-forked contract; a leading CAD-denominated stablecoin despite modest size.","sources":["https://paytrie.com/cadc","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/cad-coin","https://defillama.com"]}','["https://paytrie.com/cadc","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/cad-coin","https://defillama.com"]','2026-07-08 19:25:49');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('cryptofranc','CryptoFranc','XCHF','{"issuer":"Swiss Crypto Tokens AG, a subsidiary of Bitcoin Suisse AG, Switzerland","founders":"Bitcoin Suisse AG (founded by Niklas Nikolajsen); XCHF launched 2019","issuer_background":"XCHF was a fully-collateralized Swiss-franc stablecoin issued as a CHF-denominated bond under Swiss law (FINMA payment-token classification). IMPORTANT: Bitcoin Suisse announced its DISCONTINUATION in Aug 2024.","raised":"N/A — issued by a Bitcoin Suisse subsidiary; bond-backed.","type":"fiat-backed (CHF) — being wound down","backing":"Was fully backed by physical CHF banknotes and bank deposits, structured as a Swiss bond. Post-discontinuation, remaining funds moved to custodian CMP Group AG in Baar per a Feb 2025 Zug court order.","daily_activity":"Historically on Ethereum (ERC-20), used in Swiss DeFi (e.g., early DEX pairs). Now minimal/illiquid due to wind-down; secondary prices unreliable. (Cite: coingecko.com, bitcoinsuisse.com/cryptofranc)","audits":"Was audited monthly by Grant Thornton Bank Audit Ltd during operation.","regulatory":"Classified as a payment token under FINMA guidance; issued under Swiss bond law. Not a MiCA EMT. Now in orderly wind-down/custody.","transparency":"Strong during operation (monthly Grant Thornton audits); now defined by the court-ordered exit process.","yield":"No holder yield.","comparison":"vs USDT/USDC: was the leading CHF stablecoin; niche = Swiss-franc on-chain exposure. Weakness/edge: DISCONTINUED — no longer issued or redeemed by Bitcoin Suisse; superseded by newer CHF efforts (e.g., MiCA-oriented CHFAU).","future":"Effectively sunsetting; holders should use the Bitcoin Suisse ''XCHF Exit'' process. The CHF-stablecoin niche is passing to newer, MiCA-aligned issuers. Risk: residual illiquidity, de-peg on secondary markets, and settlement/custody logistics.","risks":"Discontinuation/illiquidity, unreliable secondary pricing, exit-process dependence.","notes":"Include as a HISTORICAL/deprecated CHF stablecoin; do not treat live-market data as reliable. Contact Bitcoin Suisse re: ''XCHF Exit''.","sources":["https://www.bitcoinsuisse.com/cryptofranc","https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/cryptofranc/","https://iq.wiki/wiki/cryptofranc"]}','["https://www.bitcoinsuisse.com/cryptofranc","https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/cryptofranc/","https://iq.wiki/wiki/cryptofranc"]','2026-07-08 19:25:49');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('jpyc','JPY Coin','JPYC','{"issuer":"JPYC Inc., Japan (registered Type II Funds Transfer Service Provider / Electronic Payment Instrument issuer)","founders":"Noritaka Okabe (founder/CEO of JPYC Inc.); company established 2021","issuer_background":"JPYC is Japan''s first FSA-approved yen-pegged stablecoin. After registering as a Funds Transfer Service Provider (Aug 2025), it launched the regulated JPYC in Oct 2025 as an Electronic Payment Instrument under Japan''s Payment Services Act.","raised":"Raised a Series B first close of ~¥1.78B (2025-2026) to build out yen-stablecoin infrastructure.","type":"fiat-backed (JPY)","backing":"1:1 Japanese yen, legally an Electronic Payment Instrument under the PSA; reserves held per Japanese funds-transfer rules. ~$20M-equivalent supply. Price ~0.0066 USD reflects JPY/USD.","daily_activity":"On Ethereum, Avalanche, Polygon (v2 migrated contracts). Aimed at payments, remittances, corporate settlement, and Web3. AML screening via Elliptic. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/jpy-coin, corporate.jpyc.co.jp)","audits":"Regulated funds-transfer reserve requirements; compliance framework strengthened with Elliptic AML integration.","regulatory":"FIRST FSA-approved yen stablecoin; registered Type II Funds Transfer Service Provider under Japan''s PSA (Electronic Payment Instrument). Strong Japanese regulatory standing. Not a MiCA EMT (non-EU).","transparency":"Regulated-issuer disclosures under the PSA; FSA oversight.","yield":"No holder yield.","comparison":"vs USDT/USDC: the compliant on-chain yen; niche = Japanese payments/remittances and yen-denominated Web3. Weakness: small supply, JPY-market size, and early adoption stage. Distinguish v2 (jpy-coin) from legacy v1 (jpy-coin-v1) and the earlier prepaid JPYC.","future":"Positioned as the default digital-yen rail as Japan''s stablecoin regime matures; first-mover regulatory advantage. Risk: small scale, JPY macro (weak yen), and execution on adoption.","risks":"JPY/USD volatility for USD users, small liquidity, version/contract confusion (v1 vs v2 vs prepaid), adoption pace.","notes":"Regulated JPYC (Oct 2025) supersedes the earlier prepaid JPYC; CoinGecko slug jpy-coin is the current v2.","sources":["https://corporate.jpyc.co.jp/en","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/jpy-coin","https://www.ledgerinsights.com/japanese-stablecoin-issuer-jpyc-receives-a-license/"]}','["https://corporate.jpyc.co.jp/en","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/jpy-coin","https://www.ledgerinsights.com/japanese-stablecoin-issuer-jpyc-receives-a-license/"]','2026-07-08 19:26:09');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('idrt','Rupiah Token','IDRT','{"issuer":"PT Rupiah Token Indonesia, Indonesia","founders":"Jeth Soetoyo, Anthony Thio, Purwoko, Evan Leonardi, and Fengkie Junis; IDRT launched Oct 2019","issuer_background":"IDRT is the first and most widely adopted Indonesian-rupiah stablecoin, giving Indonesian users a fiat-denominated on-chain rail for payments, remittances, and trading.","raised":"Not publicly detailed; issued by PT Rupiah Token Indonesia.","type":"fiat-backed (IDR)","backing":"1:1 rupiah held in an Indonesian bank account, redeemable via the platform. ~$10M-equivalent supply (~170B IDRT). Price ~0.00006 USD reflects IDR/USD.","daily_activity":"ERC-20 (Ethereum) and BEP-20 (BSC); used for IDR trading pairs and local payments/remittances. Modest but real turnover. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/rupiah-token, rupiahtoken.com)","audits":"Bank-held reserves with issuer reporting; independent-attestation cadence is limited relative to major coins.","regulatory":"Operates within Indonesia''s evolving crypto framework (Bappebti/OJK oversight of crypto assets). Not a MiCA EMT.","transparency":"Reserve backing at an Indonesian bank with issuer disclosure; smaller-scale transparency.","yield":"No holder yield.","comparison":"vs USDT/USDC: the leading rupiah coin; niche = Indonesian payments, remittances, and IDR trading. Weakness: small supply/liquidity, IDR-market size, and thinner attestations. Competes with StraitsX''s XIDR.","future":"Grows with Indonesian crypto adoption and clearer local regulation; strong first-mover in IDR. Risk: IDR volatility, regulatory shifts, small scale, and competition (XIDR).","risks":"IDR/USD volatility for USD users, Indonesian regulatory change, small liquidity, limited independent attestations.","notes":"Longest-running IDR stablecoin (since 2019); a benchmark for Indonesian on-chain rupiah.","sources":["https://rupiahtoken.com/","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/rupiah-token","https://defillama.com"]}','["https://rupiahtoken.com/","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/rupiah-token","https://defillama.com"]','2026-07-08 19:26:21');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('zarp','ZARP Stablecoin','ZARP','{"issuer":"ZARP Stablecoin (Pty) Ltd, South Africa (a juristic representative of Inves Capital (Pty) Ltd)","founders":"ZARP Stablecoin (Pty) Ltd team; South-African-rand stablecoin","issuer_background":"ZARP is a collateralized South-African-rand stablecoin whose treasury is notably managed by Old Mutual Wealth — an established South African financial institution — lending credibility to its reserves.","raised":"Not publicly disclosed; issuer-backed.","type":"fiat-backed (ZAR)","backing":"1:1 ZAR reserves, treasury managed by Old Mutual Wealth; independent auditors verify at least R1 held per ZARP in circulation. Small supply. Price ~0.055 USD reflects ZAR/USD.","daily_activity":"Natively on Base, Ethereum, Polygon, Solana; DEX liquidity on Aerodrome, Orca, Uniswap. Acquired via partners AFRIDAX, ChainEX, OVEX. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/zarp-stablecoin, zarpstablecoin.com)","audits":"Independent auditors verify 1:1 ZAR backing; treasury managed by Old Mutual Wealth adds institutional oversight.","regulatory":"Structured via a juristic-representative arrangement under Inves Capital (license pending per issuer). Operates within South Africa''s FSCA crypto-asset regime. Not a MiCA EMT.","transparency":"Independent reserve verification plus a named institutional treasury manager — relatively strong for its size.","yield":"No holder yield.","comparison":"vs USDT/USDC: the leading rand stablecoin; niche = South African payments, savings, and ZAR trading/FX. Weakness: small supply/liquidity, ZAR volatility, and pending licensing status.","future":"Grows with African crypto adoption and South African regulatory clarity; Old Mutual treasury linkage is a differentiator. Risk: ZAR macro volatility, licensing finalization, and small scale.","risks":"ZAR/USD volatility for USD users, license-pending status, small liquidity, regional-adoption dependence.","notes":"Institutional treasury management (Old Mutual Wealth) is its standout credibility feature among emerging-market coins.","sources":["https://www.zarpstablecoin.com/","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/zarp-stablecoin","https://defillama.com"]}','["https://www.zarpstablecoin.com/","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/zarp-stablecoin","https://defillama.com"]','2026-07-08 19:26:37');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('tryb','BiLira','TRYB','{"issuer":"BiLira, a Turkey-based fintech company","founders":"BiLira team (Turkish fintech founders); TRYB launched 2019","issuer_background":"TRYB is the leading Turkish-lira stablecoin. In 2023 its market cap surged >300% to ~$136M amid high lira inflation, briefly making it the second-largest non-USD-pegged stablecoin — a case study in stablecoin demand as a hedge against local-currency debasement.","raised":"Backed by BiLira; funding details limited.","type":"fiat-backed (TRY)","backing":"1:1 Turkish lira; users can issue/redeem 1 TRYB for 1 TRY. ~$4-5M current supply (~230M TRYB, well below the 2023 peak). Price ~0.024 USD reflects TRY/USD.","daily_activity":"Liquidity pools on Ethereum, Polygon, Base. Used for lira trading and cross-border flows. Supply contracted sharply from the 2023 peak. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/bilira, defillama.com)","audits":"Issuer reserve reporting; independent-attestation rigor is limited relative to major USD coins.","regulatory":"Operates within Turkey''s evolving crypto framework (increasing MASAK/CMB oversight of crypto). Not a MiCA EMT.","transparency":"Issuer-level reserve reporting; smaller-scale disclosure.","yield":"No holder yield.","comparison":"vs USDT/USDC: the lira coin; niche = Turkish trading, remittances, and (paradoxically) as a bridge OUT of lira into USD stables during inflation. Weakness: extreme TRY depreciation makes holders prefer USD stables, capping durable demand; small liquidity.","future":"Demand is inversely tied to lira stability — useful as a rail but Turks often prefer USDT for savings. Risk: severe TRY inflation/devaluation, capital controls, regulatory tightening, and supply attrition.","risks":"TRY hyper-depreciation, preference for USD stables, Turkish regulatory/capital-control risk, small liquidity.","notes":"A vivid example of how non-USD stablecoins in high-inflation economies often act as a stepping-stone to USD, not a store of value.","sources":["https://www.bilira.co","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/bilira","https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2023/09/01/lira-backed-tryb-token-becomes-worlds-second-largest-non-dollar-pegged-stablecoin"]}','["https://www.bilira.co","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/bilira","https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2023/09/01/lira-backed-tryb-token-becomes-worlds-second-largest-non-dollar-pegged-stablecoin"]','2026-07-08 19:26:51');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('real-mxn','Real MXN','MXNe','{"issuer":"Brale (regulated US stablecoin issuer) in partnership with Etherfuse","founders":"Brale (founder/CEO Ben Milne, also founder of Dwolla) with Etherfuse (David Taylor and team)","issuer_background":"MXNe (Real MXN) is a Mexican-peso stablecoin issued by Brale and backed by Etherfuse''s CETES ''Stablebonds'' — tokenized short-term Mexican government Treasury bills — making it partly RWA/yield-backed rather than pure cash.","raised":"Brale is VC-backed (US stablecoin-issuance platform); Etherfuse backed by LatAm/crypto investors.","type":"RWA-backed (MXN, CETES Treasury-bill backed)","backing":"Etherfuse CETES Stablebonds — ~7-day Mexican federal Treasury bills (CETES) — held via regulated Mexican custodians (majority at BBVA Mexico, through INDEVAL). Redeemable 1:1 for MXN. Price ~0.05-0.06 USD reflects MXN/USD.","daily_activity":"On Base (primary), Solana, Stellar; described as the most-traded MXN-pegged stablecoin, concentrated on Base. Used for on-chain payments and Mexican FX. (Cite: brale.xyz/stablecoins/MXNe, coingecko.com/en/coins/real-mxn)","audits":"RWA (CETES) held via regulated custodians (BBVA/INDEVAL); note: a risk-profile flagged Base proxy-owner control and no public live reserve feed — verify current disclosures.","regulatory":"Issued by Brale, a US-regulated issuer; underlying CETES held in regulated Mexican custody. Not a MiCA EMT.","transparency":"Backing structure disclosed (CETES via custodians), but a lack of a public live reserve feed and Base proxy-owner control were flagged — a transparency gap to watch.","yield":"Underlying CETES generate yield; MXNe itself is a payment token (yield accrues within the Stablebond structure rather than rebasing the peg token).","comparison":"vs USDT/USDC: RWA-backed Mexican-peso coin; niche = Mexican payments/FX and on-chain CETES exposure. Weakness: peso-market size, custody/transparency flags, and head-to-head competition with Bitso''s MXNB.","future":"Well-placed in LatAm''s fast-growing localized-stablecoin market (Mexico + Brazil leading); CETES backing is a differentiator. Risk: MXN volatility, custody/proxy-control concerns, reserve-transparency gaps, and MXNB competition.","risks":"MXN/USD volatility for USD users, Base proxy-owner control flag, no public live reserve feed, MXNB competition.","notes":"Distinct from Bitso/Juno''s MXNB. CETES-backed structure makes it RWA-backed rather than plain cash-backed.","sources":["https://brale.xyz/stablecoins/MXNe","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/real-mxn","https://defillama.com"]}','["https://brale.xyz/stablecoins/MXNe","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/real-mxn","https://defillama.com"]','2026-07-08 19:27:12');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('apxusd','apxUSD','apxUSD','{"issuer":"Apyx Finance (Apyx), a ''Dividend-Backed Stablecoin'' protocol","founders":"Apyx Finance team; protocol launched Feb 2026","issuer_background":"Apyx issues apxUSD, a synthetic dollar backed primarily by PREFERRED EQUITY of digital-asset-treasury (DAT) companies — notably Strategy''s STRC preferred shares — channeling their dividend cash flows on-chain. A novel and high-risk ''digital credit'' design.","raised":"Not clearly disclosed; scaled to ~$500M supply within months of launch.","type":"crypto-overcollateralized (credit-linked synthetic dollar backed by preferred equity)","backing":"Majority backing = Strategy STRC preferred shares ($100 par) plus cash/Treasury buffers; ~104% overcollateralization (narrow). ~$300M supply (down from ~$500M peak). apyUSD is the yield-bearing savings token.","daily_activity":"On Ethereum, Base, BSC; integrated with Morpho lending. DEPEGGED to ~$0.90 on June 4 2026 and later traded as low as ~$0.83 as STRC fell below par during a Bitcoin selloff. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/apxusd, defillama.com)","audits":"Third-party risk assessments (e.g., TID Research) exist; issuer criticized for not publishing off-ramp arrangements and for a slow manual redemption leg.","regulatory":"Synthetic dollar backed by securities (preferred equity) — novel and legally untested; not a GENIUS payment stablecoin or MiCA EMT.","transparency":"Publishes overcollateralization and post-mortems, but flagged for disclosure gaps on off-ramp/redemption mechanics.","yield":"Yes — apyUSD accrues dividend yield from STRC preferred shares; base apxUSD is non-yield.","comparison":"vs USDC/USDT: a credit/equity-linked synthetic dollar, NOT cash-backed; niche = high-yield seekers comfortable with DAT/Bitcoin-correlated risk. Weakness: long, correlated collateral chain (BTC to STRC to apxUSD) and DEMONSTRATED de-pegs.","future":"Stability is structurally tethered to Bitcoin/STRC; will be stress-tested on every BTC drawdown. Apyx frames de-pegs as ''expected behavior''. Risk: further de-pegs, STRC/DAT credit risk, slow redemptions, and reflexive contagion.","risks":"Bitcoin/STRC correlation, preferred-equity credit risk, narrow overcollateralization, slow manual redemption, repeated de-pegs.","notes":"Cautionary novel design: a stablecoin whose peg depends on a Bitcoin-treasury company''s preferred shares. High risk.","sources":["https://apyx.fi/","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/apxusd","https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2026/06/04/apyx-s-stablecoin-suffers-a-brief-depeg-protocol-says-its-a-feature-not-bug","https://defillama.com"]}','["https://apyx.fi/","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/apxusd","https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2026/06/04/apyx-s-stablecoin-suffers-a-brief-depeg-protocol-says-its-a-feature-not-bug","https://defillama.com"]','2026-07-08 19:28:25');
INSERT INTO "stablecoin_meta" ("slug","name","symbol","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('megausd','MegaUSD','USDM','{"issuer":"MegaETH (Layer-2) in partnership with Ethena, via Ethena''s Stablecoin-as-a-Service stack","founders":"MegaETH team (high-performance Ethereum L2) with Ethena Labs (Guy Young); USDm launched 2025-2026","issuer_background":"USDm (MegaUSD) is MegaETH''s native stablecoin, built on Ethena''s USDtb rails. Its distinctive design uses reserve YIELD to subsidize the L2''s sequencer costs, keeping transaction fees low instead of charging sequencer margins.","raised":"MegaETH raised large rounds for its L2 (incl. from Dragonfly and others); USDm is reserve-backed via Ethena''s stack.","type":"RWA-backed (via USDtb / BlackRock BUIDL)","backing":"Backed by Ethena''s USDtb, whose reserves are primarily BlackRock''s BUIDL tokenized US Treasuries (via Securitize), plus liquid stablecoins for redemptions. ~$270M supply. Mint/redeem via USDC on mainnet then bridged; redeems into USDtb rather than direct fiat at launch.","daily_activity":"Native to MegaETH; underpins the chain''s native apps and fee model. Activity tied to MegaETH ecosystem growth. (Cite: coingecko.com/en/coins/megausd, defillama.com/stablecoin/megausd)","audits":"Inherits USDtb/BUIDL fund-grade reporting (BlackRock/Securitize); Ethena reserve attestations.","regulatory":"Leans on USDtb''s tokenized-Treasury backing (with Ethena/Anchorage GENIUS-Act line of sight). Not a MiCA EMT.","transparency":"Strong via BUIDL/USDtb disclosures; a comparatively transparent RWA-backed L2 stablecoin.","yield":"Reserve yield is redirected to fund the MegaETH sequencer (network subsidy) rather than paid directly to holders — a novel ''yield-to-network'' model.","comparison":"vs USDC/USDT: a chain-native stablecoin whose reserve yield subsidizes L2 fees; niche = MegaETH ecosystem money. Weakness: dependent on MegaETH adoption and Ethena/USDtb rails; redeems to USDtb, not fiat.","future":"Grows with MegaETH ecosystem traction; the fee-subsidy model is a genuine differentiator for aligning chain and users. Risk: MegaETH adoption dependence, rate-sensitivity of the subsidy, and reliance on Ethena/BUIDL.","risks":"MegaETH ecosystem/adoption dependence, reliance on USDtb/BUIDL, indirect (USDtb) redemption, interest-rate sensitivity of the sequencer subsidy.","notes":"Note the USDM naming overlap with Mountain Protocol''s USDM — this entry is MegaETH''s USDm (MegaUSD). Built on Ethena Stablecoin-as-a-Service.","sources":["https://www.megaeth.com/blog-news/megaeth-introduces-usdm","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/megausd","https://defillama.com/stablecoin/megausd"]}','["https://www.megaeth.com/blog-news/megaeth-introduces-usdm","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/megausd","https://defillama.com/stablecoin/megausd"]','2026-07-08 19:28:41');
INSERT INTO "risk_flags" ("slug","entity_type","entity_name","level","summary","evidence","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('chain:Tron','chain','Tron','high','SEC charged founder Justin Sun with fraud, unregistered securities sales, and extensive wash trading (settled 2026 with $10M penalty, no admission of wrongdoing).','In March 2023 the SEC sued Justin Sun and his companies (Tron Foundation, BitTorrent Foundation, Rainberry) alleging: (1) unregistered offer/sale of TRX and BTT; (2) fraudulent market manipulation via wash trading — the SEC alleges Sun directed employees to conduct 600,000+ wash trades of TRX (4.5M-7.4M TRX daily, Apr 2018-Feb 2019) between two accounts he controlled to fake active trading; (3) undisclosed paid celebrity promotion. Eight celebrities were also charged. In March 2026 the case settled: Rainberry Inc. pays a $10M civil penalty and accepts an injunction; claims against Sun personally dismissed without admission of wrongdoing.','["https://www.sec.gov/newsroom/press-releases/2023-59","https://www.coindesk.com/policy/2023/03/22/tron-founder-justin-sun-sued-by-us-sec-on-securities-market-manipulation-charges","https://www.sec.gov/files/litigation/complaints/2023/comp-pr2023-59.pdf"]','2026-07-08 17:43:19');
INSERT INTO "risk_flags" ("slug","entity_type","entity_name","level","summary","evidence","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('chain:Gala','chain','Gala','high','Gala Games co-founders sued each other in 2023 over an alleged $130M token theft; co-founder Wright Thurston was separately sued by the SEC over an alleged fake crypto-mining scheme (Green United).','In Aug 2023, Gala (Blockchain Game Partners) co-founders filed dueling Utah lawsuits. CEO Eric Schiermeyer''s derivative complaint alleges co-founder Wright Thurston and his firm True North United stole ~8.6 billion GALA tokens (~$130M) in Feb 2021 — more than the total circulating GALA at the time — moving them through 43 wallets and selling via ''obfuscatory transactions.'' Thurston countersued alleging Schiermeyer wasted company assets (incl. a $5M corporate jet). Separately, in March 2023 the SEC sued Thurston, True North, and his company Green United for allegedly selling investments in a fake crypto-mining scheme where the promised GREEN token allegedly did not function as represented. All are allegations pending litigation.','["https://www.theblock.co/post/248897/gala-games-ceo-sues-co-founder-alleging-130-million-theft-pattern-of-deception","https://decrypt.co/154848/gala-games-co-founders-sue-each-other-alleging-corporate-waste-130-million-theft","https://cointelegraph.com/news/gala-games-founders-sue-court-token-theft-corporate-waste"]','2026-07-08 17:43:24');
INSERT INTO "risk_flags" ("slug","entity_type","entity_name","level","summary","evidence","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('chain:Ronin','chain','Ronin','caution','Ronin (Axie Infinity''s Sky Mavis sidechain) suffered a $625M bridge exploit in March 2022, attributed by US authorities to the OFAC-sanctioned, North Korea-linked Lazarus Group.','In March 2022, attackers compromised 5 of Ronin''s 9 validator keys (via social engineering / a gas-free RPC backdoor) and forged withdrawals of 173,600 ETH and 25.5M USDC (~$625M) — one of the largest crypto hacks ever. The breach went unnoticed for six days. In April 2022 the US Treasury (OFAC) and blockchain analysts (Elliptic, Chainalysis) tied the sanctioned wallet to North Korea''s Lazarus Group; funds were laundered through Tornado Cash. This is a security/counterparty concern, not founder misconduct — Sky Mavis has since expanded validators and reimbursed users. Flagged as caution due to the scale and the centralized-validator single-point-of-failure it exposed.','["https://www.coindesk.com/tech/2022/03/29/axie-infinitys-ronin-network-suffers-625m-exploit","https://www.coindesk.com/policy/2022/04/14/us-officials-tie-north-korean-hacker-group-to-axies-ronin-exploit","https://techcrunch.com/2022/04/15/us-officials-link-north-korean-lazarus-hackers-to-625m-axie-infinity-crypto-theft/"]','2026-07-08 17:43:34');
INSERT INTO "risk_flags" ("slug","entity_type","entity_name","level","summary","evidence","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('chain:Blast','chain','Blast','caution','Blur founder ''Pacman'' (Tieshun Roquerre)''s L2 drew heavy criticism for collecting $2B+ into a centralized 3/5 multisig before any chain existed, pyramid-like referral mechanics, and a disappointing airdrop; some early depositors called him a ''serial rug entrepreneur.''','Blast opened deposits Nov 2023 — ~3 months before mainnet — taking ETH/stablecoins into a smart contract controlled by a 3/5 multisig with no live chain, no fraud proofs, and no exit until Feb 29, 2024. Critics (Polygon''s Mihailo Bjelic and Jarrod Watts, Delphi''s Gabriel Shapiro) flagged that funds were locked with no working product; even lead investor Paradigm publicly distanced itself. Four of five multisig signers were reportedly funded by the same wallet (single-point-of-failure concern). The referral/points system was likened to a pyramid scheme. After the June 2024 airdrop, TVL and activity dropped; one $50M depositor received ~$100k and publicly called the founder a ''serial rug entrepreneur.'' These are allegations/criticisms; no confirmed misappropriation of funds.','["https://crypto.news/how-blast-gained-the-communitys-attention-and-why-is-it-called-a-scam/","https://www.ccn.com/news/what-is-blast-l2-400m-multisig-concerns/","https://www.theblock.co/post/263926/blur-ethereum-layer-2-blast-live-20-million-raise"]','2026-07-08 17:43:44');
INSERT INTO "risk_flags" ("slug","entity_type","entity_name","level","summary","evidence","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('chain:Sui','chain','Sui','caution','Sui faced widely reported (and Foundation-denied) allegations of insiders selling ~$400M during an Oct 2024 run-up; the legitimate, unresolved concern is highly concentrated insider/VC/reserve token supply with dilutive unlocks running to 2030.','In Oct 2024 an on-chain analyst alleged ''Sui insiders'' sold ~$400M in tokens during a price rally. The Sui Foundation formally denied it, stating no Foundation/Mysten Labs employees, founders, or ML investors sold that amount and attributing the flagged wallet to a locked-and-compliant infrastructure partner (redemptions of 82.6M+ SUI to exchanges since June, per analyst @defioasis). Beyond the disputed claim, the structural concern is that a large majority of SUI supply is allocated to insiders, VCs (Series A/B), the foundation, and reserves — ~52% under ''Released After 2030'' — with ~64M SUI/month unlocking, creating persistent sell pressure (a prior $63.4M unlock reportedly triggered a ~9% price slide). No proven wrongdoing; flagged for the insider-selling allegations and concentrated/dilutive tokenomics.','["https://x.com/SuiNetwork/status/1845890142906863865","https://tokenomist.ai/sui/tokenomics","https://www.kucoin.com/blog/sui-price-prediction-for-late-2026-can-post-vesting-tokenomics-trigger-a-breakout"]','2026-07-08 17:43:58');
INSERT INTO "risk_flags" ("slug","entity_type","entity_name","level","summary","evidence","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('nft:Milady Maker','nft','Milady Maker','high','Milady''s founder ''Charlotte Fang'' was doxxed in 2022 as being behind the ''Miya'' persona linked to racist/extremist content and the ''Kaliacc'' (Kali Yuga Accelerationism) group; founders later traded accusations in dueling lawsuits.','In May 2022, developer 0xngmi published a thread alleging pseudonymous founder Charlotte Fang was ''Miya,'' a persona tied to racist, antisemitic, and homophobic content and to ''Kaliacc'' (Kali Yuga Accelerationism), a group accused of pro-anorexia/self-harm and suicide-cult associations. Fang stepped down (temporarily) as prices tumbled after self-doxxing. The collection is repeatedly described by mainstream outlets (CoinDesk, CoinMarketCap, Fast Company) as one of the most controversial NFT projects. Separately, Remilia/Milady founders later fought dueling lawsuits, with NFTs losing ~40% value amid the dispute. Concerns are reputational/founder-conduct; not a financial rug.','["https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2022/05/24/milady-nft-prices-tumble-after-creator-doxxes-self-as-person-behind-controversial-miya","https://www.fastcompany.com/90756392/inside-remilia-corporation-the-anti-woke-dao-behind-the-doomed-milady-maker-nft","https://www.dlnews.com/articles/people-culture/milady-nfts-lose-a-third-of-their-value-as-founders-fight/"]','2026-07-08 17:44:07');
INSERT INTO "risk_flags" ("slug","entity_type","entity_name","level","summary","evidence","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('nft:Azuki','nft','Azuki','high','Azuki founder ''Zagabond'' (Alex Xu) admitted abandoning three prior projects; the June 2023 ''Elementals'' launch (~$38M raised, near-identical art) is widely alleged to be a soft rug, prompting a DAO clawback attempt for ~20,000 ETH.','In May 2022 pseudonymous founder Zagabond published a blog post admitting involvement in three abandoned/''rug'' projects (CryptoPhunks, Tendies, CryptoZunks); Azuki''s floor dropped on the reveal. In June 2023 the ''Elementals'' collection sold out in ~15 min raising ~$38M, but holders complained the art was near-identical to originals; the team reportedly moved 20,000 ETH from the wallet shortly after mint. Azuki''s floor fell from ~9.6 to ~6.25 ETH. An ''AzukiDAO'' proposed legal action and a ~20,000 ETH ($39M) clawback (though the DAO''s own legitimacy was questioned — contract minted 2 days prior). CryptoPhunks'' founder ''Pauly'' publicly alleged Zagabond obtained ~$3M USDC by fraudulent means. Allegations remain unproven; described by CoinDesk and others as an admitted-serial-abandoner / alleged soft rug.','["https://www.coindesk.com/business/2022/05/10/azuki-nft-founder-admits-to-abandoning-past-projects","https://blockchain.news/news/Azuki-Community-Demands-Legal-Action-Against-Founder-Zagabond-Over-Alleged-Rug-Pull-and-Calls-for-20000-ETH-Refund-76f45ab2-5bb7-4b1a-a608-aaae141810ac","https://nftevening.com/azuki-elementals-fallout-dao-proposes-clawing-back-20eth-from-zagabond-as-cryptophunks-founder-threatens-legal-actions/"]','2026-07-08 17:44:21');
INSERT INTO "risk_flags" ("slug","entity_type","entity_name","level","summary","evidence","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('nft:CloneX','nft','CloneX','high','Nike wound down RTFKT (the studio behind CloneX) by Jan 2025; investors filed a class-action calling it a ''soft rug pull,'' and a Cloudflare hosting lapse temporarily broke ~19,800 CloneX images.','Nike announced Dec 2, 2024 it would wind down RTFKT (the Nike-owned studio behind the CloneX collection, made with artist Takashi Murakami) by end of Jan 2025. On April 25, 2025 investors led by Jagdeep Cheema filed a class-action in Brooklyn federal court alleging Nike promoted the NFTs as valuable then ''pulled the rug,'' seeking $5M+ under consumer-protection laws (NY, CA, FL, OR). Separately, on ~April 24, 2025, ~19,800 CloneX avatars temporarily displayed a Cloudflare TOS-violation notice instead of artwork after RTFKT''s plan was downgraded — highlighting off-chain image dependency. Nike later sold RTFKT (Dec 2025). Flagged for the abandonment/''soft rug'' lawsuit and hosting-fragility concerns; allegations unproven.','["https://thedefiant.io/news/nfts-and-web3/class-action-lawsuit-calls-nike-s-shutdown-of-rtfkt-nft-studio-a-soft-rug-pull","https://www.techspot.com/news/107717-nike-faces-5-million-lawsuit-after-cloudflare-outage.html","https://nftplazas.com/nike-to-close-rtfkt-operations/"]','2026-07-08 17:44:29');
INSERT INTO "risk_flags" ("slug","entity_type","entity_name","level","summary","evidence","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('nft:DeGods','nft','DeGods','caution','Founder Frank DeGods (Rohun Vora) is repeatedly accused of abandoning multiple projects, including memecoins he promoted as part of an influencer group; he resigned as CEO in May 2025, immediately followed by a disputed ''wallet hack'' some suspected was a staged exit.','DeGods executed two chain migrations (Solana -> Ethereum in 2023; y00ts off Polygon, returning a $3M Polygon grant) amid sharp floor drops and ''fumbling'' apologies from Frank. In Jan 2025 he was accused of ''abandon[ing] 3 projects'' and, per MisakaTrades, abandoning several memecoins he promoted as part of the ''LA Vape Cabal'' influencer group. He resigned as CEO May 12, 2025; days later his wallet was allegedly ''hacked'' and 16 DeGods sold (~108 SOL), which some community members suspected was a staged exit. Frank stated he never did anything illegal and there were no investigations. The DUST token and y00ts were sunset in a contested ERC-404 pivot to $DEGOD. Concerns are founder-track-record/abandonment; no proven fraud.','["https://www.theblock.co/post/353994/frank-degods-announces-retirement-from-popular-y00ts-and-degods-nft-projects","https://beincrypto.com/degods-community-nft-sale-ceo-resignation/","https://decrypt.co/152866/degods-co-founder-departs-amid-falling-nft-prices"]','2026-07-08 17:44:42');
INSERT INTO "risk_flags" ("slug","entity_type","entity_name","level","summary","evidence","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('nft:Moonbirds','nft','Moonbirds','caution','Founder Kevin Rose sold ~$1.2M of PROOF/Grails NFTs just weeks after selling PROOF to Yuga Labs (Feb 2024), then deleted posts amid a community backlash calling it a betrayal; Yuga later offloaded the collection as a distressed asset.','Kevin Rose''s PROOF Collective (Moonbirds) was acquired by Yuga Labs in Feb 2024. Within ~2 weeks, Rose sold ~$1.2M of NFTs including PROOF Grails works (e.g., Fidenza 531, XCOPY''s ''When Airdrop?''), drawing heavy criticism from holders who called it opportunistic given his prior ''long-term value'' messaging; he then deleted the posts. Yuga also revoked Moonbirds'' CC0 license post-acquisition (itself contentious). Floor fell from a ~$115k peak to ~$3k at acquisition and later to ~0.3 ETH. In 2025 Yuga sold the Moonbirds IP to Orange Cap Games in what was described as a distressed-asset sale. Concerns are insider-selling optics/founder conduct; no illegality alleged.','["https://nftplazas.com/kevin-rose-sold-nfts/","https://blockworks.co/news/yuga-labs-moonbirds-sell","https://decrypt.co/217906/yuga-labs-acquires-moonbirds-proof"]','2026-07-08 17:44:50');
INSERT INTO "risk_flags" ("slug","entity_type","entity_name","level","summary","evidence","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('nft:y00ts','nft','y00ts','caution','y00ts (DeLabs, founder Frank DeGods) executed two rapid chain migrations in one year (Solana -> Polygon -> Ethereum), returning a $3M Polygon grant; later the collection was effectively sunset when DeLabs pivoted to the $DEGOD token, tying it to the same founder-track-record concerns as DeGods.','y00ts launched on Solana, migrated to Polygon in early 2023 (accepting a $3M Polygon Labs grant to fund team expansion), then in Aug 2023 announced a second migration to Ethereum — returning the $3M grant — just ~4 months later. Polygon co-founder Sandeep Nailwal stayed publicly supportive and redeployed the funds, and the grant return was viewed as commendable; some analysts were cynical about the motive (''Frank saw Rollbit 9x after ETH migration''). y00ts was later wound down as DeLabs sunset $DUST and pivoted to $DEGOD (ERC-404). Same founder (Rohun ''Frank'' Vora) carries documented accusations of abandoning prior projects (see DeGods flag). No proven fraud; flagged for migration churn and shared founder track record.','["https://www.coindesk.com/web3/2023/08/10/y00ts-nft-collection-is-migrating-to-ethereum-after-accepting-3m-grant-from-polygon","https://www.theblock.co/post/244060/polygon-based-y00ts-nfts-to-migrate-to-ethereum-return-3-million-grant","https://cointelegraph.com/news/nft-y00ts-returns-polygon-grant-migrates-to-ethereum"]','2026-07-08 17:46:15');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('usa','United States','North America','country','{"adoption_rank":4,"adoption":"4th on Chainalysis 2024 index; largest market globally at ~$1.3T on-chain value received (Jul 2023-Jun 2024), ~22.5% of global activity. Heavily institutional — spot Bitcoin ETFs launched Jan 2024 drove large institutional-sized transfers.","regulation":"No single federal framework; SEC/CFTC split jurisdiction. GENIUS Act (2025) created a federal stablecoin regime. State-level money transmitter licensing (e.g. NY BitLicense). Spot BTC and ETH ETFs approved.","upcoming_regulation":"Market-structure legislation (CLARITY Act) advancing to divide SEC/CFTC oversight. BITCOIN Act (S.954) proposed authorizing acquisition of up to 1M BTC. ARMA Act would codify the reserve into law.","gov_holdings":"Yes — Strategic Bitcoin Reserve established by Executive Order 14233 (signed Mar 6, 2025), capitalized with forfeited BTC and cannot be sold. Holdings grew from ~200,000 BTC initially to ~328,372 BTC (~$21B) by early 2026 — the largest known sovereign BTC holder.","sentiment":"Sharply pro-crypto under the Trump administration; broad public awareness, partisan divide on regulation.","notable":"First spot Bitcoin ETF approvals (Jan 2024); federal Strategic Bitcoin Reserve (2025); GENIUS Act stablecoin law (2025).","use_cases":"Institutional investment (ETFs), trading, DeFi, stablecoin settlement.","sources":["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2025/03/11/2025-03992/establishment-of-the-strategic-bitcoin-reserve-and-united-states-digital-asset-stockpile","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._Strategic_Bitcoin_Reserve"]}','["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2025/03/11/2025-03992/establishment-of-the-strategic-bitcoin-reserve-and-united-states-digital-asset-stockpile","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._Strategic_Bitcoin_Reserve"]','2026-07-08 17:42:27');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('india','India','Asia-Pacific','country','{"adoption_rank":1,"adoption":"#1 on Chainalysis 2024 index (held top spot from 2023). Ranks first in centralized services and retail, 2nd in retail DeFi, 3rd in DeFi value. Massive grassroots retail adoption despite punitive taxes.","regulation":"Legal but heavily taxed, no comprehensive bill. 30% flat tax on VDA gains (Sec 115BBH, +4% cess = ~31.2%) plus 1% TDS (Sec 194S) since Jul 2022; no loss offset. 18% GST on exchange services added mid-2025. FIU-IND registration mandatory for exchanges.","upcoming_regulation":"No dedicated crypto bill yet — ''tax first, define later'' approach. Planning to adopt OECD CARF by April 2027 for automatic offshore data sharing. Schedule VDA reporting mandatory from FY2025-26.","gov_holdings":"No known state crypto holdings.","sentiment":"Strong grassroots enthusiasm; heavy tax burden pushes users to offshore platforms. Government cautious/skeptical (RBI favors digital rupee CBDC).","notable":"2020 Supreme Court struck down RBI banking ban (IAMAI v RBI). WazirX hack (2024). Consistently tops adoption index.","use_cases":"Retail trading, DeFi, remittances, savings/hedge.","sources":["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://news.bitcoin.com/india-nigeria-indonesia-lead-chainalysis-2024-crypto-adoption-index/","https://cleartax.in/s/cryptocurrency-taxation-guide"]}','["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://news.bitcoin.com/india-nigeria-indonesia-lead-chainalysis-2024-crypto-adoption-index/","https://cleartax.in/s/cryptocurrency-taxation-guide"]','2026-07-08 17:42:46');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('nigeria','Nigeria','Sub-Saharan Africa','country','{"adoption_rank":2,"adoption":"#2 on Chainalysis 2024 index. Africa''s largest crypto market with intense grassroots use driven by naira devaluation and inflation. Strong P2P and stablecoin usage.","regulation":"Legalized/regulated after a reversal. CBN lifted its 2021 bank ban on crypto in Dec 2023. SEC introduced the Accelerated Regulatory Incentive Programme (ARIP) and licenses local exchanges; SEC granted first VASP licenses to Busha and Quidax (2025). Investments & Securities Act 2025 formally recognizes crypto assets.","upcoming_regulation":"Ongoing SEC licensing rollout; naira removed from P2P platforms; telecom-level access restrictions have kept some major exchanges offline pending full compliance.","gov_holdings":"No known state crypto holdings.","sentiment":"Very high grassroots enthusiasm, especially among youth; government historically wary (Binance executives detained 2024) but shifting to regulation.","notable":"2021 CBN bank ban then 2023 reversal; 2024 Binance standoff and executive detention; eNaira CBDC struggled with low uptake.","use_cases":"P2P trading, stablecoin dollar access, remittances, inflation hedge.","sources":["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://www.theafricareport.com/360383/nigerias-crypto-comeback-sec-approves-local-exchanges-post-binance-ban/","https://www.ibanet.org/overview-of-cryptocurrency-regulatory-landscape-nigeria"]}','["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://www.theafricareport.com/360383/nigerias-crypto-comeback-sec-approves-local-exchanges-post-binance-ban/","https://www.ibanet.org/overview-of-cryptocurrency-regulatory-landscape-nigeria"]','2026-07-08 17:42:56');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('indonesia','Indonesia','Asia-Pacific','country','{"adoption_rank":3,"adoption":"#3 on Chainalysis 2024 index, up 4 places YoY. Highest year-over-year growth in CSAO at nearly 200% and highest crypto value received in the region at ~$157.1B. ~8-9% of population participates.","regulation":"Trading legal, treated as a commodity. Oversight moved from commodities regulator Bappebti to the financial authority OJK in Jan 2025. ICO issuance banned since 2019. Exchanges must show Sharia compliance. Crypto banned as a means of payment.","upcoming_regulation":"OJK building out fuller VASP supervision and investor-protection rules under the P2SK financial-sector law.","gov_holdings":"No known state crypto holdings.","sentiment":"High retail trading enthusiasm; regulators focused on consumer protection and Islamic-finance compatibility.","notable":"Fastest-growing major market in 2024; integration of crypto trading with Sharia-compliance requirements is distinctive.","use_cases":"Retail trading/investment; token issuance blocked so little domestic project origination.","sources":["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://www.lightspark.com/knowledge/is-crypto-legal-in-vietnam","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Legality_of_cryptocurrency_by_country_or_territory"]}','["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://www.lightspark.com/knowledge/is-crypto-legal-in-vietnam","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Legality_of_cryptocurrency_by_country_or_territory"]','2026-07-08 17:43:08');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('vietnam','Vietnam','Asia-Pacific','country','{"adoption_rank":5,"adoption":"Top-5 on Chainalysis 2024 index; consistently among the world leaders in grassroots adoption. Over 17 million Vietnamese (~18% of population) hold digital assets per TripleA.","regulation":"Historic shift in 2025: Law on Digital Technology Industry (passed by National Assembly Jun 16, 2025, effective Jan 1, 2026) recognizes crypto as legal property under the Civil Code. Resolution 05/2025/NQ-CP (Sep 2025) launched a 5-year controlled pilot (2025-2030). Using crypto for payments remains illegal.","upcoming_regulation":"Pilot exchange licensing: only Vietnamese firms with ≥VND 10,000bn capital, ≥65% institutional ownership, foreign ownership capped at 49%. AML/CTF and investor-protection rules being built out.","gov_holdings":"No known state crypto holdings.","sentiment":"Very high grassroots enthusiasm; government moving from ambiguity to formal, cautious recognition.","notable":"Went from no legal framework to formally recognizing digital assets as property in 2025 — a landmark Southeast Asian move.","use_cases":"Trading, remittances, DeFi, gaming/play-to-earn (Axie Infinity founded in Vietnam).","sources":["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://chambers.com/articles/vietnam-formally-recognises-digital-assets-under-new-law","https://www.vietnam-briefing.com/news/vietnam-licensing-regime-cryptocurrency-exchanges-digital-economy.html/"]}','["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://chambers.com/articles/vietnam-formally-recognises-digital-assets-under-new-law","https://www.vietnam-briefing.com/news/vietnam-licensing-regime-cryptocurrency-exchanges-digital-economy.html/"]','2026-07-08 17:43:18');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('philippines','Philippines','Asia-Pacific','country','{"adoption_rank":8,"adoption":"Top-10 on Chainalysis 2024 index. ~10% of population uses crypto, heavily driven by remittances from overseas Filipino workers — crypto rails cut transfer fees to under 1% vs 5-7% traditional.","regulation":"Legal and regulated. Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas (BSP) licenses Virtual Asset Service Providers; SEC oversees securities-like tokens. Exchanges must register, report suspicious transactions, secure customer assets.","upcoming_regulation":"SEC finalizing Crypto-Asset Service Provider (CASP) rules; tightening on scams and unregistered offerings.","gov_holdings":"No known state crypto holdings.","sentiment":"High retail enthusiasm; play-to-earn culture strong. Scams/Ponzi schemes a recurring problem.","notable":"Global epicenter of play-to-earn gaming (Axie Infinity boom 2021). Remittance-driven adoption. Repeated crypto Ponzi scandals.","use_cases":"Remittances, play-to-earn gaming, retail trading.","sources":["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://cryptoforinnovation.org/crypto-in-nigeria-surge-in-adoption-and-regulatory-shifts/","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Legality_of_cryptocurrency_by_country_or_territory"]}','["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://cryptoforinnovation.org/crypto-in-nigeria-surge-in-adoption-and-regulatory-shifts/","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Legality_of_cryptocurrency_by_country_or_territory"]','2026-07-08 17:43:30');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('brazil','Brazil','Latin America','country','{"adoption_rank":8,"adoption":"Top-10 on Chainalysis 2024 index; rose to 5th globally in the 2025 index. ~25M Brazilians hold or transact in crypto. Market moves ~$6-8B/month, with stablecoins ~90% of volume (Receita Federal data).","regulation":"Legal Framework for Virtual Assets (Law 14,478/2022) with the Central Bank (BCB) as regulator. Comprehensive BCB VASP licensing framework takes effect Feb 2, 2026, integrating crypto firms into the financial system — among the world''s strictest. Stablecoins treated as foreign-exchange operations; algorithmic (unbacked) stablecoins and privacy coins (Monero, Zcash) banned from VASPs.","upcoming_regulation":"Bill 4308/2024 advancing to ban algorithmic stablecoins; BCB banned crypto/stablecoin settlement in cross-border payments (2026). Drex CBDC in pilot.","gov_holdings":"No confirmed sovereign reserve (a strategic BTC reserve bill, RESBit, has been proposed but not enacted).","sentiment":"High mainstream adoption; regulators pragmatic but tightening.","notable":"Stablecoin-dominated market; one of the most strictly regulated frameworks globally from 2026; advanced Drex CBDC/tokenization pilots.","use_cases":"Stablecoin dollar savings/payments, trading, cross-border transfers.","sources":["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/brazil-crypto-asset-regulatory-framework-2025/","https://www.forbes.com/sites/astanley/2025/11/19/incumbents-win-big-whats-inside-brazils-new-vasp-regulations/","https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/"]}','["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/brazil-crypto-asset-regulatory-framework-2025/","https://www.forbes.com/sites/astanley/2025/11/19/incumbents-win-big-whats-inside-brazils-new-vasp-regulations/","https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/"]','2026-07-08 17:43:41');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('ukraine','Ukraine','Europe','country','{"adoption_rank":6,"adoption":"Top-10 on Chainalysis 2024 index (historically ranked #1 grassroots). Over 12.7% of the population owns crypto. Wartime crypto donations raised tens of millions of dollars for defense and aid.","regulation":"Crypto legalized in principle by the ''On Virtual Assets'' law signed Mar 16, 2022, but full regime pending implementing tax/regulatory rules co-developed with the NBU and IMF.","upcoming_regulation":"2025 comprehensive framework aligning with EU MiCA; proposed 18% income tax plus 5% military tax on crypto-to-fiat gains. Draft legislation would authorize the central bank to hold Bitcoin as part of national reserves.","gov_holdings":"No formal reserve yet, but legislation under consideration would authorize a national Bitcoin reserve. Government has received and held donated crypto during the war.","sentiment":"Strongly pro-crypto; seen as a tool of financial resilience and wartime fundraising.","notable":"Global model for transparent wartime crypto fundraising (2022 invasion); ~$70M raised for defense/aid; potential national BTC reserve.","use_cases":"Donations/fundraising, savings, cross-border transfers amid war.","sources":["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://cointelegraph.com/news/ukraine-crypto-legalization-2025-no-tax-breaks","https://beincrypto.com/ukraine-crypto-regulation-2025/"]}','["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://cointelegraph.com/news/ukraine-crypto-legalization-2025-no-tax-breaks","https://beincrypto.com/ukraine-crypto-regulation-2025/"]','2026-07-08 17:43:54');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('russia','Russia','Europe','country','{"adoption_rank":6,"adoption":"Climbed from 13th to a top-6 position on the Chainalysis 2024 index, driven by using crypto for cross-border payments amid sanctions. Third globally in Bitcoin mining hashrate (~14%+).","regulation":"Ambiguous. Crypto cannot be used for domestic payments, but mining was legalized by Law No. 221-FZ (signed Aug 8, 2024) with heavy reporting to financial-monitoring and security services. Central bank authorized an experimental regime for crypto in cross-border trade.","upcoming_regulation":"Expanding state-controlled crypto/stablecoin rails and digital ruble CBDC for sanctions-resistant settlement. Regional mining bans (energy shortages) from Dec 2024, including occupied Ukrainian territories and seasonal Siberia bans.","gov_holdings":"No transparent official reserve; state pursues crypto infrastructure for sanctions evasion rather than a declared BTC treasury.","sentiment":"State pivoted from hostility to strategic use; public adoption tied to sanctions workarounds.","notable":"From trying to ''kill Bitcoin'' (2014) to building state stablecoin rails and mining farms to survive sanctions; digital ruble program.","use_cases":"Cross-border payments/sanctions evasion, mining, oil-trade settlement.","sources":["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://therecord.media/russia-to-ban-crypto-mining-energy-shortages","https://daviscenter.fas.harvard.edu/insights/blockchain-statecraft-russias-secret-war-financial-sovereignty"]}','["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://therecord.media/russia-to-ban-crypto-mining-energy-shortages","https://daviscenter.fas.harvard.edu/insights/blockchain-statecraft-russias-secret-war-financial-sovereignty"]','2026-07-08 17:44:05');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('china','China','Asia-Pacific','country','{"adoption_rank":20,"adoption":"~20th on Chainalysis 2024 index despite the ban. Grey-market activity persists: OTC volumes estimated ~$75B in the first nine months of 2024; still ~14% of global Bitcoin hashrate (3rd globally).","regulation":"Effectively banned. Mainland banned exchanges (2017), then in Sep 2021 the PBOC and regulators declared all crypto transactions illegal and banned mining (Jun 2021). Hong Kong (separate jurisdiction) runs a licensed VASP regime under the SFC/HKMA and passed stablecoin legislation (2025), though Beijing blocked Ant/JD.com from issuing HK stablecoins.","upcoming_regulation":"Continued mainland crackdowns (2025 stablecoin restrictions); contrast with Hong Kong''s expanding licensed framework as a controlled experiment.","gov_holdings":"Reportedly seized ~194,000 BTC from the 2019 PlusToken Ponzi; on-chain analysts suggest much of it was liquidated — current holdings ambiguous and unconfirmed.","sentiment":"Officially hostile on the mainland; persistent underground demand. Hong Kong openly pro-innovation.","notable":"2021 comprehensive ban triggered global mining migration; PlusToken seizure; digital yuan (e-CNY) CBDC; Hong Kong as the ''sanctioned'' on-ramp.","use_cases":"OTC/grey-market trading, mining (residual), capital flight; Hong Kong licensed trading and ETFs.","sources":["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Legality_of_cryptocurrency_by_country_or_territory","https://finance.yahoo.com/news/china-doubles-down-crypto-ban-134205196.html"]}','["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Legality_of_cryptocurrency_by_country_or_territory","https://finance.yahoo.com/news/china-doubles-down-crypto-ban-134205196.html"]','2026-07-08 17:44:19');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('uk','United Kingdom','Europe','country','{"adoption_rank":12,"adoption":"12th on Chainalysis 2024 index. Large, mature market skewing institutional and retail investment; strong Western Europe growth driven by the ETF cycle.","regulation":"Bringing crypto within the existing FSMA financial-services perimeter (rather than a MiCA-style standalone regime). FCA is the regulator. Crypto financial-promotions rules in force since Oct 2023. Property (Digital Assets) Bill clarifies crypto as personal property.","upcoming_regulation":"Financial Services and Markets Act 2000 (Cryptoassets) Regulations 2026 enacted Feb 4, 2026; full regime expected to come into force Oct 25, 2027. FCA published final rules Jun 30, 2026. Stablecoin issuance/custody framework (CP25/14).","gov_holdings":"No strategic reserve; UK law enforcement holds large seized BTC (e.g. tens of billions in a 2018 fraud seizure) that the Treasury has considered selling.","sentiment":"Cautious-but-constructive; government aims to make the UK a crypto hub while prioritizing consumer protection.","notable":"Financial-promotions crackdown; one of the largest BTC seizures in history held by the Met Police; phased FSMA expansion.","use_cases":"Investment/trading, stablecoins, institutional custody.","sources":["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://www.fca.org.uk/firms/new-regime-cryptoasset-regulation","https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/regulatory-regime-for-cryptoassets-regulated-activities-draft-si-and-policy-note/future-financial-services-regulatory-regime-for-cryptoassets-regulated-activities-policy-note-accessible"]}','["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://www.fca.org.uk/firms/new-regime-cryptoasset-regulation","https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/regulatory-regime-for-cryptoassets-regulated-activities-draft-si-and-policy-note/future-financial-services-regulatory-regime-for-cryptoassets-regulated-activities-policy-note-accessible"]','2026-07-08 17:44:30');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('germany','Germany','Europe','country','{"adoption_rank":null,"adoption":"Largest EU economy and a leading MiCA-licensing hub; institutional and retail investment. Germany led the EU in early MiCA CASP authorizations under BaFin.","regulation":"Fully under EU MiCA (stablecoin titles from Jun 30, 2024; full CASP regime from Dec 30, 2024). BaFin is the national regulator; domestic implementation via the Kryptomärkteaufsichtsgesetz (KMAG) and the Dec 2024 Financial Markets Digitalisation Act. Notably investor-friendly tax: private holdings sold after 12 months are tax-free (FIFO).","upcoming_regulation":"MiCA grandfathering period runs to Jul 1, 2026 (Germany chose a shorter 12-month window). CARF/DAC8 tax reporting from Jan 1, 2026 (first exchanges 2027).","gov_holdings":"No reserve; the state of Saxony notably sold ~50,000 seized BTC (~$3B) in mid-2024, a widely criticized early sale.","sentiment":"Institutionally cautious; some industry complaints that BaFin applies MiCA more strictly than peers, pushing firms to Vienna/Lisbon.","notable":"Saxony''s 2024 sell-off of ~50,000 seized BTC; EU-leading MiCA license count; famously long-term-holder-friendly tax rule.","use_cases":"Long-term investment/HODLing, institutional custody, trading.","sources":["https://www.esma.europa.eu/esmas-activities/digital-finance-and-innovation/markets-crypto-assets-regulation-mica","https://www.globallegalinsights.com/practice-areas/blockchain-cryptocurrency-laws-and-regulations/germany/","https://tangem.com/en/blog/post/crypto-taxes-in-germany/"]}','["https://www.esma.europa.eu/esmas-activities/digital-finance-and-innovation/markets-crypto-assets-regulation-mica","https://www.globallegalinsights.com/practice-areas/blockchain-cryptocurrency-laws-and-regulations/germany/","https://tangem.com/en/blog/post/crypto-taxes-in-germany/"]','2026-07-08 17:44:45');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('uae','United Arab Emirates','MENA','country','{"adoption_rank":null,"adoption":"Fast-growing hub with high per-capita activity, driven by expats, HNWIs and businesses relocating for regulatory clarity and zero personal income tax. Strong institutional and RWA-tokenization growth.","regulation":"Among the world''s most developed frameworks, multi-layered: onshore Dubai''s VARA (world''s first dedicated crypto regulator, est. 2022 under Law No. 4), federal SCA, plus free zones ADGM (FSRA) and DIFC (DFSA). VARA marketing regulations in force Oct 1, 2024 (penalties up to AED 50M or 15% of revenue). SCA-VARA cooperation agreement (Sep 2024).","upcoming_regulation":"Expanding RWA tokenization rules and stablecoin/payment-token frameworks (CBUAE Payment Token Services Regulation); continued license harmonization across authorities.","gov_holdings":"No declared sovereign BTC reserve, though state-linked entities and sovereign-wealth-adjacent players are active in digital-asset investment.","sentiment":"Strongly pro-crypto; positioned as a global magnet for crypto businesses.","notable":"World''s first standalone crypto regulator (VARA); major exchanges (Binance, others) and funds relocated to Dubai/Abu Dhabi; AED-backed stablecoin initiatives.","use_cases":"Business HQ/licensing, trading, RWA tokenization, wealth management.","sources":["https://www.vara.ae/en/","https://www.dlapiper.com/en/insights/publications/the-uae-cryptocurrency-and-digital-asset-regulation-series/2025/no-1the-regulatory-landscape-for-digital-assets-in-the-uae","https://www.forbes.com/sites/irinaheaver/2025/12/29/uae-crypto-regulations-2025-recap-vara-rwa-tokens-and-2026-outlook/"]}','["https://www.vara.ae/en/","https://www.dlapiper.com/en/insights/publications/the-uae-cryptocurrency-and-digital-asset-regulation-series/2025/no-1the-regulatory-landscape-for-digital-assets-in-the-uae","https://www.forbes.com/sites/irinaheaver/2025/12/29/uae-crypto-regulations-2025-recap-vara-rwa-tokens-and-2026-outlook/"]','2026-07-08 17:44:57');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('turkey','Turkey','MENA','country','{"adoption_rank":11,"adoption":"Around 11th on Chainalysis 2024 index and the world''s 4th-largest crypto market. Adoption driven by lira collapse — the currency lost ~60% and inflation peaked ~85.5% (2021-2023), pushing citizens into crypto as a store of value.","regulation":"Trading legal and now regulated: Law No. 7518 amending the Capital Markets Law (passed Jun 26, 2024, published Jul 2, 2024) created a licensing regime under the Capital Markets Board (CMB). Crypto is NOT legal tender — use as a payment method banned since Apr 2021 by the central bank (CBRT).","upcoming_regulation":"CMB licensing rollout (80+ firms including Binance, Bybit, OKX applied); 2% annual fee on trading income; measures aimed at exiting the FATF grey list; taxation framework under discussion.","gov_holdings":"No known state crypto holdings.","sentiment":"Very high grassroots demand as an inflation hedge; government regulating to control risks and satisfy FATF.","notable":"One of the highest ownership rates globally; inflation-driven adoption; 2021 payment ban; 2024 licensing law.","use_cases":"Inflation hedge, store of value, trading, dollar (stablecoin) access.","sources":["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://sumsub.com/blog/crypto-regulations-turkey/","https://cointelegraph.com/learn/articles/cryptocurrency-laws-and-regulations-in-turkey"]}','["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://sumsub.com/blog/crypto-regulations-turkey/","https://cointelegraph.com/learn/articles/cryptocurrency-laws-and-regulations-in-turkey"]','2026-07-08 17:45:10');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('argentina','Argentina','Latin America','country','{"adoption_rank":15,"adoption":"2nd in Latin America for crypto usage with over $91B in transactions (Jul 2023-Jun 2024). ~1/3 of Argentines use crypto for daily transactions; stablecoins act as a de facto parallel currency against a hyperinflating peso.","regulation":"Law 27,739 (2024) institutionalizes a crypto/VASP registry under securities regulator CNV, aligning with FATF standards, though BCRA has sent conflicting signals. President Milei is broadly pro-crypto and pro-''currency competition.''","upcoming_regulation":"CNV regulatory sandbox (2025) for tokenized securities; possible moves toward allowing transactions in any currency including Bitcoin.","gov_holdings":"No known state crypto holdings.","sentiment":"High grassroots adoption as an inflation refuge; enthusiasm dented by the LIBRA scandal.","notable":"$LIBRA memecoin scandal (Feb 2025) — Milei promoted a token that crashed; ~86% of buyers lost money (~$251M losses), triggering fraud probes and impeachment calls.","use_cases":"Stablecoin dollar savings, daily payments, inflation hedge, trading.","sources":["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://beincrypto.com/argentina-bitcoin-free-currency-circulation-president-milei/","https://www.forbes.com/sites/digital-assets/2025/02/24/argentinas-46-billion-crypto-scandal-largest-ever-crypto-theft/"]}','["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://beincrypto.com/argentina-bitcoin-free-currency-circulation-president-milei/","https://www.forbes.com/sites/digital-assets/2025/02/24/argentinas-46-billion-crypto-scandal-largest-ever-crypto-theft/"]','2026-07-08 17:45:19');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('el-salvador','El Salvador','Latin America','country','{"adoption_rank":null,"adoption":"Top-down, state-led rather than grassroots — real merchant/citizen usage stayed low despite the Bitcoin Law. The government (not the public) is the primary crypto actor.","regulation":"Reversed its landmark status. Became the first country to make Bitcoin legal tender (Sep 2021), but under a $1.4B IMF deal (Dec 2024) reformed the Bitcoin Law (effective ~Jan 30, 2025): removed mandatory merchant acceptance, dropped tax payment in BTC, ended the concept of BTC as ''currency,'' and is winding down the Chivo wallet. BTC acceptance now voluntary.","upcoming_regulation":"Continued IMF-program compliance (transparency, no net new public-sector BTC purchases); Digital Assets law framework remains for private VASPs.","gov_holdings":"Yes — Strategic Bitcoin Reserve Fund of ~6,250 BTC (~$740M as of early 2025). IMF states public-sector holdings are unchanged; reported increases reflect consolidation of existing government wallets.","sentiment":"Government (Bukele) remains publicly bullish; general public largely indifferent/skeptical, low everyday usage.","notable":"World''s first Bitcoin legal-tender adoption (2021) and its partial reversal under IMF pressure (2025); Bitcoin bonds and ''Bitcoin City'' plans.","use_cases":"State treasury reserve; limited retail/tourism payments; remittances (modest via Chivo).","sources":["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bitcoin_in_El_Salvador","https://www.forbes.com/sites/digital-assets/2025/02/28/el-salvadors-bitcoin-law-changes-to-secure-imf-funding/","https://www.imf.org/-/media/files/publications/cr/2025/english/1slvea2025001-print-pdf.pdf"]}','["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bitcoin_in_El_Salvador","https://www.forbes.com/sites/digital-assets/2025/02/28/el-salvadors-bitcoin-law-changes-to-secure-imf-funding/","https://www.imf.org/-/media/files/publications/cr/2025/english/1slvea2025001-print-pdf.pdf"]','2026-07-08 17:45:35');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('singapore','Singapore','Asia-Pacific','country','{"adoption_rank":75,"adoption":"75th on Chainalysis 2024 index (up from 77th) — small retail footprint but an outsized institutional and corporate hub for the region. Quality over quantity: a base for exchanges, funds and token projects.","regulation":"Clear, strict regime under the Monetary Authority of Singapore (MAS) via the Payment Services Act (Digital Payment Token licensing). MAS added stablecoin and digital-asset custody rules and restricts retail marketing/incentives. Digital Token Service Provider (DTSP) rules require even offshore-serving firms to be licensed (from mid-2025).","upcoming_regulation":"Ongoing tightening of retail access, DTSP licensing enforcement, and stablecoin single-currency-peg framework rollout.","gov_holdings":"No known state crypto holdings.","sentiment":"Pro-innovation but consumer-cautious; positioned as a trusted institutional hub, deliberately curbing retail speculation.","notable":"Reputation reset after 2022 collapses (Three Arrows Capital and Terraform Labs had Singapore ties); MAS''s ''clear but strict'' model widely cited.","use_cases":"Institutional/corporate HQ, licensed exchanges, tokenization pilots (Project Guardian).","sources":["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://www.mas.gov.sg/news?focus_areas=Crypto+Tokens&focus_areas=Digital+Currencies","https://sumsub.com/blog/singapore-crypto-regulations-all-you-need-to-know/"]}','["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://www.mas.gov.sg/news?focus_areas=Crypto+Tokens&focus_areas=Digital+Currencies","https://sumsub.com/blog/singapore-crypto-regulations-all-you-need-to-know/"]','2026-07-08 17:45:45');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('south-korea','South Korea','Asia-Pacific','country','{"adoption_rank":19,"adoption":"Ranked ~18-20 on Chainalysis 2024 index. Exceptionally active, retail-heavy trading culture — domestic exchanges (Upbit, Bithumb) see huge won-denominated volumes; the ''kimchi premium'' reflects strong local demand.","regulation":"Legal and regulated. The Virtual Asset User Protection Act took effect Jul 2024 (custody, insurance, market-abuse rules). Real-name banking accounts required; strict Travel Rule. Corporate/institutional trading historically restricted but being liberalized.","upcoming_regulation":"Phase-2 framework expanding institutional access, spot crypto ETFs under consideration, and stablecoin/won-stablecoin legislation debated in 2025. Crypto gains taxation repeatedly deferred.","gov_holdings":"No known state crypto holdings.","sentiment":"Very high retail enthusiasm (large young-investor base); regulators focused on investor protection after past scandals.","notable":"Home of Terra/LUNA (Do Kwon) whose 2022 collapse spurred the protection law; intense retail trading and altcoin speculation.","use_cases":"Retail spot trading/speculation, altcoins; growing institutional interest.","sources":["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://sumsub.com/blog/south-korea-crypto-and-travel-rule-regulations-all-you-need-to-know/","https://www.lightspark.com/knowledge/is-crypto-legal-in-south-korea"]}','["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://sumsub.com/blog/south-korea-crypto-and-travel-rule-regulations-all-you-need-to-know/","https://www.lightspark.com/knowledge/is-crypto-legal-in-south-korea"]','2026-07-08 17:46:02');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('japan','Japan','Asia-Pacific','country','{"adoption_rank":null,"adoption":"Mature, well-regulated market with steady but comparatively conservative retail participation. Early mover in exchange licensing after high-profile hacks.","regulation":"Legal and among the earliest regulated. Crypto is treated as legal property under the Payment Services Act (PSA); the Financial Services Agency (FSA) licenses exchanges. Strong custody/segregation rules post-Mt.Gox and Coincheck. Stablecoins regulated under 2023 PSA amendments.","upcoming_regulation":"Major planned shift moving crypto oversight from the PSA toward the Financial Instruments and Exchange Act (securities law) — tighter platform rules, potential lower flat tax (from up to ~55% miscellaneous income toward ~20%) and spot crypto ETFs under review.","gov_holdings":"No known state crypto holdings.","sentiment":"Cautious and safety-focused; strong consumer-protection culture after historic hacks.","notable":"Mt.Gox (2014) and Coincheck (2018) hacks shaped one of the world''s strictest exchange regimes; planned move to securities-law framework.","use_cases":"Regulated exchange trading, institutional custody, some payments.","sources":["https://www.tradingview.com/news/cointelegraph:6d9dc9bce094b:0-japan-plans-major-shift-as-crypto-moves-from-payments-to-securities-law/","https://law.asia/crypto-regulation-trends-hong-kong-japan-taiwan/","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Legality_of_cryptocurrency_by_country_or_territory"]}','["https://www.tradingview.com/news/cointelegraph:6d9dc9bce094b:0-japan-plans-major-shift-as-crypto-moves-from-payments-to-securities-law/","https://law.asia/crypto-regulation-trends-hong-kong-japan-taiwan/","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Legality_of_cryptocurrency_by_country_or_territory"]','2026-07-08 17:46:12');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('canada','Canada','North America','country','{"adoption_rank":18,"adoption":"Ranked ~18-20 on Chainalysis 2024 index. Mature market with strong institutional/ETF penetration — a global pioneer of listed crypto funds.","regulation":"Legal and regulated. Crypto trading platforms must register with securities regulators (CSA) and as MSBs with FINTRAC. CSA tightened rules on funds holding crypto (NI 81-102 amendments effective Jul 2025). Stablecoins treated as securities/derivatives absent exemptions.","upcoming_regulation":"August 2025 draft legislation to implement the OECD Crypto-Asset Reporting Framework (CARF); evolving stablecoin policy.","gov_holdings":"No known state crypto holdings.","sentiment":"Mainstream and investment-oriented; regulators emphasize investor protection within traditional securities frameworks.","notable":"Launched North America''s first spot Bitcoin/Ether ETFs (2021) and first Solana/XRP spot ETFs (2025); QuadrigaCX collapse (2019) is a cautionary tale.","use_cases":"ETF/fund investment, regulated trading, institutional exposure.","sources":["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://www.globallegalinsights.com/practice-areas/blockchain-cryptocurrency-laws-and-regulations/canada/","https://www.osler.com/en/insights/reports/2025-legal-outlook/canadas-crypto-realignment-focus-on-stablecoins-and-global-tax-transparency/"]}','["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://www.globallegalinsights.com/practice-areas/blockchain-cryptocurrency-laws-and-regulations/canada/","https://www.osler.com/en/insights/reports/2025-legal-outlook/canadas-crypto-realignment-focus-on-stablecoins-and-global-tax-transparency/"]','2026-07-08 17:46:25');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('australia','Australia','Asia-Pacific','country','{"adoption_rank":39,"adoption":"39th on Chainalysis 2024 index. Solid, affluent retail and SMSF (self-managed super fund) investment base; growing institutional interest.","regulation":"Historically light-touch (crypto taxed as property/CGT by the ATO; DCEs register with AUSTRAC). Landmark shift in 2026: the Corporations Amendment (Digital Assets Framework) Bill 2025 passed both houses Apr 1, 2026, requiring digital-asset platforms and tokenized-custody platforms to hold an AFS License from ASIC (small-platform exemption under $5,000/customer and $10M annual).","upcoming_regulation":"12-month licensing runway from the 2026 law; AUSTRAC scope expands to all digital-asset service providers from Mar 31, 2026; stablecoins to be regulated as stored-value facilities (Payments System Modernisation Bill).","gov_holdings":"No known state crypto holdings.","sentiment":"Mainstream and pragmatic; regulators moving to close consumer-protection gaps after exchange failures.","notable":"First comprehensive crypto framework passed Apr 2026; targets custody/commingling risks rather than the assets themselves.","use_cases":"Retail/SMSF investment, trading, growing custody services.","sources":["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://www.coindesk.com/policy/2026/04/01/australia-passes-crypto-licensing-bill-as-ausd24-billion-opportunity-comes-into-focus","https://sumsub.com/blog/crypto-australia/"]}','["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://www.coindesk.com/policy/2026/04/01/australia-passes-crypto-licensing-bill-as-ausd24-billion-opportunity-comes-into-focus","https://sumsub.com/blog/crypto-australia/"]','2026-07-08 17:46:35');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('kenya','Kenya','Sub-Saharan Africa','country','{"adoption_rank":21,"adoption":"Among Africa''s top crypto markets — Chainalysis ranks it high in the region, notably first in P2P transaction volume. Strong grassroots use alongside the M-Pesa mobile-money culture.","regulation":"Moving to formal regulation. The VASP Act came into force in 2025, requiring platforms to register with the Central Bank of Kenya, hold physical offices, run KYC, and have Kenyan board representation. Tax reform (effective Jul 1, 2025) repealed the 3% Digital Asset Tax and replaced it with a 10% excise duty on platform fees — cutting trader tax burden by ~96%.","upcoming_regulation":"Full VASP Act implementation and CBK licensing rollout; income/CGT treatment still being clarified.","gov_holdings":"No known state crypto holdings.","sentiment":"High grassroots adoption, especially youth; government shifting from wariness to structured regulation.","notable":"M-Pesa mobile-money legacy underpins fintech fluency; controversial Worldcoin iris-scanning operations were suspended in 2023; tax pivot in 2025.","use_cases":"P2P trading, remittances, stablecoin dollar access, freelance/gig payments.","sources":["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://www.the-star.co.ke/business/2025-11-03-kenyas-new-crypto-tax-rules-shift-focus-from-transactions-to-platform-fees","https://www.cleartax.co.ke/bitcoin-cryptocurrency-taxation-kenya.html"]}','["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://www.the-star.co.ke/business/2025-11-03-kenyas-new-crypto-tax-rules-shift-focus-from-transactions-to-platform-fees","https://www.cleartax.co.ke/bitcoin-cryptocurrency-taxation-kenya.html"]','2026-07-08 17:46:48');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('venezuela','Venezuela','Latin America','country','{"adoption_rank":10,"adoption":"Top-tier grassroots use out of necessity. ~$44.6B crypto transaction volume (Jul 2024-Jun 2025). Over 30% of businesses use crypto; USDT (''Binance dollars'') is the de facto currency amid ~229% inflation (May 2025).","regulation":"Ambiguous and unstable. The state crypto regulator Sunacrip was gutted after a 2023 corruption scandal that paused activity. No coherent framework; crypto tolerated out of practical necessity while officially monitored.","upcoming_regulation":"No clear reform path; state focus is on using crypto for its own transactions rather than regulating the public''s use.","gov_holdings":"State-backed Petro (launched 2018 to evade sanctions) quietly discontinued by Jan 2024. Rumored/unconfirmed ''shadow'' BTC reserve from converting oil-revenue USDT; state receives oil payments in USDT (est. ~80% of crude revenue).","sentiment":"Crypto is a survival tool; deep distrust of the bolivar drives organic dollarization via stablecoins.","notable":"Petro — the first state cryptocurrency — failed and was scrapped; USDT-based crypto-dollarization; PDVSA oil sales settled in stablecoins to dodge US sanctions.","use_cases":"Stablecoin (USDT) daily payments/savings, inflation survival, sanctions-evading oil settlement.","sources":["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://www.ccn.com/education/crypto/venezuela-inflation-bitcoin-usdt-p2p-crypto-lifeline/","https://www.atlanticcouncil.org/blogs/new-atlanticist/how-venezuela-uses-crypto-to-sell-oil-and-what-the-us-should-do-about-it/"]}','["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://www.ccn.com/education/crypto/venezuela-inflation-bitcoin-usdt-p2p-crypto-lifeline/","https://www.atlanticcouncil.org/blogs/new-atlanticist/how-venezuela-uses-crypto-to-sell-oil-and-what-the-us-should-do-about-it/"]','2026-07-08 17:47:00');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('pakistan','Pakistan','Asia-Pacific','country','{"adoption_rank":9,"adoption":"Top-10 on Chainalysis 2024 index. Massive grassroots base — reportedly 40M+ crypto wallets — fueled by a large freelancer economy, remittances and inflation.","regulation":"Historic reversal in 2025. Previously officials held that crypto ''would never be legal''; now the government created the Pakistan Crypto Council and approved a Pakistan Digital Assets Authority (PDAA) to license and oversee the sector.","upcoming_regulation":"PDAA build-out and licensing framework; must navigate IMF concerns. Allocation of 2,000 MW of electricity for Bitcoin mining and AI data centers announced.","gov_holdings":"Yes (announced) — a Strategic Bitcoin Reserve unveiled May 2025 (Bitcoin 2025 conference), using seized BTC that will ''never be sold.'' Plans to deploy reserve BTC into DeFi for yield were floated.","sentiment":"Rapidly shifting from prohibitionist to enthusiastic at the state level; strong grassroots demand.","notable":"One of the fastest official U-turns — from ''never legal'' to a national Bitcoin reserve and mining-energy allocation within ~2025.","use_cases":"Freelancer/remittance payments, P2P trading, inflation hedge; planned sovereign reserve/mining.","sources":["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://www.dawn.com/news/1914060","https://www.coindesk.com/policy/2025/05/28/pakistan-to-establish-a-bitcoin-strategic-reserve-allocate-2000-megawatts-of-energy-for-crypto-mining"]}','["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://www.dawn.com/news/1914060","https://www.coindesk.com/policy/2025/05/28/pakistan-to-establish-a-bitcoin-strategic-reserve-allocate-2000-megawatts-of-energy-for-crypto-mining"]','2026-07-08 17:47:13');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('north-america','North America','North America','region','{"adoption_rank":null,"adoption":"Largest crypto market globally — ~$1.3T on-chain value received (Jul 2023-Jun 2024), ~22.5% of world activity. Institutional-dominated, propelled by US spot Bitcoin/Ether ETFs.","regulation":"Maturing toward comprehensive frameworks: US GENIUS Act (stablecoins, 2025) and pending market-structure bills; Canada''s securities-based platform registration. Both moving to OECD CARF tax reporting.","upcoming_regulation":"US CLARITY/market-structure legislation and BITCOIN Act reserve proposals; Canadian CARF implementation.","gov_holdings":"US holds the largest sovereign BTC reserve (~328,372 BTC / ~$21B via the 2025 Strategic Bitcoin Reserve). Canada holds none.","sentiment":"Increasingly pro-crypto policy (US), investment-oriented and institution-led.","notable":"Epicenter of the 2024 ETF boom and the 2025 US federal Strategic Bitcoin Reserve.","use_cases":"Institutional investment (ETFs/funds), trading, stablecoin settlement.","sources":["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._Strategic_Bitcoin_Reserve","https://www.chainalysis.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/the-2024-geography-of-crypto-report-release.pdf"]}','["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._Strategic_Bitcoin_Reserve","https://www.chainalysis.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/the-2024-geography-of-crypto-report-release.pdf"]','2026-07-08 17:47:22');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('latin-america','Latin America','Latin America','region','{"adoption_rank":null,"adoption":"Among the fastest-growing regions, driven by inflation and dollar-access needs. Stablecoins dominate: Brazil rose to 5th globally (2025) with ~90% stablecoin volume; Argentina logged ~$91B in transactions (2023-24); Venezuela ~$44.6B (2024-25).","regulation":"Divergent: Brazil pursuing one of the strictest VASP/FX-integrated frameworks (from 2026); Argentina deregulating with a CNV registry; El Salvador reversed Bitcoin legal tender under IMF pressure (2025); Venezuela ambiguous.","upcoming_regulation":"Brazil''s Central Bank VASP regime and algorithmic-stablecoin ban; Argentina''s tokenization sandbox; region-wide stablecoin scrutiny.","gov_holdings":"El Salvador holds ~6,250 BTC in a Strategic Bitcoin Reserve Fund; Venezuela''s Petro was scrapped (2024) with a rumored USDT-to-BTC shadow reserve.","sentiment":"High grassroots enthusiasm as a hedge against weak currencies and capital controls; scandals (LIBRA in Argentina) dent trust.","notable":"El Salvador''s Bitcoin legal-tender experiment and reversal; Argentina''s LIBRA scandal; Venezuela''s crypto-dollarization; Brazil''s strict new regime.","use_cases":"Stablecoin dollar savings/payments, inflation hedge, remittances, sanctions/capital-control workarounds.","sources":["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/brazil-crypto-asset-regulatory-framework-2025/","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bitcoin_in_El_Salvador","https://www.ccn.com/education/crypto/venezuela-inflation-bitcoin-usdt-p2p-crypto-lifeline/"]}','["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/brazil-crypto-asset-regulatory-framework-2025/","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bitcoin_in_El_Salvador","https://www.ccn.com/education/crypto/venezuela-inflation-bitcoin-usdt-p2p-crypto-lifeline/"]','2026-07-08 17:47:35');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('europe','Europe','Europe','region','{"adoption_rank":null,"adoption":"Large, institutionalizing market with strong Western European growth during the 2024 ETF cycle. Eastern Europe features high grassroots use (Ukraine, Russia) tied to war and sanctions.","regulation":"The EU''s MiCA is the world''s first comprehensive multi-country crypto regime — stablecoin titles from Jun 30, 2024, full CASP licensing from Dec 30, 2024, with grandfathering to Jul 1, 2026. UK building a parallel FSMA-based regime (in force ~Oct 2027). Ukraine aligning to MiCA; Russia diverging toward state-controlled sanctions rails.","upcoming_regulation":"MiCA grandfathering deadline and CARF/DAC8 tax reporting (from Jan 2026); UK regime go-live 2027; Ukraine''s tax/reserve framework.","gov_holdings":"No EU sovereign reserve; Germany''s Saxony sold ~50,000 seized BTC (2024); Ukraine considering a national Bitcoin reserve.","sentiment":"Regulation-forward and consumer-protective in the West; pragmatic/necessity-driven in the East.","notable":"MiCA as the global regulatory template; Germany''s controversial seized-BTC sale; Ukraine''s wartime crypto fundraising; Russia''s sanctions-evasion pivot.","use_cases":"Institutional investment, stablecoins, cross-border payments; wartime fundraising and sanctions workarounds in the East.","sources":["https://www.esma.europa.eu/esmas-activities/digital-finance-and-innovation/markets-crypto-assets-regulation-mica","https://www.fca.org.uk/firms/new-regime-cryptoasset-regulation","https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/"]}','["https://www.esma.europa.eu/esmas-activities/digital-finance-and-innovation/markets-crypto-assets-regulation-mica","https://www.fca.org.uk/firms/new-regime-cryptoasset-regulation","https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/"]','2026-07-08 17:47:45');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('sub-saharan-africa','Sub-Saharan Africa','Sub-Saharan Africa','region','{"adoption_rank":null,"adoption":"Highest grassroots intensity relative to income — dominated by real-economy needs. Nigeria (#2 globally) and Kenya lead; heavy P2P and stablecoin usage, low institutional share. Builds on mobile-money culture (M-Pesa).","regulation":"Shifting from bans to frameworks: Nigeria lifted its 2021 bank ban (2023) and now licenses exchanges via SEC/ARIP; Kenya''s VASP Act (2025) and 10% fee-based excise duty; South Africa''s FSCA licenses crypto asset service providers.","upcoming_regulation":"Nigeria SEC licensing rollout; Kenya CBK VASP implementation; broader continental push for AML-aligned VASP rules.","gov_holdings":"No state crypto reserves in the region.","sentiment":"Very high grassroots enthusiasm, youth-driven; governments moving from wariness to regulation.","notable":"Nigeria''s ban-then-reversal and Binance standoff; Worldcoin controversy in Kenya; stablecoins as dollar proxies against weak local currencies.","use_cases":"P2P trading, remittances, stablecoin dollar access, freelance/gig payments, inflation hedge.","sources":["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://www.ibanet.org/overview-of-cryptocurrency-regulatory-landscape-nigeria","https://www.the-star.co.ke/business/2025-11-03-kenyas-new-crypto-tax-rules-shift-focus-from-transactions-to-platform-fees"]}','["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://www.ibanet.org/overview-of-cryptocurrency-regulatory-landscape-nigeria","https://www.the-star.co.ke/business/2025-11-03-kenyas-new-crypto-tax-rules-shift-focus-from-transactions-to-platform-fees"]','2026-07-08 17:48:02');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('mena','MENA','MENA','region','{"adoption_rank":null,"adoption":"Two-speed region: Turkey is a top-4 global market driven by lira collapse (inflation-hedge, high ownership), while the Gulf (UAE) is a fast-growing institutional/business hub attracting relocating firms and capital.","regulation":"Divergent. UAE has among the world''s most developed frameworks (VARA, ADGM, DIFC, federal SCA). Turkey created a CMB licensing regime (2024 Capital Markets Law amendment) while banning crypto payments. Many other MENA states remain restrictive or unclear.","upcoming_regulation":"UAE expanding RWA-tokenization and stablecoin rules; Turkey''s CMB licensing rollout and FATF grey-list exit efforts; Gulf CBDC pilots.","gov_holdings":"No declared sovereign BTC reserves, though Gulf state-linked funds are active digital-asset investors.","sentiment":"Gulf strongly pro-business/pro-crypto; Turkey grassroots-driven by economic necessity.","notable":"UAE (Dubai/Abu Dhabi) as a global crypto-business magnet with the first standalone regulator (VARA); Turkey''s inflation-fueled adoption and 2024 licensing law.","use_cases":"Turkey: inflation hedge/store of value, trading. Gulf: business HQ/licensing, RWA tokenization, wealth management.","sources":["https://www.vara.ae/en/","https://sumsub.com/blog/crypto-regulations-turkey/","https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/"]}','["https://www.vara.ae/en/","https://sumsub.com/blog/crypto-regulations-turkey/","https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/"]','2026-07-08 17:48:13');
INSERT INTO "geo_regions" ("slug","name","region","kind","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('asia-pacific','Asia-Pacific','Asia-Pacific','region','{"adoption_rank":null,"adoption":"The global grassroots-adoption leader. Central & Southern Asia and Oceania (CSAO) dominated the 2024 index with 7 of the top 20 countries; India (#1), Indonesia (fastest-growing, ~200% YoY, ~$157B received), Vietnam and Pakistan lead. Over 60% of the world''s crypto users are in Asia.","regulation":"Highly varied: China''s near-total ban vs Hong Kong''s licensed regime; Vietnam''s 2025 legal-property recognition and pilot; Japan/South Korea/Singapore mature investor-protection regimes; Indonesia moving oversight to OJK; Pakistan''s 2025 pro-crypto U-turn.","upcoming_regulation":"Vietnam''s 5-year exchange pilot; Japan''s shift to securities-law framework; Korea''s phase-2 institutional access; Australia''s 2026 licensing law; Pakistan''s PDAA.","gov_holdings":"China holds seized PlusToken BTC (~194k, status ambiguous); Pakistan announced a Strategic Bitcoin Reserve (2025); Bhutan built and then sold ~70% of a state BTC stash from hydro-powered mining.","sentiment":"Overwhelmingly high grassroots enthusiasm; regulators range from prohibition (China) to embrace (Pakistan, Vietnam).","notable":"CSAO''s top-of-index dominance; Terra/LUNA (Korea) and Axie Infinity (Vietnam/Philippines) origins; China''s ban and Hong Kong''s opening; Bhutan''s mining reserve.","use_cases":"Retail trading/DeFi, remittances, play-to-earn gaming, inflation hedge, freelancer payments; institutional hubs in Singapore/Japan.","sources":["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://chambers.com/articles/vietnam-formally-recognises-digital-assets-under-new-law","https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2026/04/11/bhutan-has-sold-70-of-its-bitcoin-in-18-months-it-may-have-stopped-btc-mining-too"]}','["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/2024-global-crypto-adoption-index/","https://chambers.com/articles/vietnam-formally-recognises-digital-assets-under-new-law","https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2026/04/11/bhutan-has-sold-70-of-its-bitcoin-in-18-months-it-may-have-stopped-btc-mining-too"]','2026-07-08 17:48:29');
INSERT INTO "rwa_depin" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('ondo-finance','Ondo Finance','rwa-treasuries','thriving','{"what_it_does":"Ondo Finance tokenizes short-term US Treasuries and money-market exposure into onchain yield-bearing tokens (OUSG for institutions/qualified purchasers, USDY as a permissionless yield token for non-US users), and is building institutional tokenization infrastructure including Ondo Chain (an L1 for RWAs) and Ondo Global Markets for tokenized securities.","category":"rwa-treasuries","founders":"Nathan Allman (CEO, ex-Goldman Sachs Digital Assets) and Pinku Surana (CTO). Founded 2021.","raised":"~$34M across seed and Series A (Founders Fund, Pantera, Coinbase Ventures, Tiger Global among backers); also raised via a 2022 CoinList token sale.","token_symbol":"ONDO","token_price":"~$0.95 (July 2025), ~$3B market cap, ~$9.5B FDV","market_metric":"~$1.6B AUM across tokenized products by Oct 2025, surpassing $1.8B TVL by late 2025. OUSG >$1.1B TVL; USDY ~$690M TVL (July 2025).","how_it_works":"OUSG holds primarily BlackRock BUIDL plus BlackRock FedFund (TFDXX), bank deposits and USDC for instant 24/7 mint/redeem. USDY is backed by short-duration Treasuries and bank demand deposits, issued by a bankruptcy-remote Delaware SPV (Ondo USDY LLC), and holders earn accrued yield. Tokens deployed across Ethereum, Solana, Sei, Mantle, Sui, Aptos, XRP Ledger.","traction":"Crossed $1B TVL Mar 2025; ~$1.6B AUM Oct 2025; >$1.8B by late 2025. Fidelity launched onchain money-market fund FDIT anchored by OUSG (>99% of FDIT assets). Ondo Global Markets surpassed $240M TVL within 48 hours of Sept 2025 launch, ~$320M by Oct 2025. Joined Mastercard Multi-Token Network. SEC closed its investigation in Nov 2025.","backing_partners":"BlackRock (via BUIDL), Fidelity (FDIT), Mastercard MTN, Founders Fund, Pantera, Coinbase Ventures. Plans to integrate Oasis Pro Markets.","business_model":"Management fees on tokenized funds (OUSG/USDY spread over underlying yield) plus infrastructure fees from Ondo Chain and Global Markets. ONDO token captures value via governance (Ondo DAO) and prospective network staking/fees on Ondo Chain; token value is currently largely narrative/governance rather than direct fee accrual.","outlook":"Bull: becomes the default tokenization rail for institutional Treasuries and securities as regulatory clarity improves, with Ondo Chain + Global Markets compounding. Base: remains a top-3 tokenized Treasury issuer growing with the sector. Bear: fee compression and competition from BlackRock/Securitize direct issuance; ONDO FDV (~$9.5B) implies large unlock overhang vs modest fee revenue. Key risk: token价值 disconnect from AUM and regulatory shifts on tokenized securities.","status":"thriving","sources":[{"title":"Ondo Finance | OUSG","url":"https://ondo.finance/ousg"},{"title":"RWA.xyz | Ondo OUSG","url":"https://app.rwa.xyz/assets/OUSG"},{"title":"Messari | Ondo Finance","url":"https://messari.io/project/ondo-finance"},{"title":"Ainvest | Ondo post-regulatory clarity catalyst","url":"https://www.ainvest.com/news/ondo-finance-post-regulatory-clarity-catalyst-rwa-tokenization-institutional-adoption-2512/"}]}','[{"title":"Ondo Finance | OUSG","url":"https://ondo.finance/ousg"},{"title":"RWA.xyz | Ondo OUSG","url":"https://app.rwa.xyz/assets/OUSG"},{"title":"Messari | Ondo Finance","url":"https://messari.io/project/ondo-finance"}]','2026-07-08 15:47:36');
INSERT INTO "rwa_depin" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('blackrock-buidl','BlackRock BUIDL','rwa-treasuries','thriving','{"what_it_does":"BUIDL (BlackRock USD Institutional Digital Liquidity Fund) is BlackRock''s tokenized money-market/Treasury fund issued on public blockchains, tokenized and administered by Securitize. It is the largest tokenized US Treasury fund in the world and functions as a yield-bearing, blockchain-native cash-management instrument for institutions.","category":"rwa-treasuries","founders":"Issued by BlackRock (world''s largest asset manager, CEO Larry Fink); tokenization by Securitize (CEO Carlos Domingo). Launched March 2024.","raised":"N/A as a fund (BlackRock is a public company). BlackRock made a strategic equity investment in Securitize in 2024.","token_symbol":"BUIDL","token_price":"$1.00 per token (stable NAV, yield paid as new tokens/dividends)","market_metric":"AUM grew from >$1B (Mar 2025) to ~$2B (Apr 2025) to ~$3B (Q2 2025 per Securitize filings); ~$2.5B by Nov 2025. Largest tokenized Treasury fund onchain.","how_it_works":"Each BUIDL token targets a stable $1 value and is backed by cash, US Treasury bills and repurchase agreements. Yield accrues daily and is paid to holders as new tokens (dividends distributed monthly). Securitize acts as registered transfer agent handling issuance, compliance and redemptions. Deployed on Ethereum (majority), plus Aptos, Arbitrum, Avalanche, Optimism, Polygon and BNB Chain.","traction":"Surpassed $1B AUM Mar 2025; paid record $4.17M dividends in Mar 2025 (largest monthly payout of any tokenized Treasury fund). Accepted as collateral on Crypto.com and Deribit (June 2025) and Binance (Nov 2025). Widely used as backing collateral by other RWA issuers (e.g., Ondo OUSG holds BUIDL).","backing_partners":"Securitize (tokenization/transfer agent), Wormhole (cross-chain), Crypto.com, Deribit, Binance (collateral venues), BNB Chain. Institutional holders across crypto and DeFi.","business_model":"BlackRock earns management fees on the fund''s AUM; Securitize earns tokenization/administration fees. No separate liquid token to speculate on — value is the yield-bearing share itself. Revenue scales directly with AUM.","outlook":"Bull: becomes the reserve cash-equivalent for onchain finance (collateral, treasury management, stablecoin backing), pulling trillions of institutional cash onchain. Base: remains the dominant tokenized Treasury fund growing with rates and adoption. Bear: AUM is rate-sensitive and saw outflows in late 2025/early 2026 as yields fell; concentration on Ethereum and reliance on Securitize. Key risk: falling interest rates reduce demand for tokenized cash yield.","status":"thriving","sources":[{"title":"The Defiant | BUIDL hits $2B AUM","url":"https://thedefiant.io/news/tradfi-and-fintech/blackrock-s-buidl-fund-hits-2-billion-aum-pays-record-4-17m-dividends-3-5m-on-295ae8a5"},{"title":"PRNewswire | BUIDL surpasses $1B AUM","url":"https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/blackrock-usd-institutional-digital-liquidity-fund-buidl-tokenized-by-securitize-surpasses-1b-in-aum-302401480.html"},{"title":"CoinDesk | BUIDL listed as collateral on Binance, BNB Chain","url":"https://www.coindesk.com/business/2025/11/14/blackrock-s-usd2-5b-tokenized-fund-gets-listed-as-collateral-on-binance-expands-to-bnb-chain"}]}','[{"title":"The Defiant | BUIDL hits $2B AUM","url":"https://thedefiant.io/news/tradfi-and-fintech/blackrock-s-buidl-fund-hits-2-billion-aum-pays-record-4-17m-dividends-3-5m-on-295ae8a5"},{"title":"PRNewswire | BUIDL surpasses $1B AUM","url":"https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/blackrock-usd-institutional-digital-liquidity-fund-buidl-tokenized-by-securitize-surpasses-1b-in-aum-302401480.html"}]','2026-07-08 15:48:07');
INSERT INTO "rwa_depin" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('franklin-templeton-benji','Franklin Templeton BENJI','rwa-treasuries','steady','{"what_it_does":"BENJI is the token representing shares of the Franklin OnChain US Government Money Fund (FOBXX), the first US-registered mutual fund to use a public blockchain as its official system of record. Retail and institutional users access it via the Benji Investments app; Franklin also white-labels the Benji technology platform to banks and other asset managers.","category":"rwa-treasuries","founders":"Franklin Templeton (Executive Chairman Jenny Johnson; digital-assets effort led by Roger Bayston/Sandy Kaul). Fund inception 2021 on Stellar.","raised":"N/A — Franklin Templeton is a public asset manager (~$1.68T total AUM as of Mar 2026).","token_symbol":"BENJI","token_price":"$1.00 per token (1 BENJI = 1 FOBXX share); 7-day effective yield ~3.58% (Apr 2026)","market_metric":"FOBXX ~$828-844M AUM (Q1 2026), 3rd-largest tokenized money-market fund. Broader BENJI suite ~$1.98B AUM (Apr 2026). On Stellar, 2nd-largest RWA by value (>$650M, Apr 2026).","how_it_works":"One BENJI token equals one share of FOBXX, a government money-market fund holding US government securities, cash and repos. Blockchain is the system of record for share ownership and transactions. Holders can convert USDC to fund purchases and transfer shares peer-to-peer. Deployed on 8 chains: Stellar (original), Polygon, Arbitrum, Aptos, Avalanche, Base, Solana, Ethereum — all representing the same underlying FOBXX pool.","traction":"Investor count grew >140% from Apr 2024 to Mar 2026, accelerating after May 2025 expansion of P2P transfers to retail. Cumulative P2P transfer volume >$211M (Mar 2026). Five-year track record (2021-2026). Mercurity Fintech and others partnering to distribute BENJI/FOBXX.","backing_partners":"Stellar Development Foundation, Avalanche, Polygon, and multiple custodians/wallets. White-label Benji platform offered to banks and asset managers.","business_model":"Management fees on FOBXX AUM plus technology-licensing revenue from white-labeling the Benji platform. BENJI is a fund share, not a speculative governance token — no separate token value-capture layer; revenue scales with AUM and platform licensees.","outlook":"Bull: Benji becomes a widely-licensed tokenization backbone for regulated funds, and multi-chain retail P2P drives BENJI into everyday onchain cash use. Base: steady growth as a trusted, regulated top-3 tokenized MMF. Bear: lags faster-moving crypto-native issuers (BUIDL, Ondo) in AUM and integrations; rate-sensitive demand. Key risk: slower institutional-distribution ramp and yield compression as rates fall.","status":"steady","sources":[{"title":"Stellar | Five Years of BENJI","url":"https://stellar.org/press/franklin-templeton-stellar-development-foundation-mark-five-years-of-benji-the-first-u-s-registered-tokenized-money-market-fund"},{"title":"Invest with Benji | Franklin Templeton","url":"https://digitalassets.franklintempleton.com/benji/"},{"title":"Avalanche | Franklin Templeton launches BENJI on Avalanche","url":"https://www.avax.network/about/blog/franklin-templeton-launches-tokenized-money-market-fund-benji-avalanche"}]}','[{"title":"Stellar | Five Years of BENJI","url":"https://stellar.org/press/franklin-templeton-stellar-development-foundation-mark-five-years-of-benji-the-first-u-s-registered-tokenized-money-market-fund"},{"title":"Invest with Benji | Franklin Templeton","url":"https://digitalassets.franklintempleton.com/benji/"}]','2026-07-08 15:48:31');
INSERT INTO "rwa_depin" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('securitize','Securitize','rwa-tokenization','thriving','{"what_it_does":"Securitize is the leading RWA tokenization platform and SEC-registered transfer agent, issuing and administering tokenized funds and securities on-chain for top asset managers.","category":"rwa-tokenization","founders":"Carlos Domingo (CEO) and Jamie Finn, founded 2017","raised":"$47M strategic round led by BlackRock (2024); went public on NYSE (ticker SECZ) in July 2026 via SPAC merger with Cantor Equity Partners II at a ~$1.25B valuation, raising ~$400M gross","token_symbol":"None (SECZ equity on NYSE; no native token)","token_price":"N/A (public equity, not a token)","market_metric":"$4B+ in assets tokenized as of Oct 2025; acts as transfer agent/tokenizer for BlackRock BUIDL (~$2.2-2.5B)","how_it_works":"Provides the compliance rails, transfer-agent services and smart-contract issuance for tokenized funds. Partners (BlackRock, Apollo, KKR, Hamilton Lane, VanEck) issue funds; Securitize handles KYC, cap-table, and on-chain token lifecycle across Ethereum, Solana, Avalanche.","traction":"$4B+ tokenized; 150+ institutional investors served; tokenized KKR Health Care Strategic Growth Fund II (first major manager fund on-chain, 2022); BUIDL is the largest tokenized money-market fund","backing_partners":"BlackRock, Apollo, KKR, Hamilton Lane, VanEck, BNY, Cantor Fitzgerald","business_model":"Fees on tokenization/administration, transfer-agent services, and marketplace/brokerage (Securitize Markets). Revenue scales with AUM tokenized.","outlook":"Bull: becomes default institutional tokenization layer as trillions of RWAs migrate on-chain; public listing gives credibility and capital. Base: steady AUM growth alongside BlackRock. Bear: commoditization of tokenization tech, or a slowdown in institutional tokenization demand. Risk: heavy dependence on the BlackRock relationship for headline AUM.","status":"thriving","sources":["https://securitize.io","https://fortune.com/2026/07/02/securitize-is-latest-crypto-company-to-go-public-as-blackrock-backed-firm-sees-stock-jump-3-on-debut/","https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/securitize-the-leading-tokenization-platform-to-become-a-public-company-at-1-25b-valuation-via-business-combination-with-cantor-equity-partners-ii-302596208.html","https://app.rwa.xyz"]}','["https://securitize.io","https://fortune.com/2026/07/02/securitize-is-latest-crypto-company-to-go-public-as-blackrock-backed-firm-sees-stock-jump-3-on-debut/","https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/securitize-the-leading-tokenization-platform-to-become-a-public-company-at-1-25b-valuation-via-business-combination-with-cantor-equity-partners-ii-302596208.html","https://app.rwa.xyz"]','2026-07-08 17:41:38');
INSERT INTO "rwa_depin" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('centrifuge','Centrifuge','rwa-credit','steady','{"what_it_does":"Centrifuge is a decentralized protocol for tokenizing and financing real-world assets (private credit, structured credit, treasuries), one of the earliest RWA-native DeFi platforms.","category":"rwa-credit","founders":"Lucas Vogelsang and Martin Quensel, founded 2017","raised":"$15M Series A (Apr 2024) from ParaFi Capital, Greenfield, Circle Ventures, IOSG, Wintermute Ventures and others; earlier seed rounds","token_symbol":"CFG","token_price":"CFG market cap ~$117M (2025); token used for governance and protocol fees","market_metric":"~$1.4B protocol TVL (DefiLlama, 2025), ranking among top RWA protocols behind Tether Gold, BUIDL, and Ondo","how_it_works":"Asset originators create pools (Tinlake/Centrifuge Pools) where real-world collateral (invoices, loans, treasuries) is tokenized as NFTs and financed by on-chain investors who receive senior/junior tranche tokens. Now expanding onto Ethereum and multiple L2s.","traction":"~$1.4B TVL; long track record since 2017; partnerships with MakerDAO/Sky, Aave and others for RWA collateral; recently launched Centrifuge V3 and treasury products","backing_partners":"ParaFi, Circle Ventures, Wintermute, Sky (MakerDAO), Aave, Coinbase Asset Management (via deRWA products)","business_model":"Management fees on pool assets and protocol revenue from asset yields; value accrues to CFG via governance and fee capture.","outlook":"Bull: becomes the open infrastructure layer for on-chain private credit as institutions adopt tokenized credit. Base: steady TVL in the $1-2B range with modest CFG appreciation. Bear: yield compression and competition from Maple/Figure erode share; CFG market cap has lagged TVL. Risk: credit defaults in underlying pools and reliance on a few large originators.","status":"steady","sources":["https://centrifuge.io","https://defillama.com/protocol/centrifuge-protocol","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/centrifuge","https://app.rwa.xyz"]}','["https://centrifuge.io","https://defillama.com/protocol/centrifuge-protocol","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/centrifuge","https://app.rwa.xyz"]','2026-07-08 17:41:55');
INSERT INTO "rwa_depin" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('maple-finance','Maple Finance','rwa-credit','thriving','{"what_it_does":"Maple Finance is an on-chain institutional asset manager and credit marketplace, offering over-collateralized and institutional lending pools plus its permissionless Syrup yield product.","category":"rwa-credit","founders":"Sidney Powell (CEO) and Joe Flanagan, founded 2019","raised":"Backed by early rounds; token migrated from MPL to SYRUP in 2024. Institutional backers include Framework Ventures, BlockTower, Maven 11","token_symbol":"SYRUP (migrated from MPL)","token_price":"SYRUP down 50%+ from its mid-2025 peak; 25% of protocol revenue funds SYRUP buybacks (MIP-019, from Nov 2025)","market_metric":"$5B assets under management and ~$2B active loans at late-2025 all-time high; TVL surpassed $4B in deposits","how_it_works":"Hybrid model: loan enforcement and accounting occur on-chain while credit decisions are made off-chain by delegates. Products span Maple Institutional (secured lending), Syrup (permissionless yield), BTC Yield, and High Yield Secured pools.","traction":"$5B AUM, $2B active loans, 99% loan repayment rate late 2025; issued largest single loan of $500M; institutional borrower base grew 4->28, allocators grew 15x to ~800; no defaults across $600M+ cumulative originations through 2024","backing_partners":"Framework Ventures, BlockTower, Maven 11; integrations with Kraken, Robinhood Chain, Binance","business_model":"Origination and management fees on lending pools; 25% of protocol revenue buys back SYRUP. Targeting $100M ARR north-star for 2026.","outlook":"Bull: captures the multi-trillion private-credit market moving on-chain, scaling Syrup to $2B TVL in 2026. Base: continued double-digit TVL growth with buyback-supported SYRUP. Bear: credit cycle turns, default rates rise from ~1% toward historical 3-5%, and SYRUP stays volatile. Risk: off-chain credit underwriting and jurisdictional/regulatory disputes (e.g. Cayman Core Foundation).","status":"thriving","sources":["https://maple.finance","https://defillama.com/protocol/maple-finance","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/maple-finance","https://app.rwa.xyz"]}','["https://maple.finance","https://defillama.com/protocol/maple-finance","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/maple-finance","https://app.rwa.xyz"]','2026-07-08 17:42:15');
INSERT INTO "rwa_depin" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('superstate','Superstate','rwa-treasuries','thriving','{"what_it_does":"Superstate builds tokenized investment funds, led by USTB (short-duration US government securities) and USCC (crypto carry), giving crypto-native institutions on-chain access to regulated yield products.","category":"rwa-treasuries","founders":"Robert Leshner (founder of Compound), founded 2023","raised":"$14M Series A (2023, co-led by Distributed Global and CoinFund); $82M Series B (Jan 2026)","token_symbol":"USTB (fund token, not a governance token)","token_price":"USTB tracks NAV (~$10+ share); targets the federal funds rate with a 0.15% management fee","market_metric":"USTB grew from ~$145M AUM (late 2024) to $900M+ (early 2026), among the top five tokenized US treasury funds globally","how_it_works":"Investors mint and redeem USTB via USDC; the fund holds short-duration US Treasury and agency securities. Uses Chainlink infrastructure for transparency and introduced real-time continuous pricing. Runs on Ethereum with multi-chain support.","traction":"$900M+ USTB AUM; 150+ institutional investors onboarded; billions in cumulative transactions; landmark partnership with Invesco to manage USTB (to be renamed Invesco Short Duration US Government Securities Fund, Q2 2026); powers Bitwise Crypto Carry Fund","backing_partners":"Invesco, Distributed Global, CoinFund, Bitwise, Chainlink","business_model":"Management fees (0.15% on USTB) on tokenized fund AUM; expanding to power third-party managers'' tokenized funds as infrastructure provider.","outlook":"Bull: becomes the tokenization engine for major asset managers (Invesco deal is the template), scaling well past $1B AUM. Base: steady growth as a top-tier tokenized treasury issuer. Bear: BUIDL and Ondo dominate distribution; margins on treasury funds are thin. Risk: yields fall if the Fed cuts rates aggressively, reducing product appeal.","status":"thriving","sources":["https://superstate.com","https://fortune.com/2026/03/24/invesco-superstate-ustb/","https://www.theblock.co/post/323995/robert-leshners-superstate-introduces-real-time-continuous-pricing-for-ustb-tokenized-treasurys-fund","https://app.rwa.xyz"]}','["https://superstate.com","https://fortune.com/2026/03/24/invesco-superstate-ustb/","https://www.theblock.co/post/323995/robert-leshners-superstate-introduces-real-time-continuous-pricing-for-ustb-tokenized-treasurys-fund","https://app.rwa.xyz"]','2026-07-08 17:42:32');
INSERT INTO "rwa_depin" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('figure-provenance','Figure / Provenance','rwa-credit','thriving','{"what_it_does":"Figure is a blockchain-based lending and capital-markets company that originates and tokenizes private credit (chiefly HELOCs) natively on its own Provenance Layer-1 blockchain.","category":"rwa-credit","founders":"Mike Cagney (co-founder of SoFi) and June Ou, founded 2018","raised":"IPO on Nasdaq (ticker FIGR) in Sept 2025 raising ~$787.5M at $25/share; valued ~$5.3B at IPO (~$7.6B after first-day pop). Earlier VC from Ribbit, DCG, Morgan Creek","token_symbol":"HASH (Provenance blockchain gas token); FIGR equity on Nasdaq","token_price":"FIGR traded ~$42 late Dec 2025 vs $25 IPO price; HASH powers the Provenance L1","market_metric":"$11.7B in on-chain outstanding loans at IPO (rwa.xyz); $16.2B HELOCs tokenized and 70%+ share of RWA private-credit tokenization by late 2025","how_it_works":"Figure''s loan-origination system runs natively on Provenance, recording each loan as a tamper-proof on-chain asset. It tokenizes HELOCs and other private credit, then finances/securitizes them, and runs Figure Markets for trading and Democratized Prime for lending against tokenized collateral.","traction":"$19B+ on-chain loans originated; $50B+ processed on Provenance; $355M blockchain securitization first to earn full S&P ratings (AAA to sub); Sixth Street JV ($200M capital + $2B liquidity); $339M adjusted net revenue in 2024; launched Solana RWA Consortium Dec 2025","backing_partners":"Sixth Street, Jefferies, Goldman Sachs (IPO), Kamino, Chainlink, Raydium (Solana consortium)","business_model":"Origination and gain-on-sale from HELOCs, servicing fees, marketplace/securitization revenue, and software licensing of its blockchain lending infrastructure.","outlook":"Bull: becomes the on-chain rails for the $420B+ US HELOC market and broader private credit, with public-company scale. Base: continues to dominate tokenized private credit while margins normalize. Bear: rate-sensitive HELOC volumes and reliance on securitization markets; competition from Maple. Risk: mortgage-credit cycle exposure and regulatory scrutiny of a single-company L1.","status":"thriving","sources":["https://www.figure.com","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Figure_Technology_Solutions","https://decrypt.co/339024/blockchain-lender-figure-nasdaq-5-3-billion-valuation","https://app.rwa.xyz"]}','["https://www.figure.com","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Figure_Technology_Solutions","https://decrypt.co/339024/blockchain-lender-figure-nasdaq-5-3-billion-valuation","https://app.rwa.xyz"]','2026-07-08 17:42:51');
INSERT INTO "rwa_depin" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('tokenized-gold','Tether Gold (XAUT) & Pax Gold (PAXG)','rwa-tokenization','thriving','{"what_it_does":"Tokenized gold products: Tether Gold (XAUT) and Paxos'' Pax Gold (PAXG) each represent one fine troy ounce of physical gold, redeemable and fully allocated, giving on-chain exposure to bullion.","category":"rwa-tokenization","founders":"XAUT issued by Tether (Paolo Ardoino, CEO); PAXG issued by Paxos (Charles Cascarilla, CEO)","raised":"Both issued by large, self-funded stablecoin firms (Tether, Paxos); no separate raise for the gold tokens","token_symbol":"XAUT (Tether Gold), PAXG (Pax Gold)","token_price":"Each token tracks the spot price of ~1 oz gold (roughly $3,400-4,000+ in 2025); price moves with bullion, not a governance token","market_metric":"Combined tokenized-gold market topped $2.57B (Sept 2025) and surpassed $4B by Dec 2025; XAUT overtook PAXG as largest after an August 2025 mint (~$1.3B+), PAXG record ~$983M","how_it_works":"Each token is backed 1:1 by physical gold held in vaults (XAUT in Switzerland; PAXG via LBMA-accredited vaults). Holders can redeem for physical bullion or cash. Attestations: BDO for XAUT, KPMG for PAXG.","traction":"Combined >90% of tokenized-gold market; XAUT holders +173% in 2025 vs PAXG +29%; Q2 2025 tokenized-gold trading volume surpassed $19B, overtaking major gold ETFs; XAUT backed by 375,572+ oz per Q3 2025 BDO attestation","backing_partners":"Tether, Paxos; LBMA-accredited vaulting; BDO and KPMG (attestations)","business_model":"Issuers earn on minting/redemption fees and storage/custody spreads; a low-cost, liquid alternative to gold ETFs with 24/7 settlement.","outlook":"Bull: tokenized gold becomes a mainstream on-chain safe-haven and collateral asset as gold prices stay elevated. Base: steady growth tracking bullion demand and DeFi collateral use. Bear: gold price reversal or preference for treasury-yield tokens over non-yielding gold. Risk: custody/attestation trust and redemption logistics; regulatory treatment of commodity-backed tokens.","status":"thriving","sources":["https://gold.tether.to","https://paxos.com/paxgold/","https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2025/09/01/tokenized-gold-market-tops-usd2-5b-as-the-precious-metal-nears-record-highs","https://www.coingecko.com/en/categories/tokenized-gold"]}','["https://gold.tether.to","https://paxos.com/paxgold/","https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2025/09/01/tokenized-gold-market-tops-usd2-5b-as-the-precious-metal-nears-record-highs","https://www.coingecko.com/en/categories/tokenized-gold"]','2026-07-08 17:43:10');
INSERT INTO "rwa_depin" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('plume','Plume Network','rwa-tokenization','early','{"what_it_does":"Plume is a purpose-built, modular blockchain (RWA L2/L1) with tokenization, compliance, and asset-management tooling integrated directly into the chain, designed as the settlement layer for real-world assets.","category":"rwa-tokenization","founders":"Chris Yin (CEO) and Teddy Pornprinya, founded 2024","raised":"~$30M total: $10M seed (May 2024, led by Haun Ventures) and $20M Series A (Dec 2024, led by Brevan Howard Digital), plus strategic investment from Apollo Global","token_symbol":"PLUME","token_price":"PLUME token live since 2025 (gas + governance); price tracked on CoinMarketCap","market_metric":"$645M RWA TVL, 280,000+ holders, and 100M+ on-chain transactions per Q3 2025 update (up from $238M TVL shortly after June 2025 mainnet launch)","how_it_works":"Plume Genesis mainnet (launched June 2025) bakes tokenization engines and compliance/KYC providers into the chain. SkyLink distributes RWA yields across 16+ networks. The chain hosts 100+ RWA deployments spanning credit, treasuries, and alternative assets.","traction":"$645M TVL, 280k+ holders, 100M+ transactions; SEC-registered Transfer Agent status; partnerships with Apollo, EY, Mastercard, and Ant Group; 100+ RWA projects deployed","backing_partners":"Haun Ventures, Galaxy Digital, Brevan Howard, Apollo Global, YZi Labs, Anchorage Digital, Mastercard, EY","business_model":"Chain-level fees (gas), value accrual to PLUME token from ecosystem activity, and monetization of integrated tokenization/compliance services.","outlook":"Bull: becomes the default RWA-specific chain as tokenization scales, leveraging its SEC transfer-agent status and Apollo backing. Base: a credible mid-tier RWA chain competing with general L2s and Ondo Chain. Bear: RWA issuers prefer established chains (Ethereum, Solana) and app-specific chains struggle for liquidity. Risk: early-stage TVL concentration and token unlock overhang.","status":"early","sources":["https://plume.org","https://plume.org/blog/q3-2025-plume-update","https://app.rwa.xyz/networks/plume","https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/plume/"]}','["https://plume.org","https://plume.org/blog/q3-2025-plume-update","https://app.rwa.xyz/networks/plume","https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/plume/"]','2026-07-08 17:43:27');
INSERT INTO "rwa_depin" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('helium','Helium','depin-wireless','steady','{"what_it_does":"Helium is a decentralized wireless network where individuals deploy hotspots to provide LoRaWAN IoT and 5G/mobile coverage, earning HNT; Helium Mobile offers a consumer phone plan offloading to the network.","category":"depin-wireless","founders":"Amir Haleem, Shawn Fanning (Napster), and Sean Carey, founded 2013 (Nova Labs)","raised":"$365M+ raised over the years (Tiger Global, a16z, Multicoin, Khosla, GV); Nova Labs is the parent company","token_symbol":"HNT (plus IOT and MOBILE subDAO tokens)","token_price":"HNT ~$0.23, market cap ~$40M (2025), down from $54.88 ATH (Nov 2021); ~180M circulating supply","market_metric":"~114,000 hotspots and 1.2M+ daily users; Helium Mobile surpassed 500,000 sign-ups; 2,721 TB cumulative carrier data offloaded (Q2 2025, +138% QoQ)","how_it_works":"Hotspot operators are rewarded in HNT/subDAO tokens for providing coverage and transferring data. Helium migrated to Solana in 2023. Data Credits (burned HNT) pay for network usage; Helium Mobile burns HNT equal to 100% of subscriber revenue.","traction":"500k+ Mobile sign-ups, ~114k hotspots, $50k+ daily Data Credit burns; AT&T offload partnership; third halving Aug 2025 cut emissions from 15M to 7.5M HNT/yr; US court dismissed SEC suit (HNT ruled not a security)","backing_partners":"AT&T (offload), Telefonica, Solana Foundation; investors a16z, Tiger Global, Multicoin","business_model":"Consumers/carriers pay in Data Credits (burning HNT) for connectivity; Helium Mobile subscription revenue funds HNT buyback-and-burn.","outlook":"Bull: carrier-offload B2B model (post-2026 pivot to infrastructure platform) drives real, revenue-backed HNT burns. Base: steady niche growth in IoT + mobile offload. Bear: token price stays depressed, subsidies unsustainable, and DePIN hype fades. Risk: leadership transition (Haleem stepped down as CEO June 2026), sale of the Mobile consumer business, and heavy reliance on token incentives for coverage.","status":"steady","sources":["https://www.helium.com","https://messari.io/report/state-of-helium-q3-2025","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/helium","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Helium_Network"]}','["https://www.helium.com","https://messari.io/report/state-of-helium-q3-2025","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/helium","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Helium_Network"]','2026-07-08 17:43:51');
INSERT INTO "rwa_depin" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('render','Render Network','depin-compute','steady','{"what_it_does":"Render Network is a decentralized GPU rendering marketplace connecting artists and studios needing render/compute power with idle GPU providers, expanding into AI compute.","category":"depin-compute","founders":"Jules Urbach (founder of OTOY / OctaneRender), network launched 2020","raised":"Backed by Multicoin, Alameda (historical), Solana Ventures; funded via token sales and OTOY","token_symbol":"RENDER (migrated from RNDR; moved to Solana)","token_price":"RENDER ~$1.60, market cap ~$835M, FDV ~$1.04B (2025); ATH $13.61 (Mar 2024), ~-88% from peak","market_metric":"Millions of frames rendered cumulatively; supply of GPU node operators worldwide; expanding into AI/ML compute workloads","how_it_works":"Creators submit render jobs paid in RENDER; distributed GPU node operators process the work and earn tokens via a Burn-and-Mint Equilibrium model. Built on OctaneRender tech; migrated to Solana for throughput. Governed by the Render Network Foundation.","traction":"Integrations with OctaneRender, Cinema 4D, and major studios/artists; expanding into AI inference; one of the longest-running DePIN compute networks; strong brand in 3D/VFX","backing_partners":"OTOY, Solana Foundation, Multicoin, Apple (OctaneX historical), NVIDIA ecosystem tooling","business_model":"Burn-and-mint: users burn RENDER to pay for rendering/compute, node operators earn newly minted tokens; fees scale with network usage.","outlook":"Bull: rides the AI-compute wave, becoming a decentralized alternative to cloud GPU for rendering and inference. Base: steady demand from its core 3D/VFX niche with modest AI upside. Bear: token far below ATH, competition from io.net/Akash and centralized clouds; render demand alone is a limited market. Risk: reliance on OTOY, GPU supply volatility, and AI-compute competition.","status":"steady","sources":["https://rendernetwork.com","https://messari.io/project/render-network","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/render","https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/render/"]}','["https://rendernetwork.com","https://messari.io/project/render-network","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/render","https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/render/"]','2026-07-08 17:44:08');
INSERT INTO "rwa_depin" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('filecoin','Filecoin','depin-data','steady','{"what_it_does":"Filecoin is a decentralized storage network where storage providers offer disk capacity for verifiable, durable, censorship-resistant data storage, paid in FIL.","category":"depin-data","founders":"Juan Benet (Protocol Labs, also creator of IPFS), mainnet launched Oct 2020","raised":"$205M ICO in 2017 (one of the largest at the time) plus prior VC from Sequoia, a16z, Union Square Ventures","token_symbol":"FIL","token_price":"FIL ~$2.19, circulating market cap ~$1.5B (Q3 2025, down 5% QoQ)","market_metric":"~1,110 PiB of data stored; 3.0 EiB total capacity; network utilization rose to 36% in Q3 2025 (from 32% Q2)","how_it_works":"Storage providers pledge FIL collateral and prove they store client data via Proof-of-Replication and Proof-of-Spacetime (plus new Proof of Data Possession). Clients pay FIL for storage deals; Filecoin Plus (Fil+) prioritizes verified large-data clients.","traction":"~1,110 PiB stored; 2,491 onboarded datasets (925 exceeding 1,000 TiB); SP consolidation improving quality; enterprise tooling (Akave S3-compatible storage); cultural/scientific archive partnerships; FEVM smart-contract layer","backing_partners":"Protocol Labs, Akave, cultural/scientific archive institutions; broad IPFS ecosystem","business_model":"Storage clients pay FIL for deals; providers earn block rewards + deal fees, backed by FIL collateral (penalties for failures).","outlook":"Bull: becomes the durable-storage backbone for Web3, AI datasets, and enterprise archives as verified paid usage grows. Base: steady utilization gains via consolidation and Fil+. Bear: capacity and token price declining, competition from cheaper centralized/S3 storage and Arweave. Risk: low utilization historically, penalty-driven fee structure, and slow enterprise adoption.","status":"steady","sources":["https://filecoin.io","https://messari.io/report/state-of-filecoin-q3-2025","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/filecoin","https://depinscan.io/projects/filecoin"]}','["https://filecoin.io","https://messari.io/report/state-of-filecoin-q3-2025","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/filecoin","https://depinscan.io/projects/filecoin"]','2026-07-08 17:44:24');
INSERT INTO "rwa_depin" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('hivemapper','Hivemapper (Bee Maps)','depin-mapping','thriving','{"what_it_does":"Hivemapper (now Bee Maps) is a decentralized street-level mapping network where drivers use purpose-built dashcams to collect road imagery, earning HONEY; the data is sold to businesses via map APIs.","category":"depin-mapping","founders":"Ariel Seidman (CEO), network launched 2022 on Solana","raised":"$32M round in 2025 (Pantera, LDA Capital, Borderless, Ajna); earlier VC including Multicoin and Craft Ventures","token_symbol":"HONEY (SPL token on Solana)","token_price":"HONEY on Solana; deflationary via burns (map-credit conversions, 75% of burns permanent) and 10% of Foundation emissions burned from July 2025","market_metric":"~36% of the world''s roads mapped (up from 1% pre-incentives); 20M+ km of unique road imagery captured in under two years","how_it_works":"Contributors mount Hivemapper/Bee dashcams and are rewarded in HONEY for capturing fresh street imagery. Businesses buy access through the Bee Maps API. New $19/month subscription (hardware + LTE + software) replaced the $589 upfront device cost.","traction":"36% of global roads mapped; enterprise partners Volkswagen ADMT (robotaxi) and Lyft; region-based staking (MIP 25) beta Nov 2025; 24/7 mapping and upload-time rewards (MIP 24) from July 2025","backing_partners":"Volkswagen ADMT, Lyft, Pantera Capital, Borderless Capital, Multicoin","business_model":"Enterprises pay (fiat/credits burning HONEY) for map imagery API access; subscription revenue from Bee Membership; token burns tie usage to deflation.","outlook":"Bull: becomes the go-to fresh-map data source for autonomous vehicles and robotaxis as demand outstrips supply. Base: steady coverage growth with expanding enterprise contracts. Bear: incumbents (Google, TomTom) and slow enterprise revenue conversion; token price weakness. Risk: supply-side (driver) growth is the bottleneck; monetization must convert coverage into recurring revenue.","status":"thriving","sources":["https://hivemapper.com","https://messari.io/project/hivemapper","https://solanacompass.com/projects/hivemapper","https://depinscan.io/projects/hivemapper"]}','["https://hivemapper.com","https://messari.io/project/hivemapper","https://solanacompass.com/projects/hivemapper","https://depinscan.io/projects/hivemapper"]','2026-07-08 17:44:42');
INSERT INTO "rwa_depin" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('geodnet','GEODNET','depin-mapping','thriving','{"what_it_does":"GEODNET is a decentralized GNSS network of satellite reference stations providing centimeter-level RTK positioning corrections for drones, robots, autonomous vehicles, and surveying.","category":"depin-mapping","founders":"Mike Horton (project creator/founder), network launched Dec 2021","raised":"Backed by ParaFi, Multicoin, Borderless Capital and others; funded via token and hardware sales","token_symbol":"GEOD (primarily on Polygon, multichain to Solana via Wormhole)","token_price":"GEOD used to reward miners, pay for RTK data, and govern; 1B total supply; 80% of data revenue buys back and burns GEOD","market_metric":"~19,800+ active Satellite Miners across 5,000+ cities and 148 countries; 20,500+ RTK base stations; ~$5M annualized revenue (Q3 2025)","how_it_works":"Operators deploy Satellite Miners (GNSS reference stations) that compute real-time correction data from GPS/GLONASS/Galileo/BeiDou signals and stream it to devices within ~20-40km, delivering centimeter-level accuracy. Miners earn GEOD; data buyers pay for RTK access.","traction":"Largest decentralized RTK network globally; revenue grew 216.9% YoY to ~$1.2M in Q3 2025 (~$5M annualized); NRCAN RTK-compliant recognition (Sept 2025); Congressional testimony (Apr 2025); partners DroneDeploy, Quectel, Solana Mobile; GEOD burns hit ATH 3.8M in Q2 2025","backing_partners":"DroneDeploy, Quectel, FrodoBots, Solana Mobile, p2p.me, Natural Resources Canada, DePIN Union","business_model":"RTK data subscriptions/usage fees paid by robotics, drone, survey, and ag customers; 80% of revenue buys back and burns GEOD, aligning token value with real usage.","outlook":"Bull: becomes the location layer for the coming robotics/autonomy wave, with revenue-backed token burns among the best in DePIN. Base: steady revenue and station growth as precision-positioning demand rises. Bear: incumbent RTK providers (Trimble, Hexagon) and slow robotics adoption cap upside. Risk: hardware-dependent supply growth and reliance on continued robotics/drone demand.","status":"thriving","sources":["https://geodnet.com","https://messari.io/report/state-of-geodnet-q3-2025","https://depinscan.io/projects/geodnet","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/geodnet"]}','["https://geodnet.com","https://messari.io/report/state-of-geodnet-q3-2025","https://depinscan.io/projects/geodnet","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/geodnet"]','2026-07-08 17:44:59');
INSERT INTO "rwa_depin" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('io-net','io.net','depin-compute','steady','{"what_it_does":"io.net is a decentralized GPU compute network (DePIN) on Solana that aggregates idle GPUs from data centers, miners, and consumers into on-demand clusters for AI/ML workloads.","category":"depin-compute","founders":"Ahmad Shadid (founder), launched 2023 on Solana","raised":"$30M Series A (2024) led by Hack VC with Multicoin, Solana Ventures, Aptos, Delphi Digital and others","token_symbol":"IO (800M total supply cap)","token_price":"IO used for compute payments, node staking, and rewards; December 2025 Incentive Dynamic Engine (IDE) replaced fixed emissions with demand-driven burns targeting removal of 150M+ IO","market_metric":"Grew from ~60,000 verified GPUs (Mar 2024) to ~327,000 by Mar 2025 (5,350 cluster-ready), across 130+ countries","how_it_works":"GPU suppliers connect hardware and earn IO (or convert to USDC); developers spin up Ray-based clusters (e.g. 8x H100 NVLink pods) in minutes at up to 70% below AWS/GCP. Products: IO Cloud, IO Intelligence, IO Worker, IO Explorer.","traction":"~327k verified GPUs; documented case studies (Wondera saved $2.48M vs AWS; FrodoBots/UC Berkeley 92.8% savings on 12,696 GPU-hours); enterprise 8x H100 clusters; IDE tokenomics overhaul Dec 2025 ties burns to real compute usage","backing_partners":"Hack VC, Multicoin, Solana Ventures, Aptos, Delphi Digital","business_model":"Marketplace take-rate on GPU compute; suppliers paid in IO/USDC; at least 50% of remaining revenue after payouts is burned (post-IDE).","outlook":"Bull: rides explosive AI-compute demand as a cheaper decentralized alternative to hyperscalers, with IDE closing the emissions-vs-revenue gap. Base: steady niche demand for cost-optimized GPU pools. Bear: hyperscaler GPU supply loosens, Akash/Render compete on price, and token stays under emission pressure. Risk: historical gap between token emissions and real revenue; reliability/verification of decentralized GPUs.","status":"steady","sources":["https://io.net","https://io.net/blog/2025-io-net-year-in-review","https://messari.io/report/understanding-io-net-a-comprehensive-overview","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/io-net"]}','["https://io.net","https://io.net/blog/2025-io-net-year-in-review","https://messari.io/report/understanding-io-net-a-comprehensive-overview","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/io-net"]','2026-07-08 17:45:17');
INSERT INTO "rwa_depin" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('grass','Grass','depin-data','steady','{"what_it_does":"Grass is a decentralized web-scraping and AI-data network (a sovereign data rollup on Solana) that pays users for sharing idle residential bandwidth to collect public web data for AI training.","category":"depin-data","founders":"Andrej Radonjic (co-founder/CEO), Wynd Network, launched 2023","raised":"$4.5M seed/pre-seed (2023, Polychain, Tribe Capital, No Limit Holdings) + $10M bridge round (led by Polychain, Tribe)","token_symbol":"GRASS (1B fixed supply on Solana)","token_price":"GRASS launched Oct 2024 (rose ~$0.6 to $3.89 in 10 days); pressured by token unlocks and Season 2 airdrop supply (170M tokens)","market_metric":"2.5M+ active nodes across 190 countries; ~1,000 TB/day scraped (peaked at 1,700 TB ATH); 7,000+ TB delivered to foundation-model labs","how_it_works":"Users install a browser extension or mobile app turning their device into a Grass Node that scrapes public web data using idle bandwidth. Validators verify data and a ZK Processor produces zero-knowledge proofs of integrity, upgrading it into a sovereign data rollup. Revenue flows to the Grass Foundation; GRASS is the settlement asset.","traction":"2.5M+ nodes; Sion multimodal upgrade (May 2025) enabled 1PB+/day of text/image/4K-video scraping; dual-point reward system (Oct 2025); data sold to AI labs","backing_partners":"Polychain Capital, Tribe Capital, No Limit Holdings; Solana ecosystem","business_model":"AI/data buyers pay the Grass Foundation for structured web data; GRASS is the value-accrual and settlement token; node operators earn GRASS for bandwidth.","outlook":"Bull: becomes the ethically-sourced data layer for AI training as datacenter scraping gets blocked and demand for fresh web data soars. Base: steady node growth with lumpy data-sales revenue. Bear: uncertain, hard-to-verify data demand; token weakness from unlocks/airdrops. Risk: early-stage experimental network, regulatory scrutiny of scraping, and reliance on converting scraped volume into paying AI customers.","status":"steady","sources":["https://www.grass.io","https://blockworks.com/news/depin-grass-reshaping-ai-data-layer","https://solanacompass.com/projects/grass","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/grass"]}','["https://www.grass.io","https://blockworks.com/news/depin-grass-reshaping-ai-data-layer","https://solanacompass.com/projects/grass","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/grass"]','2026-07-08 17:45:40');
INSERT INTO "rwa_depin" ("slug","name","category","status","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('dimo','DIMO','depin-data','early','{"what_it_does":"DIMO is a decentralized connected-vehicle network (DePIN) that lets drivers connect their cars, own and control their vehicle data, and monetize it, while businesses access standardized vehicle data via API.","category":"depin-data","founders":"Alex Rawitz, Rob Solomon, Andy Chatham, and Yevgeny Khessin, founded 2021 in Brooklyn","raised":"$9M Series A led by CoinFund (2022); additional backing from Multicoin, Framework, and others","token_symbol":"DIMO","token_price":"DIMO ~$0.025, market cap ~$10M (2025), ~408M circulating; well below $0.7856 ATH (Dec 2023)","market_metric":"~184,000 active connected devices across 50+ vehicle brands; average device ~$300 with ~$0.80/day earnings","how_it_works":"Drivers connect vehicles via the DIMO mobile app (wireless for newer cars, an adapter for older ones), feeding standardized telemetry on-chain. Businesses pay protocol fees in DIMO to access the vehicle API; token also governs upgrades and reward distribution.","traction":"~184k active devices; ''session-based economy'' pivot (rentals, pay-per-use, usage-based insurance); Japan JV with Hakuhodo KEY3 (33% stake, June 2025) and Toyota Blockchain Lab partnership; Revolut listing (Aug 2025); bridge exploit Nov 2025 (~30M DIMO / ~$2.49M stolen, core network unaffected)","backing_partners":"CoinFund, Multicoin, Hakuhodo KEY3, Toyota Blockchain Lab, Revolut (listing)","business_model":"Businesses (insurers, OEMs, mobility services) pay protocol fees in DIMO to access aggregated, consented vehicle data; drivers earn tokens for sharing data.","outlook":"Bull: rides the $1T+ connected/software-defined vehicle market by 2030, becoming the neutral data layer OEMs and insurers build on. Base: slow, steady device growth with niche B2B data revenue. Bear: tiny market cap, hard consumer adoption, and OEMs keeping data proprietary. Risk: low token price limits incentives, security (bridge exploit), and dependence on automaker cooperation.","status":"early","sources":["https://dimo.org","https://depinscan.io/projects/dimo","https://decrypt.co/324771/startup-dimo-launches-depin-venture-in-japan-to-help-automakers-monetize-vehicle-data","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/dimo"]}','["https://dimo.org","https://depinscan.io/projects/dimo","https://decrypt.co/324771/startup-dimo-launches-depin-venture-in-japan-to-help-automakers-monetize-vehicle-data","https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/dimo"]','2026-07-08 17:46:01');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('AL','Alabama','Mixed','{"stance":"Mixed","preview":"Regulates crypto under money-transmitter law; explored a Bitcoin reserve bill that stalled.","governor":"Kay Ivey (R) — broadly supportive of business/blockchain but no strong personal crypto agenda.","legislature":"Republican-controlled; generally receptive to crypto but slow to enact dedicated frameworks.","regulation":"Digital-asset businesses need a money transmitter license from the Alabama Securities Commission / Banking Dept.; the framework closely tracks federal guidelines. No BitLicense-style regime, no enacted Bitcoin reserve.","legislators":"Bitcoin-reserve style measures (e.g. SB 283) introduced in 2025 to let the treasurer invest in digital assets; remained pending.","localities":"No notable municipal bans; some data-center/mining interest in low-cost-power areas.","orgs":"Alabama has a limited organized crypto footprint — no major in-state exchange or trade association; activity centers on individual investors and some mining/data-center interest. Stand With Crypto maintains an Alabama chapter.","people":"No nationally prominent crypto founders based in-state; the ecosystem is retail- and mining-driven rather than founder-led.","universities":"Auburn University and the University of Alabama offer computer-science and business coursework touching blockchain and cryptography, but neither runs a flagship dedicated blockchain research center.","gov_use":"No operational state/local blockchain deployment and no enacted reserve; the closest government step is the stalled 2025 SB 283, which would have let the state treasurer invest in digital assets.","upcoming":"Bitcoin reserve / digital-asset investment bills listed as pending in NCSL''s 2026 tracker.","overview":"Alabama takes a mixed, cautious posture: crypto businesses operate under standard money-transmitter licensing aligned with federal rules, and the state flirted with a Bitcoin reserve in 2025 without passing one. Republican leadership is friendly in tone but has not built a dedicated legal framework, and in-state industry/academic presence is modest.","sources":["https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://decrypt.co/330965/these-u-s-states-have-passed-bitcoin-reserve-laws","https://www.innreg.com/blog/us-crypto-regulation","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]}','["https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://decrypt.co/330965/these-u-s-states-have-passed-bitcoin-reserve-laws","https://www.innreg.com/blog/us-crypto-regulation","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]','2026-07-08 20:02:17');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('AK','Alaska','Mixed','{"stance":"Mixed","preview":"No state income tax and mining-friendly power, but limited dedicated crypto law.","governor":"Mike Dunleavy (R) — pro-resource-development, generally friendly to crypto/mining but no signature crypto policy.","legislature":"Politically split legislature; little dedicated crypto legislation enacted.","regulation":"Digital-asset money transmission regulated by the Division of Banking & Securities; Alaska historically required crypto/fiat businesses to obtain a money-transmitter license and enter a Limited Licensing Agreement, creating friction. No income or capital-gains tax on crypto.","legislators":"No prominent crypto champions; occasional blockchain study measures.","localities":"Cheap hydro and stranded gas make parts of Alaska attractive for mining; no municipal bans of note.","orgs":"Alaska has a very thin crypto-industry and advocacy footprint — no significant in-state exchange, custodian, or trade association; activity is mostly individual miners exploiting stranded energy. Stand With Crypto maintains an Alaska chapter, but organized crypto presence is minimal.","people":"No nationally prominent crypto founders based in-state; the ecosystem is driven by energy-arbitrage miners rather than notable individuals.","universities":"The University of Alaska system offers general computer-science coursework but has no dedicated blockchain research center or program of note; academic crypto activity is negligible.","gov_use":"No operational state or local blockchain deployment and no Bitcoin reserve; the state''s crypto relevance is economic (tax-free, cheap-energy mining) rather than governmental. The Permanent Fund has not made a public crypto allocation.","upcoming":"No major dedicated crypto bills advancing as of 2026.","overview":"Alaska is tax-friendly (no state income or capital-gains tax) and has cheap energy attractive to miners, but it lacks a comprehensive digital-asset framework, has minimal in-state industry, advocacy, or academic presence, and has made no government blockchain moves. Its posture is mixed — welcoming in economics, undeveloped in law and institutions.","sources":["https://www.cointracker.io/blog/crypto-friendly-states","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://wifpr.wharton.upenn.edu/50-state-review-of-cryptocurrency-and-blockchain-regulation/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]}','["https://www.cointracker.io/blog/crypto-friendly-states","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://wifpr.wharton.upenn.edu/50-state-review-of-cryptocurrency-and-blockchain-regulation/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]','2026-07-08 20:00:50');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('AZ','Arizona','Pro-crypto','{"stance":"Pro-crypto","preview":"Enacted a seized-asset Bitcoin reserve law in 2025; a purchase-based reserve was vetoed.","governor":"Katie Hobbs (D) — crypto-skeptical: vetoed SB 1025 (10% fund allocation) and HB 2324, but signed the narrower HB 2749 / reserve-fund bill in May 2025.","legislature":"Republican-led legislature strongly pro-crypto, repeatedly passing reserve bills that clashed with the Democratic governor.","regulation":"HB 2749 (signed May 2025) lets Arizona hold unclaimed/forfeited crypto in its original form, creating a de-facto seized-asset reserve; staking rewards/airdrops flow into a Bitcoin and Digital Assets Reserve Fund. A 2017 law authorized blockchain LLCs and recognized smart contracts; a 2022 law let agencies accept crypto payments. Money-transmitter licensing applies to exchanges.","legislators":"Rep. Jeff Weninger and Sen. Wendy Rogers championed Bitcoin reserve and digital-asset bills; Gov. Hobbs opposed the investment-based versions (''retirement funds are not the place for untested investments''). SB 1649 (seizure-based reserve) advanced in 2026.","localities":"Low-cost-power regions attract mining; no major municipal bans.","orgs":"Stand With Crypto maintains an Arizona chapter; Coinbase''s state-policy team has publicly praised Arizona as ''a national trailblazer on smart digital asset policy.'' The Arizona Blockchain Applied Research Center (AZ BARC, founded 2019 by the Partnership for Economic Innovation) links ASU with corporate members Intel, Early Warning Services, Kudelski Security (US HQ in Phoenix), BD and Movemedical. In-state/adopted crypto firms include Token IQ, Sweetbridge, and Propy (which closed Arizona''s first blockchain home purchase).","people":"Rep. Jeff Weninger and Sen. Wendy Rogers are the leading political champions. Dragan Boscovic founded the ASU Blockchain Research Lab. Kudelski Security''s Phoenix leadership drove the AZ BARC consortium.","universities":"Arizona State University runs the ASU Blockchain Research Lab (research across finance, CS, math, zero-knowledge proofs, smart contracts) and is the academic partner for AZ BARC; ASU has offered a blockchain-and-cryptocurrency law/honors class since 2018. Student group Blockchain at ASU is active.","gov_use":"Arizona created the Bitcoin and Digital Assets Reserve Fund (2025) to hold unclaimed/forfeited crypto in native form for three years before any sale, with staking/airdrop returns retained as digital assets — one of the first US state seized-asset crypto reserves. A 2022 law authorizes state agencies to accept cryptocurrency as payment.","upcoming":"Expect renewed reserve-investment bills in 2026 (e.g. SB 1649 seizure-based reserve) after the governor blocked the 2025 purchase version.","overview":"Arizona is one of only a few states to enact a Bitcoin reserve law, though Gov. Hobbs limited it to seized/unclaimed assets after vetoing bills that would let the state buy Bitcoin. The GOP legislature is aggressively pro-crypto, ASU anchors serious blockchain research, and a 2022 law lets agencies accept crypto — creating ongoing tension with a skeptical Democratic executive.","sources":["https://www.proskauer.com/blog/crypto-in-the-capitol-states-take-the-lead-on-strategic-bitcoin-reserves","https://decrypt.co/330965/these-u-s-states-have-passed-bitcoin-reserve-laws","https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/17/texas-us-states-budgets-bitcoin-crypto-strategic-reserve.html","https://www.axios.com/local/phoenix/2025/05/12/arizona-cryptocurrency-reserve-fund-unclaimed-property","https://blockchain.asu.edu/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]}','["https://www.proskauer.com/blog/crypto-in-the-capitol-states-take-the-lead-on-strategic-bitcoin-reserves","https://decrypt.co/330965/these-u-s-states-have-passed-bitcoin-reserve-laws","https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/17/texas-us-states-budgets-bitcoin-crypto-strategic-reserve.html","https://www.axios.com/local/phoenix/2025/05/12/arizona-cryptocurrency-reserve-fund-unclaimed-property","https://blockchain.asu.edu/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]','2026-07-08 19:51:45');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('AR','Arkansas','Mixed','{"stance":"Mixed","preview":"Swung from mining-friendly (Act 851) to restricting foreign-owned miners (Acts 173/174).","governor":"Sarah Huckabee Sanders (R) — signed mining-regulation legislation; broadly conservative, security-focused on foreign-owned miners.","legislature":"Republican-controlled; initially welcomed miners (Act 851, 2023) then reined them in with Acts 173 & 174 (2024).","regulation":"Act 851 of 2023 (Arkansas Data Centers Act, backed by the Satoshi Action Fund) limited local regulation of crypto mines; Acts 173 & 174 of 2024 restored local zoning/noise authority, banned prohibited-foreign-party ownership (targeting China), gave foreign owners a year to divest, created a mandatory permitting process via the Oil and Gas Commission, and empowered the AG to investigate. Money-transmitter licensing applies to exchanges.","legislators":"Legislators shifted from a mining-rights posture to national-security concerns over Chinese-linked mining; Sen. Bryan King filed 2025 bills to regulate data-center water/electricity use (allowing the PSC to halt utility service to a blockchain network if the grid is threatened). Rep. Andrew Collins (D) opposed the foreign-ownership provisions.","localities":"Rural towns — DeWitt, Bono/Greenbrier, Cabot (Lonoke County), and near Harrison — saw noise/nuisance disputes and litigation over mining farms enabled by the 2023 law.","orgs":"The pro-crypto lobbying group Satoshi Action Fund drove the 2023 right-to-mine law — the most influential external crypto-policy actor in the state. Arkansas has little home-grown crypto industry beyond mining operators (some foreign-linked). Stand With Crypto maintains an Arkansas chapter.","people":"No prominent resident crypto founders; the defining figures are policy actors — Satoshi Action Fund lobbyists who shaped Act 851, and legislators (Sen. Bryan King, Rep. Andrew Collins) on the regulatory-response side.","universities":"The University of Arkansas offers computer-science and Walton College business coursework touching blockchain, but there is no flagship dedicated blockchain research center; the state''s crypto story is mining policy, not academia.","gov_use":"No state blockchain adoption or reserve; government engagement is regulatory — the mandatory mining permit regime (Oil and Gas Commission), foreign-ownership divestment mandate, and proposed PSC authority to halt utility service to blockchain networks straining the grid.","upcoming":"Ongoing litigation over Act 174''s foreign-ownership provisions; further mining water/energy rules (Sen. King''s 2025 bills) possible.","overview":"Arkansas swung from one of the most mining-friendly states (2023 Data Centers Act, pushed by the Satoshi Action Fund) to a restrictive posture on foreign-owned miners with Acts 173/174 (2024), amid rural noise disputes and China-ownership security concerns. Crypto ownership is unencumbered, but industrial mining faces permitting, divestment mandates, and litigation — a mixed environment.","sources":["https://hallboothsmith.com/arkansas-crypto/","https://arkansasadvocate.com/2024/05/01/proposed-arkansas-crypto-mining-regulations-head-to-governors-desk/","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://river.com/learn/is-bitcoin-mining-legal/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]}','["https://hallboothsmith.com/arkansas-crypto/","https://arkansasadvocate.com/2024/05/01/proposed-arkansas-crypto-mining-regulations-head-to-governors-desk/","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://river.com/learn/is-bitcoin-mining-legal/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]','2026-07-08 20:01:11');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('CA','California','Restrictive','{"stance":"Restrictive","preview":"Its Digital Financial Assets Law (DFAL) now requires licensing with fines up to $100K/day.","governor":"Gavin Newsom (D) — signed DFAL; supports blockchain innovation but favors strong consumer-protection guardrails. His May 2022 EO directed agencies to explore blockchain in public services.","legislature":"Democratic supermajority; consumer-protection-oriented, enacted the nation''s second comprehensive digital-asset regime.","regulation":"The Digital Financial Assets Law (AB 39 / SB 401), effective July 1, 2026, requires any firm doing digital-asset business with Californians to be licensed by the DFPI or face civil penalties up to $100,000/day. Bitcoin-ATM operators face a $1,000/day transaction limit and disclosure rules.","legislators":"Assemblymember Tim Grayson authored AB 39 (DFAL). Enforcement already active: DFPI penalized Coinme ($300K, June 2025) and Nexo ($500K, Jan 2026).","localities":"Silicon Valley remains a crypto-industry hub, but the state framework is the dominant regulatory force.","orgs":"Stand With Crypto has a California state chapter (president Carrie ''Ms. NFTy'' Lin) plus college chapters (e.g. CSU Fullerton); California is a top SWC electoral target given ~8M+ crypto-owning adults. Major crypto companies HQ''d or rooted in CA: Ripple (San Francisco), Kraken (San Francisco), Coinbase (founded in SF, now remote-first / no HQ), plus a dense Silicon Valley VC and startup ecosystem (Paradigm, a16z crypto in Menlo Park).","people":"Brian Armstrong (Coinbase co-founder/CEO); Chris Larsen and Jed McCaleb (Ripple co-founders, Larsen a major SF-based crypto philanthropist/donor); Brad Garlinghouse (Ripple CEO); Fred Ehrsam (Paradigm, Coinbase co-founder). Dan Boneh (Stanford) is a leading academic figure.","universities":"Stanford Center for Blockchain Research (founded 2018 by Dan Boneh; runs CS251 Cryptocurrencies course, co-organizes the Science of Blockchain Conference) plus the Stanford Blockchain Accelerator and Blockchain Club. UC Berkeley: Berkeley RDI (Center for Responsible, Decentralized Intelligence), Haas Blockchain Initiative (Ripple-funded), Sutardja Center Blockchain X-Lab, and student-led Blockchain at Berkeley (built the first university-accredited blockchain course). USC, UCLA, and Caltech (Blockchain Bootcamp) also active.","gov_use":"California DMV digitized ~42 million car titles on a permissioned Avalanche (Ava Labs / Oxhead Alpha) blockchain, cutting title-transfer time from ~2 weeks to minutes and adding fraud detection; titles claimable via a DMV mobile wallet app (rollout from early 2025). Stems from Newsom''s May 2022 blockchain EO.","upcoming":"NMLS began accepting DFAL applications March 9, 2026; enforcement ramping through 2026.","overview":"California adopted the second comprehensive state crypto regime after New York. The DFAL is now live, requiring licensure with steep penalties and BitLicense-like consumer protections. Despite hosting much of the crypto industry (Ripple, Kraken, Coinbase roots, Silicon Valley VCs) and leading academic research (Stanford, Berkeley), California''s regulatory posture is decidedly restrictive and enforcement-heavy — though its DMV blockchain title project is a notable government adoption.","sources":["https://dfpi.ca.gov/regulated-industries/digital-financial-assets/digital-financial-assets-law-frequently-asked-questions/","https://www.techtimes.com/articles/319477/20260701/california-crypto-law-now-live-unlicensed-platforms-risk-100k-daily-fines.htm","https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://cbr.stanford.edu/","https://blockchain.berkeley.edu/","https://www.coindesk.com/business/2024/07/30/california-dmv-puts-42m-car-titles-on-the-avalanche-network-in-digitization-push"]}','["https://dfpi.ca.gov/regulated-industries/digital-financial-assets/digital-financial-assets-law-frequently-asked-questions/","https://www.techtimes.com/articles/319477/20260701/california-crypto-law-now-live-unlicensed-platforms-risk-100k-daily-fines.htm","https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://cbr.stanford.edu/","https://blockchain.berkeley.edu/","https://www.coindesk.com/business/2024/07/30/california-dmv-puts-42m-car-titles-on-the-avalanche-network-in-digitization-push"]','2026-07-08 19:49:27');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('CO','Colorado','Pro-crypto','{"stance":"Pro-crypto","preview":"Accepts crypto for state tax payments and markets itself as blockchain-friendly under Gov. Polis.","governor":"Jared Polis (D) — one of the most pro-crypto governors nationally; launched crypto tax payments and a ''digital token'' framework.","legislature":"Democratic-controlled but with genuine bipartisan crypto interest under Polis''s leadership.","regulation":"Colorado accepts cryptocurrency for state taxes/fees (via PayPal conversion) since 2022. The Colorado Digital Token Act (2019) exempts certain utility tokens from securities registration. Money-transmitter licensing applies to exchanges. Not a BitLicense state.","legislators":"Gov. Polis has been the driving force; the Digital Token Act (2019) had bipartisan sponsorship.","orgs":"Stand With Crypto Colorado chapter; the Colorado Blockchain (nonprofit advocacy group); active Denver/Boulder startup scene; ETHDenver, the world''s largest Ethereum/Web3 community conference, is held annually in Denver.","people":"Gov. Jared Polis (early Bitcoin adopter); ETHDenver/SporkDAO organizers; Boulder and Denver Web3 founders.","universities":"University of Colorado Boulder and Colorado School of Mines offer blockchain courses and research; CU Boulder has hosted blockchain/Web3 student organizations tied to the Denver ecosystem.","gov_use":"Colorado has accepted crypto (converted to USD via PayPal) for state taxes and fees since 2022 — among the first states to do so.","localities":"Denver/Boulder host active blockchain startup communities and ETHDenver; no municipal bans.","upcoming":"Continued expansion of blockchain use in government services; no major restrictive bills pending.","overview":"Colorado is a standout pro-crypto blue state, largely due to Gov. Polis, who made it among the first to accept crypto for tax payments and championed a utility-token exemption. Denver''s ETHDenver anchors a vibrant Web3 community, and state rules are light-touch over standard money-transmitter licensing.","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://www.cointracker.io/blog/crypto-friendly-states","https://ethdenver.com/","https://www.ncsl.org/"]}','["https://www.cointracker.io/blog/crypto-friendly-states","https://cryptoslate.com/crypto-laws/","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation"]','2026-07-08 19:21:39');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('CT','Connecticut','Restrictive','{"stance":"Restrictive","preview":"2025 law bans state acceptance of crypto and adds tight consumer-protection rules.","governor":"Ned Lamont (D) — signed HB 7082 (2025) restricting state crypto use; cautious, consumer-protection-focused.","legislature":"Democratic-controlled; enacted one of the more restrictive 2025 crypto consumer-protection laws.","regulation":"Connecticut regulates virtual currency under its money-transmitter licensing law. A 2025 law (Public Act 25-66 / HB 7082) bars the state and its agencies from accepting or holding cryptocurrency and adds strict rules on crypto kiosks (ATMs), fraud disclosures, and refunds. Earlier laws (SB 443, 2018; SB 1039, 2021) created a blockchain working group and RFI process.","legislators":"Democratic leaders emphasized elder-fraud and scam prevention as the rationale for the 2025 restrictions; earlier bipartisan interest set up a blockchain master-plan working group.","localities":"No notable crypto-friendly municipal initiatives; posture is uniformly cautious.","orgs":"Connecticut lacks a large in-state crypto industry cluster; activity centers on the Stamford/Greenwich hedge-fund corridor (some funds hold digital assets) rather than crypto-native firms. Stand With Crypto maintains a Connecticut chapter. The 2018 blockchain working group drew private-sector and expert input.","people":"No marquee crypto-native founders based in-state; the most relevant figures are hedge-fund/TradFi allocators in Fairfield County exploring digital assets. Former Economic and Community Development commissioner Catherine Smith chaired the state''s blockchain working group.","universities":"Yale (economics/computer-science faculty study cryptoeconomics; Yale-linked investors back crypto funds) and the University of Connecticut (UConn) offer blockchain and cryptography coursework, but neither runs a marquee dedicated blockchain research center.","gov_use":"Connecticut''s 2025 law explicitly PROHIBITS the state and its agencies from accepting or holding cryptocurrency — a deliberate non-use stance. Earlier legislation (SB 1039, 2021) required the Dept. of Administrative Services to issue an RFI on using blockchain to make a state function more efficient, but implementation stayed experimental.","upcoming":"Implementation of the 2025 kiosk/consumer-protection rules ongoing; no pro-crypto measures advancing.","overview":"Connecticut is among the most restrictive states: its 2025 law prohibits state government from accepting or investing in crypto and imposes tight rules on crypto ATMs and disclosures. Virtual-currency businesses operate under strict money-transmitter licensing, there is no significant crypto-native industry cluster, and the consumer-protection emphasis dominates — despite earlier working-group interest.","sources":["https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2025-legislation","https://statescoop.com/as-connecticut-forms-working-group-blockchain-remains-highly-experimental-in-state-governments/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]}','["https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2025-legislation","https://statescoop.com/as-connecticut-forms-working-group-blockchain-remains-highly-experimental-in-state-governments/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]','2026-07-08 19:57:50');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('DE','Delaware','Mixed','{"stance":"Mixed","preview":"Corporate-law hub that pioneered blockchain stock ledgers; now overhauling banking code for stablecoins.","governor":"Matt Meyer (D) — continues Delaware''s business-friendly tradition; no signature crypto agenda.","legislature":"Democratic-controlled; focused on corporate/banking law rather than dedicated crypto frameworks.","regulation":"Delaware amended its General Corporation Law in 2017 (effective Aug 1, 2017) to allow blockchain-based stock ledgers, a first-in-nation move treating blockchain shares as uncertificated securities. Crypto money transmission falls under standard licensing. In 2026, SB 16 (defining digital assets) and SB 19 (a stablecoin-issuer licensing framework) mark Delaware''s first banking-code overhaul since 1981.","legislators":"Corporate-bar-driven blockchain ledger reforms (from the Delaware Blockchain Initiative); 2026 Democratic-sponsored SB 16/SB 19 modernize banking law for stablecoins.","localities":"No notable municipal crypto actions.","orgs":"Delaware''s crypto footprint is corporate/legal rather than community-driven: ~65% of Fortune 500 and >50% of US public companies incorporate here, so most major crypto companies are Delaware entities even when HQ''d elsewhere. Stand With Crypto maintains a Delaware chapter. Elite corporate law firms (Potter Anderson, Richards Layton) advise on digital-asset governance.","people":"Andrea Tinianow (former Delaware Blockchain Ombudsman, architect of the Delaware Blockchain Initiative, dubbed the ''Blockchain Czarina''); former Gov. Jack Markell launched the initiative in 2016.","universities":"University of Delaware offers blockchain/fintech coursework within its business and engineering programs but has no flagship dedicated blockchain research center; the state''s relevance is driven by corporate law rather than academic labs.","gov_use":"The Delaware Blockchain Initiative (2016, under Gov. Markell with ombudsman Andrea Tinianow) explored a state-run blockchain for corporate stockholder records; it yielded the landmark 2017 DGCL amendment authorizing blockchain stock ledgers, though the envisioned state infrastructure was not built — the law simply lets corporations use blockchain themselves.","upcoming":"2026 banking-code overhaul (SB 16 digital-asset definitions, SB 19 stablecoin licensing); watching competitive pressure as firms (e.g. Coinbase, Tesla) reincorporate to Texas/Nevada.","overview":"Delaware''s crypto relevance flows from its dominance in corporate law — it was first to authorize blockchain stock ledgers (2017) via the Delaware Blockchain Initiative, and in 2026 it began its first banking-code overhaul since 1981 to license stablecoin issuers. It lacks a dedicated academic hub and faces competition from Texas/Wyoming for incorporations, giving it a mixed, business-pragmatic posture.","sources":["https://www.globallegalinsights.com/practice-areas/blockchain-cryptocurrency-laws-and-regulations/usa/","https://cryptoslate.com/crypto-laws/","https://www.aoshearman.com/en/insights/delawarepasseslawpermittingcompaniestouseblockchaintechnologytoissueandtrackshares","https://technical.ly/civic-news/delaware-blockchain-initiative/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]}','["https://www.globallegalinsights.com/practice-areas/blockchain-cryptocurrency-laws-and-regulations/usa/","https://cryptoslate.com/crypto-laws/","https://www.aoshearman.com/en/insights/delawarepasseslawpermittingcompaniestouseblockchaintechnologytoissueandtrackshares","https://technical.ly/civic-news/delaware-blockchain-initiative/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]','2026-07-08 19:56:40');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('DC','District of Columbia','Restrictive','{"stance":"Restrictive","preview":"Federal-district seat of national regulators and every major crypto advocacy group.","governor":"Mayor Muriel Bowser (D) — no dedicated crypto policy; local government cautious.","legislature":"DC Council (Democratic); focused on consumer protection, not crypto promotion.","regulation":"DC regulates money transmission (including virtual currency) under its Money Transmitters Act via DISB. As the seat of the SEC, CFTC, Treasury, and Congress, DC is dominated by the federal regulatory apparatus rather than local crypto law.","legislators":"DC Attorney General has pursued crypto-fraud enforcement; no crypto-championing local legislators of note.","localities":"N/A — DC is a single municipality; no crypto-friendly initiatives.","orgs":"DC is the epicenter of US crypto advocacy: Coin Center (2014 think tank/501c4, led the Tornado Cash sanctions legal challenge), the Blockchain Association (2018 trade group, CEO Summer Mersinger; members include Coinbase, Kraken, Aave), the Chamber of Digital Commerce, and the American Blockchain and Cryptocurrency Association are all headquartered here. Stand With Crypto (Coinbase-founded) runs its PAC and federal lobbying from DC and has a DC chapter.","people":"Peter Van Valkenburgh & Jerry Brito (Coin Center); Summer Mersinger (Blockchain Association CEO, former CFTC commissioner); Perianne Boring (Chamber of Digital Commerce founder). These are the industry''s leading DC policy voices.","universities":"Georgetown (law and business courses on digital assets/fintech policy) and American University''s Kogod School (blockchain coursework) offer programs; DC''s academic role is policy- and law-oriented rather than protocol research.","gov_use":"No District-level blockchain adoption; DC''s government significance is federal. National crypto law (GENIUS Act on stablecoins, market-structure bills) and every major regulator (SEC, CFTC, Treasury, Federal Reserve) sit here, making DC the decisive venue for US crypto policy.","upcoming":"Local activity minimal; national policy (GENIUS Act implementation, market-structure legislation) is decided here at the federal level.","overview":"Washington, DC''s crypto significance is overwhelmingly federal — it houses the SEC, CFTC, Treasury, and Congress, plus every major advocacy group (Coin Center, Blockchain Association, Chamber of Digital Commerce, Stand With Crypto''s PAC). Locally, the District regulates virtual-currency money transmission under standard licensing with a consumer-protection posture and no crypto-promotion agenda.","sources":["https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://sumsub.com/blog/us-crypto-regulations/","https://www.coincenter.org/welcome-to-the-party-blockchain-association/","https://theblockchainassociation.org/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]}','["https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://sumsub.com/blog/us-crypto-regulations/","https://www.coincenter.org/welcome-to-the-party-blockchain-association/","https://theblockchainassociation.org/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]','2026-07-08 19:57:31');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('FL','Florida','Pro-crypto','{"stance":"Pro-crypto","preview":"No income tax and a vocal pro-crypto governor; Miami is a national crypto hub. A 2025 Bitcoin reserve bill stalled.","governor":"Ron DeSantis (R) — outspokenly pro-crypto and anti-CBDC; signed a 2023 law banning a federal CBDC as money in Florida.","legislature":"Republican-controlled and crypto-friendly, though its 2025 Bitcoin reserve bills failed before adjournment.","regulation":"No state income tax. Florida banned recognition of a federal CBDC as money (2023). Crypto businesses need money-transmitter licensing via the Office of Financial Regulation (OFR). A pilot let some state fees be paid in crypto. Not a BitLicense state. No enacted Bitcoin reserve.","legislators":"CFO/legislative leaders backed reserve and pro-crypto bills; reserve efforts (HB 487/SB 550) died when the 2025 session adjourned May 2.","orgs":"Stand With Crypto Florida chapter; Miami hosts the annual Bitcoin Conference (BTC Inc); MoonPay is HQ''d in Miami; Blockchain.com relocated its US HQ to Miami. Strong VC/crypto-founder presence.","people":"Miami Mayor Francis Suarez (MiamiCoin, pro-crypto branding); MoonPay CEO Ivan Soto-Wright (Miami); numerous crypto founders and investors relocated to South Florida.","universities":"University of Miami, University of Florida, and Florida International University offer blockchain courses and host student blockchain organizations; UM has hosted crypto-industry programming tied to Miami''s ecosystem.","gov_use":"Florida piloted accepting crypto for certain state fees/taxes (via a payment processor); Miami experimented with MiamiCoin (CityCoins) yielding city revenue before the token declined.","localities":"Miami is a major crypto hub — Mayor Suarez championed MiamiCoin and pro-crypto branding; hosts the Bitcoin Conference.","upcoming":"Reserve bills expected to return in 2026 after the 2025 versions failed.","overview":"Florida is strongly pro-crypto: no income tax, an anti-CBDC law, and a governor and Miami mayor who actively court the industry. Miami anchors a dense crypto ecosystem (Bitcoin Conference, MoonPay, relocated founders). Its 2025 Bitcoin reserve push stalled at adjournment, but the overall climate remains among the most welcoming in the country.","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://www.cointracker.io/blog/crypto-friendly-states","https://decrypt.co/330965/these-u-s-states-have-passed-bitcoin-reserve-laws","https://www.ncsl.org/"]}','["https://www.cointracker.io/blog/crypto-friendly-states","https://decrypt.co/330965/these-u-s-states-have-passed-bitcoin-reserve-laws","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2025-legislation"]','2026-07-08 19:21:12');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('GA','Georgia','Pro-crypto','{"stance":"Pro-crypto","preview":"Major Bitcoin-mining hub with cheap power and a friendly business climate; light regulation.","governor":"Brian Kemp (R) — business-friendly; supportive of the data-center/mining economy, no dedicated crypto agenda.","legislature":"Republican-controlled; generally hands-off and mining-welcoming.","regulation":"Georgia licenses crypto money transmitters and in 2016 explicitly authorized the Dept. of Banking & Finance to regulate virtual currency. Low energy costs and a friendly climate have made it a top mining state; no restrictive mining moratorium. Not a BitLicense state.","legislators":"Occasional blockchain study and pro-crypto measures; no marquee champion or opponent.","orgs":"Stand With Crypto Georgia chapter; Atlanta is a fintech/payments capital (home to Global Payments, NCR, and much of US card-processing infrastructure); Bitcoin Depot (crypto-ATM operator) is HQ''d in Atlanta; large mining operations statewide.","people":"Atlanta fintech/payments executives; Bitcoin Depot leadership; mining operators drawn by cheap power.","universities":"Georgia Tech (strong CS/cryptography research and a blockchain student organization) and University of Georgia offer blockchain courses; Georgia Tech anchors campus blockchain research.","gov_use":"No state Bitcoin reserve or crypto-payment program of note; engagement is primarily the mining economy and fintech infrastructure rather than government on-chain use.","localities":"Home to large mining operations (e.g. around Adel/Cherokee); some local noise disputes but no bans of note.","upcoming":"Digital-asset/blockchain bills listed as pending in NCSL 2026; possible mining-siting rules.","overview":"Georgia is one of the country''s largest Bitcoin-mining hubs thanks to cheap electricity, and Atlanta is a national fintech/payments capital. Regulation is light — standard money-transmitter licensing — and Republican leadership has avoided the restrictive mining moratoriums seen elsewhere, keeping the state broadly pro-crypto.","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.gatech.edu/","https://www.ncsl.org/"]}','["https://www.cnbc.com/2022/11/23/new-york-governor-signs-law-cracking-down-on-bitcoin-mining.html","https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation"]','2026-07-08 19:21:54');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('HI','Hawaii','Restrictive','{"stance":"Restrictive","preview":"Historically one of the toughest states; ran the Digital Currency Innovation Lab sandbox, now easing toward normal licensing.","governor":"Josh Green (D) — cautious; supportive of the DCIL pilot''s move toward workable licensing.","legislature":"Democratic-controlled; long consumer-protection-focused, gradually modernizing crypto rules.","regulation":"Hawaii was historically the strictest state — its double-reserve money-transmitter interpretation drove Coinbase out in 2017. The Digital Currency Innovation Lab (DCIL) sandbox (2020–2024), run by DCCA''s Division of Financial Institutions with the Hawaii Technology Development Corp., let firms operate without a money-transmitter license via a ''no action'' message; in Jan 2024 the state concluded crypto firms no longer need a Hawaii MTL (though federal and general consumer-protection law still applies).","legislators":"DFI/DCCA leadership drove the sandbox; legislators have weighed permanent frameworks.","localities":"No notable crypto-friendly municipal actions.","orgs":"The state-run DCIL was the defining institution; participants included Gemini, BitFlyer, Coinme, River Financial, SoFi, Uphold, Flexa, and Apex Crypto — but the only Hawaii-based participant was Cloud Nalu, underscoring a thin in-state industry. The HTDC (Hawaii Technology Development Corp.) co-ran the program. Stand With Crypto maintains a Hawaii chapter.","people":"Hawaii lacks marquee resident crypto founders; the notable figures are the DCCA/DFI and HTDC officials who designed the DCIL sandbox, widely praised by participants as unusually collaborative among state regulators.","universities":"The University of Hawaii offers computer-science and information-systems coursework touching blockchain, but the state has no flagship dedicated blockchain research center; its distinctive contribution is regulatory (the DCIL experiment) rather than academic.","gov_use":"Hawaii''s signature government initiative is regulatory rather than adoption: the Digital Currency Innovation Lab (2020–2024), a first-of-its-kind state sandbox jointly run by DFI and HTDC to study whether/how to regulate digital-currency firms — concluding that crypto companies no longer require a state money-transmitter license.","upcoming":"Legislation to formalize post-sandbox licensing treatment expected.","overview":"Hawaii earned a reputation as the hardest state for crypto after its reserve-doubling rule forced Coinbase out in 2017. The pioneering DCIL sandbox (2020–2024) later let firms operate and led the state to conclude crypto no longer needs a special money-transmitter license — an innovative regulatory arc — but a thin in-state industry and consumer-protection tilt keep it in the restrictive column.","sources":["https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://sumsub.com/blog/us-crypto-regulations/","https://cca.hawaii.gov/blog/digital-currency-innovation-lab-concludes/","https://cca.hawaii.gov/dfi/digital-currency-innovation-lab-2020/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]}','["https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://sumsub.com/blog/us-crypto-regulations/","https://cca.hawaii.gov/blog/digital-currency-innovation-lab-concludes/","https://cca.hawaii.gov/dfi/digital-currency-innovation-lab-2020/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]','2026-07-08 20:00:35');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('ID','Idaho','Pro-crypto','{"stance":"Pro-crypto","preview":"Conservative, light-touch state that doesn''t require money-transmitter licensing for many crypto-only activities.","governor":"Brad Little (R) — business-friendly conservative; supportive of light regulation, no signature crypto law.","legislature":"Strongly Republican; libertarian-leaning and receptive to crypto and anti-CBDC measures.","regulation":"Idaho notably does NOT require a money-transmitter license for many virtual-currency-only activities, making entry easier. No BitLicense, no income-tax quirks targeting crypto. Broadly permissive.","legislators":"GOP legislators have floated anti-CBDC and digital-asset-rights bills; measures listed pending in NCSL 2026.","orgs":"Stand With Crypto Idaho chapter; small but active local Bitcoin/mining community; cheap-power regions attract miners.","people":"Boise-area developers and small-scale miners; libertarian-leaning crypto advocates.","universities":"Boise State University and University of Idaho offer computing coursework with blockchain relevance; smaller campus crypto footprint than larger states.","gov_use":"No state Bitcoin reserve or crypto-payment program; the state''s posture is permissive/light-touch rather than participatory.","localities":"Cheap power in some regions supports small-scale mining; no municipal bans.","upcoming":"Digital-asset and blockchain bills pending per NCSL''s 2026 tracker.","overview":"Idaho takes a light-touch, permissive stance — notably not requiring money-transmitter licenses for many crypto-only businesses. Its conservative, libertarian-leaning legislature is receptive to digital-asset-rights and anti-CBDC bills, placing it comfortably in the pro-crypto camp despite limited landmark legislation.","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://legalclarity.org/a-state-by-state-look-at-cryptocurrency-laws/","https://www.ncsl.org/"]}','["https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://legalclarity.org/a-state-by-state-look-at-cryptocurrency-laws/","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation"]','2026-07-08 19:22:08');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('IL','Illinois','Restrictive','{"stance":"Restrictive","preview":"Enacted the Midwest''s first comprehensive crypto consumer-protection law in 2025.","governor":"JB Pritzker (D) — signed the Digital Assets and Consumer Protection Act (Aug 2025); consumer-protection-focused.","legislature":"Democratic-controlled; enacted comprehensive digital-asset oversight in 2025.","regulation":"The Digital Assets and Consumer Protection Act (SB 1797), signed Aug 19, 2025, gives the IDFPR authority to supervise digital-asset exchanges and business activity, requires registration, clear disclosures, and adequate capital/liquidity. Effective phased into 2027. DFPR earlier issued Digital Currency Regulatory Guidance under the Transmitters of Money Act.","legislators":"Democratic sponsors framed SB 1797 as first-in-the-Midwest consumer protection; paired with a companion consumer bill.","localities":"Chicago hosts major derivatives exchanges (CME) trading crypto futures; Cook County ran an early blockchain land-records pilot; no municipal bans.","orgs":"The Illinois Blockchain Association is a web3 advocacy coalition unifying industry voices and lobbying on policy; the earlier state-led Illinois Blockchain Initiative united DCEO, DFPR, DOI, DoIT and the Cook County Recorder. Stand With Crypto has an Illinois chapter. Chicago hosts CME Group (crypto futures/options), Block Inc. and Robinhood operations, plus firms like EZ Blockchain (flared-gas mining) and Hacken (smart-contract audits).","people":"Prof. Andrew Miller (UIUC Decentralized Systems Lab director, IC3 associate director, NSF CAREER awardee) is a leading academic; John Mirkovic led the Cook County Recorder blockchain work. Vitalik Buterin (Ethereum) has close ties, having grown up partly in the Toronto area but engaging with the UIUC Illini Blockchain community.","universities":"UIUC is a top blockchain university: the Decentralized Systems Lab (Andrew Miller), courses including CS521 (Technological Foundations of Blockchain), and student groups Illini Blockchain, CryptoClub, and a DeFi club (the 2022 Illini Blockchain Summit featured Vitalik Buterin). Also active: Northwestern Kellogg and its FinTech Bootcamp, Illinois Institute of Technology, DePaul''s Driehaus College, and Gies College of Business online blockchain courses.","gov_use":"Cook County Recorder of Deeds ran a pioneering blockchain land-records pilot (from 2016, with velox.RE on the Bitcoin blockchain), targeting ~2,000 vacant Chicago properties to build ''digital property abstracts'' and a legal blockchain-conveyance framework — among the earliest US government real-estate blockchain efforts. The statewide Illinois Blockchain Initiative explored government blockchain applications across multiple agencies.","upcoming":"IDFPR rulemaking and phased implementation of the 2025 Act through 2026–2027.","overview":"Illinois became the first Midwestern state with a comprehensive digital-asset consumer-protection regime when Gov. Pritzker signed SB 1797 in August 2025, empowering IDFPR to license and supervise crypto businesses. The registration-heavy approach places it in the restrictive column, even as Chicago anchors crypto derivatives (CME), UIUC leads academic research, and Cook County pioneered blockchain land records.","sources":["https://www.goodwinlaw.com/en/insights/blogs/2025/09/state-regulators-increase-regulations-of-crypto-exchanges-despite-industry-pushback","https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2025-legislation","https://illinoisblockchain.tech/blockchain-cook-county-final-report-1f56ab3bf89","https://decentralize.ece.illinois.edu/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]}','["https://www.goodwinlaw.com/en/insights/blogs/2025/09/state-regulators-increase-regulations-of-crypto-exchanges-despite-industry-pushback","https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2025-legislation","https://illinoisblockchain.tech/blockchain-cook-county-final-report-1f56ab3bf89","https://decentralize.ece.illinois.edu/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]','2026-07-08 19:54:38');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('IN','Indiana','Mixed','{"stance":"Mixed","preview":"Business-friendly but with limited dedicated crypto law; reserve/anti-CBDC bills floated.","governor":"Mike Braun (R) — pro-business conservative; open to crypto but no signature policy yet.","legislature":"Republican-controlled; receptive in tone, cautious in enactment.","regulation":"Indiana regulates crypto money transmission under its money-transmitter law; the Dept. of Financial Institutions says no money-transmitter license is needed for simple consumer buy/sell of virtual currency. SB 188 (2021) folded cryptocurrency into the Revised Uniform Unclaimed Property Act. No BitLicense, no enacted Bitcoin reserve. Anti-CBDC and digital-asset bills have been introduced.","legislators":"GOP legislators introduced anti-CBDC and Bitcoin-rights measures; none landmark as of 2026.","localities":"No notable municipal crypto actions.","orgs":"Indiana has a modest crypto footprint centered on Indianapolis; example firms include Blockade Games (blockchain gaming). No large statewide advocacy body dominates, though Stand With Crypto maintains an Indiana chapter.","people":"No marquee crypto-native founders based in-state; activity is startup- and hobbyist-driven rather than led by prominent figures.","universities":"Purdue University (computer science/cryptography strength) and Indiana University (Kelley School fintech, informatics) offer blockchain and cryptography coursework and student interest, but neither runs a flagship dedicated blockchain research center.","gov_use":"No operational state/local blockchain deployment; the main government touchpoint is SB 188 (2021), which brings unclaimed cryptocurrency under the state''s unclaimed-property regime. Anti-CBDC bills reflect a defensive rather than adoption-oriented stance.","upcoming":"Digital-asset/anti-CBDC bills pending per NCSL 2026 tracker.","overview":"Indiana is business-friendly and Republican-led but slow to build dedicated crypto law, relying on standard money-transmitter licensing and a 2021 unclaimed-property update. Anti-CBDC and Bitcoin-rights bills have appeared without becoming landmarks, and the in-state industry/academic footprint (Indianapolis startups, Purdue/IU coursework) is modest — leaving a mixed, wait-and-see posture.","sources":["https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://builtin.com/companies/location/indianapolis/type/blockchain-companies","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]}','["https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://builtin.com/companies/location/indianapolis/type/blockchain-companies","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]','2026-07-08 19:59:42');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('IA','Iowa','Mixed','{"stance":"Mixed","preview":"Recognizes blockchain records/smart contracts (2022) and floated public-fund crypto investment.","governor":"Kim Reynolds (R) — conservative, business-friendly; no dedicated crypto agenda.","legislature":"Republican-controlled; anti-CBDC leaning, moderate crypto legislating.","regulation":"Iowa enacted HF 2445 (2022) recognizing distributed-ledger technology and smart contracts and amending the UCC to govern controllable electronic records. Virtual-currency businesses are licensed under the Uniform Money Services Act (Coinbase, Binance, Gemini registered). HF 246/SF 403 would let Iowa invest public funds in digital assets; SF 449 would regulate crypto ATMs. No enacted reserve.","legislators":"GOP legislators raised anti-CBDC and financial-privacy themes and filed public-fund digital-asset investment bills; no marquee crypto champion.","localities":"Some data-center growth; no notable crypto-specific municipal actions.","orgs":"Iowa has a limited organized crypto footprint — no major in-state exchange or trade association. Stand With Crypto maintains an Iowa chapter (Iowa''s early presidential-caucus status draws periodic crypto-advocacy attention).","people":"No nationally prominent crypto founders based in-state; activity is retail- and policy-driven.","universities":"University of Iowa and Iowa State offer computer-science/business coursework touching blockchain, but neither runs a flagship dedicated blockchain research center.","gov_use":"No operational blockchain deployment; government engagement is legislative — the 2022 law giving legal recognition to blockchain records and smart contracts, plus pending bills (HF 246/SF 403) that would authorize public-fund investment in digital assets.","upcoming":"Public-fund digital-asset investment (HF 246/SF 403) and crypto-ATM regulation (SF 449) bills pending per NCSL tracking.","overview":"Iowa maintains a moderate posture: it legally recognizes blockchain records and smart contracts (2022 UCC update) and licenses crypto under money-services law, while GOP legislators show anti-CBDC sentiment and have floated public-fund crypto investment and crypto-ATM rules. With modest in-state industry and no enacted reserve, its net posture is mixed.","sources":["https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://www.bitcoinlaws.io/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]}','["https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://www.bitcoinlaws.io/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]','2026-07-08 20:02:31');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('KS','Kansas','Mixed','{"stance":"Mixed","preview":"Consumer-protection focus on crypto ATMs; a KPERS pension Bitcoin-ETF bill and blockchain LLC records law.","governor":"Laura Kelly (D) — pragmatic; supportive of crypto-ATM fraud protections.","legislature":"Republican-controlled legislature with a Democratic governor; mixed output.","regulation":"Kansas passed 2025 legislation adding consumer protections and transaction limits for crypto kiosks/ATMs to combat elder fraud. A 2021 State Bank Commissioner guidance clarified that pure crypto-transmission does not require a state money-transmitter license. HB 2039 (2019) lets LLCs keep records on distributed/blockchain databases. SB 34 would authorize KPERS (state pension) to invest in Bitcoin ETPs.","legislators":"Bipartisan support for the 2025 crypto-ATM consumer-protection law; SB 34 (KPERS Bitcoin-ETF investment) advanced by pro-crypto sponsors.","localities":"No notable crypto-friendly municipal initiatives.","orgs":"Kansas has a limited organized crypto footprint — no major in-state exchange or trade association. Stand With Crypto maintains a Kansas chapter. Policy activity centers on the legislature and the Office of the State Bank Commissioner rather than industry groups.","people":"No nationally prominent crypto founders based in-state; activity is policy- and retail-driven.","universities":"University of Kansas and Kansas State offer computer-science/business coursework touching blockchain, but neither runs a flagship dedicated blockchain research center.","gov_use":"No operational blockchain deployment; the notable government angle is SB 34, which would let the Kansas Public Employees Retirement System (KPERS) invest in Bitcoin exchange-traded products — a pension-level rather than treasury-reserve approach. HB 2039 (2019) permits blockchain-based LLC recordkeeping.","upcoming":"KPERS Bitcoin-ETP bill (SB 34) and other digital-asset bills pending per NCSL 2026 tracker.","overview":"Kansas blends consumer protection — 2025 rules limiting crypto-ATM transactions to fight scams — with pro-crypto measures like a 2019 blockchain-LLC-records law and SB 34 authorizing pension (KPERS) Bitcoin-ETF investment. With divided government (GOP legislature, Democratic governor) and modest in-state industry, its net posture is genuinely mixed.","sources":["https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://cryptoslate.com/market-reports/tracking-bitcoin-bills-a-state-by-state-breakdown-of-us-crypto-legislation/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]}','["https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://cryptoslate.com/market-reports/tracking-bitcoin-bills-a-state-by-state-breakdown-of-us-crypto-legislation/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]','2026-07-08 20:02:46');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('KY','Kentucky','Pro-crypto','{"stance":"Pro-crypto","preview":"Among the first states to enshrine Bitcoin self-custody rights and node-operator protections (HB 701).","governor":"Andy Beshear (D) — signed HB 701 protecting crypto rights; pragmatic and pro-innovation.","legislature":"Republican supermajority; strongly pro-crypto, passed HB 701 with broad support.","regulation":"HB 701 (2025) protects individual self-custody rights, exempts Bitcoin node operators and stakers from money-transmitter licensing, and bars new taxes on digital-asset payments. Kentucky also offered mining energy incentives (2021 tax breaks). Not a BitLicense state.","legislators":"HB 701 sponsored by Rep. Adam Bowling and colleagues; framed as a ''Bitcoin Rights'' law.","orgs":"Stand With Crypto Kentucky chapter; Satoshi Action Fund model policy behind HB 701; former coal regions repurposed for mining draw operators (e.g. facilities tied to earlier state incentives).","people":"Rep. Adam Bowling as legislative champion; mining operators leveraging cheap Appalachian power.","universities":"University of Kentucky and University of Louisville offer computing/fintech coursework and host student technology organizations with blockchain interest.","gov_use":"No state Bitcoin reserve; Kentucky''s engagement is rights-protective and mining-incentive-driven (2021 energy tax breaks) rather than treasury participation.","localities":"Former coal regions repurposed for mining with cheap power; state incentives drew miners.","upcoming":"Possible follow-on digital-asset bills building on the 2025 rights framework.","overview":"Kentucky is a clear pro-crypto leader: HB 701 (2025) made it among the first states to enshrine self-custody rights, exempt node operators from money-transmitter licensing, and block new taxes on crypto payments. Combined with earlier mining tax incentives that repurposed coal-region power, it has one of the most crypto-forward statutory frameworks in the country.","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://decrypt.co/330965/these-u-s-states-have-passed-bitcoin-reserve-laws","https://www.bitcoinlaws.io/","https://www.ncsl.org/"]}','["https://decrypt.co/330965/these-u-s-states-have-passed-bitcoin-reserve-laws","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2025-legislation","https://www.bitcoinlaws.io/"]','2026-07-08 19:22:20');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('LA','Louisiana','Pro-crypto','{"stance":"Pro-crypto","preview":"Passed a Blockchain Basics / crypto-rights law; reserve and digital-asset bills advancing.","governor":"Jeff Landry (R) — conservative, pro-crypto; supportive of digital-asset rights legislation.","legislature":"Republican-controlled; enacted crypto self-custody protections and considered a reserve.","regulation":"Louisiana passed a 2025 ''Blockchain Basics''-style law protecting self-custody, node operation, and mining rights, and barring discriminatory treatment of digital-asset payments. Money-transmitter licensing applies to exchanges. Notably, Louisiana became the first state to accept crypto for some state services (Treasury/Wallet of Satoshi pilot) in 2024. Not a BitLicense state.","legislators":"GOP sponsors advanced the crypto-rights and reserve measures; reserve bill considered but not fully enacted.","orgs":"Stand With Crypto Louisiana chapter; Satoshi Action Fund model policy; cheap Gulf-region energy attracts mining operators.","people":"State Treasurer John Fleming, who championed accepting crypto for state services; GOP legislative sponsors.","universities":"Louisiana State University (LSU) and Tulane University offer computing/fintech coursework and host student technology organizations.","gov_use":"Louisiana''s State Treasury began accepting cryptocurrency (via Bitcoin Lightning / Wallet of Satoshi and a processor) for certain state services in 2024 — an early government adoption of crypto payments.","localities":"Cheap Gulf-region energy supports mining; no municipal bans of note.","upcoming":"Bitcoin-reserve and further digital-asset bills pending per NCSL 2026.","overview":"Louisiana joined the wave of states enacting ''Blockchain Basics'' crypto-rights protections in 2025, safeguarding self-custody, mining, and node operation, and it was an early adopter of accepting crypto for state services. With a pro-crypto Republican governor and legislature and pending reserve bills, its trajectory is firmly pro-crypto.","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://www.ncsl.org/","https://www.bitcoinlaws.io/","https://www.treasury.la.gov/"]}','["https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2025-legislation","https://www.bitcoinlaws.io/","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation"]','2026-07-08 19:22:40');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('ME','Maine','Restrictive','{"stance":"Restrictive","preview":"Cautious, consumer-protection state with money-transmitter licensing and little pro-crypto law.","governor":"Janet Mills (D) — cautious; no crypto-promotion agenda.","legislature":"Democratic-controlled; consumer-protection-focused, limited crypto legislating.","regulation":"Maine requires money-transmitter licensing for virtual-currency businesses. No BitLicense, no Bitcoin reserve. Maine was among states that had not introduced dedicated digital-asset legislation in recent sessions; some study/consumer bills pending.","legislators":"No prominent crypto champions; emphasis on consumer protection and fraud.","localities":"No notable crypto-friendly municipal initiatives.","orgs":"Maine has a minimal organized crypto footprint — no major in-state exchange, custodian, or trade association. Stand With Crypto maintains a Maine chapter, but organized industry presence is negligible.","people":"No nationally prominent crypto founders based in-state; the ecosystem is retail-driven.","universities":"The University of Maine offers computer-science coursework touching cryptography/blockchain, but there is no dedicated university blockchain research center or program of note.","gov_use":"No operational state or local blockchain deployment and no reserve; Maine''s posture is regulatory (standard money-transmitter licensing) rather than adoption-oriented, and it has been one of the least active states on dedicated crypto legislation.","upcoming":"Digital-asset bills listed as pending in NCSL 2026 tracker.","overview":"Maine takes a cautious, consumer-protection-oriented approach, regulating crypto under standard money-transmitter licensing with no dedicated pro-crypto framework, reserve, or notable in-state industry/academic presence. Its Democratic leadership has not pursued crypto promotion and it ranks among the least legislatively active states, keeping it in the restrictive-leaning column.","sources":["https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://wifpr.wharton.upenn.edu/50-state-review-of-cryptocurrency-and-blockchain-regulation/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]}','["https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://wifpr.wharton.upenn.edu/50-state-review-of-cryptocurrency-and-blockchain-regulation/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]','2026-07-08 20:03:18');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('MD','Maryland','Restrictive','{"stance":"Restrictive","preview":"Consumer-protection-focused; a 2025 blockchain task force and a real-property title pilot underway.","governor":"Wes Moore (D) — no dedicated crypto agenda; cautious posture, but administration stood up a 2025 blockchain task force.","legislature":"Democratic-controlled; consumer-protection-oriented, now studying blockchain via a formal task force.","regulation":"Maryland regulates virtual-currency money transmission under standard licensing via the Office of Financial Regulation, which has issued warnings on crypto risks. No BitLicense, no reserve. A Task Force on Blockchain & Innovative Tech (est. July 30, 2025) is to report to the Governor and General Assembly by Oct 1, 2026.","legislators":"Emphasis on consumer/fraud protection; the 2025 task force pairs legislators with state officials and industry experts to chart a legislative roadmap.","localities":"No notable crypto-friendly municipal initiatives.","orgs":"The Maryland Blockchain Association (MDBA) is the lead advocacy body — co-leads the state''s 2025 blockchain task force, runs education programs and a summer conference, and received the Digital Chamber''s first State Network microgrant. The Maryland Tech Council is a partner. Stand With Crypto participates via Gilberto Nazario (Web3MD & SWC). Government Blockchain Association and Global Blockchain Business Council also engaged.","people":"Gilberto Nazario (Web3MD, Stand With Crypto) sits on the state task force; Maryland Blockchain Association leadership drives advocacy and education.","universities":"The University of Maryland system and Johns Hopkins University conduct blockchain/AI/Web3 research and collaborate with state agencies; university blockchain clubs are eligible for Digital Chamber microgrants. Johns Hopkins offers cryptography and distributed-systems research strength.","gov_use":"Maryland''s Task Force on Blockchain & Innovative Tech (2025) is evaluating government applications; a Blockchain-Based Real Property Title Pilot Study was submitted as committee testimony in March 2026. The Dept. of Information Technology (DoIT) is positioned to implement blockchain for state operations and digital services.","upcoming":"Task force report due Oct 1, 2026; real-property title pilot under study; digital-asset consumer-protection bills pending per NCSL 2026.","overview":"Maryland''s posture is cautious and consumer-protection-driven — crypto is regulated under standard money-transmitter licensing with regulator warnings — but the state is actively studying blockchain via a 2025 task force (co-led by the Maryland Blockchain Association) and a real-property title pilot, with Johns Hopkins and the University of Maryland contributing research. Restrictive-leaning but increasingly engaged.","sources":["https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://marylandblockchainassociation.org/md-task-force/","https://mgaleg.maryland.gov/cmte_testimony/2026/ecm/34263_03112026_175521-103.pdf","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]}','["https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://marylandblockchainassociation.org/md-task-force/","https://mgaleg.maryland.gov/cmte_testimony/2026/ecm/34263_03112026_175521-103.pdf","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]','2026-07-08 19:58:09');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('MA','Massachusetts','Restrictive','{"stance":"Restrictive","preview":"Aggressive securities enforcement; a GOP Bitcoin reserve bill faces a Democratic majority.","governor":"Maura Healey (D) — as former AG pursued crypto enforcement; cautious, consumer-protection-focused.","legislature":"Democratic supermajority; skeptical of state crypto investment, enforcement-minded.","regulation":"Massachusetts applies securities and money-transmitter law aggressively; its Securities Division has been among the most active enforcers. No BitLicense, no reserve. A Republican-filed Bitcoin reserve bill faces long odds in the Democratic legislature.","legislators":"GOP legislators filed a Bitcoin reserve bill; Democratic majority unlikely to advance it. Rep. Kate Lipper-Garabedian is advancing a bill to create a state blockchain and cryptocurrency commission. Ex-Secretary Galvin''s office known for enforcement.","localities":"Boston is a fintech hub, but Mayor Wu has confirmed no blockchain/crypto initiatives; some firms have opened Miami offices.","orgs":"Stand With Crypto maintains a Massachusetts chapter. Boston hosts a strong private cluster: Circle (USDC issuer, NYSE: CRCL), Algorand (Silvio Micali''s protocol), Flipside Crypto, plus VC backers like General Catalyst (invested in Circle, Bitwise). Fidelity (Boston) was an early mover, offering crypto in some 401(k)s and running Fidelity Digital Assets. The MIT Bitcoin Club organizes the MIT Bitcoin Expo/Hackathon.","people":"Jeremy Allaire (Circle co-founder/CEO); Silvio Micali (Algorand founder, MIT Turing Award laureate); Neha Narula (director, MIT Digital Currency Initiative); Anders Brownworth (DCI senior research advisor).","universities":"MIT is a global anchor via the Digital Currency Initiative (DCI, in the Media Lab; director Neha Narula) — historically central to Bitcoin Core development and CBDC research (Project Hamilton with the Boston Fed), and recent work on stablecoin risk under the GENIUS Act. MIT also hosts the MIT Bitcoin Club; Harvard and other Boston-area schools offer blockchain coursework.","gov_use":"State government is notably hands-off — no state or Boston municipal blockchain program; officials confirmed no crypto initiatives. The most consequential public-sector work is research-adjacent (MIT DCI''s Project Hamilton CBDC prototype with the Federal Reserve Bank of Boston).","upcoming":"Republican Bitcoin reserve bill and Rep. Lipper-Garabedian''s blockchain-commission bill pending, both facing a cautious majority.","overview":"Massachusetts is enforcement-heavy and skeptical at the state level: its securities regulators are among the most aggressive nationally, and pro-crypto bills face a Democratic supermajority. Yet Boston/Cambridge is a heavyweight private and academic hub — Circle, Algorand, Fidelity, and MIT''s Digital Currency Initiative — built, by legislators'' own admission, largely without state support.","sources":["https://www.bitget.com/amp/news/detail/12560604995399","https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://www.dci.mit.edu/","https://mgmtboston.com/circle/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]}','["https://www.bitget.com/amp/news/detail/12560604995399","https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://www.dci.mit.edu/","https://mgmtboston.com/circle/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]','2026-07-08 19:55:30');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('MI','Michigan','Mixed','{"stance":"Mixed","preview":"Pension funds hold Bitcoin ETFs; multiple pro-crypto bills advancing after gridlock.","governor":"Gretchen Whitmer (D) — pragmatic; no signature crypto law but tolerant of pension crypto exposure.","legislature":"Closely divided; a package of pro-crypto bills (reserve, anti-CBDC, rights) is advancing after months of deadlock.","regulation":"Michigan regulates crypto money transmission under standard licensing. The state pension system (SMRS) already holds Bitcoin-ETF shares. HB 4510 would permit (not require) pension fiduciaries to consider digital-asset ETPs; a companion bill establishes digital property rights and protects blockchain software development.","legislators":"Bipartisan sponsors introduced bills including HB 4510 (retirement-fund Bitcoin ETP investment) and digital-property-rights/anti-CBDC measures; advancing after legislative deadlock.","localities":"Detroit accepted crypto for some city tax/fee payments (2024 pilot) and hosted the Stand With Crypto ''America Loves Crypto'' tour.","orgs":"Detroit Blockchain Collective (founder Elizabeth Hansson, who is also Stand With Crypto Michigan President) is the state''s largest blockchain community group; the Michigan Blockchain Council (miblockchain.org) is the premier industry association. Detroit Ledger Technologies is a Detroit node provider. Stand With Crypto counts ~25,000 Michigan members among ~940,000 crypto owners in this battleground state; Detroit was a stop on its America Loves Crypto tour.","people":"Elizabeth Hansson (Detroit Blockchain Collective founder, SWC Michigan president); Adam Zientarski (Detroit Blockchain Center policy director, warns talent leaves for TX/CA/NY); Evan Solomon (Michigan Blockchain student-club president).","universities":"University of Michigan hosts the student-run Michigan Blockchain org (a founding member of a cross-university DAO) with Ross School of Business support; Ross offers a FinTech course covering blockchain, crypto, and smart contracts. Active student/community groups also at Michigan State, Wayne State, and Grand Valley State.","gov_use":"Detroit piloted accepting cryptocurrency for certain city tax and fee payments (announced 2024). At the state level, the SMRS pension system holds Bitcoin-ETF shares, and pending HB 4510 would formalize pension digital-asset ETP investment.","upcoming":"Multi-bill crypto package pending, including pension Bitcoin-ETP investment (HB 4510), digital property rights, and anti-CBDC measures.","overview":"Michigan sits in the mixed column: its pension system is an early Bitcoin-ETF investor, Detroit piloted crypto tax payments, and a pro-crypto bill package (pension ETPs, property rights, anti-CBDC) is advancing after gridlock. A vibrant Detroit/UMich community exists (Detroit Blockchain Collective, Michigan Blockchain), but advocates warn talent leaves for friendlier states absent clearer policy.","sources":["https://www.ccn.com/news/crypto/us-states-strategic-bitcoin-reserve-2025/","https://decrypt.co/330965/these-u-s-states-have-passed-bitcoin-reserve-laws","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://www.michiganblockchain.org/","https://bitcoinmagazine.com/politics/detroit-aims-to-drive-digital-asset-innovation-on-day-three-of-the-america-loves-crypto-tour","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]}','["https://www.ccn.com/news/crypto/us-states-strategic-bitcoin-reserve-2025/","https://decrypt.co/330965/these-u-s-states-have-passed-bitcoin-reserve-laws","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://www.michiganblockchain.org/","https://bitcoinmagazine.com/politics/detroit-aims-to-drive-digital-asset-innovation-on-day-three-of-the-america-loves-crypto-tour","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]','2026-07-08 19:56:20');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('MN','Minnesota','Mixed','{"stance":"Mixed","preview":"Consumer-protection lean with a new 2026 bank crypto-custody law and some pro-crypto bills.","governor":"Tim Walz (D) — no dedicated crypto agenda; pragmatic.","legislature":"Narrowly divided; a mix of consumer-protection and pro-crypto proposals.","regulation":"Minnesota regulates crypto money transmission under standard licensing (Coinbase, Binance, Gemini registered as money transmitters). A 2026 law (effective Aug 1) sets rules for banks and credit unions to act as crypto custodians. Bills to allow crypto for state payments and exempt small crypto transactions from tax have been introduced.","legislators":"Some GOP legislators pushed pro-crypto payment/tax bills; Democrats emphasize consumer protection. Dept. of Commerce (Deputy Commissioner Michael Crow) framed the 2026 custody law as keeping local banks competitive.","localities":"No notable crypto-friendly municipal initiatives.","orgs":"The Minnesota Blockchain Initiative (mnblockchain.org, founded 2018) is the main community hub — monthly Twin Cities meetups, a podcast, and collaboration with the University of St. Thomas School of Law. Stand With Crypto maintains a Minnesota chapter. The startup scene is young; most development happens remotely or in coastal hubs.","people":"Community-led rather than founder-led; the Minnesota Blockchain Initiative organizers and student leaders (e.g. UMN Blockchain Club president Daigan Berger, who calls the Twin Cities ''underdeveloped'' for blockchain) are the notable local voices.","universities":"University of Minnesota (Twin Cities) has a student-run UMN Blockchain organization (events, hackathons) and faculty commentary on crypto/NFTs; the University of St. Thomas School of Law collaborates with the Minnesota Blockchain Initiative on education.","gov_use":"No operational state blockchain deployment; the 2026 law enabling banks/credit unions to offer crypto custody is the main government-facing step. Bills proposing crypto acceptance for state payments remain pending.","upcoming":"Implementation of the 2026 bank crypto-custody law; digital-asset payment and consumer bills pending per NCSL 2026.","overview":"Minnesota''s posture is mixed: standard money-transmitter licensing plus a new 2026 law letting banks/credit unions custody crypto, alongside competing pro-crypto (state payments, tax) and consumer-protection proposals. A young community ecosystem (Minnesota Blockchain Initiative, UMN Blockchain) exists, but the Twin Cities remain underdeveloped versus coastal hubs.","sources":["https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://www.mprnews.org/episode/2026/06/25/banks-credit-unions-cryptocurrency-custody","https://www.mnblockchain.org/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]}','["https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://www.mprnews.org/episode/2026/06/25/banks-credit-unions-cryptocurrency-custody","https://www.mnblockchain.org/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]','2026-07-08 19:59:22');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('MS','Mississippi','Mixed','{"stance":"Mixed","preview":"Passed a Digital Asset Mining / Blockchain Basics right-to-mine law; otherwise light regulation.","governor":"Tate Reeves (R) — conservative, business-friendly; supportive of mining-rights legislation.","legislature":"Republican-controlled; enacted a right-to-mine protection.","regulation":"Mississippi passed the Digital Asset Mining Act (Senate, Feb 2023) and the Blockchain Basics Act (2024) protecting the right to mine and home-based node operation, barring discriminatory power rates, and clarifying miners are not money transmitters. The Blockchain Basics Act adds noise limits, trading freedom, and a state tax exemption for crypto cash-outs under $200. Mississippi does not require a money-transmitter license for many crypto businesses. No reserve.","legislators":"State Sen. Josh Harkins authored the Digital Asset Mining Act; GOP sponsors advanced the Blockchain Basics Act. No reserve champion of note.","localities":"Cheap-power regions attract miners; the mining law limits local bans while adding noise-pollution limits.","orgs":"The pro-Bitcoin lobbying group Satoshi Action Fund (CEO Dennis Porter) drove Mississippi''s Blockchain Basics Act, part of a multi-state template (also pushed in Ohio, South Carolina) — the dominant external policy actor. In-state crypto industry is thin beyond mining operators. Stand With Crypto maintains a Mississippi chapter.","people":"No prominent resident crypto founders; the defining figures are policy actors — Sen. Josh Harkins and Satoshi Action Fund''s Dennis Porter, who shaped the mining-rights framework.","universities":"Mississippi State and the University of Mississippi offer computer-science coursework touching blockchain/cryptography, but there is no flagship dedicated blockchain research center; the state''s crypto identity is mining policy.","gov_use":"No state blockchain adoption or reserve; government engagement is legislative — the Digital Asset Mining Act and Blockchain Basics Act protect mining/trading rights and exempt small crypto cash-outs from state tax, rather than deploying blockchain in government operations.","upcoming":"Possible follow-on digital-asset bills; nothing landmark pending.","overview":"Mississippi enacted a Digital Asset Mining Act (2023) and Blockchain Basics Act (2024) — pushed by the Satoshi Action Fund — protecting the right to mine and run nodes, barring discriminatory utility rates, and exempting small crypto cash-outs from state tax. Beyond mining-rights, regulation is light with no reserve and a thin in-state industry, giving a mixed but modestly pro-crypto lean.","sources":["https://www.bitcoinlaws.io/","https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://bitcoinist.com/crypto-mississippi-passes-bill-on-miners-rights/","https://dailyleader.com/2024/08/14/mississippis-crypto-rules-a-closer-look-at-the-blockchain-basics-act/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]}','["https://www.bitcoinlaws.io/","https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://bitcoinist.com/crypto-mississippi-passes-bill-on-miners-rights/","https://dailyleader.com/2024/08/14/mississippis-crypto-rules-a-closer-look-at-the-blockchain-basics-act/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]','2026-07-08 20:02:03');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('MO','Missouri','Pro-crypto','{"stance":"Pro-crypto","preview":"Moved to eliminate state capital-gains tax (benefiting crypto gains) and protect self-custody/mining; reserve bills pending.","governor":"Mike Kehoe (R) — conservative, pro-crypto; supportive of digital-asset rights and tax relief.","legislature":"Republican-controlled; advanced crypto-rights, anti-CBDC, and capital-gains-exemption measures.","regulation":"Missouri regulates crypto money transmission under standard licensing. In 2025 it advanced/enacted legislation eliminating state capital-gains tax (benefiting crypto gains) and protecting self-custody/mining rights. Reserve bills pending. Not a BitLicense state.","legislators":"GOP legislators championed the capital-gains repeal and Bitcoin-rights measures; reserve bill (HB/SB) pending per NCSL.","orgs":"Stand With Crypto Missouri chapter; cheap-power regions host mining; Kansas City/St. Louis fintech communities.","people":"GOP legislative sponsors of the capital-gains repeal; Missouri fintech founders and miners.","universities":"University of Missouri and Washington University in St. Louis offer computing/fintech coursework; WashU''s Olin Business School has fintech programming and student groups.","gov_use":"No state Bitcoin reserve enacted; Missouri''s headline move is fiscal (state capital-gains repeal benefiting crypto holders) rather than government on-chain use.","localities":"Cheap-power areas host mining; no municipal bans of note.","upcoming":"Bitcoin-reserve and further digital-asset bills pending per NCSL 2026.","overview":"Missouri leans clearly pro-crypto: it moved in 2025 to eliminate state capital-gains tax — a major benefit for crypto holders — and advanced self-custody and mining protections, with reserve bills pending. A Republican governor and legislature make its trajectory decidedly crypto-friendly.","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://www.bitcoinlaws.io/","https://www.ncsl.org/","https://olin.wustl.edu/"]}','["https://www.bitcoinlaws.io/","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2025-legislation","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation"]','2026-07-08 19:23:00');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('MT','Montana','Pro-crypto','{"stance":"Pro-crypto","preview":"Enacted a Right-to-Mine law and protects home mining; no money-transmitter licensing and no sales tax. Reserve bill shelved.","governor":"Greg Gianforte (R) — pro-business conservative; signed the 2023 crypto-mining protection law.","legislature":"Republican-controlled; strongly pro-mining and light-touch on crypto.","regulation":"Montana''s 2023 law (SB 178) protects the right to mine at home and in industrial facilities, bars discriminatory utility rates and local bans, and clarifies digital assets aren''t securities under state law. Notably, Montana has NO general money-transmitter licensing for crypto and no sales tax. A 2025 Bitcoin reserve bill was shelved.","legislators":"GOP sponsors advanced the mining-rights law; reserve effort failed to secure votes and was withdrawn.","orgs":"Stand With Crypto Montana chapter; local mining operators leveraging cheap power; the Satoshi Action Fund influenced the right-to-mine framework.","people":"Montana mining-industry operators; GOP legislative sponsors of SB 178.","universities":"University of Montana and Montana State University offer computing coursework with blockchain relevance; smaller campus crypto footprint.","gov_use":"No state Bitcoin reserve (2025 bill shelved); Montana''s posture is mining-rights protection rather than government on-chain use.","localities":"Hardin hosted a controversial coal-adjacent mining operation (later closed) after public pressure; otherwise mining-welcoming.","upcoming":"Possible renewed reserve or digital-asset bills after the 2025 reserve shelving.","overview":"Montana is strongly pro-crypto on mining: its 2023 Right-to-Mine law protects home and industrial mining, blocks discriminatory rates, and no general crypto money-transmitter license is required (and no sales tax). A 2025 Bitcoin reserve bill was shelved, but the overall light-touch, mining-friendly posture keeps it firmly pro-crypto.","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://decrypt.co/330965/these-u-s-states-have-passed-bitcoin-reserve-laws","https://www.bitcoinlaws.io/","https://www.ncsl.org/"]}','["https://www.hunton.com/blockchain-legal-resource/new-york-enacts-crypto-mining-moratorium","https://decrypt.co/330965/these-u-s-states-have-passed-bitcoin-reserve-laws","https://www.bitcoinlaws.io/"]','2026-07-08 19:23:11');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('NE','Nebraska','Pro-crypto','{"stance":"Pro-crypto","preview":"Home of the first-in-nation digital-asset bank charter (NFIA); Telcoin launched the first US crypto bank.","governor":"Jim Pillen (R) — business-friendly; signed Telcoin''s first-in-nation digital-asset bank charter (Nov 2025), touting Nebraska as ''leading a new era of digital payments.''","legislature":"Officially nonpartisan/unicameral (Republican-leaning); enacted a pioneering crypto-bank charter.","regulation":"The Nebraska Financial Innovation Act (NFIA, 2021) created ''digital asset depository institutions'' — a state charter for crypto banks, similar to Wyoming''s SPDI, regulated by the Dept. of Banking & Finance (NDBF). A 2023 law regulates crypto-mining energy use/registration. Money-transmitter licensing applies to exchanges.","legislators":"Sen. Mike Flood (later a US Rep.) authored the NFIA crypto-bank charter; unicameral sponsors advanced mining rules.","localities":"Norfolk, NE is home to Telcoin''s digital asset bank; cheap-power regions host mining (2023 law adds registration).","orgs":"The Nebraska Dept. of Banking & Finance (NDBF) runs the nation''s first digital-asset depository regime. Telcoin Digital Asset Bank (Norfolk) is the marquee institution — the first US bank chartered to take crypto deposits, make crypto loans, connect to Fed payment rails, and mint the eUSD stablecoin (on Ethereum/Polygon). Stand With Crypto maintains a Nebraska chapter.","people":"Paul Neuner (Telcoin founder/CEO, who testified before the legislature to shape the NFIA and chose rural Norfolk); US Rep. Mike Flood (NFIA author as a state senator); Prof. Jane Liu (University of Nebraska Omaha economist) analyzes the state''s digital-asset advantages.","universities":"University of Nebraska (Omaha and Lincoln) faculty study digital-asset economics and policy (e.g. Prof. Jane Liu at UNO); the state''s edge is regulatory/institutional rather than a flagship blockchain research lab.","gov_use":"Nebraska issued the first US ''digital asset depository institution'' charter (to Telcoin, Nov 2025) under the 2021 NFIA — a state-authorized crypto bank that can mint stablecoins (eUSD) and access Federal Reserve payment rails, a first-in-nation government regulatory framework that predated the federal GENIUS Act by years.","upcoming":"Additional digital-asset bank charter applications expected; Telcoin aims to help the ~95% of community banks that can''t build digital-asset services in-house; refinements to the framework and mining rules possible.","overview":"Nebraska is a pro-crypto standout: its 2021 Nebraska Financial Innovation Act created a purpose-built crypto-bank charter (echoing Wyoming''s SPDI model), and in Nov 2025 it issued the first-in-nation digital-asset bank charter to Telcoin — the first US bank able to take crypto deposits, mint a stablecoin (eUSD), and access Fed rails. It layers on mining-energy rules but remains broadly welcoming, anchored by genuine institutional infrastructure.","sources":["https://www.globallegalinsights.com/practice-areas/blockchain-cryptocurrency-laws-and-regulations/usa/","https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://ndbf.nebraska.gov/industries/digital-assets","https://governor.nebraska.gov/gov-pillen-signs-first-nation-digital-asset-bank-charter","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]}','["https://www.globallegalinsights.com/practice-areas/blockchain-cryptocurrency-laws-and-regulations/usa/","https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://ndbf.nebraska.gov/industries/digital-assets","https://governor.nebraska.gov/gov-pillen-signs-first-nation-digital-asset-bank-charter","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]','2026-07-08 19:59:06');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('NV','Nevada','Pro-crypto','{"stance":"Pro-crypto","preview":"No income tax, blockchain-friendly laws, and an early ban on local blockchain taxes.","governor":"Joe Lombardo (R) — business-friendly; supportive of the state''s blockchain-friendly stance.","legislature":"Democratic-controlled but with a bipartisan pro-blockchain tradition dating to 2017.","regulation":"Nevada was first to bar local governments from taxing or licensing blockchain use (SB 398, 2017) and recognizes blockchain records/smart contracts. No state income tax. Money-transmitter licensing applies. A proposed ''Innovation Zones'' crypto-city concept stalled.","legislators":"Bipartisan 2017 blockchain laws; the Blockchains LLC ''Innovation Zone'' proposal (2021) failed amid local opposition.","localities":"Storey County saw the Blockchains LLC smart-city plan (did not proceed); Reno launched a blockchain records system. No municipal bans.","orgs":"Stand With Crypto maintains a Nevada chapter. Notable in-state firms: Blockchains LLC (Reno — Jeffrey Berns'' smart-city venture), Fortress Trust and Ballet (Bobby Lee''s hardware wallet) in Las Vegas, Filament and Titan Seal (government-records-on-chain) in Reno, and Monarch (self-custody wallet/exchange). Las Vegas casinos/gaming firms increasingly pilot crypto payments.","people":"Jeffrey Berns (Blockchains LLC founder, drove the Innovation Zone / Storey County smart-city plan); Bobby Lee (Ballet wallet founder, based in Las Vegas); Jaron Lukasiewicz (Coinsetter founder, sold to Kraken, now advising LV blockchain firms); Hartej Sawhney (Hosho co-founder).","universities":"UNLV and UNR (University of Nevada, Reno) offer blockchain/fintech coursework within business and engineering programs; the state''s blockchain-friendly law and no-income-tax climate have drawn company R&D rather than a flagship dedicated research center.","gov_use":"Reno launched a first-of-its-kind blockchain record-keeping system (''Biggest Little Blockchain''), built free of charge by BlockApps, to increase transparency and accountability in city records. State law (SB 398, 2017) formally recognizes blockchain records and smart contracts for official/legal purposes and bars local blockchain taxation.","upcoming":"Digital-asset bills per NCSL 2026; expansion of Reno''s blockchain records system; no major restrictive measures.","overview":"Nevada has a long pro-blockchain track record: first state to bar local blockchain taxes and to recognize blockchain records and smart contracts, with no income tax. Reno runs a municipal blockchain records system, and the state hosts a cluster of firms (Blockchains LLC, Ballet, Fortress Trust). Despite a Democratic legislature, the bipartisan tradition and business-friendly climate keep it pro-crypto — though the ambitious Innovation Zone crypto-city plan stalled.","sources":["https://www.cointracker.io/blog/crypto-friendly-states","https://www.globallegalinsights.com/practice-areas/blockchain-cryptocurrency-laws-and-regulations/usa/","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://www.smartcitiesdive.com/news/reno-nevada-smart-city-blockchain-record/625449/","https://cointelegraph.com/news/blockchain-firm-aims-to-build-crypto-city-in-nevada-desert","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]}','["https://www.cointracker.io/blog/crypto-friendly-states","https://www.globallegalinsights.com/practice-areas/blockchain-cryptocurrency-laws-and-regulations/usa/","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://www.smartcitiesdive.com/news/reno-nevada-smart-city-blockchain-record/625449/","https://cointelegraph.com/news/blockchain-firm-aims-to-build-crypto-city-in-nevada-desert","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]','2026-07-08 19:53:10');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('NH','New Hampshire','Pro-crypto','{"stance":"Pro-crypto","preview":"First state to authorize a Strategic Bitcoin Reserve (HB 302) and a Blockchain Basics law.","governor":"Kelly Ayotte (R) — pro-crypto; signed both HB 302 (reserve) and HB 639 (Blockchain Basics).","legislature":"Republican-controlled; libertarian-leaning ''Live Free or Die'' ethos, very pro-crypto.","regulation":"HB 302 (signed May 6, 2025) lets the treasurer invest up to 5% of public funds in precious metals and digital assets over $500B market cap (effectively Bitcoin) — first-in-nation reserve authority. HB 639 (2026 ''Blockchain Basics Law'') protects self-custody, bars local bans and payment-method taxes. No income tax.","legislators":"GOP sponsors drove HB 302 and HB 639; state also explored a $100M Bitcoin-backed bond.","orgs":"Stand With Crypto New Hampshire chapter; the Free State Project fosters a crypto-adoption community; Satoshi Action Fund influenced the Blockchain Basics framework.","people":"Free State Project activists and Bitcoin advocates; state treasurer''s office implementing reserve authority.","universities":"University of New Hampshire and Dartmouth College offer computing/fintech coursework; Dartmouth''s Tuck School has fintech programming and student blockchain groups.","gov_use":"HB 302 authorizes the treasurer to hold Bitcoin as a reserve asset (up to 5% of public funds); the state also explored a $100M Bitcoin-backed bond — an early government embrace of on-chain assets.","localities":"Strong ''free state'' crypto-adoption community; merchants accept crypto in some towns like Keene and Portsmouth.","upcoming":"Implementation of reserve authority and the newly registered HB 639 (published July 2026).","overview":"New Hampshire is a national pro-crypto pioneer: HB 302 (2025) made it the first state to authorize a Bitcoin reserve (up to 5% of public funds), and HB 639 (2026) enshrined self-custody rights and barred local bans and payment-method taxes. With no income tax and a libertarian legislature, it is among the friendliest jurisdictions.","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://cryptobriefing.com/new-hampshire-bitcoin-reserve-fund/","https://www.cryptotimes.io/2026/07/04/new-hampshire-registers-hb639-blockchain-rights-crypto-protections/","https://decrypt.co/330965/these-u-s-states-have-passed-bitcoin-reserve-laws","https://www.ncsl.org/"]}','["https://cryptobriefing.com/new-hampshire-bitcoin-reserve-fund/","https://www.cryptotimes.io/2026/07/04/new-hampshire-registers-hb639-blockchain-rights-crypto-protections/","https://decrypt.co/330965/these-u-s-states-have-passed-bitcoin-reserve-laws"]','2026-07-08 19:20:56');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('NJ','New Jersey','Restrictive','{"stance":"Restrictive","preview":"Digital Asset & Blockchain Technology Act imposes licensing; enforcement-minded.","governor":"Phil Murphy (D) — cautious; oversaw enactment of a crypto-licensing framework.","legislature":"Democratic-controlled; consumer-protection and licensing-focused.","regulation":"New Jersey''s Digital Asset and Blockchain Technology Act requires licensing for digital-asset businesses via the Dept. of Banking & Insurance, layered on money-transmitter law. The Bureau of Securities has been an active enforcer (e.g. against BlockFi, Celsius). No reserve.","legislators":"Democratic sponsors advanced the licensing act; Assemblyman Andrew Zwicker (D-16, also of Princeton Plasma Physics Lab) chairs the Science, Innovation and Technology Committee that has heard blockchain-promotion bills. Regulators pursued high-profile enforcement.","localities":"Bergen County is running a landmark on-chain property-records project; Jersey City and Princeton host crypto firms.","orgs":"The New Jersey Innovation & Technology Alliance (NJITA) launched a program connecting the crypto/blockchain/AI community with policymakers and running public town halls. Stand With Crypto maintains a New Jersey chapter. Notable in-state firms: Offchain Labs (Princeton — creators of Arbitrum), plus a Jersey City-based crypto financial-services company that raised $450M+; smaller players include ONIS Solutions (Bridgewater) and SportVEST (Princeton).","people":"Steven Goldfeder and Ed Felten (Offchain Labs / Arbitrum co-founders, Princeton-rooted; Felten is a former Princeton professor and White House deputy CTO). Assemblyman Andrew Zwicker is the leading legislative voice on blockchain.","universities":"Princeton (blockchain research; Offchain Labs/Arbitrum spun out of Princeton research), Stevens Institute of Technology (blockchain courses, cybersecurity/supply-chain research), and Rutgers (Blockchain and Fintech Program at the law/business schools; a fintech-and-digital-assets course first offered spring 2021, co-taught by Profs. Yuliya Guseva and Merav Ozair).","gov_use":"Bergen County Clerk''s Office is bringing all property records on-chain via Balcony, a platform powered by Avalanche, projected to cut deed-processing time by 90%+ while reducing fraud/title disputes; Balcony''s work in Orange, NJ reportedly surfaced ~$1M in previously hidden municipal revenue.","upcoming":"Implementation of licensing rules; expansion of the Bergen County / Balcony on-chain deeds rollout; consumer-protection bills pending.","overview":"New Jersey is restrictive on licensing/enforcement — it enacted a Digital Asset and Blockchain Technology Act and its securities regulators aggressively pursued BlockFi and Celsius — yet the state hosts serious industry (Offchain Labs/Arbitrum in Princeton) and academic programs (Princeton, Stevens, Rutgers), and Bergen County''s Avalanche-based property-records project is one of the most concrete US government blockchain deployments.","sources":["https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.globallegalinsights.com/practice-areas/blockchain-cryptocurrency-laws-and-regulations/usa/","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://www.govtech.com/biz/blockchain-takes-on-big-property-records-job-in-new-jersey","https://cclg.rutgers.edu/research/blockchain-and-fintech-program/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]}','["https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://www.globallegalinsights.com/practice-areas/blockchain-cryptocurrency-laws-and-regulations/usa/","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://www.govtech.com/biz/blockchain-takes-on-big-property-records-job-in-new-jersey","https://cclg.rutgers.edu/research/blockchain-and-fintech-program/","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/"]','2026-07-08 19:52:49');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('NM','New Mexico','Restrictive','{"stance":"Restrictive","preview":"One of the strictest — requires full money-transmitter licensing with limited crypto guidance.","governor":"Michelle Lujan Grisham (D) — no crypto-promotion agenda; cautious.","legislature":"Democratic-controlled; consumer-protection-focused, minimal pro-crypto action.","regulation":"New Mexico requires a money-transmitter license for virtual-currency businesses and is often cited among the stricter states with limited crypto-specific guidance. No BitLicense, no reserve. Digital-asset bills pending per NCSL.","legislators":"No prominent crypto champions; focus on consumer protection.","localities":"No notable crypto-friendly municipal initiatives.","orgs":"New Mexico has a minimal organized crypto footprint — no major in-state exchange, custodian, or trade association. Stand With Crypto tracks the state (e.g. ~2,800 advocates in one congressional district) and maintains a New Mexico chapter, but organized industry presence is thin.","people":"No nationally prominent crypto founders based in-state; the ecosystem is retail-driven.","universities":"The University of New Mexico and New Mexico State offer computer-science coursework touching cryptography/blockchain, and Los Alamos/Sandia national labs conduct cryptography research, but there is no dedicated university blockchain center of note.","gov_use":"No operational state or local blockchain deployment and no reserve; New Mexico''s stance is regulatory (full money-transmitter licensing) rather than adoption-oriented.","upcoming":"Digital-asset bills listed pending in NCSL 2026 tracker.","overview":"New Mexico is among the stricter states, requiring full money-transmitter licensing for crypto businesses with little tailored guidance, no pro-crypto framework or reserve, and a minimal in-state industry or academic footprint. Democratic leadership keeps the focus on consumer protection, placing it firmly in the restrictive column.","sources":["https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://legalclarity.org/a-state-by-state-look-at-cryptocurrency-laws/","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/local-policy/nm"]}','["https://astraea.law/insights/state-by-state-crypto-licensing-map-2025","https://legalclarity.org/a-state-by-state-look-at-cryptocurrency-laws/","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/local-policy/nm"]','2026-07-08 20:03:04');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('NY','New York','Restrictive','{"stance":"Restrictive","preview":"Home of the notoriously strict BitLicense and a proof-of-work mining moratorium.","governor":"Kathy Hochul (D) — signed the 2022 PoW mining moratorium; consumer-protection-focused.","legislature":"Democratic-controlled; among the most cautious, enforcement-heavy legislatures on crypto.","regulation":"NYDFS runs the BitLicense (since 2015) — the strictest US regime; as of Sept 2025 only ~37 licenses were active out of 104 applications. A 2022 law imposed a two-year moratorium on new carbon-powered proof-of-work mining permits (later expired; a 2025 extension was stricken). NYDFS maintains a coin ''greenlist'' and aggressive supervision.","legislators":"Sen. Kevin Parker/Assemblymember Anna Kelles drove the mining moratorium; NYDFS Superintendent oversees strict licensing.","localities":"North Tonawanda and other towns imposed local mining/data-center moratoriums over noise.","orgs":"Stand With Crypto has a New York state chapter (NY is one of the largest crypto-owning populations). Marquee crypto companies HQ''d in NYC: Gemini (Winklevoss twins; first NYDFS BitLicense/trust charter, NASDAQ IPO 2025), Chainlink Labs, Circle (USDC issuer, moved HQ to NYC), Consensys roots, Paxos, and many TradFi firms building tokenization desks. IC3-affiliated startups (Ava Labs, Offchain Labs, Flashbots) trace to NY academia.","people":"Cameron & Tyler Winklevoss (Gemini co-founders, major crypto political donors); Emin Gün Sirer (Ava Labs founder, Cornell professor and IC3 co-director); Sergey Nazarov (Chainlink co-founder); Jeremy Allaire (Circle CEO). Prof. Ari Juels (Cornell Tech/IC3) is a leading academic.","universities":"Cornell / Cornell Tech hosts IC3 (Initiative for CryptoCurrencies and Contracts), a leading multi-university research consortium whose ecosystem spawned Chainlink, Ava Labs, Offchain Labs and Flashbots; plus the student group Cornell Blockchain. Columbia runs the Columbia-Ethereum Research Center for Blockchain Protocol Design and the Columbia-IBM Center for Blockchain and Data Transparency. NYU offers blockchain/cryptocurrency courses across CS, Tandon (Finance & Risk Engineering), and SPS, plus a high-school summer program.","gov_use":"NYC Office of Technology and Innovation released a 61-page NYC Blockchain Plan (Dec 2025) after interviewing 50+ organizations, laying out responsible pilots for digital credentials, permits/licenses, and vital records; Mayor Adams announced a ''digital asset advisory council'' and floated blockchain for vital records. State law treats blockchain-secured records and smart contracts as valid electronic records. (Official notarization uses Remote Online Notarization, not blockchain.)","upcoming":"NYC interagency blockchain working group and ''information hub'' standing up per the Dec 2025 plan; debate over reinstating/extending the mining moratorium; ongoing BitLicense refinements.","overview":"New York is the archetypal restrictive state: its BitLicense (2015) is the toughest US licensing regime, with few approvals, and it enacted the nation''s first proof-of-work mining moratorium in 2022. Yet NYC is a dense industry hub (Gemini, Circle, Chainlink) with world-class academic centers (Cornell/IC3, Columbia, NYU), and the city published a formal blockchain adoption plan in late 2025 — a cautious, enforcement-heavy state that nonetheless anchors much of the industry and research.","sources":["https://www.hunton.com/blockchain-legal-resource/new-york-enacts-crypto-mining-moratorium","https://www.govtech.com/policy/north-tonawanda-n-y-bans-new-crypto-mining-for-2-years","https://transnetinc.com/us-crypto-regulations-by-state-the-complete-2026-guide-to-restrictions-licensing","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://initc3.org/","https://www.nyc.gov/assets/oti/downloads/pdf/reports/nycoti_blockchain_plan.pdf","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gemini_(cryptocurrency_exchange)"]}','["https://www.hunton.com/blockchain-legal-resource/new-york-enacts-crypto-mining-moratorium","https://www.govtech.com/policy/north-tonawanda-n-y-bans-new-crypto-mining-for-2-years","https://transnetinc.com/us-crypto-regulations-by-state-the-complete-2026-guide-to-restrictions-licensing","https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://initc3.org/","https://www.nyc.gov/assets/oti/downloads/pdf/reports/nycoti_blockchain_plan.pdf","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gemini_(cryptocurrency_exchange)"]','2026-07-08 19:50:46');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('NC','North Carolina','Pro-crypto','{"stance":"Pro-crypto","preview":"Banned state CBDC use; an ambitious 10%-cap Bitcoin reserve bill (SB 327) is advancing.","governor":"Josh Stein (D) — pragmatic; the GOP legislature has driven crypto policy, sometimes over vetoes.","legislature":"Republican-led (near-supermajority); very pro-crypto, passed anti-CBDC and reserve measures.","regulation":"North Carolina barred state acceptance/use of a CBDC (2024, over the prior governor''s veto). It is a major mining state with cheap power. Money-transmitter licensing applies. SB 327 (2025–26) proposes a Strategic Bitcoin Reserve with a 10% cap, cold-storage mandate, and even state mining — among the most ambitious in the nation.","legislators":"Sens. Todd Johnson and Brad Overcash sponsor SB 327; GOP leaders drove the CBDC ban.","orgs":"Stand With Crypto North Carolina chapter; the Research Triangle (Raleigh-Durham) hosts fintech/blockchain startups; major mining operations in cheap-power regions.","people":"Research Triangle fintech founders and developers; SB 327 sponsors as legislative champions.","universities":"Duke University, UNC-Chapel Hill, and NC State offer blockchain courses and host student blockchain clubs; Duke has notable fintech/blockchain programming and research in the Research Triangle.","gov_use":"No live reserve yet; SB 327 would authorize a Strategic Bitcoin Reserve (up to 10% of certain funds) with cold storage and potentially state-run mining. The state bars any government CBDC use.","localities":"Major mining operations in cheap-power areas; some local noise disputes.","upcoming":"SB 327 (Bitcoin reserve, 10% cap) sits in the Senate Rules Committee; digital-asset bills pending.","overview":"North Carolina is strongly pro-crypto: it banned state CBDC use (2024) and its GOP legislature is advancing SB 327, one of the most ambitious Bitcoin-reserve bills anywhere — a 10% cap, cold-storage mandate, advisory board, and even state mining. A major mining hub anchored by the Research Triangle''s fintech ecosystem, its trajectory is decisively crypto-forward.","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://btc.network/blog/north-carolina-sb-327-bitcoin-reserve-bill-2026","https://bitcoinmagazine.com/news/north-carolina-propose-bitcoin-reserve","https://www.ncsl.org/"]}','["https://btc.network/blog/north-carolina-sb-327-bitcoin-reserve-bill-2026","https://bitcoinmagazine.com/news/north-carolina-propose-bitcoin-reserve","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation"]','2026-07-08 19:21:26');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('ND','North Dakota','Pro-crypto','{"stance":"Pro-crypto","preview":"Major mining state with cheap flared-gas power; reserve bill shelved but climate friendly.","governor":"Kelly Armstrong (R) — pro-energy, pro-mining; supportive of the state''s data-center/mining economy.","legislature":"Republican-controlled; mining- and energy-friendly, though it shelved a 2025 reserve bill.","regulation":"North Dakota is a top mining state, using cheap and flared natural gas to power operations. It regulates money transmission under standard licensing (with some crypto-friendly interpretations). No income-tax hostility. A 2025 Bitcoin reserve bill failed to secure votes and was shelved. Not a BitLicense state.","legislators":"GOP legislators back mining/energy; reserve effort withdrawn after failing votes.","orgs":"Stand With Crypto North Dakota chapter; oilfield-adjacent mining operators; the state''s data-center/energy industry drives crypto activity.","people":"Bakken oilfield and mining operators using flared gas; GOP energy-policy leaders.","universities":"University of North Dakota and North Dakota State University offer computing/energy coursework relevant to mining infrastructure; smaller campus crypto footprint.","gov_use":"No state Bitcoin reserve (2025 bill shelved); engagement is the mining/energy economy rather than government on-chain use.","localities":"Numerous industrial mining sites tied to oilfield gas; welcoming local climate.","upcoming":"Possible renewed reserve/digital-asset bills; continued mining growth.","overview":"North Dakota is a major, welcoming Bitcoin-mining state, leveraging cheap flared natural gas from its oilfields to power operations. Though a 2025 Bitcoin reserve bill was shelved for lack of votes, the pro-energy, mining-friendly Republican climate keeps its overall posture pro-crypto.","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://decrypt.co/330965/these-u-s-states-have-passed-bitcoin-reserve-laws","https://www.ncsl.org/","https://www.und.edu/"]}','["https://www.cnbc.com/2022/11/23/new-york-governor-signs-law-cracking-down-on-bitcoin-mining.html","https://decrypt.co/330965/these-u-s-states-have-passed-bitcoin-reserve-laws","https://www.ncsl.org/financial-services/cryptocurrency-digital-or-virtual-currency-and-digital-assets-2026-legislation"]','2026-07-08 19:23:23');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('WY','Wyoming','Pro-crypto','{"stance":"Pro-crypto","preview":"The nation''s most crypto-forward state: home to the first state-issued stablecoin (Frontier/FRNT), DAO LLCs, and SPDI bank charters.","governor":"Mark Gordon (R) — supportive; sits on the Wyoming Stable Token Commission and has backed the state''s digital-asset legal framework.","legislature":"Republican-controlled and strongly pro-crypto since 2018; has passed dozens of digital-asset laws with broad bipartisan support via the Blockchain Select Committee.","regulation":"Virtual Currency Act exempts crypto activity from the Money Transmitters Act (no money-transmitter license needed for many crypto businesses). Created SPDI (''crypto bank'') charters (Kraken, Custodia). Recognizes DAOs as LLCs. Digital Asset Act gives UCC property treatment. No state income tax. Not a BitLicense state. Launched the Frontier Stable Token (FRNT), first US public-entity stablecoin, on mainnet Aug 2025 across 7 chains.","legislators":"Sen. Chris Rothfuss (D) and former Rep. Tyler Lindholm long led the Blockchain Select Committee; the committee shepherded the Stable Token Act, DAO LLC law, and SPDI framework.","orgs":"Wyoming Stable Token Commission (state body issuing FRNT); Wyoming Division of Banking (SPDI oversight); Custodia Bank (Caitlin Long, Cheyenne) fighting the Fed for a master account; Kraken (first SPDI charter). Stand With Crypto has a Wyoming chapter.","people":"Caitlin Long (Custodia Bank founder, architect of many WY crypto laws); US Sen. Cynthia Lummis (R-WY), lead author of the federal GENIUS Act and a Bitcoin-reserve champion.","universities":"University of Wyoming runs the Center for Blockchain and Digital Innovation and has offered blockchain courses; the state has funded UW blockchain research and a hackathon ecosystem.","gov_use":"State issues the Frontier Stable Token (FRNT), backed by US Treasuries with 2% overcollateralization; interest revenue funnels to the state''s School Foundation Program. Exploring a blockchain land/deed-registry pilot.","upcoming":"Ongoing FRNT public sales (began Jan 2026); Division of Banking drafting DeFi service-provider guidance; potential blockchain land-registry pilot; Custodia v. Federal Reserve master-account litigation continuing.","overview":"Wyoming is widely regarded as the most crypto-friendly US jurisdiction, having pioneered SPDI bank charters, DAO LLCs, and UCC digital-asset property rules since 2018. In 2025 it became the first US public entity to issue a stablecoin (Frontier/FRNT), and it has no state income tax. Federal friction persists, notably Custodia''s fight for Fed master-account access.","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://www.govtech.com/budget-finance/wyoming-on-track-to-release-first-state-issued-stable-token","https://www.paymentsdive.com/news/wyoming-has-big-plans-for-stablecoin/810103/","https://wyoleg.gov/","https://www.uwyo.edu/"]}','["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://www.govtech.com/budget-finance/wyoming-on-track-to-release-first-state-issued-stable-token","https://www.paymentsdive.com/news/wyoming-has-big-plans-for-stablecoin/810103/","https://wyoleg.gov/","https://www.uwyo.edu/"]','2026-07-08 19:09:23');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('TX','Texas','Pro-crypto','{"stance":"Pro-crypto","preview":"Enacted the Texas Strategic Bitcoin Reserve (SB 21) and became the first state to fund one via a Bitcoin ETF; a major mining hub.","governor":"Greg Abbott (R) — strongly pro-crypto; signed SB 21 and HB 4488 (June 2025) creating and funding the Strategic Bitcoin Reserve.","legislature":"Republican-controlled and pro-crypto; Lt. Gov. Dan Patrick made SB 21 a top priority for the 89th session.","regulation":"Money-transmitter licensing applies to exchanges via the Texas Dept. of Banking, which issued early guidance treating some crypto as money. No state income tax. Not a BitLicense state. SB 21 requires cold-storage custody and Texas-based qualified providers. Major Bitcoin-mining state under ERCOT, with demand-response programs for miners.","legislators":"Sen. Charles Schwertner (R-Georgetown) authored SB 21; Rep. Giovanni Capriglione has long championed blockchain/digital-asset legislation and the state''s Work Group on Blockchain Matters.","orgs":"Texas Blockchain Council (Austin, Lee Bratcher) is a leading state industry group; Stand With Crypto Texas chapter. Major mining/company presence: Riot Platforms (Rockdale), MARA, Core Scientific, and numerous ERCOT-connected mining operations.","people":"Lee Bratcher (Texas Blockchain Council president); numerous mining executives and founders relocated to Texas post-2021.","universities":"UT Austin (McCombs Blockchain Initiative / research), Texas A&M, and Rice University offer blockchain courses and host student blockchain organizations; UT Austin has notable fintech/crypto research.","gov_use":"State holds a Strategic Bitcoin Reserve under the Comptroller of Public Accounts; Texas became the first state to actually fund its reserve, purchasing roughly $5M of BlackRock''s iShares Bitcoin Trust (IBIT).","upcoming":"Reserve funding/expansion and a Strategic Bitcoin Reserve Advisory Committee with biennial reporting; continued mining-grid policy debates at the PUC/ERCOT.","overview":"Texas is among the most crypto-forward large states, with no income tax, an established Bitcoin-mining industry, and the Texas Blockchain Council driving policy. In 2025 it enacted the Strategic Bitcoin Reserve (SB 21) and became the first state to fund one via a Bitcoin ETF. Grid/energy policy for miners remains an active area under ERCOT.","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://www.hunton.com/blockchain-legal-resource/texas-establishes-strategic-bitcoin-reserve","https://capitol.texas.gov/tlodocs/89R/analysis/html/SB00021F.htm","https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/17/texas-us-states-budgets-bitcoin-crypto-strategic-reserve.html","https://www.ncsl.org/"]}','["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://www.hunton.com/blockchain-legal-resource/texas-establishes-strategic-bitcoin-reserve","https://capitol.texas.gov/tlodocs/89R/analysis/html/SB00021F.htm","https://www.cnbc.com/2026/01/17/texas-us-states-budgets-bitcoin-crypto-strategic-reserve.html","https://www.ncsl.org/"]','2026-07-08 19:09:44');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('TN','Tennessee','Pro-crypto','{"stance":"Pro-crypto","preview":"No state income tax, home of GENIUS Act author Sen. Hagerty, and pursuing a Strategic Bitcoin Reserve plus a mining/energy hub vision around TVA.","governor":"Bill Lee (R) — generally supportive of a business-friendly, low-tax environment favorable to crypto and mining.","legislature":"Republican-supermajority General Assembly; broadly pro-crypto, advancing reserve and mining-rights legislation.","regulation":"No state income tax (crypto gains untaxed at state level). Money-transmitter licensing applies to exchanges via the Dept. of Financial Institutions. UCC ''controllable electronic records'' amendments (Public Chapter 704) take effect July 1, 2026. Home digital-asset mining protected subject to local noise ordinances. Not a BitLicense state.","legislators":"Rep. Jody Barrett (R-Dickson) filed HB 1695, the Tennessee Strategic Bitcoin Reserve Act (up to 10% of certain public funds); Sen. Kerry Roberts carried related digital-asset bills.","orgs":"Stand With Crypto Tennessee chapter; the Tennessee Valley Authority (TVA) is central to Hagerty''s mining/energy-hub vision; Oak Ridge National Laboratory cited as a research partner.","people":"US Sen. Bill Hagerty (R-TN), co-author of the federal GENIUS Act and a vocal Bitcoin-mining/energy-hub advocate.","universities":"Vanderbilt University (Owen Graduate School) co-hosting the inaugural Digital Assets and Emerging Technology Policy Summit with the Blockchain Association (April 2026); University of Tennessee and Tennessee Tech named as potential research/energy partners.","gov_use":"No live state blockchain reserve yet; the proposed Strategic Bitcoin Reserve Act would authorize treasurer allocations if enacted (effective July 1, 2026).","upcoming":"HB 1695 Strategic Bitcoin Reserve Act pending in the 114th General Assembly; UCC controllable-electronic-records amendments effective July 2026.","overview":"Tennessee pairs a no-income-tax, business-friendly posture with high-profile federal crypto leadership from Sen. Bill Hagerty, co-author of the GENIUS Act. The state is advancing a Strategic Bitcoin Reserve bill and pursuing a Bitcoin-mining/energy-hub vision leveraging TVA power and research partners like Oak Ridge, Vanderbilt, and UT.","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://bitcoinmagazine.com/politics/senator-hagertys-vision-beyond-the-genius-act-make-tennessee-a-hub-for-bitcoin-mining","https://wapp.capitol.tn.gov/apps/Billinfo/default.aspx?BillNumber=HB1695&ga=114","https://law.vanderbilt.edu/digital-assets-emerging-tech-policy-summit/","https://www.ncsl.org/"]}','["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://bitcoinmagazine.com/politics/senator-hagertys-vision-beyond-the-genius-act-make-tennessee-a-hub-for-bitcoin-mining","https://wapp.capitol.tn.gov/apps/Billinfo/default.aspx?BillNumber=HB1695&ga=114","https://law.vanderbilt.edu/digital-assets-emerging-tech-policy-summit/","https://www.ncsl.org/"]','2026-07-08 19:10:41');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('OH','Ohio','Mixed','{"stance":"Mixed","preview":"Advancing a Bitcoin Reserve Act and already moving to accept crypto for state fees, but GOP leadership has called the reserve idea ''risky.''","governor":"Mike DeWine (R) — cautious; Ohio previously (2018) let businesses pay taxes in Bitcoin before scrapping it, and DeWine has not championed the new reserve push.","legislature":"Republican-controlled General Assembly; split — some members push aggressive crypto bills while House leadership is skeptical.","regulation":"Money-transmitter licensing applies to crypto exchanges via the Dept. of Commerce. State income tax applies. Not a BitLicense state. SB 57 (Ohio Bitcoin Reserve Act) would require government entities to accept crypto and authorize a reserve fund with a 5-year hold.","legislators":"Sen. Sandra O''Brien (R-Ashtabula) introduced SB 57, the Ohio Bitcoin Reserve Act; related House bills (HB 18/HB 116) address digital-asset rights and self-custody.","orgs":"Ohio Blockchain Council (industry advocacy backing SB 57); Stand With Crypto Ohio chapter; offices of Secretary of State Frank LaRose and Treasurer Robert Sprague have supported crypto-payment adoption.","people":"US Rep. Warren Davidson (R-OH), sponsor of the federal ''Bitcoin for America Act'' allowing federal tax payment in BTC; state officials LaRose and Sprague.","universities":"Ohio State University and Case Western Reserve offer blockchain-related coursework and student organizations; various campus fintech/blockchain research initiatives.","gov_use":"In Sept 2025 the State Board of Deposit selected Grant Street Group as a processor so agencies can accept Bitcoin for fees and instantly convert to USD (no state custody); Secretary of State''s office to pilot first.","upcoming":"SB 57 Ohio Bitcoin Reserve Act pending in committee amid leadership skepticism; crypto-payment pilots rolling out via Grant Street Group.","overview":"Ohio is a mixed picture: it is operationally moving to accept crypto for state fees (converting instantly to dollars, avoiding custody) while a more aggressive Bitcoin Reserve Act (SB 57) faces skepticism from GOP House leadership who call it ''risky.'' The state has crypto-friendly constitutional officers and an active Ohio Blockchain Council.","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://ohiosenate.gov/members/sandra-obrien/news/obrien-introduces-bill-to-open-ohio-to-bitcoin","https://www.ohiosos.gov/media-center/press-releases/2025/2025-09-24/","https://legiscan.com/OH/text/SB57/id/3088016","https://www.ncsl.org/"]}','["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://ohiosenate.gov/members/sandra-obrien/news/obrien-introduces-bill-to-open-ohio-to-bitcoin","https://www.ohiosos.gov/media-center/press-releases/2025/2025-09-24/","https://legiscan.com/OH/text/SB57/id/3088016","https://www.ncsl.org/"]','2026-07-08 19:11:02');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('WA','Washington','Restrictive','{"stance":"Restrictive","preview":"One of the strictest states: DFI treats crypto as money transmission with tough custody, audit, and staking-disclosure rules.","governor":"Bob Ferguson (D) — consumer-protection oriented (as former AG); the DFI''s strict posture predates and continues under his administration.","legislature":"Democratic-controlled; focused on consumer protection rather than crypto promotion.","regulation":"Among the strictest regimes. DFI regulates crypto under the Uniform Money Services Act (RCW 19.230); custody triggers a $100,000 minimum net worth, third-party security audits, and consumer disclosures (SB 5031, 2017). Staking requires deliberate opt-in with repeated risk acknowledgments. Dept. of Revenue taxes mined crypto at market value on acquisition. Not a BitLicense state but comparably demanding.","legislators":"Legislative activity centers on consumer protection; no prominent state Bitcoin-reserve champion. The 2017 SSB 5031 established the current virtual-currency framework.","orgs":"Stand With Crypto Washington chapter; Washington DFI is the dominant regulatory actor. Home to major tech/cloud infrastructure (Microsoft, Amazon) relevant to blockchain infrastructure.","people":"Notable blockchain/tech figures in the Seattle tech ecosystem, though the state is not a magnet for crypto-native founders due to the strict regime.","universities":"University of Washington offers blockchain and distributed-systems coursework and has hosted blockchain research/student groups; Washington State University also has related programs.","gov_use":"No notable state blockchain reserve or payments program; the state''s engagement is primarily regulatory/enforcement via DFI.","upcoming":"Continued DFI enforcement and staking-disclosure requirements; no major pro-crypto reserve legislation advancing.","overview":"Washington is one of the most restrictive US states for crypto, with the DFI regulating digital-asset businesses as money transmitters under strict custody, audit, and staking-disclosure rules. There is little legislative appetite for a Bitcoin reserve, and the state''s focus remains consumer protection, though its Seattle tech ecosystem supports blockchain infrastructure.","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://dfi.wa.gov/consumers/virtual-currency-cryptocurrency-and-digital-assets-primer","https://dfi.wa.gov/documents/money-transmitters/virtual-currency-regulation.pdf","https://www.ncsl.org/","https://www.washington.edu/"]}','["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://dfi.wa.gov/consumers/virtual-currency-cryptocurrency-and-digital-assets-primer","https://dfi.wa.gov/documents/money-transmitters/virtual-currency-regulation.pdf","https://www.ncsl.org/","https://www.washington.edu/"]','2026-07-08 19:12:03');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('PA','Pennsylvania','Pro-crypto','{"stance":"Pro-crypto","preview":"Passed a bipartisan ''Bitcoin Rights'' bill (176-26) protecting self-custody; a Strategic Bitcoin Reserve Act is pending in a split legislature.","governor":"Josh Shapiro (D) — not a vocal crypto champion but oversees a state that passed strongly bipartisan digital-asset legislation.","legislature":"Split legislature (Democratic House, Republican Senate) — the only fully split statehouse — which made the bipartisan 176-26 Bitcoin Rights vote notable.","regulation":"HB 2481 ''Bitcoin Rights'' bill (passed House Oct 2024) protects self-custody, node operation, and crypto payments, and clarifies transaction taxation. Money-transmitter licensing applies to exchanges via the Dept. of Banking and Securities. State income tax applies. Not a BitLicense state.","legislators":"Reps. Mike Cabell and Aaron Kaufer (R) introduced the Strategic Bitcoin Reserve Act (HB 2664 / 2025 version allowing up to 5% of certain funds); the Bitcoin Rights bill drew broad bipartisan sponsorship.","orgs":"Satoshi Action Fund (Dennis Porter) helped draft both PA bills and model legislation nationally; Stand With Crypto Pennsylvania chapter.","people":"Dennis Porter (Satoshi Action Fund) influential in shaping PA''s model legislation; Philadelphia/Pittsburgh fintech founders.","universities":"Penn State, University of Pennsylvania (Wharton has a noted Cryptocurrency and blockchain program/online certificate), and Carnegie Mellon (strong CS/crypto research) offer blockchain courses and research; CMU is a leading blockchain/cryptography research center.","gov_use":"No live state reserve yet; the proposed Strategic Bitcoin Reserve Act would authorize treasurer allocations if enacted.","upcoming":"Strategic Bitcoin Reserve Act (2025 version, up to 5% of certain reserve funds) pending; continued momentum on the Bitcoin Rights framework.","overview":"Pennsylvania passed a strongly bipartisan ''Bitcoin Rights'' bill protecting self-custody, node operation, and crypto payments, notable given it is the only fully split US statehouse. A Strategic Bitcoin Reserve Act (up to 5% of certain funds) is pending. The Satoshi Action Fund helped craft both measures, and universities like Wharton and Carnegie Mellon anchor strong blockchain research.","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://www.forbes.com/sites/tonyaevans/2024/11/21/pennsylvania-passes-bitcoin-rights-bill-proposes-strategic-reserve/","https://www.palegis.us/house/co-sponsorship/memo?memoID=45793","https://www.ncsl.org/","https://www.wharton.upenn.edu/"]}','["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://www.forbes.com/sites/tonyaevans/2024/11/21/pennsylvania-passes-bitcoin-rights-bill-proposes-strategic-reserve/","https://www.palegis.us/house/co-sponsorship/memo?memoID=45793","https://www.ncsl.org/","https://www.wharton.upenn.edu/"]','2026-07-08 19:12:22');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('UT','Utah','Pro-crypto','{"stance":"Pro-crypto","preview":"HB 230 protects self-custody, mining, nodes, and staking; the Bitcoin-reserve clause was dropped, but Utah runs a noted regulatory sandbox.","governor":"Spencer Cox (R) — supportive of digital-innovation policy; signed HB 230 establishing broad digital-asset rights.","legislature":"Republican-supermajority; broadly pro-crypto (HB 230 passed comfortably) but cautious on a state Bitcoin reserve.","regulation":"HB 230 (2025) bars state/local governments from restricting self-custody, mining, node operation, and staking, and protects self-hosted/hardware wallets. Money-transmitter licensing applies to exchanges via the Dept. of Financial Institutions. State income tax applies. Utah''s Regulatory Sandbox (via the Office of Regulatory Relief) lets fintech/crypto firms test products. The Bitcoin-reserve provision (up to 5% of certain funds) was stripped in the Senate before passage.","legislators":"Rep. Jordan Teuscher sponsored HB 230; Sen. Kirk Cullimore led the floor debate that removed the reserve clause over adoption concerns.","orgs":"Stand With Crypto Utah chapter; Utah Office of Regulatory Relief (fintech sandbox); Silicon Slopes tech-industry hub near Salt Lake/Provo.","people":"Silicon Slopes founders and fintech entrepreneurs; Rep. Jordan Teuscher as a legislative champion.","universities":"University of Utah and Brigham Young University offer blockchain/fintech coursework and host student blockchain organizations; Utah''s tech ecosystem supports campus innovation programs.","gov_use":"Utah''s financial regulatory sandbox has hosted fintech/blockchain pilots; no state Bitcoin reserve after the HB 230 provision was dropped.","upcoming":"Possible renewed Bitcoin-reserve efforts after the 2025 removal; continued sandbox-based fintech/crypto pilots.","overview":"Utah enacted HB 230 (2025), a broad digital-asset-rights law protecting self-custody, mining, nodes, and staking, though it dropped the headline Bitcoin-reserve clause before passage. The state pairs a Republican-supermajority, pro-innovation posture with a pioneering financial regulatory sandbox and the Silicon Slopes tech hub.","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://le.utah.gov/~2025/bills/static/HB0230.html","https://cryptoslate.com/utah-pivots-away-from-state-bitcoin-reserve-in-landmark-crypto-legislation/","https://www.ncsl.org/","https://www.utah.edu/"]}','["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://le.utah.gov/~2025/bills/static/HB0230.html","https://cryptoslate.com/utah-pivots-away-from-state-bitcoin-reserve-in-landmark-crypto-legislation/","https://www.ncsl.org/","https://www.utah.edu/"]','2026-07-08 19:13:09');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('VA','Virginia','Mixed','{"stance":"Mixed","preview":"Modernized its money-transmitter law to exclude virtual currency from ''money''; earlier bills sought mining exemptions and small-transaction tax relief.","governor":"Glenn Youngkin (R, term ending Jan 2026) — business-friendly; a new governor takes office in 2026, so posture may shift.","legislature":"Closely divided General Assembly; digital-asset bills have drawn strong bipartisan votes (e.g., SB 339 passed the House 97-1).","regulation":"Money Transmission Modernization Act (HB 1942, 2025 Acts Ch. 214) creates a new Chapter 19.1 effective July 1, 2026 that defines ''virtual currency'' and expressly excludes it from ''money.'' Earlier SB 339 (2024) sought to exempt miners from money-transmitter licensing and exempt sub-$200 transactions from state capital-gains tax, and created a study workgroup. State income tax applies. Not a BitLicense state.","legislators":"Sen. Saddam Azlan Salim sponsored SB 339 (mining/tax exemptions and the study group) that informed 2025 legislation.","orgs":"Stand With Crypto Virginia chapter; Northern Virginia''s data-center corridor (the world''s largest) is relevant to mining/infrastructure and energy debates.","people":"Northern Virginia fintech and data-center executives; policy figures tied to the DC-area crypto-policy ecosystem.","universities":"George Mason University (Mercatus Center produces influential crypto/fintech policy research) and Virginia Tech offer blockchain-related coursework and research; UVA also has fintech programs.","gov_use":"No prominent state blockchain reserve or payments program; the state''s engagement is legislative/regulatory (MTMA modernization and study group).","upcoming":"Money Transmission Modernization Act Chapter 19.1 takes effect July 1, 2026; possible follow-on digital-asset bills from the study group''s recommendations.","overview":"Virginia has taken a measured, bipartisan approach: it modernized its money-transmitter framework (effective July 2026) to exclude virtual currency from the definition of ''money,'' and earlier bills sought mining exemptions and small-transaction tax relief. George Mason''s Mercatus Center is an influential in-state source of crypto policy research.","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://cointelegraph.com/news/virginia-crypto-bill-blockchain-mining-expansion","https://cryptoslate.com/crypto-laws/virginia-money-transmission-modernization-act-virtual-currency-treatment/","https://www.ncsl.org/","https://www.gmu.edu/"]}','["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://cointelegraph.com/news/virginia-crypto-bill-blockchain-mining-expansion","https://cryptoslate.com/crypto-laws/virginia-money-transmission-modernization-act-virtual-currency-treatment/","https://www.ncsl.org/","https://www.gmu.edu/"]','2026-07-08 19:13:33');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('OR','Oregon','Mixed','{"stance":"Mixed","preview":"Enacted UCC Article 12 (SB 167) recognizing digital assets and crypto collateral, but bars state acceptance of crypto payments and campaign contributions.","governor":"Tina Kotek (D) — signed SB 167 (May 2025) modernizing commercial law for digital assets; not a Bitcoin-reserve advocate.","legislature":"Democratic-controlled; pragmatic — favors legal-foundation bills over reserves or bold experiments.","regulation":"SB 167 (2025) adopts UCC Article 12 and amends Article 9 so digital assets can serve as collateral and recognizes electronic records/''electronic money.'' Oregon''s Money Transmitter Act is read to cover virtual currency including Bitcoin (DFR guidance). HB 2488 bars the state from accepting crypto payments and candidates from taking crypto campaign contributions unless authorized by the treasurer. State income tax applies. No Bitcoin-reserve proposal.","legislators":"SB 167 sponsors advanced the UCC digital-asset framework; HB 2071 (digital-asset payment/self-custody rights) remains pending in early stages.","orgs":"Stand With Crypto Oregon chapter; Oregon Division of Financial Regulation (DFR) is the key regulator. Portland tech/fintech community.","people":"Portland-area fintech and blockchain developers; no marquee crypto-native founders anchored to the state.","universities":"University of Oregon and Oregon State University offer computer-science and fintech coursework with blockchain components; student blockchain clubs exist on campuses.","gov_use":"State generally prohibited from accepting crypto payments absent treasurer authorization (HB 2488); no reserve or blockchain records pilot.","upcoming":"HB 2071 digital-asset-rights bill pending; SB 167''s UCC Article 12 provisions phasing in with a one-year compliance window for existing transactions.","overview":"Oregon takes a pragmatic, legal-foundation approach: SB 167 (2025) adopted UCC Article 12 to recognize digital assets and allow them as collateral, while the state still bars accepting crypto for payments or campaign contributions without treasurer approval. No Bitcoin reserve has been proposed, and a broader digital-asset-rights bill (HB 2071) remains early-stage.","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://www.cryptopolitan.com/oregon-signs-sb167-into-law-legal-crypto/","https://dfr.oregon.gov/help/Documents/5342-cryptocurrency.pdf","https://www.ncsl.org/","https://oregon.public.law/statutes/ors_260.011"]}','["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://www.cryptopolitan.com/oregon-signs-sb167-into-law-legal-crypto/","https://dfr.oregon.gov/help/Documents/5342-cryptocurrency.pdf","https://www.ncsl.org/","https://oregon.public.law/statutes/ors_260.011"]','2026-07-08 19:14:26');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('SD','South Dakota','Mixed','{"stance":"Mixed","preview":"No income tax and a repeatedly reintroduced Bitcoin-reserve bill (HB 1202/HB 1155), but reserve efforts have been defeated in committee.","governor":"Larry Rhoden (R) — business-friendly; has not made a Bitcoin reserve a signature priority.","legislature":"Republican-supermajority but cautious — committee defeated the 2025 reserve bill over volatility and regulatory-uncertainty concerns.","regulation":"No state personal income tax (crypto gains untaxed at state level). South Dakota notably declined to adopt some model money-transmitter virtual-currency provisions in the past, and its Division of Banking oversees money transmission. Not a BitLicense state. No enacted Bitcoin reserve.","legislators":"Rep. Logan Manhart (R) has repeatedly sponsored Bitcoin-reserve bills (HB 1202 and HCR 6006 in 2025, revived as HB 1155 in 2026) to allow up to 10% of public funds in Bitcoin.","orgs":"Stand With Crypto South Dakota chapter; South Dakota is a major trust/financial-services jurisdiction (favorable trust laws) relevant to digital-asset custody structuring.","people":"Rep. Logan Manhart as the persistent legislative champion; trust-industry professionals in Sioux Falls.","universities":"South Dakota State University and the University of South Dakota offer computing/finance coursework; smaller campus blockchain presence than larger states.","gov_use":"No live state Bitcoin reserve (proposals defeated); State Investment Council urged (via HCR 6006) to study Bitcoin as an inflation hedge.","upcoming":"HB 1155 (2026) revived reserve bill with tightened multi-party-governance and hardware-custody requirements; State Investment Council study resolution.","overview":"South Dakota has no income tax and a favorable trust-law environment, making it attractive for digital-asset structuring, but its legislature has repeatedly defeated Bitcoin-reserve bills over volatility concerns. Rep. Logan Manhart continues reintroducing reserve legislation (HB 1202 in 2025, HB 1155 in 2026).","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://sdlegislature.gov/Session/Bill/26125/279301","https://cointelegraph.com/news/south-dakota-bitcoin-reserve-bill","https://www.ncsl.org/","https://legiscan.com/SD/text/HB1202/2025"]}','["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://sdlegislature.gov/Session/Bill/26125/279301","https://cointelegraph.com/news/south-dakota-bitcoin-reserve-bill","https://www.ncsl.org/","https://legiscan.com/SD/text/HB1202/2025"]','2026-07-08 19:14:48');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('SC','South Carolina','Pro-crypto','{"stance":"Pro-crypto","preview":"Enacted S.163 (2026): protects self-custody and mining, exempts key crypto activity from money-transmitter licensing, and bans CBDC acceptance.","governor":"Henry McMaster (R) — pro-crypto; signed S.163 into law protecting self-custody and mining and banning state CBDC participation.","legislature":"Republican-controlled; overwhelmingly bipartisan on crypto (S.163 passed Senate 38-1, House 110-1).","regulation":"S.163 removes money-transmitter licensing for mining, node operation, blockchain software development, and non-fiat peer-to-peer exchange; classifies staking/mining-as-a-service as non-securities (AG retains fraud authority); protects self-custody and hardware wallets; provides tax parity for crypto payments; protects mining in industrially zoned areas (subject to noise/grid rules); and bars state acceptance of or participation in a CBDC. State income tax applies.","legislators":"Sens. Verdin and Leber sponsored S.163; Rep. Jordan Pace introduced H.4256, the Strategic Digital Assets Reserve Act (up to 10% of certain funds, 3% per-asset cap), which stalled in Ways and Means.","orgs":"Stand With Crypto South Carolina chapter; SC Office of the State Treasurer runs a Digital Assets Literacy Project; industrially-zoned mining operations in the state.","people":"Rep. Jordan Pace as a reserve champion; state Treasurer''s office active on digital-asset education.","universities":"Clemson University and the University of South Carolina offer computing/fintech coursework and host student blockchain organizations.","gov_use":"State Treasurer''s Digital Assets Literacy Project educates local governments; no Bitcoin reserve enacted (H.4256 stalled); CBDC participation banned.","upcoming":"H.4256 Strategic Digital Assets Reserve Act remains stalled in committee; implementation of S.163''s licensing and self-custody protections.","overview":"South Carolina enacted S.163, a strongly bipartisan pro-crypto law that protects self-custody and mining, exempts core crypto activities from money-transmitter licensing, provides payment tax parity, and bans state CBDC participation. A separate Bitcoin-reserve bill (H.4256) stalled, and the Treasurer runs a digital-asset literacy program.","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://www.scstatehouse.gov/sess126_2025-2026/bills/163.htm","https://bitcoinmagazine.com/news/south-carolina-enacts-bitcoin-friendly-law","https://treasurer.sc.gov/what-we-do/for-governments/digital-assets/","https://www.ncsl.org/"]}','["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://www.scstatehouse.gov/sess126_2025-2026/bills/163.htm","https://bitcoinmagazine.com/news/south-carolina-enacts-bitcoin-friendly-law","https://treasurer.sc.gov/what-we-do/for-governments/digital-assets/","https://www.ncsl.org/"]','2026-07-08 19:15:53');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('WV','West Virginia','Mixed','{"stance":"Mixed","preview":"A Bitcoin-reserve ''Inflation Protection Act'' was introduced but not enacted, while lawmakers advance crypto-ATM licensing rules.","governor":"Patrick Morrisey (R) — business-friendly; not a prominent Bitcoin-reserve champion.","legislature":"Republican-supermajority; interested but cautious — reserve bill referred to committee, ATM regulation advancing.","regulation":"Money transmission overseen by the Division of Financial Institutions. HB 5353 would bring crypto ATMs/kiosks under money-transmission rules with licensing, annual fees, disclosures, and daily limits (anti-fraud focus). State income tax applies. Not a BitLicense state. No enacted Bitcoin reserve.","legislators":"Sen. Chris Rose introduced the Inflation Protection Act of 2025 (up to 10% of treasury funds in digital assets/precious metals, on-chain or via ETFs, requiring a $750B+ market cap — effectively Bitcoin only).","orgs":"West Virginia Blockchain Foundation (wvblockchain.org) is an in-state policy/advocacy group tracking technology legislation; Stand With Crypto West Virginia chapter.","people":"Sen. Chris Rose as the reserve sponsor; West Virginia Blockchain Foundation organizers.","universities":"West Virginia University offers computing and fintech coursework; smaller campus blockchain footprint than larger states.","gov_use":"No live state Bitcoin reserve; engagement is primarily consumer-protection (crypto-ATM regulation) and a pending reserve proposal.","upcoming":"Inflation Protection Act (Bitcoin reserve) pending in Banking and Insurance; HB 5353 crypto-ATM licensing advancing.","overview":"West Virginia is a mixed case: a Bitcoin-reserve ''Inflation Protection Act'' (up to 10% of treasury funds) was introduced but not enacted, while the legislature advances consumer-protection rules bringing crypto ATMs under money-transmission licensing. The West Virginia Blockchain Foundation tracks state technology policy.","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://www.wvblockchain.org/policy","https://cointelegraph.com/news/west-virginia-digital-asset-allocation-bill","https://westvirginiawatch.com/2026/02/26/wv-legislature-advances-bills-that-would-regulate-crypto-atms/","https://www.ncsl.org/"]}','["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://www.wvblockchain.org/policy","https://cointelegraph.com/news/west-virginia-digital-asset-allocation-bill","https://westvirginiawatch.com/2026/02/26/wv-legislature-advances-bills-that-would-regulate-crypto-atms/","https://www.ncsl.org/"]','2026-07-08 19:16:10');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('WI','Wisconsin','Mixed','{"stance":"Mixed","preview":"Its state pension board was an early spot-Bitcoin-ETF investor via BlackRock''s IBIT, then fully exited the position in Q1 2025.","governor":"Tony Evers (D) — not a crypto policy driver; the state''s notable crypto action came from the independent investment board, not the executive.","legislature":"Split control historically; no marquee state Bitcoin-reserve legislation — Wisconsin''s crypto story is investment-driven, not statutory.","regulation":"Money transmission overseen by the Dept. of Financial Institutions; crypto exchanges generally need licensing. State income tax applies. Not a BitLicense state. No dedicated Bitcoin-reserve statute.","legislators":"No high-profile state crypto-reserve champion; policy attention has centered on the investment board''s ETF moves rather than legislation.","orgs":"State of Wisconsin Investment Board (SWIB) — among the first US public pension funds to hold a spot Bitcoin ETF; Stand With Crypto Wisconsin chapter.","people":"SWIB investment officers who made and unwound the Bitcoin ETF position; Milwaukee/Madison fintech community.","universities":"University of Wisconsin–Madison offers computer-science and fintech coursework and hosts student blockchain groups; Marquette University has related finance programs.","gov_use":"SWIB (the state pension board) bought a large spot Bitcoin ETF stake (BlackRock IBIT, peaking around $300M+) in 2024, then liquidated the entire position in Q1 2025 amid a price drop and tariff-driven market turmoil.","upcoming":"No active state reserve legislation; future SWIB exposure decisions are investment calls rather than statutory mandates.","overview":"Wisconsin''s crypto profile is investment-driven: its independent pension board (SWIB) was an early spot-Bitcoin-ETF holder via BlackRock''s IBIT before fully exiting in Q1 2025. There is no dedicated state Bitcoin-reserve statute, and the legislature has not pursued one, making the state a mixed, market-participation case rather than a policy leader.","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2025/05/16/wisconsin-sells-entire-350m-spot-bitcoin-etf-stake","https://decrypt.co/320373/wisconsin-pension-fund-300m-blackrock-bitcoin-etf-tariff-turmoil","https://www.ncsl.org/","https://www.wisc.edu/"]}','["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2025/05/16/wisconsin-sells-entire-350m-spot-bitcoin-etf-stake","https://decrypt.co/320373/wisconsin-pension-fund-300m-blackrock-bitcoin-etf-tariff-turmoil","https://www.ncsl.org/","https://www.wisc.edu/"]','2026-07-08 19:16:29');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('VT','Vermont','Mixed','{"stance":"Mixed","preview":"An early blockchain innovator (BBLLCs, blockchain evidence law) that now imposes strict money-transmission custody rules and aggressive crypto-kiosk regulation.","governor":"Phil Scott (R) — pragmatic; the state''s crypto posture is driven more by the Dept. of Financial Regulation than the executive.","legislature":"Democratic-controlled; balances early blockchain-innovation laws with strong consumer-protection measures.","regulation":"Adopted the Money Transmission Modernization Act (2024) with strict revisions: licensees must hold customer virtual currency in identical type/amount, cannot use wrapped tokens or derivatives to back native-token obligations, and cannot use unlicensed custodians. Crypto is treated as property. Act 110 (8 V.S.A. § 2577) heavily regulates virtual-currency kiosks (moratorium expired July 1, 2025; $1,000 daily cash limit; mandatory blockchain-analytics screening). Not a BitLicense state.","legislators":"Legislative focus has been consumer protection (Act 110 kiosk rules) rather than a Bitcoin reserve; earlier bipartisan support created the BBLLC and blockchain-evidence frameworks.","orgs":"Stand With Crypto Vermont chapter; Vermont Dept. of Financial Regulation (DFR) is the central regulator; the state''s BBLLC statute has attracted blockchain-entity formation.","people":"Blockchain-entity founders using Vermont''s BBLLC structure; DFR officials shaping kiosk and custody rules.","universities":"University of Vermont offers computing/complex-systems coursework with blockchain relevance; smaller campus crypto footprint.","gov_use":"Since 2016 (HB 868), blockchain-verified records are admissible as evidence in Vermont courts — an early government recognition of blockchain; no state Bitcoin reserve.","upcoming":"Processing of virtual-currency kiosk applications following the July 2025 moratorium expiry; continued MTMA custody-rule enforcement.","overview":"Vermont was an early blockchain innovator — pioneering blockchain-based LLCs (BBLLCs) and recognizing blockchain records as court evidence since 2016 — but pairs that with some of the strictest money-transmission custody rules (via its MTMA adoption) and aggressive crypto-kiosk consumer-protection regulation. The result is a genuinely mixed stance.","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://www.fintechlawblog.com/2024/08/14/vermont-enters-a-new-age-of-virtual-currency-money-transmission/","https://law.justia.com/codes/vermont/title-8/chapter-79/section-2577/","https://www.blankrome.com/publications/vermont-continues-its-blockchain-play-look-inside-states-new-legislation","https://www.ncsl.org/"]}','["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://www.fintechlawblog.com/2024/08/14/vermont-enters-a-new-age-of-virtual-currency-money-transmission/","https://law.justia.com/codes/vermont/title-8/chapter-79/section-2577/","https://www.blankrome.com/publications/vermont-continues-its-blockchain-play-look-inside-states-new-legislation","https://www.ncsl.org/"]','2026-07-08 19:17:35');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('RI','Rhode Island','Mixed','{"stance":"Mixed","preview":"Regulates crypto via money-transmitter law and cracked down on crypto-ATM fraud, but also licensed X for custody and is building a regulatory sandbox.","governor":"Dan McKee (D) — signed the 2025 crypto-ATM consumer-protection law; oversees a business-regulation department that has been relatively open to crypto licensing.","legislature":"Democratic-controlled; balances consumer protection (kiosk fraud) with economic-development/blockchain-growth proposals.","regulation":"Crypto overseen under money-transmitter law via the Dept. of Business Regulation (DBR), with AML and data-protection requirements; certain non-convertible/on-chain-only tokens exempt. The 2025 crypto-ATM law (S 0016A/H 5121A) requires kiosk operators to register as money transmitters, provide live support, cap daily limits ($2,000 new / $5,000 existing customers), and add warnings/receipts. State income tax applies. Not a BitLicense state.","legislators":"Sen. Victoria Gu (chair, AI & Emerging Technologies Committee) and Rep. Julie Casimiro sponsored the crypto-ATM fraud law; separate bills propose an ''Economic Growth Blockchain Act'' and a Bitcoin small-transaction tax exemption (up to $5,000/month).","orgs":"Stand With Crypto Rhode Island chapter; RI Dept. of Business Regulation (notably licensed X for crypto custody/transmission); state developing a regulatory sandbox.","people":"Sen. Victoria Gu as an emerging-tech legislative leader; DBR officials advancing crypto licensing.","universities":"Brown University and the University of Rhode Island offer computing/fintech coursework and host student blockchain organizations.","gov_use":"No state Bitcoin reserve; the state''s notable move is its DBR granting X a crypto custody/transmission license and developing a regulatory sandbox to attract crypto/blockchain firms.","upcoming":"Economic Growth Blockchain Act and Bitcoin small-transaction tax-exemption bill pending; rollout of the regulatory sandbox.","overview":"Rhode Island takes a mixed approach: it regulates crypto firmly under money-transmitter law and enacted a 2025 crypto-ATM fraud-protection statute, while also positioning itself as blockchain-friendly — licensing X for crypto custody/transmission and building a regulatory sandbox. Pending bills would boost blockchain business and exempt small Bitcoin transactions from tax.","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://rhodeislandcurrent.com/2025/02/12/r-i-house-bill-would-limit-transactions-add-warning-labels-to-crypto-kiosks/","https://coingeek.com/rhode-island-set-to-regulate-crypto-using-money-transmitter-laws/","https://cointelegraph.com/news/rhode-island-introduces-vital-blockchain-growth-act","https://www.ncsl.org/"]}','["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://rhodeislandcurrent.com/2025/02/12/r-i-house-bill-would-limit-transactions-add-warning-labels-to-crypto-kiosks/","https://coingeek.com/rhode-island-set-to-regulate-crypto-using-money-transmitter-laws/","https://cointelegraph.com/news/rhode-island-introduces-vital-blockchain-growth-act","https://www.ncsl.org/"]','2026-07-08 19:18:01');
INSERT INTO "us_states" ("abbr","name","stance","profile","sources","updated_at") VALUES ('OK','Oklahoma','Pro-crypto','{"stance":"Pro-crypto","preview":"First US state to codify a ''Bitcoin Rights'' law (HB 3594): protects self-custody, mining, nodes, and staking, and exempts miners/validators from money-transmitter licensing.","governor":"Kevin Stitt (R) — pro-crypto; signed HB 3594 (May 2024) making Oklahoma the first state to enshrine self-custody rights.","legislature":"Republican-supermajority; strongly pro-crypto, passing the Bitcoin Rights Act with broad support.","regulation":"HB 3594 bars extra taxes on crypto payments, legalizes home and industrial mining (subject to existing noise/data-center rules), protects self-custody (self-hosted/hardware wallets), permits node operation and staking, and exempts miners/validators from money-transmitter licensing. Directs the Corporation Commission not to set discriminatory power rates for miners. State income tax applies. Not a BitLicense state.","legislators":"Rep. Brian Hill (R) authored HB 3594; Sen. Bill Coleman (R) carried it in the Senate. A separate strategic Bitcoin reserve effort has been discussed but not enacted.","orgs":"Oklahoma Bitcoin Association (educated lawmakers, drove HB 3594); Satoshi Action Fund (model policy); Stand With Crypto Oklahoma chapter; mining investment such as Polaris Technologies'' ~$100M/200MW facility near Tulsa.","people":"Oklahoma Bitcoin Association organizers; Rep. Brian Hill as legislative champion; mining-industry operators drawn by cheap power.","universities":"University of Oklahoma and Oklahoma State University offer computing/fintech coursework and host student technology organizations with blockchain interest.","gov_use":"No state Bitcoin reserve enacted; the state''s posture is rights-protective and mining-friendly rather than treasury-participatory.","upcoming":"Possible strategic Bitcoin reserve legislation in future sessions; continued mining expansion under HB 3594''s protections.","overview":"Oklahoma was the first US state to enact a sweeping ''Bitcoin Rights'' law (HB 3594, 2024), protecting self-custody, mining, node operation, and staking, and exempting miners/validators from money-transmitter licensing. Backed by the Oklahoma Bitcoin Association and Satoshi Action Fund model policy, it has attracted major mining investment, though it has not (yet) created a state Bitcoin reserve.","sources":["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://www.coindesk.com/policy/2024/05/15/sweeping-bitcoin-rights-bill-becomes-law-in-oklahoma","https://www.oklahomabitcoin.org/policy","https://decrypt.co/230962/bitcoin-self-custody-right-law-mining-oklahoma","https://www.ncsl.org/"]}','["https://www.standwithcrypto.org/","https://www.coindesk.com/policy/2024/05/15/sweeping-bitcoin-rights-bill-becomes-law-in-oklahoma","https://www.oklahomabitcoin.org/policy","https://decrypt.co/230962/bitcoin-self-custody-right-law-mining-oklahoma","https://www.ncsl.org/"]','2026-07-08 19:19:21');
INSERT INTO "scam_traces" ("slug","name","category","amount_usd","profile","sources","updated_at","net_usd","recovered_usd","victims","start_date","collapse_date","status","chains","confidence","source_checked_at") VALUES ('bybit-2025','Bybit Hack (2025)','exploit',1500000000,'{"summary":"On 21 February 2025, DPRK''s Lazarus Group (FBI cluster ''TraderTraitor''/UNC4899) executed the largest crypto theft in history, draining ~401,347 ETH plus liquid-staking tokens (~$1.4-1.5B) from a Bybit Ethereum multisig cold wallet in a single transaction. Rather than breaking the exchange''s infrastructure or the multisig cryptography, the attackers compromised the supply chain of Safe{Wallet} (the third-party multisig UI Bybit used): they socially-engineered a Safe developer''s macOS machine on ~4 Feb 2025, pivoted into Safe''s AWS environment, and on 19 Feb injected targeted malicious JavaScript into app.safe.global. When Bybit ran a routine cold-to-warm ETH transfer on 21 Feb (~14:13 UTC), the signers were shown a legitimate-looking transaction on their Ledgers while actually authorizing an operation=1 delegatecall that overwrote the proxy''s implementation (masterCopy) storage slot, handing wallet control to the attacker and sweeping the balance. ZachXBT submitted definitive Lazarus attribution to Arkham within ~5 hours (19:09 UTC), and the FBI issued a formal ''TraderTraitor'' PSA on 26 Feb 2025 with 51 flagged addresses. The stolen ETH was laundered in ~10 days: liquid-staking tokens were unwrapped to native ETH, ~83% (~361,255 ETH, ~$900M) was swapped to Bitcoin via the decentralized cross-chain protocol THORChain, and the BTC was atomized across thousands of wallets; ~$200M (~15%) went ''dark'' through the no-KYC service eXch. By 4 Mar 2025, Bybit CEO Ben Zhou reported ~77% still traceable, ~20% dark via eXch, and only single-digit percentages frozen.","actor":"Lazarus Group / TraderTraitor / UNC4899 (also tracked as Jade Sleet, Slow Pisces, APT38) — DPRK state-sponsored, under the Reconnaissance General Bureau; proceeds fund the nuclear/ballistic-missile program.","technical":"The attack was a frontend supply-chain compromise of the multisig signing surface, not a smart-contract or key-theft exploit. Around 4 Feb 2025 a Safe{Wallet} developer''s macOS workstation was compromised via a malicious Docker project (''MC-Based-Stock-Invest-Simulator-main'' beaconing to getstockprice[.]com), a classic Lazarus social-engineering lure; the attackers then stole AWS session tokens to bypass MFA and reach Safe''s AWS/S3-CloudFront infrastructure. On 18 Feb they pre-deployed the malicious contract bytecode on Ethereum mainnet, and on 19 Feb injected JavaScript into app.safe.global''s S3 bucket that patched executeTransaction/signTransaction (and useGasLimit) to activate ONLY for Bybit''s specific wallet (0x1Db92e2EeBC8E0c075a02BeA49a2935BcD2dFCF4) and signer addresses, staying invisible to all other users. On 21 Feb Bybit initiated a normal cold-to-warm transfer; the injected code silently rewrote the transaction so that instead of an ERC-20 transfer it set operation=1 (delegatecall) targeting the attacker contract 0x96221423681A6d52E184D440a8eFCEbB105C7242. Because delegatecall runs external code in the CALLER''s storage context, the attacker''s fake transfer(address,uint256) function wrote to storage slot 0 — the slot holding the Gnosis Safe masterCopy/implementation pointer — replacing it with the malicious implementation 0xbDd077f651EBe7f7b3cE16fe5F2b025BE2969516. This ''blind signing'' problem is the crux: the calldata was not human-readable, the Ledger devices showed only opaque hex, and a similar legitimate delegatecall (an mETH transfer on 14 Jan 2025) made the pattern look plausible, so ~3 signers approved it. Once slot 0 was overwritten the proxy pointed to attacker-controlled logic granting a sweep of all funds; two minutes after the exploit tx, clean JavaScript was re-uploaded to the S3 bucket to erase the evidence. Root cause per Sygnia, Verichains and Mandiant: no Bybit-side vulnerability — the compromise was entirely in the Safe{Wallet} delivery pipeline, exploiting excessive delegatecall attack surface and UI-trust.","timeline":[{"date":"2025-02-04","event":"Safe{Wallet} developer (''Developer1'') macOS machine compromised via malicious Docker project beaconing to getstockprice[.]com; ~12 days of AWS reconnaissance begin."},{"date":"2025-02-18","event":"Attackers deploy the malicious contract bytecode (delegatecall target 0x9622...7242 / implementation 0xbDd0...9516) on Ethereum mainnet."},{"date":"2025-02-19","event":"Malicious JavaScript injected into Safe{Wallet}''s AWS S3 bucket serving app.safe.global (last-modified 17:29 UTC), targeting only Bybit''s wallet/signers."},{"date":"2025-02-21","event":"~13:30 UTC Bybit begins a routine cold-to-warm transfer; ~14:13 UTC the exploit tx (0xb614...072c) executes the delegatecall, sweeping 401,347 ETH + LSTs (~$1.5B). Funds split across ~39-50 wallets. 19:09 UTC ZachXBT submits Lazarus proof to Arkham."},{"date":"2025-02-22","event":"eXch declines Bybit''s request to freeze/assist; laundering exceeds ~$160M within the first 48 hours."},{"date":"2025-02-23","event":"Ben Zhou publicly appeals to eXch; Bybit reports ~$42.89M frozen in a day; laundered total passes ~$200M."},{"date":"2025-02-24","event":"THORChain becomes the primary ETH-to-BTC conduit; daily volume spikes toward billions."},{"date":"2025-02-26","event":"FBI issues PSA (I-022625-PSA) attributing the theft to DPRK ''TraderTraitor'' with 51 flagged ETH addresses. Sygnia + Verichains preliminary reports (shared by Zhou) confirm no Bybit-side flaw. THORChain node operators pause the ETH chain, but the pause is reversed within ~30 minutes; developer ''Pluto'' later resigns."},{"date":"2025-03-04","event":"Zhou reports ~77% (417,348 ETH / ~$1B) still traceable, ~20% (~79,655 ETH / ~$200M) gone dark via eXch, ~$100M through OKX Web3 proxy (~$65M untraceable); 83% (361,255 ETH) already converted to BTC across ~6,954 wallets."},{"date":"2025-03-20","event":"Zhou reports 86.29% of stolen ETH converted to BTC; funds now dispersed across ~35,000+ wallets."},{"date":"2025-04-22","event":"Zhou update: ~27% of funds have ''gone dark'' after passing through mixers (Wasabi, CryptoMixer, Tornado Cash, Railgun) and bridges (THORChain, eXch, Lombard, LiFi, Stargate, SunSwap) toward OTC/P2P fiat."},{"date":"2025-04-30","event":"German BKA + Frankfurt cybercrime prosecutors seize eXch servers (>8 TB data) and ~EUR 34M / ~$38M in crypto — one day before eXch''s planned 1 May shutdown."},{"date":"2025-07-09","event":"Chainalysis reports the first crypto seizure in Greece connected to the Bybit case."}],"entities":[{"name":"Lazarus Group / TraderTraitor / UNC4899","role":"attacker","detail":"DPRK RGB state hacking cluster; executed the supply-chain compromise and laundering. Also tied to Phemex, BingX, Poloniex, Ronin, Harmony, DMM Bitcoin, WazirX thefts."},{"name":"Bybit","role":"victim","detail":"Dubai-based exchange; lost ~$1.5B. CEO Ben Zhou led public response, covered customer losses, launched the Lazarus Bounty Program."},{"name":"Safe{Wallet} / Safe Ecosystem Foundation","role":"facilitator (compromised)","detail":"Multisig platform whose developer machine and AWS/S3 frontend delivery pipeline were breached; the malicious JS was served from app.safe.global."},{"name":"Bybit ETH cold wallet","role":"victim wallet","detail":"0x1Db92e2EeBC8E0c075a02BeA49a2935BcD2dFCF4 (Gnosis Safe proxy)."},{"name":"Gnosis Safe masterCopy (legit implementation)","role":"victim contract","detail":"0x34CfAC646f301356fAa8B21e94227e3583Fe3F5F — the implementation slot overwritten by the exploit."},{"name":"Attacker delegatecall contract","role":"attacker","detail":"0x96221423681A6d52E184D440a8eFCEbB105C7242 — fake ERC-20 whose transfer() wrote to storage slot 0."},{"name":"Malicious implementation","role":"attacker","detail":"0xbDd077f651EBe7f7b3cE16fe5F2b025BE2969516 — new masterCopy written to slot 0, granting the sweep."},{"name":"Exploiter primary wallet","role":"attacker","detail":"0x47666Fab8bd0Ac7003bce3f5C3585383F09486E2 — first recipient of the drained 401,347 ETH."},{"name":"THORChain","role":"launderer (facilitator)","detail":"Decentralized cross-chain protocol; ~$900M ETH swapped to BTC; ~100 node operators earned ~$5.5M in fees; a pause vote was reversed in ~30 min."},{"name":"eXch","role":"launderer (facilitator)","detail":"No-KYC swap service (est. 2014); laundered ~$200M (~15%) of Bybit funds; refused freeze requests; seized/shut by German authorities 30 Apr 2025."},{"name":"OKX Web3 proxy","role":"facilitator","detail":"~$100M routed through it; ~$65M (23,553 ETH) untraceable; OKX paused DEX aggregator amid scrutiny."},{"name":"ZachXBT","role":"investigator","detail":"Independent on-chain investigator; submitted definitive Lazarus attribution to Arkham within hours; top bounty contributor."},{"name":"Sygnia / Verichains / Mandiant","role":"investigator","detail":"Forensic firms; established the root cause was Safe{Wallet}''s frontend, not Bybit. Mandiant tied it to UNC4899 and MythicAgents tooling."},{"name":"Chainalysis / TRM Labs / Elliptic","role":"investigator","detail":"Blockchain analytics firms tracing funds, freezing, and confirming DPRK/eXch links."},{"name":"FBI / IC3","role":"enforcement","detail":"Issued PSA I-022625-PSA (26 Feb 2025) attributing to DPRK TraderTraitor; published 51 addresses."},{"name":"German BKA + Frankfurt cybercrime prosecutors","role":"enforcement","detail":"Seized eXch infrastructure and ~$38M on 30 Apr 2025."}],"hops":[{"from":"Bybit ETH multisig cold wallet (0x1Db92e2EeBC8E0c075a02BeA49a2935BcD2dFCF4)","to":"Exploiter primary wallet 0x47666Fab8bd0Ac7003bce3f5C3585383F09486E2","amount":"401,347","asset":"ETH (+ 90,375 stETH, 15,000 cmETH, 8,000 mETH, 90 USDT)","chain":"Ethereum","txhash":"0xb61413c495fdad6114a7aa863a00b2e3c28945979a10885b12b30316ea9f072c","txurl":"https://etherscan.io/tx/0xb61413c495fdad6114a7aa863a00b2e3c28945979a10885b12b30316ea9f072c","note":"Injected Safe{Wallet} JS rewrote the routine transfer to operation=1 delegatecall to attacker contract 0x9622...7242, whose transfer() overwrote proxy storage slot 0 with malicious implementation 0xbDd0...9516, sweeping the full cold wallet.","date":"2025-02-21"},{"from":"Exploiter primary wallet","to":"~39-50 intermediary distribution wallets (~10,000 ETH each)","amount":"401,347","asset":"ETH","chain":"Ethereum","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/bybit-exchange-hack-february-2025-crypto-security-dprk/","note":"Funds fanned out within hours to fragment the trail (''flood the zone''); ~$160M laundered in the first 48 hours, >$200M by 23 Feb, >$400M by 26 Feb.","date":"2025-02-21"},{"from":"Intermediary wallets","to":"mETH/stETH/cmETH unwrap + DEX swaps to native ETH","amount":"~113,375","asset":"LST->ETH","chain":"Ethereum","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.trmlabs.com/resources/blog/the-bybit-hack-following-north-koreas-largest-exploit","note":"Liquid-staking tokens unwrapped to native ETH (and some routed via Binance Smart Chain and Solana) to make funds freely bridgeable.","date":"2025-02-22"},{"from":"Intermediary wallets","to":"THORChain cross-chain router (ETH->BTC)","amount":"~361,255","asset":"ETH","chain":"Ethereum->Bitcoin","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.dlnews.com/articles/defi/thorchain-role-in-lazarus-laundering-is-big-defi-problem/","note":"~83% of stolen ETH (~$900M) swapped to native BTC via THORChain over ~1 week; ~100 node operators earned ~$5.5M in fees; a node vote to pause the ETH chain was reversed within ~30 minutes and developer ''Pluto'' resigned.","date":"2025-02-24"},{"from":"THORChain output","to":"~6,954 Bitcoin wallets (rising to ~35,000+)","amount":"~10,003 (avg 1.71 BTC/wallet)","asset":"BTC","chain":"Bitcoin","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2025/03/04/bybit-says-77-of-stolen-funds-from-record-usd1-4b-hack-still-traceable","note":"BTC atomized across thousands of wallets, then held largely stationary pending OTC/P2P liquidation; by 20 Mar Zhou reported 86.29% converted to BTC.","date":"2025-02-26"},{"from":"Intermediary wallets","to":"eXch no-KYC instant exchange","amount":"~79,655 (ETH-equiv) / ~$200M","asset":"multi","chain":"multi","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.elliptic.co/blog/the-rise-and-fall-of-exch-the-dark-service-used-by-north-korea-to-launder-200-million-stolen-from-bybit","note":"eXch refused Bybit''s block requests; ~15% of proceeds (~$200M) went ''dark'' through it before German seizure. Later routed through Wasabi, CryptoMixer, Tornado Cash, Railgun and bridges (Lombard, LiFi, Stargate, SunSwap).","date":"2025-02-27"},{"from":"Intermediary wallets","to":"OKX Web3 DEX proxy","amount":"~40,233 / ~$100M (23,553 ETH / ~$65M untraceable)","asset":"ETH","chain":"multi","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2025/03/04/bybit-says-77-of-stolen-funds-from-record-usd1-4b-hack-still-traceable","note":"~$100M routed via OKX''s Web3 aggregator; ~$65M flagged untraceable. OKX later paused its DEX aggregator amid regulatory scrutiny.","date":"2025-03-01"},{"from":"Laundering cluster","to":"Frozen by Tether/Circle/exchange partners","amount":"~$42.89M (day-one) rising; single-digit % overall","asset":"USD-equiv","chain":"multi","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.theblock.co/post/351344/bybit-ceo-says-nearly-28-of-1-4-billion-hacked-crypto-gone-dark","note":"Coordinated freezes by Tether, Circle, THORChain relayers, ChangeNOW, FixedFloat, CoinEx, Bitget; Bybit''s Lazarus Bounty paid ~$4.3M to 18 contributors (top: Mantle, Paraswap, ZachXBT).","date":"2025-03-04"},{"from":"eXch infrastructure","to":"Seized by German BKA / Frankfurt prosecutors","amount":"~$38M + >8TB data","asset":"multi","chain":"multi","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.dlnews.com/articles/regulation/german-police-shutter-crypto-mixer-tied-to-bybit-hack/","note":"30 Apr 2025 takedown — Germany''s 3rd-largest crypto confiscation; eXch had facilitated >$1.9B in transactions total.","date":"2025-04-30"}],"aftermath":"Bybit remained solvent — Zhou secured bridge loans and processed a record withdrawal spike (~350,000 requests) without halting, and covered all customer losses, publicly closing the reserve gap within ~72 hours. The Lazarus Bounty Program paid out ~$4.3M to 18 contributors (top: Mantle, Paraswap, ZachXBT). Enforcement wins were partial: the FBI''s 26 Feb PSA published 51 addresses and urged industry-wide blocking; German authorities seized eXch (~$38M + 8TB data) on 30 Apr 2025; and Chainalysis reported the first Greek crypto seizure tied to the case on 9 Jul 2025. Despite ~77% being traceable at day 11, the vast majority was never recovered — as of early 2026 investigators (zeroShadow) estimated $100M-$500M still unaccounted, with most funds off-ramped via OTC/P2P. Safe{Wallet} restored mainnet with a phased rollout that temporarily removed native Ledger integration and hardened its delivery pipeline; Bybit and others accelerated adoption of independent transaction-verification and clear-signing.","industry_impact":"The hack reframed exchange security around the signing supply chain rather than key custody: it proved that a fully cryptographically-sound multisig can be defeated by compromising the UI that human signers trust, elevating ''blind signing'' to a top-tier systemic risk. Concrete shifts: rapid industry push for clear-signing / calldata decoding on hardware wallets, independent out-of-band transaction verification (verifying the raw calldata, operation type and target against the displayed UI), monitoring/alerting on delegatecall and proxy-implementation changes, minimizing delegatecall attack surface with purpose-built vaults, and hardening frontend CI/CD and cloud (AWS) credential hygiene against session-token theft. It also intensified the policy debate over ''neutral'' decentralized infrastructure: THORChain''s node community declining to block flows (and reversing a pause in 30 minutes) and eXch''s refusal-then-seizure echoed the Tornado Cash complicity debate and strengthened the case for treating no-KYC mixers/bridges as sanctionable laundering conduits. Finally, it validated the ''freeze fast or lose it'' reality — recovery hinged on off-ramp cooperation speed, driving tighter exchange/stablecoin coordination and faster analytics-to-enforcement pipelines.","analysis":"The Bybit heist inverted the usual playbook: instead of a smart-contract bug or stolen keys, Lazarus attacked the signing supply chain (a compromised Safe{Wallet} developer machine -> AWS session tokens -> targeted frontend JS), defeating a 3-of-N multisig by deceiving human signers via blind signing rather than breaking cryptography. The single malicious lever was operation=1 (delegatecall), which let a fake ERC-20 transfer() rewrite storage slot 0 (the implementation pointer) and swap the wallet''s logic. Laundering then favored speed and automation over classical anonymity — ''flooding the zone'' with ~39-50 intermediary wallets, LST unwraps, and a decentralized cross-chain router (THORChain) that has no KYC and cannot be subpoenaed, followed by hyper-atomization across tens of thousands of BTC wallets and a no-KYC exit (eXch). Recovery hinged not on on-chain tracing (funds stayed ~77% traceable) but on how fast fiat/stablecoin off-ramps could freeze funds; ~20-28% went permanently dark within days. Prevention decisively shifted to hardening the multisig signing UI, clear-signing, and verifying transaction calldata independently of the displayed UI.","parallels":"This is the direct successor to Lazarus''s earlier bridge/exchange thefts — Ronin ($625M, 2022) and Harmony ($100M, 2022) — but where those relied on Tornado Cash, Bybit shows the group''s post-sanction migration to THORChain, Railgun and eXch, exactly the adaptation Harmony''s dormancy-then-Railgun pivot foreshadowed. The Safe{Wallet} UI supply-chain compromise echoes the social-engineering entry vectors of Ronin (fake job lure) and the broader TraderTraitor campaign (malicious npm/Docker projects), showing Lazarus consistently targets humans and tooling rather than protocol math. In scale it dwarfed and displaced the Ronin ($625M) and Poly Network ($611M, 2021) records — the single theft exceeded North Korea''s entire 2024 haul (~$1.34B). The THORChain governance clash and eXch''s refusal-then-seizure mirror the Tornado Cash ''neutral infrastructure vs. complicity'' debate that ended in developer prosecutions.","legal":"The FBI issued PSA I-022625-PSA on 26 Feb 2025 attributing the theft to DPRK/TraderTraitor (Lazarus) and publishing 51 flagged Ethereum addresses, tying proceeds to DPRK''s nuclear/ballistic-missile financing (the regime is estimated to have stolen $5B+ in crypto since 2017 and $1.34B in 2024 alone). The laundering conduit eXch was raided and shut down by German prosecutors (Frankfurt cybercrime office + BKA) on 30 Apr 2025, with >8TB of data and ~EUR 34M/~$38M seized — Germany''s third-largest crypto confiscation — after eXch had facilitated an estimated >$1.9B in transactions. Chainalysis reported the first crypto seizure in Greece connected to the case on 9 Jul 2025. Jurisdictional friction centered on THORChain, a decentralized protocol whose ~100-node community voted NOT to sustain a block (reversing a pause within ~30 minutes), prompting developer ''Pluto'' to resign to limit legal exposure — mirroring the Tornado Cash developer prosecutions.","confidence":"high — The attack mechanism (Safe{Wallet} supply-chain compromise, delegatecall/slot-0 overwrite), the exploit tx and contract addresses, DPRK/TraderTraitor attribution, the THORChain/eXch laundering route, and the eXch seizure are all well-established via multiple forensic firms (Sygnia, Verichains, Mandiant, Chainalysis, TRM, Elliptic), the FBI PSA, German BKA statements, and Bybit CEO disclosures. Precise per-hop amounts, exact wallet counts, and the final recovered/lost totals are best-available estimates that shifted over time and remain partly alleged/approximate.","sources":["https://www.ic3.gov/PSA/2025/PSA250226","https://www.nccgroup.com/research/in-depth-technical-analysis-of-the-bybit-hack/","https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/bybit-exchange-hack-february-2025-crypto-security-dprk/","https://www.trmlabs.com/resources/blog/the-bybit-hack-following-north-koreas-largest-exploit","https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/lazarus-hacked-bybit-via-breached-safe-wallet-developer-machine/","https://www.elliptic.co/blog/the-rise-and-fall-of-exch-the-dark-service-used-by-north-korea-to-launder-200-million-stolen-from-bybit","https://www.dlnews.com/articles/defi/thorchain-role-in-lazarus-laundering-is-big-defi-problem/","https://www.dlnews.com/articles/regulation/german-police-shutter-crypto-mixer-tied-to-bybit-hack/","https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2025/03/04/bybit-says-77-of-stolen-funds-from-record-usd1-4b-hack-still-traceable","https://www.theblock.co/post/351344/bybit-ceo-says-nearly-28-of-1-4-billion-hacked-crypto-gone-dark"]}','["https://www.ic3.gov/PSA/2025/PSA250226","https://www.nccgroup.com/research/in-depth-technical-analysis-of-the-bybit-hack/","https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/bybit-exchange-hack-february-2025-crypto-security-dprk/","https://www.trmlabs.com/resources/blog/the-bybit-hack-following-north-koreas-largest-exploit","https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/lazarus-hacked-bybit-via-breached-safe-wallet-developer-machine/","https://www.elliptic.co/blog/the-rise-and-fall-of-exch-the-dark-service-used-by-north-korea-to-launder-200-million-stolen-from-bybit","https://www.dlnews.com/articles/defi/thorchain-role-in-lazarus-laundering-is-big-defi-problem/","https://www.dlnews.com/articles/regulation/german-police-shutter-crypto-mixer-tied-to-bybit-hack/","https://www.coindesk.com/markets/2025/03/04/bybit-says-77-of-stolen-funds-from-record-usd1-4b-hack-still-traceable","https://www.theblock.co/post/351344/bybit-ceo-says-nearly-28-of-1-4-billion-hacked-crypto-gone-dark"]','2026-07-08 20:33:41',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "scam_traces" ("slug","name","category","amount_usd","profile","sources","updated_at","net_usd","recovered_usd","victims","start_date","collapse_date","status","chains","confidence","source_checked_at") VALUES ('ronin-2022','Ronin Bridge Hack (2022)','bridge hack',625000000,'{"summary":"On 23 March 2022, the DPRK''s Lazarus Group stole 173,600 ETH and 25.5M USDC (~$625M at peak reporting; ~$540M at Elliptic''s initial estimate) from the Ronin bridge, the Ethereum sidechain built by Sky Mavis for Axie Infinity — the largest crypto theft in history at the time. The entry vector was social engineering: a Lazarus operative posed as a recruiter and, after multiple fake interview rounds, sent a senior Sky Mavis engineer a malware-laden PDF ''job offer'' that compromised the company''s IT infrastructure. Ronin used a proof-of-authority bridge requiring 5-of-9 validator signatures; the attackers captured 4 Sky Mavis validator keys via lateral movement and obtained the decisive 5th signature by abusing a gas-free RPC node still whitelisted for the Axie DAO — a permission granted in Nov 2021 to handle transaction load and never revoked when discontinued in Dec 2021. With 5 keys they forged two withdrawal transactions and drained the bridge. The theft went undetected for six days — Sky Mavis lacked large-outflow monitoring — until a user''s failed 5,000-ETH withdrawal exposed it on 29 March. The FBI/OFAC attributed it to Lazarus/APT38 and sanctioned the exploiter wallet on 14 April 2022.","actor":"Lazarus Group / APT38 (BlueNorOff) — DPRK state-sponsored; FBI/CISA cluster codename ''TraderTraitor'' for the fake-recruiter crypto-theft operations","technical":"The Ronin bridge was secured not by a smart-contract vulnerability but by a 5-of-9 proof-of-authority multisig: any withdrawal from the bridge escrow required valid signatures from at least five of nine designated validator nodes. Sky Mavis operated four of those validators; the remaining five were run by third parties, including the Axie DAO. The compromise began at the human layer — a senior engineer was spear-phished via a fake LinkedIn/recruiter approach and opened a trojanized PDF ''offer document'' on a corporate device, letting Lazarus establish a foothold and move laterally through Sky Mavis IT infrastructure until it held the private keys to all four Sky Mavis validators. Four signatures were insufficient, so the attackers exploited a stale configuration: in November 2021, to absorb heavy user load, the Axie DAO had allowlisted Sky Mavis to sign transactions on the DAO''s behalf through a gas-free RPC node; this arrangement ended in December 2021 but the allowlist grant was never revoked, so once inside Sky Mavis systems the attacker could obtain the fifth (Axie DAO) signature through that same RPC node. Holding five keys, the attacker called the bridge''s withdrawERC20For function in two sequential transactions (the primary drain tx 0xc28fad5e8d5e0ce6a2eaf67b6687be5d58113e16be590824d6cfa1a94467d0b7 against the Ronin bridge contract 0x1a2a1c938ce3ec39b6d47113c7955baa9dd454f2), forging withdrawals of 173,600 ETH and 25,500,000 USDC to the exploiter address 0x098B716B8Aaf21512996dC57EB0615e2383E2f96, which had been pre-funded ~1.0569 ETH from an exchange to pay gas. Because the bridge had no anomaly/large-outflow alerting, the drain sat unnoticed for six days. Root causes: over-concentrated validator trust (only 9 signers), custody/key-management failure via a spear-phish, an un-revoked stale permission, and absent outflow monitoring.","timeline":[{"date":"2021-11","event":"Axie DAO allowlists Sky Mavis to sign transactions on its behalf via a gas-free RPC node to handle heavy Axie Infinity load — the permission that later yields the 5th signature."},{"date":"2021-12","event":"The Axie DAO delegation is discontinued, but the allowlist access is never revoked (the decisive latent flaw)."},{"date":"2022-03-23","event":"Attack executed. Exploiter wallet 0x098B… pre-funded ~1.0569 ETH for gas; two forged withdrawals (tx 0xc28fad…) drain 173,600 ETH and 25.5M USDC via withdrawERC20For."},{"date":"2022-03-28","event":"Attacker begins cashing out ~$21M of ETH to centralized exchanges (incl. Huobi, FTX, Crypto.com-linked wallets) before exchanges announce cooperation."},{"date":"2022-03-29","event":"Breach discovered after a user cannot withdraw 5,000 ETH; Sky Mavis/Ronin issue a public community alert. 25.5M USDC swapped to ETH via 1inch/Uniswap to escape Circle freeze."},{"date":"2022-04-04","event":"Attacker begins continuous ~6,000-ETH batch deposits into Tornado Cash; ultimately >$455M of Ronin funds cycled through the mixer."},{"date":"2022-04-14","event":"US Treasury/OFAC attributes the theft to Lazarus and adds exploiter address 0x098B… to the SDN list — the first time a specific hack wallet was sanctioned. FBI issues formal attribution."},{"date":"2022-04-22","event":"OFAC adds 3 additional addresses (that had held ~50k stolen ETH) to the SDN list, extending the designation."},{"date":"2022-08-08","event":"OFAC sanctions Tornado Cash itself (press release jy0916), citing >$455M of the Ronin proceeds as primary justification — first sanctioning of an on-chain decentralized protocol."},{"date":"2022-09-08","event":"Chainalysis + US law enforcement announce recovery of >$30M (~10% of stolen funds) — first-ever seizure of crypto stolen by a North Korean group."},{"date":"2023-02","event":"Norway''s Økokrim confiscates ~$5.8M in Ronin-linked crypto — Norway''s largest-ever crypto seizure; total recovered climbs toward ~$40M."},{"date":"2023-04","event":"DOJ charges DPRK Foreign Trade Bank rep Sim Hyon Sop and OTC-trader co-conspirators in crypto-laundering conspiracies tied to DPRK hack proceeds; concurrent OFAC sanctions."}],"entities":[{"name":"Lazarus Group / APT38 (BlueNorOff)","role":"attacker","detail":"DPRK Reconnaissance General Bureau state-sponsored unit; executed the intrusion and laundering. FBI/CISA codename cluster ''TraderTraitor''."},{"name":"0x098B716B8Aaf21512996dC57EB0615e2383E2f96","role":"attacker","detail":"Primary ''Ronin Bridge Exploiter'' wallet; received 173,600 ETH + proceeds; OFAC-sanctioned 14 Apr 2022."},{"name":"Sky Mavis","role":"victim","detail":"Developer of Axie Infinity and operator of 4 of the 9 Ronin validators; a compromised senior engineer was the initial foothold."},{"name":"Axie DAO","role":"victim","detail":"Ran a 5th validator; its un-revoked gas-free-RPC allowlist to Sky Mavis provided the decisive 5th signature."},{"name":"Ronin bridge contract 0x1a2a1c938ce3ec39b6d47113c7955baa9dd454f2","role":"victim","detail":"The bridge escrow contract; drained via withdrawERC20For."},{"name":"Tornado Cash","role":"facilitator","detail":"Ethereum mixer through which >$455M of Ronin ETH was laundered in ~6,000-ETH batches; OFAC-sanctioned 8 Aug 2022 (jy0916)."},{"name":"ChipMixer","role":"facilitator","detail":"Bitcoin mixer; per SlowMist ~3,460 BTC of converted proceeds routed through it after ETH→renBTC→BTC bridging."},{"name":"Binance / Huobi / FTX / Crypto.com","role":"facilitator","detail":"Centralized exchanges used as early off-ramps (~$21M / ~440 BTC). Binance froze a tranche of funds and cooperated with law enforcement."},{"name":"Sim Hyon Sop + OTC traders (Wu HuiHui, Cheng Hung Man, ''Chen'')","role":"launderer","detail":"DPRK Foreign Trade Bank rep and OTC-trader network charged by DOJ (Apr 2023) with laundering DPRK hack proceeds via HK front companies."},{"name":"Chainalysis (Erin Plante / Crypto Incident Response)","role":"investigator","detail":"Traced funds and enabled the Sept 2022 $30M seizure; documented the 12,000+ address, chain-hopping laundering."},{"name":"Elliptic, TRM Labs, SlowMist, Merkle Science","role":"investigator","detail":"Independent blockchain-forensics firms that reconstructed the fund flow and mixer usage."},{"name":"US Treasury/OFAC, FBI, DOJ (NCET), CISA, Norway Økokrim","role":"enforcement","detail":"Attribution, SDN sanctions, indictments, and international seizures."}],"hops":[{"from":"Ronin Bridge escrow contract 0x1a2a1c938ce3ec39b6d47113c7955baa9dd454f2 (5-of-9 validator multisig)","to":"Ronin Bridge Exploiter 0x098B716B8Aaf21512996dC57EB0615e2383E2f96","amount":"173,600 + 25,500,000","asset":"ETH + USDC","chain":"Ethereum","txhash":"0xc28fad5e8d5e0ce6a2eaf67b6687be5d58113e16be590824d6cfa1a94467d0b7","txurl":"https://etherscan.io/tx/0xc28fad5e8d5e0ce6a2eaf67b6687be5d58113e16be590824d6cfa1a94467d0b7","note":"Two forged withdrawals via withdrawERC20For using 4 compromised Sky Mavis keys + 1 Axie DAO signature obtained through a still-whitelisted gas-free RPC node. Exploiter wallet pre-funded ~1.0569 ETH for gas.","date":"2022-03-23"},{"from":"Exploiter 0x098B…","to":"25.5M USDC swapped to ~8,562 ETH via 1inch/Uniswap","amount":"25,500,000","asset":"USDC→ETH","chain":"Ethereum","txhash":"","txurl":"https://slowmist.medium.com/report-on-the-ronin-network-exploit-and-aml-analysis-of-stolen-funds-692b2a589a96","note":"Stablecoins converted to native ETH to escape Circle''s USDC freeze (ETH cannot be frozen at issuer level). SlowMist: 25.5M USDC → 8,562.6801 ETH.","date":"2022-03-29"},{"from":"Exploiter 0x098B… + connected wallets","to":"Centralized exchanges (Huobi, FTX, Crypto.com-linked)","amount":"~21,000,000 (USD) / ~440 BTC","asset":"ETH / BTC","chain":"Ethereum / Bitcoin","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.elliptic.co/blog/540-million-stolen-from-the-ronin-defi-bridge","note":"Early off-ramp attempts before exchanges announced cooperation: Merkle Science tracked ~3,750 ETH + ~1,220 ETH to exchanges; SlowMist tracked 439.78 BTC withdrawn via Huobi/FTX. Binance later froze a tranche.","date":"2022-03-28"},{"from":"Exploiter cluster","to":"Tornado Cash mixer","amount":"~175,100","asset":"ETH","chain":"Ethereum","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.trmlabs.com/resources/blog/north-koreas-lazarus-group-moves-funds-through-tornado-cash","note":"Continuous ~6,000-ETH batch deposits into Tornado Cash; SlowMist estimates ~175,100 ETH sent to the mixer; OFAC cites >$455M of Ronin funds cycled through it.","date":"2022-04-04"},{"from":"Tornado Cash withdrawals","to":"ETH→renBTC→Bitcoin, then ChipMixer","amount":"~3,460","asset":"ETH→BTC","chain":"Ethereum→Bitcoin","txhash":"","txurl":"https://slowmist.medium.com/report-on-the-ronin-network-exploit-and-aml-analysis-of-stolen-funds-692b2a589a96","note":"Post-mix ETH swapped to renBTC via 1inch/Uniswap, bridged to Bitcoin, then ~3,460 BTC routed through ChipMixer; ~2,871 BTC withdrawn out the far side.","date":"2022-05"},{"from":"Additional Lazarus wallets","to":"OFAC SDN designation (exploiter + 3 more addresses)","amount":"~50,000","asset":"ETH","chain":"Ethereum","txhash":"","txurl":"https://home.treasury.gov/policy-issues/financial-sanctions/recent-actions/20220414","note":"14 Apr 2022 OFAC sanctions 0x098B…; 22 Apr 2022 adds 3 addresses that had held ~50k stolen ETH.","date":"2022-04-22"},{"from":"Post-sanctions laundering","to":"Chain-hopping across 12,000+ addresses (ETH→BNB→USDD→BitTorrent chain, etc.)","amount":"remaining balance","asset":"multi-asset","chain":"cross-chain","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/axie-infinity-ronin-bridge-dprk-hack-seizure/","note":"After Tornado Cash was sanctioned (Aug 2022), Lazarus pivoted to DeFi chain-hopping/bridging across 12,000+ addresses to obscure source of funds.","date":"2022-08"},{"from":"Traced cash-out zones","to":"Law-enforcement seizure (Chainalysis-assisted) + Norway Økokrim seizure","amount":"~40,000,000 (USD)","asset":"multi-asset","chain":"cross-chain","txhash":"","txurl":"https://cointelegraph.com/news/law-enforcement-recovers-30-million-from-ronin-bridge-hack-with-the-help-of-chainalysis","note":"Sept 2022: >$30M seized (~10%); Feb 2023: Norway confiscates ~$5.8M — combined recoveries ~$40M.","date":"2022-09-08"}],"aftermath":"Recoveries: on 8 Sept 2022 Chainalysis and US law enforcement announced the seizure of >$30M — the first-ever recovery of crypto stolen by a North Korean group (~10% of the haul), and in Feb 2023 Norway''s Økokrim confiscated a further ~$5.8M, bringing combined recoveries to ~$40M. Sanctions/enforcement: OFAC sanctioned the exploiter wallet on 14 Apr 2022 (first designation of a specific hack address), added 3 more addresses on 22 Apr, and on 8 Aug 2022 sanctioned Tornado Cash itself — the first sanctioning of an on-chain decentralized protocol (later reversed by the Fifth Circuit in 2024 and delisted in 2025). No DPRK operatives have been arrested (beyond US jurisdiction); enforcement instead targeted destination infrastructure and the laundering network — the DOJ''s Apr 2023 charges against Foreign Trade Bank rep Sim Hyon Sop and OTC traders for laundering DPRK hack proceeds. Sky Mavis: raised ~$150M (led by Binance) to reimburse users, reopened the bridge in late June 2022 with a redesigned architecture, immediately increased validators from 9 to 11 (target 21, then 100+), and added a circuit-breaker with daily withdrawal limits and mandatory human review for large withdrawals.","industry_impact":"Ronin became the canonical case that cross-chain bridges concentrate catastrophic risk and that operational security (key custody, spear-phishing resistance, permission hygiene, outflow monitoring) — not contract audits — is the real bridge attack surface. It drove industry-wide adoption of circuit breakers / rate limits / withdrawal delays on bridges, larger and more decentralized validator sets, hardware-isolated signing and work-only devices, and continuous large-outflow anomaly monitoring. On the regulatory side it triggered the first-ever wallet-specific OFAC designation and, months later, the sanctioning of Tornado Cash — reshaping how mixers are treated and forcing Lazarus to abandon Tornado Cash for cross-chain ''chain-hopping'' across thousands of addresses, which in turn pushed forensics firms toward cross-chain tracing tooling. The public-private Chainalysis/DOJ/Økokrim recovery established the template for seizing state-sponsored crypto theft proceeds and demonstrated that blockchain transparency enables partial clawback even against DPRK tradecraft.","confidence":"high — the mechanism (5-of-9 validator compromise via spear-phish + un-revoked Axie DAO allowlist), the drain tx, the exploiter address, the OFAC/Treasury actions, and the ~$40M recovery are all confirmed by primary sources (Sky Mavis post-mortem, OFAC, DOJ, Chainalysis); specific mixer volumes and BTC/ChipMixer routing figures are forensics-firm estimates (SlowMist/Elliptic/TRM) and are best treated as well-supported approximations rather than exact ledger truth.","legal":"US Treasury/OFAC designated exploiter address 0x098B… on 14 Apr 2022 (first hack wallet ever sanctioned), added 3 more on 22 Apr, and sanctioned Tornado Cash on 8 Aug 2022 (jy0916) citing the Ronin laundering; that mixer designation was struck down by the Fifth Circuit in Nov 2024 and delisted in Mar 2025. FBI/CISA attributed the theft to Lazarus/APT38 (''TraderTraitor'', advisory AA22-108A). DOJ''s National Cryptocurrency Enforcement Team charged Sim Hyon Sop and OTC-trader co-conspirators in Apr 2023 for laundering DPRK hack proceeds. No arrests of the DPRK perpetrators — enforcement targets destination infrastructure, exchange freezes, and the laundering network.","analysis":"Ronin is the canonical proof that decentralization relocates rather than removes trust: the bridge''s cryptography was sound, but validator-key custody and a stale whitelist config were the true attack surface, breached entirely through a human (fake-job spear-phish) vector. The launderers first tried CEX off-ramps, then retreated to Tornado Cash the moment exchanges announced cooperation — a pivot pattern repeated across Lazarus cases — and after the mixer was sanctioned they pivoted again to cross-chain chain-hopping across 12,000+ addresses. The sheer volume (>$455M) overwhelmed Tornado Cash''s anonymity set, ironically making the flows more clusterable and directly triggering the mixer''s sanctioning. The six-day detection gap — a bridge holding hundreds of millions with no large-outflow alerting — is the single most repeated operational lesson of the incident.","parallels":"Ronin and Harmony Horizon (2022) are near-twins: both are cross-chain bridges felled by validator/multisig key compromise (not contract bugs), both used the fake-recruiter ''TraderTraitor'' social-engineering lure, and both laundered overwhelmingly through Tornado Cash in ~6,000-ETH batches — a shared Lazarus fingerprint; both are cited together in OFAC''s Tornado Cash designation. The Bybit hack (2025) is the evolutionary next step, swapping Tornado Cash for THORChain/eXch after sanctions and attacking the Safe{Wallet} signing UI instead of validator keys. Contrast with non-state bridge hacks like Poly Network (2021, funds returned) and Wormhole (2022, Jump Crypto reimbursed): where a lone or reimbursed actor exists funds are often recovered, whereas Lazarus''s DPRK backing makes its bridge proceeds effectively unrecoverable beyond the ~10% seized.","sources":["https://roninchain.com/blog/posts/back-to-building-ronin-security-breach-6513cc78a5edc1001b03c364","https://thehackernews.com/2022/07/hackers-used-fake-job-offer-to-hack-and.html","https://etherscan.io/tx/0xc28fad5e8d5e0ce6a2eaf67b6687be5d58113e16be590824d6cfa1a94467d0b7","https://www.elliptic.co/blog/540-million-stolen-from-the-ronin-defi-bridge","https://slowmist.medium.com/report-on-the-ronin-network-exploit-and-aml-analysis-of-stolen-funds-692b2a589a96","https://www.merklescience.com/blog/hack-track-analysis-of-ronin-network-exploit","https://www.trmlabs.com/resources/blog/north-koreas-lazarus-group-moves-funds-through-tornado-cash","https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/axie-infinity-ronin-bridge-dprk-hack-seizure/","https://home.treasury.gov/policy-issues/financial-sanctions/recent-actions/20220414","https://home.treasury.gov/news/press-releases/jy0916","https://www.cisa.gov/news-events/cybersecurity-advisories/aa22-108a","https://www.justice.gov/usao-dc/pr/north-korean-foreign-trade-bank-rep-charged-role-two-crypto-laundering-conspiracies","https://cointelegraph.com/news/law-enforcement-recovers-30-million-from-ronin-bridge-hack-with-the-help-of-chainalysis"]}','["https://roninchain.com/blog/posts/back-to-building-ronin-security-breach-6513cc78a5edc1001b03c364","https://thehackernews.com/2022/07/hackers-used-fake-job-offer-to-hack-and.html","https://etherscan.io/tx/0xc28fad5e8d5e0ce6a2eaf67b6687be5d58113e16be590824d6cfa1a94467d0b7","https://www.elliptic.co/blog/540-million-stolen-from-the-ronin-defi-bridge","https://slowmist.medium.com/report-on-the-ronin-network-exploit-and-aml-analysis-of-stolen-funds-692b2a589a96","https://www.merklescience.com/blog/hack-track-analysis-of-ronin-network-exploit","https://www.trmlabs.com/resources/blog/north-koreas-lazarus-group-moves-funds-through-tornado-cash","https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/axie-infinity-ronin-bridge-dprk-hack-seizure/","https://home.treasury.gov/policy-issues/financial-sanctions/recent-actions/20220414","https://home.treasury.gov/news/press-releases/jy0916","https://www.cisa.gov/news-events/cybersecurity-advisories/aa22-108a","https://www.justice.gov/usao-dc/pr/north-korean-foreign-trade-bank-rep-charged-role-two-crypto-laundering-conspiracies","https://cointelegraph.com/news/law-enforcement-recovers-30-million-from-ronin-bridge-hack-with-the-help-of-chainalysis"]','2026-07-08 20:34:16',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "scam_traces" ("slug","name","category","amount_usd","profile","sources","updated_at","net_usd","recovered_usd","victims","start_date","collapse_date","status","chains","confidence","source_checked_at") VALUES ('ftx-2022','FTX Mystery Drain (2022)','fraud',477000000,'{"summary":"Hours after FTX filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy on 11 November 2022, ~$663M flowed out of FTX/FTX.US wallets, of which Elliptic assessed ~$477M as an unauthorized theft (the remainder moved to custody). The simultaneous drain of two supposedly independent entities fueled an ''inside job'' theory that SBF himself floated. That theory was overturned in early 2024: a DOJ indictment (unsealed Jan 2024) revealed the drain was a SIM-swap attack by the ''Powell SIM Swapping Crew'' — ringleader Robert Powell plus Emily Hernandez and Carter Rohn — who, on the very day of the bankruptcy filing, SIM-swapped an FTX employee''s AT&T account, intercepted the SMS one-time codes, and drained the wallets. The thieves then converted stablecoins to unfreezable ETH via DEXes, bridged ETH to Bitcoin through RenBridge (ironically owned by FTX-sister Alameda) and later THORSwap, and layered the BTC through ChipMixer and Sinbad. A dormant ~72,500 ETH tranche was reactivated on 30 Sept 2023, days before SBF''s trial.","actor":"''Powell SIM Swapping Crew'' — Robert Powell, Emily Hernandez, Carter Rohn (indicted 2024); laundering path later touched Sinbad, a Blender rebrand tied to Lazarus. Not a DPRK operation.","hops":[{"from":"FTX / FTX.US hot wallets","to":"Thief consolidation wallet 0x59ABf3837Fa962d6853b4Cc0a19513AA031fd32b","amount":"~477,000,000","asset":"multi (ETH/stables)","chain":"multi","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.elliptic.co/blog/the-477-million-ftx-hack-following-the-blockchain-trail","note":"Simultaneous drain of FTX global and FTX.US after a SIM-swap of an FTX employee gave the crew the SMS one-time codes","date":"2022-11-12"},{"from":"Thief wallet","to":"DEX swaps to ETH","amount":"~280,000,000","asset":"stables→ETH","chain":"Ethereum","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.cnbc.com/2022/11/21/ftx-theft-hackers-start-to-launder-477-million-of-stolen-crypto.html","note":"Stolen stablecoins consolidated into ETH (unfreezable) via decentralized exchanges; ~$94M lost to slippage/fees during rushed laundering","date":"2022-11-20"},{"from":"Thief wallet","to":"RenBridge (ETH→renBTC→BTC)","amount":"~74,000,000","asset":"ETH→renBTC","chain":"Ethereum→Bitcoin","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.elliptic.co/blog/analysis/477-million-in-unauthorized-transfers-from-ftx","note":"Ether converted to renBTC and bridged to Bitcoin via RenBridge — a service owned by FTX sister firm Alameda","date":"2022-11-20"},{"from":"Bitcoin proceeds","to":"ChipMixer","amount":"2,849","asset":"BTC","chain":"Bitcoin","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.elliptic.co/blog/the-477-million-ftx-hack-following-the-blockchain-trail","note":"Of ~4,536 BTC converted, ~2,849 BTC pushed through ChipMixer (seized by law enforcement April 2023)","date":"2022-11-25"},{"from":"Dormant ~72,500 ETH tranche","to":"THORSwap (ETH→BTC)","amount":"~120,000,000","asset":"ETH→BTC","chain":"Ethereum→Bitcoin","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.elliptic.co/blog/the-477-million-ftx-hack-following-the-blockchain-trail","note":"~72,500 ETH sat dormant until 30 Sep 2023 — days before Bankman-Fried''s trial — then bridged via THORSwap after RenBridge shut down","date":"2023-09-30"},{"from":"Bitcoin proceeds","to":"Sinbad mixer","amount":"~40,000,000","asset":"BTC","chain":"Bitcoin","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.elliptic.co/blog/the-477-million-ftx-hack-following-the-blockchain-trail","note":"After the ChipMixer seizure, the thieves switched to Sinbad — a rebrand of OFAC-sanctioned Blender used by Lazarus","date":"2023-10-01"}],"legal":"A US DOJ indictment (District of Columbia), unsealed January 2024 after arrests, charged Robert Powell, Emily Hernandez and Carter Rohn of the ''Powell SIM Swapping Crew'' with conspiracy, wire fraud and aggravated identity theft for the >$400M drain (FTX = ''Victim Company-1''), plus SIM-swaps of ~50 victims between Mar 2021 and Apr 2023. Hernandez entered a guilty plea; the indictment explicitly rebutted SBF''s ''inside job'' speculation. Laundering touched OFAC-sanctioned infrastructure lineage (Sinbad/Blender); ChipMixer was dismantled in an April 2023 international operation accused of laundering ~$3B. Recovery was complicated by FTX''s concurrent bankruptcy estate and Bahamian regulator seizures, which caused persistent early misattribution.","analysis":"A rare case where laundering choices themselves became forensic evidence: routing through Alameda-owned RenBridge and the funds reactivating exactly as SBF''s trial began deepened suspicion, yet the actual perpetrators were an unrelated US-based SIM-swap crew, not insiders or a state actor. The chain-of-custody was ultimately cracked by a combination of on-chain tracing (Elliptic) and traditional telecom/identity-fraud investigation (the SIM-swap trail through AT&T and a Texas mobile store). It is also a masterclass in on-chain spoofing FUD — ZachXBT debunked fake meme-coin ''hacker'' activity manufactured via spoofed ERC-20 transfer logs. Lesson: SMS-based 2FA is a catastrophic single point of failure, and bridge/mixer provenance can out an actor even when the initial theft leaves no on-chain attribution.","parallels":"Unlike the Lazarus bridge hacks (Ronin, Harmony, Bybit), FTX was a SIM-swap by a domestic criminal crew, placing it alongside other SIM-swap heists like the 2022-2023 wave that also hit individual crypto holders — the shared root cause is SMS/telecom 2FA weakness, not smart-contract or validator flaws. Yet the laundering toolkit overlapped directly with Lazarus''s: RenBridge (also used in the Harmony laundering), ChipMixer, and Sinbad/Blender — showing a common post-theft ''plumbing'' shared across unrelated threat actors. The ''mystery drain amid a collapse'' optics echo Mt. Gox, where an exchange failure and missing coins similarly blurred the line between hack, insider theft and mismanagement before forensics untangled it.","sources":["https://www.elliptic.co/blog/the-477-million-ftx-hack-following-the-blockchain-trail","https://www.elliptic.co/blog/analysis/477-million-in-unauthorized-transfers-from-ftx","https://www.cnbc.com/2022/11/21/ftx-theft-hackers-start-to-launder-477-million-of-stolen-crypto.html","https://krebsonsecurity.com/2024/02/arrests-in-400m-sim-swap-tied-to-heist-at-ftx/","https://www.nbcnews.com/tech/crypto/three-people-indicted-400-million-ftx-hack-conspiracy-rcna136976","https://cointelegraph.com/news/crypto-sleuth-debunks-3-biggest-misconceptions-about-the-ftx-hack"]}','["https://www.elliptic.co/blog/the-477-million-ftx-hack-following-the-blockchain-trail","https://www.elliptic.co/blog/analysis/477-million-in-unauthorized-transfers-from-ftx","https://www.cnbc.com/2022/11/21/ftx-theft-hackers-start-to-launder-477-million-of-stolen-crypto.html","https://krebsonsecurity.com/2024/02/arrests-in-400m-sim-swap-tied-to-heist-at-ftx/","https://www.nbcnews.com/tech/crypto/three-people-indicted-400-million-ftx-hack-conspiracy-rcna136976","https://cointelegraph.com/news/crypto-sleuth-debunks-3-biggest-misconceptions-about-the-ftx-hack"]','2026-07-08 19:42:45',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "scam_traces" ("slug","name","category","amount_usd","profile","sources","updated_at","net_usd","recovered_usd","victims","start_date","collapse_date","status","chains","confidence","source_checked_at") VALUES ('euler-2023','Euler Finance Hack (2023)','exploit',197000000,'{"summary":"On 13 March 2023 an attacker drained ~$197M from Euler Finance by exploiting a missing health check in the donateToReserves function — code added to patch an earlier ''first depositor'' bug. The flaw let a borrower donate their own collateral into an unhealthy state while the function burned eTokens but not the matching dTokens, creating fake debt/phantom low deposits. Using a ~$30M DAI flash loan from Aave, the attacker levered ~10x, pushed their position underwater, then self-liquidated to claim a liquidation bonus larger than the donation loss, siphoning DAI, wETH/stETH, wBTC and USDC. An MEV bot accidentally front-ran the first exploit transaction, complicating tracing. Uniquely, after Euler deployed a firm public-pressure campaign (neutral messaging, a $1M bounty on the attacker''s identity, and a media blackout to sustain the attacker''s anxiety), the perpetrator — self-identifying as ''Jacob'' — apologized (''I fucked up... Forgive me'') and returned essentially all recoverable funds; because ETH appreciated during negotiations, ~$240M gross was returned by 3 April 2023. A 100-ETH transfer to a Lazarus/Ronin-linked address remains an unexplained wrinkle.","actor":"Pseudonymous ''Jacob'' — returned funds, never publicly identified. A 100-ETH transfer touched a Lazarus-linked Ronin address (Chainalysis flagged possible misdirection by a separate group; Lazarus separately tried to counter-exploit ''Jacob'')","hops":[{"from":"Aave flash-loan pool","to":"Attacker contract (funded by 0xb66cd966670d962C227B3EABA30a872DbFb995db)","amount":"30,000,000","asset":"DAI","chain":"Ethereum","txhash":"0xc310a0affe2169d1f6feec1c63dbc7f7c62a887fa48795d327d4d2da2d6b111d","txurl":"https://etherscan.io/tx/0xc310a0affe2169d1f6feec1c63dbc7f7c62a887fa48795d327d4d2da2d6b111d","note":"~$30M DAI flash loan; ~$20M deposited for eDAI then levered ~10x to seed the self-liquidation exploit against Euler''s eToken/dToken accounting flaw","date":"2023-03-13"},{"from":"Tornado Cash","to":"Attacker wallet 0xb66cd9… (gas seed)","amount":"1","asset":"ETH","chain":"Ethereum","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/euler-finance-flash-loan-attack/","note":"Initial gas / contract-creation funding came out of OFAC-sanctioned Tornado Cash to mask origin","date":"2023-03-13"},{"from":"Euler pools","to":"Attacker wallet 0xb66cd9…","amount":"~197,000,000","asset":"DAI/wETH/stETH/wBTC/USDC","chain":"Ethereum","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/euler-finance-flash-loan-attack/","note":"Self-liquidation at an artificial discount siphoned the contract balance across multiple assets; an MEV bot front-ran the first tx","date":"2023-03-13"},{"from":"Attacker wallet 0xb66cd9…","to":"Tornado Cash","amount":"~7,000","asset":"ETH","chain":"Ethereum","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/euler-finance-flash-loan-attack/","note":"A portion routed into Tornado Cash before negotiations began","date":"2023-03-16"},{"from":"Attacker wallet 0xb66cd9…","to":"Ronin/Lazarus-linked address","amount":"100","asset":"ETH","chain":"Ethereum","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/euler-finance-flash-loan-attack/","note":"On 17 Mar, 100 ETH moved to an address that previously received Ronin-hack funds — Chainalysis flagged likely misdirection; Lazarus separately attempted to counter-exploit ''Jacob'' via a malicious decryptor","date":"2023-03-17"},{"from":"''Jacob'' return address","to":"Euler Finance treasury/deployer","amount":"51,000","asset":"ETH","chain":"Ethereum","txhash":"0xf69c53b82273764989cdecf75b6daabb0c0bd30b4e659bca080948126c1f992c","txurl":"https://etherscan.io/tx/0xf69c53b82273764989cdecf75b6daabb0c0bd30b4e659bca080948126c1f992c","note":"Largest single return, part of ~54,000 ETH returned by 25 Mar (3,000 ETH on 18 Mar + 51,000 ETH on 25 Mar) after Euler''s bounty + reversal pressure","date":"2023-03-25"},{"from":"''Jacob'' return addresses","to":"Euler Finance treasury","amount":"7,000 ETH + 10,000,000 DAI","asset":"ETH+DAI","chain":"Ethereum","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.coindesk.com/business/2023/04/03/euler-says-all-recoverable-funds-stolen-in-200m-hack-have-been-returned","note":"Final tranches; by 3 April Euler confirmed all recoverable funds returned (~$240M gross as ETH had appreciated)","date":"2023-04-03"}],"legal":"No indictment — the negotiated full return short-circuited prosecution, and Euler dropped its $1M bounty on the attacker''s identity once funds were returned. The exploit interacted with OFAC-sanctioned Tornado Cash (sanctioned Aug 2022) for both gas-seeding and partial layering. The 100-ETH transfer to a Lazarus-linked Ronin address was noted by Chainalysis but never resolved into attribution; the Euler team''s own account describes Lazarus actively attempting to counter-exploit ''Jacob'' during the standoff. No law-enforcement action was needed given the near-total recovery.","analysis":"The canonical ''white-hat by coercion'' outcome: a deliberately cold negotiation posture — neutral tone, a $1M identity bounty to sustain the attacker''s anxiety, a media blackout to starve them of information, and credible reversal/reputational threats — recovered ~100% of funds without law enforcement. It worked because the attacker was a lone actor who had not yet cashed out through a mixer to fiat, so the funds were still on-chain and reversible in effect. The presence of Tornado Cash gas-seeding and the 100-ETH Ronin-linked hop show how easily forensic misdirection can be manufactured. Contrast with Lazarus cases where funds are irrecoverable: the deciding variable is whether the actor intends and is able to launder to fiat before pressure lands.","parallels":"Euler is the mirror image of the Lazarus bridge hacks (Ronin, Harmony, Bybit): same-era, comparable ~$200M scale, but a lone negotiable actor rather than a state launderer — hence near-total recovery instead of near-total loss. Mechanically it belongs with the DeFi flash-loan / accounting-bug exploits (e.g. the self-liquidation and oracle/accounting manipulations seen across 2021-2023 lending protocols) rather than the key-custody bridge failures. Its ''hacker returns the money after public pressure'' arc directly echoes Poly Network (2021), where the $611M attacker (''Mr. White Hat'') also returned nearly all funds — both show that when the thief is identifiable/coercible and hasn''t reached irreversible off-ramps, negotiation beats forensics. The uninvited Lazarus cameo (the 100-ETH hop and the counter-exploit attempt) ties even this recovery back to the DPRK cluster.","sources":["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/euler-finance-flash-loan-attack/","https://www.euler.finance/blog/war-peace-behind-the-scenes-of-eulers-240m-exploit-recovery","https://www.coindesk.com/tech/2023/03/28/hacker-behind-200m-euler-attack-apologizes-returns-millions-in-ether-dai-to-protocol","https://www.coindesk.com/business/2023/04/03/euler-says-all-recoverable-funds-stolen-in-200m-hack-have-been-returned","https://etherscan.io/tx/0xc310a0affe2169d1f6feec1c63dbc7f7c62a887fa48795d327d4d2da2d6b111d","https://etherscan.io/tx/0xf69c53b82273764989cdecf75b6daabb0c0bd30b4e659bca080948126c1f992c"]}','["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/euler-finance-flash-loan-attack/","https://www.euler.finance/blog/war-peace-behind-the-scenes-of-eulers-240m-exploit-recovery","https://www.coindesk.com/tech/2023/03/28/hacker-behind-200m-euler-attack-apologizes-returns-millions-in-ether-dai-to-protocol","https://www.coindesk.com/business/2023/04/03/euler-says-all-recoverable-funds-stolen-in-200m-hack-have-been-returned","https://etherscan.io/tx/0xc310a0affe2169d1f6feec1c63dbc7f7c62a887fa48795d327d4d2da2d6b111d","https://etherscan.io/tx/0xf69c53b82273764989cdecf75b6daabb0c0bd30b4e659bca080948126c1f992c"]','2026-07-08 19:44:04',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "scam_traces" ("slug","name","category","amount_usd","profile","sources","updated_at","net_usd","recovered_usd","victims","start_date","collapse_date","status","chains","confidence","source_checked_at") VALUES ('harmony-2022','Harmony Horizon Bridge Hack (2022)','bridge hack',100000000,'{"summary":"On 23–24 June 2022, the DPRK''s Lazarus Group (APT38) drained ~$100M (Elliptic: ~$99.6M–$99.7M) from Harmony''s Horizon Ethereum<->BSC bridge by compromising the private keys behind its multisig, not by exploiting a smart-contract bug. Horizon''s fatal flaw was a 2-of-5 signing threshold: the keys were stored doubly-encrypted (passphrase + KMS) on hot signing servers, but the attackers — who forensic logs show began probing the infrastructure around 2 June 2022 — decrypted enough keys to sign fraudulent withdrawals of 14 different assets (ETH, WBTC, USDC, USDT, DAI, BUSD, BNB, AAVE, SUSHI, FRAX, etc.) across ~14 transactions on Ethereum and Binance Smart Chain, affecting roughly 65,000 wallets. Stolen tokens were swapped to ETH via DEXs, consolidated to ~85,700 ETH, then layered through Tornado Cash''s 100-ETH pool in ~857 programmatic transactions (27 June–2 July 2022) with withdrawals routed via relayers to sets of ~10 fresh addresses — a durable Lazarus fingerprint. Tornado Cash was OFAC-sanctioned on 8 Aug 2022 mid-operation, so the funds sat dormant ~7 months; on 13 Jan 2023 Lazarus pushed >$60M through the Railgun privacy protocol (Elliptic found ~70% of all Railgun volume in that window was Harmony money, defeating the anonymity set), swapped toward BTC, and attempted CEX cash-out where Binance and Huobi froze portions. The FBI, with CISA and Treasury, formally attributed the theft to Lazarus/APT38 on 23 Jan 2023 and tied proceeds to DPRK''s WMD/ballistic-missile programs.","actor":"Lazarus Group / APT38 (DPRK state-sponsored)","technical":"The attack was a key-custody compromise, not a contract exploit. Horizon''s Ethereum-side bridge was governed by a Gnosis/ConsenSys-derived MultiSigWallet with an unusually weak 2-of-5 threshold, meaning any two of five signer keys could authorize arbitrary withdrawals — a risk publicly flagged on Twitter in April 2022. Harmony encrypted the signer keys twice (passphrase plus a key-management service) and split them so no single machine held multiple plaintext keys, but the keys were still loaded in plaintext on hot signing servers to sign legitimate transactions. Lazarus gained a foothold via the ''TraderTraitor'' campaign (CISA advisory AA22-108A): spear-phishing crypto-firm employees with fake, malware-laced job/recruitment applications, which likely gave backdoor access to bridge infrastructure; a week before the hack a subgraph-service software vulnerability had also exposed internal server addresses in Harmony''s private cloud. Server logs timestamped from ~2 June 2022 show the intruder studying the bridge and decrypting keys. On 23–24 June the attacker used the compromised keys to call the multisig''s confirmation/execution flow (the compromised signer submitted and a second key confirmed transactions) and executed ~14 withdrawals draining 14 assets across Ethereum and BSC into attacker address 0x0d04...eD00. The root cause chain is therefore: over-permissive 2-of-5 threshold + plaintext keys on internet-facing signers + social-engineering initial access.","timeline":[{"date":"2022-04","event":"A Twitter user publicly warns Horizon''s low multisig threshold could enable a nine-figure hack if two signer keys are compromised."},{"date":"2022-04-18","event":"FBI/CISA/Treasury publish joint advisory AA22-108A describing the DPRK ''TraderTraitor'' social-engineering/malware campaign against crypto firms."},{"date":"2022-06-02","event":"Server logs later show the attacker began probing Horizon bridge infrastructure and decrypting signer keys."},{"date":"2022-06-23","event":"Harmony team notified of the malicious attack; ~$100M drained from the Horizon Ethereum/BSC bridge across ~14 transactions."},{"date":"2022-06-24","event":"Harmony publicly discloses the hack, halts the Horizon bridge, notifies exchanges; Elliptic estimates ~$99.7M stolen and within days attributes it to Lazarus/APT38."},{"date":"2022-06-26","event":"Analysts (incl. Polygon CISO Mudit Gupta) identify a compromised 2-of-5 multisig / plaintext hot-key servers as the cause."},{"date":"2022-06-27","event":"Stolen tokens swapped to ETH via DEXs and consolidated; ~85,851 ETH split across 14 addresses to begin mixing."},{"date":"2022-06-27 to 2022-07-02","event":"~85,700 ETH laundered through Tornado Cash''s 100-ETH pool in ~857 automated transactions; Elliptic/Merkle Science demix ~143–148 withdrawal addresses."},{"date":"2022-07-27","event":"Harmony proposes a hard fork minting up to 4.97B new ONE tokens to reimburse victims (or 2.48B for ~50%); community backlash over inflation."},{"date":"2022-08-08","event":"US Treasury OFAC sanctions Tornado Cash, citing Lazarus laundering (incl. Ronin and Harmony) — occurs mid-laundering."},{"date":"2022-09-29","event":"Harmony withdraws the minting plan and publishes a revised ''0% minting'', treasury-funded recovery approach."},{"date":"2023-01-13","event":"Lazarus moves >$60M of the stolen ETH through the Railgun privacy protocol; ~70% of Railgun volume that window is Harmony funds."},{"date":"2023-01-14 to 2023-01-16","event":"Funds swapped toward BTC and deposited at exchanges; Binance and Huobi identify, block and seize portions (CZ: ~124 BTC / ~$2.84M recovered)."},{"date":"2023-01-23","event":"FBI formally confirms Lazarus/APT38 responsibility, publishes DPRK-controlled ETH and BTC wallet addresses, links proceeds to DPRK WMD/missile programs."}],"entities":[{"name":"Lazarus Group / APT38","role":"attacker","note":"DPRK state-sponsored threat actor; executed intrusion and laundering."},{"name":"Harmony Protocol / Horizon Bridge","role":"victim","note":"Operator of the exploited 2-of-5 multisig Ethereum<->BSC bridge; ~65,000 wallets across 14 assets affected."},{"name":"Exploiter primary wallet (H1)","role":"attacker","address":"0x0d043128146654C7683Fbf30ac98D7B2285DeD00","note":"Initial consolidation address; received stolen assets in ~9 transactions."},{"name":"Conversion wallets H2 / H3","role":"launderer","address":"0x9E91ae672E7f7330Fc6B9bAb9C259BD94Cd08715 / 0x58F4BACcb411ACef70A5f6DD174Af7854fc48Fa9","note":"Received ERC-20s from H1, swapped to ETH via DEXs, returned clean ETH to H1."},{"name":"Splitter wallets H4–H11","role":"launderer","address":"0x1Ec6F83b55C3F4CeFc630442716872BA15f16430, 0x4507AC1bdF4Ae5E61ffceC3A9AEDA312E2505970, 0x432A9Cb4353bed67EC5351734d4a44C0826847Ae, 0x8a0858888bEEb5D1435Ecd3657831699f169c3f4, 0x89f89D61644c6e606efb25A01210159f102FbD8b, 0x40eFc580e5cb5701797a762990D9E690108DADfD, 0x20dBCcD46eEF96A1b78383Cf0D26bB575EC00201","note":"Fan-out addresses (FBI-listed) that split ~85,851 ETH into 14 wallets feeding Tornado Cash."},{"name":"Tornado Cash (100-ETH pool)","role":"facilitator","note":"Ethereum mixer used to layer ~85,700 ETH; OFAC-sanctioned 8 Aug 2022. Elliptic: >$96M of Harmony funds through it."},{"name":"Railgun","role":"facilitator","note":"Privacy protocol used 13 Jan 2023 to launder >$60M; ~70% of its volume that window was Harmony funds, defeating anonymity."},{"name":"Binance","role":"enforcement","note":"Identified, blocked and seized funds; CZ reported ~124 BTC (~$2.84M) recovered after a further transfer attempt to Huobi was thwarted."},{"name":"Huobi","role":"enforcement","note":"Cooperating exchange that froze/blocked a portion of the Railgun-routed cash-out."},{"name":"FBI (Los Angeles & Charlotte), CISA, US Treasury","role":"enforcement","note":"Attributed to Lazarus on 23 Jan 2023 with DOJ National Cryptocurrency Enforcement Team and US Attorneys (C.D. Cal., D.D.C.); published wallet list."},{"name":"Elliptic / Merkle Science / TRM Labs","role":"investigator","note":"Blockchain forensics firms that traced funds, demixed Tornado Cash withdrawals, and attributed to Lazarus."}],"hops":[{"from":"Horizon Bridge MultiSigWallet (2-of-5)","to":"Exploiter wallet H1 0x0d043128146654C7683Fbf30ac98D7B2285DeD00","amount":"~99,600,000","asset":"14 assets (ETH/WBTC/USDC/USDT/DAI/BUSD/BNB/AAVE/SUSHI/FRAX etc)","chain":"Ethereum + BSC","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.merklescience.com/blog/hack-track-analysis-of-harmonys-horizon-bridge-exploit","note":"~9 transactions from bridge to H1; keys obtained via TraderTraitor social engineering, only 2 of 5 needed. ~$1.79M held on the BSC side.","date":"2022-06-24"},{"from":"H1","to":"Conversion wallets H2 0x9E91ae672E7f7330Fc6B9bAb9C259BD94Cd08715 and H3 0x58F4BACcb411ACef70A5f6DD174Af7854fc48Fa9","amount":"ERC-20 basket","asset":"tokens","chain":"Ethereum","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.merklescience.com/blog/hack-track-analysis-of-harmonys-horizon-bridge-exploit","note":"H2/H3 swapped the ERC-20s to ETH via DEXs, then returned ''clean'' ETH to H1; ~72,770 ETH sent back.","date":"2022-06-26"},{"from":"H1","to":"Splitter H4 0x1Ec6F83b55C3F4CeFc630442716872BA15f16430 -> H5/H6/H7 and H8 0x8a0858888bEEb5D1435Ecd3657831699f169c3f4 -> H9/H10/H11","amount":"~85,851","asset":"ETH","chain":"Ethereum","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.merklescience.com/blog/hack-track-analysis-of-harmonys-horizon-bridge-exploit","note":"Two-branch fan-out: 18k+ ETH per branch split into 14 addresses to prepare mixing. All addresses FBI-listed.","date":"2022-06-27"},{"from":"14 splitter addresses","to":"Tornado Cash 100-ETH pool (T100)","amount":"~85,700","asset":"ETH","chain":"Ethereum","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.trmlabs.com/resources/blog/north-koreas-lazarus-group-moves-funds-through-tornado-cash","note":"~857 programmatic deposits 27 Jun–2 Jul 2022; automated scripting inferred from inter-deposit timing (>$96M total Harmony funds per Elliptic).","date":"2022-06-27"},{"from":"Tornado Cash withdrawals (via relayers)","to":"~143–148 fresh withdrawal addresses (sets of ~10)","amount":"~84,663","asset":"ETH","chain":"Ethereum","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.elliptic.co/blog/analysis/fbi-confirms-north-korea-s-lazarus-group-as-hackers-behind-100-million-harmony-horizon-bridge-theft","note":"Elliptic demix heuristic: each address received only from the 100-ETH pool via relayer, 2–10 hits, went dormant; sets of 10 addresses cumulatively took 60 withdrawals then rotated — a Lazarus fingerprint.","date":"2022-07-02"},{"from":"70 of 143 Tornado withdrawal addresses -> 70 intermediary addresses","to":"Railgun privacy protocol","amount":"~41,792 ETH (>$60M)","asset":"ETH","chain":"Ethereum","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.fbi.gov/news/press-releases/fbi-confirms-lazarus-group-cyber-actors-responsible-for-harmonys-horizon-bridge-currency-theft","note":"11–14 Jan 2023: 75 txns to intermediaries then into Railgun; ~99.9% of Railgun deposits that window / ~70% of all-time Railgun volume were Harmony funds — defeating the mix.","date":"2023-01-13"},{"from":"Railgun output","to":"VASP deposits -> BTC; portions frozen at Binance/Huobi","amount":"~124 BTC recovered (~$2.84M) of >$60M attempted","asset":"BTC","chain":"multi","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.fbi.gov/news/press-releases/fbi-confirms-lazarus-group-cyber-actors-responsible-for-harmonys-horizon-bridge-currency-theft","note":"Swapped to BTC and deposited at 3 exchanges; Binance & Huobi blocked/seized portions; remainder moved to FBI-published BTC addresses (e.g. bc1q2ar35d9ayrv0plzywlaxs8y7s8h5zkvn6fe4mj).","date":"2023-01-14"}],"aftermath":"Recoveries were modest: Binance and Huobi froze/seized portions of the Jan-2023 Railgun cash-out (Changpeng Zhao reported ~124 BTC, ~$2.84M, blocked after a further Huobi-transfer attempt was thwarted); the vast majority of the ~$100M remains with the DPRK. There were no arrests — Lazarus operators are inside North Korea, beyond US jurisdiction — so enforcement took the form of the FBI/CISA/Treasury attribution (23 Jan 2023), OFAC''s 8 Aug 2022 sanctioning of Tornado Cash (which named the Harmony and Ronin laundering), publication of dozens of DPRK-controlled ETH and BTC wallet addresses for VASP blocklisting, and coordinated exchange freezes. Harmony itself first proposed a hard fork to mint up to 4.97B new ONE tokens for ~100% victim reimbursement (or 2.48B for 50%); fierce community backlash over inflation forced a reversal to a treasury-funded ''0% minting'' recovery plan in Sept 2022, and full reimbursement never materialized. Harmony hardened Horizon''s Ethereum side from 2-of-5 to 4-of-5 and improved key isolation and infrastructure security.","industry_impact":"Harmony, arriving three months after Ronin, cemented cross-chain bridges as the highest-value single-point-of-failure in crypto (>$1B stolen from bridges in 2022) and reframed ''bridge security'' as key-custody and validator-threshold security rather than smart-contract security — driving industry moves toward higher multisig thresholds, HSM/MPC key custody, hardware isolation of signers, and away from low-N-of-M schemes. It was a primary evidentiary basis for OFAC''s unprecedented sanctioning of Tornado Cash (a smart contract) in Aug 2022, a watershed in crypto AML policy. Forensically it validated demixing heuristics (relayer-only inflows, 10-address rotating sets, batch timing) that let firms cluster mixed funds and pre-position VASP blocklists, and it documented Lazarus''s real-time adaptation to sanctions — dormancy then migration from Tornado Cash to Railgun — which foreshadowed later pivots (eXch/THORChain in the 2025 Bybit hack). It also reinforced that the ''TraderTraitor'' fake-recruiter lure is the dominant DPRK initial-access vector, prompting crypto firms to harden employee anti-phishing and developer-endpoint controls.","confidence":"high","analysis":"Harmony shows Lazarus adapting to sanctions in real time: when Tornado Cash was sanctioned mid-laundering they parked funds dormant for seven months, then migrated to the next privacy protocol (Railgun) — but because Harmony money dominated Railgun''s tiny anonymity set (~70% of volume), the mixing failed and the trail stayed traceable. The ''~10-address relayer set / batched Tornado deposit'' automation is a durable Lazarus fingerprint that let Elliptic/TRM/Merkle Science cluster the flows despite mixing. Root cause was governance/threshold hygiene: a 2-of-5 multisig meant compromising a minority of keys sufficed, and the keys fell to social engineering (TraderTraitor) plus plaintext hot-key servers rather than any contract flaw. Lesson: bridge security is key-custody security, and mixer sanctions push — rather than stop — state launderers.","parallels":"Harmony is effectively Ronin''s twin, three months apart: both cross-chain bridges broken by multisig/validator key compromise via the same TraderTraitor fake-recruiter lure, both laundered overwhelmingly through Tornado Cash in batched transactions with rotating relayer sets — the shared Lazarus signature linking the cases forensically. Its dormancy-then-Railgun pivot foreshadows the Bybit (2025) migration to THORChain/eXch after further sanctions, showing a continuous Lazarus adaptation curve. Where non-state bridge hacks like Wormhole (2022, Jump reimbursed) or Poly Network (2021, returned) end in recovery, Harmony — like Ronin — ends in designation-and-freeze because the DPRK actor is unreachable.","legal":"The FBI publicly attributed the theft to Lazarus/APT38 on 23 Jan 2023 (with CISA and Treasury, DOJ''s National Cryptocurrency Enforcement Team, and the US Attorneys for C.D. Cal. and D.D.C.), tied it to the ''TraderTraitor'' malware campaign (advisory AA22-108A), published DPRK-controlled ETH and BTC wallet addresses, and explicitly linked proceeds to funding DPRK''s WMD/ballistic-missile programs. The primary laundering tool, Tornado Cash, was OFAC-sanctioned on 8 Aug 2022 — during this laundering operation. Portions of the Railgun-routed funds were frozen with cooperating VASPs (Binance ~124 BTC) in Jan 2023. No arrests: DPRK actors are beyond US jurisdiction, so enforcement relies on attribution, address designation, and exchange-level freezes.","sources":["https://www.fbi.gov/news/press-releases/fbi-confirms-lazarus-group-cyber-actors-responsible-for-harmonys-horizon-bridge-currency-theft","https://www.cisa.gov/news-events/cybersecurity-advisories/aa22-108a","https://home.treasury.gov/news/press-releases/jy0916","https://www.elliptic.co/blog/analysis/fbi-confirms-north-korea-s-lazarus-group-as-hackers-behind-100-million-harmony-horizon-bridge-theft","https://www.merklescience.com/blog/hack-track-analysis-of-harmonys-horizon-bridge-exploit","https://www.trmlabs.com/resources/blog/north-koreas-lazarus-group-moves-funds-through-tornado-cash","https://www.halborn.com/blog/post/explained-the-harmony-horizon-bridge-hack","https://www.coindesk.com/policy/2023/01/23/fbi-north-korean-hackers-behind-100-million-horizon-bridge-theft","https://techcrunch.com/2023/01/24/north-korea-fbi-harmony-horizon-crypto/","https://cointelegraph.com/news/backlash-as-harmony-proposes-minting-4-97b-tokens-to-reimburse-victims","https://blockchaingroup.io/guides/harmonys-horizon-bridge-exploit-a-crypto-money-laundering-case-study/"]}','["https://www.fbi.gov/news/press-releases/fbi-confirms-lazarus-group-cyber-actors-responsible-for-harmonys-horizon-bridge-currency-theft","https://www.cisa.gov/news-events/cybersecurity-advisories/aa22-108a","https://home.treasury.gov/news/press-releases/jy0916","https://www.elliptic.co/blog/analysis/fbi-confirms-north-korea-s-lazarus-group-as-hackers-behind-100-million-harmony-horizon-bridge-theft","https://www.merklescience.com/blog/hack-track-analysis-of-harmonys-horizon-bridge-exploit","https://www.trmlabs.com/resources/blog/north-koreas-lazarus-group-moves-funds-through-tornado-cash","https://www.halborn.com/blog/post/explained-the-harmony-horizon-bridge-hack","https://www.coindesk.com/policy/2023/01/23/fbi-north-korean-hackers-behind-100-million-horizon-bridge-theft","https://techcrunch.com/2023/01/24/north-korea-fbi-harmony-horizon-crypto/","https://cointelegraph.com/news/backlash-as-harmony-proposes-minting-4-97b-tokens-to-reimburse-victims","https://blockchaingroup.io/guides/harmonys-horizon-bridge-exploit-a-crypto-money-laundering-case-study/"]','2026-07-08 20:44:42',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "scam_traces" ("slug","name","category","amount_usd","profile","sources","updated_at","net_usd","recovered_usd","victims","start_date","collapse_date","status","chains","confidence","source_checked_at") VALUES ('multichain-2023','Multichain Exploit (2023)','bridge hack',126000000,'{"summary":"On 6-7 July 2023, ~$126M (some trackers counted up to ~$130M+ across nine chains) was abnormally withdrawn from the cross-chain bridge Multichain (formerly Anyswap), overwhelmingly from its Fantom bridge (~$118-120M in WBTC, wETH, USDC, USDT, DAI and LINK) plus its Moonriver (~$6.8M) and Dogecoin (~$666K, ~85% of deposits) bridges. Multichain marketed itself as trustless MPC (multi-party computation) infrastructure, but its MPC key shards were effectively controlled solely by CEO/founder Zhaojun He (赵君) — who, unbeknownst to the team and users, had been detained by Chinese police in Kunming on 21 May 2023, with his computers, phones, hardware wallets and mnemonic phrases confiscated. With the sole operator detained, the July withdrawals had no legitimate signer; login/IP forensics traced the movements to Kunming. Chainalysis and most analysts assess the event as an ambiguous insider / law-enforcement-seizure / rug event rather than a classic external smart-contract exploit — notably the mover left ~$65M in freezable stablecoins (USDC/USDT) untouched, atypical of a profit-motivated thief. In the aftermath, Zhaojun''s sister moved residual router-pool balances into two wallets she controlled ''for asset preservation,'' before she too was detained (~13 July 2023), freezing further movement. Multichain ceased operations on 14 July 2023; the bridge briefly and mysteriously reopened for ~2 hours on 1 Nov 2023, letting a single wallet net ~$1M in arbitrage before going dormant again.","technical":"Multichain routed cross-chain transfers through ''router'' and pool contracts on each chain whose custody was governed by an MPC (multi-party computation) signing scheme — conceptually a threshold multisig where a private key is split into shards held by multiple SMPC nodes that jointly sign withdrawal transactions without ever reconstructing the full key. The security model assumed those shards were distributed across independent parties; in reality all shards and the node infrastructure were controlled by CEO Zhaojun He, so the ''distributed'' signer set collapsed to a single point of control. There was no contract bug, reentrancy, or oracle manipulation: the withdrawals were validly MPC-signed transactions that drained the locked assets, meaning whoever held the keys (or seized devices) could authorize transfers to arbitrary addresses. On the Fantom bridge the mover pulled 1,023 WBTC (~$30.9M), 7,214 wETH (~$13.6M), ~$57M USDC across two addresses, ~$27.6M USDT, plus DAI/LINK, dispersing them to a handful of freshly funded EOAs. Crucially the assets were NOT swapped or run through a mixer — they sat in destination wallets, and the mover made no attempt to escape stablecoin blacklisting, which let Circle and Tether freeze ~$65M. That behavioral signature (validly-signed drains + no laundering + retention of freezable assets + prior CEO arrest + Kunming IPs) is why the incident reads as a custody/seizure/insider event rather than an adversarial hack, though the truth is obscured by opaque Chinese detentions. The single-operator key custody — rather than any cryptographic weakness in MPC itself — was the true vulnerability.","timeline":[{"date":"2023-05-21","event":"Multichain founder/CEO Zhaojun He detained by Chinese police in Kunming; computers, phones, hardware wallets and mnemonic phrases confiscated. Kept secret from users and much of the team."},{"date":"2023-05-24","event":"Team''s operational access to the MPC node servers is revoked/lost; a planned server upgrade cannot be completed, causing bridge malfunctions and stuck/delayed cross-chain transfers."},{"date":"2023-05-31","event":"Multichain publicly acknowledges ''delayed transactions'' and inability to reach the team member with server access; MULTI token sells off amid outage rumors."},{"date":"2023-06-01","event":"Fantom-based DeFi projects begin fleeing Multichain-bridged tokens; Binance had already swapped out and closed deposits for affected bridged assets (effective ~7 July)."},{"date":"2023-07-06","event":"~$126M abnormally withdrawn via validly MPC-signed transactions: ~$118-120M from the Fantom bridge (WBTC, wETH, USDC, USDT, DAI, LINK), ~$6.8M from Moonriver, ~$666K (~85%) from the Dogecoin bridge. Multichain warns users to stop using the service and revoke approvals."},{"date":"2023-07-07","event":"PeckShield publishes an on-chain breakdown of destination wallets and per-asset amounts. Community and Chainalysis begin debating hack vs. rug/inside job."},{"date":"2023-07-08","event":"Circle blacklists three addresses freezing ~$63M USDC; Tether also freezes USDT — ~$65M total frozen by stablecoin issuers."},{"date":"2023-07-09","event":"Zhaojun''s sister moves remaining router-pool assets to two Ethereum wallets she controls (0x1eed63... and 0x6b6314...), described by the team as ''asset preservation.''"},{"date":"2023-07-13","event":"Chinese police detain the sister (per information from Zhaojun''s family); the status of the ''preserved'' assets becomes uncertain."},{"date":"2023-07-14","event":"Multichain announces it is ceasing operations — unable to access funds, servers, or even take down its own front-end. Confirms CEO and sister arrests; MULTI token drops ~12%."},{"date":"2023-11-01","event":"Bridge mysteriously reopens for ~2 hours after 117+ days of dormancy; wallet 0x4372... arbitrages depegged Fantom-side wrapped assets (WBTC ~80% below market), turning ~1.9M FTM (~$280K) into ~$1.2-1.9M in BTC/ETH/USDT bridged out, netting ~$1M before the bridge goes dark again."},{"date":"2024-07-08","event":"Singapore High Court (Judicial Commissioner Mohamed Faizal) rules Multichain owes the Fantom Foundation ~$2.2M; finds the CEO''s total control over bridge assets breached Multichain''s user agreement. Multichain never defended the suit."}],"actor":"Suspected insider / single-point-of-failure custody — not externally attributed. Multichain CEO/founder Zhaojun He (赵君) held effective sole control of all MPC key shards and the node infrastructure; his 21 May 2023 detention in Kunming left the keys/devices in the hands of Chinese authorities (or persons with access to them). The July withdrawals were validly MPC-signed and traced to Kunming IPs. His sister subsequently moved residual funds to wallets she controlled before her own detention. Whether the drains were executed by the CEO''s proxies, opportunistic insiders, or under law-enforcement seizure is genuinely unresolved; a Singapore court found his ''ultimate privileges and control over the cryptocurrency assets'' contravened the user agreement, reinforcing the single-point-of-failure view. No external threat actor (e.g., Lazarus) has been credibly linked.","entities":[{"name":"Zhaojun He (赵君)","role":"facilitator/insider (alleged)","detail":"Multichain founder & CEO; held sole effective control of MPC key shards and node servers. Detained by Chinese police in Kunming on 21 May 2023; devices, hardware wallets and mnemonics confiscated."},{"name":"Zhaojun He''s sister","role":"launderer/preserver (alleged)","detail":"On ~9 July 2023 moved remaining router-pool assets to two wallets she controlled ''for asset preservation''; detained by Chinese police ~13 July 2023."},{"name":"Multichain (formerly Anyswap) Foundation Ltd","role":"victim/operator","detail":"Cross-chain bridge protocol; ceased operations 14 July 2023. One of two entities Fantom sued in Singapore."},{"name":"Multichain Pte Ltd","role":"facilitator (alleged)","detail":"Entity whose ''sudden incorporation'' shortly before the breach Fantom flagged as a possible vehicle for diverted assets; the Singapore judge declined to rule on the diversion allegation."},{"name":"Fantom Foundation / Michael Kong","role":"victim/investigator","detail":"Fantom''s bridge was the most exposed (~$120M). CEO Michael Kong initially defended Multichain, later grew skeptical (''too trusting''); hired law firm King & Wood Mallesons to investigate and won a ~$2.2M Singapore judgment. Complained ex-employees were ''entirely uncooperative.''"},{"name":"PeckShield","role":"investigator","detail":"Security firm that produced the first on-chain breakdown of destination wallets and per-asset amounts on 7 July 2023."},{"name":"Chainalysis","role":"investigator","detail":"Framed the event as ''possible hack or rug pull,'' highlighting that the mover left freezable USDC/USDT untouched — atypical of a profit-driven external hacker."},{"name":"Circle","role":"enforcement/facilitator","detail":"Blacklisted three addresses, freezing ~$63M USDC tied to the drain."},{"name":"Tether","role":"enforcement/facilitator","detail":"Froze USDT associated with the stolen funds; combined with Circle ~$65M frozen."},{"name":"Binance / CZ","role":"facilitator","detail":"Had already swapped out and closed deposits for Multichain-bridged tokens before the drain; CZ stated Binance users were unaffected."},{"name":"Chinese police (Kunming)","role":"enforcement","detail":"Detained the CEO (21 May 2023) and his sister (~13 July 2023); seized devices/keys. Investigation opaque; no public disclosure of recovery or charges."},{"name":"Wallet 0x9d5765ae1c95c21d4cc3b1d5bba71bad3b012b68","role":"attacker/destination","detail":"Received ~$16-20M in DAI, LINK and USDT from the Fantom bridge drain."},{"name":"Wallet 0x48bead89e696ee93b04913cb0006f35adb844537","role":"attacker/destination","detail":"Received the ~$6.8M drained from the Moonriver bridge (WBTC, USDT, USDC, DAI)."},{"name":"Wallet 0x1eed63efba5f81d95bfe37d82c8e736b974f477b","role":"launderer/destination","detail":"First ''asset preservation'' wallet the sister moved residual funds to (~9 July 2023)."},{"name":"Wallet 0x6b6314f4f07c974600d872182dcde092c480e57b","role":"launderer/destination","detail":"Second ''asset preservation'' wallet controlled by the sister; movement froze after her detention."}],"hops":[{"from":"Multichain Fantom bridge (WBTC pool)","to":"0x622e5 (destination EOA)","amount":"~30,900,000","asset":"1,023 WBTC","chain":"Fantom→Ethereum","txhash":"","txurl":"https://dailyhodl.com/2023/07/08/web3-crypto-project-multichain-hit-with-126000000-exploit-peckshield/","note":"PeckShield: 1,023 WBTC (~$30.9M) moved to 0x622e5 via a validly MPC-signed withdrawal; not swapped or mixed","date":"2023-07-06"},{"from":"Multichain Fantom bridge (wETH pool)","to":"0x418e (destination EOA)","amount":"~13,600,000","asset":"7,214 wETH","chain":"Fantom→Ethereum","txhash":"","txurl":"https://dailyhodl.com/2023/07/08/web3-crypto-project-multichain-hit-with-126000000-exploit-peckshield/","note":"PeckShield: 7,214 wETH (~$13.6M) sent to 0x418e","date":"2023-07-06"},{"from":"Multichain Fantom bridge (USDT pool)","to":"0x027F (destination EOA)","amount":"~27,600,000","asset":"USDT","chain":"Fantom→Ethereum","txhash":"","txurl":"https://dailyhodl.com/2023/07/08/web3-crypto-project-multichain-hit-with-126000000-exploit-peckshield/","note":"PeckShield: ~$27.6M USDT to 0x027F","date":"2023-07-06"},{"from":"Multichain Fantom bridge (USDC pool)","to":"0xefeef (destination EOA)","amount":"~30,000,000","asset":"USDC","chain":"Fantom→Ethereum","txhash":"","txurl":"https://dailyhodl.com/2023/07/08/web3-crypto-project-multichain-hit-with-126000000-exploit-peckshield/","note":"PeckShield: ~$30M USDC to 0xefeef (part of ~$57M USDC drained across two addresses)","date":"2023-07-06"},{"from":"Multichain Fantom bridge (altcoins)","to":"0x9d5765ae1c95c21d4cc3b1d5bba71bad3b012b68","amount":"~16,000,000-20,000,000","asset":"DAI/LINK/USDT","chain":"Fantom→Ethereum","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.coindesk.com/business/2023/07/06/multichain-bridges-experience-unannounced-outflows-of-over-130m-in-crypto","note":"CoinDesk/PeckShield: DAI, LINK and USDT (~$16-20M) sent to 0x9d57...b012b68","date":"2023-07-06"},{"from":"Multichain Moonriver bridge","to":"0x48bead89e696ee93b04913cb0006f35adb844537","amount":"~6,800,000","asset":"WBTC/USDT/USDC/DAI","chain":"Moonriver","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.coindesk.com/business/2023/07/06/multichain-bridges-experience-unannounced-outflows-of-over-130m-in-crypto","note":"CoinDesk: entire ~$6.8M Moonriver drain routed to 0x48BeAD...4537","date":"2023-07-06"},{"from":"Multichain Dogecoin bridge","to":"Unknown destination","amount":"~666,000","asset":"bridged USDC/DOGE","chain":"Dogecoin","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/multichain-exploit-july-2023/","note":"Chainalysis: ~$666K removed — ~85% of total Dogecoin bridge deposits","date":"2023-07-06"},{"from":"Destination wallets (USDC/USDT)","to":"Circle & Tether blacklist (frozen)","amount":"~65,000,000","asset":"USDC/USDT","chain":"Ethereum","txhash":"","txurl":"https://blockonomi.com/circle-blocks-63-million-usdc-tied-to-multichain-attack/","note":"Circle blacklisted 3 addresses freezing ~$63M USDC; Tether froze USDT — ~$65M total immobilized. Mover made no attempt to swap out of freezable assets","date":"2023-07-08"},{"from":"Remaining router-pool balances","to":"0x1eed63efba5f81d95bfe37d82c8e736b974f477b","amount":"part of ~$220M residual","asset":"multi","chain":"Ethereum","txhash":"","txurl":"https://etherscan.io/address/0x1eed63efba5f81d95bfe37d82c8e736b974f477b","note":"Sister moved residual funds ''for asset preservation'' to a self-controlled wallet (~9 July 2023)","date":"2023-07-09"},{"from":"Remaining router-pool balances","to":"0x6b6314f4f07c974600d872182dcde092c480e57b","amount":"part of ~$220M residual","asset":"multi","chain":"Ethereum","txhash":"","txurl":"https://etherscan.io/address/0x6b6314f4f07c974600d872182dcde092c480e57b","note":"Second ''preservation'' wallet; movement froze after the sister''s ~13 July detention","date":"2023-07-09"},{"from":"Binance (FTM)","to":"0x4372 (Nov-restart arbitrageur)","amount":"~280,000","asset":"1.9M FTM","chain":"Binance→Fantom","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.dlnews.com/articles/defi/user-profits-after-multichain-bridge-mysteriously-restarts/","note":"1 Nov 2023: wallet 0x4372 withdrew 1.9M FTM (~$280K), swapped for deeply-discounted WBTC on Spookyswap during the ~2h bridge reopening","date":"2023-11-01"},{"from":"0x4372 via reopened Multichain bridge","to":"Binance (BTC/ETH/USDT)","amount":"~1,200,000-1,900,000","asset":"28.4 WBTC / 357 ETH / 298K USDT","chain":"Fantom→Ethereum→Binance","txhash":"","txurl":"https://cointelegraph.com/news/trader-exploits-multichain-opening-to-turn-280k-to-1-9m-community-suspects-insider-job","note":"Arbitraged Fantom-side depegged wrapped assets (WBTC ~80% below market) to ~$1.2-1.9M; sole beneficiary of the mysterious ~2h reopening — widely suspected insider-coordinated","date":"2023-11-01"}],"legal":"No US enforcement action — this is a China-jurisdiction matter. CEO Zhaojun He (detained Kunming, 21 May 2023) and his sister (detained ~13 July 2023) had hardware wallets, phones and mnemonic seeds confiscated by Chinese police; at least several other employees were reportedly detained (one ex-employee cited five, unverified). The Chinese investigation is opaque — no charges, indictment, or recovery have been publicly disclosed. On 8 July 2024 the Singapore High Court (Judicial Commissioner Mohamed Faizal) ruled Multichain owed the Fantom Foundation ~$2.2M, finding the CEO''s ''ultimate privileges and control over the cryptocurrency assets'' contravened Multichain''s user agreement — reinforcing the single-point-of-failure/inside-job view. Fantom sued two entities (Multichain Foundation Ltd and Multichain Pte Ltd) and flagged the ''sudden incorporation'' of Multichain Pte Ltd just before the breach as a possible diversion vehicle, but the judge expressly declined to rule on that allegation (''I am not making any finding on the merits of these assertions''). Multichain never appeared to defend the suit.","analysis":"The archetypal ''decentralization theater'' collapse: a protocol sold as trustless MPC was in fact a single point of failure because one person (the CEO) held effective control of all key shards and node infrastructure. When that person was removed by a state (arrest), the assets were left exposed and swept via validly-signed transactions — whether by the CEO''s proxies, opportunistic insiders, or law enforcement is genuinely ambiguous, because the on-chain fingerprints (fresh destination EOAs, no swaps, no mixer, retention of freezable stablecoins, then self-custody ''preservation'' wallets, then dormancy) are consistent with rug, insider theft and seizure alike. Unlike Lazarus cases there was no laundering craft — the funds simply moved to controlled wallets and froze when the controllers were jailed and when Circle/Tether blacklisted ~$65M. The mover''s failure to escape stablecoin freezing is the single strongest tell that this was not a profit-optimizing external hacker. The mysterious ~2-hour November 2023 reopening — which enriched exactly one arbitrage wallet — strongly implies residual insider key access. Core lesson: key-management centralization, not cryptography, is the true bridge risk, and geopolitical/jurisdictional custody (China) can freeze a forensic case entirely.","aftermath":"Multichain ceased operations 14 July 2023 and never returned; MULTI token collapsed (~12% on the day, effectively to zero as an operating protocol). Circle blacklisted three addresses (~$63M USDC) and Tether froze USDT, immobilizing ~$65M — the only meaningful ''recovery'' lever, though those funds sat frozen rather than returned to users. No China criminal outcome (charges, sentences, or clawback) has been publicly disclosed; the CEO, his sister, and reportedly several employees remained detained/out of contact. Fantom won a ~$2.2M Singapore judgment (July 2024) but faced an uncooperative, non-appearing defendant, making collection doubtful. Fantom itself pivoted away from the Multichain dependency and rebranded/migrated toward its Sonic chain. Ecosystems that had relied on Multichain-bridged assets (Fantom, Moonriver, Moonbeam, KCC and others) suffered depegs and had to unwind or reissue bridged tokens. The November 2023 reopening netted one wallet ~$1M and deepened suspicion of lingering insider control, but produced no user recovery.","industry_impact":"Multichain became the canonical case that ''MPC/threshold signing is only as decentralized as its operator set'' — catalyzing scrutiny of bridge key custody, node-operator independence, and proof-of-reserves/attestation for locked bridge assets. It reinforced the post-Ronin/Harmony consensus that centralized signer control is the dominant bridge risk, pushing projects toward more independent validators, timelocks, withdrawal limits, and multi-org key ceremonies. It highlighted a distinct, hard-to-mitigate threat class: jurisdictional/key-person risk, where the arrest or coercion of a single controller (or seizure of their devices) can drain or freeze a protocol regardless of code quality — a governance and legal-structuring problem, not a Solidity one. The episode also showcased stablecoin issuer freezing (Circle/Tether) as a de facto emergency control that can immobilize tens of millions within hours, sharpening the ongoing debate over centralized censorship capability in ''DeFi.'' Finally, it demonstrated how opaque foreign detentions can permanently stall attribution and recovery, and it accelerated user/DeFi flight away from single-operator bridges toward canonical/native bridging and battle-tested designs.","confidence":"medium — Well-established: the ~$126M drain, per-chain/per-asset breakdown, destination wallets, the ~$65M Circle/Tether freeze, the CEO''s May 2023 Kunming detention and sole key control, the sister''s ''preservation'' transfers and detention, the 14 July shutdown, the Nov 2023 reopening arbitrage, and the July 2024 Singapore judgment. Alleged/unresolved: the precise identity and intent of the July 6 mover (external hack vs. insider/rug vs. law-enforcement seizure), the diversion-to-Multichain-Pte-Ltd theory, and whether the Nov 2023 restart was insider-coordinated — all remain unproven due to opaque Chinese detentions and a non-appearing defendant.","sources":["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/multichain-exploit-july-2023/","https://www.coindesk.com/business/2023/07/06/multichain-bridges-experience-unannounced-outflows-of-over-130m-in-crypto","https://www.coindesk.com/business/2023/07/14/crypto-bridging-protocol-multichain-ceases-operations","https://dailyhodl.com/2023/07/08/web3-crypto-project-multichain-hit-with-126000000-exploit-peckshield/","https://blockonomi.com/circle-blocks-63-million-usdc-tied-to-multichain-attack/","https://www.dlnews.com/articles/defi/multichain-halts-use-of-crypto-bridge-saying-ceo-arrested/","https://www.dlnews.com/articles/defi/singapore-court-fuels-view-multichain-hack-was-inside-job/","https://www.dlnews.com/articles/defi/singapore-judge-sides-with-fantom-in-multichain-case/","https://www.dlnews.com/articles/defi/user-profits-after-multichain-bridge-mysteriously-restarts/","https://cointelegraph.com/news/trader-exploits-multichain-opening-to-turn-280k-to-1-9m-community-suspects-insider-job","https://decrypt.co/148559","https://www.forbes.com/sites/digital-assets/2023/07/07/multichain-missing-120-million-of-cryptocurrencies-and-its-ceo-pulls-the-plug/"]}','["https://www.chainalysis.com/blog/multichain-exploit-july-2023/","https://www.coindesk.com/business/2023/07/06/multichain-bridges-experience-unannounced-outflows-of-over-130m-in-crypto","https://www.coindesk.com/business/2023/07/14/crypto-bridging-protocol-multichain-ceases-operations","https://dailyhodl.com/2023/07/08/web3-crypto-project-multichain-hit-with-126000000-exploit-peckshield/","https://blockonomi.com/circle-blocks-63-million-usdc-tied-to-multichain-attack/","https://www.dlnews.com/articles/defi/multichain-halts-use-of-crypto-bridge-saying-ceo-arrested/","https://www.dlnews.com/articles/defi/singapore-court-fuels-view-multichain-hack-was-inside-job/","https://www.dlnews.com/articles/defi/singapore-judge-sides-with-fantom-in-multichain-case/","https://www.dlnews.com/articles/defi/user-profits-after-multichain-bridge-mysteriously-restarts/","https://cointelegraph.com/news/trader-exploits-multichain-opening-to-turn-280k-to-1-9m-community-suspects-insider-job","https://decrypt.co/148559","https://www.forbes.com/sites/digital-assets/2023/07/07/multichain-missing-120-million-of-cryptocurrencies-and-its-ceo-pulls-the-plug/"]','2026-07-08 20:46:56',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "scam_traces" ("slug","name","category","amount_usd","profile","sources","updated_at","net_usd","recovered_usd","victims","start_date","collapse_date","status","chains","confidence","source_checked_at") VALUES ('pig-butchering-usdt-2025','Pig-Butchering USDT Ring / Heartland Bank (2023-2025)','pig-butchering',225000000,'{"summary":"A Southeast-Asia-based ''pig butchering'' (sha zhu pan) romance-investment fraud network operating out of Manila-linked scam compounds processed roughly $3B and ensnared 430+ victims worldwide (at least 60 in the US) by building trust over time and steering victims into fake trading portals that showed fabricated gains, then blocked withdrawals. One victim was Shan Hanes, CEO of Heartland Tri-State Bank (Elkhart, Kansas), who embezzled $47.1M of bank funds across 11 wires (May-Jul 2023), collapsing the FDIC-insured institution. The investigation began in late 2023 when Tether proactively froze 39 wallet addresses holding ~$225M in stolen USDT; on 18 June 2025 the US Attorney (District of Columbia) and Secret Service filed a civil forfeiture complaint for ~$225,364,961 in USDT — the largest crypto-confidence-scam seizure in US and Secret Service history. Investigators used Last-In-First-Out (LIFO) tracing to follow victim funds from 93 scam deposit addresses through peel chains and cross-chain swaps (Ethereum, Bitcoin, TRON) into a web of 144 OKX accounts, and Tether recovered the funds via a burn-and-reissue mechanism. A separate Nov 2023 DOJ/Secret Service case seized ~$9M USDT.","actor":"Southeast Asian scam-compound network (Manila / Philippines call-center ties; Vietnamese-KYC OKX account cluster). Victim/embezzler: Shan Hanes, former Heartland Tri-State Bank CEO (24-year sentence)","hops":[{"from":"Victims (incl. Shan Hanes wires)","to":"93 scam-controlled deposit addresses","amount":"~47,100,000","asset":"USDT","chain":"Ethereum","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.coindesk.com/policy/2025/06/18/doj-ties-kansas-bank-collapse-to-225-million-pig-butchering-seizure","note":"Hanes sent 11 wires (May-Jul 2023) converted to USDT; victim funds first landed in 93 known scam deposit addresses","date":"2023-07-01"},{"from":"Scam deposit addresses","to":"Intermediary addresses (peel chains / structured hops)","amount":"~9,000,000","asset":"USDT→multi","chain":"Ethereum→multi","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.trmlabs.com/resources/blog/doj-and-u-s-secret-service-seize-9-million-in-tether-and-disrupts-pig-butchering-operation","note":"Funds rapidly split across ~103 addresses and swapped between assets to break the trail (Nov 2023 sub-case); LIFO tracing later reconstructed the flow","date":"2023-08-01"},{"from":"Ethereum intermediary addresses","to":"TRON (bridged/swapped)","amount":"~7,900,000","asset":"USDT (ERC20→TRC20)","chain":"Ethereum→Tron","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.trmlabs.com/resources/blog/doj-and-u-s-secret-service-seize-9-million-in-tether-and-disrupts-pig-butchering-operation","note":"~88% of withdrawals moved to the TRON blockchain (cheaper USDT rails favored by SE-Asia launderers)","date":"2023-08-05"},{"from":"Laundering network","to":"144 OKX exchange accounts (of 237 traced)","amount":"~225,000,000","asset":"USDT","chain":"multi","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.cnbc.com/2025/06/18/doj-crypto-scams.html","note":"DOJ identified 144 OKX accounts (of 237 tied to 434 victims) with shared Vietnamese-KYC docs, Philippines-geolocated IPs, matching KYC-photo settings and shared devices — exposing the laundering web","date":"2024-06-01"},{"from":"Aggregated laundering wallets","to":"~$3B processed through hundreds of wallets/accounts","amount":"~3,000,000,000","asset":"USDT","chain":"multi","txhash":"","txurl":"https://fortune.com/crypto/2025/06/18/doj-225-million-phillipines-scam-compound-usdt-pig-butchering/","note":"Total network throughput across the compound''s accounts; OTC/marketplace layers provided cash-out for the SE-Asia compounds","date":"2025-01-01"},{"from":"Tether-frozen USDT (39 addresses)","to":"US Secret Service wallet (burn-and-reissue) → civil forfeiture","amount":"225,364,961","asset":"USDT","chain":"multi","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.trmlabs.com/resources/blog/us-doj-announces-largest-ever-seizure-of-funds-related-to-crypto-scams","note":"Tether froze 39 addresses (late 2023), burned the original tokens, and reissued equivalent USDT to a Secret Service wallet, enabling the $225.36M forfeiture — largest crypto-scam seizure in US/USSS history","date":"2025-06-18"}],"legal":"DOJ (US Attorney, District of Columbia + US Secret Service) filed a civil forfeiture complaint for ~$225,364,961 in USDT on 18 June 2025 (75-page complaint applying LIFO tracing across 237 OKX accounts / 434 victims), plus a separate ~$9M USDT seizure in Nov 2023. Shan Hanes was sentenced to 24 years (Aug 2024) for embezzling $47.1M; the FDIC absorbed the Heartland Tri-State Bank loss. Recovery hinged on Tether''s freeze-and-reissue of centrally-issued USDT (Tether has frozen $2.7B+ tied to illicit activity across 255+ agencies) and OKX''s data on the account cluster — not on-chain tracing alone. The Manila/Philippines scam-compound layer (often human-trafficking-backed) remains the enforcement gap; funds are subject to forfeiture proceedings aimed at eventual victim restitution.","analysis":"This case contrasts sharply with the Lazarus playbook: the launderers used no mixer, relying instead on speed, chain-hopping (ETH→TRON for cheap rails), peel chains, and fan-out across hundreds of exchange accounts, plus an OTC cash-out layer serving SE-Asia compounds. That reliance on a centrally-issuable stablecoin (USDT) is the fatal weakness — Tether can freeze, burn and reissue, and centralized exchanges (OKX) can be compelled to surrender KYC/IP/device data that clusters the accounts. The forensic breakthroughs were LIFO tracing plus behavioral clustering (shared KYC photos, IPs, devices), not mixer de-anonymization. Lesson for the Scam Tracker: stablecoin issuer cooperation and CEX off-ramps are where pig-butchering funds are actually recoverable, while the trafficking-backed compound and OTC layer is the true root that on-chain forensics alone cannot dismantle.","parallels":"This is the mirror opposite of the Lazarus bridge/exchange hacks: where DPRK actors flee to decentralized, freeze-proof rails (Tornado Cash, THORChain, eXch) and keep the money, this network trusted a centrally-controllable stablecoin (USDT) and CEX accounts (OKX) — so ~$225M was frozen and clawed back. It sits alongside other industrialized SE-Asia ''sha zhu pan'' operations and the Huione Guarantee marketplace ecosystem (targeted separately by FinCEN in 2025) as part of the same trafficking-backed fraud economy. As a social-engineering confidence scam that preys on human trust rather than code, it is the modern, crypto-rails descendant of affinity/Ponzi frauds like BitConnect and OneCoin — the difference being that stablecoin issuer freezes now offer a recovery path those earlier fiat/off-chain schemes never had.","sources":["https://www.justice.gov/usao-ks/pr/former-ceo-failed-bank-sentenced-prison","https://www.coindesk.com/policy/2025/06/18/doj-ties-kansas-bank-collapse-to-225-million-pig-butchering-seizure","https://www.cnbc.com/2025/06/18/doj-crypto-scams.html","https://www.trmlabs.com/resources/blog/us-doj-announces-largest-ever-seizure-of-funds-related-to-crypto-scams","https://www.trmlabs.com/resources/blog/doj-and-u-s-secret-service-seize-9-million-in-tether-and-disrupts-pig-butchering-operation","https://fortune.com/crypto/2025/06/18/doj-225-million-phillipines-scam-compound-usdt-pig-butchering/"]}','["https://www.justice.gov/usao-ks/pr/former-ceo-failed-bank-sentenced-prison","https://www.coindesk.com/policy/2025/06/18/doj-ties-kansas-bank-collapse-to-225-million-pig-butchering-seizure","https://www.cnbc.com/2025/06/18/doj-crypto-scams.html","https://www.trmlabs.com/resources/blog/us-doj-announces-largest-ever-seizure-of-funds-related-to-crypto-scams","https://www.trmlabs.com/resources/blog/doj-and-u-s-secret-service-seize-9-million-in-tether-and-disrupts-pig-butchering-operation","https://fortune.com/crypto/2025/06/18/doj-225-million-phillipines-scam-compound-usdt-pig-butchering/"]','2026-07-08 19:48:35',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "scam_traces" ("slug","name","category","amount_usd","profile","sources","updated_at","net_usd","recovered_usd","victims","start_date","collapse_date","status","chains","confidence","source_checked_at") VALUES ('mtgox','Mt. Gox','exchange collapse',450000000,'{"summary":"Mt. Gox, the Tokyo exchange that at its peak handled ~70% of all Bitcoin trades, lost ~850,000 BTC (roughly 750,000 customer + 100,000 house coins, ~$450M at the Feb 2014 collapse; ~200,000 BTC were later found in an old pre-June-2011 wallet, cutting the net loss to ~650,000 BTC). Contrary to the myth of a single 2014 hack, the Japanese security firm WizSec and researcher Kim Nilsson established that the theft was a slow bleed beginning in 2011: attackers copied the hot-wallet ''wallet.dat'' private-key file (unencrypted before Bitcoin 0.4, Sept 2011) and periodically siphoned coins, extracting the bulk of ~630,000 BTC by mid-2013 while the exchange kept refilling its compromised hot wallet, unknowingly running at fractional reserve for years. The stolen coins flowed to wallets controlled by Alexander Vinnik, and ~300,000 BTC were funneled into the BTC-e exchange to be sold/laundered. Nilsson cracked the case using a decisive insight: the launderer cycled some stolen coins BACK through Mt. Gox, whose (leaked, partially reconstructed) internal account data let WizSec link the receiving accounts to the online identity ''WME'' and thence to Vinnik. Vinnik was arrested in Greece in July 2017; in June 2023 the US charged Alexey Bilyuchenko and Aleksandr Verner with the underlying hack and laundering ~647,000 BTC. Creditor repayments finally began in July 2024 and remain ongoing into late 2025.","actor":"The intruders who breached Mt. Gox from 2011 (later charged: Alexey Bilyuchenko & Aleksandr Verner, Russian nationals). Laundering was coordinated by Alexander Vinnik (online alias ''WME'') via the BTC-e exchange; Bilyuchenko later co-founded BTC-e with Vinnik. WizSec/Kim Nilsson characterized Vinnik as launderer, not the original hacker. Ex-CEO Mark Karpeles, long suspected, was effectively cleared by the 2023 US indictment.","technical":"The catastrophic primitive was that Bitcoin Core wallets before v0.4.0 (released Sept 23, 2011) stored private keys UNENCRYPTED in a plaintext ''wallet.dat'' file — so an attacker who obtained the file obtained spending authority over every address in it, with no password to crack. Mt. Gox ran its hot wallet on a server that also hosted a WordPress install (a plausible entry vector), and forensics showed the machine was rooted and its logs wiped; rather than abusing the wallet RPC interface, the attackers simply copied wallet.dat. In the March 2011 incident ~80,000 BTC were swept in a single transaction to one address and never moved again. The main September 2011 compromise was worse because Bitcoin''s shared ''keypool'' (100 pre-generated keys) caused address reuse: the thief could spend not only the coins present at copy time but every future deposit that landed on any reused address, so the wallet kept bleeding as customers deposited. That same keypool/address-reuse behaviour confused Mt. Gox''s internal accounting into misreading some of the thief''s spends as customer DEPOSITS, crediting user accounts and pushing the books further out of balance. Because staff refilled the hot wallet from cold storage whenever it ran low — not realizing it was compromised — they were effectively hand-feeding coins to the attacker, which is why an eight-figure BTC drain stayed invisible for roughly two years. Nilsson reconstructed the whole flow by combining leaked Mt. Gox deposit/withdrawal records (~2 million addresses) with the public blockchain, clustering the receiving wallets, and exploiting the launderer''s mistake of cycling coins back through Mt. Gox accounts tied to the ''WME'' identity.","timeline":[{"date":"2010-07","event":"Mt. Gox launched by Jed McCaleb (repurposed from a Magic: The Gathering card-trading site)."},{"date":"2011-02","event":"Mark Karpeles agrees to take over Mt. Gox from McCaleb; ownership handover begins."},{"date":"2011-03-01","event":"Main server (co-hosting WordPress) is rooted; attackers copy the unencrypted hot-wallet wallet.dat and sweep ~80,000 BTC to address 1FeexV6bAHb8ybZjqQMjJrcCrHGW9sb6uF (never moved since)."},{"date":"2011-06-19","event":"Public ''price-crash'' incident: ~2,000 BTC drained after McCaleb''s admin account is compromised; a bogus trade briefly crashes BTC to $0.01."},{"date":"2011-09-11","event":"Main theft begins: hot-wallet keys stolen via a second copied wallet.dat, enabling a slow multi-year siphon of ~630,000 BTC to Vinnik-controlled wallets through mid-2013."},{"date":"2011-09-23","event":"Bitcoin 0.4.0 ships wallet encryption — days too late for Mt. Gox."},{"date":"2013-05-14","event":"US Homeland Security seizes Mt. Gox''s Dwolla/US bank accounts over unlicensed money-transmitter issues, freezing USD withdrawals."},{"date":"2014-02-07","event":"Mt. Gox halts all BTC withdrawals, citing ''technical'' issues."},{"date":"2014-02-10","event":"Blames transaction malleability bug (later shown to be a distraction, not the cause of the loss)."},{"date":"2014-02-24","event":"Website goes dark; a leaked internal ''crisis strategy'' doc pegs the loss at ~744,408 BTC."},{"date":"2014-02-28","event":"Files for civil rehabilitation (minji saisei) in Tokyo, declaring ~850,000 BTC lost (~$473M)."},{"date":"2014-03-07","event":"Rescan of old-format wallets finds ~199,999.99 BTC in a pre-June-2011 wallet, cutting net loss to ~650,000 BTC (announced ~Mar 20)."},{"date":"2014-03-09","event":"Files Chapter 15 bankruptcy protection in the US (Dallas)."},{"date":"2014-04-16","event":"Abandons rehabilitation; Tokyo court orders liquidation."},{"date":"2015-04","event":"WizSec publishes findings that most coins were stolen from the hot wallet gradually beginning late 2011, not in a single 2014 hack."},{"date":"2015-08-01","event":"Mark Karpeles arrested in Japan (embezzlement/data-manipulation charges)."},{"date":"2017-07-25","event":"Alexander Vinnik arrested in Greece at US request; BTC-e seized by international law enforcement."},{"date":"2017-07-26","event":"FinCEN assesses a $110,003,314 penalty on BTC-e (aka Canton Business Corp) plus $12M on Vinnik; DOJ/NDCal indicts Vinnik for laundering >$4B."},{"date":"2017-09","event":"BTC-e operators relaunch as WEX; WEX later collapses, itself defrauding users."},{"date":"2019-03","event":"Karpeles convicted in Japan of data manipulation (suspended sentence); acquitted of embezzlement."},{"date":"2020-08","event":"Vinnik extradited from Greece to the United States (after a stint in France)."},{"date":"2021-10","event":"Tokyo court approves the Mt. Gox civil-rehabilitation plan; creditor repayment framework set."},{"date":"2023-06-09","event":"DOJ (SDNY & NDCal) unseals charges against Alexey Bilyuchenko and Aleksandr Verner for the Sept-2011 hack and laundering ~647,000 BTC; Bilyuchenko also charged with co-running BTC-e."},{"date":"2024-05-03","event":"Vinnik pleads guilty in NDCal to money-laundering conspiracy (18 U.S.C. 1956(h))."},{"date":"2024-07-05","event":"Trustee begins moving/distributing coins; large Mt. Gox-labeled BTC transfers briefly weigh on the market."},{"date":"2024-07-24","event":"Bitstamp/Kraken begin distributing BTC and BCH proceeds to verified creditors."},{"date":"2025-02-11","event":"US dismisses Vinnik''s case and returns him to Russia in a prisoner swap for detained American teacher Marc Fogel; Vinnik forfeits >$100M in assets."},{"date":"2025-10-27","event":"Trustee Nobuaki Kobayashi again extends the base repayment deadline (was Oct 31, 2025) with court approval; ~34,689 BTC (~$3.9B) still awaiting distribution."}],"entities":[{"name":"Mt. Gox (Tibanne Co., Ltd.)","role":"victim","detail":"Tokyo-based exchange; at peak ~70% of global BTC volume. Lost ~850,000 BTC (net ~650,000 after old-wallet recovery)."},{"name":"Mark Karpeles","role":"victim","detail":"CEO/owner from 2011. Long suspected of the theft; effectively cleared by the 2023 US indictment. Convicted in Japan of data manipulation (2019, suspended), acquitted of embezzlement."},{"name":"Jed McCaleb","role":"victim","detail":"Founder who sold Mt. Gox to Karpeles in 2011; hot wallet stolen from his server in the March 2011 incident."},{"name":"Alexey Bilyuchenko","role":"attacker","detail":"Russian national; charged (2023, SDNY) with the Sept-2011 hack and laundering ~647,000 BTC, and (NDCal) with co-operating BTC-e with Vinnik. Believed in Russia; sentenced there in 2023 for embezzling successor exchange WEX."},{"name":"Aleksandr Verner","role":"attacker","detail":"Russian national; charged (2023, SDNY) with conspiring in the Mt. Gox hack and laundering. Whereabouts unknown; charged in absentia."},{"name":"Alexander Vinnik (alias ''WME'')","role":"launderer","detail":"Operated BTC-e; laundered the Mt. Gox coins plus proceeds of many other hacks. Arrested Greece 2017, extradited to US 2020, pleaded guilty 2024, returned to Russia in 2025 prisoner swap after forfeiting >$100M."},{"name":"BTC-e (Canton Business Corporation)","role":"facilitator","detail":"No-KYC exchange (2011-2017), 1M+ users, >$9B in transactions; laundered ~$4B in criminal proceeds incl. >300,000 BTC traceable to Mt. Gox. Seized July 2017; $110M FinCEN penalty."},{"name":"New York Bitcoin Broker (Exchange-1)","role":"facilitator","detail":"Per DOJ, wired >$6.6M (Mar 2012-Apr 2013) to overseas accounts controlled by the hackers in exchange for ''credit'' on an online exchange through which >300,000 stolen BTC were laundered."},{"name":"WizSec / Kim Nilsson","role":"investigator","detail":"Independent forensic team that reconstructed the theft timeline and unmasked Vinnik via the ''WME'' account link and the coins cycled back through Mt. Gox."},{"name":"US DOJ (SDNY & NDCal), IRS-CI, FBI, USSS, HSI","role":"enforcement","detail":"Brought the 2017 BTC-e/Vinnik case and the 2023 Bilyuchenko/Verner charges; coordinated the BTC-e seizure."},{"name":"FinCEN","role":"enforcement","detail":"First-ever US action against a foreign-located MSB: $110,003,314 penalty on BTC-e and $12M on Vinnik (July 2017)."},{"name":"Nobuaki Kobayashi (Rehabilitation Trustee)","role":"investigator","detail":"Court-appointed trustee managing the ~142,000 BTC / 143,000 BCH estate and creditor repayments via Kraken, Bitstamp, SBI VC Trade and others."},{"name":"1FeexV6bAHb8ybZjqQMjJrcCrHGW9sb6uF","role":"attacker","detail":"Destination of the ~80,000 BTC March-2011 theft; coins never moved (thief likely lost the keys)."}],"hops":[{"from":"Mt. Gox hot wallet (McCaleb''s server, wallet.dat copied)","to":"1FeexV6bAHb8ybZjqQMjJrcCrHGW9sb6uF","amount":"~80,000","asset":"BTC","chain":"Bitcoin","txhash":"e67a0550848b7932d7796aeea16ab0e48a5cfe81c4e8cca2c5b03e0416850114","txurl":"https://blog.wizsec.jp/2020/06/mtgox-march-2011-theft.html","note":"March 1, 2011 single-sweep theft during the McCaleb->Karpeles handover; swept ~2h after the wallet.dat copy. Coins have NEVER moved since — distinct from the main theft.","date":"2011-03-01"},{"from":"Mt. Gox hot wallet (2nd wallet.dat copied)","to":"Attacker-controlled wallets","amount":"~630,000","asset":"BTC","chain":"Bitcoin","txhash":"","txurl":"https://blog.wizsec.jp/2017/07/breaking-open-mtgox-1.html","note":"Main theft from Sept 11, 2011 to mid-2013: keypool address-reuse let the thief spend both existing coins and every future deposit; staff unknowingly refilled the compromised hot wallet.","date":"2011-09-11"},{"from":"Attacker wallets","to":"Vinnik-controlled laundering wallets","amount":"~630,000","asset":"BTC","chain":"Bitcoin","txhash":"","txurl":"https://blog.wizsec.jp/2017/07/breaking-open-mtgox-1.html","note":"Stolen coins periodically forwarded to Vinnik-controlled wallets; the SAME wallets also laundered coins from other 2011-2012 thefts (Bitcoinica, Bitfloor and more).","date":"2012-06-01"},{"from":"Vinnik wallets / hackers'' accounts","to":"New York Bitcoin Broker (Exchange-1)","amount":">300,000","asset":"BTC","chain":"Bitcoin","txhash":"","txurl":"https://therecord.media/mt-gox-stolen-bitcoin-indictment-russian-nationals","note":"DOJ 2023: a NY-based broker wired >$6.6M (Mar 2012-Apr 2013) to the hackers'' overseas accounts in return for exchange ''credit'', through which >300,000 stolen BTC were laundered.","date":"2012-03-01"},{"from":"Vinnik wallets","to":"BTC-e exchange (sold / laundered)","amount":"~300,000","asset":"BTC","chain":"Bitcoin","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.fincen.gov/news/news-releases/fincen-fines-btc-e-virtual-currency-exchange-110-million-facilitating-ransomware","note":"FinCEN/DOJ: BTC-e processed >300,000 BTC traceable to the Mt. Gox theft; some moved straight to BTC-e internal storage rather than customer deposit addresses, hinting at a Vinnik-BTC-e relationship.","date":"2013-01-01"},{"from":"Vinnik wallets","to":"Mt. Gox accounts linked to alias ''WME'' (traceback foothold)","amount":"unspecified","asset":"BTC","chain":"Bitcoin","txhash":"","txurl":"https://blog.wizsec.jp/2017/07/breaking-open-mtgox-1.html","note":"Cycling stolen coins BACK through Mt. Gox let WizSec link the receiving accounts to the ''WME'' identity; WME''s public complaint about confiscated Bitcoinica coins exposed the name Alexander Vinnik.","date":"2013-06-01"},{"from":"BTC-e (laundering-as-a-service hub)","to":"Proceeds of many hacks/ransomware/darknet markets worldwide","amount":"~4,000,000,000","asset":"USD-equiv","chain":"multi","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.justice.gov/archives/opa/pr/russian-nationals-charged-hacking-one-cryptocurrency-exchange-and-illicitly-operating-another","note":"DOJ: BTC-e (2011-2017) served 1M+ users and moved >$9B, laundering ~$4B in proceeds of intrusions, ransomware, identity theft, corrupt officials, and narcotics/darknet (Silk Road, AlphaBay, Hansa).","date":"2017-07-26"},{"from":"Mt. Gox rehabilitation estate (~142,000 BTC recovered)","to":"Creditors via Kraken / Bitstamp / SBI VC Trade etc.","amount":"~142,000","asset":"BTC","chain":"Bitcoin","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.coindesk.com/business/2024/07/24/bitstamp-to-start-distributing-mt-gox-proceeds-on-thursday","note":"Trustee Kobayashi began distributing ~142,000 BTC + 143,000 BCH + JPY from July 2024; staggered to limit market impact. As of Oct 2025 ~34,689 BTC (~$3.9B) still pending, deadline extended again.","date":"2024-07-24"}],"aftermath":"Recoveries: ~200,000 BTC surfaced in an old pre-June-2011 wallet in March 2014, forming the core of the rehabilitation estate (~142,000 BTC + ~143,000 BCH). Because BTC appreciated from ~$450 (2014) to five figures, the estate became a rare bankruptcy with a surplus, and creditor repayments began July 2024 via Kraken/Bitstamp/SBI, still ongoing into late 2025 (~34,689 BTC / ~$3.9B pending; deadline re-extended Oct 27, 2025). Enforcement: BTC-e was seized (July 2017) and hit with a $110,003,314 FinCEN penalty (plus $12M on Vinnik) — the first US action against a foreign-located MSB; Vinnik was extradited (2020), pleaded guilty (2024), forfeited >$100M, then was returned to Russia in a Feb 2025 prisoner swap for Marc Fogel. In June 2023 the DOJ charged Bilyuchenko and Verner with the hack and laundering ~647,000 BTC (both believed in Russia; charged in absentia); Bilyuchenko had already been sentenced in Russia for defrauding successor exchange WEX. Mark Karpeles, long the prime suspect, was cleared by the indictment; in Japan he received a suspended sentence for data manipulation and was acquitted of embezzlement. The ~80,000 BTC from March 2011 remain frozen at their original address, apparently lost forever.","industry_impact":"Mt. Gox is the founding trauma of crypto custody and the birth of blockchain forensics. Operationally, it entrenched the doctrine of cold-storage majority reserves, multisig, hardware-encrypted keys, withdrawal monitoring/reconciliation, and (eventually) proof-of-reserves — precisely the controls whose absence let a plaintext wallet.dat copy drain an exchange for two years undetected. The case validated blockchain analysis as an investigative discipline (WizSec''s leaked-ledger + on-chain reconciliation method presaged Chainalysis/Elliptic/TRM), and it established the ''laundering-as-a-service'' model: a shared no-KYC utility (BTC-e/Vinnik) servicing many unrelated thefts, which drove the regulatory logic behind BSA/FinCEN reach over foreign MSBs, VASP KYC/AML rules, and later mixer sanctions. It also normalized cross-border crypto enforcement (Greece/France/US extradition tug-of-war) and, uncomfortably, showed such defendants can become geopolitical bargaining chips (the Fogel swap).","analysis":"Mt. Gox is the origin story of modern crypto forensics: the theft was invisible for years because it was a gradual hot-wallet drain, not a dramatic single breach, and it was cracked not by tracing alone but by an operational-security slip — the launderer moving coins back through the victim exchange, whose reconstructed internal ledger tied deposit accounts to the ''WME'' alias and then to Vinnik. It also established the template of laundering-as-a-service: Vinnik/BTC-e were a shared money-laundering utility, not the original thieves, so one nexus serviced many unrelated hacks. The technical root cause was mundane but decisive — unencrypted pre-0.4 wallet.dat plus keypool address-reuse — a reminder that catastrophic losses often stem from boring key-management failures, not exotic cryptography breaks. Recovery was ultimately possible for creditors (~142,000 BTC survived) precisely because BTC''s appreciation over a decade turned a ~$450M loss into a multi-billion-dollar estate — the opposite of cases where laundered funds vanish permanently.","parallels":"Mt. Gox is the root node many later cases trace back to. The BTC-e/Vinnik ''WME'' laundering nexus handled not just Mt. Gox but the contemporaneous Bitcoinica and Bitfloor thefts (2011-2012), and DOJ charged BTC-e with laundering proceeds of ransomware, intrusions and narcotics rings worldwide — making it the direct ancestor of the dedicated laundering infrastructure (mixers like Tornado Cash/Blender, no-KYC swaps like eXch) later used by Lazarus in Ronin, Harmony and Bybit. Its ''was it a hack, insolvency, or insider theft?'' ambiguity prefigures the FTX mystery drain and the Multichain collapse, where exchange failure blurred theft, mismanagement and seizure. As a custodial exchange whose single point of failure was opaque internal control of customer keys, it is the archetype that Multichain''s ''decentralization theater'' and FTX/Alameda commingling later re-ran, and Vinnik''s laundering-as-a-service role foreshadows the professionalized OTC/Huione cash-out layer behind today''s pig-butchering networks.","legal":"Alexander Vinnik was arrested in Greece in July 2017 at US request; the DOJ (NDCal) indicted him for operating BTC-e and laundering >$4B (FinCEN separately fined BTC-e $110,003,314 and Vinnik $12M). Extradited to the US in 2020 (via France), he pleaded guilty on May 3, 2024 to money-laundering conspiracy (18 U.S.C. 1956(h)), facing up to 20 years and responsible for >$121M in losses. Before US sentencing, on Feb 11, 2025 the US dismissed the case and returned him to Russia in a prisoner swap for detained American teacher Marc Fogel, with Vinnik forfeiting >$100M in assets. In June 2023 the DOJ (SDNY/NDCal) charged Alexey Bilyuchenko and Aleksandr Verner with the Sept-2011 Mt. Gox hack and conspiring to launder ~647,000 BTC; Bilyuchenko was also charged with co-running BTC-e with Vinnik but remains in Russia (sentenced there in 2023 for embezzling successor exchange WEX). Mt. Gox itself entered Japanese civil rehabilitation; creditor repayments began July 2024 with the deadline repeatedly extended (again on Oct 27, 2025).","confidence":"high — the theft timeline/mechanism (WizSec) and the enforcement facts (FinCEN penalty, Vinnik guilty plea, 2023 Bilyuchenko/Verner indictment, 2025 prisoner swap, creditor repayments) are well-established from primary sources; the precise per-hop BTC amounts and Vinnik-vs-hacker role split are forensic reconstruction/allegation (Bilyuchenko & Verner charged in absentia, not convicted in the US).","sources":["https://blog.wizsec.jp/2017/07/breaking-open-mtgox-1.html","https://blog.wizsec.jp/2020/06/mtgox-march-2011-theft.html","https://www.justice.gov/archives/opa/pr/russian-nationals-charged-hacking-one-cryptocurrency-exchange-and-illicitly-operating-another","https://www.fincen.gov/news/news-releases/fincen-fines-btc-e-virtual-currency-exchange-110-million-facilitating-ransomware","https://www.justice.gov/archives/opa/pr/btc-e-operator-pleads-guilty-money-laundering-conspiracy","https://therecord.media/mt-gox-stolen-bitcoin-indictment-russian-nationals","https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/politics-news/russian-money-launderer-freed-exchange-marc-fogel-rcna191859","https://www.coindesk.com/business/2024/07/24/bitstamp-to-start-distributing-mt-gox-proceeds-on-thursday","https://www.coindesk.com/policy/2025/02/12/us-to-release-jailed-btc-e-operator-vinnik-in-russia-prisoner-swap","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mt._Gox","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alexander_Vinnik"]}','["https://blog.wizsec.jp/2017/07/breaking-open-mtgox-1.html","https://blog.wizsec.jp/2020/06/mtgox-march-2011-theft.html","https://www.justice.gov/archives/opa/pr/russian-nationals-charged-hacking-one-cryptocurrency-exchange-and-illicitly-operating-another","https://www.fincen.gov/news/news-releases/fincen-fines-btc-e-virtual-currency-exchange-110-million-facilitating-ransomware","https://www.justice.gov/archives/opa/pr/btc-e-operator-pleads-guilty-money-laundering-conspiracy","https://therecord.media/mt-gox-stolen-bitcoin-indictment-russian-nationals","https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/politics-news/russian-money-launderer-freed-exchange-marc-fogel-rcna191859","https://www.coindesk.com/business/2024/07/24/bitstamp-to-start-distributing-mt-gox-proceeds-on-thursday","https://www.coindesk.com/policy/2025/02/12/us-to-release-jailed-btc-e-operator-vinnik-in-russia-prisoner-swap","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mt._Gox","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alexander_Vinnik"]','2026-07-08 20:53:06',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "scam_traces" ("slug","name","category","amount_usd","profile","sources","updated_at","net_usd","recovered_usd","victims","start_date","collapse_date","status","chains","confidence","source_checked_at") VALUES ('bitconnect','BitConnect (2016-2018)','ponzi',2400000000,'{"summary":"BitConnect was a lending-and-staking Ponzi scheme built around its own token, BitConnect Coin (BCC), that at its January 2018 peak carried a market capitalization above $3.4 billion. Investors were told to buy BCC and lock it into a ''Lending Program'' where a proprietary ''BitConnect Trading Bot'' and ''Volatility Software'' would trade the crypto markets and pay guaranteed daily interest — advertised at roughly 1% per day, or ~40% per month with compounding. No such trading engine existed: earlier investors were paid with the deposits of later investors, the textbook Ponzi structure, while a global multi-level-marketing (MLM) affiliate network earned referral commissions that gave it viral, cult-like growth. On 17 January 2018, after cease-and-desist orders from Texas and North Carolina securities regulators, BitConnect abruptly shut the Lending Program; BCC collapsed ~90%+ within hours and effectively went to zero. The US DOJ later called it the largest cryptocurrency fraud ever charged, estimating global investor losses over $2.4 billion. Founder Satish Kumbhani was indicted in 2022 and remains a fugitive.","actor":"Satishkumar ''Satish'' Kumbhani, an Indian national who founded and controlled BitConnect, orchestrating the scheme with a network of promoters. Lead US promoter Glenn Arcaro ran the North American affiliate operation. The scheme was propelled by a decentralized MLM promoter army whose YouTube ''BitConnect!'' hype (including Carlos Matos''s viral ''Wasa wasa wasaaa'' speech) became internet legend.","technical":"BitConnect operated a closed-loop token economy. Users bought Bitcoin, sent it to BitConnect, and exchanged it for BCC on BitConnect''s own internal exchange (BCC had little liquidity anywhere else, so BitConnect controlled the price). BCC was then ''lent'' back to the platform for a fixed term (the higher the deposit, the longer the lock-up), during which the fictitious ''BitConnect Trading Bot'' supposedly generated the advertised ~1%/day returns from volatility trading. In reality returns were paid from new deposits. A four-tier referral/MLM commission structure paid promoters for recruiting downlines, which is what drove the exponential growth typical of Ponzi-MLM hybrids. When regulators moved and inflows slowed, the model could not sustain payouts; Kumbhani shut the Lending Program and, per the DOJ indictment, directed promoters to manipulate BCC''s price to fake legitimate demand while insiders cashed out. Proceeds were laundered by commingling and cycling funds through a cluster of BitConnect wallets and international exchanges to obscure control; BitConnect operated as an unlicensed money transmitter that deliberately evaded FinCEN registration.","timeline":[{"date":"2016-02","event":"BitConnect launches; BCC token and the ''Lending Program'' promising ~1%/day begin recruiting via an aggressive MLM affiliate network."},{"date":"2017-11","event":"BCC enters the crypto top-20 by market cap during the 2017 bull run; the Carlos Matos ''BitConnect!'' hype speech goes viral, and skeptics (Vitalik Buterin, Mike Novogratz) publicly call it a Ponzi."},{"date":"2018-01-03","event":"BCC reaches its all-time high near $463, a market cap above $3.4 billion."},{"date":"2018-01-04","event":"Texas State Securities Board issues an emergency cease-and-desist order against BitConnect; North Carolina follows days later."},{"date":"2018-01-17","event":"BitConnect abruptly closes the Lending Program and exchange, blaming ''bad press'' and DDoS attacks; BCC crashes ~90% within hours and continues toward zero."},{"date":"2021-09","event":"US promoter Glenn Arcaro pleads guilty in the Southern District of California to conspiracy to commit wire fraud tied to BitConnect."},{"date":"2021-09","event":"The SEC charges BitConnect, Kumbhani, Arcaro and BitConnect''s promoter network with orchestrating a fraudulent, unregistered ~$2 billion offering."},{"date":"2022-02-25","event":"A federal grand jury (S.D. Cal.) indicts Satish Kumbhani on wire-fraud, commodity-price-manipulation, unlicensed-money-transmission and international money-laundering conspiracy counts; DOJ estimates $2.4B in global losses. Kumbhani is at large."},{"date":"2022-09","event":"Glenn Arcaro is sentenced to 38 months and ordered to pay ~$24M restitution; the DOJ moves to sell seized crypto to compensate victims."}],"hops":[{"from":"Retail investors worldwide (BTC deposits)","to":"BitConnect internal exchange / wallet cluster","amount":"~2,400,000,000","asset":"BTC/BCC","chain":"Bitcoin","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.justice.gov/archives/opa/pr/bitconnect-founder-indicted-global-24-billion-cryptocurrency-scheme","note":"Investors bought BTC and swapped for BCC on BitConnect''s own low-liquidity exchange, giving the operators price control.","date":"2017-11-01"},{"from":"New investor deposits","to":"Earlier investors (fake ''trading bot'' interest)","amount":"unspecified","asset":"BCC","chain":"internal ledger","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.sec.gov/newsroom/press-releases/2021-172","note":"Classic Ponzi payout: no trading bot existed; ~1%/day interest was funded by fresh deposits.","date":"2017-12-01"},{"from":"BitConnect wallet cluster","to":"International exchanges (commingled/cycled)","amount":"unspecified","asset":"BTC","chain":"Bitcoin","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.justice.gov/archives/opa/pr/bitconnect-founder-indicted-global-24-billion-cryptocurrency-scheme","note":"Per the DOJ indictment, proceeds were laundered by commingling, cycling and exchanging across BitConnect wallets and foreign exchanges to conceal control.","date":"2018-01-20"}],"entities":[{"name":"Satishkumar ''Satish'' Kumbhani","role":"founder/mastermind","person":true,"detail":"Indian national, founder of BitConnect; indicted Feb 2022 on five felony counts (up to 70 years); fled and remains a fugitive.","links":[{"title":"DOJ: BitConnect Founder Indicted in $2.4B Scheme","url":"https://www.justice.gov/archives/opa/pr/bitconnect-founder-indicted-global-24-billion-cryptocurrency-scheme"},{"title":"SEC charges (2021-172)","url":"https://www.sec.gov/newsroom/press-releases/2021-172"}]},{"name":"Glenn Arcaro","role":"lead US promoter","person":true,"detail":"Top North American BitConnect promoter; pleaded guilty Sept 2021, sentenced to 38 months and ~$24M restitution.","links":[{"title":"DOJ SDCA: promoter guilty plea/sentencing coverage","url":"https://www.justice.gov/usao-sdca/pr/founder-fraudulent-cryptocurrency-charged-2-billion-bitconnect-ponzi-scheme"}]},{"name":"Carlos Matos","role":"promoter (viral figure)","person":true,"detail":"Investor/promoter whose ecstatic ''BitConnect! Wasa wasa wasaaa'' stage speech became a defining meme of the crypto-Ponzi era.","links":[{"title":"BitConnect (Wikipedia)","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BitConnect"}]},{"name":"US SEC","role":"enforcement","detail":"Charged BitConnect, Kumbhani, Arcaro and the promoter network in 2021 with a fraudulent unregistered ~$2B securities offering.","links":[{"title":"SEC press release 2021-172","url":"https://www.sec.gov/newsroom/press-releases/2021-172"}]},{"name":"US DOJ (S.D. Cal.), FBI, IRS-CI","role":"enforcement","detail":"Criminal indictment and asset seizure; called it the largest crypto fraud charged to date.","links":[{"title":"DOJ indictment press release","url":"https://www.justice.gov/archives/opa/pr/bitconnect-founder-indicted-global-24-billion-cryptocurrency-scheme"}]}],"analysis":"BitConnect is the archetypal crypto Ponzi-MLM hybrid: it fused an old-fashioned pyramid recruitment engine with a proprietary-token flywheel and an impossible ''guaranteed ~1%/day'' return that no legitimate strategy can produce. Its two structural tells were textbook — guaranteed high fixed returns regardless of market conditions, and a closed internal exchange where the operator controlled the token''s price. What made it uniquely 2017 was distribution: a global army of YouTube/Telegram affiliates paid on a multi-tier referral scheme, turning promotion into a viral, quasi-religious movement. The collapse was triggered not by running out of money first but by regulators (Texas/NC cease-and-desist orders) spooking inflows — once new deposits slowed, the Ponzi math failed instantly, which is why the shutdown and ~90% crash happened in a single day.","parallels":"BitConnect is the direct spiritual predecessor of the other guaranteed-yield token Ponzis in this set: PlusToken (same ''wallet + guaranteed returns + MLM referral'' template, same year-plus later collapse) and Forsage (smart-contract-native MLM matrix). It shares OneCoin''s fake-technology core (a nonexistent ''trading bot'' vs OneCoin''s nonexistent blockchain) and cult-of-personality marketing. Unlike founder-fraud collapses such as Celsius or Terra — where a real product existed but was misrepresented — BitConnect had no real yield engine at all, placing it closer to pure Ponzi (OneCoin, PlusToken) than to the mismanaged-real-business failures (FTX, Celsius).","aftermath":"BCC went to zero, wiping out most participants (though very early entrants who exited before Jan 2018 profited at later victims'' expense). Enforcement: Glenn Arcaro pleaded guilty (2021) and was sentenced to 38 months plus ~$24M restitution; the SEC obtained judgments against the promoter network. Founder Satish Kumbhani was indicted in Feb 2022 but fled and remains a fugitive (reportedly in India), so he has never faced trial. The DOJ moved to liquidate seized crypto to compensate victims, and BitConnect became the most-cited cautionary tale of the 2017 ICO/altcoin mania.","industry_impact":"BitConnect''s spectacular collapse became shorthand for ''obvious crypto Ponzi'' and hardened public and regulator skepticism of guaranteed-yield lending products — a skepticism that would resurface around Celsius and other 2022 yield platforms. Its DOJ indictment was notable for being the first to allege a cryptocurrency (BCC) functioned as a manipulated commodity, an early marker of how criminal law would stretch to cover token markets. It also spotlighted MLM referral mechanics as a red flag and drove exchanges and app stores to scrutinize ''guaranteed daily interest'' offerings.","legal":"SEC (2021): civil fraud charges against BitConnect, Kumbhani, Arcaro and promoters for an unregistered ~$2B securities offering. DOJ (S.D. Cal.): Glenn Arcaro pleaded guilty Sept 2021 (38 months, ~$24M restitution, 2022); Satish Kumbhani indicted Feb 2022 on conspiracy to commit wire fraud, wire fraud, conspiracy to commit commodity price manipulation, operating an unlicensed money-transmitting business, and international money-laundering conspiracy — up to 70 years if convicted; he remains a fugitive. The commodity-manipulation count was described as the first time a cryptocurrency was charged as a manipulated commodity.","confidence":"high — the scheme mechanics, the Jan 2018 collapse, the ~$2.4B DOJ loss estimate, the SEC charges, Arcaro''s guilty plea/sentence and Kumbhani''s fugitive indictment are all confirmed by primary DOJ/SEC sources; exact total victim losses are estimates given BitConnect''s opaque internal ledger.","sources":["https://www.justice.gov/archives/opa/pr/bitconnect-founder-indicted-global-24-billion-cryptocurrency-scheme","https://www.justice.gov/usao-sdca/pr/founder-fraudulent-cryptocurrency-charged-2-billion-bitconnect-ponzi-scheme","https://www.sec.gov/newsroom/press-releases/2021-172","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BitConnect","https://www.coindesk.com/policy/2022/02/25/us-justice-department-indicts-bitconnect-founder","https://www.ssb.texas.gov/news-publications/4-billion-crypto-promoter-ordered-halt-fraudulent-sales"]}','["https://www.justice.gov/archives/opa/pr/bitconnect-founder-indicted-global-24-billion-cryptocurrency-scheme","https://www.justice.gov/usao-sdca/pr/founder-fraudulent-cryptocurrency-charged-2-billion-bitconnect-ponzi-scheme","https://www.sec.gov/newsroom/press-releases/2021-172","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BitConnect","https://www.coindesk.com/policy/2022/02/25/us-justice-department-indicts-bitconnect-founder","https://www.ssb.texas.gov/news-publications/4-billion-crypto-promoter-ordered-halt-fraudulent-sales"]','2026-07-08 20:44:41',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "scam_traces" ("slug","name","category","amount_usd","profile","sources","updated_at","net_usd","recovered_usd","victims","start_date","collapse_date","status","chains","confidence","source_checked_at") VALUES ('onecoin','OneCoin (2014-2017)','ponzi',4000000000,'{"summary":"OneCoin was a multi-billion-dollar pyramid/Ponzi scheme run out of Sofia, Bulgaria from 2014, marketed globally through a multi-level-marketing network as the ''Bitcoin killer.'' Its central deceit was that OneCoin had NO real blockchain: prosecutors established the coin''s value was simply dictated by the company itself rather than by any mining, ledger, or market, and members were sold overpriced ''educational packages'' bundled with tokens they could barely redeem. Founder Ruja Ignatova — the self-styled ''Cryptoqueen,'' a German national with a Oxford-adjacent PhD persona — built a cult-of-personality movement, headlining stadium events (famously Wembley Arena) before vanishing. Victims invested over $4 billion worldwide. On 25 October 2017, days after a sealed US indictment, Ignatova boarded a flight from Sofia to Athens and disappeared; she has been a fugitive ever since and in June 2022 became the only woman on the FBI''s Ten Most Wanted list. Co-founder Karl Sebastian Greenwood, her brother Konstantin Ignatov, and money-launderer lawyer Mark Scott were all convicted.","actor":"Dr. Ruja Ignatova (German national, ''Cryptoqueen''), founder and mastermind, now a long-term fugitive. Co-founder Karl Sebastian Greenwood ran the MLM sales machine. Ignatova''s brother Konstantin Ignatov took over leadership after she vanished. Florida attorney Mark Scott laundered ~$400M of proceeds through fake private-equity funds. The scheme relied on a global MLM promoter network selling ''education packages.''","technical":"OneCoin was not a cryptocurrency in any technical sense — there was no functioning public blockchain, no proof-of-work mining, and no independent price discovery. Internally, prosecutors showed the ''value'' of OneCoin was a number that OneCoin''s own staff set and periodically increased to create the illusion of appreciation. Members bought tiered ''educational packages'' (from ~€100 to ~€100,000+) that came with ''tokens'' which could be ''mined'' into OneCoins and, supposedly, later cashed out on an internal exchange (xcoinx) that was heavily gated with withdrawal limits and was eventually shut down, trapping funds. Revenue came from package sales and a multi-tier MLM commission structure rewarding recruitment — the pyramid engine — not from any economic activity. Fund flows were fiat-heavy (wires through a web of shell companies and banks across dozens of countries), which is what made Mark Scott''s fake ''Fenero'' private-equity funds necessary to launder ~$400M into hard assets. An August 2014 internal email from Ignatova listed exit-strategy option one as ''Take the money and run and blame someone else.''","timeline":[{"date":"2014","event":"OneCoin launches from Sofia, Bulgaria; global MLM sales of ''educational packages'' begin, pitched as an early-stage ''Bitcoin killer.''"},{"date":"2016-06","event":"Ruja Ignatova headlines a sold-out Wembley Arena event in London, cementing the cult-of-personality ''Cryptoqueen'' brand."},{"date":"2017-10-12","event":"A sealed US indictment is filed in the Southern District of New York charging Ignatova with wire-fraud and money-laundering conspiracies."},{"date":"2017-10-25","event":"Ignatova flies from Sofia to Athens and disappears; she has never been seen publicly since."},{"date":"2018","event":"Mark Scott, the US lawyer, is arrested for laundering ~$400M of OneCoin proceeds through offshore ''Fenero'' funds."},{"date":"2019-03","event":"Konstantin Ignatov (Ruja''s brother, who ran OneCoin after her disappearance) is arrested at Los Angeles International Airport."},{"date":"2019-10","event":"Konstantin Ignatov pleads guilty in SDNY to fraud and money-laundering charges and cooperates; Mark Scott is convicted at trial of money laundering."},{"date":"2019-12","event":"Co-founder Karl Sebastian Greenwood is arrested (extradited from Thailand); he later pleads guilty (Dec 2022) to wire fraud and money laundering."},{"date":"2022-06","event":"The FBI adds Ruja Ignatova to its Ten Most Wanted Fugitives list — the only woman on it; the US State Department offers a reward up to $5M for information."},{"date":"2023-09","event":"Karl Greenwood is sentenced to 20 years in prison and ordered to forfeit ~$300M."}],"hops":[{"from":"Global members (''education package'' payments)","to":"OneCoin shell-company bank accounts","amount":"~4,000,000,000","asset":"fiat (EUR/USD wires)","chain":"banking","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.justice.gov/usao-sdny/pr/co-founder-multi-billion-dollar-cryptocurrency-pyramid-scheme-onecoin-pleads-guilty","note":"Members wired fiat for packages; there was no blockchain, so this was a fiat pyramid dressed as crypto. Value of ''OneCoin'' was set internally.","date":"2015-06-01"},{"from":"OneCoin accounts","to":"Mark Scott ''Fenero'' offshore PE funds (laundering)","amount":"~400,000,000","asset":"fiat","chain":"banking","txhash":"","txurl":"https://www.justice.gov/usao-sdny/pr/former-partner-locke-lord-llp-convicted-manhattan-federal-court-conspiracy-commit-money","note":"Attorney Mark Scott funneled ~$400M through sham private-equity funds into real estate, a yacht, and luxury assets; convicted of money laundering.","date":"2016-01-01"},{"from":"Members'' ''OneCoin'' balances","to":"Trapped (xcoinx internal exchange shut down)","amount":"unspecified","asset":"OneCoin (fictional)","chain":"none","txhash":"","txurl":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OneCoin","note":"The internal ''exchange'' had withdrawal caps and was eventually closed, leaving members unable to cash out — confirming the coins had no external value.","date":"2017-01-01"}],"entities":[{"name":"Dr. Ruja Ignatova (''Cryptoqueen'')","role":"founder/mastermind","person":true,"detail":"German national, founder of OneCoin; indicted 2017, fled 25 Oct 2017, FBI Ten Most Wanted since June 2022; still at large. $5M State Dept reward.","links":[{"title":"State Dept reward for Ruja Ignatova","url":"https://www.state.gov/reward-for-information-german-national-ruja-ignatova"},{"title":"Ruja Ignatova (Wikipedia)","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ruja_Ignatova"},{"title":"FBI: Cryptoqueen now on Ten Most Wanted (NBC)","url":"https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/justice-department/cryptoqueen-now-one-fbis-10-wanted-rcna36139"}]},{"name":"Karl Sebastian Greenwood","role":"co-founder","person":true,"detail":"Ran the OneCoin MLM sales network; pleaded guilty Dec 2022; sentenced Sept 2023 to 20 years and ~$300M forfeiture.","links":[{"title":"DOJ: OneCoin co-founder guilty plea","url":"https://www.justice.gov/usao-sdny/pr/co-founder-multibillion-dollar-cryptocurrency-scheme-onecoin-sentenced-20-years-prison"}]},{"name":"Konstantin Ignatov","role":"leader after founder fled","person":true,"detail":"Ruja''s brother; arrested at LAX March 2019; pleaded guilty Oct 2019 to fraud/money-laundering and cooperated with prosecutors.","links":[{"title":"DOJ: OneCoin co-founder (Ignatov) pleads guilty","url":"https://www.justice.gov/usao-sdny/pr/co-founder-multi-billion-dollar-cryptocurrency-pyramid-scheme-onecoin-pleads-guilty"}]},{"name":"Mark S. Scott","role":"money launderer (attorney)","person":true,"detail":"Former Locke Lord partner; convicted 2019 of laundering ~$400M via sham ''Fenero'' offshore funds.","links":[{"title":"DOJ: Attorney convicted of laundering $400M for OneCoin","url":"https://www.justice.gov/usao-sdny/pr/former-partner-locke-lord-llp-convicted-manhattan-federal-court-conspiracy-commit-money"}]},{"name":"US DOJ (SDNY), FBI, US State Department","role":"enforcement","detail":"Indictments, convictions, FBI Ten Most Wanted listing, $5M reward for Ignatova.","links":[{"title":"State Dept reward","url":"https://www.state.gov/reward-for-information-german-national-ruja-ignatova"}]}],"analysis":"OneCoin is the purest ''fake technology'' crypto fraud in this set: unlike BitConnect (a fake yield engine on a real, if worthless, token) or Terra (a real but fragile protocol), OneCoin literally had no blockchain — the coin was a database number the company incremented at will. That made it a fiat pyramid scheme wearing crypto branding, which is why laundering required traditional finance plumbing (shell companies, sham PE funds) rather than mixers. Its growth engine was a classic MLM: recruits paid for tiered ''education packages,'' and commissions rewarded downline recruitment, not any product. The cult-of-personality element — Ignatova''s stadium spectacles and academic mystique — was central to overriding investors'' skepticism, a social-engineering pattern that recurs across affinity frauds.","parallels":"OneCoin shares BitConnect''s MLM recruitment engine and fake-technology core, and PlusToken''s global retail victim base and eventual founder flight. Its ''no real blockchain, value set internally'' mechanic is the extreme end of the same spectrum as Celsius/Terra misrepresentation — but where those had real (if misused) products, OneCoin had none. The founder-vanishing pattern (Ignatova disappearing pre-arrest) mirrors QuadrigaCX''s Gerald Cotten ''death'' and Thodex''s Faruk Fatih Özer fleeing to Albania — the exit-scam playbook of the operator physically disappearing with the money. Mark Scott''s fiat-laundering-via-sham-funds is a traditional-finance analogue to the crypto-mixer laundering seen in the DPRK bridge hacks.","aftermath":"Convictions: Karl Greenwood — 20 years + ~$300M forfeiture (2023); Mark Scott — convicted of money laundering (2019), later sentenced; Konstantin Ignatov — pleaded guilty and cooperated (2019). Ruja Ignatova remains a fugitive nearly a decade on, subject of the BBC ''Missing Cryptoqueen'' podcast; persistent unproven theories suggest she may have been murdered by associates. Victim recovery has been minimal relative to the ~$4B taken. OneCoin became the defining example that ''a cryptocurrency with no verifiable blockchain'' is a red flag.","industry_impact":"OneCoin taught regulators, journalists, and the public that ''crypto'' branding can be pure theater — driving the now-standard due-diligence question: is there an actual, verifiable, public blockchain? It elevated MLM structure and non-redeemable internal tokens to top-tier fraud red flags, and its cross-border fiat laundering exposed how professional enablers (lawyers, bankers) are essential to scaling such schemes. The FBI Ten Most Wanted listing and the BBC podcast made OneCoin a mainstream cultural touchstone for crypto fraud, arguably the most publicly recognized crypto scam alongside FTX.","legal":"US DOJ (SDNY): Ruja Ignatova indicted 2017 (wire-fraud and money-laundering conspiracies) — fugitive. Konstantin Ignatov: arrested 2019, pleaded guilty, cooperated. Mark Scott: convicted 2019 of money laundering (~$400M via Fenero funds). Karl Sebastian Greenwood: pleaded guilty Dec 2022, sentenced Sept 2023 to 20 years plus ~$300M forfeiture. Numerous parallel actions and warnings issued by regulators across Europe, Asia, and elsewhere during OneCoin''s operation.","confidence":"high — the absence of a real blockchain, the ~$4B scale, the indictments/convictions of Greenwood, Scott and Ignatov, and Ignatova''s fugitive status/FBI listing are all confirmed by DOJ, State Department and court records; the exact laundering totals and Ignatova''s current whereabouts/fate remain uncertain.","sources":["https://www.justice.gov/usao-sdny/pr/co-founder-multi-billion-dollar-cryptocurrency-pyramid-scheme-onecoin-pleads-guilty","https://www.justice.gov/usao-sdny/pr/co-founder-multibillion-dollar-cryptocurrency-scheme-onecoin-sentenced-20-years-prison","https://www.justice.gov/usao-sdny/pr/former-partner-locke-lord-llp-convicted-manhattan-federal-court-conspiracy-commit-money","https://www.state.gov/reward-for-information-german-national-ruja-ignatova","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OneCoin","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ruja_Ignatova","https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/justice-department/cryptoqueen-now-one-fbis-10-wanted-rcna36139"]}','["https://www.justice.gov/usao-sdny/pr/co-founder-multi-billion-dollar-cryptocurrency-pyramid-scheme-onecoin-pleads-guilty","https://www.justice.gov/usao-sdny/pr/co-founder-multibillion-dollar-cryptocurrency-scheme-onecoin-sentenced-20-years-prison","https://www.justice.gov/usao-sdny/pr/former-partner-locke-lord-llp-convicted-manhattan-federal-court-conspiracy-commit-money","https://www.state.gov/reward-for-information-german-national-ruja-ignatova","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OneCoin","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ruja_Ignatova","https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/justice-department/cryptoqueen-now-one-fbis-10-wanted-rcna36139"]','2026-07-08 20:47:11',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "scam_traces" ("slug","name","category","amount_usd","profile","sources","updated_at","net_usd","recovered_usd","victims","start_date","collapse_date","status","chains","confidence","source_checked_at") VALUES ('celsius-2022','Celsius Network Collapse (2022)','fraud',4700000000,'{"technical":"Celsius Network operated a centralized crypto lending platform (the ''Earn Interest Program'') that took custody of customer deposits (BTC, ETH, stablecoins and others) promising high yields and safety under the slogan ''Unbank Yourself.'' Rather than holding deposits safely, Celsius commingled customer funds and deployed them into uncollateralized institutional loans, undisclosed high-risk DeFi and market bets, and — critically — used customer deposits to fund open-market buybacks of its own CEL token to prop up its price. On Ethereum, Celsius held over $1B in on-chain assets at peak, with its largest positions being ~$638M of Lido staked ETH (stETH) and ~$251M of its own CEL token (per Arkham). CEL is an ERC-20 (contract 0xaaaebe6fe48e54f431b0c390cfaf0b017d09d42d, ''CelsiusToken'', 4 decimals, ~35.7M max supply). The scheme collapsed when a liquidity crisis (partly driven by stETH depeg and leveraged positions) forced Celsius to freeze all withdrawals on June 12, 2022.","timeline":[{"date":"2018","event":"Celsius launches Earn Interest Program; CEL token sold. SEC later alleges these were unregistered securities offerings from inception.","source":"https://www.sec.gov/newsroom/press-releases/2023-133"},{"date":"2020","event":"Per SEC, Celsius and Mashinsky begin fraudulently supporting CEL''s price via manipulative buybacks far in excess of publicly disclosed purchases.","source":"https://www.sec.gov/newsroom/press-releases/2023-133"},{"date":"2022-05","event":"Mashinsky falsely claims in online video ''Celsius is stronger than ever, we have billions of dollars in liquidity'' while executives quietly withdraw funds.","source":"https://www.ftc.gov/news-events/news/press-releases/2023/07/ftc-reaches-settlement-crypto-platform-celsius-network-charges-former-executives-duping-consumers"},{"date":"2022-06-12","event":"Celsius freezes all customer withdrawals citing ''extreme market conditions.''","source":"https://www.cftc.gov/PressRoom/PressReleases/8749-23"},{"date":"2022-07-13","event":"Celsius files Chapter 11 bankruptcy in SDNY Bankruptcy Court; ~$4.7B in customer funds trapped; liabilities exceed assets by >$1B.","source":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Celsius_Network"},{"date":"2023-07-13","event":"Coordinated action: DOJ (SDNY) unseals indictment of Mashinsky & Cohen-Pavon; SEC, CFTC, and FTC file parallel charges; Celsius agrees to $4.7B FTC judgment.","source":"https://www.justice.gov/usao-sdny/pr/celsius-founder-and-former-chief-revenue-officer-charged-connection-multibillion"},{"date":"2023-09-13","event":"Roni Cohen-Pavon pleads guilty to conspiracy, securities fraud, market manipulation, and wire fraud; agrees to cooperate against Mashinsky.","source":"https://cointelegraph.com/news/former-celsius-exec-pleads-guilty-criminal-charges"},{"date":"2024-01-31","event":"Celsius exits bankruptcy under restructuring plan; assets (incl. new Bitcoin miner Ionic Digital) distributed to creditors.","source":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Celsius_Network"},{"date":"2024-12-03","event":"Mashinsky pleads guilty before Judge John G. Koeltl to one count commodities fraud and one count of a scheme to manipulate CEL.","source":"https://www.justice.gov/usao-sdny/pr/celsius-founder-and-former-ceo-alexander-mashinsky-pleads-guilty-multi-billion-dollar"},{"date":"2025-05-08","event":"Mashinsky sentenced to 12 years in prison; agrees to forfeit $48M and real estate; cannot appeal per plea deal.","source":"https://www.justice.gov/usao-sdny/pr/founder-celsius-sentenced-12-years-fraud-and-market-manipulation"}],"tradecraft":"CEL token price manipulation via customer-funded open-market buybacks (spending hundreds of millions to artificially inflate price); commingling of customer deposits with proprietary trading and market-support operations; ''HODLing'' deception — Mashinsky publicly claimed he was not selling CEL while contemporaneously offloading tens of millions of dollars of CEL (sometimes selling back to Celsius itself) at the inflated prices he had engineered; false public statements about profitability, liquidity, and asset safety to prevent a bank run; insider withdrawals two months before freezing customer withdrawals.","aftermath":"Celsius filed Chapter 11 on July 13, 2022 and exited bankruptcy January 31, 2024, distributing remaining assets (including equity in new Bitcoin miner Ionic Digital) to creditors. Over $2.5B has been distributed to eligible creditors; recovery for many users was only a fraction of deposits, and CEL holders were hit hardest. The bankruptcy estate''s on-chain balance shrank to ~$5M. Arkham Intelligence became a central tracker of Celsius''s estate wallets during distribution.","industry_impact":"Part of the 2022 crypto-lender contagion alongside BlockFi, Voyager, and Genesis. First-ever FTC enforcement action against a digital-asset company. Cemented regulatory posture that CeFi ''Earn''-style yield products are unregistered securities. Mashinsky''s conviction joined the wave of high-profile crypto-executive prosecutions (SBF/FTX, CZ/Binance, Do Kwon/Terra).","lessons":"CeFi ''high yield, always safe'' promises are structurally incompatible — the yield had to come from undisclosed high-risk deployment of commingled customer funds. A native token whose price is propped up by the issuer spending customer money is not a real asset. ''Not your keys, not your coins'': custodial deposits became unsecured bankruptcy claims.","red_flags_in_hindsight":["Unsustainable advertised yields (up to ~18%) with vague explanations of source","CEO doing weekly AMA hype videos (''Unbank Yourself'', ''stronger than ever'')","Issuer buying back its own token to support price","Commingling of customer funds with proprietary trading","Public ''HODLing'' claims while insiders sold","Executives withdrawing funds shortly before the withdrawal freeze"],"legal":"CRIMINAL (DOJ/SDNY): Alexander Mashinsky indicted 2023-07-13 (securities fraud, commodities fraud, wire fraud, conspiracy, market manipulation — 7 counts); pleaded guilty 2024-12-03 to commodities fraud + CEL manipulation scheme; sentenced 2025-05-08 to 12 years by Judge John G. Koeltl; $48M forfeiture + real estate. Roni Cohen-Pavon (ex-CRO) pleaded guilty 2023-09-13, cooperated, sentenced to time served + supervised release, ~$1M restitution + $40K fine. CIVIL/REGULATORY: SEC (fraud + unregistered securities + CEL manipulation), CFTC (fraud + unregistered commodity pool operator; permanent trading/registration ban on Mashinsky), FTC ($4.7B judgment against Celsius, largely suspended; $10M against Mashinsky + lifetime crypto/financial ban). FTC case against co-founders Shlomi Daniel Leon and Hanoch ''Nuke'' Goldstein ongoing.","parallels":"BlockFi, Voyager Digital, and Genesis (fellow collapsed crypto lenders); FTX (SBF); Terra/LUNA (Do Kwon) as native-token-price-support failures."}','["https://www.justice.gov/usao-sdny/pr/founder-celsius-sentenced-12-years-fraud-and-market-manipulation","https://www.justice.gov/usao-sdny/pr/celsius-founder-and-former-chief-revenue-officer-charged-connection-multibillion","https://www.justice.gov/d9/2023-07/u.s._v._mashinsky_and_cohen-pavon_indictment.pdf","https://www.sec.gov/newsroom/press-releases/2023-133","https://www.cftc.gov/PressRoom/PressReleases/8749-23","https://www.ftc.gov/news-events/news/press-releases/2023/07/ftc-reaches-settlement-crypto-platform-celsius-network-charges-former-executives-duping-consumers","https://www.cnbc.com/2025/05/08/celsius-ceo-alex-mashinsky-sentenced-to-12-years-in-crypto-fraud-case.html","https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Celsius_Network"]','2026-07-08 21:15:48',4700000000,NULL,600000,'2018-01-01','2022-07-13','resolved-criminal','ethereum','high','2026-07-08');
